description: The Asics Gel Kayano 14 White Midnight W is a sleek and stylish running shoe that offers both comfort and performance. The shoe features a white and midnight colorway that is both eye-catching and versatile. The upper is made of a breathable mesh material that allows for maximum airflow, while the Gel cushioning system in the sole provides excellent shock absorption and support. The Asics Gel Kayano 14 White Midnight W is set to release on February 5th, 2023, with a retail price of $150. This shoe is perfect for runners who want a comfortable and stylish shoe that can keep up with their active lifestyle. Something we love about the Asics Gel Kayano 14 White Midnight W is the combination of style and performance. Our experts think that the standout feature of this shoe is the Gel cushioning system, which provides excellent support and shock absorption. Overall, we love the Asics Gel Kayano 14 White Midnight W for its sleek design, comfortable fit, and excellent performance.

name: Blueberry
title: Jordan 12 Retro Blueberry
description:
The Air Jordan 12 Retro Blueberry reimagines an iconic design with a fresh twist, fusing heritage and modernity in a bold new colorway. Inspired by the original Cherry Air Jordan 12, this version trades vibrant red for an eye-catching game royal blue, paired with a clean white upper and subtle black accents. The smooth white leather upper provides a crisp canvas, while textured overlays and silver metal eyelets bring the classic silhouette to life.

Every detail of the Blueberry speaks to Jordan Brand’s unmatched craftsmanship. Black hits on the tongue, inner lining, and heel tab add contrast, while game royal blue pops on branding elements and textured mudguards—giving the sneaker its "Blueberry" moniker. The result is a harmonious balance of style and functionality, perfect for fans looking to elevate their collection or turn heads on the streets.

Set to release on December 18, 2024, the Air Jordan 12 Retro Blueberry carries a retail price of $210. This fresh take on the classic Air Jordan 12 combines nostalgia and innovation, making it an essential pick for sneakerheads and collectors alike.

name: Black Toe (2024)
title: Jordan 14 Retro Black Toe (2024)
description:
The Jordan 14 Retro Black Toe (2024) is a triumphant return for the iconic AJ14 trainer. This updated design features premium materials, which gives it a stunning visual effect of sleek luxury. Its low-to-the-ground style was inspired by sports car ground effect aerodynamics.

This Air Jordan 14 has been remodeled for the present day, with a mottled leather ice-white upper punctuated by wavy panels of midnight black. The sole has white claws reaching across the distinctive black toe to create a dramatic effect. The shoe also has the latest Nike Air Zoom cushioning unit.

This shoe has always been special, being the model that Michael Jordan wore when he made his last basket in the NBA. Our reviewers not only appreciate the upgrade; they also find it irresistible collectible. It's a milestone trainer to have in one's collection. The Jordan 14 Retro Black Toe (2024) was released on 2 November 2024, priced at $210.

name: Graphite Grey Black
title: ASICS Gel-NYC Graphite Grey Black
description:
The ASICS Gel NYC Graphite Gray Black is an ode to the original model that was initially released in the early 2000s. This pair of shoes mixes retro influences with athleticism.

The Graphite Gray Black ASICS Gel NYC is designed to be a modern running shoe with retro vibes. The upper part of the shoe is based off the original GEL-NIMBUS 3 and contains various embellishments from the MC-PLUS V design. It has a black body that is composed of leather and mesh and features gray overlays. Lightweight foams are used for the base of the shoe to help with cooling.

One feature of this model that our experts particularly like is the gel technology inserts that are included in the midsole that help to provide additional support. The ASICS Gel NYC Graphite Gray Black was first released on April 14th, 2023, for an initial retail price of $130.

name: Lakers Away
title: Nike Kobe 8 Protro Lakers Away
description:
The Nike Kobe 8 Protro Lakers Away is a bold new release that combines legendary performance with iconic Lakers flair. Featuring a sleek black engineered knit upper, this colorway brings the energy of a Lakers away game to the court. Gold embroidered Nike swooshes and Kobe Bryant’s signature in gold on the black heel clip add a touch of luxury, while the white outsole provides contrast against the black midsole. This Lakers-inspired colorway brings the competitive intensity of Kobe's road performances to life.

As part of the Kobe Protro line, the Kobe 8 continues to offer cutting-edge technology while paying homage to one of the most beloved basketball sneakers ever made. The Protro updates include advanced cushioning and materials, making this sneaker a top choice for athletes and sneakerheads alike. The performance-driven design, combined with the sleek look of the Lakers Away colorway, makes this a standout addition to any Kobe collection.

Released on September 6, 2024, the Nike Kobe 8 Protro Lakers Away retailed at $190. The black, university gold, white, and court purple colorway pays tribute to the Lakers’ iconic uniforms. Whether on the court or in your rotation, this Kobe 8 Protro is a must-have for fans of the Black Mamba and basketball culture.

name: Satin Bred (Women's)
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Satin Bred (Women's)
description:
Unveiling the epitome of timeless design with the Jordan 1 Retro High OG Satin Bred (Women's) in the ever-classic Black/University Red/White colorway. The sophisticated satin finish adorns the iconic silhouette, exuding a blend of vintage charm and modern-day chic.

Every step in these sneakers resonates with the legacy of the Jordan brand, making a bold statement in today's fashion scene. The contrasting hues of black and university red, punctuated with white accents, embody a narrative of enduring style and basketball heritage.

Released on October 4th, 2023, at a retail price of $180, this trending sneaker is not just a pair of shoes, but a passport to a legacy celebrated across generations. Seize the essence of cool encapsulated in every stitch of the Jordan 1 Retro High OG Satin Bred, and step into a story that continues to redefine sneaker culture.

name: Olympic (2024)
title: Jordan 6 Retro Olympic (2024)
description:
Originally released in 2000, then retro'd again in 2012, the Jordan 6 Retro Olympic (2024) is a classic colorway of a fan-favorite silhouette. Released during the Paris Olympics, the sneaker's colorway pays homage to the red, white, and blue of the United States.

Debuting in 1991, the Jordan 6 has donned many iconic colorways, but the Olympic color is perhaps once of the most desired and recognizable. This 2024 release marks the 3rd time this sneaker has released, which has come only once every 12 years (2000, 2012, and 2024). The white upper with midnight navy accepts and varsity red touches bring this classic style to life.

The Jordan 6 Retro Olympic (2024) released on August 3rd, 2024, for a retail price of $200. Lock in this OG classic today on StockX.

name: Legend Blue (2024) (GS)
title: Jordan 11 Retro Legend Blue (2024) (GS)
description:
The Jordan 11 Retro Legend Blue (2024) (GS) is a relaunch of Tinker Hatfield’s sleek basketball shoe from 1995. It features a white base with Legend Blue and black accents.

Originally launched in 1996 as the "Columbia" colorway, this Legend Blue, grade school–sized version of the Jordan 11 Retro features a leather and mesh construction. The shiny patent leather overlays come in clean white, showing off the sneaker’s rounded toe and aerodynamic shape. Legend Blue details can be found on the semi-translucent rubber outsole, the Jumpman logo embroidered on the heel, and the tongue tag. In terms of technology, a carbon fiber plate runs the full length of the shoe and a Zoom Air unit provides cushioning. The back tab and collar come in black, contrasting the light Legend Blue and white.

Our experts at StockX like the heritage detailing, including the number 23 on the back tab. The Jordan 11 Retro Legend Blue (2024) (GS) was released on December 14, 2024, and sold for $185.

name: Hyper Royal Malachite
title: Nike SB Dunk Low Hyper Royal Malachite
description:
The Nike SB Dunk Low Hyper Royal Malachite is a low-top basketball shoe with a bold and modern design.

This version of the Nike SB Dunk Low is made with a suede upper. The base of the upper is a royal blue color on the sides, the toebox, and around the heel. The toebox is perforated for breathability. White suede overlays line the toebox, laces, and around the heel. The Nike Swoosh appears on both sides in a rich Malachite Green color. The blue tongue also contains a white Nike patch with green text, and the Nike brand name is stitched on the heel in green. The tongue and insole are cushioned for extra comfort, and the sole is made of rubber for traction and grip.

What we like most about this shoe is the bold green and blue color blocking. This design helps the shoe stand out. The Nike SB Dunk Low Hyper Royal Malachite was released on April 24, 2024, for a price of $115.

name: Nigel Sylvester Driveway Grey
title: Jordan 4 RM SP Nigel Sylvester Driveway Grey
description:
The Jordan 4 RM SP Nigel Sylvester Driveway Grey reinvents the classic Jordan Brand silhouette through BMX athlete Nigel Sylvester’s creative lens.

Anthracite-colored suede dominates the upper, while tonal TPU side panels with molded eyelets connect to the front lace system. Thin anthracite laces wind through the eyelets and keep the lightly padded tongue in place. Inspired by the original Air Jordan 4, the polyurethane midsole houses a visible air sole unit in the heel, which provides springy cushioning. "BIKE AIR" branding and a Swoosh logo in white decorate the heel near a small black Jumpman logo.

Our experts at StockX like the tiny Swoosh logo in University Red on the suede mudguard. It provides a pop of color against the dark upper and complements the University Red in the Air sole unit. The Jordan 4 RM SP Nigel Sylvester Driveway Grey was released on August 8, 2024, and sold for $160.

name: One Piece Straw Hat Luffy
title: Puma Suede One Piece Straw Hat Luffy
description:
The Puma Suede One Piece Straw Hat Luffy sneaker is a vibrant homage to the beloved protagonist of the iconic anime series, One Piece. Dressed in shades of feather grey and platinum grey, this sneaker captures the spirit of adventure and determination that Luffy embodies. Designed for fans who carry the essence of exploration and the dream of finding their own "One Piece," this edition marries the timeless appeal of Puma Suede with the adventurous heart of the Straw Hat crew.

Luffy, known for his unwavering resolve and charismatic leadership, inspires the design of this sneaker. The color palette, though understated, reflects the simplicity and depth of Luffy's character, offering a versatile look that can accompany fans on their own quests and daily adventures. The sneaker features subtle nods to the One Piece series that resonate with fans, making it a wearable piece of the saga they cherish.

Launched on March 23, 2024, for $85, the Puma Suede One Piece Straw Hat Luffy quickly sailed into the hearts of sneaker collectors and anime enthusiasts alike. Its release is celebrated as a moment when the paths of fashion and anime crossed, creating a sneaker that's not only a testament to Luffy's journey but also an invitation to wearers to set sail on their own adventures. This sneaker is a symbol of the journey, friendship, and dreams that define One Piece.

name: Lakers Home
title: Nike Kobe 8 Protro Lakers Home
description:
The Nike Kobe 8 Protro Lakers Home brings the energy of the Staples Center straight to your feet. This crisp white colorway is the perfect homage to the Lakers’ home uniforms, featuring a white engineered mesh upper, white midsole, and matching outsole. The purple embroidered Nike swoosh and Kobe’s signature in gold on the heel clip provide striking contrasts, while the gold Kobe logos on the tongue and heel tie the entire design together in true Lakers fashion.

As part of the Protro line, the Kobe 8 Lakers Home brings modern performance technology to one of the most iconic basketball sneakers ever. With its lightweight construction, responsive cushioning, and durable materials, this sneaker is built for both the court and the streets. The Lakers Home colorway blends performance and style, making it a must-have for any fan of Kobe Bryant and the Lakers dynasty.

Released on September 6, 2024, the Nike Kobe 8 Protro Lakers Home retailed at $190. The white, court purple, and university gold colorway celebrates the Lakers’ rich history and Kobe’s incredible legacy. Whether you’re rocking these on the court or adding them to your collection, the Lakers Home edition of the Kobe 8 Protro is a timeless tribute to basketball greatness.

name: Zebra
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Zebra
description:
Debuted in 2017, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Zebra is known as one of the most renowned colorways in the Yeezy line. It features a white and black marbled Primeknit upper with a white side-stripe and red "SPLY-350" text. At the base, a cushioned Boost sole provides comfort and support.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Zebra released in February of 2017 and retailed for $220.

name: Patta 20th Anniversary Chlorophyll
title: Nike Air Max 1 Patta 20th Anniversary Chlorophyll
description:
Celebrate 20 years of Patta with the Nike Air Max 1 Patta 20th Anniversary Chlorophyll, which released in 2024 and pays homage to the 5th anniversary model which released in 2009.

This sneaker features a grey, white, and green upper with a white midsole. This sneaker is highly coveted by sneakerheads due to it's similarly to the 5th anniversary model that released in 2009, that has similar color blocking. The Patta and Air Max branding can be seen on the tongue in white and green stitching. We love this sneaker due to its bold colors and OG references, making for a classic sneaker that you truly cannot go wrong with.

The Nike Air Max 1 Patta 20th Anniversary Chlorophyll released on September 13th, 2024, for a retail price of $160.

name: Carbon
title: adidas Yeezy Foam RNR Carbon
description:
The adidas Yeezy Foam RNR Carbon, released on August 8, 2023, continues to push the boundaries of sneaker design.

adidas utilized a robust blend of foam and rubber to construct the Yeezy Foam RNR, exhibiting a slick aesthetic in a striking Carbon colorway. The shoe's innovative one-piece design delivers unparalleled comfort, while strategic perforations ensure superior breathability. This isn't just footwear, it's a nod to the relentless innovation that defines the Yeezy brand.

Bold, and supremely comfortable, the adidas Yeezy Foam RNR Carbon was introduced on August 8, 2023, at a retail price of $80.

name: Aluminum Core Black (Women's)
title: adidas Handball Spezial Aluminum Core Black (Women's)
description:
The adidas Handball Spezial in Aluminum Core Black W (women’s) is an iteration of the original shoe that became popular with handball players in the late 1970s. As the latest colorway added to the collection, this shoe is rooted in history but features technological upgrades for comfort.

This women’s adidas Handball Spezial features a classic and simple design with the ultimate levels of comfort. The flexible rubber outsole provides bounce and energy return, while the soft suede upper and tongue provide soft comfort. Branding details include the classic 3-Stripes in black leather on the midsoles and the adidas name on the tongue. This simple design also features black leather on the heel.

At Stock X, we think the standout feature of this shoe is the classic and simple colorway. The combination of black, Cloud White, and Aluminum color patterns ensures that this shoe goes with any outfit, whether it's sportswear or your daily street style. The adidas Handball Spezial in Aluminum Core Black for women was released on July 19th, 2023, for a retail price of $110.

name: Gold Medal (2024)
title: Nike Kobe 4 Protro Gold Medal (2024)
description:
The Nike Kobe 4 Protro Gold Medal 2024 is a re-release of an iconic colorway that pays tribute to Kobe Bryant's legendary performance at the 2008 Olympics. This sneaker, featuring a striking white, dark obsidian, varsity red, and metallic gold colorway, celebrates Kobe’s pivotal role in the Redeem Team, where he led Team USA to victory and secured his place in Olympic history. The Protro line brings modern performance upgrades to this classic silhouette, combining heritage with innovation.

Designed with advanced tech, the Kobe 4 Protro features enhanced cushioning for superior comfort and support, making it perfect for both on-court performance and off-court style. The shoe’s low-cut design allows for maximum agility, while the Flywire technology offers a secure fit. The heel features the number 10 to honor the number Kobe wore in the Olympics. The colorway’s gold accents symbolize the triumph and excellence of Kobe’s Olympic journey, making this sneaker a meaningful addition to any collection.

Released on August 6, 2024, the Nike Kobe 4 Protro Gold Medal retailed at $190. This sneaker’s blend of white, dark obsidian, varsity red, and metallic gold captures the essence of a significant moment in basketball history. With its blend of historical significance and modern enhancements, the Kobe 4 Protro Gold Medal continues to resonate with fans and athletes alike.

name: Supersonic Light Bone Black
title: Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Supersonic Light Bone Black
description:
The Nike Vomero 5 Supersonic Light Bone Black takes on a running shoe silhouette with a low-top design, emphasizing comfort and performance.

The Supersonic Light Bone Black Nike Vomero 5 is constructed with a combination of synthetic leather and mesh in a primarily Light Bone upper with black accents. The molded heel counter and quarter-panel cage feature glow-in-the-dark accents, complemented by a signature Swoosh in synthetic white leather. The full-length Phylon midsole provides lightweight cushioning, incorporating Zoom Air technology for support, and is accompanied by a glow-in-the-dark rubber outsole. Nike branding is prominently displayed on the tongue, heel, and midsole for a touch of brand recognition.

What our experts say is the standout feature of the Nike Vomero 5 Supersonic Light Bone Black is the unique construction, which makes it an ideal choice for runners seeking enhanced comfort and performance. The sneaker combines an airy upper with a responsive midsole to create an ideal running shoe. The shoe debuted on August 1st, 2023, for $175.

name: Cherry (2022)
title: Jordan 11 Retro Cherry (2022)
description:
The Air Jordan 11 Cherry brings a Chicago colorway to the iconic patent leather sneaker. Cherry red patent leather mudguards surround the majority of the upper, alongside white leather and a matching Cherry red Jumpman. The lining features Cherry red cotton and with the signature 23 debossed on the heel tab. An icy blue outsole and Cherry red carbon fiber plate complete 2022’s Jordan 11 iteration.

The Air Jordan 11 Cherry was released on December 10, 2022 with a retail price of $225.

name: Aunt Pearl
title: Nike KD 17 NRG Aunt Pearl
description:
The Nike KD 17 NRG Aunt Pearl commemorates Kevin Durant's late aunt with its meaningful design and striking aesthetics. This edition continues the tradition of blending basketball performance with heartfelt storytelling, and combines unique materials and design elements in an unforgettable silhouette.

Aunt Pearl's version of the KD 17 NRG by Nike features a predominantly pink foam textile upper, accented with iridescent "KD" branding on the tongue and heel. Embroidered details on the heel overlay add depth and symbolize the emotional connection behind the design. The midsole integrates responsive Zoom Air cushioning in the forefoot, complemented by an Air Strobel unit in the heel. This shoe was introduced to honor Durant's aunt and raise awareness for cancer research.

One thing we love about the Nike KD 17 NRG Aunt Pearl is its intricate embroidery that honors Kevin Durant’s family legacy. Additionally, the cushioning system blends advanced Zoom Air and Air Strobel technology, which offers impressive performance. Released on 15th November 2024, this heartfelt design retailed at $150.

name: Chrome
title: Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Chrome
description:
The Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Chrome combines elements from lifestyle and running sneakers in the Nike catalog. It features a technical silhouette reminiscent of running shoes from the early ’00s and modern updates for comfort.

The upper is made of breathable mesh in Photon Dust with accents in Gridiron and Chrome. Metallic Chrome details on the forefoot overlays and the Swoosh stand out against the neutral background. Honeycomb-like paneling in the heel supports the ankle and helps the shoe keep its shape, while the front lace closure provides a secure fit. A Zoom Air unit adds bulk to the midsole and protects against impact stress. Finally, the black rubber outsole boasts a complex traction pattern that grips the ground.

Our experts at StockX like the tongue’s logo tag, which features NIKE VOMERO 5 in boxy print and peeks out above the laces. The Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Chrome was launched on April 1, 2024, and sold for $160.

name: Clear Pink Arctic Night (Women's)
title: adidas Handball Spezial Clear Pink Arctic Night (Women's)
description:
The adidas Handball Spezial Clear Pink Arctic Night (Women's) has transcended its original handball roots to become a streetwear staple. This iteration features a Clear Pink and gum color scheme.

The Clear Pink Arctic Night showcases the Clear Pink color scheme and includes Arctic Night 3-Stripes on the sides. There is also a shade resembling navy blue on the branding found on the tongue, insole, and heel tabs. Additionally, "Spezial" text branding, alongside a trefoil logo, embellishes the lateral sides of the shoe. Crafted from a blend of suede and leather, this shoe exudes a nostalgic aesthetic, while the gum outsole enhances its retro appeal. This sneaker boasts a rounded toe design, coupled with a front lace-up closure for a secure and customizable fit and is equipped with a branded insole for enhanced comfort during wear.

What our experts love about the adidas Handball Spezial Clear Pink Arctic Night (Women's) is its timeless and classic design. This sneaker exudes a retro aesthetic complete with a gum sole, a nod to its handball heritage. The sneaker released on 2nd July 2023 for $110.

name: Veneer (2020/2024)
title: Nike Dunk Low Veneer (2020/2024)
description:
Following February 2020’s release of the Nike Dunk Low Plum, Nike made the next step to completely retro the 2001 CO.JP Ugly Duckling Pack with the re-release of the Nike Dunk Low Veneer. Similar to the Plum Dunk Low, the Veneer colorway had never seen a retro until this 2020.

The Nike Dunk Low Veneer arrived in its OG form. Premium suede wraps the upper in shades of brown, green, and purple, providing nostalgic appeal for those who missed out on the 2001 issue. A mesh tongue, embroidered Nike lettering on the heel, and a white and purple sole add finishing touches to this cult classic.

The Nike Dunk Low CO.JP Veneer released in November of 2020 and retailed for $100. The Nike Dunk Low CO.JP Veneer released again in April of 2024 and retailed for $115.

name: Supreme Baroque Brown
title: Nike Air Force 1 Low Supreme Baroque Brown
description:
The Supreme Air Force 1 is back, this time in a classic brown colorway fit for your fall rotation. Supreme has a storied history of working with Nike on collaborative efforts, including various Air Force 1s that release seasonally through the brand's collections. This Baroque Brown colorway first released during the Supreme Fall/Winter 2023 season.

The Nike Air Force 1 Low Supreme Baroque Brown released on November 2nd, 2023, for a retail price of $124.

name: Neapolitan (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Neapolitan (Women's)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Neapolitan (Women's) finds inspiration in the chocolate brown, vanilla white, and strawberry pink of Neapolitan ice cream and cakes.

Originally seen on the Air Jordan 23 "Neapolitan," the Neapolitan colorway adds a soft touch to the classic Dunk Low silhouette. Summit White is the base color and can be found across the upper, the midsole, and the sockliner. The color-blocked forefoot and heel overlays display Light Orewood Brown, while the Swoosh logos on the side panels feature chocolatey Baroque Brown. The strawberry-inspired Pink Foam details add pops of color on the heel tab, the tongue’s woven logo tag, and a small Swoosh on the toe box. Like other Dunk Low models, the Neapolitan iteration has perforations across the vamp, a low-top silhouette, and a lace closure with chunky laces.

Our StockX experts like the splashes of Baroque Brown on the Foam Pink logo tags. The Nike Dunk Low Neapolitan (Women's) was released on April 9, 2024, and retailed at $115.

name: Maroon Gold Metallic (Women's)
title: adidas Samba OG Maroon Gold Metallic (Women's)
description:
The adidas Samba OG Maroon Gold Metallic (Women's) takes the classic Samba silhouette design and applies a rich colorway of maroon with Metallic Gold details.

The upper construction boasts smooth leather in maroon, while the toecap is made of soft suede in tonal maroon. The difference in textures creates subtle contrast and a luxury feel. The signature serrated 3-Stripes logo on the side panels is made of white leather. ‘SAMBA’ in Metallic Gold lettering runs along the 3-Stripes logo on the lateral side panel and complements the gold adidas logo printed on the tongue tag. Both the tongue and heel collar come in Cream White, which adds to the sneaker’s vintage appeal.

Our experts at StockX like the use of gum rubber on the durable outsole. The women’s size adidas Samba OG Maroon Gold Metallic (Women's) was released on February 9th, 2024, and retailed at $100.

name: St. John's
title: Nike Dunk Low SP St. John's
description:
Nike celebrated the 35th Anniversary of the Nike Dunk by releasing the Nike Dunk Low SP St. John's (2020), now available on StockX. The Nike Dunk debuted as part of the 1985 Nike College Color’s program, a program that delivered footwear in the school colors of 12 popular basketball programs allowing fans to support their favorite teams from head to toe. This St. John's colorway was among the first collegiate colorways Nike released, breaking the mold for colorways used on basketball shoes.

The Nike Dunk Low SP St. John's is composed of a white leather upper with red leather overlays. A white midsole, red outsole, and classic Nike branding on the tongue completes the design. These sneakers released in June of 2020 and retailed for $100 and again in October of 2023 and retailed for $110.

name: Smoke Grey Gum 3M Swoosh
title: Nike Dunk Low Smoke Grey Gum 3M Swoosh
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Smoke Grey Gum 3M Swoosh draws inspiration from the Nike Skateboarding Orange Label collection. However, the grey tone colorway and use of premium materials upgrade the classic low-top silhouette synonymous with Nike SB sneakers.

The grey suede and tumbled leather overlays balance out the clean, white upper and the light brown of the gum sole. The heel tabs, which feature ‘NIKE’ in white stitching, and the soft, cloth liner add additional accents in Light Iron Ore and Smoke Grey. Featuring laces with a reflective, speckled pattern, the lace cage houses a mesh tongue displaying Nike branding.

Something we love about this shoe is the 3M reflective detailing on the grey panel Swoosh. It increases visibility during low lighting and exemplifies the attention to detail found in this Nike Dunk Low variation. The Nike Dunk Low Smoke Grey Gum 3M Swoosh was released on October 3, 2023, and retailed at $115.

name: Medium Soft Pink Malachite
title: Nike Dunk Low Retro SE Medium Soft Pink Malachite
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Retro SE Medium Soft Pink Malachite is a low-top basketball sneaker made with a unique colorway.

This iteration of the Nike Dunk Low Retro SE comes with an upper made of a mix of leather and suede. The base of the upper is a medium soft pink leather, which appears on the sides, toebox, and around the heel. The toebox is also perforated. Green suede overlays contrast with the pink leather, outlining the toebox, the laces, and snaking down around the heel. The Nike Swoosh on both sides also appears in green suede. The pink cushioned tongue also contains a Nike patch, and the Nike brand name is stitched onto the green heel tab in light pink. The rubber sole is white on top and green on the bottom, and is patterned for grip on the court.

What we like best about this shoe is the combination of leather and suede on the upper, which allows for extra cushioning and style. The Nike Dunk Low Retro SE Medium Soft Pink Malachite was released on April 9, 2024, for a retail price of $125.

name: Black Max Orange (Women's)
title: Nike Shox TL Black Max Orange (Women's)
description:
The Nike Shox TL Black Max Orange W was released as part of the Nike Shox TL collection giving the original silhouette a nocturnal vibe. This sneaker in women's sizing arrives in a Black/​Black-Metallic Hematite-Max Orange colorway.
​
​The Nike Shox TL Black Max Orange is constructed in a mix of mesh and nylon satin to deliver a lightweight padded, mesh-lined collar and modified upper cage. Mesh segments ensure breathability with the black matching laces and Max Orange colored branding on the tongue and heel complete the upper design. The sole features several resistant and flexible full-length Shox columns for responsive cushioning from heel to toe.
​
​Our experts think the standout feature in the Shox TL version in Black Max Orange for Women is the unique black color scheme defined by distinctive ballistic and open mesh composition reinforced with a glossy TPU overlay. The Nike Shox TL Black Max Orange W was released on July 25th, 2019, and sold for $170.

name: White Gym Red (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Next Nature White Gym Red (Women's)
description:
The women's Nike Dunk Low Next Nature White Gym Red (W) features a white Flyleather upper with Gym Red overlays and Swooshes. From there, matching soles and woven tongue labels add the finishing touch.

The women's Nike Dunk Low Next Nature White Gym Red (W) released in May of 2022 and retailed for $105.

name: G-Dragon Peaceminusone Para-Noise 3.0
title: Nike Air Force 1 Low G-Dragon Peaceminusone Para-Noise 3.0
description:
Disclaimer: Please be aware of paint fragility regarding the first layer of color on the upper. Due to the thin coating of paint, colors may rub off.

Introducing the Nike Air Force 1 Low G-Dragon Peaceminusone Para-Noise 3.0, the third installment in the highly coveted collaboration between Nike and South Korean artist G-Dragon utilizing the Air Force 1 base. This special edition features a black leather upper that wears away over time to reveal hidden artwork by G-Dragon, adding a personal, creative touch to every pair. The sneaker showcases contrasting swooshes in yellow, pink, and blue, with a signature sunflower logo on the tongue and custom graphics on the insoles, giving this sneaker a vibrant and artistic vibe.

In keeping with the Air Force 1’s legendary status in both basketball and streetwear, the Para-Noise 3.0 incorporates G-Dragon’s unique artistic flair with features like brushstrokes along the midsole, custom pins, and a special-edition box. Since its debut in 1982, the Air Force 1 has evolved into one of the most iconic sneakers in Nike’s lineup, and this collaboration adds yet another layer of creativity to its storied history.

Released on September 14, 2024, the Nike Air Force 1 Low G-Dragon Peaceminusone Para-Noise 3.0 retailed at $200. The black, new emerald, pinkfire, tour yellow, and blue gale colorway, paired with G-Dragon’s signature artwork, makes this release a statement piece for both sneakerheads and art enthusiasts alike. This collaboration continues to redefine what a sneaker can be—a canvas for both fashion and expression.

name: Paris Olympics Wet Cement (GS)
title: Jordan 4 Retro SE Paris Olympics Wet Cement (GS)
description:
The Jordan 4 Retro SE Paris Olympics Wet Cement GS edition captures the excitement of the 2024 Summer Olympics with its trendy monochromatic color palette . Featuring a striking colorway of smoke grey, iron grey, and cement grey, this sneaker is one of the most anticipated releases of the year. Its bold and modern aesthetic makes it a standout in the Jordan 4 lineup.

The Jordan 4 Retro Wet Cement is constructed with a mix of premium materials, ensuring both comfort and durability. The upper combines smooth and textured leathers, creating a dynamic look and feel. The midsole features the signature Air cushioning for maximum comfort, making it perfect for everyday wear. The varying shades of grey give the sneaker a sophisticated yet edgy vibe, ideal for those who want to make a statement.

Released on July 27, 2024, the Jordan 4 Retro SE Paris Olympics GS edition retailed at $170. Its smoke grey, iron grey, and cement grey colorway embodies a sleek and modern look that has quickly become a favorite among sneakerheads. Combining classic design with contemporary flair, the Jordan 4 Retro continues to capture the hearts of basketball fans and sneakerheads alike.

name: Space Jam (GS)
title: Jordan 11 Retro Low Space Jam (GS)
description:
The Jordan 11 Retro Low Space Jam (GS) finds inspiration in the adult-sized high-top iteration of the Jordan 11 Retro "Space Jam."

This low-top sneaker features an upper made of durable ballistic mesh in black with a shiny, black patent leather mudguard that wraps around the shoe. The Phylon midsole comes in white and houses a full-length Air-sole unit plus a carbon fiber plate. The translucent rubber outsole wraps around the midsole and provides a glimpse of Varsity Blue rubber. In addition, Varsity Blue elements can be found on the Jumpman logos on the tongue and heel tab. Extra cushioning in the heel adds stability and supports the ankle, while the slightly oversized tongue pops out of the lace cage.

Our StockX experts like how the wavy pattern on the mudguard matches the outsole. The grade-school-sized Jordan 11 Retro Low Space Jam (GS) was released on May 18, 2024, and retailed at $150.

name: There Skateboards
title: Nike SB Dunk Low There Skateboards
description:
The Nike SB Dunk Low There Skateboards is a stylish collaboration between Nike SB and the California based skate brand, There Skateboards. Dressed in a sleek black, gorge green, and summit white colorway, this Dunk captures the essence of skate culture with its clean lines and minimalist approach. The collaboration reflects the shared values of craftsmanship and authenticity, making this release particularly special for fans of both brands.

The Nike SB Dunk has always been a symbol of the intersection between skateboarding and street fashion, and this partnership with There Skateboards underscores that connection. The design includes premium materials like smooth leather and suede, giving the sneaker both durability and a refined edge. Subtle branding details like the There logo on the tongue and insole make this collaboration distinct while maintaining the timeless appeal of the SB Dunk.

Released on August 6, 2024, the Nike SB Dunk Low There Skateboards retailed at $135. The black, gorge green, and summit white colorway offers a versatile yet stylish look that’s perfect for skaters and collectors alike. Whether you’re hitting the pavement or just looking to elevate your style, this Dunk offers the ideal mix of function and fashion.

name: Drake NOCTA Certified Lover Boy
title: Nike Air Force 1 Low Drake NOCTA Certified Lover Boy
description:
Previously dubbed "Certified Lover Boy", the new premium Drake-inspired AF1 is now known as the "Love You Forever." This sentiment is inspired by Drake’s favorite childhood book with subtle added details of the scripted "Love You Forever" on the midsole, in the same white color. Additional design elements include customized laces, NOCTA logo on left heel, and a new perforation pattern on toe box.
​
The special-edition Drake Nike Air Force 1 Low released December of 2022 for $160.

name: Black White (2024)
title: Nike Air DT Max '96 Black White (2024)
description:
The Nike Air DT Max '96 Black White (2024) is a shoe designed as a revival of the original design from the 1990s.

This iteration of the Nike Air DT Max ‘96 is constructed with a white leather base for the upper. The upper is covered with a black leather overlay that looks like it’s dripping from the top in streaks down the white midsole and into the outsole. Black also forms the toe cap, and on the lateral side, the black streaks have perforations that reveal a Varsity Maize yellow color underneath. Small yellow Nike swooshes also appear on each side of the ankle, and a black strap over the laces contains a white Nike swoosh. The heel contains a yellow Swoosh and the word "AIR," while the tongue also features branding elements. The white wavy outsole contains a visible Air DT Max unit in the heel.

What we like most about this particular sneaker is the way the black overlays look like they’re dripping down the shoe’s upper. The Nike Air DT Max '96 Black White (2024) was released on June 14, 2024, for $170.

name: Photon Dust Pink Foam (Women's)
title: Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Photon Dust Pink Foam (Women's)
description:
The Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Photon Dust Pink Foam (Women's) adds metallic-silver accents to the upper and splashes of Pink Foam across the sole unit.

The layered sneaker, Photon Dust Pink Foam (Women's) Nike Zoom Vomero 5, finds inspiration in running shoes from the early 2000s, which can be seen in the synthetic leather overlays and the plastic caging on the side panels. The synthetic leather allows the metallic silver to shine, while reflective accents provide visibility in low lighting. The combination of loose weave mesh in Pure Platinum and ventilation ports on the heel allows the foot to breathe and stay cool. In terms of technology, snappy Zoom Air cushioning adds a responsive feel, and the rubber outsole grips the ground.

Our experts at StockX like the straightforward logo tag, which displays "NIKE VOMERO 5" lettering and matches the black accents across the shoe. The Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Photon Dust Pink Foam (Women's) was originally released on August 1, 2024, and sold for $160.

name: White (Women's)
title: Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 White (Women's)
description:
The women's Nike Air Force 1 Low White silhouette (W) continues the tradition of the 1982 Air Force 1. The sneaker features an all-white leather upper with a perforated toe box and Swoosh overlays. A Nike heel embroidery and white sole completes the design.

The women's Nike Air Force 1 Low White 2018 (W) released in January 2018 and retailed for $90. The retail price was increased to $115 in 2023.

name: Give Her Flowers (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Give Her Flowers (Women's)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Give Her Flowers (Women's) paints the Nike Dunk Low in an off-white Sail with flower details.

This off-white sneaker was first announced as one of Nike’s Valentine’s Day 2024 products and features romantic elements. For example, ‘you deserve flowers’ is printed across the Medium Soft Pink insole in delicate cursive lettering. A gold pin with a red rose and green leaves can be found on the heel panels. The leather upper comes in Sail, while the textile overlays feature a floral pattern in the same color. Like other Dunk Low models, the signature leather Swoosh streaks across the side panels and wraps around the heel. The sneaker sits on a rubber cupsole that comes in complementary Sail.

Our StockX experts like the University Red ‘Nike’ lettering on the tongue’s logo tag. It adds a pop of color that matches the rose pin. The women’s size Nike Dunk Low Give Her Flowers (Women's) was released on March 8th, 2024, and retailed at $115.

name: Sail All-Star
title: Nike Kobe 6 Protro Sail All-Star
description:
The Nike Kobe 6 Protro Sail All-Star brings a fresh twist to an iconic silhouette. This edition stands out with its sail-dominated upper, offset by a striking black Swoosh and subtle platinum violet accents. Unlike previous versions of the Kobe 6, this release introduces a bold new starry pattern on the upper, replacing the signature snakeskin texture on the medial sides of the upper. This design choice not only elevates the shoe’s visual appeal but also nods to Kobe Bryant’s star power and celebrates the 2025 NBA all star weekend, making it a must-have for collectors and hoopers alike.

Further refining its look, the sneaker features light bone tones across the midsole and heel, creating a balanced contrast with the white outsole. The platinum violet lining adds a unique pop of color without overpowering the shoe’s clean aesthetic. Performance-wise, the Kobe 6 Protro maintains its low-cut profile and responsive cushioning, ensuring optimal comfort on and off the court. Whether styled casually or laced up for a game, this pair seamlessly merges function with fashion.

Released on February 13, 2025, the Nike Kobe 6 Protro Sail All-Star hit shelves at a retail price of $190, quickly becoming a sought-after addition to the Kobe lineup. Its refined blend of sail, black, light bone, white, and platinum violet gives it a timeless appeal, while the innovative design elements make it a standout among past iterations.

name: Silver Off White
title: Onitsuka Tiger Mexico 66 Silver Off White
description:
The Onitsuka Tiger Mexico 66 drops in a striking Silver/Off White palette, seamlessly merging vintage vibes with contemporary fashion.

At the forefront of the sneaker game, this classic silhouette has reinvented itself once again. Featuring leather craftsmanship, the shimmering silver upper is complemented beautifully by muted off-white highlights, and an off white midsole making it an instant head-turner. But it isn't just about aesthetics; the Mexico 66 is a statement piece with a history. When you lace up, you're not only joining the fashion-forward crowd but also honoring the iconic legacy of Onitsuka Tiger.

This trendsetting blends classic old-school charm with modern flair. The Onitsuka Tiger Mexico 66 in Silver/Off White was available at an initial retail price of $120.

name: Pine Green
title: Jordan 4 Retro SB Pine Green
description:
Nike SB’s collaboration with Jordan helps create the ultimate sneaker for the skatepark to the basketball court, with the release of the Jordan 4 Retro SB Pine Green.

The Jordan 4 Retro SB Pine Green used a white leather upper with a Neutral Grey suede mudguard. The limited edition sneakers sit on top of a white and Pine Green midsole which is highlighted by a red air unit. Nike used a gum outsole to help with increased grip while skateboarding.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro SB Pine Green released March 20, 2023, with a retail price of $225.

name: Dark Green Cloud White
title: adidas Campus 00s Dark Green Cloud White
description:
The adidas Campus 00s Dark Green Cloud White comes in a dark green, cloud white, and off-white color scheme.

The Dark Green Cloud White adidas Campus 00s has an upper that is constructed from dark green suede. The shoe's padded collar offers support and comfort. The sneaker's rubber outsole is durable and provides traction and stability. The perforated ventilation holes on the sides of the upper of the shoe provide breathability. In addition, the shoe has an EVA midsole for padding and support. The shoe features the signature 3-Stripes logo on the lateral sides, "CAMPUS" text on one side, and Trefoil branding on the tongue and heel.

The adidas Campus 00s Dark Green Cloud White was released on March 15, 2023, and sold for a retail price of $110.

name: Galaxy (2025)
title: Nike Air Foamposite One Galaxy (2025)
description:
The Nike Air Foamposite One Galaxy (2025) revives one of the most legendary sneaker releases of all time. Originally launching in 2012 as part of Nike Basketball’s All-Star "Galaxy Pack," the Foamposite quickly became a cultural icon, sparking massive hype and even chaotic release-day stories. More than just a sneaker, the "Galaxy" Foamposite represented the intensity of sneaker culture, and now, in 2025, it's making its highly anticipated return. The futuristic obsidian and black Foamposite shell serves as a base, allowing the cosmic theme to take center stage, while anthracite accents complete the sleek aesthetic.

Just like its predecessor, the 2025 edition retains the signature glow-in-the-dark outsole, adding to its out-of-this-world appeal. Details like the "Remove Before Flight" pull tabs and Penny Hardaway’s 1 Cent logo remain intact, staying true to the original design that captivated sneakerheads over a decade ago. This drop isn’t just another rerelease—it’s a revival of one of the most sought-after sneakers in history.

Landing on February 21, 2025, the Nike Air Foamposite One Galaxy (2025) retailed at $230, bringing back the magic of the original with a fresh perspective. Dressed in obsidian, black, and anthracite, this pair is a must-have for collectors and those looking to own a piece of sneaker history.

name: Cool Grey (2021)
title: Jordan 11 Retro Cool Grey (2021)
description:
Since its debut in 2001, the Air Jordan 11 Cool Grey has become one of the most celebrated colorways in the Jordan 11 catalog.

The Air Jordan 11 Cool Grey (2021) features a Cool Grey Durabuck upper with patent leather overlays and a signature Jumpman embroidery on the collar. From there, a white midsole and an icy blue translucent outsole complete the design.

The Air Jordan 11 Cool Grey (2021) released in December of 2021 and retails for $225.

name: Grey Gum (Kids)
title: adidas Campus 00s Grey Gum (Kids)
description:
The adidas Campus 00s Grey Gum (GS) was designed particularly for grade schoolers and comes in a Grey Three and Cloud White colorway.

The upper of the Campus 00s Grey Gum is made of a premium suede material that is durable and provides comfort. The shoe has a low-top silhouette with the collar below the ankle, making it more lightweight and flexible. This design makes it easier for the wearer to move quickly and perform activities that require agility, such as playing basketball or running. The 3-Stripes branding is prominently displayed on the side, while the adidas logo is on the heel. The shoe's interior has a textile lining that adds comfort and breathability.

Our experts say that one of the standout features of the adidas Campus 00s Grey Gum (GS) is the gum rubber outsole, which adds contrast and provides grip. The outsole also has a herringbone traction pattern, which ensures stability and traction on any surface. The shoe was released on February 18th, 2023 at a retail price of $80.

name: White Metallic Gold
title: New Balance 1906R White Metallic Gold
description:
The New Balance 1906R White Metallic Gold comes in a metallic silver and metallic gold color scheme.

The New Balance 1906R White Metallic Gold adopts a classic silhouette with white leather and gold embellishments. The upper is breathable and lightweight, with a cushioned collar and tongue for comfort. The midsole is constructed from lightweight EVA foam for cushioning and support. Durable rubber is used to construct the outsole, which provides grip and steadiness. The shoe also features "N" branding in a contrasting gold and black colorway on both lateral sides.

The New Balance 1906R White Metallic Gold was made available on August 12th, 2022, for a retail price of $155.

name: Bred (2025)
title: Jordan 1 Retro High '85 OG Bred (2025)
description:
The Air Jordan 1 Retro High '85 OG Bred (2025) brings back one of the most iconic colorways in sneaker history. Originally launched in 1985 and famously "banned" by the NBA, this black and varsity red design has come to symbolize rebellion and style. For its 40th anniversary, Jordan Brand delivers a meticulously designed updated edition that is a return to the styling of the original with premium leather construction and its unmistakable color blocking.

With a slightly taller build and a larger, sleeker swoosh compared to more recent retros, this pair is as close to the 1985 version as it gets. The black leather base is accented with varsity red overlays and a clean white midsole, while additional features include a rubber outsole for durability, extra laces, and a nostalgic hangtag. Each pair is packaged in its original-style box, completing the retro experience for collectors and fans alike.

Released on February 14, 2025, during the NBA All-Star Weekend, the Jordan 1 Retro High '85 OG Bred retailed for $250. Dressed in black, varsity red, and white, this drop was said to be limited to just 10,000 pairs worldwide, making it one of the rarest Jordan 1 releases in years.

name: Ascent
title: adidas AE 1 Ascent
description:
The adidas AE 1 Ascent adds a sleek colorway of Charcoal and Core Black to NBA player Anthony Edward’s first signature sneaker with adidas.

The mid-top Ascent adidas AE 1 sits on a lightweight, TPU-encased Jet Boost and LightStrike midsole, which finds support in a full-length torsional plate. While the upper is crafted from tightly woven mesh, TPU side panels with a honeycomb-like construction bolster the shoe and allow the foot to breathe. The TPU side panels also feature a marbled pattern in Charcoal that makes the "Ascent" stand out from other adidas AE 1 models. Although the sneaker boasts minimal branding details, a rubberized 3-Stripes logo graces the molded back heel.

Our experts at StockX like the oversized herringbone traction pattern on the rubber outsole because it provides grip while complementing the honeycomb pattern on the side panels. The adidas AE 1 Ascent was released on July 20, 2024, and retailed at $120.

name: Nina Chanel Abney Bicoastal (Women's)
title: Jordan 3 Retro SP Nina Chanel Abney Bicoastal (Women's)
description:
The Jordan Air Jordan 3 Retro SP Nina Chanel Abney Bicoastal (Women's) is a stunning collaboration that merges fine art with sneaker culture. Featuring a unique colorway of bicoastal green, black, malachite, and fossil, this sneaker stands out with its striking design elements. The green canvas and suede upper, combined with rope laces, offers a fresh and stylish look. The modified Jumpman logo on the tongue, a first for a Jordan retro collaboration, adds a distinctive touch that highlights the innovative approach taken in this design.

This sneaker celebrates the artistic brilliance of Nina Chanel Abney, a fine artist known for her bold and vibrant works. The Jordan 3, first introduced in 1988, is reinterpreted through Abney's creative lens, resulting in a sneaker that is both a piece of art and a fashion statement. The leather heel tab with a chenille Nike Air logo adds to the unique aesthetic, making this model a must-have for collectors.

Released on June 20, 2024, and retailing at $225, the Jordan Air Jordan 3 Retro SP Nina Chanel Abney Bicoastal (Women's) is a standout piece in any collection. This sneaker seamlessly blends the heritage of the Jordan brand with contemporary artistic expression, offering a stylish and culturally significant addition to your wardrobe. Don’t miss out on this exceptional model that embodies the spirit of innovation and creativity.

name: Earth Strata Gum (Women's)
title: adidas Samba OG Earth Strata Gum (Women's)
description:
The adidas Samba OG Earth Strata Gum (Women's) dresses the Samba OG silhouette in a rich Earth Strata hue, with accents in Footwear White and Gold Metallic.

Sourcing design inspiration from indoor soccer shoes, the Earth Strata Gum (Women's) adidas Samba OG iteration features a smooth calf leather construction. The thin overlay across the toebox and the eyelets are crafted from calf suede and come in Earth Strata. Additional Earth Strata accents are located on the thin laces, the leather tongue, the collar, and the insole. However, the leather heel mustache and serrated 3-stripes logo feature clean Footwear White. Contributing a heritage detail, the gum rubber outsole provides grippy traction underfoot.

Our experts at StockX appreciate the leather insole and collar, which increase the sneaker’s premium appeal and pay tribute to the OG models. The women’s size adidas Samba OG Earth Strata Gum (Women's) was originally released on August 1, 2024, and was priced at $100.

name: Collegiate Green (Women's)
title: adidas Samba OG Collegiate Green (Women's)
description:
The adidas Samba can be traced all the way back to the 1950s, but adidas continues to come up with ways to makes its iconic silhouette look modern in the present day. The adidas Samba OG Collegiate Green (Women's), which is a women's-exclusive shoe, accomplishes this goal by covering the Samba with a set of new colors.

This version of the adidas Samba features a soft full-grain leather upper done up in Collegiate Green with matching suede overlays. It also includes Cream White accents found on the tongue, Three Stripes logos, and heel. There is a gum rubber midsole and a gum rubber cupsole as well that finish off the sneaker's look.

What our sneaker experts like best about this Samba, though, are the gold foil details sprinkled throughout the shoe. They help tie its appearance together and give it the more modern appearance adidas was going for. The adidas Samba OG Collegiate Green (Women's) was released on January 22, 2024, when it retailed for $100.

name: Maroon Preloved Brown (Women's)
title: adidas SL 72 OG Maroon Preloved Brown (Women's)
description:
The adidas SL 72 OG Maroon Preloved Brown (Women’s) is a slim sneaker whose design has become a classic since the release of the first version in 1972.

This iteration of the adidas SL 72 OG comes with a suede and textile upper. The base is a dark brown shade with lighter brown suede overlays rounding out the toebox, coming up from the toe under the laces, under the midsole, and around the heel. The three stripes logo appears on the midsoles in a beige color. There is a gold adidas logo stamped onto the brown heel collar, while the tongue also bears a logo patch. The slim rubber outsole also has the adidas logo embossed onto it.

Our favorite feature of this shoe is the slim build. This gives the shoe a retro and classic look. The adidas SL 72 OG Maroon Preloved Brown (Women’s) was first released on March 28, 2024, for a retail price of $100.

name: Black
title: YZY Pods Black
description: DISCLAIMER: The YZY Pods Black comes in three sizes 1, 2 & 3. The sizes listed use updated US and EU conversions directly from the manufacturer. Please note that the Yeezy Pod Black runs slightly big, so if you are between sizes, it is best to size down.

name: Miami Dolphins
title: Nike Dunk Low Miami Dolphins
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Miami Dolphins takes a classic sports shoe silhouette and dresses it in the iconic colors of the legendary NFL franchise.

The Miami Dolphins colorway of the Nike Dunk Low-Top sports a base of white leather with the signature perforations in the toe box for breathability. Overlays adorn the upper in iconic Miami Dolphin turquoise that matches the sock liner that's padded at the collar. The orange leather Nike swoosh matches the orange heel tab with white Nike branding. White Nike branding appears on the turquoise insole, while turquoise Nike branding adorns the white tongue tag.

What we enjoy most about this sneaker is the way the sole unit locks in the Miami Dolphins colors as well as the Nike Dunk dependability. A white foam midsole and turquoise rubber outsole provide impact absorption and traction for sports or everyday wear. The Nike Dunk Low Miami Dolphins was released on January 17, 2024, for a retail price of $115.

name: Wonder Quartz (Women's)
title: adidas Samba OG Wonder Quartz (Women's)
description:
The adidas Samba OG Wonder Quartz (Women's) adds a subdued colorway of Wonder Quartz and Cloud White, plus a dark gum sole to the Samba OG silhouette.

The dark gum hue contrasts the light pink Wonder Quartz without distracting from the classic Samba OG design. The upper is crafted entirely from smooth leather, which gives the sneaker a premium feel. While the base comes in Cloud White, Wonder Quartz is on the serrated 3-Stripes. Both the heel tab and the T-shaped toebox overlay boast a light tan tone that complements the other colors.

Our experts at StockX like the metallic silver logo tag on the tongue because it matches the "samba" on the side panel. In addition, the tag displays a trefoil and "adidas" lettering. The women's size adidas Samba OG Wonder Quartz (Women's) was initially launched on May 1, 2024, and sold for a price of $100.

name: Magic Beige Collegiate Green (Women's)
title: adidas Gazelle Bold Magic Beige Collegiate Green (Women's)
description:
The adidas Gazelle Bold Magic Beige Collegiate Green Women’s combines neutral colors and the brand’s classic Gazelle style. The upper part of the shoe is made from a suede material, while the bottom is composed of rubber.

A new take on the original model, the Collegiate Green Gazelle Bold Magic Beige for women has a suede base that is Sweden Beige color. The mudguard is made up of a suede as well, which is a slightly darker shade. On the side of the shoe, there are the 3-Stripes in a dark green leather. The classic gum sole is Neutral Tan color.

What our experts love about this model is the extra thick gum sole that is designed to provide the wearer with ultimate comfort. The adidas Gazelle Bold Magic Beige Collegiate Green Women’s was first released on July 26th, 2023, and had a starting retail value of $120.

name: Triple Black Leather
title: New Balance 9060 Triple Black Leather
description:
The New Balance 9060 Triple Black Leather applies a black-on-black colorway and premium materials to the 9060’s technical silhouette.

This New Balance 9060 combines elements from two high-performance predecessors – the 990 and the 860. While several technical features are borrowed from the 990, the sneaker’s style details come from the 860. The upper features black mesh with soft suede and synthetic leather overlays. The incorporation of mesh allows the foot to breathe and reduces the shoe’s overall weight. The overlays create a wavy pattern that complements the curves of the chunky midsole and rubber outsole. The signature New Balance ‘N’ can be found on the side panels in tonal black leather.

Our StockX experts like the addition of a stacked ABZORB midsole, which gives the shoe a semi-bulky appearance and reduces impact stress. The New Balance 9060 Triple Black Leather was released on September 24th, 2023, and retailed at $170.

name: Midnight Navy
title: Jordan 4 Retro Midnight Navy
description:
The Air Jordan 4 Retro White Midnight Navy dresses in white, midnight navy, and light smoke grey colorway.

The upper of this Retro Air Jordan 4 sneaker is constructed from white leather with black support Wings, a matching black heel tab with embossed Jumpman branding, and navy molded eyelets. A second Jumpman icon adorns the woven tongue tag in crimson. The shoe rides on a two-tone polyurethane midsole, featuring encapsulated Air technology in the forefoot and a visible unit in the heel.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro White Midnight Navy was released on the 29th of October, 2022, for an initial retail price of $210.

name: Black Pure Silver
title: ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Black Pure Silver
description:
The ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Black Pure Silver is a running shoe that pays homage to the style of the late 2000s with updated materials and construction.

This version of the ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 is made with a black mesh upper for breathability. Synthetic leather overlays can be seen across the midsole in black and silver forming the classic ASICS design. There are also black overlays around the toebox and heel for extra support. The ASICS logo appears in silver on the cushioned tongue, and GEL branding appears in silver on the heel. The shoe is equipped with a TRUSSTIC support system and trademark Gel cushioning for comfort and shock absorption.

What makes these shoes stand out is the black colorway. The black with a few accents of silver elevates these shoes from a simple running shoe to a stylish fashion choice. The ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Black Pure Silver was released on January 1, 2024, for a price of $150.

name: Rose Whisper (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Rose Whisper (Women's)
description:
The women's Nike Dunk Low Rose Whisper arrives in a classic two-tone color blocked look similar to the original Nike Dunks of the 1980s. This Dunk offers a warm palette primed for the summer weather, with a white and Rose Whisper leather construction. Matching woven tongue labels contribute to the design's retro feel, while an EVA foam sole provides cushioning.

The women's Nike Dunk Low Rose Whisper released in June of 2022 and retailed for $100.

name: Big Bubble Air Max Day (2024)
title: Nike Air Max 1 '86 OG Big Bubble Air Max Day (2024)
description:
The Nike Air Max 1 '86 OG Big Bubble Air Max Day (2024) is a special-edition sneaker that was released to celebrate Air Max Day.

The sneaker boasts a white mesh construction with suede overlays in Royal Blue and Sail. Unlike other Nike Air Max 1 models released as part of Air Max Day, the "Big Bubble Air Max Day" iteration features a Volt midsole that catches the eye. The tongue’s inner lining also showcases a panel of Volt synthetic material. The oversized window in the heel displays visible Air Max units and four circular cut outs.

Something our StockX experts like is the ‘3.26’ on the tongue’s logo tag. It represents the date of Air Max Day and comes in chunky Blue Volt letters. The Nike Air Max 1 '86 OG Big Bubble Air Max Day (2024) was launched on March 26th, 2024, and sold for $150.

name: Black Metallic Gold
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Black Metallic Gold
description:
The Jordan 1 Retro High OG Black Metallic Gold adds stark black and metallic-gold color blocking to this classic Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG variation.

Premium leather provides durable structure to the upper, while the solid rubber outsole adds traction underfoot. Although the base construction comes in black, metallic-gold accents decorate the perforated vamp, the Swoosh large logo, the heel, and the overlay across the ankle. The natural rubber tone of the outsole complements the metallic gold, while the midsole’s Sail hue gives the sneaker a retro feel. In keeping with tradition, the Air Jordan Wings logo is displayed across the metallic-gold leather.

Our experts like the gold "NIKE AIR" lettering on the tag because it stands out against the black tongue and contributes to the sneaker’s black-on-gold aesthetic. The Jordan 1 Retro High OG Black Metallic Gold was originally released on August 10, 2024, and was priced at $180.

name: Valentine's Day Treat Yourself (2025) (Women's)
title: Jordan 3 Retro Valentine's Day Treat Yourself (2025) (Women's)
description:
The Jordan 3 Retro Valentine’s Day Treat Yourself (2025) (Women’s) is a love letter to sneaker enthusiasts who appreciate a perfect blend of style and nostalgia. Dressed in a luxurious washed coral leather upper, this special edition release stays true to the classic Jordan 3 silhouette while adding a romantic twist. The iconic elephant print appears on the mudguard and heel in a shimmering pink hue, creating a subtle contrast that elevates the overall design.

Adding to its charm, gym red accents highlight the Jumpman logos and lower eyelets, giving the pair a striking pop of color. A standout feature is the set of two red jewel charmss, allowing wearers to personalize their look with a little extra sparkle. The midsole is finished in sail, complementing the pink upper, while a semi-translucent pink gum outsole provides the perfect finishing touch. Whether worn for a Valentine's date or simply as an everyday statement piece, this pair is a must-have for sneaker lovers.

Released on February 1, 2025, the Jordan 3 Retro Valentine’s Day Treat Yourself (2025) (Women’s) retailed at $200 and quickly captured the hearts of collectors and casual wearers alike. With its romantic washed coral, gym red, and sail colorway, this sneaker celebrates love and style in a way only Jordan Brand can.

name: White Green
title: New Balance 550 White Green
description:
The New Balance 550 White Green features a smooth white leather upper with a grey suede toe wrap and green detailing. From there, a New Balance Basketball woven tongue label and matching sole completes the design.

The New Balance 550 White Green released in June of 2021 and retailed for $120.

name: Oxidized Green (GS)
title: Jordan 4 Retro Oxidized Green (GS)
description:
The Jordan 4 Retro Oxidized Green (GS) is a child-sized basketball shoe crafted of premium materials with metallic details.

Like the adult-sized version, the Oxidized Green (GS) Jordan 4 Retro features a smooth leather base in white with white mesh on the quarter panels and above the toebox. Metallic Green accents are on the free-floating eyestays and the panel running along the midsole. The sneaker offers additional padding around the ankle and a thick tongue, which contributes to the shoe’s bulky aesthetic. Visible Air units provide responsive cushioning, seen through windows in the heel. Finally, the rubber outsole increases traction and comes in Oxidized Green, white, and Neutral Grey.

Our StockX experts like the sneaker’s minimal branding, including Jumpman logos on the oversized tongue and the heel. The grade school-sized Jordan 4 Retro Oxidized Green (GS) was released on June 15, 2024, and retailed at $150.

name: Powder Blue (2024)
title: Jordan 9 Retro Powder Blue (2024)
description:
The Air Jordan 9 Retro Powder Blue 2024 revives a fan favorite colorway with a fresh execution. It features a white leather upper that's both luxurious to the touch and robust for wear. Black components grace the tongue, eyelets, liner, pull tabs, and midsole, highlighted by the iconic Jumpman. These dark accents set the stage for the dark powder blue featured on the midsole, inner lining, tongue branding, and logo on the heel pull tabs, imbuing the sneaker with a cool, collected charm that makes this sneaker truly stand out.

Every aspect of the sneaker is infused with intention—the powder blue adorns the midsole creating a visual synergy that's both striking and sophisticated. The Air Jordan 9's unique globe emblem on the heel celebrates Jordan's global influence, while the intricate stitch patterns and layered panels add depth and texture to the design.

The release of the Air Jordan 9 Retro Powder Blue on March 23, 2024, for $210, marked a triumphant return of a beloved colorway. The launch celebrated Jordan's global appeal, with the sneaker's white and black composition setting the stage for the serene powder blue, ensuring its place in the annals of sneaker culture as a testament to timeless design and universal appeal.

name: Military Black
title: Jordan 4 Retro Military Black
description:
Jordan Brand flipped one of its original Air Jordan 4 colorways for the Air Jordan 4 Military Black.

Pulling its color-blocked style from the Air Jordan 4 Military Blue, the Air Jordan 4 Military Black features a smooth white leather upper with a light grey Durabuck toe wrap and netted TPU inserts. Military Black eyelets, heel tabs, and underlays add a stark contrast to the upper. At the base, a white, black, and light grey sole with a visible Air unit completes the design.

The Air Jordan 4 Military Black released in May of 2022 and retailed for $210.

name: Black Red
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Black Red
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Black Red is one of the first original colorways to drop after the silouhette’s debut in 2016. Despite its original 2017 release, the 350 V2 Black Red restocked in 2020, giving fans a second chance at grabbing a pair at retail.

The adidas Yeezy 350 V2 Black Red features familiar style cues that made the silhouette popular today. The upper consists of black Primeknit material for breathability. A black ribbed midsole encases an entire BOOST cushioning system for added comfort. Lastly, signature "SPLY-350" is knitted along the lateral side of each pair.

The adidas Yeezy 350 V2 originally released in February of 2017 and retailed for $220.

PLEASE NOTE: This page is for the original and restock, so production dates may vary.

name: Drake NOCTA White
title: Nike Hot Step 2 Drake NOCTA White
description:
The Nike Hot Step 2 Drake NOCTA White is an updated version of Nike’s Hot Step, which features a primarily white upper with metallic chrome accents.

The upper is made of a smooth synthetic leather material, forming ripples along the side panels. Textile webbing locks the laces in place and creates a snug fit for the cushioned tongue. In addition, the heel boasts cushioning, which contributes to the sneaker’s slightly bulky silhouette. Other features include NOCTA’s signature sockliner, which displays NOCTA branding embossed into metallic chrome synthetic leather. The Nike branding details, such as the small Swoosh logos on the side panel and the toe box, are discreet.

Our experts like the University Gold details on the G-Tek rubber outsole. They add splashes of color and break up the white colorway. The Nike Hot Step 2 Drake NOCTA White was released on May 9, 2024, and retailed for $200.

name: Black Toe (2023)
title: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG Black Toe (2023)
description:
The Jordan 1 Retro Low Black Toe, dropped on July 29, 2023, and presents a blend of classic and contemporary, It’s a style that carries the proud legacy of its predecessors.

The upper of the Jordan 1 Retro Low showcases a striking blend of premium black and white leathers, accented by a vibrant red heel counter. Classic elements, such as the iconic Swoosh and the timeless 'Wings' logo, are in black, tying the whole look together. All this sits atop a clean, white midsole, proving that simplicity can still make a statement.

The Jordan 1 Retro Low Black Toe landed on the market on July 29, 2023, at a retail price of $140.

name: Salt
title: adidas Yeezy Desert Boot Salt
description:
The adidas Yeezy Desert Boot Salt, Influenced by military and utility design, was made available as part of Season 7 lineup collection.

This version was made of breathable mesh, suede, and nubuck with a Salt color palette. Its disassembled design lines are reminiscent of the 500 sneakers. Rubber outsoles are .finished in complementary colors. A 3M fluorescent nylon pull tab runs the entire length of the tongue's spine. A thick foam midsole with EVA cushioning and a serrated rubber outsole, both of which take on tonal colors dependent on the upper, complete the overall design.

The adidas Yeezy Desert Boot Salt first debuted on 14 September 2019 and retailed at $200.

name: Halo
title: Nike Kobe 9 Elite Low Protro Halo
description:
The Nike Kobe 9 Elite Low Protro Halo honors the late basketball legend Kobe Bryant with performance-driven features and an angelic, white colorway.

Released on the athlete’s birthday and Mamba Day, the Halo Nike Kobe 9 Elite Low Protro boasts an all-white color scheme that immortalizes Kobe. The Flyknit upper creates a locked-in feel without sacrificing breathability or flexibility, while React Foam provides responsive cushioning in the midsole.  Another performance upgrade is the exterior grip on the rubber outsole, which supports the foot’s natural movements. Like other sneakers decked out in the Halo colorway, splashes of black add contrast on both sides of the extended midsole.

Our experts at StockX like the iridescent detailing on the Swoosh logos. This inclusion brings cohesion to the low-top sneaker and the feeling of being touched by angels. The Nike Kobe 9 Elite Low Protro Halo was originally released on August 23, 2024, and retailed at $240.

name: Bright Red Clear Pink (Women's)
title: adidas Handball Spezial Bright Red Clear Pink (Women's)
description:
The adidas Handball Spezial Bright Red Clear Pink (Women's) is an elegant lifestyle sneaker that takes its inspiration from handball sneakers from the 1970s. This updated shoe specifically sized for women offers classic comfort in an eye-catching colorway.

The Bright Red Clear Pink colorway of the Women's adidas Handball Spezial features an upper primarily of a warm red hue. Red suede serves as the base of the upper as well as the overlays on the toe, eye stays, and heel. Light pink suede is used for the construction of the heel tab and the iconic adidas three stripes along the side panel. The laces are pink and the sock liner is red. Spezial branding with an adidas trefoil adorns the top of the third stripe on the lateral side.

What our shoe experts enjoy most about this sneaker is the intricately patterned sole unit. The gum rubber of the midsole sports embossed triangles and embossed adidas trefoil branding. The gum rubber outsole is grooved with circles for traction. The adidas Handball Spezial Bright Red Clear Pink (Women's) was released on November 17, 2023, for a retail price of $110.

name: Copper Fade
title: adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Copper Fade
description:
The adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Copper Fade is composed of a copper Primeknit upper with a signature translucent TPU lace cage unit. At the base, a black and copper adiPRENE sole provides cushioning and stability.

The adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Copper Fade released in December of 2021 and retailed for $200.

name: Olive (2024)
title: Jordan 9 Retro Olive (2024)
description:
The Jordan 9 Retro Olive (2024) marks the return of a beloved, off-court colorway that has steadily grown in popularity since its debut in 1993. First introduced during Michael Jordan’s first retirement from the NBA, the Jordan 9 captured his global influence with its sleek design, despite Jordan not wearing it on the basketball court. The Olive colorway, featuring a mix of black, true red, and light olive, was an experimental shift from the usual Bulls-inspired colors, and while it initially underperformed, it has since gained a cult following.

This 2024 release aims to stay true to the original design, with premium materials and a shape that captures the sneaker’s iconic status. The black upper is paired with olive overlays, creating a rugged yet stylish look that works both on and off the court. The true red accents on the branding add a pop of color to the otherwise understated palette, making this one of the most anticipated Jordan releases of the year.

Released on November 16, 2024, the Jordan 9 Retro Olive (2024) retailed for $210. With its rich history and bold color scheme, this sneaker is perfect for Jordan fans and sneaker enthusiasts looking to add a timeless piece to their collection.

name: City of Love Burgundy Crush
title: Nike SB Dunk Low City of Love Burgundy Crush
description:
The Nike SB Dunk Low City Of Love Burgundy Crush embodies the depth and richness of Paris's cultural tapestry, presented through a captivating colorway of burgundy crush, dark team red, earth, dark pony, and university red. This sneaker is a tribute to the city’s artistic legacy and the undying romance that Paris is known for, designed for those who draw inspiration from the world around them.

Echoing the hues of Parisian sunsets and the historic bricks that line the Montmartre district, the Burgundy Crush colorway is both a celebration of the city’s natural beauty and its storied past. The sneaker’s luxurious materials and intricate design details, such as the embroidered branding and unique insole, reflect the craftsmanship and creativity synonymous with Paris. It’s a sneaker for those who wear their hearts on their soles, embracing the blend of tradition and contemporary flair that defines Paris.

Introduced on February 9, 2024, for $125, the Nike SB Dunk Low City Of Love Burgundy Crush quickly rose to prominence among those who cherish both the art of skateboarding and the art of living. Its release commemorates the enduring influence of Paris on the creative world, offering a sneaker that captures the essence of the city's elegance, creativity, and love, and inviting wearers to make every day a journey through the City of Love.

name: University Red
title: Nike Kobe 8 Protro University Red
description:
With a bold University Red and white color palette, the Nike Kobe 8 Protro University Red breathes new life into Kobe Bryant’s eight signature basketball shoe with Nike.

Designed for performance on the basketball court, the University Red Nike Kobe 8 Protro boasts a breathable upper made of ultra-lightweight, engineered mesh in University Red. Additional University Red accents can be found on part of the midsole, the laces, the collar, the tongue, and the insole. Pops of crisp white add contrast to the embroidered Swoosh logos, Bryant’s geometric sword logo on the tongue and heel, part of the sole unit, and the athlete’s signature. The white, rubber outsole features a grippy herringbone traction pattern, while the midsole houses responsive React foam.

Our experts at StockX like the generous padding around the collar, which protects the ankle and adds comfort. The Nike Kobe 8 Protro University Red was released on September 6, 2024, and sold for $190.

name: Year of the Dragon (2024)
title: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG Year of the Dragon (2024)
description:
2024 is the Year of the Dragon, and Jordan brand is here to celebrate with the new Jordan 1 Retro Low OG Year of the Dragon (2024). The low-top sneaker features leather accents with a scale-like pattern, and boasts a luxurious grey satin liner. Upon release early in 2024, the sneaker sold out instantly, garnering significant interest on the secondary market as one of the hottest sneakers of the new year.

The Jordan 1 Retro Low OG Year of the Dragon (2024) released on Janaury 24th, 2024, for a retail price of $160.

name: Fear Pack (2023)
title: Jordan 3 Retro Fear Pack (2023)
description:
Dive into the past and embrace the future with the Jordan 3 Retro Fear Pack (2023). A decade after its initial release, this iconic colorway returns, capturing the essence of Jordan's legacy. Crafted from dark grey nubuck with tonal elephant print overlays, the design pays homage to the original while forging its own path. Black suede on the collar and tongue is set off by the embroidered Jumpman logo in Total Orange, a vibrant nod to Jordan's boldness on and off the court.

This sneaker is more than just a throwback—it's a statement. The eyelets echo the striking Total Orange, complemented by a second Jumpman icon on the back heel. The shoe is built for comfort and durability, with an orange-tinged Air-sole unit and a blend of 3 colors on the polyurethane midsole that blend performance with style. It's a perfect match for those who appreciate the history of the game and the evolution of sneaker culture.

The Air Jordan 3 "Fear Pack" is set to release on November 25th, 2023, retailing at $200. Available in full family sizes, this release is a piece of history reborn. Capture the spirit of MJ's own words, "I'm scared of what I won't become", and step into greatness with the Fear Pack.

name: Haven (Translucent Outsole)
title: Nike Book 1 Haven (Translucent Outsole)
description:
Celebrate the bond between man and his best friend with the Nike Book 1 Haven, inspired by Devin Booker's cherished canine companion.
