Decked out in a sleek black and hemp-metallic red bronze colorway, this sneaker is a fitting tribute to Booker's off-court loyalty and on-court prowess. Ideal for thpse who appreciate the fusion of personal storytelling and athletic performance, the Nike Book 1 Haven is a testament to friendship and dedication.

Devin Booker's first pro model sneaker is engineered to excel, incorporating cushioning for explosive play and a stable, supportive fit that reflects his dynamic gameplay. The Haven colorway is not just visually striking; it's built with top-tier sneaker technology, featuring a breathable upper, responsive Cushlon cushioning, a Nike Zoom air bag in the heel and a traction pattern designed for quick cuts and agile moves on the court. These kicks are ready to accompany you on every quest on and off the court.

Released on April 6, 2024, for $140, the Nike Book 1 Haven promises to be a game-changer in both style and function. With its meaningful design and superior tech, it’s poised to become a go-to sneaker for those looking to channel Booker's excellence. Lace up a pair and feel the inspiration behind each stride.

name: Summit White Pure Platinum (Women's)
title: Nike P-6000 Summit White Pure Platinum (Women's)
description:
The Nike P-6000 Summit White Pure Platinum (Women's) is a performance running sneaker, featuring a Summit White base with Pure Platinum, Wolf Gray, and Metallic Summit White details.

This shoe’s technical running silhouette finds inspiration in running sneakers from the 2000s, such as the Pegasus 25. For example, the white upper serves as a background for a collection of overlays that form sporty lines in Pure Platinum and Wolf Gray. Carved-out designs on the midsole mimic these lines and speak to the sneaker’s 2000s roots. While the upper is made of breathable mesh, the overlays come in leather and synthetic leather. The sneaker boasts a soft foam midsole, a supportive insole, and a durable rubber outsole.

Our experts at StockX like the light padding around the tongue and heel that contributes to the sneaker’s Y2K aesthetic. The women’s size Nike P-6000 Summit White Pure Platinum (Women's) was released on December 19th, 2023, and retailed at $120.

name: Mushroom Timberwolf
title: New Balance 9060 Mushroom Timberwolf
description:
The New Balance 9060 Mushroom Timberwolf puts a futuristic spin on classic New Balance designs, including the 99X, the 991, and the 860.

The Mushroom Timberwolf colorway of the New Balance 960 sports an upper of lightweight and breathable white mesh with pig suede overlays in complementary shades of gray, tan, and brown. The classic side panel N logo is constructed from pale embroidered dashed lines that match the cream-colored shoelaces. The heel features a semi-translucent CR device as well as NB branding. The sock liner is cream-colored and the black insole and gray tongue each sport New Balance branding. The outsole is black rubber with a red diamond traction pattern.

What we love most about this sneaker is the high-performance sole unit. The midsole is constructed of ABZORB in an exaggerated wavy pattern with ABZORB SBS in the heel for cushioning and impact absorption. The New Balance 9060 Mushroom Timberwolf was released on September 22, 2023, for a retail price of $150.

name: International Blue
title: Nike Air Foamposite One International Blue
description:
The Nike Air Foamposite One International Blue reapplies the International Blue colorway, also known as Royal, to the Foamposite One.

As one of the most popular colorways in the Foamposite One line, the International Blue colorway features International Blue on the molded polyurethane panels. Giving the International Blue Nike Air Foamposite One sneaker its sleek silhouette, these panels have a wavy design and fit snugly around the foot. Black makes up the other half of the colorway and can be found on the nubuck upper, the lining, the mesh tongue, and the thin laces. Branding details include Penny Hardaway's "1 Cent" logo on the heel and a mini Swoosh near the toebox.

Our experts like the black and International Blue spots on the midfoot’s carbon fiber shank because they pay homage to the OG Foamposite One from 1997. The Nike Air Foamposite One International Blue was released on September 13, 2024, and sold for $240.

name: Sail
title: Jordan 5 Retro SE Sail
description:
The Jordan 5 Retro SE Sail is a special edition of the iconic high-top men’s basketball shoe that comes in a Sail and black colorway.

This version of the Jordan 5 Retro SE is made with premium material, including leather and textile cushioning. The upper of the shoe comes in a Sail beige color, which adorns the base and the overlays. On each side of the shoe under the laces there is a small window showcasing the white mesh cushion. Black detailing adorns the white rubber outsole under the forefoot, and there’s a visible Air unit in the heel. The Jumpman logo appears in black on the heel and on the tongue. The tongue is made of flat canvas for more flexibility of movement.

What we like best about this shoe is the black shark tooth design under the forefoot. This adds a pop of visual appeal to the otherwise simple shoe. The Jordan 5 Retro SE Sail was released on April 13, 2024, for a retail price of $210.

name: Taxi
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Taxi
description:
The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG Yellow Toe brings back the distinct color blocking as well as the sneaker´s high silhouette.

This Retro OG Air Jordan 1 comes in an all leather build that combines a white base with a yellow toe box, and some yellow overlays in the heel and ankle area. A contrasting black appears in the toe and lace area, Swoosh, and Wings logo on the lateral side. A classic AJ1 white midsole and a yellow rubber outsole round off the design.

The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG Yellow Toe was released on the 24th of September 2022, and retailed for $170.

name: White Black
title: Nike Blazer Mid 77 Vintage White Black
description:
The Nike Blazer is a monument in the history of Nike Basketball. The design was first popularized by NBA great George "The Iceman" Gervin in the 1970s and is now a classic lifestyle sneaker.

The Nike Blazer Mid 77 Vintage White Black features a smooth white leather upper with grey suede mudguards and black Swooshes. A white sole and classic Nike branded woven tongue label complete the design.

The Nike Blazer Mid 77 Vintage White Black released in March of 2019 and retailed for $100.

DISCLAIMER: There are two different variations of tongue tags for the Nike Blazer Mid 77 Vintage White Black (BQ6806-100). The standard Bold Nike Spellout logo, as shown, as well as the Nike Heritage Script logo variations are both passable under this product page.

name: Core Black White
title: adidas Campus 00s Core Black White
description:
The adidas Campus 00s Core Black White is an elegant, stealthy lifestyle shoe that originally debuted in the '80s but now rocks a Y2K retro vibe.

The Core Black / Cloud White colorway of the adidas Campus 00s features an upper of black suede with a black suede overlay on the eye stays. The signature adidas three stripes are serrated black matte leather and feature white stitching that stands out. The heel tab is the same matte black leather with singular white stitching. adidas trefoil branding graces both the heel tab and the tongue tag. The lining is a black textile, and the laces and insole are also black. Campus branding appears along the top of the third side panel stripe.

The aspect of this shoe our StockX experts enjoy the most is the unrelieved black of the sole unit. The foam midsole is black with tonal stitching, and it sits on top of a black rubber outsole with a herringbone traction pattern. The adidas Campus 00s Core Black White was released on December 22, 2023, for a retail price of $110.

name: Ultramarine (2024)
title: Nike Air Max 180 Ultramarine (2024)
description:
The Nike Air Max 180 Ultramarine (2024) is a stunning reissue of the classic 1991 design by Tinker Hatfield. This sneaker features a white neoprene upper with suede overlays, highlighted by vibrant ultramarine blue and solar red accents. The signature exposed Air unit adds a futuristic touch, making this sneaker both a fashion statement and a functional piece of footwear. The bold color scheme and high-quality materials ensure that this sneaker stands out in any crowd.

Since its introduction, the Air Max 180 has been celebrated for its revolutionary 180-degree Air unit, providing maximum comfort and cushioning. The Ultramarine colorway, one of the most iconic in the Air Max lineup, is known for its eye-catching design and vibrant colors. The 2024 re-release faithfully replicates the original, offering the same striking visuals and superior comfort.

Priced at $150, the Nike Air Max 180 Ultramarine (2024) was released on May 24, 2024. This sneaker is not just a piece of athletic footwear but a piece of cultural history. The Ultramarine colorway brings a fresh yet nostalgic vibe, making it a must-have for sneaker collectors and fashion enthusiasts alike. Don’t miss your chance to own this timeless classic and experience the perfect blend of style, comfort, and heritage.

name: Pirate Black (2023)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Pirate Black (2023)
description:
Introducing the return of the iconic adidas Yeezy Boost 350 in the Pirate Black colorway. Featuring an all-black primeknit upper, the Pirate Black Yeezy Boost 350 blends high-end streetwear with sleek minimalist design.

The sneakers boast a full-length Boost midsole, providing unparalleled comfort and performance.Black laces, inner lining, and heel tab complete the monochromatic look, capturing the essence of the original release. Whether you're hitting the streets or hitting the gym, the Yeezy Boost 350 Pirate Black is the ultimate pair of sneakers to express your personal style.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Pirate Black made its triumphant return on June 1, 2023, with a retail price of $230.

name: Wolf Grey
title: Nike Kobe 8 Protro Wolf Grey
description:
The Nike Kobe 8 Protro Wolf Grey updates Kobe Bryant’s eighth signature Nike basketball shoe with a sleek white and Wolf Grey color palette.

Celebrating Bryant’s on-court performance legacy, the Wolf Grey Nike Kobe 8 Protro boasts enhancements designed to support agile movements. For instance, the upper is crafted from ultra-lightweight, engineered mesh that provides breathability and doesn’t weigh down the foot. The responsive React midsole cushions against impact, while the thin laces thread through reinforced eyelets for a secure fit. Although the mesh, laces, collar, and part of the midsole come in Wolf Grey, the Swoosh logos, Bryant’s signature, the sheath and sword logos on the heel and tongue, and part of the midsole come in white.

Our experts at StockX like the way the white and Wolf Grey complement each other, creating a timeless, neutral colorway. The Nike Kobe 8 Protro Wolf Grey was released on September 6, 2024, and sold for $190.

name: Birch Peacoat
title: Onitsuka Tiger Mexico 66 Birch Peacoat
description:
The Onitsuka Tiger Mexico 66 Birch Peacoat is a sneaker from the Onitsuka Tiger Mexico 66 series in a "Birch Peacoat" colorway.

This Mexico 66 sneaker features a predominantly birch upper made of leather with suede overlays on the heel and forefoot panel. Peacoat accents on the signature Mexico 66 stripes on the sides and the ‘Tiger’ branded heel tab contrast the upper. Other details include birch laces and ‘Onitsuka Tiger’ branding on the tongue and insoles. Rounding out the design is a thin sole with AMPLIFOAM™ cushioning at the heel and an original outsole compound for extra grip.

What our experts particularly love about this Onitsuka Tiger Mexico 66 sneaker is its iconic design and distinctive colorway. The timeless design and unique color scheme create a classic and versatile look, while the premium construction guarantees comfort and performance. The  Onitsuka Tiger Mexico 66 Birch Peacoat was released on August 1st, 2023, retailing at $130.

name: Linen (2016/2024)
title: Nike Air Force 1 Low Linen (2016/2024)
description:
The Nike Air Force 1 Low Linen is a special edition sneaker that was released exclusively for the Japan market back in 2001 and then re-released in 2016 to celebrate the opening of Kith's Miami store. They were re-released on a wider scale in 2024.

The shoe features a light brown (linen) colorway with atmosphere pink and true white accents. Atmosphere pink is seen on the Swoosh and outsole while true white appears on the laces and midsole. The shoe maintains the Air Force 1 signature design with the stitching around the midsole and placement of panels on the upper and sides.

What we love about the Nike Air Force 1 Low Linen (2016/2024) is the thick sole unit which incorporates Air units to deliver responsive cushioning across the whole underfoot. This helps to improve comfort especially when wearing the shoes for an extended period. The shoes were released for a retail price of $120 on December 1st, 2016. The Nike Air Force 1 Low Linen (2016/2024) was re-released for a retail price of $135 on June 13th, 2024.

name: Beluga Reflective
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Beluga Reflective
description:
One of Yeezy's most celebrated designs received a reflective makeover with the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Beluga Reflective.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Beluga Reflective builds off of the original Beluga colorway by adding reflective qualities and speckled orange accents to its Primeknit upper. Signature details like a Boost sole and orange side stripe complete the design.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Beluga Reflective released in December of 2021 and retailed for $240.

name: Better Scarlet
title: adidas Gazelle Indoor Better Scarlet
description:
The adidas Gazelle Indoor Better Scarlet reimagines the classic Gazelle silhouette with a bold colorway of Better Scarlet with accents in Cloud White that give the sneaker a vintage, varsity athletics look.

The use of suede on the upper provides depth of color and richness to the Better Scarlet, while the white leather 3-Stripes logo and heel tab give the Better Scarlet adidas Gazelle Indoor a timeless feel. The cotton laces, the trefoil on the heel, and the texturized tongue come in Better Scarlet, while the adidas branding on the tongue boasts Cloud White. The semi-transparent gum rubber outsole bears adidas branding beneath the heel and provides traction on a variety of surfaces.

Our experts at StockX like the way this sneaker blends heritage and modern elements to create a retro-inspired shoe with a contemporary twist. The adidas Gazelle Indoor Better Scarlet was released on May 30, 2024, and retailed at $120.

name: Court Purple
title: Nike Kobe 8 Protro Court Purple
description:
Step onto the court with confidence in the Nike Kobe 8 Protro Court Purple, a sneaker that combines elegance with performance. Inspired by Kobe Bryant's unparalleled legacy, this model features a White/Court Purple/White colorway that exudes sophistication. Paying homage to the basketball giant and his daughter, the numbers 8, 24, and 2 are thoughtfully incorporated throughout the upper, making each pair a symbol of excellence and remembrance.

The Nike Kobe 8 Protro Court Purple is designed for those who demand the best in both function and fashion. Its advanced technology ensures peak performance during play, while the striking Court Purple highlights showcase a sense of style that is both bold and refined. This sneaker reflects the spirit of innovation and dedication that Kobe brought to every game, tailored for a generation that values legacy and looks.

Released on February 8, 2024, and priced at $190, the Nike Kobe 8 Protro Court Purple presents a new colorway that captures the heart of sneaker fans and basketball players alike. It's not just a shoe; it's a tribute to a legend and his impact on the game, making it an essential piece for those who celebrate greatness on and off the court.

name: Fear (2024) (GS)
title: Jordan 4 Retro Fear (2024) (GS)
description:
The Jordan 4 Retro Fear (2024) (GS) relaunches the recognizable silhouette from 2013, this time in a grade school size. It boasts a grayscale colorway with white, black, Anthracite, and Pure Platinum hues.

The sneaker is part of Jordan Brand’s Fear Pack, which promotes fearlessness and overcoming obstacles. The upper is crafted from open-weave mesh in black with layered nubuck overlays in Anthracite and light gray. Signature Air Jordan 4 elements include the nubuck lace cage, TPU eyelets, and visible Air-Sole units in the heel. The 2024 grade-school Jordan 4 Retro Fear showcases a speckled pattern across the midsole that complements the gray tones. The branding details are oversized, including a white Jumpman logo on the heel and a premium tongue tag with Michael Jordan’s signature.

Our experts at StockX like the subtle pop of color provided by the red hue on the Air-Sole units. The grade school-sized Jordan 4 Retro Fear (2024) (GS) was released on November 16, 2024, and sold for $160.

name: X-Ray (GS)
title: Nike Kobe 5 X-Ray (GS)
description:
In grade school sizes, the Nike Kobe 5 X-Ray (GS) is a sneaker featuring a Deep Royal Blue, Baltic Blue, and Glacier Blue upper. The upper displays printed artwork of foot bones, in the style of an X-ray image, across the quarter, accented by the Swoosh. Kobe branding appears on the tongue and heel, and the Deep Royal Blue midsole and Glacier Blue outsole finish the look.

American athletic brand Nike is known for outfitting the top NBA players with signature shoes, and they worked with Kobe Bryant from the early 2000s. The Nike Kobe series is known for its bold and forward-leaning aesthetic, with the occasional out-there design, such as the 5 X-Ray, which surely stands alone.

Our experts feel that the 5 X-Ray's best feature is its edgy and unique imagery. Cross laces help little ones put them on. The Nike Kobe 5 X-Ray (GS) was released on October 17, 2024, and retailed for $120.

name: Championship Court Purple
title: Nike Dunk Low Championship Court Purple
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Championship Purple features a white leather upper with Championship Purple overlays and Swooshes. Nike embroidery at the heel pays tribute to the original 1985 design. At the base, a white and purple sole adds the finishing touch.

The Nike Dunk Low Championship Purple releases in May of 2022 and retails for $100.

name: Year of the Mamba Eggplant
title: Nike Kobe 5 Protro Year of the Mamba Eggplant
description:
The Nike Kobe 5 Protro Year of the Mamba Eggplant celebrates Kobe Bryant's legacy with a design inspired by the elegance and wisdom of the snake in Chinese culture. Wrapped in a stunning metallic purple upper, the sneaker exudes power and poise, while black accents and a translucent outsole add layers of depth to its aesthetic. The iconic swoosh is accented by a golden snake that appears on the side of the upper, paying homage to Bryant's Mamba mentality both on and off the court.

Engineered for performance, the Kobe 5 Protro combines cutting-edge cushioning with a supportive fit. The addition of snakeskin details along the heel and upper adds texture and character to the design, while its streamlined silhouette ensures agility and speed. Perfectly balancing style and functionality, this pair is a tribute to Bryant’s enduring influence in sports and culture.

Set to release on January 9, 2025, the Nike Kobe 5 Protro Year of the Mamba Eggplant will retail for $190. Whether you’re on the court or collecting for nostalgia, this sneaker is a celebration of Kobe's legacy and his transformative spirit.

name: Vast Grey
title: Nike Zoom Vomero 5 SP Vast Grey
description:
The Nike Zoom Vomero 5 SP Vast Grey is a limited-edition release that is part of the Nike Zoom Vomero 5 series.​
​​
​The Vast Grey Nike Zoom Vomero 5 SP features an upper that is made of breathable mesh with durable TecTuff overlays and reflective 3M detailing and has a midsole that is equipped with a combination of Zoom Air technology and Cushlon foam cushioning to provide support and protection for the foot. The shoe has a Vast Grey colorway with hits of black and white.
​
​The Nike Zoom Vomero 5 SP Vast Grey was released on February 1, 2019 and again on February 22, 2023, at a retail price of $160.

name: Bred Velvet (Women's)
title: Jordan 11 Retro Bred Velvet (Women's)
description:
The Jordan 11 Retro Bred Velvet (Women's) is an iteration of the classic "Bred" colorway on the iconic Jordan 11, this time with a velvet upper and in a women's exclusive size run.

Last released in 2019, the Bred 11s are one of the most sought after retros, as they represent Michael Jordan's comeback to win his fourth NBA championship in 1996. This velvet version provides a lux alternative to the standard leather option that the 2019 version has. This sneaker has an all-black upper, white mid-sole, and red sole along with a red Jumpman logo on the outer heel.

The Jordan 11 Retro Bred Velvet (Women's) released on November 11th, 2024, for a retail price of $230. We love this sneaker due to its luxury take on a classic sneaker, making it something you truly cannot go wrong with.

name: Black (Women's)
title: UGG Lowmel Black (Women's)
description:
Crafted using recycled materials, the UGG Lowmel Black (Women's) is a comfortable sneaker designed to feel good, body and sole. This shoe is specifically designed for women.

The upper of the Black (Women's) UGG Lowmel, built for comfort, is fashioned from black suede with recycled ballistic canvas mesh at the toe box and padded collar. A padded, oversized tongue and a black webbing pull tab at the heel to ease on/off are also black. Thick plaid laces made from recycled polyester fibers are meant to be worn loose and open. Tonal UGG branding is embossed on the tongue and lateral heel. The molded EVA footbed is supported under foot by a sugarcane EVA outsole with a starburst pattern for absorbing impact and providing grip.

Our favorite aspect of this women’s sneaker is the UGG plush upcycled wool sock liner and the Lyocell insole that envelope your foot in yet another layer of comfort. The UGG Lowmel Black (Women's) was released on August 1, 2023, for $150 retail.

name: Electric Pack Olympic Safari
title: Nike SB Dunk Low Electric Pack Olympic Safari
description:
The Nike SB Dunk Low Electric Pack Olympic Safari is a commemorative sneaker that honors skateboarding at the 2024 Paris Olympics. It features Nike’s signature "Safari" print and splashes of Monarch and Chlorine Blue.

At the Electric Pack Olympic Safari Nike SB Dunk Low, The suede upper in Phantom serves as a low-key background for the tonal heel and forefoot overlays covered in Safari print’s iconic black speckles. The rubber cupsole, Swoosh logo, tongue, back tab, and collar come in black, while Monarch orange decorates the collar lining and appears on the heel tab’s ‘NIKE’ embroidery. Zoom Air cushioning in the insoles and padding around the tongue and collar further elevates this eye-catching sneaker.

Our experts at StockX like the inclusion of Chlorine Blue laces. They add a pop of color that makes this low-top sneaker live up to its "Electric" name. The Nike SB Dunk Low Electric Pack Olympic Safari was released on August 9, 2024, and sold for $125.

name: Triple White
title: New Balance 9060 Triple White
description:
The New Balance 9060 Triple White takes the classic 9060 silhouette and adds an all-white colorway. Including white on the upper, outsole, midsole, and lining allows the sneaker’s design elements to stand out.

This version of the 9060 finds inspiration in the 990 and the 860, giving the lifestyle shoe an early 2000s aesthetic. It features wavy leather overlays on the upper that complement the wavy pattern on the thick midsole. The upper is made of breathable mesh, while the heel displays a transparent CR device. This feature can be found on other 9060 models and supports heel stability. Although the curving logo on the tongue resembles the lace jewel on the 991, the diamond-like pattern of the outsole finds inspiration in the 860.

Our StockX experts like how ABZORB cushioning and pods in the midsole contribute to the sneaker’s chunky appearance. The New Balance 9060 Triple White was released on January 12th, 2024, and retailed at $150.

name: Lucky Green
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Lucky Green
description:
Jordan Brand continued its pattern of Lucky Green colorways in early 2023, with the release of the Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG Lucky Green. The Air Jordan 1 is the third model to receive the Lucky Green treatment following the Jordan 2 and Jordan 3.

The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG is constructed using a leather upper, brought to life with shades of white, black and Lucky Green throughout. Lucky Green Nike branding sits on top of the black tongue and insoles of the sneaker. The sneakers are tied together with Lucky Green laces.

The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG Lucky Green released April 15, 2023, with a retail price of $180.

name: Verdy Visty
title: Nike SB Dunk Low Verdy Visty
description:
The Nike SB Dunk Low Verdy Visty is a fresh and playful take on the iconic SB Dunk model, brought to life through a collaboration with Japanese artist Verdy. This eye-catching sneaker takes inspiration from Verdy’s character, "VISTY," blending creativity and street style in a standout design. The color palette is a pastel dream, with blue gaze, light arctic pink, and bicycle yellow tones adding a whimsical touch to the classic silhouette.

One of the most unique aspects of the Verdy Visty Dunk is its mix of materials. The fuzzy, hairy texture on the toe box, mid panel, tongue, and heel collar adds dimension and personality to the sneaker, while the pink leather Nike swoosh adds a smooth contrast. The pastel blue corduroy upper rounds out the design, giving the shoe a vintage, yet modern aesthetic. The yellow midsole and matching laces bring an extra pop of color, making this Dunk an instant standout whether you're skating or styling.

Released on September 19, 2024, the Nike SB Dunk Low Verdy Visty retailed at $135. The VISTY character makes a fun appearance on the inside tag and even comes with a special keychain, adding a personal touch to each pair. For those looking to combine fashion, art, and skate culture, this sneaker is the perfect way to express your individuality.

name: Utility Black
title: adidas Yeezy 450 Utility Black
description:
The adidas Yeezy 450 Utility Black is made of synthetic fibers, a product of a combination of petroleum-based ethylene-vinyl acetate and foam from algae.

The design of adidas Yeez 450 Utility Black is renowned for its comfortable, tight, sock-like fit as well as its fashionable mesh style. The shoe has a semitranslucent rubber outsole and thermoplastic polyurethane (TPU) for performance and flexibility. The design of adidas Yeezy 450 comes in Utility Black.

adidas Yeezy 450 Utility Black was released on February 8, 2022 at a retail price of $200.

name: Red Cement (GS)
title: Jordan 4 Retro Red Cement (GS)
description:
The Jordan 4 Retro Red Cement (GS) presents a fusion of colors, textures, shapes, and materials that will make any grade school kid wearing this sneaker the talk of the playground.

The Grade School version of the Jordan 4 Retro Red Cement sports a white mesh upper overlaid with tumbled white leather along with hits of red synthetic with black speckles along the mud guard, eye stays, and heel tab. Black synthetic hits appear as the waffle eye stays and the toe cap, matching the black sock liner and insole. The Jumpman logo appears in red on the tongue and insole and black on the heel as a raised rubber decal. The white foam midsole encapsulates visible Air for ultimate cushioning.

What are sneaker experts enjoy most about this shoe is the rubber outsole with herringbone traction in pods of black, white, and red, accented with a red Jumpman, thus providing traction and echoing the tri-color look of the upper. The Jordan 4 Retro Red Cement (GS) was released on September 9, 2023 for retail price of $150.

name: Triple Black
title: Nike Air Max 95 Essential Triple Black
description:
The Nike Air Max 95 Essential Triple Black 2020/2023 was originally unveiled as one of Nike’s Nike Air Max 95 model sneakers in January 2020.

The Nike Air Max 95 Essential Triple Black 2020/2023 is dressed in a black-on-black colorway. The sneaker features a black mesh-constructed upper on top of a black leather base. The black tongue’s top features an "air max" labeling detail. Completing the design is the black rubber sole with Air Max units fitted within the heel and forefoot for extra comfort. The black rubber outsole is patterned for maximum traction.

During its initial unveiling in January 2020, Nike Air Max 95 Triple Black 2020 retailed at $170.

name: Cream Sweet Pink
title: ASICS GEL-Kayano 14 Cream Sweet Pink
description:
The ASICS GEL-Kayano 14 Cream Sweet Pink is a technical running sneaker boasting metallic silver and Sweet Pink accents.

While the Cream Sweet Pink ASICS GEL-Kayano 14’s mesh construction, including the web of faux-leather overlays and mesh underlays, pays homage to GEL-Kayano models from the early 2000s, the use of shiny metallic silver gives the sneaker a futuristic upgrade. In addition, Sweet Pink accents add pops of color on the midsole pods, the ASICS branding, and the rubber outsole. Toshikazu Kayano didn’t design this version of the GEL-Kayano; however, the shoe still maintains its iconic layered construction and GEL technology underfoot. This cushioning system provides advanced shock absorption without weighing down the foot.

Our experts at StockX appreciate the sneaker’s sustainable features, including the sockliner, which is crafted using a dyeing process that reduces water consumption by 33 percent and carbon emissions by 45 percent. The ASICS GEL-Kayano 14 Cream Sweet Pink was released on May 1, 2024, and retailed at $150.

name: Collegiate Green Semi Green Spark (Women's)
title: adidas Handball Spezial Collegiate Green Semi Green Spark (Women's)
description:
The adidas Handball Spezial Collegiate Green Semi Green Spark (Women's) is a retro sneaker that finds inspiration in the original sneaker from the 1970s.

Although the original shoe was designed for playing handball on indoor courts, this version does not have a specific sports designation. However, the rubber outsole provides traction on a variety of surfaces and the front lacing system ensures a secure fit. The upper is made from soft suede in Collegiate Green with tonal overlays crafted from the same material. The serrated 3-Stripes on the side panel, the retro-inspired tongue logo tag, the collar, and the laces all come in Semi-Green.

A feature our StockX experts like is the branding details. Although you cannot find adidas branding on the heel counter, ‘SPEZIAL’ and a small trefoil are printed along the serrated 3-Stripes logo in metallic gold. The women’s size adidas Handball Spezial Collegiate Green Semi Green Spark (Women's) was released on November 27th, 2023, and retailed at $110.

name: Conductor (Women's)
title: Nike Sabrina 2 Conductor (Women's)
description:
The Nike Sabrina 2 Conductor (Women's) is part of Sabrina Ionescu’s second performance basketball shoe collaboration with Nike.

Like other sneakers in the collection, the Conductor (Women's) Nike Sabrina 2 includes Cushlon 3.0 foam in the midsole, a firmer Cushlon foam wrapping around the midsole, and a responsive Nike Zoom Air in the forefoot that propels you forward. Other technical features include the "S"-inspired herringbone traction pattern on the rubber outsole, which supports quick directional changes. The mesh upper features an internal containment system with stitched cables that provide a locked-in feel supported by the lace closure system.

Our experts like the zigzag patterns around the heel that represent shards of glass and symbolize Sabrina Ionescu breaking the glass ceiling. Other symbolic elements include the ‘i’ on the heel, which represents the first letter of the WNBA player’s last name. The Nike Sabrina 2 Conductor (Women's) was released on July 12, 2024, and sold for $130.

name: Metallic Blue
title: Jordan 1 Retro Low '85 Metallic Blue
description:
The Jordan 1 Retro Low 85 Metallic Blue finds inspiration in the "Metallic Blue" colorway, which was launched in 1985 as part of Jordan’s High Metallic Series.

This reimagined sneaker takes the Air Jordan 1 Retro Low silhouette and applies Metallic Blue accents to the sneaker's clean Summit White base. The upper is made of leather with tonal overlays and bright white laces winding through eyelets in the lace cage. The Swooshes and the heel tab both come in Metallic Blue, while the collar lining and the rubber outsole boast a similar blue without the metallic glisten. In terms of branding, the Air Jordan wings logo is printed across the heel tab and ‘NIKE AIR’ can be found on the tongue’s woven logo tag.

Something our StockX experts like is the sneaker’s simple design, which allows the metallic elements to shine without overwhelming the shoe. The Jordan 1 Retro Low 85 Metallic Blue was released on March 17th, 2024, and retailed at $160.

name: Patent Black White Gold
title: Jordan 1 Mid Patent Black White Gold
description: Jordan Brand is releasing a true piece of treasure, so cop the Jordan 1 Mid Patent Black White Gold. This AJ1 Mid comes with a white upper with black and gold accents, gold Nike "Swoosh", white midsole, and a black sole. These sneakers released in December 2018 and retailed for $110. Pirates would break their necks for these, so place a Bid now on StockX.

name: Hot Lava (2024)
title: Nike Air Tech Challenge II Hot Lava (2024)
description:
The Nike Air Tech Challenge II Hot Lava (2024) is a re-release of one of the most iconic tennis shoes ever made. Originally debuting in the late 1980s, the Air Tech Challenge II took the courts by storm with its bold design and revolutionary features. Worn by tennis legend Andre Agassi, this sneaker broke barriers in both performance and style, influencing not just the tennis world but also pop culture. The hot lava colorway, with its fiery accents, became an instant classic and remains relevant today as a bold statement piece.

Featuring a mix of phantom, hot lava, black, silver, and pale ivory, this re-release stays true to the original design while offering slight updates for modern comfort. The vibrant hot lava detailing is the shoe’s standout feature, while the durable leather construction and Air cushioning ensure lasting support on and off the court. Whether you're hitting tennis balls or making a statement on the street, the Nike Air Tech Challenge II Hot Lava continues to turn heads with its timeless appeal.

Released on August 30, 2024, the Nike Air Tech Challenge II Hot Lava (2024) retailed for $150. This iconic sneaker remains a must-have for fans of retro tennis style and those who appreciate its cultural influence and bold design.

name: Triple Black
title: Nike SB Dunk Low Pro Triple Black
description:
Released ahead of Halloween, the Nike SB Dunk Low Pro Triple Black paints the familiar silhouette in a spooky monochromatic colorway.

Although the Halloween accents are subtle, they make the triple black version of the SB Dunk Low stand out from other models. For example, Nike’s signature orange label, part of the insole, and the care instructions are the only colorful accents on the shoe. They pop against the all-black nubuck on the Swoosh, forefoot, and heel overlays, vamp, eyelets, and heel tab. Completing the dark aesthetic, the laces and rubber outsole also come in black. Perforations across the vamp allow the foot to breathe, while padding in the tongue and collar protects the ankle.

Our experts like that this sneaker was released only in skate shops, giving the sneaker an exclusive feel. The Nike SB Dunk Low Pro Triple Black was released on October 1, 2024, and sold for $115.

name: DMP Gratitude (2023) (GS)
title: Jordan 11 Retro DMP Gratitude (2023) (GS)
description:
Unleash the legend on the schoolyard with the Jordan 11 Retro DMP Defining Moments / Gratitude (GS). This Grade School iteration brings a slice of hoops history to the forefront, featuring the iconic Black/White/Metallic gold colorway that's been reimagined for the cool kids on the block. The patent leather shines bright, setting off the gold accents that are as much about winning as they are about style.

The GS version isn't just a smaller size; it's a big statement. With the same meticulous design as the adult model, the GOLD Jumpman emblem and the heritage-rich '23' grace the heel, capturing the glory of the court. The GS model ensures the next generation can walk, run, and play in a sneaker that's built for champions.

Drop the mundane and step into the extraordinary on December 9, 2023. Priced at $185, the Jordan 11 Retro DMP Defining Moments (GS) isn't just a sneaker—it's a trophy for the feet, a celebration of Jordan's legacy.

name: Slate
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Slate
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Slate Core Black Slate takes on a sock like design that is complemented with a neutral two-tone color scheme.

The Yeezy Boost 350 by adidas in black upper utilizes tan Primeknit construction, highlighted by distinctive center stitching down the vamp. A contrasting black streak adorns the lateral side with signature ‘SPLY-350’ branding. The shoe sits atop a Boost midsole, confined in a semi-translucent TPU cage for durability and support.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Slate Core Black Slate was originally released on the 3rd of September 2022, and initially retailed at $230.

name: Travis Scott Light Chocolate
title: Nike Zoom Field Jaxx Travis Scott Light Chocolate
description:
The Nike Zoom Field Jaxx Travis Scott Light Chocolate is a performance shoe designed in collaboration with American rapper Travis Scott.

The Travis Scott Light Chocolate Nike Zoom Field Jaxx features an off-white mesh base thickly woven for extra visual texture. This mesh makes up the toe box and sides. White leather overlays form the toe cap, mudguard, eyestays, ankle strap, and heel area, while the mudguard is separated from the rest by a thin cream strip. A forefoot strap also appears over the laces in white leather, while Shark branding is seen underneath it on the inner side. The Nike swoosh crosses the sides in a Light Chocolate brown color, while the tongue also bears Cactus Jack branding in Light Chocolate. The Nike swoosh appears as the mouth inside a drawn face on the heel, and the shoe sits on a branded brown midsole complete with Air technology.

What we like best about this sneaker is the unique branding, including the face on the heel. The Nike Zoom Field Jaxx Travis Scott Light Chocolate will be released in January 2025 for $170.

name: UNC (Women's)
title: Jordan 1 Low UNC (Women's)
description:
The women's Jordan 1 Low UNC (W) features a white and blue leather upper with standard white acting as the base of the silhouette and wrapped up in the pale tones of the University Blue overlays. From there, blue on the "Jumpman" logo tongue, laces, and Nike "Swoosh" and a University Blue outsole complete the design.

The women's Jordan 1 Low UNC (W) released in February of 2020 and retailed for $90.

name: Yellow Ochre
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Yellow Ochre
description:
The Jordan 1 Retro High OG in Yellow Ochre/Black/Sail is a vibrant celebration of the Air Jordan legacy. This edition's Yellow Ochre colorway brings an electrifying twist to the classic silhouette, making it a standout piece in any sneaker collection.

Accented with Black and Sail, the sneaker's bold Yellow Ochre hue ensures that it's not just another pair of Jordans; it's a fashion statement. Crafted with excellence, this sneaker combines high-quality materials and comfort, embodying the spirit of Michael Jordan's legendary performance.

Released on January 13, 2024, with a retail tag of $180, the Jordan 1 Retro High OG Yellow Ochre is a piece of sneaker history, a canvas of artistry, and a symbol of enduring style. It's a must-have for those who value both legacy and contemporary fashion.

name: Wales Bonner Wonder Clay Royal
title: adidas Samba Nylon Wales Bonner Wonder Clay Royal
description:
The adidas Samba Nylon Wales Bonner Wonder Clay Royal updates the Samba with Wales Bonner’s signature bespoke house codes. This collaboration creates a sneaker with retro inspirations and premium materials.

The upper is crafted from smooth leather in Wonder Clay, while the T-shaped overlay across the toe and the panels around the laces are on tonal shaggy suede. The textural contrast between these materials mirrors details found in other Wales Bonner products. Splashes of Team Royal Blue grace the 3-Stripes logo, the multicolor laces, and the dual branding on the tongue’s logo tag. Although the collar is lined with smooth blue leather, it comes in a slightly lighter shade. Finishing the vintage look, a gum rubber outsole wraps around the base of the sneaker.

Our experts at StockX like the exaggerated stitching on the heel and tongue. The adidas Samba Nylon Wales Bonner Wonder Clay Royal was released on May 21, 2024, and retailed at $160.

name: Drake NOCTA Black
title: Nike Hot Step 2 Drake NOCTA Black
description:
The Nike Hot Step 2 Drake NOCTA Black is an athletic shoe with a synthetic leather upper in black. The upper features a curved linear aesthetic, with black and white checkered mudguard windows accented by the Nike Swoosh. NOCTA branding appears on the tongue, while a black midsole with a visible Air unit and University Gold traction pads define the black outsole.

NOCTA is chart-topping Canadian hip-hop artist Drake’s clothing brand, which has teamed up with American athletic wear powerhouse Nike. The name is derived from Drake’s nocturnal creative process, and the collection is identified by its fashion-forward, minimal aesthetic, a direction that the brand applies to clothing, footwear, and accessories.

In our opinion, the Hot Step 2's best feature is its Black color palette, which is emphasized by the hidden pop of color on the sole. The Nike Hot Step 2 Drake NOCTA Black was released on September 28, 2024, and retailed for $200.

name: Inter Miami CF Messi Pink
title: adidas Samba Inter Miami CF Messi Pink
description:
The adidas Samba Inter Miami CF Messi Pink is part of a collaboration between adidas Samba and the internationally renowned soccer player Lionel Messi. This sneaker pays homage to Messi’s time with Inter Miami CF through a colorway that represents the team’s colors.

The upper is crafted from pink leather with black accents on the 3-Stripes logo, the heel tab, and the branding on the sockliner. The sneaker’s signature T-shaped toecap comes in pink suede, while the cotton laces are also pink. Branding details include "SAMBA" printed along the 3-Stripes logo in metallic gold ink and the Inter Miami CF "M" found on the tongue in shiny black lettering.

Our experts at StockX like the inclusion of a neutral-tone gum outsole, which reminds the wearer of the sneaker’s Samba heritage. The adidas Samba Inter Miami CF Messi Pink was released on April 1, 2024, and retailed for $120.

name: University Blue
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG University Blue
description:
Jordan Brand paid homage to MJ’s alma mater with the Air Jordan 1 High University Blue. The University Blue colorway is prominent in the Jordan 1’s history. The first UNC-inspired Jordan 1 dates back to 1985 when the Jordan 1 debuted. Since then, there have been numerous iterations of the UNC 1, most recently the Jordan 1 Retro High Fearless UNC To Chicago. Jumpman is building off of its past and switching it up this week with a new iteration.

The upper of the Air Jordan 1 High University Blue is composed of a white and black tumbled leather upper with University Blue Durabuck overlays. Following traditional Jordan 1 detailing, a Nike Air woven label is located on the tongue and an Air Jordan Wings Logo is printed on the ankle. A white midsole and University Blue outsole complete rejuvenated classic.

The Air Jordan 1 High University Blue released in March of 2021 and retailed for $170.

name: Off-White Varsity Maize
title: Nike Air Force 1 Mid SP Off-White Varsity Maize
description:
The Nike Air Force 1 Mid SP Off White Varsity Maize represents a collaboration between Nike and Virgil Abloh’s fashion house Off-White. This sneaker takes an iconic silhouette and a retro colorway and infuses it with hallmark Off-White creativity.​
​​
​The Off White X Nike Air Force 1 Mid-Top Varsity Maize SP sports an upper with a base of tumbled white leather and perforations in the toe box. The overlays and ankle strap are maize-colored tumbled leather, while the side-panel Nike swoosh is white tumbled leather. The laces are maize and an extra pair of white laces threads through fly cables on the upper. The white foam midsole houses visible Air and sits atop a maize rubber outsole where the classic AF1 traction pattern has been enhanced with track spikes.​
​​
​What we love most about this creative shoe is the Off-White branding. Characteristic Off-White text appears on the medial upper while a white grim reaper graphic is embroidered on the lateral heel. The Nike Air Force 1 Mid SP Off White Varsity Maze was released on November 9, 2023, for a retail price of $205.

name: Trophy Room Rookie Card Away
title: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG Trophy Room Rookie Card Away
description:
The Air Jordan 1 Retro Low OG Trophy Room Away elegantly bridges the gap between sports heritage and contemporary sneaker culture. Set in a classic palette of sail, black, varsity red, and muslin, this sneaker pays homage to the legendary lineage of Air Jordan 1s while infusing it with the exclusive allure of Trophy Room, the renowned sneaker store founded by Michael Jordan's son. Designed for those who value both the history and the exclusivity of their footwear, this edition is a testament to the enduring legacy of the Jordan brand and the unique vision of Trophy Room.

This sneaker distinguishes itself with meticulous design details, including an embroidered Nike Swoosh, luxurious red satin accents throughout, and exquisite gold wings logo on the heel. These elements not only highlight the craftsmanship involved but also elevate the sneaker to a piece of collectible art, resonating with the tastes of sneakerheads and Jordan enthusiasts alike. The collaboration represents a seamless blend of Michael Jordan's storied career and his son's contemporary influence on the sneaker world.

Released on March 21, 2024, for $140, the Air Jordan 1 Retro Low OG Trophy Room Away quickly captivated the hearts of collectors and fans, becoming a coveted piece in many collections. Its launch is celebrated as a moment that offered sneaker aficionados a unique piece that's steeped in basketball lore and exclusivity.

name: Moonrock Linen
title: New Balance 9060 Moonrock Linen
description:
The New Balance 9060 Moonrock Linen takes elements from the 990 and updates this retro silhouette with futuristic design details.

Taking cues from heritage performance running sneakers, the 9060 Moonrock Linen boasts a bulky midsole and a rubber outsole with enhanced traction. The chunky midsole houses New Balance’s signature ABZORB technology and SBS cushioning, both of which provide responsive cushioning without weighing the foot down. In terms of branding, the New Balance ‘N’ can be found on the lateral side panel and the tongue houses an embedded triangular tag that reads ‘9060.’ Like other 9060 models, this version has a transparent CR device, which wraps around the heel.

Our StockX experts like the Dark Arctic accents on the heel and around the quarter panel because they contrast the sneaker’s light upper. The New Balance 9060 Moonrock Linen was released on November 30th, 2023, and retailed at $150.

name: Black White Gum (Kids)
title: adidas Campus 00s Black White Gum (Kids)
description:
The adidas Campus 00s Black White Gum (GS) low-top lifestyle shoe embraces a minimalist design aesthetic, featuring suede uppers adorned with the iconic three-stripes and Trefoil logo.

The Black White Gum adidas Campus 00s for grade schoolers boasts an entirely suede upper in Core Black, with striking Cloud White smooth leather 3-Stripes featuring distinctive sawtooth edges on both the medial and lateral mid-panels. Cloud White Trefoil logos adorn the Core Black suede heel tabs and tongues, free from any textual branding. Meanwhile, adidas text branding can be spotted on the Core Black insoles. Staying true to the OG Campus, the shoe is finished with a white midsole and a caramel-colored gum outsole, completing its overall design.

What our experts love about the adidas Campus 00s Black White Gum (GS) is its throwback design. This sneaker captures the essence of a bygone era with its classic suede upper, Cloud White Three Stripes, and sawtooth-edged detailing. It pays homage to the timeless style of the OG Campus silhouette, making it a nostalgic and fashionable choice for those who appreciate vintage-inspired footwear. The shoe debuted for $70 on February 17th, 2023.

name: College Navy
title: Nike Kobe 8 Protro College Navy
description:
Paying tribute to Kobe Bryant’s legacy, the Nike Kobe 8 Protro College Navy was released alongside the "Wolf Grey" and "University Red" editions as part of Nike’s Fall 2024 collection.

The College Navy Nike Kobe 8 Protro basketball shoe boasts a slim design and a collegiate color palette of College Navy and white. Designed to improve a player's on-court performance, the sneaker features several enhancements, including a responsive React foam midsole and a grippy herringbone traction pattern on the outsole. However, the standout feature is the lightweight engineered mesh on the upper. It comes in College Navy and allows the foot to breathe without sacrificing durability. Contrasting the dark College Navy base, white can be found on Bryant’s sword in a sheath logo on the tongue and heel, the rubber outsole, the embroidered Swoosh logos, and the athlete’s signature.

Our experts like the reinforced eyelets because they provide a secure fit. The Nike Kobe 8 Protro College Navy was released on September 6, 2024, and sold for $190.

name: White Black Gum (Women's)
title: adidas Sambae White Black Gum (Women's)
description:
The adidas Sambae White Black Gum (Women's) takes an iconic silhouette and adds details to make it freshly unique. Originally designed for the indoor soccer court, these shoes specifically sized for women can now be worn for a variety of indoor sports and training or to complete any outfit.

The White Black Gum colorway of the Women's adidas Sambae features an upper with a base of smooth white nubuck leather with a stitch-and-turn off-white suede T-toe overlay on the forefoot. The signature adidas three stripes on the side panel are composed of textured black embroidery, as is the heel. The adidas trefoil adorns the white leather tongue and the white textile insole. Samba branding in gold script rests just above the third side panel stripe.

The aspect of this sneaker that our StockX experts enjoy the most is a slightly raised gum rubber platform sole. Translucent gum rubber sneaks up onto the upper, while the outsole is grooved with circles and trefoil lugs for multi-directional traction. The adidas Sambae White Black Gum (Women's) was released on December 1, 2023, for $110 retail.

name: Drake White Chrome
title: Nike NOCTA Glide Drake White Chrome
description:
The Nike NOCTA Glide Drake White Chrome is an all-white version of the Nike NOCTA Glide, a collaboration between Nike and Canadian rapper Drake. The sneaker finds inspiration in the Nike Zoom Flight 95 but incorporates mesh instead of premium leather on the upper.

Like other iterations of the NOCTA Glide, the "White Chrome" model comes with bubble-like chrome detailing on the bulky, foam midsole and 3M reflective piping. A Zoom Air unit in the forefoot complements the Phylon midsole and adds extra cushioning. The midfoot overlay is made of a breathable woven textile and features a small Swoosh. In addition, NOCTA branding can be found on the padded tongue and debossed on the chrome details on the heel.

Something our experts love is the triple-branded insole, which features logos from Nike, NOCTA, and G-Tek. The Nike NOCTA Glide Drake White Chrome was released on October 27, 2023, and retailed at $160.

name: Barons
title: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG Barons
description:
The Jordan 1 Retro Low OG Barons is a commemorative sneaker that celebrates the 30th anniversary of Michael Jordan’s time with the Birmingham Barons, a Double-A affiliate team of the Chicago White Sox.

The low-top Barons Jordan 1 Retro Low OG boasts a leather upper in white, black, and Wolf Gray, a colorway that pays tribute to the baseball team’s colors. While the base comes in white, Wolf Gray overlays provide subtle color blocking. Small perforations on the vamp and the mesh material of the tongue allow the foot to breathe, even though the upper is constructed entirely from smooth leather. The flat tongue displays a woven tag with ‘NIKE AIR’ lettering in Wolf Gray, while the Air Jordan Wings can be found on the heel tab.

Our experts at StockX like the way the black accents on the laces, the Swoosh logos, and the leather heel tab contrast the Wolf Gray and white across the upper. The Jordan 1 Retro Low OG Barons was released on July 20, 2024, and sold for $140.

name: White (Travis Scott Cactus Jack Utopia Edition)
title: Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 White (Travis Scott Cactus Jack Utopia Edition)
description:
Unveiled on July 28, 2023, the Nike Air Force 1 Low Travis Scott Cactus Jack Utopia Edition is more than just a sneaker; it's the embodiment of Travis’ creative genius, this shoe echoes with the sounds and themes of his groundbreaking album, 'Utopia’.

Radiating in a dominant all-white shade, this iconic silhouette carries the legacy of the Air Force 1 with a touch of Travis Scott's unique artistry. Crafted with precision, the sneaker showcases the word 'Utopia' imprinted on its heel - a direct nod to Scott's most recent album.

But there's more. The Utopia graphic doesn't just serve aesthetic vibes; it’s a celebration of music and streetwear colliding. The fusion of leather and subtle design details crafts an aesthetic that's both sleek and statement-making. Dive into the Utopia with this pair of sneakers that retailed at $150.

Please note: by listing this item for sale, you agree to ship within the normal shipping window. Shipping deadlines will not be extended to accommodate shipping delays from the retailer.

name: Medium Olive (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Medium Olive (Women's)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Medium Olive W dresses the archival hoops shoe in traditional two-tone color blocking.
​
​The all-leather upper of this Dunk Low Medium for women by Nike merges a crisp white base with olive green overlays and a color-matched Swoosh. Underpinning the sneaker is a traditional rubber cupsole, featuring white sidewalls that contain a lightweight foam wedge for cushion. Underfoot, the olive rubber outsole includes the brand´s herringbone traction pattern that rounds off the silhouette.
​
​The Nike Dunk Low Medium Olive W was released the 9th of September 2022 and originally retailed at a price of $110.

name: Union LA Bephies Beauty Supply Summer of ‘96
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG SP Union LA Bephies Beauty Supply Summer of ‘96
description:
The Jordan 1 Retro High Union LA Bephies Beauty Supply The Summer of ‘96 hit the shelves on August 24, 2023. Bringing the heat with an iconic silhouette, this edition reinvents the Jordan 1 narrative.

Drenched in a fresh sail, wolf grey, muslin, pale vanilla, kinetic green, and university gold colorway, this sneaker is a canvas of culture and style. What makes it stand out? The intricate woven pattern that seamlessly wraps around the entirety of the shoe, marking its distinct identity in the Jordan 1 lineup. The design is a flawless blend of the past meeting the present.

Priced at a cool $200, the Jordan 1 Retro High Union LA Bephies was a must-cop from the jump on August 24, 2023.

name: White Thunder (PS)
title: Jordan 4 Retro White Thunder (PS)
description:
The Jordan 4 Retro White Thunder (PS) adds a monochromatic colorway of black and white to the beloved Jordan Brand silhouette from 1989.

The black upper is crafted from mesh and nubuck, which gives the White Thunder (PS) Jordan 4 Retro sneaker a premium, velvety feel. Additional black details can be found on part of the midsole, the long tongue, and the plastic wings. Pops of white decorate the midsole, the TPU eyelets, and the Jumpman logo. The signature molded mesh on the side panels stands out because it has a looser weave than the mesh used on many Air Jordan 4 models. Another notable feature is the foam midsole that cushions against impact.

Our experts at StockX like the oversized, white Jumpman logo on the heel, which is a nod to Michael Jordan’s gravity-defying athletic skills. The preschool-sized Jordan 4 Retro White Thunder (PS) was released on August 24, 2024, and sold for $100.

name: Wave Runner
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Wave Runner
description:
The Yeezy 700 Boost Wave Runner is the shoe that led Yeezy's pivot from a sleek, minimal aesthetic to a chunky, 90s inspired one. This was the gateway sneaker between knit runners like the 350 and the grungy skate look of the 550. The Yeezy 700 Wave Runner features a grey mesh and leather upper with black suede overlays and teal mesh underlays. At the base, a thick Boost sole and contrasting hits of orange complete the design.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Wave Runner originally released in November of 2017, and most recently re-released in March of 2022 for a retail price of $300.

name: Flat Pewter
title: Nike P-6000 Flat Pewter
description:
The Nike P-6000 Flat Pewter is a design inspired by the 2006 Nike Air Pegasus running shoe. This comfortable, supportive, breathable sneaker shoe aims for an early 2000's aesthetic.

The Flat Pewter iteration of the Nike P-6000 sports of base of matte gray mesh overlaid with strips of white leather and metallic-looking synthetic material with hits of aqua-green TPU. Gray suede overlays cover the toe and heel. A Nike swoosh in white leather adorns the side panel while embroidered Nike swooshes grace the toe box and heel tab. The gray tongue features a silver tongue tag with Nike branding and the green insoles that match the TPU have Nike swooshes in black.

What we enjoy most about this shoe is its dependable sole unit. The stacked foam midsole provides cushioning and impact absorption and rests atop a rubber outsole in black, green, and white that provides traction. The Nike P-6000 Flat Pewter was released on September 25, 2023, for a retail price of $120.

name: Bad Bunny Paso Fino
title: adidas Response CL Bad Bunny Paso Fino
description:
The adidas Response CL Bad Bunny Paso Fino is part of a collaboration between adidas and the Puerto Rican singer Bad Bunny. The sneaker takes the classic Response CL silhouette and incorporates Wild West elements inspired by Bad Bunny’s love of Western films.

The Ecru Tint, Bronze Strata, and Earth Strata colorway takes cues from the desert environment, leather, rust, and rich earth. Overlapping shapes and curved lines in leather across the mesh upper evoke desert formations such as mountains and rock outcroppings. The 3-Stripes cross the side panel, connecting the midsole and lace cage. The sneaker features the recognizable Response CL rubber outsole known for its bulky appearance and cushioning support.

Our StockX experts love the splashes of purple on the tongue and midsole, which represent the pops of color found in the otherwise monotone desert landscape. The adidas Response CL Bad Bunny Paso Fino was released on October 28, 2023, and retailed at $160.

name: True Pink (Women's)
title: adidas Gazelle Bold True Pink (Women's)
description:
The adidas Gazelle Bold True Pink (Women's) upgrades the Gazelle Bold silhouette with a watermelon-inspired colorway of True Pink and green.

However, the most eye-catching feature is the gum rubber platform underfoot. It features three layers of adidas outsoles that form a gradient of gum color. Each outsole displays ‘adidas’ and a small trefoil embossed into the material. The upper is made of True Pink suede with a tonal T-shaped toebox in the same color. Both the serrated 3-Stripes logo and the heel tab come in green and are outlined with Cloud White. The ‘GAZELLE’ lettering in metallic gold serves as a reminder of the shoe’s 1970s heritage and origin on the indoor courts.

Our StockX experts like the color combination on the texturized tongue. The ‘adidas’ logo features True Pink and green, while the tongue serves as a Cloud White background. The women’s size adidas Gazelle Bold True Pink (Women's) was released on December 15th, 2023, and retailed at $100.

name: Reverse Goldenrod (2024)
title: Nike Dunk Low Reverse Goldenrod (2024)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Reverse Goldenrod (2024) takes a classic silhouette and dresses it in a contrasting dual colorway that pops.

The 2024 Reverse Goldenrod Nike Dunk Low-Top features an upper constructed from smooth goldenrod leather on the forefoot, with the toe box featuring the classic perforations. The base of the heel, collar, and tongue are made of tightly woven goldenrod textile. All the overlays on the upper as well as the side-panel Nike Swoosh are black tumbled leather. Black laces match the black sock liner and insole. This eye-catching upper rests on a white foam midsole and a black rubber outsole with grooves and circles designed for traction and impact absorption.

But what we enjoy most about this shoe are the various hits of branding. Nike branding is embroidered in goldenrod on the heel tab, and a small black hang tag on the lateral collar features a backwards mini goldenrod Nike Swoosh. Nike branding appears in goldenrod on the tongue patch and insole and is embossed on the outsole. The Nike Dunk Low Reverse Goldenrod (2024) was released on February 8, 2024, for a retail price of $125.

name: Cherry (2023)
title: Jordan 12 Retro Cherry (2023)
description:
Dive deep into sneaker history with the Jordan 12 Retro Cherry, a silhouette that's more than just a shoe—it's a legacy. Dating back to its 1997 debut, the "Cherry" colorway was a showstopper, accompanying MJ during his iconic 1996-97 NBA season. Fast forward to 2023, this classic is making a comeback, and it promises to be as monumental as its storied past.

Embracing its roots, with flashy red accents, pebbled leather-constructed mudguards, matching midsoles, and shiny silver hardware paired with pristine white, quilted uppers, delivering a style that's both nostalgic and fresh.

This is one drop you don't want to miss. Set to release on October 28, 2023, for a retail price of $210, the Jordan 12 Retro Cherry is all about celebrating history, quality, and unmatched style. Get ready to step out with a piece of Jordan legacy.

name: Trocadéro Gardens
title: Nike SB Dunk Low Trocadéro Gardens
description:
The Nike SB Dunk Low Trocadéro Gardens is a skateboarding shoe with a warm colorway of Amber Brown, Pale Ivory, Guava Ice, Hemp, Crimson Tint, and Neutral Olive.

The Trocadéro Gardens Nike SB Dunk Low celebrates the 2024 Paris Olympics. It pays tribute to the Jardins du Trocadéro, which hosts the opening ceremony, and Champions Park, where victors interact with fans. The sneaker’s warm colorway mimics the soft sunrises seen from the gardens. The upper is made entirely of leather with Amber Brown accents on the vamp, the heel area, the laces, and the inner lining. The signature Swoosh logos check across the side panels and come in Guava Ice, which matches the mudguard.

Our StockX experts like the Neutral Olive accents, including the stitching on the midsole, the outline of the Swoosh logos, and the heel tab. The Nike SB Dunk Low Trocadéro Gardens was released on June 3, 2024, and retailed at $125.

name: Cream White Beige (Women's)
title: adidas Handball Spezial Cream White Beige (Women's)
description:
The adidas Handball Spezial Cream White Beige (Women's) paints the classic adidas Handball Spezial silhouette in Neutral Cream, Wonder Beige, and Magic Beige.

Originally introduced in 1979 as an indoor handball shoe, this version of the Spezial maintains its roots through retro-inspired design elements. For example, the sneaker boasts a T-shaped toebox and an upper constructed with premium materials. Although the base is made of smooth leather in Cream, the toebox features shaggy suede in Magic Beige. Other standout features include the leather serrated 3-Stripes logo on the side panels and ‘SPEZIAL’ printed on the lateral side in Metallic Gold. The sneaker boasts a gum rubber outsole that which provides traction without distracting from the neutral upper.

Our StockX experts like the exposed stitching on the heel tab because it matches the Wonder Beige of the Trefoil logo. The women’s size adidas Handball Spezial Cream White Beige (Women's) was released on December 29th, 2023, and retailed at $110.

name: Night Indigo
title: adidas Handball Spezial Night Indigo
description:
The adidas Handball Spezial Night Indigo reimagines the Handball Spezial with a dark colorway of Night Indigo with Cream White accents.

Cream White on the heel tab, the 3-Stripes logo, and the collar lining give the sneaker a worn-in feel, which speaks to the adidas Handball Spezial's retro athletic roots. The upper is crafted from soft suede, while the 3-Stripes logo and the heel tab come in smooth leather. The heel panel, toebox overlay, and serrated edges of the lace cage are also suede. Instead of natural or light gum, the rubber outsole features a dark gum hue that complements the Night Indigo suede. Another retro touch is the vintage-inspired tag on the tongue that displays "adidas handball spezial" in Night Indigo letters.

Our experts at StockX like the metallic "SPEZIAL" lettering on the lateral side panel. The adidas Handball Spezial Night Indigo was released on May 1, 2024, and sold for $100.

name: Italian Camo (2024)
title: Nike Kobe 6 Protro Italian Camo (2024)
description:
Introducing the Nike Kobe 6 Protro Italian Camo 2024, a sleek rendition of the classic Kobe 6, set to captivate with its unique camouflage pattern inspired by Kobe Bryant's early years in Italy. The colorway, a sophisticated blend of black, crimson bog, and khaki, is a stylish nod to Kobe's formative experiences and his enduring legacy. Tailored for those who admire the subtleties of design and the stories behind them, this sneaker combines the essence of Kobe's history with cutting-edge footwear technology.

The Kobe 6 Protro isn't just about its standout Italian Camo aesthetic; it's a powerhouse of sneaker tech. The shoe is engineered with advanced performance features like Zoom Air cushioning for responsive comfort, a Cushlon midsole for lightweight support, and a durable outsole that pays homage to Kobe's multidirectional playing style. The sneaker's unique texture mimics a snake's skin, reflecting Kobe's "Black Mamba" persona, while the innovative tech ensures these shoes stand up to the demands of both performance and everyday wear.

On April 13, 2024, the Nike Kobe 6 Protro Italian Camo dropped at a retail price of $190. This release offers a piece of basketball royalty's origin story, wrapped in modern performance and timeless design. Embrace the spirit of Kobe's legacy and add a touch of Italian finesse to your sneaker collection with this 2024 re-release. It's a sneaker that celebrates history, innovation, and the endless pursuit of greatness, perfect for those who walk the path less traveled.

name: Collegiate Green Lucid Pink (Women's)
title: adidas Gazelle Indoor Collegiate Green Lucid Pink (Women's)
description:
The adidas Gazelle Indoor Collegiate Green Lucid Pink (Women's), a classic sneaker specifically sized for women, takes a signature 1960s silhouette and dresses it in eye-popping colors.

The Women’s Collegiate Green Lucid Pink adidas Gazelle Indoor has an upper of lightweight Rich Green suede, overlaid with the signature adidas three stripes in white leather with serrated edges and tonal stitching. Gold Gazelle branding adorns the green suede along the outer edge of the top stripe. The laces and tongue, along with the sock liner, match the luxuriant green of the upper, and the tongue features gold adidas trefoil branding. The midsole is constructed from cushioning EVA foam, overlaid with translucent gum rubber on the sidewall surrounding the entire shoe. The outsole is made from gum rubber, with the traction sporting an adidas trefoil pattern.

The detail our sneaker experts appreciate most about this shoe is the unfussy hit of bright pink leather on the heel tab. A lifestyle sneaker specifically sized for women, the adidas Gazelle Indoor Collegiate Green Lucid Pink (Women's), was released on May 26th, 2023, for $100 retail.

name: Fire Red (2022)
title: Jordan 3 Retro Fire Red (2022)
description:
The Air Jordan 3 Retro Fire Red 2022 brings back an OG colorway from the year 1988.

The top section of the Retro Fire Red is crafted from white leather with elephant print overlays done in dark gray at the heel and forefoot. The model also features contrasting fire red accents on the midsole, eyelets, and perforated leather collar. An airsole is nestled underfoot in the heel section, and the sneaker gets a fire red Jumpman on the tongue and a Nike Air logo on the heel.

The Air Jordan 3 Retro Fire Red 2022 was released on the 10th of September 2022 and initially retailed for $210.

name: Denim
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Denim
description:
The Jordan 1 Retro High OG Denim adds a denim construction to the recognizable Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG silhouette.

The Denim Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG base comes in white denim with a light tie-dye-like pattern in light blue, while the forefoot and heel overlays are made from faded indigo denim. The overlays boast single or double lines of stitches, which keep the denim from fraying and contribute to the sneaker’s casual aesthetic. The panel around the collar and the signature Swoosh logos on the side panels feature dark indigo. Finally, the tongue displays a retro-inspired woven tag with "NIKE AIR" spelled out in dark blue, while a white Air Jordan Wings logo is printed across the heel.

Our StockX experts like how the Summit White laces and rubber outsole in Gum Medium Brown provide vintage touches. The Jordan 1 Retro High OG Denim was initially released on June 15, 2024, and sold for $180.

name: Kobe Bryant Lakers Home
title: Nike Air Force 1 Low Retro QS Kobe Bryant Lakers Home
description:
The Nike Air Force 1 Low Retro QS Kobe Bryant Lakers Home takes inspiration from a pivotal moment in basketball history—the 2002-2003 NBA season, when Kobe Bryant made waves during his sneaker free agency. Paying homage to the Black Mamba’s legendary career with the Lakers, this edition showcases a classic white leather upper accented with varsity maize and varsity purple details, reminiscent of the Lakers’ iconic home jersey. The addition of Bryant's jersey number and the Kobe logo stitched on the heel solidifies its place as a collector’s piece.

This sneaker balances nostalgia with premium design. Every element, from the debossed Kobe logo on the outer heel to the clean yet bold colorway, exudes sophistication and style. The versatility of this color palette makes it a statement both on and off the court. Whether you're a lifelong Lakers fan or just appreciate the legacy of Kobe Bryant, this pair delivers a meaningful blend of history and sneaker culture.

Released on December 6, 2024, at a retail price of $130, the Nike Air Force 1 Low Retro QS Kobe Bryant Lakers Home is more than just a sneaker—it’s a celebration of basketball heritage. Featuring white, varsity maize, and varsity purple hues, this limited edition is a must-have.
model: Nike Air Force 1 Low Retro QS

name: Black White
title: Onitsuka Tiger Mexico 66 Black White
description:
The Onitsuka Tiger Mexico 66 presents itself in an effortlessly sleek Black/White combo, blending the iconic retro silhouette with today's streetwear sensibilities.

Riding high on the trend wave, this sneaker is a testament to timeless design. It showcases leather artistry throughout its upper, while black dominates and is accented by crisp white contrasts. The streamlined aesthetic is not only visually pleasing but also perfectly aligns with the current sneaker zeitgeist. Beyond its visual appeal, it carries the legacy of Onitsuka Tiger. Rocking the Mexico 66 means you're not just wearing a shoe; you're wearing an icon.

For the admirers of classics, the Onitsuka Tiger Mexico 66 in Black & White debuted with a retail price of $130.

name: Best of adi Stormtrooper
title: adidas AE 1 Best of adi Stormtrooper
description:
The adidas AE 1 Best of adi Stormtrooper is part of NBA player Anthony Edwards’ signature collaboration with adidas.

This sneaker draws inspiration from Kobe Bryant’s adidas Crazy 1 Stormtrooper, which also took elements from Star Wars’ iconic Imperial soldiers. The AE 1 Best of adi Stormtrooper features an off-white TPU panel that looks like Stormtrooper body armor. The white panels cover the area from heel to toe on the sides and boast a honeycomb pattern that conforms to the shape of the foot. The panel forms an arrow-like pattern that contributes to the sneaker's futuristic appeal. The rest of the upper is made of lightweight textile that wraps around the ankle and boasts an ultra-secure front lace closure.

Our experts at StockX like the way the name ‘Best of adi’ pays tribute to adidas’ impact on sports history and performance. The adidas AE 1 Best of adi Stormtrooper was released on March 1st, 2024, and retailed at $120.

name: Athletic Department Deep Royal Blue
title: Nike Air Max 1 Athletic Department Deep Royal Blue
description:
The Nike Air Max 1 Athletic Department Deep Royal Blue presents a subtly elegant shoe with a classic design that delivers high-performance capabilities and style that fits in anywhere.
​
The Athletic Department Deep Royal Blue iteration of the Nike Air Max 1 features an upper with a base constructed from white mesh that keeps the shoe lightweight and provides breathability. Suede in shades of gray overlay the forefoot, eye stays, side panel, and heel, providing an aesthetic element as well as structure. A dark blue suede mud guard surrounds the shoe and sports an iridescent mini swoosh. The same blue is echoed in a sock liner and the side-panel Nike swoosh that sneaks beneath the heel.
​
What our experts enjoy most about this shoe is the sole unit that revolutionized sneakers. Visible Air is housed in the white foam midsole. The outsole is constructed from black rubber lugged for traction and white rubber vented for midsole expansion. The Nike Air Max 1 Athletic Department Deep Royal Blue was released on September 7, 2023, for a retail price of $150.

name: White Grey
title: New Balance 550 White Grey
description:
The New Balance 550 White Grey features a white leather upper with monochromatic perforated leather overlays and puffed New Balance logos. From there, a woven New Balance Basketball tongue label and matching sole completes the design.

The New Balance 550 White Grey released in June of 2021 and retailed for $100.

name: Triple Black
title: New Balance 9060 Triple Black
description:
The New Balance 9060 Triple Black exemplifies the essence of simplicity and versatility in a sports shoe.

Constructed with a breathable mesh and soft suede upper, the Triple Black New Balance 9060 prioritizes both comfort and temperature regulation, preventing overheating. Predominantly black, the mesh upper introduces a slightly softer dark charcoal hue, creating a balanced contrast. The iconic midfoot "N" motifs seamlessly integrate with the understated sole units, contributing to a unified aesthetic. The tongue logo pays homage to the original 991 lace jewel. Underneath, the sculpted pod midsole incorporates ABZORB, ENCAP, and SBS cushioning for optimal comfort.

The most noteworthy feature of the New Balance 9060 Triple Black is its sculpted pod midsole, which includes ABZORB, ENCAP, and SBS cushioning. This aspect ensures enduring comfort, establishing the shoe as an excellent choice for everyday wear. The sneaker was originally sold for $150 on September 22nd, 2023.

name: Triple White
title: adidas Ultra Boost 1.0 DNA Triple White
description:
The adidas Ultra Boost 1.0 DNA Triple White takes on a monochromatic design, dressed in Cloud White from heel to toe, featuring adidas signature technologies, including PRIMEKNIT and Boost.

The Triple White adidas Ultra Boost 1.0 DNA upper is made of PRIMEKNIT material, which gives it a lightweight and breathable feel. The midsole features adidas’ Boost technology, ensuring support and comfort. Underfoot, the Stretchweb outsole flexes naturally, while the Continental™ rubber outsole provides traction and grip. For brand recognition, the sneaker features the iconic 3-Stripes on the lateral and medial sides, with an adidas logo on the tongue tag. With a lace closure for a secure fit, this shoe provides both comfort and an eco-conscious design.

What stands out in the adidas Ultra Boost 1.0 DNA Triple White is its commitment to sustainability, as its upper incorporates a high-performance yarn made from at least 50% Parley Ocean Plastic, repurposed from plastic waste intercepted in remote coastal areas and shorelines, preventing ocean pollution. The remaining 50% of the yarn is recycled polyester. The shoe was released on January 1st, 2023, for $200.

name: White
title: Nike Air VaporMax Plus White
description:
The Nike Air VaporMax Plus White features an off-white neoprene upper with a white TPU cage and gray Swooshes. From there, the shoe's signature translucent outsole and VM branding on the heel complete the design.

The Nike Air VaporMax Plus White released in February of 2018 and retailed for $190.

name: Triple White
title: Nike P-6000 Triple White
description:
The Nike P 6000 Triple White have a plain white color and are made from a mix of genuine leather, nylon, mesh, faux leather, and rubber.

The Nike P 6000 Triple White has a lace-up closure style and a prominent tongue with Nike branding on it. The shoe also has a small Nike Swoosh at the front that merges with the rubber sole. They have a thick sole and a side profile featuring horizontal and vertical lines that create a mesh pattern with the Nike Swoosh on both sides of the shoe.

The Nike P 6000 Triple White debuted at the retail price of $100 in June 2019.

name: Dark Smoke Grey Varsity Red
title: Jordan 1 Low SE Craft Dark Smoke Grey Varsity Red
description:
The Jordan 1 Low SE Craft Dark Smoke Gray Varsity Red is a special edition, low-top sneaker that applies soft suede and leather to the Air Jordan 1 silhouette.

Suede overlays cross the primarily leather upper, while the tongue is made of a textile material that provides a soft sheen. The entire upper is dressed in Dark Smoke Gray. However, two pairs of stitched lines run up the round toe and come in Varsity Red thread. In addition, the heel features the Air Jordan wings logo in suede, outlined by two sets of Varsity Red stitched lines. Other branding details include the suede Swoosh on the side panels and the Jumpman logo embroidered on the tongue in Dark Smoke Gray.
