Our StockX experts like the way the speckled pattern on the rubber outsole breaks up the black-on-black aesthetic. The Jordan 1 Low SE Craft Dark Smoke Gray Varsity Red was released on December 27th, 2023, and retailed at $125.

name: Designed by Japan (Women's)
title: Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Designed by Japan (Women's)
description:
The Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Designed by Japan (Women's) is a layered multicolored sneaker that finds inspiration in the "Moon Shoe" designed by Nike co-founder Bill Bowerman. Although the sneaker boasts a variety of colors, most of the tones are neutral or earthy, which prevents the hues from clashing.

The base comes in Pale Ivory with full-grain leather, soft suede, synthetic, plastic, and mesh details across the upper. The suede overlays in Pale Ivory are thin and create a web-like pattern. Black leather Swooshes reach across the side panels and complement the black on the rubber outsole. However, the outsole also features Light Bone, Aquarius Blue, and Orange-brown hues. The traction pattern pays homage to the waffle sole found on the "Moon Shoe."

Our StockX experts like the addition of layered Aquarius Blue, Light Bone, and White on the bulky midsole. The Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Designed by Japan (Women's) was released on May 10, 2024, and retailed at $180.

name: White Grey Fog
title: Nike Air Max 95 Essential White Grey Fog
description:
The Nike Air Max 95 Essential White Grey Fog is white with grey fog accents. The footwear is designed with a mesh upper, reinforced with full-grain leather overlays. It has white, fast-lace laces and can be slipped on. Its sole is flat with a thickness of 4cm. The footwear insoles are non-removable with a textile lining. Themidsole is made of foam. The footwear further has visible Nike Air cushioning. A small Nike Swoosh is on one side of the heel.
​
The Nike Air Max 95 Essential White Grey Fog was released in November 2021 at a retail price of $170.

name: Panda (Women's)
title: Jordan 1 Mid Panda (Women's)
description:
The Jordan 1 Mid Panda (Women's) was released as part of the Jordan 1 Mid collection and was specifically made in women's sizes.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid Panda for women is designed with a black-and-white color scheme that mimics the appearance of a panda. The Nike Swoosh is also black and can be seen on the side, while the Air Jordan Wings logo appears in white. The shoe also features a rubber outsole that provides traction and grip, even on slippery surfaces. In addition, the shoe is lined with a padded collar and tongue, which provide extra cushioning and support.

Our experts believe that one of the most notable features of the Jordan 1 Mid Panda (Women's) is the mid-top silhouette. This design provides additional support and protection to the ankle, which makes the shoe ideal for sporty activities. The sneaker debuted on June 20th, 2023, and retailed for $125.

name: Chestnut (Women's)
title: UGG Lowmel Chestnut (Women's)
description:
The UGG Lowmel Chestnut (Women's) is a hybrid sneaker made for women that features some elements of the classic UGG boot.
   
This iteration of the UGG Lowmel comes in a Chestnut brown color that is dominant throughout. True to its hybrid nature, the upper is made of suede, recycled canvas, and recycled polyester. The toe box and ankle area are Chestnut polyester, while layered suede overlays round out the toe and form the sides, eyestays, mudguard, and heel counter. Recycled canvas in a tan color outlines the heel counter. UGG branding is debossed into the lateral heel, and another UGG patch is seen on the tongue. The heel has a pull tab, and the inside is lined with recycled wool. The shoe sits on a thick foam outsole. 

What we like best about this shoe is that it provides all the comfort of a boot or slipper but can be worn outside. The UGG Lowmel Chestnut (Women's) was initially released on June 24, 2024, for $150.

name: University Blue
title: Nike Dunk Low Retro University Blue
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Retro University Blue highlights a timeless design with bold, inspired color blocking. This retro sneaker redefines the iconic Dunk silhouette with vibrant colors and a meticulous finish, showing off a lovely mixture of original designs with striking visuals.

The University Blue Dunk Low Retro by Nike comes with smooth leather panels in white and bright blue, giving you a two-tone design. Blue overlays extend across the toe box, eyestays, and heel, while Nike branding appears in matching blue and white on the tongue tag and heel tab. The foam midsole provides lightweight comfort, with a rubber outsole for traction. Introduced in 1985, the Dunk revolutionized basketball footwear, later gaining a cult following in casual wear.

Something we love about the Nike Dunk Low Retro University Blue is its low-profile silhouette that gives you added versatility, and its two-tone leather overlays for a dynamic visual contrast. This sneaker retailed at $115 when it was released on October 1, 2024.

name: Naruto Shippuden Kakashi
title: Crocs Classic Clog Naruto Shippuden Kakashi
description:
The Crocs Classic Clog Naruto Shippuden Kakashi is part of a collaboration between Crocs and Naruto Shippuden, a Japanese manga and anime series created by Masashi Kishimoto.

This slip-on shoe pays tribute to Kakashi Hatake, a ninja and protagonist in the series, through colors and motifs. For example, the clog boasts a green base, which symbolizes Kakashi Hatake’s uniform. Several Jibbitz charms can be found on the upper, including a ninja star, a replica of the ninja’s face, a red rectangle featuring fighting characters, a weapon, and a cat-like mask. Instead of a traditional heel strap, this Croc comes with a padded strap that resembles bomber jacket material. There is also a small pouch, which can be attached to the heel strap with a snap.

Our StockX experts like the enhanced traction on the underside of the shoe, which comes in contrasting navy. The Crocs Classic Clog Naruto Shippuden Kakashi was released on February 27th, 2024, and retailed at $70.

name: Granite
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Granite
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Granite boasts the iconic Yeezy silhouette, known for its low-top design and sleek, sock-like fit. The sneaker primarily takes on neutral tones in granite and Core Black for a neutral and versatile look.

The Granite adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 is constructed with a PRIMEKNIT upper, designed for lightweight flexibility and breathability. The minimalist sneaker is placed on top of a complete-length Boost midsole, which becomes visible through openings in the rubber outsole that offers traction. The sidewalls are enveloped in semi-transparent TPU to enhance durability and provide added support. The Yeezy sneaker takes on the classic lace closure, and for branding, the Granite PRIMEKNIT upper showcases 'SPLY-350' across its center in a contrasting Core Black stitching.

What we love about adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Granite is its minimalist design. This shoe embodies simplicity and understated elegance with its predominantly Granite colorway, subtle accents, and clean lines. The sneaker was released on August 28th, 2023, for $230.

name: Sand Dark Cherry (Women's)
title: UGG Tasman Slipper Sand Dark Cherry (Women's)
description:
The UGG Tasman Slipper in Sand Dark Cherry (Women's) is a versatile slipper, combining a plush natural wool lining with soft suede and an embroidered braid for an easy slip-on silhouette.

Designed with a light and durable outsole reminiscent of the classic boot, the Sand Dark Cherry UGG Tasman Slipper (Women’s) is suitable for both indoor and outdoor wear. The interior is lined with sumptuous natural wool, ensuring warmth and comfort. Crafted from soft suede, the slipper exudes a luxurious feel, featuring subtle UGG branding on the lateral side. An added touch of elegance comes from the embroidered braid incorporated into the design.

The distinctive quality of the UGG Tasman Slipper in Sand Dark Cherry (Women’s) is its authentic sheepskin lining. This element not only elevates the comfort level of the slippers, but also introduces a hint of opulence to their overall appeal. The slipper debuted for $110 on December 13th, 2023.

name: White
title: Nike Air Max Plus White
description:
The Nike Air Max Plus White is a versatile shoe, ideal for everyday use and an active lifestyle. There is air cushioning on the heels and forefront, allowing for full-length cushion and support. The ankles are also well-supported. The wavy design lines are complemented with the plastic accents and breathable mesh on the upper of the shoe. The shoe also features colored air pods to provide a touch of contrast, and the all-white color of the Nike Air Plus White gives it a clean look.

The Nike Air Max Plus White was released in January of 2019 for $150.

name: Cardboard
title: adidas Samba OG Cardboard
description:
The adidas Samba OG Cardboard is a version of the shoe originally intended as a soccer shoe, but it has transformed into an icon of street style.

This version of the adidas Samba OG comes in a unique Cardboard and Brown Desert colorway. The upper is made of brown woven mesh, which allows for breathability and style. Suede overlays in a Cardboard color line the toebox and run up the middle of the shoe and underneath the laces. The typical three stripes logo appears on the midsole in white leather and also on the heel collar. An adidas logo patch can be found stamped onto the tongue in a lighter brown color. The rubber outsole shares the Brown Desert colorway.

What we like best about this shoe is the look of the woven mesh upper. It departs from traditional shoe design and makes the sneaker stand out. The adidas Samba OG Cardboard was released on March 8, 2024, for a price of $100.

name: Onyx (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Foam RNR Onyx (Kids)
description:
The futuristic clog receives a muted, one-note makeover in the adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Kids "Onyx."

The molded upper is made of black injected EVA foam and has strategically placed vents all over the vamp and side sections for increased ventilation and comfort. The footbed includes a top layer that is soft and textured for ease of stepping in. Only the adidas logo, which has a wavy traction pattern for multi-surface grip, is used for exterior branding.

The adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Onyx Kids was originally released in June 2022, at $60 and in March 2024, at a retail price of $65.

name: Utility Black
title: adidas Yeezy 500 Utility Black
description:
The hiking-inspired adidas Yeezy 500 Utility Black features a durable black mesh and suede upper that is prime for daily wear. From there, a sculptural adiPRENE sole offers responsiveness and support.

The adidas Yeezy 500 Utility Black originally released in July of 2018 for $200, and then restocked in November of 2020 and November of 2021.

name: Legend Light Brown
title: Jordan 1 Low SE Legend Light Brown
description:
As part of the Method of Make series, the Jordan 1 Low SE Legend Light Brown reimagines the AJ1 Low using premium materials and a contemporary color scheme. It boasts neutrals, including Sail, Legend Light Brown, Archaeo Brown, and Neutral Grey.

Creating a sophisticated feel, the base is constructed from leather in Sail, while the suede overlays at the heel and forefoot come in Legend Light Brown. The eyelets, the signature Swoosh logo, the Jumpman logo, and the Air Jordan Wings logo embroidered on the heel showcase soft Archaeo Brown. The minimalist branding on the tongue contributes to the sneaker’s premium appearance, while the perforations on the toebox allow the foot to breathe.

Our experts at StockX like the midsole’s off-white hue. Here, encapsulated Air units provide responsive cushioning without adding a distracting design detail. The Jordan 1 Low SE Legend Light Brown was released on July 18, 2024, and sold for $125.

name: Travis Scott Medium Olive (TD)
title: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG SP Travis Scott Medium Olive (TD)
description:
The Jordan 1 Retro Low OG SP Travis Scott Medium Olive (TD), in toddler sizes, is a low-top athletic shoe featuring a Medium Olive leather upper contrasted by Sail overlays and the Swoosh in black, placed in a reverse orientation. In red, the Nike, Travis Scott, and Jordan Wings logos accent the tongue and heel. The Muslin midsole and Medium Olive outsole complete the aesthetic.

The Air Jordan 1 is one of the American athletic shoe brand Nike’s crowning achievements for its unparalleled longevity and popularity. Travis Scott is a rapper, producer, and songwriter from Houston, Texas, whose records have topped charts since the 20-teens. Nike tapped Scott to apply his signature aesthetic to the Jordan 1 Retro, one of their iconic styles. The shoe comes with accessories, like pink and black laces.

Our experts feel that the best features of the Jordan 1 Retro Medium Olive are the rounded toe cap, sole pattern, and ventilation holes of this limited-edition shoe. The Jordan 1 Retro Low OG SP Travis Scott Medium Olive (TD) was released on September 28, 2024, and retailed at $50.

name: The Powerpuff Girls Buttercup
title: Nike SB Dunk Low The Powerpuff Girls Buttercup
description:
Embrace the bold and daring with the Nike SB Dunk Low The Powerpuff Girls Buttercup. This edition captures Buttercup's fearless and tough personality, reflected in the Mean Green/Black/Lotus Pink colorway. The design elements of the sneaker are as dynamic and powerful as Buttercup herself, making a strong statement.

The sneaker's striking color palette is complemented by its high-quality construction and attention to detail, embodying the spirit of the fierce Powerpuff Girl. This Dunk Low is not just a shoe; it's an expression of Buttercup's unyielding energy and charisma.

Released on December 14 at skate shops and on SNKRS, and priced at $135, the Nike SB Dunk Low The Powerpuff Girls Buttercup is a perfect mix of style and attitude. Sneaker enthusiasts and fans of the show will not want to miss this unique and spirited sneaker.​

name: Washed Pink (Women's)
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Washed Pink (Women's)
description:
Jordan Brand is giving this Jordan 1 release to the ladies, with the women’s-exclusive Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG Washed Pink.
​​
​The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG Washed Pink is constructed using pink suede and white leather across the uppers, with muslin and sail accents around the collar and midsole to help give the sneaker a vintage themed look. White laces tie the sneaker together over the muslin colored tongue.
​
​The women’s-exclusive Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG Washed Pink released April 22, 2023, with a retail price of $180.

name: Palomino
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Palomino
description:
Introducing the Jordan 1 Retro High OG Palomino. Drenched in a stylish Black/Metallic Gold/Palomino/Sail colorway, this sneaker commands attention, blending tradition with a bold, modern edge.

The meticulously crafted leather and nubuck upper, touched with shades of palomino and black, resonate opulence. Signature details like the iconic Jordan wings logo and the flowing Swoosh bring the perfect juxtaposition, harmonizing old-school vibes with new colors. The Metallic Gold Nike Air logo on the tongue adds the perfect pop of color.

Launched on September 2, 2023, with a launch price of $180, the Jordan 1 Retro High OG Palomino offers a fresh take on a timeless classic. Elevate your collection, and get your pair on StockX now.

name: Light Carbon
title: Nike Dunk Low SE Light Carbon
description:
The Nike Dunk Low SE Light Carbon finds inspiration in the original basketball shoe from the 1980s, but adds modern upgrades, including a subdued colorway of Light Carbon, Platinum Tint, and white.

The upper is made of white leather with Light Carbon overlays that create a subtle color-blocking effect. The leather is designed to soften over time, which contributes to the sneaker’s vintage appearance. Due to its padded collar and low-top design, the sneaker resembles a skateboarding shoe. It boasts a foam midsole with responsive cushioning and a rubber outsole with Nike’s signature pivot hoops pattern. This design allows the sneaker to grip the ground, improving traction without sacrificing durability.

Our StockX experts like the suede Swoosh checking across the side panels. Its color matches the lining and complements the base. The Nike Dunk Low SE Light Carbon was released on January 1st, 2024, and retailed at $125.

name: Sail Plum Eclipse (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Sail Plum Eclipse (Women's)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Diffused Taupe (Women's) was released alongside several Dunk Low variations with subdued palettes, including Hemp Sail and Cacao Wow. It pays tribute to iconic Nike basketball shoe silhouettes from the ‘80s while utilizing premium materials.

On this Nike Dunk Low for women the upper is crafted entirely from smooth leather with perforations across the vamp and the Swoosh checked across the side. The use of leather gives the shoe a slightly cushiony appearance that adds a minimal amount of bulk to the silhouette. The Diffused Taupe colorway includes Sail, Plum Eclipse, and Diffused taupe, which presents as an off-white base with taupe accents on the overlays, lace cage, heel tab, and rubber outsole.

Our experts at StockX love the Swoosh detail in Plum Eclipse, which contrasts the light tones found on the rest of the shoe. The women’s size Nike Dunk Low Diffused Taupe (Women's) was released on December 1, 2023, and retailed at $110.

name: Panda (2023) (Women's)
title: Jordan 1 Low Panda (2023) (Women's)
description:
The Air Jordan 1 Low Panda (2023) (W) arrives in a white, black, and white color palette.

The Low Panda Jordan 1 (2023) (W) has an upper that is constructed from durable materials, including a combination of supple leather and suede. The shoe's cushioned midsole and supportive collar ensure a comfortable fit. The outsole is made of a durable rubber material with a traditional tread pattern, providing traction and stability. The shoe's toe box is perforated for ventilation. The sneaker features black Swoosh branding on either lateral side, the Jumpman logo on the tongue, and the Air Jordan Wings logo on the heel.

The women’s rendition of the Air Jordan 1 Low Panda (2023) (W) was released on March 10, 2023, and sold for a retail price of $110.

name: USC
title: Nike Dunk Low USC
description:
Nike has done it again with the Nike Dunk Low USC, code style DD1391-602 sneaker design featuring the University of Southern California Trojans' official colors.

Nike Dunk Low USC is constructed of leather material on the upper and rubber on the outsole. Nike Dunk Low USC features a colorway composed of white, gym red, and yellow covering 90% of the upper, with yellow Nike branding at the heel and tongue. A white perforated vamp and a red suede Swoosh complete the design of this sneaker.

Nike Dunk Low USC was released at a retail price of $100 on November 9, 2022.

name: Travis Scott Medium Olive (PS)
title: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG SP Travis Scott Medium Olive (PS)
description:
The Jordan 1 Retro Low OG SP Travis Scott Medium Olive (PS), in pre-school sizes, is an athletic shoe with a low-top silhouette. The leather upper is done in Medium Olive overlaid with Sail at the tip, lace panel, and heel, accented by a reversed Swoosh in black. Travis Scott and Jordan wings branding accents the heel, while the Nike branding appears on the tongue. The midsole and outsole combo in Muslin and Medium Olive completes the look.

Nike introduced the Air Jordan 1 to the public in 1985 after designing it for Michael Jordan in 1984, and from there, the shoe went on to have legendary status. Classic and iconic, the Jordan 1 retro has been reimagined in myriad variations. In 2024, Nike worked with Houston, Texas-based artist Travis Scott on his signature Jordan 1 Retro, which features his stitched mouth-face artwork.

In our opinion, the Retro Low OG SP's best feature is its unusual branding and stitching, which distinguish it from other models. The Jordan 1 Retro Low OG SP Travis Scott Medium Olive (PS) was released on September 28, 2024, and retailed for $60.

name: Mambacita
title: Nike Kobe 8 Protro Mambacita
description:
Unveil the Nike Kobe 8 Protro "Mambacita," a sneaker that beautifully encapsulates the spirit of Kobe Bryant's beloved daughter, Gianna 'Gigi' Bryant. This sneaker is a heartfelt homage, merging innovative design with profound meaning. The white, metallic gold, and black colorway are elegantly adorned with butterflies across the upper.

Crafted with precision, the Nike Kobe 8 Protro "Mambacita" incorporates advanced basketball technology, ensuring that every step and jump is supported by superior comfort and control. This model features a lightweight construction and responsive cushioning, which are integral to the Protro series, aiming to offer enhanced performance on the court. Additionally, the sneaker highlights Gigi's name & jersey number '2', prominently displayed on the back of the heel clip, symbolizing her continuing legacy within the basketball community and beyond.

Launched on Gigi’s birthday May 1, 2024, and priced at $190, these sneakers are a symbol of legacy and inspiration. The release of the Nike Kobe 8 Protro "Mambacita" was a significant sneaker moment, celebrating Gigi’s life and her impact. Embrace this exclusive release, which comes complete with special packaging, echoing the exceptional quality and sentiment of the Mamba & Mambacita legacy.

name: Dark Onyx (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Slide Dark Onyx (Kids)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Slide Dark Onyx (Kids) is a child-sized version of the signature Yeezy Slide in a monotone colorway with no accent colors.

This slide has a unibody build, which means it’s made from one piece of injected EVA foam. This material is both lightweight and durable but appears hefty. The open-toe design allows air to circulate through the slide and keeps the foot from feeling confined. Sticking to its Yeezy roots, the slide boasts a minimalist silhouette and subdued branding details. For example, a debossed adidas logo can be found on the soft footbed. Something that makes this shoe stand out is the oversized, serrated outsole, which is also made of EVA foam. It provides traction while contrasting the smooth upper.

Our StockX experts like the way the slide turns up at the toe. The kid-sized adidas Yeezy Slide Dark Onyx (Kids) was released on March 7th, 2024, and retailed at $50.

name: Philly (2024)
title: Nike Kobe 4 Protro Philly (2024)
description:
Introducing the Nike Kobe 4 Protro Philly 2024, a stunning tribute to Kobe Bryant's birthplace and the historical city of Philadelphia. Cloaked in the patriotic varsity royal, white, and university red, this sneaker encapsulates the spirit of Philly with a design that's as bold and fearless as the city's own story. Designed for the trendsetters, the Kobe 4 Protro Philly celebrates the fusion of Bryant's origins with the iconic American heritage.

Engineered with cutting-edge sneaker technology, the Kobe 4 Protro Philly boasts a Zoom Air unit in the heel for responsive cushioning, a Flywire-laced upper for a lock-down fit, and a Phylon midsole for lightweight support, all underlined by the star-spangled collar lining that pays homage to the City of Brotherly Love. This sneaker is a style statement a marvel of design that nods to the past while propelling you forward with unrivaled comfort and durability.

Released on April 13, 2024, for $190, the Nike Kobe 4 Protro Philly is a piece of basketball and American history. With its Philadelphia-inspired colorway and advanced performance features, it stands as a beacon of honor to the city that gave birth to one of basketball's greatest legends. This re-release brings with it the opportunity to walk in the shoes of greatness, combining Philly's rich heritage with the performance legacy Kobe Bryant left behind.

name: White Neutral Pink (Women's)
title: ASICS Gel-1130 White Neutral Pink (Women's)
description:
The ASICS Gel-1130 White Neutral Pink (Women's) adds a rose gold-inspired colorway of white and Neutral Pink to the Gel-1130’s technical silhouette.

While the base comes in airy, white mesh, the signature tiger strip overlays are made from synthetic leather in the White Neutral Pink (Women's) ASICS Gel-1130. The change in materials from genuine leather to synthetic makes this version of the Gel-1130 stand out from models dating back to the early 2000s. It gives the sneaker a modern upgrade and allows the metallic silver accents to catch the light. Although the sneaker draws inspiration from previous interpretations of the Gel-1000 series, its stability-centric construction more closely follows the Gel-Kayano 14.

Our experts at StockX like the way the Neutral Pink and metallic silver accents work together to create a sneaker that honors its retro roots while presenting something new. The women’s size ASICS Gel-1130 White Neutral Pink (Women's) was released on June 1, 2014, and sold for $115.

name: Team Gold
title: Nike Dunk Low Team Gold
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Team Gold arrives in a white, team gold-wolf grey-white color palette.

The Low Team Gold Nike Dunk adopts a classic silhouette with an upper that is made of leather, which provides durability. The shoe's midsole is constructed from a supportive and cushioning foam material. The sneaker's outsole features a durable rubber material with a textured pattern that provides traction. The shoe features the Nike Swoosh on the lateral sides and "NIKE" branding on the heel.

The Nike Dunk Low Team Gold was released on March 14, 2023, and was sold at a retail price of $110.

name: Travis Scott Black Phantom
title: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG SP Travis Scott Black Phantom
description:
Travis Scott closed out 2022 with the return of his signature Jordan 1 Low, this time in a new Black Phantom colorway.

The silhouette returned with his signature backwards Nike Swoosh but with a new contrast stitch design. The all black nubuck sneakers feature a Nike Air logo on the tongue and an Air Jordan Wings logo on the right heel tab. Red, Black, and White/Black laces are included and an embroidered Bee is located on the heel tab of the left sneaker inspired by Travis’ daughter, Stormi.

The Air Jordan 1 Retro Low OG SP Travis Scott Black Phantom released December 15, 2022 with a retail price of $150.

name: Hello Kitty (Women's)
title: adidas Sambae Hello Kitty (Women's)
description:
The adidas Sambae Hello Kitty (Women's) pays homage to the iconic cat character created by Yuko Shimizu for Sanrio through Hello Kitty-themed details and colors.

The white, calf leather upper of the Hello Kitty (Women's) adidas Sambae features embroidered outlines of Hello Kitty in white thread, including the character’s signature bow and cat ears. In addition, the right shoe displays a metal lace jewel with Hello Kitty’s face, while the left shoe features a big, plastic bow in red at the top of the lace closure system. Hello Kitty details and the adidas trefoil grace the white insole, while the signature gum rubber outsole comes in Clear Pink and the flat, leather tongue reveals adidas branding.

Our experts at StockX like the use of black on the 3-Stripes logos, the heel tab, and the tongue’s adidas branding because it matches the color used to outline Hello Kitty. The women’s size adidas Sambae Hello Kitty (Women's) was released on June 14, 2024, and retailed at $115.

name: Black (Kids)
title: UGG Tasman II Slipper Black (Kids)
description:
The UGG Tasman II Slipper Black Kids is slip-on footwear sized for kids that can serve as a slipper or a shoe.

The upper section of this Tasman II Slipper is made of black suede with UGG Tasman braid detailing around the cuff. The lining and insole are made from 17 mm pure upcycled wool. The shoe also features 100% recycled polyester fiber binding and a heat-embossed logo on the upper. Composed of Treadlite technology, the lightweight outsole is for both cushioning and sunburst-pattern traction.

The UGG Tasman II Slipper Black Kids was released in January 2018 at a retail price of $70.

name: Clear Jade
title: Nike Dunk Low Clear Jade
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Clear Jade takes a classic silhouette and dresses it in a two-tone colorway that pops.​
​​
​The Clear Jade Nike Dunk Low-Top features a white leather upper with a perforated toebox for breathability. Clear Jade leather is used for the side panel Nike Swoosh and the overlays surrounding the toebox, eyestays, heel, and collar. The tongue is white with Clear Jade trim, and a white branding patch with Clear Jade Nike branding. The padded sock liner is Clear Jade, and the insole is Clear Jade with white Nike branding. The foam cushion midsole is fully sewn-in and sits atop a rubber cup sole. The outsole is Clear Jade rubber with a traction pattern in concentric circles.​
​
​The detail that our sneaker experts appreciate most about this sports shoe is the white embroidery that makes up the Nike branding on the Clear Jade heel tab. The Nike Dunk Low Clear Jade was released on July 1st, 2023, for a retail price of $110.

name: Moment
title: Puma LaMelo Ball LaFrancé Amour Moment
description:
The Puma LaMelo Ball LaFrancé Amour Moment is an all-over-beige addition to NBA player LaMelo Ball’s signature LaFrancé lifestyle fashion label and Puma.

Incorporating elements from streetwear fashion and sportswear, this sneaker, the Moment Puma LaMelo Ball LaFrancé Amour, boasts an exaggerated silhouette with oversized cotton laces and chunky padding in the collar. The earth-toned Alpine Snow colorway complements the splashes of cream across the upper and lets the overlapping upper design take center stage. The internal EVA midsole stretches the entire length of the shoe, while the rubber cupsole adds stability. LaFrancé lettering in a light-brown hue can be found underfoot, on the tongue, and on the heel’s pull tab. Although the upper is crafted from leather and textile, the inner lining is made from a lightweight synthetic material.

Our experts like the textured outsole, which displays Puma and LaFrancé branding in gothic, graffiti-inspired lettering. The Puma LaMelo Ball LaFrancé Amour Moment was released on July 19, 2024, and sold for $110.

name: Craft Photon Dust
title: Jordan 4 Retro SE Craft Photon Dust
description:
After releasing previously in Nikes Dunk, Air Max 90 and Air Force One models, Jordan Brand is getting the Photon treatment, with the release of the Air Jordan 4 Retro SE Craft Photon Dust.

The Air Jordan 4 SE Phototon Dust is constructed with leather and suede uppers consisting of various shades of grey. Jordan Brand is changing directions with the Air Jordan 4s mesh cage and replacing it with a soft suede and a cracked leather cage wing.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro SE Craft Photon Dust released February 11, 2023, with a retail price of $210.

name: Eggplant (2024)
title: Nike Air Foamposite One Eggplant (2024)
description:
The Nike Air Foamposite One Eggplant 2024 is a bold retro of a classic silhouette, bringing back the iconic eggplant colorway. The striking combination of black and varsity purple across the sneaker's futuristic, molded upper provides a visual impact that's both nostalgic and forward-thinking.

Nike's Foamposite technology has always been about pushing the boundaries of sneaker design, and the Eggplant 2024 edition is no exception. Its seamless, liquid-like upper and distinctive color transition showcase Nike's commitment to innovation and style. The sneaker's durability and comfort are unmatched, making it suitable for both performance and everyday wear. With its rich history and eye-catching design, the Nike Air Foamposite One Eggplant 2024 is a must-have for collectors and new fans alike.

Released on February 29, 2024, and priced at $240, the Nike Air Foamposite One Eggplant 2024 pays homage to its roots. This sneaker has quickly become a sought-after item among enthusiasts, blending history, and style.

name: White Black
title: New Balance 550 White Black
description:
Taking cues from the 1989 New Balance P550, the New Balance 550 White Black features a smooth white leather upper with perforated overlays and black piping. Puffed New Balance logos decorate the quarter panel. At the base, a matching white and black sole completes the design.

The New Balance 550 White Black released in November of 2021 and retailed for $110.

name: Weatherman (2024)
title: Nike KD 4 Weatherman (2024)
description:
The Nike KD 4 Weatherman (2024) brings back one of the most iconic colorways in the KD line, inspired by Kevin Durant's childhood dream of becoming a weatherman. This re-release features a lush green upper with volt, black, and team orange accents, creating a visually striking design. The sneaker's standout feature is the weather pattern graphics on the upper and outsole, which pay homage to Durant's passion for meteorology before he discovered his talent for basketball. This unique design element makes the KD 4 Weatherman a must-have for both sneaker enthusiasts and KD fans.

The KD 4 Weatherman first made waves in 2011 and has remained a favorite among sneakerheads. This 2024 version retains the original's bold aesthetics. The vibrant colorway, highlighted by lush green and volt, captures attention, while the weather-inspired graphics add a layer of storytelling that connects to Durant’s personal history. The black and team orange details further enhance the dynamic look, making this sneaker a standout on and off the court.

Priced at $130, the Nike KD 4 Weatherman (2024) was released on May 21, 2024. This re-release not only celebrates Kevin Durant's journey but also offers a piece of sneaker history with a fresh twist. Whether you're a long-time fan or new to the KD line, this sneaker combines heritage, design, and performance in one compelling package. Make sure to add this iconic model to your collection and step out in style with the KD 4 Weatherman.

name: Origins Waterway
title: Nike Air Max Plus Origins Waterway
description:
The Nike Air Max Plus Origins Waterway applies a serene palm tree pattern to the Air Max Plus to celebrate Sean McDowell, the designer behind this iconic sneaker.​
​
The palm trees represent one of the natural elements that inspired Sean McDowell while he created the Air Max. Although other versions of the Air Max Plus feature sunset colors, the "Origins Waterway" variation boasts a white background with palm trees printed in Waterway and Fiberglass. This gives the sneaker a tonally cooler appearance than other models. The upper is made of a lightweight synthetic mesh with wavy lines winding across the exterior in a silver-like hue. The chunky midsole displays visible Air Max units in the heel and forefoot. In terms of branding, a yellow logo on the heel displays ‘TN AIR’ and the tongue houses a Swoosh and ‘AIR’ lettering.
​​
​Our experts at StockX like the way the lines across the upper mimic wind blowing through the palm trees. The Nike Air Max Plus Origins Waterway was released on October 31st, 2023, and retailed at $190.

name: Wonder White Maroon (Women's)
title: adidas Samba OG Wonder White Maroon (Women's)
description:
The adidas Samba OG Wonder White Maroon (Women's) adds a Wonder White, Putty Grey, and maroon colorway to one of the German footwear manufacturer’s most recognizable silhouettes.

Debuting in the 1950s, the Samba was originally designed as a soccer sneaker but has since become a lifestyle staple. The Wonder White Maroon (Women's) adidas Samba OG features a smooth, Wonder White leather construction with suede accents in Putty Green. The suede detailing on the toebox overlay and the heel mustache gives the sneaker a premium fee without sacrificing its sporty roots. However, what makes this sneaker stand out is the addition of rich maroon detailing. For instance, the leather 3-Stripes logo, the laces, and the classic adidas branding on the tongue come in maroon.

Our experts at StockX like the contrasting stitching, which can be found throughout the sneaker. The women’s size adidas Samba OG Wonder White Maroon (Women's) was released on August 1, 2024, and sold for $100.

name: Travis Scott Olive (Women's)
title: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG SP Travis Scott Olive (Women's)
description:
Travis Scott is back in 2023, following up his previous release of the Air Jordan 1 Retro Low Phantom in 2022, with another Air Jordan 1 Retro Low collaboration. The Jordan 1 Retro low OG SP Travis Scott Olive released exclusively in womens sizing.

The Air Jordan 1 Low OG SP Travis Scott Olive is constructed with white leather and black nubuck uppers. Travis continued to use his signautre reverse style Nike Swoosh, in an olive green colorway. The limited edition sneakers have an aged midsole that sits on top of an olive green outsole.

The women's-exclusive Air Jordan 1 Retro Low OG SP Travis Scott Olive released April 26, 2023, with a retail price of $150.

name: White Black Panda (PS)
title: Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black Panda (PS)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black PS features an entirely white leather upper with black overlays. The touches of black continue to the Swoosh branding, and the vintage basketball shoe is finished off with a padded collar and nylon mesh tongue, a white midsole, and a black outsole and treading. 

The Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black PS was released in March 2021 and originally retailed for $65.

name: Silver Classic Crimson
title: New Balance 1906R Silver Classic Crimson
description:
The New Balance 1906R Silver Classic Crimson is a colorway of the 2000s-inspired running shoe containing cushioning technology.

This version of the New Balance 1906R is made with a lightweight white upper. Synthetic overlays in silver with Classic Crimson accents cross the entire upper, from the toebox to the laces, across the midsole, and back to the heel. The midsole also features a black mesh panel. The New Balance N appears on both sides of the shoe in crimson, white, and silver with N-Lock branding in the middle. The heel is supported by a silver TPU cage that has an NB logo on it, and three red stripes are found above it. The tongue also sports a logo patch.

What we like most about this shoe is the ACTEVA LITE, N-ergy, and ABZORB cushioning in the midsole, sole, and outsole that all work together to make this shoe extra comfortable. The New Balance 1906R Silver Classic Crimson was released on November 16, 2023, for a price of $155.

name: 25th Anniversary
title: Nike Air Max Plus 25th Anniversary
description:
The Nike Air Max Plus 25th Anniversary was released to celebrate the 25th anniversary of the original Nike Air Max Plus. This commemorative sneaker features a color scheme and design that pay tribute to prominent Air Max colorways, including "Palm," "Hyper Blue," "Fireberry," and "Sanguine."

Like other Air Max Plus models, the 25th Anniversary variation boasts a polyurethane midsole with a midfoot shank inspired by the curve of a whale’s tail. The upper is made of breathable mesh, displaying a color gradient that fades from light blue to Varsity Blue to purple to red with a palm pattern. Each color represents one of the famous Air Max colorways. A TPU cage supports the soft upper and mimics the sway of palm trees moving in the breeze.

Our StockX experts like visible Air Max units in the chunky midsole. The Nike Air Max Plus 25th Anniversary was released on November 9, 2023, and retailed at $185.

name: Better Scarlet Cloud White
title: adidas Campus 00s Better Scarlet Cloud White
description:
The adidas Campus 00s Better Scarlet Cloud White is a standalone sneaker that was released by the German sport company.

The Campus 00s Better Scarlet Cloud White has a lace-up design, making them easy to put on and take off. The laces are made from high-quality material, allowing for easy adjustment to ensure that the sneakers fit your feet. The heel is also well-cushioned to support your feet, making them ideal for individuals who stand or walk for long periods. The outsole is made from rubber, and the pattern is designed to provide a good grip on all surfaces.

We think that the standout feature of the adidas Campus 00s Better Scarlet Cloud White sneakers is its classic design that combines Better Scarlet and Cloud White colorways. Additionally, the high-quality suede material used in the upper part of the sneakers makes them durable. The shoe was released on April 26th, 2023 at a retail price of $110.

name: by Salehe Bembury Niagara
title: Crocs Pollex Clog by Salehe Bembury Niagara
description:
The Crocs Pollex Clog by Salehe Bembury Niagara clog features a unique collaboration between Crocs and renowned footwear designer Salehe Bembury. The slide has a unique silhouette that is composed of three of Salehe Bembury’s signature fingerprints combined, available in the Niagara colorway.

The Niagara Salehe Bembury Crocs Pollex Clog showcases a "Niagara" color scheme, drawing inspiration from the Serene Gray tones observed at Niagara Falls. With its distinctive concave ridges, this model offers a breathable design, enhanced by intricate cut-out details, and is completed with the addition of a side strap for added functionality. The neutral color scheme is harmoniously paired with a lightweight foam construction, while the concave ridges serve as a practical water siphoning system. The adjustable heel strap proudly showcases dual branding from both Crocs and Salehe Bembury, featuring embossed logos for a distinctive touch.

What our experts love about Crocs Pollex Clog by Salehe Bembury Niagara is its unique design. This collaboration with Salehe Bembury combines elements inspired by nature with innovative design details to create a unique clog that’s not only visually striking, but also comfortable and practical. The clog debuted for $85 on July 20th, 2023.

name: Mirage V2 (Translucent Outsole)
title: Nike Book 1 Mirage V2 (Translucent Outsole)
description:
The Nike Book 1 Mirage V2 (Translucent Outsole) pays tribute to NBA player Devin Booker through details that represent his life and basketball career.

The insoles come in a vibrant Safety Orange and feature a barcode with numbers that represent the area codes of Phoenix, AZ - where he plays for the Phoenix Suns, and Grand Rapids, MI - his hometown. Booker’s jersey number can also be found on the barcode. The Safety Orange insole contrasts the sneaker’s all-gray base, which features Ashen Slate, Football Gray, and Light Carbon. The upper is made of velvety nubuck with panels of soft textile. Perforations run across the vamp and along the collar, allowing the foot to breathe and adding a style element.

Our experts at StockX like the heel pull tab, which has four loops that fold over each other. The Nike Book 1 Mirage V2 (Translucent Outsole) was released on February 29th, 2024, and retailed at $140.

name: Reverse Panda
title: Nike Dunk Low Jumbo Reverse Panda
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Jumbo Reverse Panda arrives following the classic "Panda" style, with the sneaker achieving a harmonious balance of black and white tones across its low-top silhouette.

The Reverse Panda Nike Dunk Low Jumbo textile base layers sport a predominantly black tone, while the textured leather overlays starkly contrast in Crisp White. These overlays extend to elongated panels on the tongue. The mesh base and padded tongue have a Sleek Black finish, while the leather overlays and Swooshes come to life in bright white. Various accents of contrast stitching in white, including on the standard black laces, add subtle detail. Below, the sole unit undergoes modifications, with added reinforcement at the toe and a distinct traction pattern.

What our experts love about the Nike Dunk Low Jumbo Reverse Panda is its distinctive and innovative design. This sneaker takes the iconic "Panda" color blocking theme and flips it on its head, creating a fresh and captivating twist on a classic. The sneaker debuted for $120 on June 20th, 2023.

name: Bred Toe
title: Jordan 1 Low Bred Toe
description:
The Jordan 1 Low Bred Toe takes cues from the 2018 Air Jordan 1 High Bred Toe with its signature black and red color blocking. The upper is composed of white, black, and red leather, with black and red leather smothering the vamp, Swoosh, and heel while white leather is prominent on the quarter panel. From there, an embroidered Wing logo on the heel and a Jumpman tongue label complete the design.

The Jordan 1 Low Bred Toe released in December of 2021 and retailed for $100.

name: Scarlet Cloud White
title: adidas Gazelle Indoor Scarlet Cloud White
description:
The adidas Gazelle Scarlet Cloud White iconic silhouette makes its entrance with a vibrant red suede upper, featuring a contrasting three-stripes logo, and is perched atop a semi-translucent gum outsole, creating a distinct and eye-catching appearance.

The Scarlet Cloud White adidas Gazelle combines a rich red leather and suede upper with the brand's signature 3-Stripes logo in white, creating a striking contrast. Its design features a contrasting heel counter and a round toe, maintaining the classic Gazelle silhouette. The lace-up closure at the front provides a secure fit, while the tongue with a printed logo and the branded insole offer subtle branding elements. Completing the look is a gum-rubber sole that not only provides traction, but also adds to the sneaker's overall aesthetic appeal.

What our experts love about the adidas Gazelle Scarlet Cloud White is its vintage design. These sneakers pay homage to the iconic Gazelle silhouette from the past, boasting classic elements that have made it a timeless favorite among enthusiasts. The sneaker debuted for $150 on July 15th, 2022.

name: Metallic Silver (Women's)
title: Jordan 1 Mid SE Metallic Silver (Women's)
description:
The Jordan 1 Mid SE Metallic Silver (Women's) is a special edition sneaker that reimagines the Air Jordan 1 Mid silhouette with shiny Metallic Silver overlays and accents.

This mid-top sneaker boasts a white leather construction with tonal stitching and complementary white laces. The mudguard, forefoot, and collar overlays, Swoosh logo, and heel panel are constructed from distressed leather in Metallic Silver. The crinkled texture of the leather makes it look like tin foil and catches the light. Branding details include the Air Jordan Wings logo printed on the collar overlay in white, the Jumpman logo on the tongue tag, and an additional Jumpman logo on the synthetic sockliner.

Our experts at StockX like that the sockliner comes in Wolf Gray instead of white or Metallic Silver because it adds a gentle contrast to the Chrome-themed upper. The women’s sized Jordan 1 Mid SE Metallic Silver (Women's) was released on March 20, 2024, and retailed at $135.

name: Georgia Peach (Women's)
title: Jordan 3 Retro Georgia Peach (Women's)
description:
The Jordan 3 Retro Georgia Peach (Women’s) is a high-top basketball shoe that takes its color inspiration from the colorful fruit.

This version of the Jordan 3 Retro is made with a paneled and textured white leather upper. A white overlay provides support around the bottom, while further overlays in a black and gray elephant skin pattern round out the toebox and the heel. Cosmic Clay orange is prevalent on some of the eyestays, while the Air Jordan Jumpman logo appears on both the heel and the tongue in Cosmic Clay. The same color rounds out the heel above a visible Air unit. A white and gray rubber outsole completes the shoe’s look.

Our favorite thing about this shoe is the Cosmic Clay orange accents, which give the otherwise simple shoe a pop of color. The Jordan 3 Retro Georgia Peach (Women’s) was released on April 23, 2024, for a price of $200.

name: Triple White
title: Nike SB Dunk Low Pro Triple White
description:
The Nike SB Dunk Low Pro Triple White upgrades the SB Dunk Low Pro silhouette with an ultra-clean white colorway and minimalist design.

Channeling basketball shoes from the 1980s, this skateboarding shoe is part of Nike’s Orange Label series, which releases performance-driven, skateboard shop exclusives. From the Swoosh logo to the overlays, the Triple White Nike SB Dunk Low Pro sneaker boasts an all-white leather construction with perforations across the toe box. However, the Orange Label branding on the tongue and insole breaks up the monochromatic color scheme. Padding in the collar and tongue offers support, while the midsole houses a cushioning Zoom Air unit. Finally, durable, white laces wind through the front lace closure system.

Our experts like the hoops pivot circles on the rubber outsole, which increase traction on a variety of urban surfaces, including asphalt and concrete. The Nike SB Dunk Low Pro Triple White was released on July 28, 2024, and sold for $115.

name: Drake NOCTA Total Orange
title: Nike Hot Step 2 Drake NOCTA Total Orange
description:
The Nike Hot Step 2 Drake NOCTA Total Orange is a sneaker designed by Nike and the rapper Drake inspired by the "Turf Trainer" look from the 1990s.

This iteration of the Nike Hot Step 2 comes in a fully orange colorway. The upper is made of orange polyurethane containing raised stripes running from the front to the back. The tongue and laces appear in the same shade of orange. The only deviations from this colorway are the shiny silver blocs on each side above the heel and midsole. These appear around a small fabric section with a small silver Nike Swoosh. "NOCTA" also appears in this section. The heel also contains a patch of silver branding, and there’s a visible Air unit underneath the chunky orange heel. The tongue also contains a logo patch.

Our favorite thing about this shoe is the completely orange and silver build. This design makes the shoes stand out. The Nike Hot Step 2 Drake NOCTA Total Orange was released on April 4, 2024.

name: A Ma Maniére Violet Ore
title: Jordan 4 Retro SP A Ma Maniére Violet Ore
description:
James Whitner’s A Ma Maniére and Jordan Brand partner up for this luxury AJ 4 silhouette. The new Air Jordan 4 A Ma Maniére features a deeply rich Violet Ore and vintage cream tones. Sleek metallic pins, tonal mesh detailing and a quilted interior add luxe detailing throughout the silhouette.

The Air Jordan 4 A Ma Maniére released in November of 2022 and retailed for $225.

name: Wonder White Black (Women's)
title: adidas Handball Spezial Wonder White Black (Women's)
description:
The adidas Handball Spezial Wonder White Black (Women's) applies a two-tone colorway of Wonder White and black to the classic Handball Spezial silhouette.

Originally designed as an indoor court shoe, the Handball Spezial is now a lifestyle sneaker with retro roots. The upper is crafted from premium leather in Wonder White with black details. For example, the 3-Stripes logo on the side panel, the heel tab, the collar, and the tongue come in black. Unlike other models, the "Wonder White Black" iteration features a T-shaped toebox made of soft suede in Magic Beige. Branding details include ‘SPEZIAL’ in metallic gold lettering on the side panel and a Wonder White trefoil on the heel tab.

Something our StockX experts like is the traditional gum rubber outsole. Due to its semi-transparent construction, it reveals the upper and the 3-Stripes beneath the gum. The women’s size adidas Handball Spezial Wonder White Black (Women's) was released on December 29th, 2023, and sold for $110.

name: Resin (2022/2024)
title: adidas Yeezy Slide Resin (2022/2024)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Slide Resin (2022/2024) is the result from a collaboration between American rapper Kanye West´s brand and German sport and lifestyle manufacturer adidas.

The Resin Slide is crafted from injected-molded EVA foam. The one-piece build sandal features a pale green finish throughout the lightly textured exterior. Branding is displayed on a tonal adidas logo debossed on the soft footbed. Underfoot, deep horizontal ridges cut throughout the sandal outsole, resulting in an sawtooth pattern for grip.

The adidas Yeezy Slide Resin (2022/2024) was first released on the 24th of September 2022, and originally had a retail price of $70.

name: SpongeBob SquarePants Patrick Star
title: Crocs Classic Clog SpongeBob SquarePants Patrick Star
description:
The Crocs Classic Clog SpongeBob SquarePants Patrick Star updates the Crocs silhouette with motifs and colors inspired by the animated starfish from the SpongeBob SquarePants universe.

The upper is made of a lightweight and water-friendly material with ventilation ports that increase breathability. The top of the shoe comes in a light pink that mimics Patrick’s skin tone, while the underfoot area features a pattern that matches his shorts. This Croc includes several Patrick-themed Jibbitz charms, including a model of the character, a coconut, a jar of mayonnaise, and a tube of SPF 45 sunscreen. The adjustable ankle strap displays the quote "is mayonnaise an instrument?" while Patrick’s face graces the interior footbed

Our experts at StockX like the light traction pattern underfoot, which helps the shoe grip the ground. The Crocs Classic Clog SpongeBob SquarePants Patrick Star was released on May 22, 2024, and retailed at $70.

name: Seafoam (Women's)
title: Jordan 4 Retro Seafoam (Women's)
description:
Jordan Brand is bringing back the Jordan 4 for the first time in adult sizing, in 2023 with the release of the Jordan 4 Retro Seafoam. The Retro Jordan 4 Seafoams released exclusively in womens sizing.

The Air Jordan 4 Seafoam (W) received the same color-blocking treatment as the Jordan 4 Fire Red, and Jordan 4 Military Blue. The Seafoam Air Jordan 4 features a smooth white leather upper, with a black midsole and heel tab. Seafoam green eyelets, mudguard, sock lining, and tongue and heel logos, add a layer of contrast to the sneaker.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro Seafoam (W) released February 9, 2023, with a retail price of $210.

name: NERF (2024)
title: Nike KD 4 NERF (2024)
description:
The Nike KD 4 NERF 2024 reintroduces one of the most hyped and beloved colorways in the KD line. Originally released in 2011, the NERF colorway features a playful and vibrant mix of concord, bright crimson, black, cool grey, and green strike, drawing inspiration from the nostalgic NERF toys. This re-release brings back the excitement and energy that surrounded its initial launch, making it a must-have for fans of the KD series and sneaker enthusiasts.

The KD 4 is known for its lightweight and responsive design, perfect for dynamic players like Kevin Durant. The Hyperfuse construction provides breathability and durability, while the Adaptive Fit system ensures a snug and secure fit. The bold and colorful design of the NERF colorway adds a fun twist to this performance-driven sneaker, making it stand out both on and off the court.

Released on August 9, 2024, the Nike KD 4 NERF retailed at $150. This concord, bright crimson, black, cool grey, and green strike colorway reaffirms the KD 4’s place in sneaker history. Loved for its unique design and advanced technology, the KD 4 NERF continues to capture the hearts of basketball fans and fashion-forward individuals.

name: Hyper Violet (GS)
title: Jordan 4 Retro Hyper Violet (GS)
description:
The Jordan 4 Retro Hyper Violet (GS) updates the Air Jordan 4 Retro silhouette with a white-on-white base and bold Hyper Violet accents.

This sneaker boasts a white leather upper with layers of tonal panels on the sides. The rubber outside and TPU eyelets provide splashes of Hyper Violet, which complement the Jumpman logos on the tongue and heel. A patch of mesh peeks out from behind the leather panels and adds a contrasting texture to the otherwise smooth upper. The padded mid-cut collar and tongue contribute to the sneaker's bulky appearance; however, the thick midsole completes the chunky aesthetic. Finally, the white midsole houses visible air units that cushion against impact.

Our StockX experts like the incorporation of semi-translucent rubber on the outsole because it gives the Hyper Violet depth of color. The grade school-sized Jordan 4 Retro Hyper Violet (GS) was released on April 26, 2024, and retailed at $150.

name: Onyx
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Onyx
description:
Yeezy expanded their 380 line with a new colorway in the Yeezy Boost 380 Onyx. Unlike 2020’s earlier releases like the Yeezy 380 Mist and Pepper, the Onyx colorway is the first 380 to feature primarily black and dark brown uppers.

The Yeezy 380 Onyx features a black and dark brown camo-print Primeknit upper with a flat black side spot. Similar to past colorways, a dark translucent BOOST sole delivers the ultimate cushioning experience that is primed to keep your feet fresh with style.

The Yeezy Boost 380 Onyx released in November of 2020 for $230.

name: Dark Mocha
title: Jordan 1 Retro High Dark Mocha
description:
Jordan Brand continued their Black Toe design theme in 2020 and released the Jordan 1 High Dark Mocha, now available on StockX. The Dark Mocha 1 was one of the most anticipated releases in 2020 due to its familiar colorblocking that referenced two of the greatest Jordan 1s of all-time, the Jordan 1 Travis Scott and the Jordan 1 Black Toe.

The upper of the Jordan 1 High Dark Mocha features a Sail leather base with black leather surrounding the toe box and Mocha suede on the heel and ankle. A black leather Swoosh, Jordan Wings logo on the ankle, and Nike Air branding on the tongue pays homage to branding that can be found on the original 1985 Jordan 1. A Sail midsole and black outsole complete this Black Toe design.

The Jordan 1 High Dark Mocha released in October of 2020 and retailed for $175.

To shop all Air Jordan 1 shoes, click here.

name: Venice Beach (2024) (GS)
title: Nike Kobe 8 Protro Venice Beach (2024) (GS)
description:
The Nike Kobe 8 Protro Venice Beach (2024) (GS) is a sneaker for grade schoolers, with a design was inspired by the graffiti of Venice Beach.

This iteration of the Nike Kobe 8 Protro features a flexible and breathable mesh upper with a gray base. The upper has a tie-dye effect, featuring bright colors like orange, red, yellow, green, and blue. The Nike Swoosh appears across the outside midsole in gray outlined in yellow, and you can find it once again in yellow under the ankle on the inner side. Blue supports line the heel and run under the forefoot. Kobe’s signature can be found in orange on the lateral heel. On the thin tongue, you will find Kobe’s yellow and gray logo outlined in black.

Our favorite feature of this shoe is the bold color scheme. The combination of these bright colors makes the shoe perfect for summer. The Nike Kobe 8 Protro Venice Beach (2024) (GS) was released on April 13, 2024, for a retail price of $120.

name: Anthracite Smoke Grey
title: Nike P-6000 Anthracite Smoke Grey
description:
The Nike P-6000 Anthracite Smoke Grey harks back to the early 2000s, adding even more sporty lines. Its throwback design combines previous Pegasus models in a comfortable package with a long and proud sporting pedigree.

Taking its cues from the Nike Pegasus 5 and the Pegasus 2002, this trainer has the same textile upper with leather overlays. These are breathable to help cool down your feet. A foam midsole provides both comfort and an elevated, athletic look. The shaded colorway combines shades of gray with stark black. The shoes are winterized so that you can wear them all year round.

We really like this mash-up. The original styling comes through strongly while also clearly bringing an up-to-date edge. The athletic credentials of the shoe are unquestioned, and we really appreciate the small touches, like the reflective Swoosh and other details to help with low-light visibility. The Nike P-6000 Anthracite Smoke Grey was released on 15 October 2024 for $120.

name: Black Royal Blue
title: Jordan 1 Mid Black Royal Blue
description:
The Jordan 1 Mid Black Royal Blue is a mid-top offering of the Jordan 1 in a "Black Royal Blue" colorway.

This Jordan 1 sneaker features a leather upper with a Royal Blue base and black overlays. Royal Blue appears on the ankle collar, perforated toebox, mid panel, the Jumpman logo on the tongue, and the Jordan "Wings" emblem etched on the collar flap. Black features on the eyestays, forefoot panel, laces, tongue, Swooshes, collar flaps, heel, padded mesh lining, and the insoles with Royal Jumpman logos. Rounding out the design is an AJ 1 sole unit with a white midsole and a Royal Blue rubber outsole. 

What our experts particularly love about this sneaker is its classic two-tone color scheme and iconic design, which gives it a timeless and versatile look, ideal for those looking for a blend of heritage and contemporary appeal. The Jordan 1 Mid Black Royal Blue was released on September 25th, 2023, retailing at $125.

name: Thunder (2023) (GS)
title: Jordan 4 Retro Thunder (2023) (GS)
description:
The Air Jordan 4 Retro Thunder (2023) (GS) comes in a black and tour yellow color scheme.

The Retro Thunder Jordan 4 (2023) (GS) features an upper that is a combination of leather and mesh and is constructed in black and yellow accents. The Thunder colorway features yellow accents on the midsole, lacing eyelets, and lining. The heel of the shoe features an Air unit that provides impact protection and responsive cushioning. The rubber outsole provides grip and durability, while the cushioned midsole provides stability and sturdiness. The sneaker's design is completed with the signature Jumpman logo on both the tongue and heel.

The grade-schooler sizing of the Air Jordan 4 Retro Thunder (2023) (GS) was released on May 13, 2023, and was sold for a retail price of $150.

name: Industrial Blue Sashiko
title: Nike Dunk Low Industrial Blue Sashiko
description:
Nike is drawing inspiration from Japan, using traditional Sashiko stitching on the 2023 release of the Nike Dunk Low Industrial Blue Sashiko.

Nikes Dunk Low Industrial Blue Sashiko is constructed using denim uppers that feature white contrast stitching across the blue denim paneling. Traditional Japanese Sashiko stitching designs are sewn into the toe box and heel tab. The Nike Dunk Low Sashiko features white Nike branding on the tongue and insoles.
The Nike Dunk Low Industrial Blue Sashiko released March 9, 2023, with a retail price of $120.

name: All-Star The Future
title: adidas AE 1 All-Star The Future
description:
The adidas AE 1 All-Star is a futuristic sneaker that is part of a collaboration between adidas Basketball and NBA player Anthony Edwards.

The "All-Star" version stands out from other adidas AE 1 models due to the metallic panels that race up the sides. Each panel comes with a honeycomb design that forms a sleek arrow-like shape from the heel to toe. The smooth edges reflect light and contribute to the signature sneaker’s futuristic appearance. As light bounces off the panel, it creates the illusion of movement and produces burgundy, bronze, and iridescent green tones. The textile upper comes in all-black, while a Boost midsole provides lightweight energy return.

Our experts at StockX like the bold adidas branding on the heel, which features the 3-stripes in vibrant neon. Anthony Edward’s branding can also be found on the small tongue logo tag. The adidas AE 1 All-Star was released on February 16th, 2024, and retailed at $120.

name: Anthracite (2023)
title: Nike Air Foamposite One Anthracite (2023)
description:
Enter the realm of futuristic style with the Nike Air Foamposite One Anthracite. This 2023 edition, dressed in an enigmatic Black/Anthracite/Black colorway, represents the pinnacle of sneaker innovation. With its foamposite material, this sneaker offers a seamless blend of durability, comfort, and a distinctly modern aesthetic.

The Anthracite colorway is a muted statement that provides versatility for any outfit. The sneaker's advanced features ensure a snug, comfortable fit, making it a reliable choice for daily wear or special occasions.

Launched on December 12, 2023, at $240, the Nike Air Foamposite One Anthracite is a testament to Nike's commitment to pushing the boundaries of design and functionality. This sneaker is a must-have for those who live at the intersection of technology and trendsetting.

name: Georgia Red Clay
title: adidas AE 1 Georgia Red Clay
description:
The adidas AE 1 Georgia Red Clay is a basketball shoe designed as a collaboration between the brand and American NBA player, Anthony Edwards.

This version of the adidas AE 1 comes in a Red Clay colorway. The textile upper in Preloved Scarlet allows for flexibility and breathability, while the combined BOOST and LightStrike midsole in Red Clay is lightweight and allows for cushioning and extra energy return. This midsole appears in a unique honeycomb design. The heel of the shoe features the adidas logo in black, while you will find Anthony Edwards’ logo in black on the tongue. The rubber outsole sharing the same clay color completes the look and adds grip and traction.

What we like best about this shoe is the unique design of the midsole, which is both stylish and functional. The adidas AE 1 Georgia Red Clay was introduced on April 4, 2024, for a price of $120.

name: UNC University Blue
title: Jordan 5 Retro UNC University Blue
description:
Michael Jordan is paying homage to his alma mater, The University of North Carolina, with the release of the Air Jordan 5 Retro UNC University Blue.

The Jordan 5 UNC comes in the Tar Heels signature University Blue across the uppers and is dressed with University Blue laces, and lace locks. A black midsole with white and University Blue detailing separates the translucent blue outsole from the suede uppers. The sneakers are topped off with a silver reflective 3M tongue with a black jumpman logo.

The Air Jordan 5 Retro UNC University Blue released March 5, 2023, with a retail price of $225.

name: Bred Shadow
title: Jordan 1 Mid Bred Shadow
description:
The Jordan 1 Mid Bred Shadow is a mid-top shoe with a look inspired by the OG Shadow colorway.

This version of the Jordan 1 Mid is made with a full leather upper. The base is black, which adorns most of the shoe except for the perforated toebox, the ankle strap, and the heel, which all appear in a darker gray color. The Nike Swoosh also shows up in gray across both midsoles, and the Air Jordan logo appears stamped in black on the lateral side of the ankle strap. A red Jumpman logo appears on the black tongue, and the sock liner is the same bold red color. A rubber white and red outsole completes the look.

What we like most about the shoe are the pops of red on the outsole, the tongue, and the sock liner. These add bold contrast to the otherwise black and gray design. The Jordan 1 Mid Bred Shadow was released on January 23, 2024, for a retail price of $125.

name: Stone Teal
title: adidas Yeezy 450 Stone Teal
description:
Making a splash on May 31, 2023, the adidas Yeezy 450 Stone Teal are the epitome of innovation and style. These unique sneakers are drenched in the Stone Teal colorway, a hypnotic blend of earthy hues that make the shoe a standout in any setting.

With a design that challenges conventional sneaker architecture, the 450's offer an avant-garde aesthetic highlighted by an intricately woven upper nestled in an eccentric, claw-like sole. The shoes embrace comfort, with the sock-like construction ensuring an effortlessly snug fit. The adidas Yeezy 450 Stone Teal isn't just a shoe; it's a statement piece, guaranteed to turn heads and garner compliments. Let these sneakers elevate your style game, providing a distinctive edge that's unmatched in the sneaker world.

The adidas Yeezy 450 Stone Teal hit the streets on May 31, 2023, carrying a retail price of $210.

name: Barons (GS)
title: Jordan 12 Retro Barons (GS)
description:
The Jordan 12 Retro Barons (GS), in grade school sizes, is a high-top athletic shoe with a black tumbled leather upper featuring radiating quilted stitch lines accented by a gray lizard texture mudguard. Jumpman branding appears on the tongue and heel tab, accented by Jordan and 23 branding. The black and gray midsole features a full-length Zoom Air unit and a carbon fiber plate within.

When American athletic wear brand Nike began collaborating with NBA phenomenon Michael Jordan in the 1980s, the world needed to be made aware of the impact the partnership would create. Decades later, Jordan's brand Jordan 12 was inspired by his time with the Birmingham Barons, the Double-A league affiliate of Chicago’s White Sox. Michael Jordan played for the Barons during their 1994 season.

Our experts feel that the best feature of the Jordan 12 Retro is its branding, which is blended strategically throughout the shoe. The Jordan 12 Retro Barons (GS) was released on September 28, 2024, and retailed for $150.

name: Atmosphere Grey
title: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG Atmosphere Grey
description:
The Jordan 1 Retro Low OG Atmosphere Grey is a low-cut basketball-inspired sneaker that features a minimalistic design. It is constructed using premium materials, including a mixture of genuine leather and synthetic material.

The upper of the Air Jordan 1 Retro Low OG Atmosphere Grey is designed with a combination of layered leather and synthetic panels, providing a supportive and comfortable fit. The sole unit of the shoe features an encapsulated Air cushioning unit, which offers excellent shock absorption and responsiveness. The outsole is made from a high-quality rubber material that provides traction on a variety of surfaces. It also features a classic pivot point design, which allows for smooth and fluid movement on the court.

We believe that the standout feature of the Jordan 1 Retro Low OG Atmosphere Gray is its sleek and minimalistic design. It has a Sail and Atmosphere Grey colorway with the Nike Swooshes on both sides. The Jordan 1 Retro Low OG Atmosphere Grey was released on August 25th, 2023, at a retail price of $140.

Please note, the midsole on the Jordan 1 Retro Low OG Atmosphere Grey come 'pre-aged' directly from the manufacturer.

name: Metropolis Jasper Green
title: ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Metropolis Jasper Green
description:
The ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Metropolis Jasper Green draws elements from heritage models to create a technical sneaker with shiny metallic-silver accents and splashes of bright Jasper Green.

The mesh construction of the Metropolis Jasper Green ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 comes in Metropolis, a dark-gray hue that serves as a subtle backdrop for the leather overlays in metallic silver. Hits of Jasper Green cover the branding details on the mesh tongue and heel and add pops of color on the otherwise white midsole. Gel technology in the heel provides responsive cushioning, while the Trusstic system in the arch increases stability and reduces twisting motions. Finally, the sock liner was made using a dyeing method that reduces water consumption by up to 33 percent.

Our experts at StockX like that even though this version of the Gel-Kayano wasn’t designed by Toshikazu Kayano, it retains design elements drawn from the early 2000s. The ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Metropolis Jasper Green was released on June 3, 2024, and sold for $150.

name: Frozen Moments (Women's)
title: Jordan 4 Retro Frozen Moments (Women's)
description:
The Jordan 4 Retro Frozen Moments made its debut on August 26, 2023. Cementing itself as a must-have, this iteration of the Jordan legacy showcased a balanced new design palette.

Crafted with precision, the sneaker flashes a blend of light iron ore, sail-neutral grey, black, and metallic silver, bringing a balanced and understated aesthetic to the iconic Jordan 4 silhouette. The defining feature is its meticulous craftsmanship and the fusion of these nuanced colors with suede and leather overlays on the upper. The iconic wings on the side panel boast a flashy metallic silver hue that make the sneaker pop.

With a lineage known for excellence and style, the Jordan 4 Retro Frozen Moments dropped at a retail price of $210.

name: Metallic Burgundy
title: Jordan 1 Retro High '85 OG Metallic Burgundy
description:
The Jordan 1 Retro High '85 OG Metallic Burgundy is a relaunch of one of the rarest Air Jordan 1 models, a shoe originally released in 1985 as part of the Metallic Series.

The 2024 iteration of the Air Jordan 1 Retro High Metallic Burgundy features an upper made of premium leather in white with tonal leather overlays. Metallic Burgundy details can be found on the area around the collar, the Swoosh logos, and the Jordan Wings logo. In addition, the tongue tag displays ‘NIKE AIR’ in chunky Metallic Burgundy letters. The rubber outsole also features Metallic Burgundy and Nike’s signature pivot traction pattern. While perforations across the vamp allow the foot to breathe, the traditional front lace closure provides a secure fit.

Our experts at StockX like the contrast between the white base and Metallic Burgundy details. The Jordan 1 Retro High '85 OG Metallic Burgundy was released on June 22nd, 2024, and retailed at $180.

name: KoRn Follow The Leader
title: adidas Campus 2 KoRn Follow The Leader
description:
The adidas Campus 2 KoRn Follow The Leader is part of a collaboration between adidas and Korn, an American nu metal band. It pays homage to Korn's album "Follow The Leader," which was released in 1998.

This special-edition sneaker boasts a low-top silhouette and a shaggy suede upper. While Carbon makes up the base, Footwear White and Off-White provide accents. The leather heel tab, the "adidas" embroidery on the tongue, and the serrated 3-stripes logo on the side panel come in Footwear White, while the midsole displays Off-White. Branding details include "adidas" on the underside of the tongue, "KORN" on the heel, and "Campus" on the outer side panel in Korn’s signature font.

Our experts like the addition of Off-White on the midsole because it gives the sneaker a worn-in, vintage feel. The adidas Campus 2 KoRn Follow The Leader was released on May 15, 2024, and retailed at $150.

name: Year of the Dragon
title: Nike Ja 1 Year of the Dragon
description:
Celebrating the Chinese New Year, the Nike Ja 1 Year of the Dragon is a stylish homage to cultural heritage and basketball performance. The White, Aquarius Blue, Glacier Blue, and Metallic Gold colorway makes a striking statement, designed to captivate a dynamic, energetic audience.

The sneaker's design focuses on agility and responsiveness, suited for dynamic play. It features a lightweight yet durable construction, with cushioning that offers both comfort and support. The Year of the Dragon edition of the Nike Ja 1 is not just a sports shoe; it's a symbol of power and prosperity, resonating with its wearers' aspirations.

Launched on January 3, 2024, the Nike Ja 1 Year of the Dragon, priced at $140, has garnered attention for its unique design and cultural significance, making it a sought-after piece in sneaker collections.

name: Light Blue
title: adidas Handball Spezial Light Blue
description: The adidas Handball Spezial Light Blue is a classic sneaker that combines style and functionality. The shoe features a light blue suede upper with white leather accents and a gum sole. The iconic adidas stripes are present on the sides, while the brand's logo is embossed on the heel. The Handball Spezial is designed for indoor sports, with a non-marking rubber outsole that provides excellent grip on the court. The shoe also features a cushioned insole for added comfort. Released on February 18, 2019, the Handball Spezial Light Blue retails for $100. With its timeless design and high-quality materials, this sneaker is a must-have for any adidas fan or sports enthusiast.

name: The Powerpuff Girls Bubbles
title: Nike SB Dunk Low The Powerpuff Girls Bubbles
description:
The Nike SB Dunk Low The Powerpuff Girls Bubbles edition brings a playful and vibrant twist to the iconic Dunk Low silhouette. Inspired by the cartoon show, this Dunk Low is a perfect representation of sugar, spice, and everything nice, channeling the charm and energy of Bubbles. ​
​​
​Featuring the colorway Blue Chill/​Deep Royal Blue, this sneaker is a visual treat, capturing the essence of Bubbles' character. Each design element is thoughtfully crafted to reflect the cheerful and spirited nature of one of the beloved Powerpuff Girls. ​
​​
​Released on December 14 at skate shops and on December 15 on SNKRS, the Nike SB Dunk Low The Powerpuff Girls Bubbles was priced at $135. This sneaker is a must-have for fans of the series and sneaker collectors alike, offering a unique blend of nostalgia and style.

name: Alexis Sablone Chameleon
title: Nike SB Dunk Low Alexis Sablone Chameleon
description:
The Nike SB Dunk Low Alexis Sablone Chameleon is a creative collaboration between Nike SB and pro skateboarder, Alexis Sablone. Known for her unique style both on and off the board, Sablone draws inspiration from chameleons for this standout design. The sneaker features an oil green, desert moss, and white colorway with chameleon-like color-shifting panels and scale-textured overlays that make it truly one-of-a-kind. The playful design is a nod to the ever-evolving world of skateboarding and style.

The Nike SB Dunk has been a cultural icon since its debut in the early 2000s, blending performance features with a design that has transcended the skate world. This latest iteration continues that legacy, featuring Sablone’s logo on the heel and interior of the sneaker. The green scale overlays reveal a purple layer underneath, adding a dynamic touch that changes as the shoes wear in. This mix of artistry, functionality, and personal expression makes the Alexis Sablone Chameleon Dunk an instant classic that appeals to skaters and sneaker enthusiasts alike.

Released on August 22, 2024, the Nike SB Dunk Low Alexis Sablone Chameleon retailed at $135. Its oil green, desert moss, and white colorway, combined with the unique wear-and-reveal feature, ensures this sneaker is more than just a stylish piece—it's a statement. Whether you’re skating or simply making a fashion statement, this collaboration captures the essence of both skate culture and Sablone’s creative spirit.

name: Classic Green
title: Nike SB Dunk Low Classic Green
description:
Dressed in Classic Green, black, and white, this Nike SB Dunk Low Classic Green also features the popular Air Jordan 1’s "Black Toe" color blocking. The Nike SB Dunk Low Classic Green features a white leather upper with black overlays and Swooshes completed with Classic Green in the rear, laces, and tongue branding. The Nike SB Dunk Low Classic Green gets an extra chunky tongue with the Nike SB tag fixed at the top. Beneath the feet, a white midsole offers cushioning, and a matching green rubber outsole provides traction.

The Nike SB Dunk Low Classic Green was released in June 2021 and retailed for $110.

name: Sanddrift Light Armory Blue
title: Nike Dunk Low Sanddrift Light Armory Blue
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Sanddrift Light Armory Blue is a low-top sneaker that finds inspiration in the basketball shoes of the 1980s. However, the colorway of Coconut Milk, Light Armory Blue, Sanddrift, Sesame, and Hemp gives the sneaker a modern upgrade.

While the base is made of calf suede in Coconut Milk, the contrasting suede overlays come in three tan tones. These warm hues serve as a backdrop for the Armory Blue branding details. For example, Swooshes on the side panels, ‘NIKE’ on the woven tongue logo tag, and ‘NIKE’ stitched across the heel counter all come in Armory Blue. In addition, the outsole is made of rubber with Nike’s signature pivot hoop traction pattern in Medium Brown.
