Our experts at StockX like the addition of Armory Blue laces, a feature that tonally ties the shoe together. The Nike Dunk Low Sanddrift Light Armory Blue was released on February 2nd, 2023, and retailed at $135.

name: Black Cement (2024) (GS)
title: Jordan 3 Retro Black Cement (2024) (GS)
description:
The Jordan 3 Retro Black Cement (2024) (GS) is a relaunch of Tinker Hatfield’s iconic sneaker with gray elephant-print detailing and an eye-catching colorway of black, Fire Red, Cement Grey, and Sail.

Originally released in 1988 and last seen in 2013, the Black Cement (2024) (GS) Jordan 3 Retro boasts a tumbled leather upper in black with tonal stitching. Elephant print decorates the leather overlays at the forefoot and heel, while perforations add texture to the gray leather around the collar. Pops of Fire Red stand out on the Jumpman logo, the first three eyelets, the bottom of the shoe, and the underside of the tongue. Padding in the tongue and collar completes the look and protects the ankle.

Our experts like the tonal contrast provided by the raised, white Nike Air logo on the heel. The grade school-sized Jordan 3 Retro Black Cement (2024) (GS) was released on November 23, 2024, and sold for $150.

name: All Night
title: Nike Air Max Dn All Night
description:
The Nike Air Max Dn All Night is a shoe containing the all new Dynamic Air Max unit in the heel with a few pops of color in the design.

This iteration of the Nike Air Max Dn features a mostly black colorway. The breathable textile upper is accented with Dark Smoke Gray dashes, giving it a kind of haptic pattern. The bottom of the upper is supported with black outlines, while the Nike Swoosh shows up in the arches of the foot in a bright crimson color. Air Max logos can be seen both on the tongue and on the heel. The logo on the heel is situated within a shiny oval that fades from dark blue to dark pink. The Dynamic Air units visible in the heel also take on a pink color, adding another pop of vibrance to the otherwise all-black design.

Our favorite feature of this shoe is the contrast between the black and pink/crimson that appears on the signature branding elements. The Nike Air Max Dn All Night was first released on March 26, 2024, for a retail price of $160.

name: Pink Glow (Women's)
title: adidas Gazelle Bold Pink Glow (Women's)
description:
The adidas Gazelle Bold Pink Glow W, features 3 major colors: pink glow, victory blue, and gum.
​
This women’s (W) sneaker has a suede upper that comes in a pink hue with the brand´s 3-Stripes displayed on both sides. The outsole of this shoe is made of semi-transparent rubber and it also features a synthetic lining throughout. A pink lace closure and a "Gazelle" inscription in a metallic shade complete the look of this pair.
​
The adidas Gazelle Bold Pink Glow W was made available for purchase on December 14th, 2022, at a release price of $120.

name: Gift of Mamba
title: Nike Kobe 4 Protro Gift of Mamba
description:
The Nike Kobe 4 Protro Gift of Mamba emerges in a striking Black/Black-University Gold colorway, showcasing a perfect blend of luxury and performance. The upper is crafted from light black suede, complemented by a faux snakeskin pattern on the mudguard, collar, and Swoosh, adding a touch of elegance and edge.

The sneaker's design is a tribute to the late Kobe Bryant, featuring his iconic logo and signature in university gold for a regal effect. The heel counter proudly displays the number "24," debossed, symbolizing Kobe's legacy. The university gold accents stand out against the black suede, creating a visually impactful design.

The Nike Kobe 4 Protro Gift of Mamba released on December 27, 2023, and retailed for $180, making it a must-have for both sneaker collectors and Kobe fans.

name: Cream White Preloved Brown
title: adidas Samba OG Cream White Preloved Brown
description:
The adidas Samba OG Cream White Preloved Brown dresses the Samba OG in a vintage-inspired colorway with hues reminiscent of hardwood floors and clean varsity lettering.

Joining the ranks of adidas Samba OG models with neutral colorways, the Cream White Preloved Brown version features an upper crafted from smooth leather, textile, and suede. Cream White serves as the base, while Preloved Brown accents highlight the heel mustache and the serrated 3-Stripes logo. The suede eyelets and toe box overlay come in Wonder White, providing a textural contrast. Completing the design, the gum rubber outsole offers a grippy feel, while the fabric lining keeps the foot comfortable.

Our experts like the metallic silver adidas branding on the tongue and the "SAMBA" lettering on the outside panel. This color choice gives the sneaker a contemporary touch without detracting from the retro aesthetic. The adidas Samba OG Cream White Preloved Brown was released on June 1, 2024, and sold for $100.

name: Reverse Panda
title: Nike Dunk Low Reverse Panda
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Reverse Panda features the Nike Swoosh logo in black on the tongue and also on the heel padding behind the ankle.

The Nike Dunk Low Reverse Panda has a clean white color throughout, including the sole, with contrasting touches of black. The shoe also features a lace-up closure style with black laces. The Nike Swoosh is found on both sides, also in black, and these meet behind the ankle and below the white heel padding.

The Nike Dunk Low Reverse Panda first debuted in Asia in June, 2022, and then in the UK and Europe in July of 2022 at a retail price of $100.

name: Core Black Cloud White Gold
title: adidas Superstar Core Black Cloud White Gold
description:
The adidas Superstar Core Black Cloud White Gold was created with a slip-on design.

This sneaker, in a black and white color scheme, features a "shell" design construction with a heel pull tab. It also has branding throughout, including adidas' serrated 3-Stripes detail and the Superstar box logo. On the tongue, there are golden details, too. Its elastane upper offers a snug fit, and the EVA outsole features deep flex grooves. The interior features an OrthoLite sock liner. The rubber outsole provides grip.

The adidas Superstar Core Black Cloud White Gold was released on February 1, 2022, at a retail price of $90.

name: Black
title: Maison Mihara Yasuhiro Peterson 23 OG Sole Canvas Low Black
description:
The Maison Mihara Yasuhiro Peterson 23 OG Sole Canvas Low Black takes a traditional lifestyle sneaker and infuses it with a warped sense of iconic style that will turn heads everywhere you go.

This classic Low-Top is constructed from black canvas and sports white deco stitching across the upper, at the collar, eye stays, heel, and midfoot. A sturdy white rubber toe cap surrounded by black foxing adds extra support and protection, and it matches the flat white laces that thread through the silver metal eyelids. MMY branding graces the tongue tag as well as the tonal license plate on the bumper. The black rubber outsole features a crosshatch diamond pattern of grooves that provides impact absorption, flexibility, and traction.

The stand-out feature of this sneaker is its chunky, bumpy, undulating white platform foam midsole that designer Mihara created by first molding it out of clay. The Maison Mihara Yasuhiro Peterson 23 OG Sole Canvas Low Black was released on August 1, 2023, for a retail price of $315.
model: Maison Mihara Yasuhiro Peterson 23 OG Sole Canvas Low

name: Red Thunder
title: Jordan 4 Retro Red Thunder
description:
Following similar color blocking as the Air Jordan 4 Thunder, the Air Jordan 4 Red Thunder features an all-black Durabuck upper with red netted underlays and eyelets. On the tongue, a signature Air Jordan Flight patch is stitched. A vibrant red midsole and Jumpman heel tab complete the retro design.

The Air Jordan 4 Red Thunder releases in January of 2022 and retails for $190.

name: Steel Grey Orca
title: New Balance 2002R Steel Grey Orca
description:
The New Balance 2002R Steel Grey Orca is an iteration of the New Balance 2002R running sneaker in a ‘Steel Grey Orca’ colorway.

This sneaker’s upper is made of a Grey mesh base cut out by Steel and Lead Grey leather overlays on the toe box. Lead Grey accents also appear on the upper eyelets, quarter panel, and the upper part of the tongue. The top overlay, which dominates the upper, features a premium Suede build in a Steel Grey tone highlighted by a Light Grey ‘N’ logo with a White outline and ‘2002R’ branding on the lateral ankle. A White Absorb midsole and a Black N-ergy outsole round out the design.

The New Balance 2002R Steel Grey Orca White was made available on October 21st, 2022, retailing at $140.

name: Palomino
title: Jordan 3 Retro Palomino
description:
Redefining classic style with a fresh color twist, the Jordan 3 Retro Palomino dropped on July 29, 2023. The Retro Palomino shows off the enduring appeal of the Jordan line.

It exhibits a superior blend of light Orewood Brown, metallic gold, light British Tan, and Palomino. This mix gives the sneaker an earthy touch, amped up with the luxury of metallic gold accents. The iconic silhouette stays true to the Jordan 3 model but carries a distinctive visual twist.

The Jordan 3 Retro Palomino, a combination of retro charm and forward-looking design, was released on July 29, 2023, with a retail price of $200.

name: Tuna Blue
title: ASICS Gel-1130 Tuna Blue
description:
The ASICS Gel-1130 Tuna Blue combines elements from decades of innovative ASICS designs. This technical running sneaker draws inspiration from the ninth version of the GEL-1000 and stability running shoes from the early 2000s, including the Gel-Kayano 14.

At the Tuna Blue ASICS Gel-1130, instead of genuine leather, synthetic leather makes up the overlays layered across the white mesh upper. This gives the sneaker a contemporary feel and allows the metallic silver hues to catch the light. The overlays boast a deep Tuna Blue hue with black outlines, while the chunky white midsole matches the color of the mesh base. Padding around the thick collar protects the ankle and the front lace closure system secures the shoe.

Our StockX experts appreciate the GEL technology in the midsole, which provides responsive cushioning and adds a technical upgrade to this retro runner. The ASICS Gel-1130 Tuna Blue was released on May 1, 2024, and sold for $100.

name: Black White Grey
title: Nike Air Max Correlate Black White Grey
description:
The Nike Air Max Correlate Black White Grey is a comfortable yet flexible shoe that provides all of the best athletic qualities while still being stylish.

The Nike Air Max Correlate Black White Grey provides an ample amount of heel support and has a particularly cushioned sole. Splashes of pink and green appear in contrast to the black, white, and grey pattern that makes up a majority of the shoe. The upper part of the Nike Air Max Correlate Black White Grey molds to the foot, helping to provide support and protection while still remaining comfortable.

First released in May 2022 at a starting price of $155.

name: White Pure Silver
title: ASICS Gel-1130 White Pure Silver
description:
The ASICS Gel-1130 White Pure Silver is a performance running sneaker that finds inspiration in the ninth version of the Gel-1000 and the GEL-KAYANO.

Synthetic overlays in black and metallic Pure Silver replace traditional leather and give the sneaker a contemporary look. The sneaker boasts a mesh upper in white with a loose weave. This loose weave allows the foot to breathe and is lightweight. The bulky midsole features Gel technology in the heel, which delivers responsive cushioning. ASICS, in black lettering, runs diagonally down the tongue and is one of the few visible branding elements. Like other ASICS Gel-1130 models, the White Pure Silver iteration features an adjustable lace closure.

Our experts at StockX like the way the black details on the overlays complement the black tread on the rubber outsole. The ASICS Gel-1130 White Pure Silver was released on February 15, 2024, and retailed at $95.

name: Summit White Baroque Brown
title: Nike Dunk Low Next Nature Summit White Baroque Brown
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Next Nature Summit White Baroque Brown is part of the Next Nature series, which means the sneaker is crafted from at least 20 percent recycled materials.

This sneaker draws comparisons to the Air Jordan 1 Low Reverse Mocha due to the similar colorway and color blocking, as well as the low-top silhouette. However, the Summit White Baroque Brown Nike Dunk Low Next Nature incorporates richer hues, including a Baroque Brown base, Summit White on the overlays, and khaki on the Swoosh and the heel tab. The upper is crafted from leather with a grainy texture, while the overlays feature smooth synthetic leather. Finally, the cushioned midsole boasts a Sail hue that gives it an aged finish.

Our experts like the grippy rubber outsole, which comes in Baroque Brown and features a subtle speckled pattern. The Nike Dunk Low Next Nature Summit White Baroque Brown was released on June 11, 2024, and sold for $125.

name: Off White
title: New Balance 2002R Off White
description:
The New Balance 2002R Off White is a running shoe that comes in a Beige Off White colorway.

This sneaker features an upper constructed with mesh, leather and suede with grey tones around the collar. Other details include jersey lining, a padded tongue and collar, the "N" logo on the sides, and the "2002R" on the lateral just below the collar. Rounding out the design is a textured ACTEVA LITE rubber midsole that utilizes the ABZORB cushioning technology and a black treaded N-ergy rubber outsole.

The New Balance 2002R Off White was released on September 2nd, 2022, retailing at $120.

name: White Shark Skin
title: ASICS Gel-1130 White Shark Skin
description:
The ASICS Gel-1130 White Shark Skin is a stability running shoe with design details that mimic the pattern of shark skin.

Finding inspiration in the Gel-KAYANO 14 and other sneakers in the Gel-1000 catalog, the Gel-1130 White Shark Skin boasts a breathable mesh upper. Unlike previous iterations, this model incorporates synthetic leather instead of genuine leather in the overlays. When light hits the synthetic overlays, it produces a silvery sheen that is reminiscent of shark skin. Splashes of silver also add to the sneaker’s open ocean aesthetic. Other notable elements include gel technology in the heel, which provides responsive cushioning and protects against impact on hard materials such as pavement. The sneaker also houses ASICS’ signature Trusstic support system, which improves stability and can be found in many 2000s running shoes.

Our StockX experts like the dope-dyeing of the inner lining. This dyeing technique provides lasting color and reduces carbon emissions. The ASICS Gel-1130 White Shark Skin was released on January 1st, 2024, and retailed at $95.

name: Playoffs Bred (2019)
title: Jordan 11 Retro Playoffs Bred (2019)
description:
Please Note: Both plastic shoe trees are required for verification.
Jordan Brand brings back a monument of Jordan hype with the Air Jordan 11 Retro Playoffs Bred, now available on StockX. These sneakers represent MJ’s comeback from retirement to win his fourth title with the Chicago Bulls and the 1996 Finals MVP. This is the fourth time this colorway has been retroed since it’s original debut.

This Jordan 11 features a black upper with shiny patent leather overlays and red detailing. A red translucent outsole, white midsole, and "23" insignia on the heel completes the design. These sneakers released in November of 2019 and retailed for $220.

name: Reverse Metallic
title: Jordan 5 Retro Reverse Metallic
description:
If you're looking for a striking-looking trainer with top-class credentials, the Jordan 5 Retro Reverse Metallic is right up there. It's an almost surrealistic take on the traditional high-top basketball shoe, with ultra-modern contours and high-tech accents.

This is a fascinating update on the Air Jordan 5. It has an ice white upper punctuated with black panels on the sole and collar. The leather upper has a synthetic mesh cut-out panel for breathability. The collar has a high front, crested by a long tongue, and an ultra-low back. The midsole has jagged white highlighting that creates a dramatic effect.

Our experts are very taken by this design. It's aggressive but also very familiar at the same time. It screams aggressive hoop action and makes one want to get out and play. The transparent air capsule in the heel adds the perfect high-performance touch. The Jordan 5 Retro Reverse Metallic was released on 7 December 2024, priced at $200 retail.

name: Stone Salt
title: adidas Yeezy 500 Stone Salt
description:
The adidas Yeezy 500 Stone Salt hails from the branch of adidas that used to work in collaboration with Kanye West. This singular-looking sneaker sports the Yeezy vibe, with comfort and innovation working hand in glove.

The Stone Salt adidas Yeezy 500 features an upper base of lightweight, breathable gray mesh that is padded at the collar for enhanced comfort. Overlays of premium leather and cow suede undulate across the upper in shades ranging from beige to gray. A mudguard crafted from abrasion-resistant beige-gray rubber adds both durability and aesthetic uniqueness to this upper. The adiPrene+ midsole is structured in light gray pods for ultimate cushioning and shock absorption. Completing the form and function of this shoe is a gray rubber abstract outsole that enhances comfort while offering traction.

The aspect of this shoe that we enjoy the most is the addition of Ortholite insoles. That extra touch of underfoot attention emphasizes how indulgently comfortable these sneakers are. The adidas Yeezy 500 Stone Salt was released on March 11, 2024, for $210 retail.

name: Mauve
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Mauve
description:
The Jordan 1 Retro High OG Mauve is part of Nike’s Holiday 2023 Retro Footwear line-up. Like many shoes in this collection, the Jordan 1 Retro High OG in Mauve includes elements inspired by archival footwear with a modern twist.

What sets this high-top sneaker apart from others is the straightforward White and Sky J Mauve colorway. While the base is all white, the leather overlays, synthetic inner liner, laces, Swoosh logos, and ‘NIKE AIR’ branding on the tongue feature Sky J Mauve. Similarly, the rubber outsole features Sky J Mauve, contrasting the white midsole and stitching.

What do our StockX experts love about this sneaker? The Wings detailing on the lateral ankle comes in White, while the same detailing on other Jordan 1 Retro High OG sneakers comes in Black. The Jordan 1 Retro High OG Mauve was released on October 14, 2023, and retailed at $180.

name: University Blue Black
title: Jordan 1 Mid University Blue Black
description:
The Jordan 1 Mid University Blue Black dresses a classic silhouette in an eye-catching dual chromatic colorway relieved by a hit of white on the midsole, thus creating a style that's ready for action.

The University Blue Black Air Jordan 1 Mid-Top features an upper with a smooth black leather base sporting perforations in the toe box for enhanced breathability. University Blue leather covers the toe cap, vamp, eye stays, heel, and collar, as well as composing the quarter panel Nike Swoosh. Black laces crisscross over a blue nylon tongue featuring a black Jumpman logo, and the black sock liner and black insole with a blue Jumpman logo continue the colorway. A black Wings logo stamped on the blue-collar overlay completes the gorgeous aesthetic of this upper.

What our sneaker experts appreciate most about this shoe is the white rubber midsole encapsulating Air supported beneath by a blue rubber outsole with the classic Jordan traction pattern for multi-directional grip. The Jordan 1 Mid University Blue Black was released on July 14th, 2023, for $125 retail.

name: Naruto Itachi
title: Crocs Classic Clog Naruto Itachi
description:
The Crocs Classic Clog Naruto Itachi Blue Red pays homage to Itachi Uchiha, a ninja character in the Naruto manga and anime series created by Masashi Kishimoto.

The clog features a dark blue base with cloud-like motifs in red across the upper. It also includes several Jibbitz charms, including a black ninja throwing star and a miniature of the iconic character. Like other Classic Crocs models, this version is made from croslite resin, which is lightweight and durable. Ventilation ports along the sides allow the foot to breathe, while the pivoting heel strap supports a secure fit. A metal tab across the top of the clog displays an emblem associated with Itachi Uchiha.

Our StockX experts like the outsole's traction pattern because it provides grip on various surfaces. The Crocs Classic Clog Naruto Itachi Blue Red was released on June 10, 2024, and retailed for $70.

name: Championship Red
title: Nike Dunk Low Championship Red
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Championship Red features a University Red leather upper with white leather overlays and Swooshes. A matching sole and woven tongue label adds the finishing touches to this retro design.

The Nike Dunk Low Championship Red released in September of 2021 and retailed for $100.

name: Cactus Plant Flea Market White (2024)
title: Nike Air Force 1 Low Cactus Plant Flea Market White (2024)
description:
The Nike Air Force 1 Low Cactus Plant Flea Market White (2024) is one of Cactus Plant Flea Market (CPFM)’s distinctive reinterpretations of the classic Air Force 1 Low. It features an all-white construction with quirky detailing that blends Nike and CPFM’s house codes.

Although the sneaker boasts a white-on-white color scheme, the colorway actually includes white and Light Bone, which is slightly warmer. The upper is crafted from smooth and texturized leather, creating a subtle contrast. The right shoe features "AIR" in bubble letters on the outer side panel, while "SUNSHINE" wraps around both sides of the left shoe. The signature Swoosh logo can be found behind the bubble lettering and over the leather overlays. Nike branding decorates the heel tab and the tongue’s logo tag.

Our experts like light padding around the collar, which bulks up the shoe’s silhouette. The Nike Air Force 1 Low Cactus Plant Flea Market White (2024) was released on May 7, 2024, and retailed at $150.

name: Drake Black
title: Nike NOCTA Glide Drake Black
description:
The Nike NOCTA Glide Drake Black is a special edition sneaker released as part of a collaborative effort between Nike and Canadian rapper and musician Drake that was included in the NOCTA collection.

The Nike NOCTA Glide features a black and white color scheme with a significant part of the upper appearing in black while the midsole is white and the outsole is translucent grey with a touch of orange on the underfoot. It also has carbon-inspired mudguards running across both side panels and a white chunky midsole providing reinforcement on the shoe. Some of the branding details on the shoe include Nike branding on the eyestays and the NOCTA trident logo and glossy NOCTA badges on the tongue.

What our experts love about the Nike NOCTA Glide Drake Black is the contemporary design. The carbon-inspired mudguards add a unique style to the shoes while the pods on the midsole offer structural support. The shoes were initially released at the retail price of $160 on the 29th of June, 2023.

name: Supreme Black
title: Nike SB Darwin Low Supreme Black
description:
The Nike SB Darwin Low Supreme Black is a low-top sneaker that’s part of a Spring 2024 collaboration between Nike Skateboarding and Supreme, a streetwear label known for its bold branding and contributions to skater fashion.

Celebrating the 30th anniversary of the Air Darwin from 1994, the Nike SB Darwin Low Supreme Black boasts an all-black construction with splashes of white on the branding details. The Swoosh on the heel, the small "SUPREME" tag on the side panel, the Swoosh on the toe, and the tongue’s logo tag feature white accents. The upper is made of canvas for durability, while the midsole is crafted from lightweight Phylon foam and houses an air unit.

Our experts like that this sneaker pays homage to the Air Darwin, the first sneaker to display a backward Swoosh, by printing a backward Swoosh on the heel. The Nike SB Darwin Low Supreme Black originally hit the market on May 2, 2024, and retailed at $118.

name: Summit White Midnight Navy
title: Nike Dunk Low Summit White Midnight Navy
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Summit White Midnight Navy is a cultural icon sneaker designed by Peter Moore. 

The Nike Dunk Low leather upper has a base of Summit White with Midnight Navy overlays that envelop the heel and toe. A grey Nike Swoosh can be seen on the side, and the woven tongue tag and heel tab display Nike branding in navy blue. The low-top design rests on a standard Nike rubber cupsole with white sidewalls and a black rubber outsole.

The Nike Dunk Low Summit White Midnight Navy was released on 1st February 2023, retailing at $110.

name: White Sail Vast Grey
title: Nike P-6000 White Sail Vast Grey
description:
The Nike P-6000 White Sail Vast Grey reimagines the original Nike P-6000 released in the 00s with a neutral colorway of white, Sail, Vast Grey, and Light Bone.

The combination of vertical and horizontal overlays across the breathable mesh upper is a throwback to the original sneaker, while the layers of Sail, Light Bone, and Vast Grey add a contemporary upgrade. The overlays help the upper fit snugly against the foot, and the front lace system provides added security. The laces come in a crisp white that matches the tone on the mesh tongue and the base.

Our StockX experts like the subtle branding, including a Swoosh in Light Bone with an embroidered border along the side panel. In addition, the tongue displays a leather tag with NIKE, and P-6000 is printed on the side panel. The Nike P-6000 White Sail Vast Grey was first released on March 29, 2024, and then retailed at $120.

name: Pink Foam (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Pink Foam (Women's)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Pink Foam (Women's), available in women’s sizes, is a low-top basketball-style sneaker featuring a leather upper in Pink Foam with White Overlays. The Swoosh and heel tab accent the colorway in Playful Pink and coordinate with the tongue accent and outsole. Nike branding appears on the tongue, and a white midsole completes the aesthetic.

The Nike Dunk originated in the 1980s as an initiative that the American sneaker powerhouse conceptualized called the College Colors Program, in which Nike created sneakers and warm-ups in school colors. Since then, the Dunk has lived on in numerous colorways and is one of the brand’s most beloved and reimagined styles, proving to be a versatile canvas for reinvention.

Our experts feel that the Dunk Low Pink Foam's best feature is its sweet and preppy color palette. The Nike Dunk Low Pink Foam (Women's) was released on September 1, 2024, and retailed for $110.

name: Salt
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Salt
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Jade Ash is a collaboration design that features a monochromatic Primeknit upper with a Boost sole underneath.

This  Jade Ash sneaker by adidas and Yeezy  has an upper that is crafted from Primeknit and is available in the salt colorway, with an intersection of black contrasting 3-Stripe on its lateral side with an SPLY-350 lettering. The shoe comes with ribbed salt Boost soles underneath for traction and cushioning. It also features matching salt laces.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Jade Ash was first released on the 22nd of October 2022, and it had a suggested retail price of $230.

name: Shelltoe Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles
title: adidas Superstar Shelltoe Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles
description:
The adidas Superstar Shelltoe Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles is part of a line of sneakers that pay tribute to the Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles. The nostalgic sneaker also celebrates the 40th anniversary of the Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles franchise.

What makes this sneaker stand out is the colorway inspired by the crime-fighting turtles: olive green, red, and black. The white toecap also features a turtle shell design. The upper is made of leather in olive green with the serrated 3-Stripes logo along the side panels in red. Each serrated stripe is outlined in dark green and ‘SHELLTOE’ in gold lettering runs along the 3-Stripes logo. The sneaker boasts subtle elements that celebrate the turtles, including a lace charm and ‘NINJA POWER’ inscribed under the tongue.

Our StockX experts like the turtle shell design on the tongue’s adidas logo tag. The adidas Superstar Shelltoe Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles was released on March 22nd, 2024, and retailed at $130.

name: Core Black Red
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Core Black Red
description: If anyone is discussing what's hotter than the earth's core, then the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Core Red must be a part of the discussion. Bringing hot lava vibes, these come with a core black upper and sole. There's also a core black "SPLY-350" branding across a scorching hot core red stripe on both sides. These dropped in November 2016 and retailed at $220. Add more sauce to your sneaker collection and buy now on StockX.

name: Reverse Duck Camo
title: Nike Air Max 90 Reverse Duck Camo
description:
Nike celebrated Air Max Day 2020 by releasing the Nike Air Max 90 Reverse Duck Camo. This colorway is a fresh take on the classic Atmos Air Max 90 design that debuted in 2013.

This Air Max 90 consisted of an Infrared mesh upper with a Duck Camo mudguard and black quarter panels. A Nike Air branded heel tab, white midsole, and a mixed infrared and black outsole completes the design.

The Nike Air Max 90 Reverse Duck Camo released in March of 2020 and retailed for $140. The Nike Air Max 90 Reverse Duck Camo re-released in September of 2024.

name: White University Blue
title: Nike Air Max 1 White University Blue
description:
The Nike Air Max 1 White University Blue remains a timeless essential in any collection, boasting a classic silhouette presented in a color scheme of white, University Blue, black, and Photon Dust.

The White University Blue Nike Air Max 1 upper predominantly features a white mesh base, with University Blue accents highlighting the suede mudguards and lateral Swooshes. This same blue extends to the mesh inner lining, branding, tongue, and the visible Air Max heel unit. Gray suede overlays are strategically placed on the midfoot, heels, and vamp. Sitting atop a white midsole and black rubber outsole, the shoe maintains a clean and classic look. The Air Max bubble's pillars introduce a touch of the University of North Carolina Blue underfoot, while the surrounding foam adopts a "colorless" finish. The waffle-patterned outsole echoes the color-blocking, reminiscent of debut styles from 1987.

The distinctive feature of the Nike Air Max 1 White University Blue is the use of University Blue tints, adding a lively touch to the overall neutral palette, setting the shoe apart as a truly unique piece. The sneaker debuted for $140 on October 15th, 2023.

name: Panda Black White (2021/2024)
title: Nike Dunk High Panda Black White (2021/2024)
description:
The Nike Dunk High Panda Black White 2021 features a smooth white leather upper with perforations on the toe box. Black leather overlays, eyestays and Swooshes match the black laces. The rubber outsole is black with a concentric-circles pattern for traction. The midsole is white with visible threading around the shoe. Black Nike branding appears on the white tongue and the heel features a black loop with arcs of white-on-white horizontal threading below it.
​
​ The Nike Dunk High Panda Black White 2021 was released on January 27, 2022 at a retail price of $115. The Nike Dunk High Panda also re-released in 2024.

name: Oil
title: adidas Yeezy Desert Boot Oil
description: Compliment the Coachella fit with the adidas Yeezy Desert Boot Oil. This Yeezy Boot comes with an oil upper, oil midsole, and an oil sole. These sneakers released in April 2019 and retailed for $200. Buy some fresh boots for Sunday Service, right here on StockX.

name: Ivory Clay Grey
title: ASICS Gel-NYC Ivory Clay Grey
description:
The ASICS Gel-NYC Ivory Clay Grey takes its inspiration from the ASICS GEL-NIMBUS 3 and the MC-PLUS V and fuses it with tooling from the GEL-CUMULUS 16.

The Ivory Clay Grey iteration of the ASICS Gel-NYC has an upper with a base of breathable ivory mesh. This is overlaid with undulating strips of silver, grey, and black leather and synthetics that lend the shoe style and support. GEL branding is embroidered on the ivory mesh window in the center of the heel, while ASICS branding appears on a grey lateral overlay, the grey mesh tongue, and the black insoles.

Our experts really enjoy the sole unit of this ASICS sneaker. The lightweight ivory foam midsole incorporates GEL technology with inserts in the rear and forefeet. The black rubber outsole is arranged in large pods, grooved for traction and impact absorption. The ASICS Gel-NYC Ivory Clay Grey was released on July 1, 2023, for a $130 retail price.

name: Core Black True Pink (Women's)
title: adidas Campus 00s Core Black True Pink (Women's)
description:
The adidas Campus 00s Core Black True Pink (Women's) is a retro-inspired sneaker that takes cues from adidas’ early 2000s catalog and skateboarding style.

This low-top sneaker features a slightly bulk silhouette with extra padding on the tongue and around the collar. Another feature that sets it apart from the Campus 80s is the trefoil logo on the tongue. Like the shoe’s proportions, the trefoil is oversized and resembles branding from the 2000s. The upper is made of soft suede in Core Black, while True Pink details add a subtle pop of color. The serrated 3-Stripes logos on the side panels and the trefoil on the tongue come in True Pink. However, the trefoil on the heel tab and the ‘CAMPUS’ lettering along the 3-Stripes feature Cloud White.

Our StockX experts like the durable rubber outsole that contributes to the sneaker’s skater aesthetic. The women’s size adidas Campus 00s Core Black True Pink (Women's) was released on December 1st, 2023, and retailed at $110.

name: Wonder Quartz Black Gum (Women's)
title: adidas Gazelle Bold Wonder Quartz Black Gum (Women's)
description:
The adidas Gazelle Bold Wonder Quartz Black Gum (Women's) adds a layered gum rubber platform to the classic Gazelle silhouette.

This version of the Gazelle Bold boasts a clean colorway of Wonder Quartz and Core Black. The upper construction features suede in Wonder Quartz and tonal shaggy suede on the T-shaped toebox. The serrated 3-Stripes logos on the side panels and the heel tab come in Core Black. However, what makes this sneaker stand out is the platform, which features 3 layers of stacked gum rubber outsoles. Each outsole displays a different shade of gum and ‘adidas’ lettering with the signature trefoil logo. Another stand-out design element is the bumpy texture on the tongue. It speaks to the sneaker’s bold aesthetic and serves as a backdrop for the tongue branding.

Something our StockX experts like is the way the sneaker pays tribute to indoor court sneakers from the 1970s. The women’s size adidas Gazelle Bold Wonder Quartz Black Gum (Women's) was released on February 1st, 2024, with a $120 retail price.

name: Playoffs (2023)
title: Jordan 8 Retro Playoffs (2023)
description:
Introducing a legend reborn: the Jordan 8 Retro Playoffs. Cloaked in a sophisticated Black, True Red, and White colorway, this iconic shoe is a trip down memory lane for any sneakerhead. If you're looking for legendary, this is it. Donned by the GOAT himself during his epic 1993 playoff run with the Chicago Bulls, this pair is as iconic as it gets.

Crafted with premium materials, the upper showcases a blend of textures. Rewind back to '93, and envision MJ's killer moves during his monumental playoff journey with the Chicago Bulls. Yes, this is the very model he laced up! It's not just a sneaker. It's a symbol of perseverance, legacy, and sheer excellence. The signature crossover straps and chenille tongue logo make it unmistakably Jordan.

The Jordan 8 Retro Playoffs is where historic moments meet modern swagger. Released at a retail price of $210, it's a must-have for any collection, melding sports lore with style.

name: Coconut Milk
title: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG EX Coconut Milk
description:
The Jordan 1 Retro Low OG EX Coconut Milk is an iteration of the deconstructed Air Jordan 1 Low OG EX sneaker in a ‘Coconut Milk’ colorway.

This low-cut sneaker features an upper made of a breathable textile base dressed in Crisp White on the toebox and quarter panel and Off-White overlays on the forefoot, eyelets, and heel. The overlays sport exposed foam construction, giving this sneaker a deconstructed look. Black Swooshes on the sides with an exposed foam outline contrast the upper. Other details include a ‘Nike Air’ branding on the padded tongue tags, white laces, and the iconic ‘Wings’ logo on a suede heel tab. A Sail midsole with aged sidewalls and a black rubber outsole complete the design.

Our experts particularly love this sneaker’s design and colorway. The exposed foam finish and the Coconut Milk colorway give this Air Jordan 1 a bold and stylish look. The Jordan 1 Retro Low OG EX Coconut Milk was released on May 25th, 2023, for a retail price of $140.

name: Neapolitan (Women's)
title: Jordan 11 Retro Neapolitan (Women's)
description:
Take a sweet stride in the all-new Women's Jordan 11 Retro "Neapolitan". A tasteful tribute to the classic Jordan heritage, this sneaker brings a deliciously fresh colorway to the iconic silhouette. The Sail/Velvet Brown hue swirls around the premium leather and ballistic mesh upper, reminiscent of the classic Neapolitan ice cream trio, while keeping the legendary Jordan aesthetics intact.

The Jordan lineage is rich with innovative designs and the Jordan 11 Retro "Neapolitan" is no exception. It's a sneaker that speaks volumes about its legacy, the ingenuity in design echoes the relentless spirit of Michael Jordan that still resonates in the sneaker culture. This pair isn’t just a sneaker, it’s a narrative of heritage meeting modernity head-on, ready to charm the sneakerheads and Jordan loyalists alike.

The Jordan 11 Retro "Neapolitan" is a testament to the enduring allure of the Jordan brand, a blend of tradition and contemporary design, a statement of style that stands out in a crowd. Set to drop on November 11, 2023, at a retail price of $225, this pair is a scoop of Jordan heritage, a sprinkle of innovative design, and a whole lot of cool. Grab a pair and step into a legacy that’s as tasteful and timeless as the Neapolitan colorway it sports.

name: Triple Black
title: Nike Air Max 270 Triple Black
description:
Crafted from a breathable mesh and canvas upper, the Nike Air Max 270 Triple Black now features 270 degrees of visible Air for extra comfort. Drawing inspiration from the sleek Air Max 180, the Nike Air Max 270 Triple Black features a slip-in bootie construction to deliver a great fit. The sneaker boasts a Max Air unit with 270 degrees of air encapsulated in the heel. The sneaker utilizes lightweight and soft neoprene across the upper to ensure airflow to the foot.

The Nike Air Max 270 Triple Black was released in March 2018 at a retail price of $160.

name: Toro Bravo
title: Jordan 6 Retro Toro Bravo
description:
Stepping into 2023 with undeniable swagger, the Jordan 6 Retro made its fiery entrance with the Toro Bravo edition, released on May 24, 2023. This model features a bold blend of premium materials, proving once again why Jordan brand continues to lead the sneaker game.

The upper is adorned with Varsity Red premium suede, giving it that stand-out Jordan style. The eye-catching red is contrasted perfectly with black accents throughout, from the midsole to the iconic Jumpman logo, ensuring a strong visual impact on and off the court. A translucent outsole anchors this design, complementing the vibrant upper and maintaining the timeless silhouette of the Jordan 6 Retro. Inside, you'll find a sockliner designed for comfort, making these sneakers as wearable as they are stylish.

The Jordan 6 Retro Toro Bravo debuted on May 24, 2023, with a retail price of $200.

name: Howard University
title: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG Howard University
description:
The Jordan 1 Retro Low OG Howard University is a special edition sneaker paying homage to the rich history and cultural significance of Howard University. Featuring a bold colorway of white, gym red, midnight navy, neutral grey, sail, and muslin, this release celebrates the iconic HBCU’s legacy while delivering a fresh look to the Jordan 1 Retro Low OG silhouette. The mix of colors represents school pride, blending classic Air Jordan styling with Howard’s vibrant spirit.

This pair showcases the familiar low-cut design, making it perfect for both casual wear and collectors alike. The premium leather construction and signature Nike Air branding give this sneaker a timeless appeal, while the Howard University-inspired color scheme & small embroidered red Nike swoosh on the mudguard adds a unique touch to the design.

Released on October 12, 2024, the Jordan 1 Retro Low OG Howard University retailed for $140. With its tribute to one of the most influential HBCUs and its stylish colorway, this release is a must-have for both Jordan fans and those looking to celebrate Howard’s legacy.

name: MiUSA Grey
title: New Balance 990v6 MiUSA Grey
description:
The New Balance 990v6 Grey is another recent addition to the New Balance brand´s running catalog.

This 990v6 model in a grey color scheme features an upper mesh base with premium suede overlays. Branding elements are scattered throughout; for example, the V6 is noted in red on the tongue. The shoe features a sole unit underfoot with a contoured midsole. Its heels feature a series of curves and lines and a rubber outsole at the base. The sole utilizes ABZORB cushioning pluse Fuel Cell and ENCAP technology.

The New Balance 990v6 Grey was released on November 4th, 2022, at a retail price of $200.

DISCLAIMER: There are two versions of this shoe with the same style ID but they have a slight variation on the heel. The first version is shown in our product imagery and includes a New Balance NB logo on the heel. The second version has an American flag in. Both versions are acceptable for sellers to sell and buyers could receive either version in their order.

name: Black Anthracite
title: Nike Air Max Terrascape Plus Black Anthracite
description:
The Nike Air Max Terrascape Plus Black Anthracite comes in a mixture of two main colors that define its look: black and anthracite.

This Nike Air Max Terrascape Plus in Black Anthracite sneaker features a grid-like black base with embroidery of wavy design lines on the toe and heel. The shoe also features some green shades on the eyelets and has a black lacing system. A linear pattern for traction and AIR unit soles complete the look of these shoes.

The Nike Air Max Terrascape Plus Black Anthracite was released on November 10th, 2022 with a suggested retail price of $185.

name: Brazil (2020/2024)
title: Nike Dunk Low Brazil (2020/2024)
description:
Nike brought back another popular Nike Dunk from the early 2000s with the release of the Nike Dunk Low Brazil (2020/2024), now available on StockX. The original Nike Dunk Low Brazil debuted in 2001 in both high and low cut variations.

This Dunk Low Brazil features a yellow leather upper with green overlays and white detailing. A white midsole, green outsole, and yellow Nike branding on the heel complete the design. These sneakers released in May of 2020 and retailed for $100 USD. The Nike Dunk Low Brazil (2020/2024) restocked in February of 2024 and retailed for $115 USD.

name: Footwear White
title: adidas BW Army Footwear White
description:
The adidas BW Army Footwear White presents a timeless silhouette that emanates a minimalist aesthetic.

Rooted in the 70s-era German Army Trainer (GAT) design, often underestimated but brimming with history, the Footwear White adidas BW Army boasts a sleek white leather upper subtly adorned with the iconic adidas branding on the side and heel. Suede overlays elevate the design, adding a touch of sophistication to its overall appeal. Staying true to the classic GAT form, the shoe features the gummy sole and two-tone uppers. Providing comfort, the shoes come with a padded collar and tongue, along with a cushioned insole. The classic look is complemented by a full-length gum rubber outsole underfoot. The finishing touches include a trefoil logo on the tongue and adidas branding on the sole, encapsulating the brand’s rich heritage.

The standout characteristic of the adidas BW Army Footwear White lies in its minimalist design, paying homage to the vintage German army trainers from the past. The shoe debuted for $105 on June 16th, 2017.

name: Pure (Restock Pair)
title: adidas Yeezy Slide Pure (Restock Pair)
description:
DISCLAIMER: US and UK sizing is the same and does not require any conversion.
The adidas Yeezy Slide Pure (Restock Pair) features a slightly different composition than the original adidas Yeezy Slide Pure that debuted in the spring of 2021. Instead of a smooth EVA foam construction, it has a pebbled, more textural touch. At the base, a grooved sole and cushioned footbed completes the design.

The adidas Yeezy Slide Pure (Restock Pair) released in December of 2021 and retailed for $60.

To shop the original adidas Yeezy Slide Pure, click here.

name: Black Cool Grey
title: Nike P-6000 Black Cool Grey
description:
The Nike P-6000 Black Cool Grey is a shoe that takes its design inspiration from the original Pegasus model with Phylon cushioning inside.

This iteration of the Nike P-6000 is constructed with a breathable mesh upper in a Cool Grey color. Black overlays form the toe cap and run from the front to the back of the shoe in horizontal lines. More black overlays, but this time with a hint of shine, run vertically from the laces to the sole, crossing over the horizontal lines. The Nike swoosh appears in black on top of the toe box and on each side in silver outlined in black. The heel is also supported by a perforated black overlay and sports a black Nike swoosh. The tongue also sports the Nike brand name, while a white rubber outsole completes the design.

Our favorite thing about this sneaker is that all the overlays are the same color: black. This gives the shoe a sleek and streamlined design. The Nike P-6000 Black Cool Grey was released on January 5, 2024, for $110.

name: Bad Bunny Chalky Brown
title: adidas Campus Light Bad Bunny Chalky Brown
description:
The adidas Campus Light Bad Bunny Chalky Brown is a notable collaboration between adidas and the Latin music superstar – Bad Bunny. The sneaker adopts a classic low-top silhouette with clean lines in a blend of and beige, brown, and Cream White hues.

The Bad Bunny Chalky Brown adidas Campus Light incorporates a brown suede upper with a textured finish, complemented by matching 3-Stripe branding. It also features a unique double-tongue construction. The shoe boasts an updated cream-colored rubber mudguard that transitions seamlessly from a wavy pattern into a sturdy rubber cup sole. Underneath, the outsole showcases a herringbone traction pattern for reliable grip. The branding is minimalistic, with the iconic adidas 3-Stripes on the sides and Bad Bunny's recognizable logo on the tongue.

What our experts find most impressive about the adidas Campus Light Bad Bunny Chalky Brown is the collaboration between the giant sportswear brand and the Latin music superstar Bad Bunny. This sneaker represents a fusion of Bad Bunny's distinctive style and the classic adidas Campus silhouette, making it ideal for fans of both fashion and music. The adidas sneaker debuted for $160 on July 29th, 2023.

name: Triple Black
title: Nike Air Max 2017 Triple Black
description:
The Nike Air Max 2017 Triple Black was created for individuals that are active. This model can be worn for everyday walking and more intense exercise.

This model has a cushioned, supportive sole that was designed with support and comfort in mind. The upper body of the shoe, like the sole, is completely black, and made out of a mixture of leather and mesh. The Nike swoosh symbol can be subtly found in the lower part of the shoe near the heel.

The Nike Air Max 2017 Triple Black had a starting release date of August 2017. This model was released with a starting retail price of $160.

name: Lightning (2021)
title: Jordan 4 Retro Lightning (2021)
description:
Originally released in 2006, the Air Jordan 4 Retro Lightning (2021) is one of the most renowned retro Jordan 4 colorways in Jordan Brand's catalog. It features a Tour Yellow Durabuck upper with black netted panels and dark grey eyelets. On the tongue, a black Jordan Flight logo patch with white and yellow accents complements the upper. From there, a Jumpman logo on the heel tab and white midsole with a visible Air unit completes the design.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro Lightning (2021) released in August of 2021 and retailed for $220.

name: Sand (Kids)
title: UGG Lowmel Sand (Kids)
description:
The UGG Lowmel Sand (Kids) is a casual shoe with a soft, plush lining for added warmth and comfort. It has added padding for better foot and ankle support while your kid runs or plays. The shoe is a neutral shade of sand, making it versatile and suitable for wearing with an array of outfits. A sneaker design gives it a kid-friendly look and feel.

This shoe is part of the UGG's kid collection. UGG is a brand from Australia that is recognized for its shoes and boots, which are made of high-end materials like sheepskin. The UGG Lowmel Sand is made of suede and enhanced with recycled wool.

The UGG Lowmel Sand (Kids) features the label´s symbol embossed on the back of the shoe for brand identification. In addition to the overall design, our team likes the pattern of two-tone laces and heel strap, which makes the shoe easier to put on. UGG released this shoe on June 25th, 2024. It originally retailed for $100.

name: The Powerpuff Girls Blossom
title: Nike SB Dunk Low The Powerpuff Girls Blossom
description:
Step into style and sophistication with the Nike SB Dunk Low The Powerpuff Girls Blossom. Representing Blossom's intelligent and graceful character, this sneaker is adorned in a Lotus Pink/Digital Pink/Medium Soft Pink colorway. The design is a fitting tribute to the leader of the Powerpuff Girls, combining elegance with a touch of playfulness. The Blossom edition of the Dunk Low is a harmonious blend of soft hues and quality materials, encapsulating Blossom's charm and poise.

Released on December 14 at skate shops and on SNKRS for $135, the Nike SB Dunk Low The Powerpuff Girls Blossom is an enchanting addition to any sneaker collection. It's a celebration of the hit cartoon and beautiful design, making it a highly desirable piece for fans and sneakerheads​.

name: Lucky Green
title: Jordan 1 Low Lucky Green
description:
Jordan brand continues its Lucky Green trend with the release of the Air Jordan 1 Low Lucky Green. The Air Jordan 1 Low gets the Lucky Green treatment after it was recently released on the Air Jordan 1 High, 2, and 3 models.

The Air Jordan 1 Low Lucky Green is constructed using Lucky Green and black color blocking across the uppers. Jordan brand stitched a black Air Jordan Wings logo on the sneakers heel, and Jumpman logo on the tongue. The low cut sneakers are laced with flat black laces.

The Air Jordan 1 Low Lucky Green released May 1, 2023, with a retail price of $110.

name: Concord
title: Jordan 1 Low SE Concord
description:
Jordan is going back to the classics in 2023, releasing a special edition Air Jordan 1 Low in the popular black and white Concord colorway.

The Jordan 1 Low SE Concord’s draw inspiration from the Air Jordan 11 Concord, highlighted by the sneakers combination of black patent leather, and white leather uppers. Jordan brand used a translucent blue outsole, and added a white Air Jordan Wings logo placed on the heel of each sneaker.

The Air Jordan 1 Low SE Concord released January 17, 2023, with a retail price of $120.

name: Protection Pack Black Grey
title: New Balance 2002R Protection Pack Black Grey
description:
The New Balance 2002R Protection Pack Black Grey comes in a black and gray color palette.

The New Balance 2002R Protection Pack Black Grey has an upper that is constructed from a variety of black and gray materials, including durable mesh and breathable synthetic overlays. The classic "N" emblem appears in contrasting white and black on the sides. The midsole features a white and grey colorway. The ABZORB technology included in the shoe's cushioned midsole provides shock absorption and responsiveness. The shoe’s black outsole is constructed from long-lasting rubber with a directional tread pattern for superior grip and traction. The lacing system offers a customized fit, while the cushioned tongue and collar provide comfort and stability.

The New Balance 2002R Protection Pack Black Grey was released for a retail price of $170 on March 3rd, 2023.

name: Glacier Blue
title: Nike Dunk Low Glacier Blue
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Glacier Blue takes a silhouette that was introduced in 1985 and dresses it in an ethereal colorway that locks in its timeless style.

This classic sneaker features a leather upper where the base is smooth and white, with signature perforations in the toebox for enhanced ventilation and comfort. Ice Blue leather forms the overlays in classic Nike Dunk color blocking. The light blue lining of the white mesh tongue matches the light blue mesh sock liner. The white foam midsole provides cushioning and support underfoot. The light blue outsole, just a fraction of a shade lighter than the light blue leather on the upper, completes the look of this shoe as it provides durable, multidirectional traction.

What we enjoy most about this shoe is the subtle, yet noticeable branding. A white embroidered Nike wordmark hits the heel in classic fashion, while the tongue tag sports the iconic Nike branding. The Nike Dunk Low Glacier Blue was released on July 6, 2024, for $115 retail.

name: Playoffs (2023)
title: Jordan 13 Retro Playoffs (2023)
description:
The Jordan 13 Retro Playoffs are making another return in 2023, its first appearance since its last retro in 2011. Michael Jordan debuted the Air Jordan 13 Playoffs in the 1998 NBA All-Star game, and continued to wear the sneakers throughout the season en route to his record breaking sixth NBA championship.
​
​Tinker Hatfield's original design for the Jordan 13 was inspired by Jordan’s aggressive play style, which was referred to as a Black Cat. The retro sneaker features black leather uppers, suede mudguards, and holographic eyes that sit below each collar.
​
​The Air Jordan 13 Retro Playoffs (2023) released February 18, 2023, with a retail price of $210.

name: Halo
title: Nike Kobe 8 Protro Halo
description:
Unveiled on August 23, 2023, the Nike Kobe 8 Protro Halo signals the epic return of the iconic Kobe line.

Drenched in a pristine all-white colorway, this sneaker stands as an embodiment of purity, legacy, and unparalleled style. A true nod to the rebirth of the legendary Nike Kobe series, this piece is all about legacy and finesse. From its seamless upper construction to the intricate detailing, every aspect echoes Kobe's timeless style and unwavering commitment to the game. An embodiment of both on-court prowess and off-court style, this sneaker is a must-have for any collection.

Mamba mentality isn't just a mindset; it's a lifestyle. And for those looking to embody that spirit, the Nike Kobe 8 Protro Halo was made available at a retail price of $180. Truly, a timeless tribute to basketball royalty.

name: Alternate Royal Toe
title: Jordan 1 Low Alternate Royal Toe
description:
The Jordan 1 Low Alternate Royal Toe presents a classic silhouette that has fun with the color blocking in this tried-and-true sneaker.

The Alternate Royal Toe iteration of the Jordan 1 Low-Top begins with a base of smooth white leather along the side panel. The perforated toe box is tumbled blue leather, and the toe overlay is black tumbled leather. We see more tumbled royal blue leather on this upper on the side panel Nike swoosh and the heel overlay. Black tumbled leather also covers the eye stays, and collar. The nylon tongue, sock liner, laces, and insole are all black. The white foam of the midsole matches the side panel, and the royal blue rubber outsole with traction ties the look of this whole shoe together.

What we enjoy most about this shoe is the placement of the Jordan branding. An embroidered black Wings logo adorns the royal blue heel, while a royal blue Jumpman is featured on the black tongue and black insole. The Jordan 1 Low Alternate Royal Toe was released on September 20, 2023, for a retail price of $115.

name: Travis Scott Canary (PS)
title: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG SP Travis Scott Canary (PS)
description:
The Jordan 1 Retro Low OG SP Travis Scott Canary (PS) is a "Special Project (SP)" sneaker, which means it’s created in the Nike lab and incorporates premium materials. This sneaker is also a collaborative project between American rapper Travis Scott and the Jordan Brand.

The white leather construction serves as a backdrop for Canary, Racer Blue, and red accents, which intentionally use the kid-friendly primary colors. The forefoot overlays, the toebox mudguard, the heel panel, the laces, the heel tab, the tongue, and the collar lining come in bright Canary, which contrasts with the Racer Blue Swoosh logo on the side panels. In terms of branding, the heel tab displays the Jordan Wings logo, the red "NIKE" lettering graces the tongue tab, and the "cactus jack" in red is printed on the inner side panel.

Our StockX experts like the inclusion of one reverse Swoosh and one standard Swoosh. The preschool-sized Jordan 1 Retro Low OG SP Travis Scott Canary (PS) was launched on May 25, 2024, and sold for $65.

name: Wheat (GS)
title: Timberland 6" Boot Wheat (GS)
description: The Timberland 6 Wheat GS is a classic boot that has been updated with modern materials and construction techniques. The upper is made from premium nubuck leather that is both durable and comfortable. The boot is also waterproof, making it perfect for outdoor activities. The wheat colorway is a timeless look that will never go out of style. The release date for this boot was January 1st, 2018, and it retails for $130. The Timberland 6 Wheat GS is a versatile boot that can be worn with a variety of outfits, from jeans to khakis. It is a must-have for anyone who wants a durable and stylish boot that can handle any weather conditions.

name: White Metallic Silver Max Orange (Women's)
title: Nike Shox TL White Metallic Silver Max Orange (Women's)
description:
The Nike Shox TL White Metallic Silver Max Orange (Women's) is a revival of the iconic 2003 Nike Shox TL.

Like the original, the Nike Shox TL White Metallic Silver for women features a white nylon-base upper, detailed with glossy taped overlays, TPU strips that provide lightweight support, a mesh-lined tongue with a Nike Shox logo in Max Orange, a notched collar, Nike Swooshes in metallic silver on the sides, and another Max Orange Nike Shox logo on the heel. All the logos are embroidered. Its upper sits atop a dozen Shox columns which offer the shoe a distinctive look and a carbon rubber outsole.

We all agree that the most attractive feature of the Nike Shox TL White Metallic Silver Max Orange (Women's), released on the 1st of May, 2019, at a retail price of $170, is the Shox columns. These columns cushion every stride and add the bounce-back effect needed on walks and long runs. The Nike Shox TL White Metallic Silver Max Orange (Women's) also re-released in 2023 and 2024.

name: Dazzling Blue
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Dazzling Blue
description:
The adidas Yeezy 350 V2 Dazzling Blue is reminiscent of the 2016 Yeezy 350 V2 Black Friday Pack. Instead of featuring a marbled pattern and sheer side stripe, it opts for a solid black Primeknit upper and blue side stripe with "SPLY-350" text. At the base, a muted Boost sole offers comfort and support.

The adidas Yeezy 350 V2 Dazzling Blue released in February of 2022 and retailed for $220.

name: UNC Toe (GS)
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG UNC Toe (GS)
description:
The Jordan 1 Retro High OG UNC Toe (GS) draws inspiration from the University of North Carolina’s blue-and-white color scheme, which is a tribute to Michael Jordan's alma mater.

The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG UNC Toe was released in grade-school sizes, and it features a perforated toe, which helps improve ventilation. The sneaker has a cushioned sole unit that provides shock absorption, enhancing comfort for daily wear. Additionally, the sneaker has a durable rubber outsole with a herringbone pattern that ensures traction and grip on any surface. The Nike Swoosh and Air Jordan logo are black while the Nike Air on the tongue is in University Blue.

Something we love about the Jordan 1 Retro High OG UNC Toe (GS) shoe is its high-top design. This provides ankle protection and stability, making it ideal for both casual and athletic use. The shoe debuted on July 22nd, 2023, and retailed for $140.

name: Black Cat
title: Jordan Spizike Low Black Cat
description:
The Jordan Spizike Low Black Cat continues the legacy of Michael Jordan and director Spike Lee’s partnership by applying an all-black colorway to the Air Jordan Spizike Low.

This shoe pays homage to Lee’s contributions to film history and the iconic triple-black "Black Cat" colorway, known for its sleek, stealthy look. Taking elements from previous Air Jordan sneakers, including the Air Jordan 3, 4, 5, and 6, this version of the Spizike boasts soft cushioning in the tongue and collar. Velvety nubuck deepens the black’s rich hue, while the mudguard is crafted from suede and the heel and toe overlays display the signature elephant print.

Our experts like the way the all-black aesthetic reaches the shiny midsole and durable rubber outsole. In addition, visible air units in the heel complete the look and speak to the sneaker’s Jordan-brand heritage. The Jordan Spizike Low Black Cat was released on June 11, 2024, and sold for $160.

name: Volt Concord
title: Nike Air Zoom Alphafly Next% 3 Volt Concord
description:
The Nike Alphafly 3 Volt Concord is a cutting-edge distance running shoe designed to maximize performance while delivering a truly unique aesthetic.

Crafted from Nike’s Flyknit material, the Alphafly features ZoomX foam in the midsole, which is one of Nike's most responsive and lightweight cushioning materials. This foam provides exceptional energy return, allowing runners to maintain speed and efficiency over long distances. Strategically placed Air Zoom pods in the forefoot minimize energy loss and enhance toe-off for a powerful and efficient running experience, while a full-length carbon fiber plate in the midsole delivers stability. A rubber outsole with patterned traction ensures a reliable grip on many surfaces.

What our experts enjoy most about the Nike Alphafly 3 Volt Concord, however, is its vibrant colorway, which combines a predominantly Volt yellow background with pops of Dusty Cactus, Total Orange, and Concord blue. This shoe originally retailed for a price of $285 on April 4, 2024.

name: DJ Khaled We The Best Crimson Bliss
title: Jordan 5 Retro DJ Khaled We The Best Crimson Bliss
description:
The Air Jordan 5 Retro DJ Khaled We The Best Crimson Bliss is a collaboration between footwear brand and the American musician.

This Retro Air Jordan 5 comes in crimson bliss , leche blue-sail colorway. The upper is coral leather with a Leche Blue quilted lining. Each heel overlay has the Nike Air logo on the right and 'We the Best' on the left. Reflective silver tongues feature Jumpman branding. Off-white polyurethane midsole with blue shark-tooth detailing and Air-sole unit in heel. Mismatched Jumpman and 'We the Best' branding appear on the outsoles.

The Air Jordan 5 Retro DJ Khaled We The Best Crimson Bliss was released on the 28th of November 2022, retailing for $225.

name: Yin Triple Black
title: Anta Kai 1 Yin Triple Black
description:
The Anta Kai 1 Triple Black is a collaboration between NBA player Kyrie Irving and Anta, a sportswear label based in China.

The Triple Black Anta Kai 1 pays homage to Irving’s graceful yet powerful style of play through its sleek design and graphics, including a silver shield motif on the tongue. The silver shield provides a pop of metallic against the all-black upper, midsole, and outsole. The minimalist upper is made from a lightweight synthetic material and doesn’t include the intricate patterns found on other Anta Kai 1 models. However, a small, silver "11" can be found on the forefoot, representing Irving’s preferred jersey number. Something that makes this sneaker stand out is the dual closure system. It features a traditional lace closure and a strap that crosses the forefoot.

Our experts at StockX like the oversized pull tab on the heel because it assists with applying and removing the sneaker. The Anta Kai 1 Triple Black was released on June 3, 2024, and retailed for $125.

name: Aunt Pearl
title: Nike KD 16 Aunt Pearl
description:
The Nike KD 16 NRG Aunt Pearl continues the tradition of paying tribute to Kevin Durant’s Aunt Pearl, who offered support in his formative years and lost her battle with lung cancer in 2000.

This sneaker stands out from other "Aunt Pearl" variations due to the floral-debossed overlay which covers the mesh upper and features a paisley pattern. Durable TPU support wings connect to the midsole and boast rose-like blooms beneath a transparent seal. The Phylon midsole comes with a Zoom Air unit in the forefoot and a responsive Air Strobel unit beneath the heel. The sneaker features a primarily pink colorway of White, Fierce Pink, Pink Foam, and Hyper Pink.

Something our StockX experts love is the addition of fuzzy laces. These light-hued laces complement the textile-like mesh of the upper and the woven material that makes up the tongue. The Nike KD 16 NRG Aunt Pearl was released on October 27, 2023, and retailed at $170.

name: Protection Pack White
title: New Balance 1906D Protection Pack White
description:
The New Balance 1906D Protection Pack White comes in a primarily white colorway with TurtleDove accents.​
​​
​The 1906D Protection Pack White sneaker features a ABZORB responsive midsole, and a N-ERGY outsole which offers shock absorption and durability. The Crimson branding N-ERGY appears on the midsole creating some contrast. The shoe's upper is made of high-quality leather, which provides both durability and a comfortable fit. The design of the upper also includes mesh, which allows for maximum airflow, keeping your feet cool and dry during even the most intense workouts.​
​​
​We think that one of the standout features of the New Balance 1906D Protection Pack White is its design. The shoe features a leather upper with suede overlays, adding both style and durability to the shoe's design. The combination of both materials also adds dimension to the design. The shoe was released on July 22nd, 2023 at a retail price of $170.​
​​
​

name: Big Bubble Royal (Women's)
title: Nike Air Max 1 '86 OG Big Bubble Royal (Women's)
description:
The Nike Air Max 1 '86 OG Big Bubble Royal Women's sneaker is a meticulous recreation of a legendary design, reviving the classic with a colorway that blends white, royal blue, neutral grey, and black. This edition pays tribute to the original Air Max 1's groundbreaking introduction, offering enthusiasts a taste of the past with the distinctive "Big Bubble" feature that set the sneaker world ablaze. Designed for those who appreciates the fusion of heritage and contemporary style, this sneaker is a nod to the pioneers of sneaker culture.

What sets the '86 OG Big Bubble version apart is the enhanced air unit in the heel, providing a glimpse into the sneaker innovation that revolutionized comfort and aesthetics in athletic footwear. This detail, coupled with the iconic colorway, makes the sneaker not only a piece of history but also a testament to Nike's enduring influence on sportswear design. The blend of royal blue and neutral tones on a pristine white base offers a look that's both fresh and timeless, appealing to a wide range of tastes and styles.

Released on March 22, 2024, for $150, the Nike Air Max 1 '86 OG Big Bubble Royal quickly ascended to must-have status among sneaker aficionados and style mavens. Its launch is celebrated for reintroducing a classic silhouette with its original specifications to a new generation. It's a piece of athletic history, a homage to innovation, and a beacon of timeless style.

name: Faded Ash Rock (Women's)
title: ASICS Gel-1130 Faded Ash Rock (Women's)
description:
The ASICS Gel-1130 Faded Ash Rock (Women's) applies a white base and metallic Faded Ash Rock details to the Gel-1130's technical silhouette.

This running shoe pays homage to several sneakers from the early 2000s, including the ninth iteration of the Gel-1000 series and the GEL-KAYANO 14. For example, the sneaker boasts a breathable mesh construction and a slightly bulky silhouette. However, this iteration of the Gel-1130 features synthetic leather paneling instead of traditional leather overlays. The use of synthetic leather gives the sneaker a modern upgrade and allows the Faded Ash Rock hue to catch the light. The gel technology in the heel represents another upgrade and cushions against impact. In terms of technology, ASICS’ signature support system adds stability without decreasing flexibility.

Our StockX experts appreciate that the upper is made with at least 20 percent recycled materials. The women’s size ASICS Gel-1130 Faded Ash Rock (Women's) was released on January 1st, 2024, and retailed at $95.

name: Travis Scott Cactus Jack
title: Nike Mac Attack QS SP Travis Scott Cactus Jack
description:
The Nike Mac Attack QS SP Travis Scott Cactus Jack is unveiled in an engaging Light Smoke Grey, Black, and White color combination, incorporating a mix of leather and mesh across its upper. The mesh is prominently featured on the vamp and side panels, while high-quality leather forms the majority of the shoe’s construction.

This sneaker stands out with its gray and black color scheme, infused with the signature Travis Scott flair. The sneaker's standout feature is the iconic reverse Swoosh in black leather, adding a rebellious edge to its appearance. The Cactus Jack logo, embroidered on the spine, and a blue and black checkerboard pattern on the tongue tag add unique Travis Scott touches, completing the overall look.

What sets this sneaker apart is its functional design and comfortable fit. It features a white rubber midsole and a grey outsole, ensuring durability and stability. The Travis Scott x Nike Mac Attack QS SP Cactus Jack is set to release on December 19, 2023, at a retail price of $120, offering a perfect blend of style and performance for sneaker enthusiasts.

name: Aqua
title: Jordan 6 Retro Aqua
description:
Enter the realm of iconic basketball legacy with the Jordan 6 Retro Aqua, revamped in a vibrant Black, Bright Concord, and Aquatone colorway.

Dripping with history, this Retro silhouette gets a refreshing twist. The upper's supple suede is highlighted by Bright Concord accents on the Jumpan logo and rubberized heel tab, ensuring that perfect mix of premium style and function. Dive into the unexpected brilliance of Aquatone, seamlessly blending with the stark Black upper and Bright Concord hues on the midsole– a color fusion never witnessed before on this iconic model. Signature Jordan elements remain, from the pull-tab at the rear of the heel. But what steals the show? The uncharted Aqua color way elements that's ready to make waves.

The Jordan 6 Retro Aqua is a throwback with a fresh splash. Dropped at $200, it's the bridge between vintage Jordan and contemporary cool.

name: Action Bronson Rosewater
title: New Balance 1906R Action Bronson Rosewater
description:
The New Balance 1906R Action Bronson Rosewater is part of a collaboration between New Balance and American rapper Action Bronson that reworks the well-known 1906R silhouette.

This Action Bronson Rosewater New Balance 1906R stands out because of its vibrant colorway, which features splashes of fuchsia and orange across a light green base. In addition, blue details can be found on the rubber outsole, the New Balance "N," and the "new balance 1906" lettering on the tongue. The upper is crafted from durable mesh with supportive TPU overlays and reflective detailing. The rubber outsole features a segmented design with blue, orange, light orange, and brown sections. Finally, thin, green laces wind through the eyelets, providing the last color-blocking detail.

Our StockX experts like the sneaker’s dual branding, including "Baklava" and "New Balance 1906." The New Balance 1906R Action Bronson Rosewater was released on May 31, 2024, and retailed at $185.

name: Almost Blue Yellow (Women's)
title: adidas Gazelle Bold Almost Blue Yellow (Women's)
description:
The adidas Gazelle Bold Almost Blue Yellow (Women’s) reimagines the classic Gazelle silhouette with a triple stacked platform and a colorway of Almost Blue, Bright Blue, and Almost Yellow.

The platform features three layers of rubber soles that form a gradient of gum tones, ranging from natural to semi-dark gum. Each gum sole displays adidas’ and a trefoil debossed into the area beneath the heel. The upper is nubuck in Almost Blue, while the 3-Stripes logo is Bright Blue leather. Something that makes this sneaker stand out is the heel tab, which is made from Bright Blue terrycloth-like material and pays homage to the use of terrycloth in early Adidas footwear designs. In addition, the same material is used on the Almost Yellow inner lining.

Our StockX experts like the oversized, metallic ‘GAZELLE’ lettering on the side panel. The women’s size adidas Gazelle Bold Almost Blue Yellow (Women’s) was released on March 11, 2024, and sold for $120.

name: Azael
title: adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Azael
description:
Yeezy introduces a new variation of the 700 with the Yeezy 700 V3 Azael, now available on StockX. The third incarnation of the Yeezy 700 is one of the most sophisticated designs we’ve seen from the ongoing collaborations, playing with shape, line, texture, and even expectations. The outer shell is reminiscent of a race car and an astronaut’s suit with a sole unit that feels progressive and substantial.

This 700 V3 is composed of an azael upper composed of monofilament engineered mesh with RPU overlays for structure and durability. The RPU cage has glow-in-the-dark features, along with 3M reflective detailing on the toe. The EVA midsole and herringbone rubber outsole completes the design. These sneakers released in December of 2019 and retailed for $200.

name: White Black
title: Nike Air Max 1 White Black
description:
The Nike Air Max 1 White Black paints the Air Max 1 silhouette in a contrasting colorway of white, black, and Pure Platinum.

Like the original Air Max 1 from 1987, the "White Black" version was designed with comfort in mind and includes design elements that pay tribute to the original. For example, the sneaker features wavy mudguards and overlapping overlays. The waffle design on the rubber outsole is another feature that pays homage to the sneaker’s running roots. It also provides traction without adding bulky lugs. While white is the base’s dominant color, the leather overlays come in Pure Platinum and the mudguard is black. Notable branding elements include the Swooshes on the side panels and the retro-inspired logo tag on the tongue.

Our StockX experts appreciate the transparent windows in the heel, which allow you to see the Air Max unit. The Nike Air Max 1 White Black was released on January 4th, 2024, and retailed at $140.

name: Black Anthracite
title: Nike Air VaporMax 2021 FK Black Anthracite
description:
The Nike Air VaporMax 2021 FK Black Anthracite was designed with both utility and sustainability in mind.

The uppers are made out of stretchy and breathable Flyknit fabric, and they are adorned by the brand’s iconic Swoosh symbol. There is also a classic Nike symbol that is featured on the insoles. The Nike Air VaporMax 2021 FK Black Anthracite is made out of 40% recycled content by weight. The Nike Air VaporMax 2021 FK Black Anthracite has two cushioning units that are sizable yet sleek. These units sit across recycled rubber outsoles and are bolstered by recycled TPU clips.

What our experts like the most in the Nike Air VaporMax 2021 FK Black Anthracite is its sleek design and total black colorway. The midsole and outsole complete the Nike sneaker making it one of the classics and recognizable designs of the Nike Air lines. The sneaker was first released in June of 2021 at a starting price of $200.

name: Radiant Emerald
title: Nike Kobe 8 Protro Radiant Emerald
description:
Dive into the game with the Nike Kobe 8 Protro Radiant Emerald, a sneaker that blends cutting-edge design with a tribute to a basketball legend. This sneaker captures the essence of Kobe Bryant's dynamic playstyle and his legacy on the court, featuring a sleek White/Radiant Emerald/White colorway that stands out in any crowd. The numbers 8, 24, and 2 are displayed on the upper, symbolizing Kobe's iconic numbers with the Lakers and his daughter Gianna's number 2, making it more than just a shoe; it's a piece of history.

Crafted for the modern athlete and styled for the streets, the Kobe 8 Protro Radiant Emerald is engineered with performance technology that ensures comfort and responsiveness. Its lightweight construction and supportive fit adapt seamlessly to rapid movements, embodying the agility and precision Kobe was known for. The vibrant Radiant Emerald accents add a fresh pop of color, perfectly suited for individuals who appreciate a mix of heritage and style.

The Nike Kobe 8 Protro Radiant Emerald, retailing at $190, made its mark on February 8, 2024. This brand-new colorway not only honors the legacy of Kobe and Gianna but also serves as a fashionable statement piece for sneaker enthusiasts and basketball players alike, making it a must-have addition to any collection.

name: Metallic
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Metallic
description:
Composed of a light grey nylon upper with metallic "700" branding and reflective detailing, the adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Metallic beams with the futuristic aesthetic that Yeezy has garnered a reputation for. A thick Boost sole at the base supplies the responsiveness and comfort needed for everyday wear.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Metallic released in December of 2021 and retailed for $220.

name: Black Canvas
title: Jordan 4 Retro SE Black Canvas
description:
The Air Jordan 4 Retro SE Black Canvas arrives in a neutral color scheming with contrasting touches of crimson red.

This Black Canvas Air Jordan is a mid-top sneaker with a black canvas upper complemented by a gray tonal suede which covers the eyelets and forefoot overlays. A gray Jumpman logo graces the heel and woven tongue tag, with the latter getting a crimson Flight logo. The sneaker also rides on a two-tone polyurethane midsole with visible Air-sole cushioning in the heel.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro SE Black Canvas was released on the 5th of October 2022, and retailed at a price of $210.

name: Bad Bunny San Juan
title: adidas Gazelle Indoor Bad Bunny San Juan
description:
