The adidas Gazelle Indoor Bad Bunny San Juan is part of a collaboration between adidas and Bad Bunny, a Puerto Rican singer and rapper.

This sneaker pays homage to the performer’s birthplace through the name "San Juan" and by adding a colorway of Core White, blue, and red that represents the nation’s flag and the coastal capital city. The mixed-material upper is crafted in shades of blue from shaggy suede, smooth leather, synthetic materials, and textiles. The iconic serrated 3-Stripe logo runs up the side panel and is made of Core White leather. Core White details can also be found on the laces, the panels forming the lace cage, and the collar lining, while red stitching appears on the tongue.

Our experts at StockX like the metallic gold lettering that reads "adidas SAN JUAN" on the side panel. The adidas Gazelle Indoor Bad Bunny San Juan was released on June 23, 2024, and retailed at $140.

name: Glow Pink
title: adidas Bermuda Glow Pink
description:
The adidas Bermuda Glow Pink draws inspiration from the coastal scenery of Bermuda, reimagining it with a palette of soft pastel colors.

The Glow Pink adidas Bermuda showcases a timeless aesthetic, featuring darker suede uppers complemented by lighter overlays at the heel tab. The distinct Three Stripes branding with serrated edges on both the medial and lateral mid-panels takes on a lighter clear pink hue. The suede tongues in Glow Pink proudly display the clear pink Trefoil branding. Finishing touches include Trefoil branding at the tongues and sole unit, harmonizing linings, and lace-up closures. The design is elegantly concluded with a gum rubber sole unit in a rich toffee color.

The standout characteristic of the adidas Bermuda Glow Pink is its captivating two-tone design. The interplay between the darker suede uppers and the lighter heel tab overlays contributes to a visually appealing aesthetic that exudes timeless style. The sneaker debuted for $100 on May 11th, 2023.

name: Utility Black
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Utility Black
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Utility Black features a muted Utility Black mesh, leather, and suede monochrome upper. From there, a Utility Black Boost midsole and gum outsole completes the design.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Utility Black released in June of 2019 and retailed for $300.

name: Preloved Green
title: adidas Handball Spezial Preloved Green
description:
The adidas Handball Spezial Preloved Green is a shoe that was originally designed for the handball court, but has now become a street-style staple.

This version of the adidas Handball Spezial comes with a paneled suede upper in Preloved Green. Suede overlays in the same color appear on the toebox and around the heel. The adidas three stripes appear on the midsoles in a Cream White color, and "SPEZIAL" and the adidas trefoil logo appear in gold on the lateral side. The heel collar sports the same Cream White color. For a final note of branding, there is an adidas patch on the tongue, and an adidas logo is also stamped into the brown gum rubber outsole under the heel.

Our favorite thing about this shoe is its streamlined color scheme, which allows for simplicity and easy styling. The adidas Handball Spezial Preloved Green was released on March 15, 2024, for a retail price of $110.

name: Red Cloud White (Women's)
title: adidas Gazelle Bold Red Cloud White (Women's)
description:
The adidas Gazelle Bold Red Cloud White (Women's) is a women’s exclusive sneaker from the adidas Gazelle Bold lineup in a red and Cloud White colorway. 

This adidas Gazelle Bold features a Vivid Scarlet suede upper highlighted by white leather detailing on the serrated edge three stripes on the sides and the heel tab. More white detailing appears on the padded tongue and branded insoles. Traditional details include Metallic Gold "GAZELLE" wording on the lateral next to the three stripes and a  T-toe overlay on the vamp. Other details include Vivid Scarlet laces and gold adidas branding on the tongue. The highlight of this sneaker is the platform sole unit, which comprises three stacked layers of the traditional sole unit in Vintage Off-White. 

Our experts particularly love this sneaker’s modern update and vibrant colorway, which gives it a stylish and eye-catching appearance. The adidas Gazelle Bold Red Cloud White (Women's) was released on May 14th, 2023, retailing at $120.

name: Quartz Grey
title: New Balance 9060 Quartz Grey
description: The New Balance 9060 Quartz Grey Team Cream Sea Salt is a sleek and stylish sneaker that is perfect for both casual and athletic wear. The shoe features a combination of premium materials, including suede and mesh, which provide both durability and breathability. The colorway of the shoe is a unique blend of grey, cream, and sea salt, which gives it a distinctive and eye-catching look. The release date for the New Balance 9060 Quartz Grey Team Cream Sea Salt is set for May 1st, 2023, and the retail price is $150. This shoe is sure to be a hit with sneaker enthusiasts and New Balance fans alike. Something we love about the New Balance 9060 Quartz Grey Team Cream Sea Salt is the attention to detail that has gone into its design. From the premium materials to the unique colorway, every aspect of this shoe has been carefully considered. Our experts think that the standout feature of the New Balance 9060 Quartz Grey Team Cream Sea Salt is its versatility. Whether you're hitting the gym or running errands, this shoe is sure to keep you comfortable and stylish. Overall, we love the New Balance 9060 Quartz Grey Team Cream Sea Salt and think it's a must-have for any sneaker collection.

name: Taxi Flip (GS)
title: Jordan 12 Retro Taxi Flip (GS)
description:
The Jordan 12 Retro Taxi Flip (GS) is a grade school-sized shoe that preserves many elements of the original shoe that came out in 1996 inspired by the Japanese flag.

This version of the Air Jordan 12 Retro is made with a white leather upper sectioned off into lines by vertical stitching. A black snakeskin-textured leather mudguard appears, stretching from the toe around the side to the arch. A red support appears over the arch on the mudguard and is branded with the word "JUMPMAN." The tongue features a red Jumpman logo, while the heel features a black pull tab with another Jumpman logo for easy on and off. The black strip under the pull tab is branded with the Jordan brand name, and the number 23 appears on the heel in red. A black rubber outsole finishes off the look.

What we love most about this sneaker is the unique vertically sectioned upper formed by the stitching in the white leather, which is a deviation from most AJ shoes. The Jordan 12 Retro Taxi Flip (GS) was released on May 25, 2024, for $150.

name: Lucky Green (Women's)
title: Jordan 5 Retro Lucky Green (Women's)
description:
The Jordan 5 Retro Lucky Green (Women's) applies bold Lucky Green accents and a Crisp White base to the recognizable Jordan 5 Retro silhouette.

Released ahead of Saint Patrick’s Day, this basketball AJ 5 boasts Lucky Green accents on the insole, the padded collar, the lace closure system’s toggle, and the angular midsole. While the Jumpman logo on the heel comes in gray, the logo on the tongue is embroidered with Lucky Green thread. The upper is made of a combination of leather and synthetic materials, including mesh on the quarter panels and smooth leather overlays. Featuring a zig-zag pattern and Nike Air cushioning underfoot, the midsole sits on a durable rubber outsole.

Our StockX experts like the ‘23’ embroidered on the heel, which pays homage to Michael Jordan’s legacy. The women’s size Jordan 5 Retro Lucky Green (Women's) was released on February 28th, 2024, and retailed at $200.

name: Untouchable
title: Puma LaMelo Ball LaFrancé Amour Untouchable
description:
The Puma LaMelo Ball LaFrancé Amour Untouchable adds a Puma Black and Glowing Pink colorway to NBA star LaMelo Ball’s chunky, Y2K-inspired sneaker.

As part of a collaboration between Puma and Ball’s brand LaFrancé, the Untouchable Puma LaMelo Ball LaFrancé Amour sneaker embraces exaggerated silhouettes and oversized detailing. For instance, extra-wide black laces thread through the eyelets and create an overlapping pattern over the lace cage. Padding in the tongue and collar gives the sneaker a bulky appearance, while the thick EVA midsole furthers the exaggerated look and spans the full length of the shoe. Although the upper is crafted from a combination of leather, textile, and synthetic leather, the sockliner and insole are 100 percent textile.

Our experts like the bubble-like, graffiti-inspired LaFrancé branding on the midsole. The bulbous shapes match the oval textile detailing in Glowing Pink on the upper. The Puma LaMelo Ball LaFrancé Amour Untouchable was released on July 19, 2024, and retailed for $110.

name: Victor Wembanyama Alien
title: Nike Air Zoom GT Hustle 2 Victor Wembanyama Alien
description:
The Nike Air Zoom GT Hustle 2 Victor Wembanyama Alien edition is a bold statement in performance basketball footwear, inspired by the rising star Victor Wembanyama. This special edition features a multi-color design dominated by striking black and green hues, creating a visually captivating aesthetic. The sneaker includes a glow-in-the-dark sole that reads "Be Unique Every Day," adding a unique touch that resonates with Wembanyama's out-of-this-world nickname, "alien." The metallic swoosh further enhances the sneaker's futuristic appeal, making it a standout both on and off the court.

Designed for optimal performance, the Nike Air Zoom GT Hustle 2 incorporates advanced technology to meet the demands of modern basketball players. The alien logo on the heel serves as a tribute to Wembanyama's unique presence in the basketball world, symbolizing his extraordinary skills and potential. The combination of black and green, along with the glow-in-the-dark features, ensures that this sneaker is not just about performance but also about making a bold style statement.

Priced at $170, the Nike Air Zoom GT Hustle 2 Victor Wembanyama Alien was released on May 15, 2024. This sneaker merges cutting-edge design with the name recognition of the NBA's newest star, offering a perfect blend of style and functionality. Celebrate Victor Wembanyama and embrace the "alien" spirit with this unique and stylish sneaker.

name: Magnet
title: New Balance 9060 Magnet
description:
The New Balance 9060 Magnet represents a fresh interpretation of the refined style and innovation-driven design found in the classic 99X series.

With a magnet colorway accented by shades of gray, the New Balance 9060 showcases a modern and streamlined aesthetic. Its contemporary appeal is emphasized by suede overlays and a mesh upper, coupled with flat cotton laces and TPU eyelets. Drawing influence from the 990, the 9060 Magnet incorporates sway bars across the entire upper, creating a visually dynamic effect. Wavy lines and exaggerated proportions on a sculpted pod midsole enhance the familiar cushioning technologies of ABZORB and SBS. Inspired by the original 991 lace jewel, the tongue logo adds a distinctive touch, while the diamond outsole pattern, borrowed from the classic 860, completes the overall design.

The standout characteristic of the New Balance 9060 Magnet lies in its advanced cushioning technology. Featuring ABZORB and SBS technologies in the sole, the shoe delivers dynamic and lightweight cushioning for optimal comfort and performance. The sneaker debuted for $150 on September 25th, 2023.

name: Protection Pack Sandstone
title: New Balance 2002R Protection Pack Sandstone
description:
The New Balance 2002R Protection Pack Sandstone is a sneaker built using the MR 2002 as inspiration. Combining an aesthetic from the early 2000s, durability, support, and comfort, this running shoe delivers.

The upper of the Protection Pack Sandstone iteration of the New Balance 2002R is created using a mesh-like textile base overlaid with nubuck leather that gives the shoe both style and support. The fusion of the two materials creates balance and breathability to offer your foot comfort stride after stride. The laces, tongue, and sock liner are all a creamy sand color to match the primary color represented throughout the upper. New Balance branding appears on the gray insoles and the gray tongue tag.

What we love most about this shoe is the high-tech and high-performance capabilities of the sole unit. Stability Web technology provides arch support, while a midsole created from ABZORB, N-ergy, and ABZORB SBS in the heel provides cushioning and energy return. The gray rubber outsole provides more impact absorption and traction. The New Balance 2002R Protection Pack Sandstone was released on September 21, 2023, for a retail price of $160.

name: Leopard Off White (Women's)
title: adidas Sambae Leopard Off White (Women's)
description:
The adidas Sambae Leopard Off White (Women's) is a sneaker for women that features an oversized midsole and unique design elements.
   
This version of the adidas Sambae features an off-white suede upper. Hairy off-white suede in a lighter cream color forms the t-shaped toe cap and the eyestays, while the adidas three stripes adorn each side in leopard print, attached to the side panels with decorative white stitching. The Samba brand name appears in black above the first stripe on the lateral side. The heel collar is black, and the tongue also has a black adidas logo patch. The gum rubber midsole is thick, adding a chunkiness to the design. 

What we think stands out about this sneaker are the leopard-print branding elements, which are eye-catching but still allow the overall design to be subtle. The adidas Sambae Leopard Off White (Women's) was released on June 1, 2024, for $110.

name: White Midnight (GS)
title: ASICS Gel-1130 White Midnight (GS)
description:
The ASICS Gel-1130 White Midnight (GS) is a stability running shoe that draws inspiration from the Gel-Kayano series, in particular the Gel-Kayano 14, and the ninth iteration of the GEL-1000 series.

Originally introduced in 2008, the White Midnight (GS) ASICS Gel-1130 features white mesh underlays that provide breathability and create an airy feel. While previous models used genuine leather to create the supportive overlays, this version replaces genuine leather with faux leather. This materials upgrade gives the sneaker a modern look while paying tribute to archived design details. In addition, the sneaker boasts GEL technology in the heel for shock absorption and a TRUSSTIC support system for improved stability.

Our experts at StockX like the Midnight details on the rubber outsole, collar lining, and overlays, which break up the sneaker’s primarily white and silver aesthetic. The grade school-sized ASICS Gel-1130 White Midnight (GS) was released on March 3, 2024, and retailed at $85.

name: Dark Marina Blue
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Dark Marina Blue
description:
The Air Jordan 1 High Dark Marina Blue arrives with a smooth black leather upper with Dark Marina Blue overlays and Swooshes. On the ankle wrap, a black Jordan Wings logo pays homage to the origins of the Air Jordan 1. From there, a contrasting white and blue Air sole completes the design.

The Air Jordan 1 High Dark Marina Blue releases in February of 2022 and retails for $170.

name: Yellow Ochre
title: Jordan 6 Retro Yellow Ochre
description:
The Jordan 6 Retro Yellow Ochre changes up the color blocking introduced in the 2014 Air Jordan 6 Carmine release, all while delivering dependable support, comfort, and style. 

The Yellow Ochre colorway of the Air Jordan 6 Retro sports a base of yellow nubuck with perforations along the side panel for breathability. White tumbled leather overlays with perforations on the collar give this shoe its signature look. White laces criss-cross under a yellow neoprene lace cover adorned with a black Jumpman. A Jumpman also appears on the yellow lace lock. A yellow Jumpman graces the white heel just beneath a black and yellow synthetic pull tab for ease of on/off.

The aspect of these sneakers that we enjoy the most is the high-performance sole unit. The midsole constructed of black, white, and light gray polyurethane encapsulates an Air unit in the forefoot and houses a visible Air unit in the heel. The outsole of both translucent and matte white rubber sports traction lugs and a yellow Jumpman. The Jordan 6 Retro Yellow Ochre was released on January 27, 2024, for $200 retail.

name: Travis Scott Canary (TD)
title: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG SP Travis Scott Canary (TD)
description:
The Jordan 1 Retro Low OG SP Travis Scott Canary (TD) is a Special Project (SP) sneaker launched by American rapper Travis Scott and Jordan Brand. This means it’s crafted in the Nike lab using premium materials and design patterns.

This low-top sneaker boasts an all-leather upper construction with a light silver base and overlays in bright Canary. Although the reinforced stitching is tonal, it appears oversized due to the sneaker’s small size. Large Swoosh logos in Racer Blue check across the side panels, while a woven tongue tag bears "NIKE" lettering in crimson. The upper sits on a durable rubber outsole, which features a standard traction pattern and a Gum Medium Brown hue.

Our StockX experts like Travis Scott’s CACTUS JACK branding, which can be found beneath the Swoosh, on the inner side panel, in crimson ink. The toddler-sized Jordan 1 Retro Low OG SP Travis Scott Canary (TD) was launched on May 25, 2024, and sold for $50.

name: A Ma Maniére Dawn (Women's)
title: Jordan 5 Retro A Ma Maniére Dawn (Women's)
description:
Step into the dawn of a new era with the exclusive A Ma Maniére x Air Jordan 5 "Dawn". This collaboration infuses classic elegance with a street-ready edge. The leather upper pairs with a gleaming metallic silver tongue, preserving the silhouette's celebrated features like the prominent "23" on the heel and the distinctive shark teeth design. ​
​​
​Echoing the hues of early morning skies, the "Dawn" presents a color palette of Photon Dust, Black, Diffused Blue, and Pale Ivory. It's an all-new colorway, a testament to A Ma Maniére's finesse and Jordan's timeless appeal. The slimmed-down collar and pre-yellowed quarter panel netting, round out the exclusive design elements.​
​​
​Released on November 17, 2023, and priced at $225, this women's exclusive sneaker is a must-have for collectors and style mavens alike. Grab your pair and witness the rise of a new icon.

name: Field Purple
title: Jordan 12 Retro Field Purple
description:
Making a statement with vibrant color and unmistakable style, the Jordan 12 Retro Field Purple made its grand entrance on July 29, 2023. This colorway showcases a new aesthetic for the classic silhouette, pushing boundaries and setting trends.

The Jordan 12 Retro stands out with its bold field purple and black leather upper, giving the classic silhouette an unexpected twist. The sneaker's iconic design elements are amplified, from the unique eyelets to the distinctive '23' at the heel. This unique color contrast is sure to grab attention and turn heads.

The Jordan 12 Retro Field Purple was launched on July 29, 2023, with a retail price of $200.

name: Triple White
title: Jordan 1 Low Triple White
description:
The Air Jordan 1 Low Triple White 2022 is a silhouette that arrives in a monochromatic colorway.

The smooth white leather upper of this Low Air Jordan 1 has perforations in the toe box, white leather overlays, and a white leather Swoosh. This sneaker also features a white rubber cupsole and an Air-sole unit in the heel. A white debossed Jumpman appears on the white padded tongue, a black Jumpman boasts on the white insole, and an embroidered white Wings logo is displayed on the white heel.

The Air Jordan 1 Low Triple White 2022 was released on September 1st, 2022, at a price of $110.

name: Chicago Lost and Found (GS)
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Chicago Lost and Found (GS)
description:
The Jordan 1 Retro High OG Chicago Lost and Found (GS) arrives in the classic 1985 silhouette with a color scheme of varisity red, black, sail and muslin hues.
​
​This sneaker for grade-schooler´s upper is primarily white, with contrasting red and cracked black overlays. Besides the black Swooshes on the sides, the shoe also features "NIKE AIR" branding on the muslin tongues, Wings on the collars, and printed insoles. White midsoles and contrasting red rubber outsoles complete the design.
​
​The Jordan 1 Retro High OG Chicago Lost and Found (GS) was released on the 19th of November 2022 and originally retail for $140.

name: Keep Rippin Stop Slippin 2.0
title: Nike Air Max 1 Keep Rippin Stop Slippin 2.0
description:
The Nike Air Max 1 Keep Rippin Stop Slippin 2.0, originally introduced in 2008, makes a return featuring a gray mesh foundation complemented by off-white suede overlays along the medial side and black hairy suede mudguards.

The Air Max 1 Keep Rippin Stop Slippin 2.0 introduces a modern twist to the original by integrating safari print onto the mudguard and Swoosh, achieved through the use of long hairy suede. Vast Gray emerges as the primary color for the mesh base, while Pearl White embellishes the suede overlays on the midfoot, heel, and vamp. Black details stand out on the lace set and sections of hairy suede, with reddish cedar accents appearing on the mini Swoosh located on the mudguard, sock liner, and the embroidery of Keep Rip'n Stop Slip'n on the heel.

The standout characteristic of the Nike Air Max 1 Keep Rippin Stop Slippin 2.0 are the embroidered phrases "Keep Rip’n" and "Stop Slip’n" in red on the heel. The sneaker debuted for $160 on November 28th, 2023.

name: Chestnut (Kids)
title: UGG Tazz Slipper Chestnut (Kids)
description:
The UGG Tazz Slipper Chestnut (Kids) adopts the silhouette of its predecessor, the Tasman, but introduces bold features, including a SugarSole EVA outsole and midsole with a combined height of one inch.

A chestnut colorway adorns this UGG Tazz Slipper for kids. On the upper, this slipper clads a suede material with a plush matte finish. Across the vamp is a raised knit boundary running from the toe tip. There is an embossed UGG branding embellishing the lateral side. The collar breaks from the monochrome chestnut hue, and it introduces a colorful finish with a Tasman braid made from recycled polyester in white and dark red colors. A vibrantly colored pull tab adorns the heel counter.

What stands out in the UGG Tazz Slipper Chestnut (Kids)? We like the white, comfy lining of this slipper, made from UGGplush recycled wool. The vamp features lyocell lining, while the insole clads in wool and additional branding in red. When this slipper was released on January 25th, 2023, it retailed at $85.

name: Black Racer Blue
title: Nike Air Max Plus Premium Black Racer Blue
description:
The Nike Air Max Plus Premium Black Racer Blue displays a color gradient from black to Phantom to Racer Blue and the shoe’s signature TPU overlays.

The Black Racer Bule Nike Air Max Plus Premium was inspired by nature, where the overlays take on a wavy design that emulates waves or swaying palm trees. They create the feeling of movement across the upper and support the airy mesh. Another nature-inspired element is the midfoot arch, which supports the foot and resembles a whale’s tale. Starting from the heel, the upper fades from black to Racer Blue with a genuine leather mudguard in black wrapping around the shoe. The sole unit includes visible Nike Air units that offer lightweight support and give the sneaker a technical appearance.

Our experts like the bright white Swoosh logos on the side panels. Even though they’re small, in our option, these iconic logos are all the branding the shoe needs. The Nike Air Max Plus Premium Black Racer Blue was released on July 14, 2024, and sold for $190.

name: Chicago Split
title: Nike Dunk Low Chicago Split
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Chicago Split boasts a fierce colorway combo of University Red, Black, Light Silver, and White. This sneaker dropped on July 14, 2023. Challenging conventional aesthetics, this Dunk Low model remixes a classic silhouette with a split color design, creating a bold contrast that demands attention.

The upper features university red and white on the medial and lateral sides respectively, with light silver and black dressing the Swoosh logo lending the design its 'split' distinction. A clean white midsole offset the strong, contrasting colors, and a black and white outsole completes the design.

The Nike Dunk Low Chicago Split hit the shelves on July 14, 2023, at a retail price of $110.

name: Photo Blue
title: Nike Dunk Low Retro Photo Blue
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Retro Photo Blue applies a crisp colorway to the standard Dunk Low Retro silhouette.

While the upper features Summit White leather with Platinum White overlays, the accents come in electric Photon Blue. For example, the Swoosh logos on the side panels and the rubber outsole boast Photon Blue. This color can also be found on the insole, the tongue’s woven logo tag, and the ‘NIKE’ lettering embroidered across the heel tab. Like other versions of the Dunk Low Retro, the "Photo Blue" iteration comes with perforations across the vamp that allow the foot to breathe. This low-top sneaker offers a front lace closure with Crisp White laces that match the midsole.

Our experts at StockX appreciate the way the sneaker subtly displays tri-tone color-blocking. This feature sets it apart from earlier iterations of the Dunk Low Retro. The Nike Dunk Low Retro Photo Blue was released on February 13th, 2024, and sold for $115.

name: Black White Anthracite
title: Nike Air Max 97 Black White Anthracite
description:
Featuring Max Air cushioning and a durable design, the Nike Air Max 97 Black White Anthricite brings a 90’s favorite to a new generation. The Nike Air Max 97 Black White Anthricite takes on a blend of materials, including reflective piping, water ripple lines, and full-length Max Air cushioning. The synthetic upper is lightweight yet durable, and it’s served up with welded overlays and a rubber outsole for traction. For the season, the Nike Air Max 97 Black White Anthricite takes on a black and white look, with the Swoosh done in white.

The Nike Air Max 97 Black White Anthricite was released in October 2019 and retailed for $160.

name: Hyper Royal Smoke Grey
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Hyper Royal
description:
The Air Jordan 1 Retro High Hyper Royal features a white leather upper with fading blue suede overlays.
​
​The Swoosh and padded collar have neutral grey contrast accents, adding to the vintage-inspired aesthetic. A stitched Nike tongue tag and a Jordan Wings logo are branding elements on the lateral collar flap. The high-top shoe has encapsulated Nike Air units and is mounted on a regular AJ1 rubber cup sole. A white midsole, a Light Smoke Grey outsole, and a blue woven Nike Air branding embroidered on the tongue are the final details.
​
​The Air Jordan 1 Retro High Hyper Royal debuted on 7 July 2018 and retailed at $160.

name: Obsidian Summit White
title: Nike P-6000 Obsidian Summit White
description:
The Nike P-6000 Obsidian Summit White adds an upper dressed in a selection of white hues and accents in dark Obsidian to the P-6000 silhouette.

Inspired by running sneakers from the early 2000s, the Obsidian Summit White Nike P-6000 is designed for comfort. The breathable mesh upper in Phantom allows the foot to breathe, while genuine and synthetic leather overlays in Summit White provide structure and contribute to the sneaker’s 2000s aesthetic. Another comfort-first feature is the foam midsole, which adds lightweight cushioning underfoot. Obsidian creates contrast on the Swoosh, the rubber outsole, and the laces. In addition, the "NIKE" lettering printed on the tongue, the Swoosh on the heel, and the "P-6000" on the overlays come in Obsidian.

Our experts like the molded synthetic leather Swoosh logo on the side panel because it gives the sneaker dimension. The Nike P-6000 Obsidian Summit White was released on June 6, 2024, and sold for $110.

name: Metallic Gold (Women's)
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Metallic Gold (Women's)
description:
The Jordan 1 Retro High OG Metallic Gold (Women's) adds gold details and a white leather upper to the iconic Jordan 1 silhouette.

The sneaker features a retro, high-top design, inspired by the original Air Jordan 1, with leather overlays in Tonal White. Metallic Gold can be found across the Swooshes on the side panels, around the collar, and on the Jordan Wings logo. In addition, the tongue boasts a logo tag with a clean white base and Metallic Gold stitching. Like other versions of the Jordan 1 Retro High OG, the Metallic Gold variation features perforations across the vamp that allow the foot to breathe. The rubber outsole comes in Gum Light Brown and complements the gold accents.

Our StockX experts like the gold-tone lace charm, which hangs from a metal chain and displays Nike Air branding. The women’s size Jordan 1 Retro High OG Metallic Gold (Women's) was released on February 14th, 2024, and retailed at $180.

name: Paris
title: Jordan 1 Low Paris
description:
The Jordan 1 Low Paris features a white, Sky Grey, and Football Grey textile, leather, and suede upper, with smooth leather making a minimal appearance in white on the quarter panels of the shoe. From there, the collar and tongue of the silhouette are both outfitted in sporty textiles and a debossed "Air Jordan" logo with a grey Nike "Swoosh" complete the design.

The Jordan 1 Low Paris released in February of 2020 and retailed for $130.

name: Ascent Pack MX Grey
title: adidas AE 1 Low Ascent Pack MX Grey
description:
The adidas AE 1 Low MX Gray is a creation from NBA player Anthony Edwards that boasts a sleek silhouette and a marbled pattern on the TPU side panels.

The basketball sneaker MX Gray adidas AE 1 Low features a mesh upper in Core Black that complements the Silver Pebble and Wonder Beige found on the TPU side panels and the rubber outsole. Featuring a honeycomb-like construction, the TPU side panels provide airflow and contribute to the sneaker’s eye-catching design. The ultra-lightweight midsole promotes energy return with LightStrike and Boost technologies, while the rubber outsole's herringbone pattern provides superior traction. Finally, the rubberized 3-Stripes logo in Silver Pebble adorns the molded heel.

Our experts at StockX appreciate Anthony Edward’s subtle branding elements, including the woven tongue tag that displays the athlete’s signature stylized anthill logo. The adidas AE 1 Low MX Gray was released on July 20, 2024, and sold for $110.

name: Bleached Coral
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Bleached Coral
description:
Following the classic Black Toe theme, the Air Jordan 1 High OG Bleached Coral features a smooth white leather upper with black overlays and light grey Durabuck heel wraps. Tradition Nike woven tongue labels and Jordan Wings Logos on the collars add a retro feel. From there, a white and light grey Air sole completes the design.

The Air Jordan 1 High OG Bleached Coral releases in July of 2022 and retails for $180.

name: Silver Green Putty Mauve (Women's)
title: adidas Samba OG Silver Green Putty Mauve (Women's)
description:
The adidas Samba OG Silver Green Putty Mauve (Women’s) is a women’s sneaker that takes design inspiration from the original 1950s indoor soccer shoe.

This version of the adidas Samba OG is made with a white leather upper, featuring hairy suede detailing in a beige color. The suede detailing lines the toebox, runs up the middle, and under the laces. The iconic three stripes appear on the midsole in green and the word "SAMBA" tracks on top of the first stripe in black. The green tongue features an adidas logo patch, while the cushioned heel also appears in the same shade of green. The rubber outsole allows for traction, and the shoe is made from at least 20% recycled materials.

What we like most about this shoe is the hairy suede detailing, which gives the otherwise simple design a touch of uniqueness. The adidas Samba OG Silver Green Putty Mauve (Women’s) was first released on March 8, 2024, for a price of $100.

name: Why So Sad?
title: Nike SB Dunk Low Pro Why So Sad?
description:
The Nike SB Dunk Low Pro Why So Sad features a mixture of colors, with coastal blue and light current blue being the dominant hues.

The upper of this Low Nike SB Dunk is made from leather material and there is a white Fat-style SB lacing system. The lateral heel of this shoe features an embroidered chicken that seems to be riding on a skateboard. Additionally, the heels and the tongues of this sneaker have Nike SB branding.

The Nike SB Dunk Low Pro Why So Sad retailed at a price of $120 at the time of its release on November 4, 2022.

name: Geode
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Geode
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Geode is a collaboration product between adidas and music icon Kanye West’s Yeezy brand. Initially released as a Yeezy supply exclusive in 2021, this colorway had a wider launch in Spring 2022.

Unique in appearance, this colorway features a lilac nylon upper, with the 700 branding on the lateral side. It also features tongues, laces, and a collar done in a charcoal hue. These highlights lie atop an enclosed Boost Black Sole Unit.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Geode was widely launched on the 19th of April, 2022. At the time of its release, this shoe commanded a retail price of $220.

name: Black Leopard (Women's)
title: adidas Campus 00s Black Leopard (Women's)
description:
The adidas Campus 00s Black Leopard (Women’s) presents the bulky Campus 00s silhouette with a Core Black base and leopard print details.

Like other versions of the adidas Campus 00s, the "Black Leopard" variation has extra padding around the collar, which gives it a chunk aesthetic like skateboarding shoes from the early 2000s. The round toe and thick cotton laces also contribute to the sneaker’s retro skater look. The upper is crafted from Core Black leather, while the serrated 3-Stripes logo displays leopard print. The leather heel tab balances out the eye-catching leopard print with Wonder Beige. Three branding details can be found on the exterior: a trefoil logo on the tongue, "campus" lettering, and a trefoil on the heel tab.

Our experts at StockX like the perforations between the 3-Stripes logo because they allow the foot to breathe. The women’s size adidas Campus 00s Black Leopard (Women’s) was released on June 11, 2023, and sold for $110.

name: Bacon (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low PRM Bacon (Women's)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low PRM Bacon (Women’s) presents an exclusive colorway for women, drawing inspiration from the iconic 2004 release of the Air Max 90 "Bacon."

Showcasing a Sail tumbled leather foundation, the Nike Dunk Low PRM Bacon (Women’s) is enhanced by Sport Red suede eyestays and overlays. Touches of Sheen Pink adorn the mesh tongues and leather Swooshes, while Medium Brown accents on the heel tabs and tongue labels add vibrancy to the design. The low-top silhouette is positioned on a classic cupsole, featuring white sidewalls and a brown rubber outsole.

A distinctive aspect of the Nike Dunk Low PRM Bacon (Women’s) is its unique color palette. This particular Dunk Low pays homage to its celebrated predecessor, boasting a vibrant color scheme and incorporating iconic design elements. The combination of these features makes the shoe a standout and appealing addition to the Nike Dunk Low collection. The sneaker debuted for $125 on December 21st, 2023.

name: Nightmare
title: Nike Ja 2 Nightmare
description:
The Nike Ja 2 Nightmare is focused on all the aspects that made Ja Morant an NBA star. It's designed to provide lots of responsive support for quick turns, with a bouncy feel in the sole to help you get up high.

This model upgrades the Nike Ja 1 with extra padding at the ankles and a characteristic waterfall collar lining. The nightmare colorway features a shiny red upper with contrasting black swathes that give a racing stripes effect. The under-sole traction pattern is modeled on the lorry tires that Ja trained with as a youngster.

Our experts like this new version of a shoe that made a real splash when it was first introduced. It's extremely visually attractive, but what makes it special is the underlying technology. It features modern gizmos like a sidewall guardrail and a dynamic ankle sleeve for optimal on-court performance. The Nike Ja 2 Nightmare was released on 25 October 2024 and retailed at $120.

name: Valentine's Day (2024) (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Valentine's Day (2024) (Women's)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Valentine's Day (2024) (Women's) reconfigures the colors and fabrics of a classic silhouette. The bold, romantic colors of this sneaker specifically sized for women complement the Nike Dunk dependability.

The Women's Valentine's Day 2024 version of the Low-Top Nike Dunk features an upper with rich, red suede overlays atop a white leather base. Red also appears on the laces, sock liner with the padded collar, and rubber outsole with a circular traction pattern that facilitates pivots. The insole is deep red, with white Nike branding, and the red heel sports embroidered red-on-red Nike branding. The white hue is echoed on the tongue and on the foam midsole, which provides cushioning and impact absorption.

The aspect of this sneaker that delights us the most is the burgundy-colored Nike swoosh with a faint red lining that courses across the side of the shoe, providing contrast and eye-catching style. The Nike Dunk Low Valentine's Day (2024) (Women's) was released on January 23, 2024, for $115.

name: Suede Black
title: Birkenstock Boston Soft Footbed Suede Black
description:
The Birkenstock Boston Soft Footbed Suede Black is a version of the recognizable Birkenstock Boston clog model that comes with an upper and footbed lining made of soft suede.

One element that makes this shoe stand out is the inclusion of an additional foam layer in the footbed. This provides additional comfort and reduces the impact caused by walking. The clog comes with an adjustable suede strap, which can be loosened or tightened with a metal buckle. Although the branding elements are minimal, ‘BIRKENSTOCK’ is embossed on the lateral side, and ‘BIRKENSTOCK’ can also be found on the metal buckle. The clog boasts an EVA sole that is both flexible and durable.

Our experts at StockX love the contrast between the black sole, the black upper, and the tan-toned footbed. The Birkenstock Boston Soft Footbed Suede Black was released on June 30, 2023, and retailed at $155.

name: Dusty Olive
title: Nike Dunk Low Dusty Olive
description:
Dusty Olive, brown, and Pro Gold suede make up the majority of the Nike Dunk Low Dusty Olive’s upper. Brown canvas wraps around the heel leading to a white embroidered "NIKE" logo resting on a Pro Gold suede heel tab. A Pro Gold outsole and white midsole finish up this new Nike Dunk retro.

The Nike Dunk Low Dusty Olive released in June of 2021 for $110, and again in November of 2023 for $120.

name: Collegiate Red Lucid Pink (Women's)
title: adidas Gazelle Bold Collegiate Red Lucid Pink (Women's)
description:
The adidas Gazelle Bold Collegiate Red Lucid Pink (Women's) adds a bold colorway of Collegiate Red and Lucid Pink to the Gazelle Bold silhouette.

Like previous iterations of the Gazelle Bold, the Collegiate Red Lucid Pink version sits on a triple-stacked gum rubber sole. Each layered sole displays adidas lettering and a trefoil debossed into the material near the heel. In addition, the soles fade from light to dark gum. The upper is constructed from suede in Collegiate Red with splashes of Lucid Pink on the 3-Stripes logo, the heel counter, and the laces. In addition, a Lucid Pink adidas tag is printed across the flat, white tongue.

Our StockX experts like that the upper design stays true to the original streamlined Gazelle from the 1970s. The women’s size adidas Gazelle Bold Collegiate Red Lucid Pink (Women's) was released on April 7, 2024, and retailed at $120.

name: Monaco Blue
title: ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Monaco Blue
description:
The ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Monaco Blue is an updated version of the Gel-Kayano 14 featuring a late 2000s aesthetic with newer technology. This iteration was the first shoe in the line to be designed by someone other than Toshikazu Kayano.

This version of the ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 is made of a Monaco Blue mesh upper with synthetic leather overlays appearing in silver and Slack across the midsole. The toe is also rounded out by a silver overlay. The shoe features original GEL technology for shock absorption and cushioning. The sock liner is also produced in a way that reduces carbon emissions by 45%, so this shoe is also more sustainable than other models.

What we like most about this sneaker is the Monaco Blue base and the pops of the same shade that appear on the rubber outsole. These notes of color make the otherwise basic shoe stand out. The ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Monaco Blue was first released on August 26th, 2021, at a retail price of $160.

name: Grinch
title: Nike Vapor Edge Kobe 6 SE Grinch
description:
The Nike Vapor Edge Kobe 6 SE Grinch dresses the Vapor Edge Kobe 6 in a vibrant green colorway inspired by Dr. Seuss’s beloved Christmas character.

The Grinch Nike Vapor Edge Kobe 6 SE reimagines Kobe Bryant’s recognizable basketball shoe for the football field. For instance, it boasts sturdy studs placed across the outsole plate in a wide pattern. However, what makes this sneaker stand out is its Grinch-inspired colors, including Green Apple and Volt. The upper features a layer of durable TPU and snake-skin patterns in Green Apple. Adding contrast, black Swoosh logos reach across the side panels, while Bryant’s signature sheathed sword logo in Bright Crimson decorates the tongue. Other Bright Crimson details can be found on Bryant’s signature and details across the outsole.

Our experts at StockX appreciate the shoe’s form-fitting design supported by Vaper Edge technology underfoot. The Nike Vapor Edge Kobe 6 SE Grinch was released on November 22, 2024, and sold for $230.

name: Silver Green (Women's)
title: adidas Samba OG Silver Green (Women's)
description:
The adidas Samba OG Silver Green Womens combines the classic Samba style with rich neutral colors. It has the brand’s go-to rubber gum sole, as well as a body made from suede.

The Silver Green Samba OG model is a colorway that was made exclusively for the brand’s women’s line. It has the original Samba model that was designed by adidas founder Adi Dassler himself. The bottom of the shoe has a neutral-colored gum sole. The body of this sneaker is made from a mixture of suede and leather that are in a rich, earthy, green color.

A feature that our experts enjoy about this model is the 3-Stripes with a serrated design that are on the side, as they help the green color of the base to pop. The adidas Samba OG Silver Green Womens was first released on August 9th, 2023, and had a starting retail price of $110.

name: Sea Salt Moonbeam
title: New Balance 530 Sea Salt Moonbeam
description:
The New Balance 530 Sea Salt Moonbeam, inspired by retro aesthetics, embraces a laid-back style crafted with lightweight mesh uppers, durable synthetic overlays, and the iconic ABZORB midsole for both support and comfort.

With a palette of pastel beige tones adorning the uppers, the Sea Salt Moonbeam New Balance 530 achieves a stylish Y2K aesthetic, featuring a synthetic overlay and breathable mesh. Enhanced with plush ABZORB cushioning underfoot, a technology engineered to absorb impact effectively, and robust traction rubber outsoles, these running shoes showcase the brand's unmistakable "N" logos along the sidewalls. Additional brand detailing includes the "NB" tongue patch, the "530" tag on the lateral side, and the "N" logo on the toe.

The standout characteristic of the New Balance 530 Sea Salt Moonbeam lies in its remarkable ABZORB cushioning underfoot. This feature, designed to absorb impact, ensures unparalleled comfort for the wearer, making these shoes ideal for any daily pursuits. The sneaker debuted for $100 on October 10th, 2023.

name: J Balvin
title: Jordan 2 Retro J Balvin
description:
The Air Jordan 2 Retro J Balvin is a sneaker that came to be as a result of a collaboration between Nike and J Balvin to help tell the story of his mental health journey.

The Retro J Balvin Air Jordan 2 has an energetic blue color scheme and is coupled with cloud graphics on the heel counter and sock liner. The pair of sneakers has rainbow stitching throughout the entirety of the shoe and J Balvin’s signature smiley face branding on the heel. It also features a light-up Wings logo on the tongue that illuminates when pressed.

The Air Jordan 2 Retro J Balvin was released on the 15th of September, 2022, with its retail price set at $300.

Please note: the light up tongues on the Air Jordan 2 Retro J Balvin's are not replaceable or rechargeable (and thus may not light up).

name: Mural
title: adidas AE 1 Low Mural
description:
The adidas AE 1 Low Mural paints the AE 1’s signature TPU support cage in Acid Red, contrasting the rich Core Black upper.

Originally worn by NBA player Anthony Edwards during Game 1 of the 2024 NBA Playoffs, the basketball shoe boasts an ultra-lightweight knit upper and TPU overlays with a honeycomb pattern. The geometric, honeycomb pattern allows the foot to breathe while providing structure to the upper. The Mural adidas AE 1 Low sports several personalized elements, including Anthony Edward’s signature on the tongue’s woven tag. In terms of branding, a rubberized 3-Stripes logo appears on the heel in Acid Orange. The rubber outsole also comes in Acid Orange, which blends with the Acid Red TPU cage to create a sorbet-like effect.

Our experts like the choice of simple black laces because it allows the rest of the design to standout. The adidas AE 1 Low Mural was released on August 5, 2024, and sold for $110.

name: White Swoosh Panda
title: Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 White Swoosh Panda
description: The Nike Air Force 1 07 Low White Swoosh Panda is a stylish and versatile sneaker that combines classic design with modern features. The shoe features a white leather upper with black accents and a panda graphic on the heel. The iconic Nike Swoosh is also featured in white on the sides. The shoe is made with high-quality materials, including a durable rubber sole and a comfortable foam midsole. The release date for this shoe is January 31, 2023, and with a retail price of $130. Whether you're looking for a casual everyday shoe or a stylish addition to your sneaker collection, the Nike Air Force 1 07 Low White Swoosh Panda is a great choice.

name: Aquarius Blue
title: Nike Air Max Plus Aquarius Blue
description:
The Nike Air Max Plus Aquarius Blue applies a watery color gradient of Aquarius Blue to the Air Max Plus silhouette.​
​​
​Like other versions of the Nike Air Max Plus, the "Aquarius Blue" iteration features a plastic cage across the upper that resembles waves, ripples, or even palm fronds. Originally designed as a performance running shoe, this sneaker boasts a breathable mesh and synthetic upper with Air units underfoot. The Air units provide lightweight cushioning that doesn’t weigh down the foot. In addition, the rubber outsole offers traction and works with the supportive midfoot arch. This design mimics the shape of a whale’s tail and adds another technical element to the sneaker.​
​​
​Our StockX experts like the polished rubber toe cap because it catches the light and stands out from the textile mudguard elements. The Nike Air Max Plus Aquarius Blue was released on December 12th, 2023, and retailed at $180.

name: Atmosphere (Women's)
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Atmosphere (Women's)
description:
The women's Air Jordan 1 High Atmosphere follows the classic Black Toe color blocking format with a white and dark navy leather upper. Light pink patent leather on the ankle and vamp nods to the pink bubblegum that Michael Jordan chewed throughout his time on the hardwood. Woven Nike tongue labels and a signature Jordan Wings logo draw inspiration from the original 1985 Jordan 1 design.

The women's Air Jordan 1 High Atmosphere released in December of 2021 and retailed for $170.

name: Jubilee 25th Anniversary
title: Jordan 11 Retro Jubilee 25th Anniversary
description:
In 2020, Jordan Brand celebrated 25 years of one of their most popular models, the Jordan 11. To commemorate the famed silhouette, Michael Jordan and Nike released the Jordan 11 Jubilee. The sneaker’s distinct colorway was inspired by original sketches from the designer of the 1995 sneaker, Tinker Hatfield.

The Jordan 11 Jubilee showcases everything Hatfield envisioned for the sneaker 25 years ago; a performance product that can be worn easily both on and off the court. Features such as the two types of leather on the upper with hits of metallic lettering and Jumpman emblem add luxe elements to the athletic sneaker. A white midsole and foggy translucent outsole deliver contrast to the black sneaker. Carbon fiber plating on the sole provides stability and power to the wearer’s feet on the court.

The Jordan 11 Jubilee 25th Anniversary released in December of 2020 for $220.

name: Ashen Slate
title: Jordan 1 Low Ashen Slate
description:
The Air Jordan 1 Low Ashen Slate tread and cushioning provide basic comfort and support. This shoe is ideal for everyday life, as well as light exercise and walking about.

This specific model has a black sole and a white midsole. The shoe features a white base with gray leather overlays. The Nike swoosh shape can be seen in a darker blue, with the same blue used for the tongue and the lining of the shoe.

The Air Jordan 1 Low Ashen Slate first was released onto the market in May of 2022. The retail price for this item started at $110.

name: A Ma Maniére
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG A Ma Maniére
description:
The Air Jordan 1 A Ma Maniére features a premium cracked leather upper with burgundy reptilian-textural leather collars and Swooshes. Silky quilted lining and custom woven tongue and insole labels add a sense of luxury. At the base, a yellowed sole provides a vintage feel to complete the design.

The Air Jordan 1 A Ma Maniére released in November of 2021 and retailed for $200.

name: Grey White (Women's)
title: adidas Gazelle Bold Grey White (Women's)
description:
The adidas Gazelle Bold Gray White (Women's) was originally crafted as an all-around training show. However, it’s attention to comfort along with its minimalist design have made it a footwear favorite in both sports and casual lifestyle alike.

It features a suede upper in a solid gray hue, which provides a versatile and neutral base for the shoe. Contrasting white details pop in the iconic three stripes on the sides, the heel, the lacing system, and the tongue. The low-top design and cushioned insole deliver all-day comfort and freedom of movement. A padded collar and tongue offer additional support around the ankle, and a durable rubber outsole with a textured pattern provides reliable traction.

What our experts love most about the adidas Gazelle Bold Grey White (Women's) is the subtle branding, from the Trefoil logo on the tongue to the embossed "adidas" on the sole, to the metallic "Gazelle" running adjacent to the three stripe pattern on the sides. These shoes originally retailed for $120 when they first released on December 13, 2022.

name: Olivine
title: New Balance 9060 Olivine
description:
The New Balance 9060 Olivine is a sneaker that pays homage to the design of the 99X model with several modern and futuristic updates.

This iteration of the New Balance 9060 is made with a high-quality leather and breathable mesh upper. Light olive green mesh forms the base of the upper, while leather and synthetic overlays adorn the midsole, toe, and heel in different shades of green. The New Balance "N" logo appears on the midsoles under the laces, with one of them being solid white outlined in green and the other being made up of white dashes. The heel collar is a dark olive green and displays the "NB" logo, while the "NB 9060" logo appears on the tongue. The durable rubber outsole provides excellent grip, while the sole is cushioned with ABZORB cushioning.

Our favorite feature of this shoe is the muted green colorway. This allows the shoe to exude style and functionality in a subtle way. The New Balance 9060 Olivine was released on March 30, 2024, for a retail price of $160.

name: Bred Toe 2.0
title: Jordan 1 Low Bred Toe 2.0
description:
The Jordan 1 Low Bred Toe 2.0 is a popular sneaker model from the Jordan Brand, a subsidiary of Nike. It is a low-top re-imagination of the Air Jordan 1 shoe, a model that was initially released for sale in the 1980s as the signature shoe for the legendary basketball player Michael Jordan.

This Bred Toe 2.0 model maintains the same design elements and style as the high-top version but features a lower cut, making it a more casual and versatile option. The Jordan 1 Lows are crafted from a variety of materials, including leather, suede, and synthetic materials. The use of different materials allows for a range of color and texture variations. This model has a color range that is composed of black, white, and red.

A feature that our team of experts particularly likes about the Jordan 1 Low Bred Toe 2.0 model is the dark red gum sole that allows for both traction and comfort. This model was first released on September 29th of 2023 for a starting price of $115.

name: Action Bronson Medusa Azul
title: New Balance 1906R Action Bronson Medusa Azul
description:
Created as part of American rapper Action Bronson’s second series with New Balance, the New Balance 1906R Action Bronson Medusa Azul adds cool blue tones and rich earthy hues to the recognizable 1906R silhouette.

While the Action Bronson Medusa Azul New Balance 1906R boasts all the technical features associated with the 1906R, including segmented ABZORB SBS pods beneath the heel and flexible cushioning in the midsole, the "Medusa Azul" colorway makes it stand out from other models. The upper construction features light blue mesh as the base, golden brown mesh below the ‘N’ logo, and synthetic overlays in light grayish purple. Co-branding details decorate the tongue, the insole, and the silicone hangtag, while durable boot laces secure the front closure system.

Our experts at StockX like the colorblocking on the midsole and outsole, which highlights the ABZORB SBS pods and other technical features. The New Balance 1906R Action Bronson Medusa Azul was released on June 21, 2024, and retailed at $185.

name: Laser Fuchsia (GS)
title: Nike Dunk Low Laser Fuchsia (GS)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Laser Fuchsia (GS) offers an iconic silhouette dressed in a crisp, clean, dual colorway that Nike rolled out exclusively for kids. This sneaker sized specifically for grade school kids will garner attention on the playground with its eye-popping colors.

The Laser Fuchsia Nike Dunk Low-Top for Grade School kids sports classic color blocking that starts with a pristine base of white leather with signature perforations in the toe box. This white is echoed in the leather heel tab, the laces, the tongue, and the mesh sock liner. Overlays of smooth fuchsia leather adorn this shoe, providing hits of bright contrast. The insole is also bright pink with white Nike branding, and fuchsia Nike branding adorns the heel and woven tongue tag.

What we enjoy most about this colorful sneaker is the way the sole unit locks in the colorway. The white foam midsole with tonal stitching and the fuchsia rubber outsole with pivot traction lock in the iconic look of this shoe. The Nike Dunk Low Laser Fuchsia (GS) was released on October 24, 2022, for $90 retail.

name: Dune Red
title: Jordan 13 Retro Dune Red
description:
The Jordan 13 Retro Dune Red reintroduces the Air Jordan 13 Retro silhouette with an updated combination of colors and materials.

Instead of tumbled or pebbled leather, the dimpled overlays are a texturized textile in Dune Red. In addition, the upper is synthetic leather and microfiber, which provide a softer finish than animal-derived materials can produce. Terra Blush accents are on the microfiber and a panel along the midsole. Like other Jordan 13 Retro models, this version displays the signature holographic eye on the medial heel. In terms of branding, the padded tongue boasts a Jumpman logo in Dune Red, and the area beneath the laces houses a Dune Red "JORDAN" logo tag with white lettering.

Our StockX experts like the paw-like outsole, which pays tribute to Michael Jordan’s "Black Cat" alter ego. The Jordan 13 Retro Dune Red was released on June 25, 2024, and retailed at $210.

name: Summit White Light Smoke Grey
title: Nike Dunk Low Retro Summit White Light Smoke Grey
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Retro Summit White Light Smoke Gray takes the Nike Dunk Low basketball-inspired silhouette and upgrades it with a white and gray colorway.

The low-top sneaker features leather underlays in Summit White with leather overlays in Light Smoke Gray. As seen on other Nike Dunk Low Retro models, the color difference between the overlays and underlays on the "Summit White Light Smoke Gray" variation creates a color-blocking effect. In terms of branding, a medium-gray Swoosh reaches across the side panels, the tongue displays a Nike logo tag, and the heel features ‘NIKE’ embroidered in light gray thread.

Our StockX experts like the slightly darker gray tone on the rubber outsole. It contrasts the lighter tones on the subdued upper without distracting from the design. The Nike Dunk Low Retro Summit White Light Smoke Gray was released on March 1st, 2024, and retailed at $115.

name: CO.JP Reverse Ultraman (2024)
title: Nike Dunk Low QS CO.JP Reverse Ultraman (2024)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low QS CO.JP Reverse Ultraman (2024) is part of the CO.JP series and boasts a heritage colorway of Varsity Red and silver.

Although the colorway was first seen in 1999, it’s not the only heritage element applied to the Dunk Low QS CO.JP Reverse Ultraman (2024). The sneaker boasts signature color blocking, including a Varsity Red base with forefoot and toe overlays in silver. In addition, the laces, Swoosh logos on the side panels, and rubber outsole also come in silver. Branding details include "NIKE" in red printed across the heel tab and silver "NIKE" lettering on the Varsity Red tongue tag. This sneaker has the "Quickstrike (QS)" designation, which means it was released by Nike in a limited quantity.

Our experts like the layer of white on the midsole, which balances out the bold color blocking. The Nike Dunk Low QS CO.JP Reverse Ultraman (2024) was released on May 3, 2024, and retailed at $125.

name: Stone Island Dark Green
title: New Balance 574 Legacy Stone Island Dark Green
description:
The New Balance 574 Legacy Stone Island Dark Green is part of a collaboration between New Balance and Stone Island, a luxury menswear label based in Ravarino, Italy, that reinterprets the New Balance 574 silhouette.

In keeping with Stone Island’s design aesthetic, this New Balance 574 Legacy is crafted from premium yet durable materials, including ripstop fabric and velvety nubuck. While the dark green, brown, and khaki colorway has military influences, the sneaker also incorporates design details from Stone Islands' 1980s catalog. Stone Islands’ recognizable compass logo acts as a tongue tag, while "NEW BALANCE" can be found on the heel tab, and the "N" is made from a rubberized material.

Our StockX experts like the "STONE ISLAND PRODUCT RESEARCH" lettering, which pays tribute to the research the brand puts into developing and applying high-quality materials. The New Balance 574 Legacy Stone Island Dark Green was released on June 14, 2024, and retailed for $140.

name: Infrared
title: Jordan 4 Retro Infrared
description:
The Air Jordan 4 Infrared features a tonal grey Durabuck upper with black TPU mesh inserts, tech straps, and heel tabs. Hits of Infrared on the lacing system and woven Jordan Flight tongue label add a sharp contrast to the neutral-toned base. From there, a white sole with visible Air units completes the design.

The Air Jordan 4 Infrared released in June of 2022 and retailed for $200.

name: Triple White (GS)
title: Nike Air Force 1 Low LE Triple White (GS)
description:
The Nike Air Force 1 Low LE Triple White GS  features triple white leather upper perforations on the toebox as well as two perforations under each Swoosh. The Swoosh and overlays are also white leather. The outsole is white with a concentric-circles pattern and stars in the rubber. The midsole is white with a hidden Air compartment. The midsole says "AIR" in white. A silver tab saying "AF1" is on the top of the white laces.

This grade school-sized shoe, the Nike Air Force 1 Low LE Triple White GS, was released on April 13, 2021 at a retail price of $90.

name: Stone Taupe
title: adidas Yeezy Foam RNR Stone Taupe
description:
The adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Stone Taupe is a part of the Yeezy line, which is a collaborative partnership between adidas and the American hip-hop artist Kanye West.​
​​
​The upper of the Yeezy Foam RNNR in Stone Taupe is made from a material called Foamposite, which is known for its durability and lightweight feel. It provides a snug fit that is comfortable for all-day wear. The shoe also has a laceless design, with a slip-on construction that makes it easy to put on and take off. The outsole of the shoe has a grooved texture that provides traction on both wet and dry surfaces.​
​​
​We think that one of the most impressive features of the adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Stone Taupe is its unique sole unit. The shoe features a mix of adidas' classic Boost technology and a foam sole. This combination provides the perfect balance of cushioning and responsiveness, while also keeping the shoe lightweight and comfortable. The adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Stone Taupe was released on August 30th, 2023 at a retail price of $90.​
​​
​

name: Core Black White
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Core Black White
description:
The adidas Yeezy 350 V2 Core Black White features a simple black Primeknit upper with "SPLY-350" text on a cream side stripe. From there, responsive Boost technology in the sole offers comfort and support.

The adidas Yeezy 350 V2 Core Black White released in December of 2016, and restocked in March of 2022 for $220.

name: Reverse Grinch (GS)
title: Nike Kobe 6 Protro Reverse Grinch (GS)
description: DISCLAIMER: All Grade School Nike Kobe 6 Protro Reverse Grinch's will come in the standard Nike orange box.

name: Triple Black
title: adidas Ultra Boost 1.0 DNA Triple Black
description:
The adidas Ultra Boost 1.0 DNA Triple Black is a new colorway of the Ultra Boost 1.0 DNA line of sneakers.

The Ultra Boost 1.0 DNA Triple Black features a Primeknit upper that is both flexible and breathable, allowing for a snug fit that will keep your feet comfortable and supported no matter how long your run or workout. The shoe also features a Boost midsole, which offers energy return and cushioning, making it perfect for those who need protection from the impact of running, jumping, and other high-intensity activities. The shoe's Continental rubber outsole provides traction on both wet and dry surfaces, giving you the confidence to tackle any terrain with ease.

We think that the standout feature of the adidas Ultra Boost 1.0 DNA Triple Black is its sleek design. The use of black on black gives the shoe a clean and minimalist look that is both stylish and understated. The shoe was released on November 30th, 2022 at a retail price of $200.

name: Core Black Clear Pink Gum (Women's)
title: adidas Handball Spezial Core Black Clear Pink Gum (Women's)
description:
The adidas Handball Spezial Core Black Clear Pink Gum (Women's) finds inspiration in the original models from the 1970s. However, this sneaker boasts an updated colorway of Core Black and Clear Pink with a gum rubber outsole.

The upper is made of soft suede that gives the sneaker a velvety finish, while the lining is crafted from a breathable synthetic material. Drawing inspiration from the adidas Originals archive, the sneaker displays the serrated 3-Stripes on the side panel and a classic toe overlay in tonal Core Black. Clear Pink can be found on the 3-Stripes, the laces, the lining, the collar, and the adidas logo tag on the tongue. Additional branding details include SPEZIAL and a tiny trefoil printed in Metallic Gold ink along the 3-Stripes.

Our StockX experts like the ‘adidas’ lettering embossed into the rubber outsole. The women’s size adidas Handball Spezial Core Black Clear Pink Gum (Women's) was released on October 31st, 2023, and retailed at $110.

name: MX Rock
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 MX Rock
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 MX Rock features a marbled black, grey, and brown Primeknit upper styled in a pattern similar to the Yeezy 350 V2 MX Oat, only with dark tones. In signature fashion, a cushioned Boost sole, heel tab, and mesh side stripe complete the design.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 MX Rock released in December of 2021 and retailed for $220. The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 MX Rock released again in March of 2024 and retailed for $230.

name: Black Silver
title: Salomon XT-6 Gore-Tex Black Silver
description:
The Salomon XT-6 Gore-Tex Black Silver takes Salomon’s signature trailing running technologies and applies them to a city-inspired sneaker.

This lightweight runner boasts an upper made of synthetic mesh, which is designed to keep debris from entering the shoe. Gore-Tex bonds to the mesh upper and creates a protective layer that is waterproof and windproof yet also breathable. The sneaker features an all-black construction with reflective stripes that form triangular shapes and spell out SALOMON. The EnergyCell midsole provides responsive cushioning on concrete, compact soil, and rough terrain, while the rubber tread provides traction. A toggle lace closure with thin, durable laces secures the shoe and allows for easy adjustments. Branding details can be found on the inner side panel and the tongue tag.

Our StockX experts like that the reflective details match the silver accents on the black midsole. The Salomon XT-6 Gore-Tex Black Silver was released on January 27, 2024, and retailed at $200.

name: Craft Medium Olive (GS)
title: Jordan 4 Retro SE Craft Medium Olive (GS)
description:
The Jordan 4 Retro SE Craft Medium Olive (GS) is a special edition, grade school-sized version of the Jordan 4 SE Craft Medium Olive.

The sneaker boasts a mixed-material construction with an earthy green colorway of Khaki, Medium Olive, Pale Vanilla, and Sail. The upper is made of overlapping nubuck and hairy suede panels, which gives the shoe a patchwork look and a velvety feel. A hairy suede underlay with a grid-like texture embossed into the material adds a pop of solid texture. Khaki laces weave through the eyelets before connecting to the leather support wings. In addition, a visible Air-sole unit can be seen through transparent windows in the heel.

Our experts like the Jumpman insignia patch, which comes in Pale Vanilla and peeks through the laces on the tongue. The grade school-sized Jordan 4 Retro SE Craft Medium Olive (GS) was released on November 18th, 2023, and retailed at $160.

name: Chrome Blue
title: New Balance 9060 Chrome Blue
description:
The New Balance 9060 Chrome Blue is a running shoe with a monochromatic and eye-catching color scheme.

This version of the New Balance 9060 features a breathable and flexible mesh upper in a light blue color. Suede overlays in different shades of darker blue snake across the entire upper. The New Balance N appears on both sides – on one side in solid white outlined in dark blue and on the other side made up of small white dashes. The NB logo also adorns the heel, and an NB 9060 logo is found on the tongue. The chunky gray outsole features the ABZORB logo, as the shoe is equipped with this extra cushioning.

Our favorite feature of this shoe is the all-blue color scheme. It gives the shoe a clean and cohesive overall look. The New Balance 9060 Chrome Blue was released on April 20, 2024, for a sale price of $150.

name: Night Navy Gum
title: adidas Samba OG Night Navy Gum
description:
The adidas Samba OG Night Navy Gum is a classic sneaker with a history that dates back as far as the 1950s. The shoe was first designed as a soccer training shoe but has since transitioned into a lifestyle icon.

The shoes have a leather upper with suede overlays while the sole is constructed from durable rubber material. The upper showcases a Navy-blue color scheme with white accents around the collar lining and heel area as well as on the iconic three stripes seen on the side panels. Other branding details include the gold foil patch placed on the tongue with a trefoil logo.

A standout feature on the adidas Samba OG Night Navy Gum is the T-toe design on the edge of the toe box. It is made using suede material and enhances the shoe’s durability while also improving its vintage aesthetic. The shoes were released for retail priced at $100 on 14th April 2023.

name: Voltage Purple (2024)
title: Nike Air Max Plus OG Voltage Purple (2024)
description:
The Nike Air Max Plus OG Voltage Purple (2024) is a re-release of the original sneaker. This vibrant shoe celebrates the 25th anniversary of the Air Max model with a colorway of Voltage Purple with Total Orange accents.

The upper is made of airy mesh with leather accents in black on the tongue, mudguard, and heel. Like other Nike Air Max Plus OG models, the "Voltage Purple" iteration features wavy lines that curve across the upper and support the foot. Total Orange accents can be found on the tongue’s logo tag, the small Swoosh on the side panel, and the components on the sneaker’s rubber tread. In addition, the shoe boasts visible Air Max units, which can be seen through windows in the forefoot and heel. Each window displays Total Orange Air Max units.

Our StockX experts like the sneaker’s shell-like fit that houses a discrete front lacing system. The Nike Air Max Plus OG Voltage Purple (2024) was released on January 20th, 2024, and retailed at $180.

name: Forrest Gump (2024)
title: Nike Classic Cortez Forrest Gump (2024)
description:
The Nike Classic Cortez Forrest Gump (2024) is a re-release of the classic Cortez sneaker worn by Tom Hank’s character in the Oscar-winning film Forrest Gump.

The sneaker boasts an all-white upper made of leather with Varsity Red and Varsity Blue accents. The laces and the lace cage also come in clean white. The Swoosh logos on the side panels, the leather heel tab, and the NIKE stitching on the tongue display Varsity Red, while a layer of foam on the midsole provides a stripe of Varsity Blue. The full-length foam midsole has a heritage wedge shape and protects against impact. The rubber outsole boasts a herringbone traction pattern, which grips the ground and adds a serrated element underfoot.

Our experts like the metallic silver hardware on the laces that displays the Nike Swoosh logo. The Nike Classic Cortez Forrest Gump (2024) was released on May 8, 2024, and retailed at $110.

name: Black Toe (2024) (GS)
title: Jordan 14 Retro Black Toe (2024) (GS)
description:
The Jordan 14 Retro Black Toe (2024) (GS) relaunches the iconic white, black, and Varsity Red colorway for the fourth time. And, in a grade-school size, the color scheme is accessible to a wider audience.

Inspired by sports cars, the Black Toe (2024) (GS) Jordan 14 Retro boasts smooth lines and a streamlined feel. The upper is crafted from premium leather in white with black suede accents on the toe. Unlike the most recent relaunch, this version doesn’t have perforations across the vamp. Additionally, the collar lining, tongue, laces, and back tab come in black, while white decorates the midsole. The chrome-plated shank plate in the midsole adds stability, while encapsulated Zoom Air units provide cushioning underfoot. Other notable features include the Jumpman and oversized "23" in Metallic Silver on the heel.

Our experts at StockX like the small Jumpman logo on the outer side, which draws inspiration from Ferrari branding. The Jordan 14 Retro Black Toe (2024) (GS) was released on November 2, 2024, and sold for $150.

name: Ceramic
title: Nike Dunk Low Ceramic
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Ceramic made its return in 2020. Originally released in 2001, the Ceramic colorway was a part of the "Ugly Duckling" pack with fellow pack-mates the Veener and Plum, which have each seen a retro treatment in 2020. This week’s release brings back the nearly 10-year old colorway, giving fans of the OG pair a way to re-up or add it to their collection.

Similar to the other colorways within the pack, the Nike Dunk Low Ceramic is composed of a premium suede upper. Orange appears throughout the upper with hits of black and green on the toe and Nike Swoosh. Lastly, a mesh tongue wraps the sneaker up, bringing it back in true original form.

The Nike Dunk Low Ceramic released in November of 2020 for $100. The Nike Dunk Low Ceramic re-released in 2024.

name: Wizards
title: Jordan 3 Retro Wizards
description:
Jordan Brand is paying homage to the final stages of Michael Jordan's NBA playing career with the Washington Wizards, with the release of the Jordan 3 Retro Wizards.

The Jordan 3 Retro Wizards features a similar design compared to the Air Jordan 3 Retro True Blue, but with a few twists. Jordan Brand used orange across the lace eyelets and Jumpman logo on the tongue compared to the red color scheme on the Air Jordan 3 True Blue.

The Air Jordan 3 Retro Wizards released April 29, 2023, with a retail price of $210.

name: Mustard Seed (Women's)
title: UGG Tazz Slipper Mustard Seed (Women's)
description:
The UGG Tazz Slipper in Mustard Seed Women’s dropped on September 1, 2023. This slipper fuses the timeless allure of UGG with a fresh twist, perfect for the modern enthusiast.

Crafted in a vibrant Mustard Seed hue, this Tazz Slipper shines with classic Tasman braiding encircling the cuff, evoking an effortless style synonymous with UGG. The spotlight, however, is on its elevated platform sole standing tall at 1.5 inches (38 mm), merging a classic design with an edgy touch.

But what's truly captivating about the Tazz design is the iconic UGG comfort paired with unmatched quality. Imagine stepping on clouds while flaunting the fashion-forward aesthetic. The UGG Tazz Slipper Mustard Seed, where comfort meets chic, was introduced on September 1, 2023, and initially graced the market at a sleek $120.

name: Shadow Grey Castlerock
title: New Balance 9060 Shadow Grey Castlerock
description:
The New Balance 9060 Shadow Grey Castlerock adds a gray-on-gray colorway to the technical 9060 lineup.

A mix of gray tones, including Castlerock and Shadow Grey, cover the upper and extend over the midsole. Featuring a chunky silhouette and visible tech, the Shadow Grey Castlerock New Balance 9060 combines retro Y2K and futuristic aesthetics. The upper is crafted from lightweight yet durable mesh with supportive suede overlays. These overlays overlap, creating a layered look and a feeling of movement. Drawing inspiration from early 2000s running sneakers, the sculpted midsole pods house Abzorb and SBS cushioning. The diamond outsole pattern provides superior traction and gives a nod to the 860 silhouette.

Our StockX experts appreciate the inclusion of design elements from the 991, including the 9060 tongue logo. It pays homage to the 991’s shiny lace jewel. The New Balance 9060 Shadow Grey Castlerock was released on October 11, 2024, and sold for $150.

name: White Black Pebbled Leather
title: Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 White Black Pebbled Leather
description:
The Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 White Black Pebbled Leather features a white pebbled leather upper with black Swooshes and heel panels. Woven Nike labels on the tongue offer a retro feel. At the base, a white Air sole adds the finishing touch.

The Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 White Black Pebbled Leather released in January of 2021 and retailed for $90.

name: Game Royal
title: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG Game Royal
description:
The Jordan 1 Retro Low OG Game Royal dresses this iconic Jordan 1 silhouette with the famous "Chicago" color-blocking pattern from 2018.

Released as part of Jordan Brand’s Holiday 2024 lineup, the Game Royal version of the Jordan 1 Retro Low OG boasts an all-leather construction. The base comes in clean white, while Game Royal provides contrasting blue on the forefoot and heel overlays, the eyelets, the heel pull tab, and the durable rubber outsole. Splashes of black decorate the Swoosh logos and the collar lining. In addition, the branding details also come in black—take a look at the "NIKE AIR" lettering on the tongue tag and the Jordan Wings logo printed on the heel tab.

Our experts at StockX like that the leather tongue comes in white instead of black—a difference between this model and the original "Chicago" color-blocking scheme. The Jordan 1 Retro Low OG Game Royal was released on November 30, 2024, and sold for $140.

name: Escargot
title: Nike SB Dunk Low Escargot
description:
The Nike SB Dunk Low Escargot was released ahead of the 2024 Paris Olympics and celebrates one of France’s most famous dishes.

The base of the Escargot Nike SB Dunk Low features soft suede in Pear with smooth leather overlays in rich Sesame. This unusual color combination represents the garlic butter with parsley used in the escargot cooking process. Sticking to its skateboarding roots, this version of the SB Dunk Low boasts thick padding in the tongue and around the collar. Metallic-silver accents can be found on the Swoosh logos and the leather heel tab, while additional Pear hues decorate the "NIKE" embroidery on the heel and the Nike Skateboarding branding on the tongue tag.

Our experts at StockX like that the metallic-silver accents represent the silver platter upon which escargot is served. In addition, the insole invokes white plate imagery celebrating Paris’s culinary history. The Nike SB Dunk Low Escargot was released on October 1, 2024, and sold for $125.

name: Playoffs (2022)
title: Jordan 12 Retro Playoffs (2022)
description:
In celebration of its 25th Anniversary, Jordan Brand brought back the shoe that Michael Jordan wore while winning his 5th NBA Title, the Air Jordan 12 Retro Playoffs.

Debuted in 1997, the Air Jordan 12 Playoff captures Michael Jordan and the Chicago Bulls' dominance in the 1990s era of NBA basketball. This 2022 model sticks to the original design, featuring a black tumbled leather upper with a white textural mudguard and red Jumpman embroidery on the tongue. At the heel, a woven Jordan label and "23" text add subtle branding. At the base, a white sole with carbon fiber detailing completes the design.

The Air Jordan 12 Playoffs released in March of 2022 and retailed for $210.

name: White Malachite Green
title: ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 White Malachite Green
description:
The ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 White Malachite Green is a running shoe featuring a 2000s aesthetic with updated materials for better performance.

This version of the ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 features a white mesh upper. Silver and black synthetic overlays run across the toebox and midsole in the signature ASICS pattern. Malachite Green overlays run in a curve from the heel to the arch of the foot, adding a pop of color. The ASICS logo also appears in the same shade of green on the tongue, while GEL appears on the heel and GEL-KAYANO 14 appears in black text on one of the green overlays.
