The outsole is white, gray, and Malachite Green. Gel technology cushioning in the shoe also provides extra shock absorption.

What we like most about this shoe is the Malachite Green accents. These add a welcoming and bright pop of color to the otherwise simple shoe. The ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 White Malachite Green was first released on January 10, 2024, for a price of $150.

name: Cool White (Women's)
title: Nike M2K Tekno Cool White (Women's)
description:
The Nike M2K Tekno is a white sneaker for women. It mixes classic Nike history with a modern Monarch franchise chunky look.

The Nike M2K Tekno has a white leather upper, white overlays, and a perforated toe box. A white Swoosh enclosed in a grey lining is on the side panels. It also has a zigzag foam white midsole that runs to the heel tab. The laces, tongue, and sock liner are all white. The shoe also features a treaded outsole that spikes into the midsole and an extending mudguard.

This women’s Nike M2K Tekno debuted on 17th November 2018. It retailed at $90.

name: Phantom Repaired Denim Swoosh
title: Jordan 1 Low SE Phantom Repaired Denim Swoosh
description:
The Jordan 1 Low SE Phantom Repaired Denim Swoosh is a special-edition sneaker that adds distressed denim details to the Jordan 1 Low silhouette.

This low-top sneaker boasts a premium leather upper in Off-White with suede overlays near the forefoot and panels, creating a lace cage in Phantom. Instead of suede, the collar uses leather in Phantom, while the leather heel tab features Amber Brown. This neutral color combination creates a subtle color-blocking effect. However, the detail that makes this sneaker stand out is the Swoosh on the lateral and medial side panels. It displays a patchwork of faded, distressed denim in Traditional Indigo, Washed Indigo, and Faded Yellow.

Our StockX experts like the way the rubber outsole tonally matches the Amber Brown details on the heel and around the collar. The Jordan 1 Low SE Phantom Repaired Denim Swoosh was released on January 19th, 2024, and retailed at $110.

name: Olive (2024) (GS)
title: Jordan 5 Retro Olive (2024) (GS)
description:
The Jordan 5 Retro Olive (2024) (GS) is a child-sized version of the recognizable Jordan 5 Retro. It features a contrasting colorway of Army Olive and Solar Orange.

The colorway comes from Jordan Brand’s archive and was first seen in 2006. Like other Air Jordan 5 models, this version features silver reflective detailing on the tongue, lace locks, and side panel netting. The upper is made of velvety suede in Army Olive, while Solar Orange details can be found across the shoe. For example, the padded collar lining, the shark tooth pattern on the midsole, and the Jumpman logo on the tongue all come in Solar Orange. Another standout feature is the glass-like toggle on the lace cage, which features a splash of Solar Orange.

Our experts at StockX like the translucent rubber outsole. It provides durable traction while supporting the Air cushioning in the midsole. The grade school-sized Jordan 5 Retro Olive (2024) (GS) was released on March 2nd, 2024, and retailed at $160.

name: Light Smoke Grey
title: Jordan 1 Low Light Smoke Grey
description:
The Air Jordan 1 Low Light Smoke Grey comes with a classic appearance that pinpoints Michael Jordan's historic first signature shoe.

The Air Jordan 1 Low Light Smoke Grey features a white leather upper, overlaid with grey at the heel and toe. Black laces, liners, and Swooshes give these kicks a distinct look, as do the outsole, collar, and tongue. Hits of red, black, and white are prominent in the design’s accompanying details. A white midsole and black outsole completes this retro design.

The Air Jordan 1 Low Light Smoke Grey released in September of 2020 and retailed for $90.

name: Beam Pink (Women's)
title: adidas Gazelle Indoor Beam Pink (Women's)
description:
The adidas Gazelle Indoor Beam Pink (Women’s) is an indoor athletic shoe in women’s sizing with a bright colorway.

This version of the adidas Gazelle Indoor is made with a suede upper in a shade of pink. This color dominates most of the shoe, with an overlay around the toebox and running up under the laces in one shade lighter. The iconic adidas three stripes appear across the midsole in leather in an even brighter pink, while the word "GAZELLE" appears in shiny gold on the lateral side next to the first stripe. The heel collar also appears in bright pink leather to match the stripes, and the tongue is textured pink with an adidas logo patch. A classic gum rubber outsole completes the look.

What stands out about this shoe is the bright pink colorway. This monochromatic look is bold. The adidas Gazelle Indoor Beam Pink (Women’s) was released on January 1, 2024, for a retail price of $120.

name: Silver Black
title: New Balance 1906R Silver Black
description:
The New Balance 1906R Silver Black leans into Y2K trends with a striking colorway of metallic silver, black, and white.

Featuring a low-top, lace-up design inspired by sneakers from the early 2000s, this version of the 1906R boasts a white mesh base with black accents on the heel, sock liner, rubber outsole, and ribbons threading through the signature New Balance N logo. However, the shiny silver overlays crisscrossing the upper stand out the most. The ABZORB SBS heel increases stability, while the ABZORB midsole protects against impact stress. Finally, the N-ergy technology in the outsole adds superior shock absorption as the Stability Web supports the midfoot arch.

Our experts at StockX like the classic New Balance 1906R branding, including "1906R" on the overlays, "NB RUNNING" on the tongue, and "NB" on the heel. The New Balance 1906R Silver Black was released on June 1, 2024, and sold for $155.

name: Crystal Pink
title: New Balance 9060 Crystal Pink
description:
The New Balance 9060 Crystal Pink takes the 9060’s technical silhouette and applies a Pink Haze base with silver and off-white accents.

The upper is made of breathable mesh with overlapping suede overlays that give the sneaker the illusion of layers. True to its technical roots, this running shoe features a chunky rubber sole with an ABZORB midsole and lightweight SBS cushioning. The oversized ‘N’ on the lateral side comes in silver leather and is outlined in white, while the ‘N’ on the medial side panel is made of suede with lines stitched across in silver thread. The lace cage houses tonal white laces that match the white outline surrounding the ‘N.’

Something our StockX experts like is the incorporation of slightly off-white rubber on the outsole. It gives the sneaker a worn-in feel that contributes to its throwback aesthetic. The New Balance 9060 Crystal Pink was released on July 26th, 2023, and retailed at $160.

name: Black White
title: New Balance 9060 Black White
description:
The New Balance 9060 Black White arrives in a black-and-white color palette.

The New Balance 9060 Black White has a black upper made of synthetic material with black and white embellishments and a white midsole. The black upper is made up of mesh, suede, and synthetic leather. The shoe bears a white "N" logo on the lateral sides and an "NB" logo on the tongue. The midsole is entirely white and incorporates ABZORB's signature cushioning. The shoe's outsole is black and made of rubber for grip and stability.

The New Balance 9060 Black White was made available on March 4, 2023, and retails for $150.

name: Chestnut (Women's)
title: UGG Disquette Slipper Chestnut (Women's)
description:
The UGG Disquette Slipper Chestnut W is footwear sized for women (W) that come with plush lining and a thick outsole.

This slipper features a soft upper in a chestnut brown colorway with a rounded toe, a raised center seam, and heat-embossed UGG branding on the lateral side. This model has a sheepskin insole with a branding patch and a sheepskin collar and lining. The 1-inch platform outsole is constructed from Treadlite by UGG as well as EVA. Recycled polyester fibers bind this slipper together.

The UGG Disquette Slipper Chestnut W was released in January 2021 at a retail price of $100.

name: Off-White Black
title: Nike Air Force 1 Mid Off-White Black
description:
The Nike Air Force 1 Mid Off-White honors the 40th Anniversary of the Nike Air Force 1 by refreshing the classic design with Abloh's signature avante-garde style. It arrives with a black, wood grain-textured lightweight mesh upper with ripstop collar straps and clear TPU Swooshes. From there, a warped midsole with multi-colored sections of a track-inspired spiked outsole reference past Nike Off-White designs like the Nike Waffle Racer and Air Zoom Tempo Next%.

The Nike Air Force 1 Mid Off-White Black released in June of 2022 and retailed for $185.

name: Georgia Bulldogs
title: adidas AE 1 Georgia Bulldogs
description:
The adidas AE 1 Georgia Bulldogs celebrates NBA player Anthony Edwards’ college years with the Georgia Bulldogs. The sleek AE1 silhouette gets an upgrade with the Bulldogs’ team colors: black and red.

At the Georgia Bulldogs adidas AE 1, the upper is made of thick, black mesh with a texture similar to canvas, while the TPU wings support the side panels. These wings come in bold red and feature a honeycomb-like pattern, allowing the foot to breathe. Crafted with performance in mind, the midsole houses Lightstrike foam underfoot and responsive Boost technology in the heel. Finishing the look, all the branding elements come in clean white.

Our experts at StockX like the combination of Anthony Edwards and adidas’ branding. For example, the heel displays a rubberized 3-Stripes logo, while the athlete’s logo graces the black tongue tag. The adidas AE 1 Georgia Bulldogs was released on September 7, 2024, and sold for $120.

name: Light Orewood Brown
title: Nike Air Foamposite One Light Orewood Brown
description:
The Nike Air Foamposite One Light Orewood Brown is part basketball sneaker and part streetwear shoe. It features a molded Foamposite upper that gives the sneaker a futuristic appearance.

Like other basketball shoes in Nike’s catalog, the Light Orewood Brown Nike Air Foamposite One displays the signature one-cent logo on the rubber outsole, a feature first introduced by NBA legend Penny Hardaway. The sneaker also boasts responsive cushioning designed for the basketball court. The Foamposite upper comes in Light Orewood Brown with a matte finish, while the inner bootie creates a secure fit around the ankle. Unlike traditional basketball shoes, this sneaker features a lace cage that extends across the vamp and into the toebox. The laces come in black and match the bootie and collar.

Our experts at StockX like the one-cent logo embroidered on the heel. The Nike Air Foamposite One Light Orewood Brown was released on May 31, 2024, and sold for $240.

name: Cement Grey
title: Jordan 11 Retro Low Cement Grey
description:
Jordan Brand is including the iconic Air Jordan 11 silhouette in their Spring/Summer 2023 campaign, with the release of the Jordan 11 Retro Low Cement Grey.

The Jordan 11 Retro Low Cement Grey draws inspiration from the Air Jordan 11 Retro Cool Grey and the Air Jordan 3 Retro White Cement. Jordan Brand used a white mesh upper with a grey patent leather mudguard. The limited edition sneakers are laced with white rope laces and sit on top of icy blue outsoles.

The Air Jordan 11 Retro Low Cement Grey released April 1, 2023, with a retail price of $190.

name: Panda
title: Jordan 1 Low TD Cleat Panda
description:
The Jordan 1 Low TD Cleat Panda reimagines an iconic basketball shoe into cleats meant for football players. The Jordan 1 Low TD Cleat is a men's shoe where the TD stands not for toddler, but for "touchdown."

The Jordan 1 Low TD Cleat in a white and black "Panda" colorway features an upper of white tumbled leather with toebox perforations and black tumbled leather overlays. The side panel Nike Swoosh, collar, and eyestays are also tumbled black leather. The tongue is white with a black patch that features a white Jumpman logo. The laces, sock liner, and insole are also black.

What our experts appreciate most about this shoe is the gridiron construction of the outsole, with the studs placed wide apart for flexibility and traction on the football field. The Jordan 1 Low TD Cleat Panda was released on June 7, 2023, for a retail price of $140.

name: Chestnut (Women's)
title: UGG Classic Ultra Mini Platform Boot Chestnut (Women's)
description:
The UGG Classic Ultra Mini Platform Chestnut W is a women’s sized slip-on ankle boot that is available in a chestnut colorway.

This Ultra Mini Platform model by Australian shoe company UGG is a take on the 70’s version, maintaining iconic staples such as the sheep skin interior and the suede upper, as well as the color. The upgraded version gets a 2-inch platform sole on the Treadlite outsole underfoot, and the design keeps branding minimal, with only a leather patch appearing at the back.

The UGG Classic Ultra Mini Platform Chestnut W was first released on the 2nd of November 2022 and retailed for $150.
model: UGG Classic Ultra Mini Platform Boot

name: Wolf Grey Midnight Navy
title: Jordan 1 Low Wolf Grey Midnight Navy
description:
The Jordan 1 Low Wolf Grey Midnight Navy adds color blocking in white, Wolf Grey, and Midnight Navy to this low-top sneaker, creating clear distinctions between each color and a clean look.

Panels of smooth Midnight Navy leather wrap around the Jordan 1 Low Wolf, as crisp white forms a layer beneath. The signature Swoosh logo, also made from leather, checks across the side panels in Wolf Grey. In addition, Wolf Grey accents decorate the Jumpman logo on the leather tongue and the Air Jordan Wings logo embroidered onto the heel. Perforations across the toebox allow the foot to breathe, while the front lace closure system provides a secure fit with white laces.

Our experts at StockX like the Midnight Blue-colored rubber outsole, which adds balance to the sneaker and completes the color-blocking effect. The Jordan 1 Low Wolf Grey Midnight Navy was released on June 14, 2024, and sold for $115.

name: University Red
title: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG University Red
description:
The Jordan 1 Retro Low OG University Red is part of Nike’s 2023 holiday collection and builds upon the legacy of the original AF1. This retro-inspired sneaker draws inspiration from varsity sports styles of the ‘80s while boasting an upgraded colorway.

Although the shoe bears a resemblance to the Jordan 1 Retro Low White Varsity Red launched in 2015, the University Red is brighter than the Varsity Red. A clean white hue drives the color palette and can be found on the leather upper, overlays, and tongue. The Swoosh, inner liner, heel, and rubber outsole feature pops of University Red. On the bottom, the foam midsole and encapsulated Air unit add cushioning without weighing down the shoe.

Our experts at StockX love the Wings logo embroidered in white thread onto the heel, which complements the Nike Air branding on the tongue. The Jordan 1 Retro Low OG University Red was released on October 13, 2023, and retailed at $140.

name: White Black
title: Alexander McQueen Oversized White Black
description:
DISCLAIMER: The included laces for this product vary by season.

The Alexander McQueen Oversized White Black is an oversized sneaker that is primarily made out of calf leather.

The Alexander McQueen Oversized White Black sneaker a rounded rubber toe as well as a rubber sole. The majority of the shoe is a bright white color. On the heel of the shoe, there are black details. The shoe also has perforated air holes in order to help make them be more breathable. The Alexander McQueen Oversized White Black also has white laces.

The Alexander McQueen Oversized White Black first became available on the market in December of 2019. This model of shoes had a starting retail price of $590.

name: White Black
title: Nike Air Max 270 White Black
description:
Crafted from a breathable mesh and canvas upper, the Nike Air Max 270 White Black now features 270 degrees of visible Air for extra comfort. Drawing inspiration from the sleek Air Max 180, the Nike Air Max 270 White Black features a slip-in bootie construction to deliver a great fit. The sneaker boasts a Max Air unit with 270 degrees of air encapsulated in the heel. The sneaker utilizes lightweight and soft neoprene across the upper to ensure airflow to the foot.

The Nike Air Max 270 White Black was released in March 2018 at a retail price of $160.

name: Cage 2 Metallic Silver
title: Nike Air Zoom Spiridon Cage 2 Metallic Silver
description:
The appearance of the Nike Air Zoom Spiridon Cage 2 Metallic Silver is influenced by two major colors: metallic silver and light smoke gray.

The Metallic Silver Nike Air Zoom Spiridon, commonly known as the Cage 2, features a mesh upper in silver and gray. Along with a black outlined Swoosh logo on the sides, it features patent and metallic silver leather overlays on the sides, toe, and heel areas. The heel sports a red Swoosh logo, while the front has white laces. A clear air cell with a glossy black cage surrounding it can be found at the heel of the white, foam-filled midsole.

The Nike Air Zoom Spiridon Cage 2 Metallic Silver had $140 as the recommended market price during its launch on April 13th, 2020.

name: Protection Pack Eclipse
title: New Balance 2002R Protection Pack Eclipse
description:
The New Balance 2002R Protection Pack Eclipse combines elements of the New Balance 2002 and the 860 and lends an edgy design to the upper. Dressed in a stealthy colorway with hits of earth tones, this runner also has a bit of a trail shoe vibe.

The Protection Pack Eclipse iteration of the New Balance 2002R features an upper with a base of black ripstop overlaid with layers of jagged dark blue and gray nubuck that give the upper both style and structure. The heel counter is black, laid over a goldish-tan ripstop with New Balance branding. Cord laces with a lock at the top complete the rough and ready look of this upper.

What our experts appreciate most about this shoe is its high-performance sole unit. The midsole is constructed of ABZORB boosted with N-ergy, with absorbing SBS in the heel for enhanced cushioning. The black rubber outsole is ridged and lugged for traction and vented for midsole expansion. The New Balance 2002R Protection Pack Eclipse was released on September 21, 2023, for $160 retail.

name: Washed Black
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Washed Black
description:
Jordan Brand is giving the Air Jordan 1 a washed look, with the release of the Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG Washed Black.

The Jordan 1 Retro High OG Washed Black is constructed using white leather and Washed Black uppers. Hints of grey are placed around the collar, while the sail colored midsole helps give the sneaker an aged design. The limited edition Air Jordan 1’s are tied together with white laces and feature a white Air Jordan Wings logo above the Swoosh.

The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG Washed Black released June 10, 2023, with a retail price of $180.

name: Birch Black
title: Onitsuka Tiger Mexico 66 Vintage Birch Black
description:
The Onitsuka Tiger Mexico 66 Vintage Birch Black is a lifestyle sneaker that takes its inspiration from training shoes that originally debuted at the Mexico Games in 1966.

The Vintage Birch Black colorway of the Onitsuka Tigers Mexico 66 features an elegant upper of textured birch-colored cow leather. The black tiger stripes coursing across the side panel are in cow suede. A T-toe overlay, an eye stay overlay, and heel overlays are in a richer birch cow suede that matches the sock liner. The flat cotton laces and tongue match the lighter hue of the upper base. Heel-cross reinforcements add both stability and style to this shoe. Onitsuka Tiger branding adorns the heel tab, the tongue tag, and the black insole that has perforations for breathability.

The aspect of this Onitsuka sneaker that we enjoy the most is the subtle yet durable and dependable sole unit. Underneath a thin foam midsole, a rubber outsole is grooved in a consistent pattern for traction and impact absorption. The Onitsuka Tiger Mexico 66 Vintage Birch was released on July 22, 2023, for a retail price of $130.

name: Blue Grey
title: Jordan 13 Retro Blue Grey
description:
The Jordan 13 Retro Blue Gray updates the classic Jordan 13 Retro silhouette with blue/gray accents against a Crisp White base.

The upper is made of white, tumbled leather with blue/gray panels crafted from synthetic suede. The velvety texture of the synthetic suede contrasts the quilted design across the uppers. The outsole draws inspiration from a panther’s paw, featuring a pod design that grips the ground without sacrificing flexibility. Like other Air Jordan 13 Retro models, the "Blue Gray" version features a Zoom Air unit in the heel and forefoot. There is also a holographic eye on the heel that is secured by reinforced stitching.

Our experts at StockX like the way the Yellow Ochre details on the Jumpman logo and ‘JORDAN’ logo tag match splashes of color on the rubber outsole. The Jordan 13 Retro Blue Gray was released on February 10th, 2024, and retailed at $200.

name: Wheat
title: Timberland 6" Basic Boot Wheat
description: The Timberland 6 Basic Wheat is a classic and timeless boot that has been a staple in the fashion industry for decades. Made with premium nubuck leather, these boots are durable and built to last. The wheat colorway is versatile and can be paired with a variety of outfits, making it a great addition to any wardrobe. Released on January 1st, 2018, the Timberland 6 Basic Wheat has been a popular choice among sneaker enthusiasts and fashionistas alike. Retailing at $140, these boots are a great investment for anyone looking for a high-quality and stylish shoe. One of the standout features of the Timberland 6 Basic Wheat is its waterproof construction, making it perfect for any weather condition. The padded collar and anti-fatigue technology also provide added comfort and support for all-day wear. Something we love about Timberland 6 Basic Wheat is its ability to seamlessly transition from a casual day out to a more formal occasion. Our experts think the best features are its durability, comfort, and versatility. Whether you're hiking through the mountains or walking through the city streets, the Timberland 6 Basic Wheat is a reliable and stylish choice.

name: Concepts Orange Lobster
title: Nike SB Dunk Low Concepts Orange Lobster
description:
The Nike SB Dunk Low Concepts Orange Lobster comes toned in a mixture of three main colors: electro orange, orange frost, and white.

This Low Nike SB Dunk features a nubuck upper with varying orange tones, softly speckled overlays, and a tonal Swoosh accented in white. The interior lining is embellished with a bib-inspired pattern, and the white mesh tongue is embellished with a woven Nike SB tag. The shoe boasts an orange rubber outsole and a cupsole with black sidewalls.

The Nike SB Dunk Low Concepts Orange Lobster was set to retail at $120 at its market launch on December 20th, 2022.

name: Fuchsia Pink
title: New Balance 9060 Fuchsia Pink
description:
The New Balance 9060 Fuchsia Pink is a low-top performance shoe designed by James Lee and Yue Wu. 
   
The Fuchsia Pink New Balance 9060 features an upper with a base of Pale Pink mesh for breathability. Suede overlays in a bright Fuchsia color cross the upper to form the toecap, eyestays, mudguard, midfoot, and heel. The New Balance N appears in an off-white color on the lateral side, and again on the inner side in embroidered pink dashed stitching. The white leather heel collar also contains pink NB branding, while the tongue features a 9060 patch. A pink support is seen at the heel, and the shoe sits on a chunky Pale Pink midsole with ABZORB cushioning and brighter pink accents. The outsole is black.

Our favorite thing about this sneaker is the Fuchsia colorway, which is bold and elegant at the same time. The New Balance 9060 Fuchsia Pink was released on August 15, 2024, for $150.

name: Lucky Green
title: Jordan 1 Mid Lucky Green
description:
Reminiscent of St. Patrick's Day and the luck of the Irish, the Jordan 1 Mid Lucky Green offers a classic mid-top silhouette in crisp two-tone color blocking.

The upper of the Jordan 1 Mid with a Lucky Green/white/black colorway has a side panel, collar, and perforated toe box made of white leather. Green leather overlays on the mudguard, vamp, heel counter, eye stays, and collar match the green leather Swoosh and the green nylon tongue. The white laces match the upper and the white Foam midsole with encapsulated Air cushioning.

What our sneaker experts love most about this shoe are the black hits – the sock liner, the rubber outsole with the signature Air Jordan traction pattern, the Wings logo stamped on the collar overlay, and the Jumpman logo on the tongue tag. Just in time for St. Patrick's Day, the Jordan 1 Mid Lucky Green was released on March 1st, 2023, for a retail price of $125.

name: Flax Wheat
title: Nike Air Force 1 Low Flax Wheat
description:
The Nike Air Force 1 Low Flax Wheat pays unofficial homage to the classic wheat Timberland work boot with its monochromatic flax suede uppers and overlays. Boot styled two-tone rope laces and top eyelets with metal grommets provide functionality and a rugged appeal. At the base, a matching flax Air sole is geared for daily wear and tear.

The Nike Air Force 1 Low Flax Wheat originally released in September of 2019 for $100, restocked in April of 2022 for $130 and currently sits at a retail price of $135.

name: Velocity Blue
title: adidas AE 1 Velocity Blue
description:
The adidas AE 1 Velocity Blue is a signature sneaker created by adidas Basketball and NBA player Anthony Edwards.

This high-performance basketball shoe features a bold Velocity Blue base with two visible Lime Green accents. The adidas logo on the heel and the Anthony Edwards branding on the tongue’s tag come in Lime Green. LightStrike foam and a full-length Boost unit can be found in the midsole. They provide energy return without weighing the foot down and contribute to the sneaker’s technical silhouette. The upper is made of durable textile with TPU support Wings on the side panels. These support wings provide stability and feature a honeycomb-like design.

Something our StockX experts like is the choice of color-matching the TPU support wings to the textile upper. It gives the sneaker cohesion and doesn’t distract from the design. The adidas AE 1 Velocity Blue was released on March 8th, 2024, and retailed at $120.

name: Industrial Blue
title: Jordan 1 Low Industrial Blue
description:
The Jordan 1 Low Industrial Blue is a low-top basketball shoe that pays homage to the classic design but with a modern twist.

This iteration of the Jordan 1 Low comes with an upper made of white leather. This forms the toe box, which is perforated for breathability, the midsoles, and the tongue. Textured leather overlays in Industrial Blue create a layered design. They round out the toe box, attach the bottom of the laces to the sole, and form the ankle area and heel counter. The Nike swoosh also appears in Industrial Blue across each side. The heel features an embroidered Air Jordan logo, while the tongue sports a blue Jumpman logo. A white rubber sole and light gray outsole form the bottom of the shoe.

What we like best about this sneaker is the textured overlays, as they add visual interest to the otherwise smooth shoe. The Jordan 1 Low Industrial Blue was released on April 9, 2024, for $125.

name: Leather Triple White
title: Nike Air Max 90 Leather Triple White
description:
The Nike Air Max 90 Leather Triple White 2020 takes on a 1990 original design, and is covered in an all-white finish.
​
​The sneaker is constructed of white TPU eyelets, a mesh upper with stitched leather overlays, a waffle-tread rubber outsole for traction and an Air-infused midsole for cushioning. Further, it displays Air Max units on both medial sides with a padded tongue panel printed with a Nike Swoosh emblem. Additionally, this Air Max Triple version has printed Nike branding on its heel.
​
​The Nike Air Max 90 Leather Triple White 2020 debuted on July 28th, 2020, and retailed at $130.

name: Fog
title: Nike SB Dunk Low Fog
description:
The Nike Dunk SB Low Fog is a skateboarding sneaker that slightly resembles the Nike Dunk SB High Fog released in 2005. Designed to provide individuals with the comfort they need while skateboarding, this sneaker features a black suede upper contrasted with a gray leather Nike Swoosh logo on its side and a grey Nike SB branding on its heel. It also features a mesh tongue, black laces, a dark midsole, a black rubber sole, and a gum rubber outsole.

The Nike Dunk SB Low Fog was released in 2021. Originally, it had a retail price of $100.

name: Ochre
title: adidas Yeezy Slide Ochre
description:
The adidas Yeezy Slide Ochre is constructed entirely of EVA foam in a monochromatic fashion. A soft footbed offers immediate step-in comfort for daily wear. From there, deep groove treads on the sole provide traction and support.

The adidas Yeezy Slide Ochre released in December of 2021 and retailed for $60.

name: Cement Grey (GS)
title: Jordan 3 Retro Cement Grey (GS)
description:
The Jordan 3 Retro Cement Grey (GS) reinterprets designer Tinker Hatfield’s signature silhouette from the late 1980s in a kid-appropriate size.

This mid-top sneaker boasts a classic colorway of Summit White, Cement Grey, Fire Red, and Black. At the Cement Grey (GS) Jordan 3 Retro, the upper is crafted from premium smooth and texturized leather in white with perforations along the collar. Paying tribute to the OG models, this "Cement Grey" iteration features elephant skin print overlays at the heel and toebox. A Jumpman logo in Fire Red decorates the padded leather tongue, while the heel displays a black Jumpman logo. Visible Zoom Air units in the heel provide a responsive feel, while the foam midsole increases comfort.

Our experts at StockX like the way the Cement Grey rubber outsole matches the hints of grey in the elephant skin print. The grade school-sized Jordan 3 Retro Cement Grey (GS) was released on August 31, 2024, and sold for $150.

name: Phantom Light Bone
title: Nike Dunk Low Phantom Light Bone
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Phantom Light Bone is a low top sneaker crafted in a color palette of Phantom, Sail, Light Bone, and Coconut Milk tones, accented by Saturn Gold.

Since it first debuted in 1985 as a basketball shoe, the Nike Dunk has gained a legion of admirers. Over the years, Nike has rendered numerous editions of the sneaker, playing with all of the possible aesthetics enabled by its paneled construction. With the Phantom Light Bone colorway, Nike riffs on textures and shades of white and gray to create a clean aesthetic. A mix of ribbed and knit textiles are the base, while suede emphasizes the toebox and coordinates with the heel panel, accented by a leather mudguard and Nike Swoosh. Other details include cream laces, foam tongues, and the midsole and outsole in Coconut Milk and Light Bone.

In our opinion, the best feature of the Dunk Low is its muted color palette, which makes for an interesting alternative to typical white sneakers. The Nike Dunk Low Phantom Light Bone released on April 1, 2024, and retailed for $135.

name: Reverse Panda
title: Jordan 1 Mid Reverse Panda
description:
The Jordan 1 Mid Reverse Panda is a mid-top basketball sneaker featuring a colorway that resembles a panda bear.

This version of the Jordan 1 Mid features an upper made of white leather. It is perforated at the toebox to allow extra air flow. White leather overlays can be seen around the toebox, heel, and up under the laces. There is also a white leather ankle strap. The Nike Swoosh appears in black on both midsoles, while the heel is rounded out in black, too. A black Air Jordan logo can also be found on the ankle strap on the lateral side. A black and white rubber outsole provides grip and traction both on and off the court.

What we like best about this shoe is the clean black and white colorway, which gives it a sleek look. The Jordan 1 Mid Reverse Panda was released on December 12, 2023, for a retail price of $125.

name: White Halo Blue Gum (Women's)
title: adidas Samba OG White Halo Blue Gum (Women's)
description:
The adidas Samba OG White Halo Blue Gum (Women's) presents the Samba OG silhouette in a primarily Cloud White base with Halo Blue and Off White accents.

Originally designed as an indoor soccer shoe, this retro-inspired adidas Samba boasts a leather upper with a classic toe overlay in velvety nubuck. Heritage details include the low-cut design and the serrated 3-Stripes logo on the side panels. Halo Blue can be found on the 3-Stripes, the collar, and the trefoil logo tag on the tongue. While many Samba shoe variations print ‘SAMBA’ in metallic gold along the 3-Stripes, this edition displays ‘SAMBA’ in Halo Blue. The lining is made of textile and includes ‘adidas’ and the trefoil as a repeated pattern.

Our StockX experts like the inclusion of Cloud White laces, which maintains the white-on-white theme. The women’s size adidas Samba OG White Halo Blue Gum (Women's) was released on November 19th, 2023, and sold for $100.

name: Carmine (2021)
title: Jordan 6 Retro Carmine (2021)
description:
The Air Jordan 6 Carmine returned in its original form in 2021. The nearly 20-year-old colorway first made its appearance in 1991 during Michael Jordan’s ’91-’92 season and brought in a new form of color blocking to the signature silhouette.

The Air Jordan 6 Carmine combines red, white, and black colors to represent the Chicago Bulls’ signature colors. The upper features bold red and white colors that help the model pop while on foot. From there, the upper is met with a white and black midsole, with hits of an icy blue outsole appear as well. The final touch to this OG’s return is the signature "Nike Air" on the heel, replacing 2008 and 2012 retros’ "Jumpman" logo.

The Air Jordan 6 Carmine released in February of 2021 for $200.

name: Travis Scott Reverse Mocha
title: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG SP Travis Scott Reverse Mocha
description:
Nodding to the Air Jordan 1 High Travis Scott Mocha, the Air Jordan 1 Low Travis Scott Reverse Mocha offers a similar Mocha and off-white palette but in a reverse-style color blocking. Its upper is constructed with a Mocha Durabuck base, white leather overlays, and signature reverse Swooshes. Hits of red on the Wings logo heel embroidery and woven tongue label gives a sharp contrast to the design's neutral look. From there, a yellowed Air sole adds a vintage feel.

The Air Jordan 1 Low Travis Scott Reverse Mocha released in July of 2022 and retailed for $190.

name: Silver Metallic Blue Agate
title: New Balance 1906R Silver Metallic Blue Agate
description:
Meet the New Balance 1906R Silver Metallic Blue Agate, a fresh iteration of the much-lauded 1906R model. Released on December 8, 2023, this sneaker quickly captured the attention of the masses with its unique blend of retro design and contemporary aesthetics. Featuring a sleek silver metallic hue complemented by blue agate accents, this sneaker is a testament to New Balance's commitment to innovation and style.

The New Balance 1906R has garnered immense popularity for its exceptional comfort and suave design, and the Silver Metallic Blue Agate colorway is no exception. It stands out with its sea salt touches that enhance the metallic and blue agate tones, embodying a sense of sophistication and modernity. The sneaker's silhouette is a nod to New Balance's rich heritage while propelling the brand into the forefront of trendy fashion.

Available for $155, the New Balance 1906R Silver Metallic Blue Agate is a true statement piece. Its launch was not merely a release but an event that underscored the resurgence of classic sneaker profiles in today's fashion landscape. Whether paired with casual wear or as a complement to a more dressed-up look, these kicks are versatile, stylish, and an embodiment of New Balance's distinguished craftsmanship and forward-thinking design.

name: Canyon Purple (Women's)
title: Jordan 4 Retro Canyon Purple (Women's)
description:
The Air Jordan 4 Retro Canyon Purple W was inspired by Tinker Hatfield’s 1989 design. This shoe replaces the traditional leather or nubuck build.

This Air Jordan 4 for women has an upper that is crafted from shaggy suede in a vibrant purple color finish. Lime green accents land on the speckled eyelets and midsole, while the signature Jumpman logo graces the woven tongue tag in Safety Orange. The bright hues are offset by contrasting hits of black on the molded wings, Jumpman-embossed heel tab, and herringbone-traction rubber outsole.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro Canyon Purple W was released on the 15th of October 2022, and originally retailed for $200.

name: Concepts Mellow
title: Nike Air Max 1 SP Concepts Mellow
description:
PLEASE NOTE: Print Patterns May Vary. In collaboration with Boston-based boutique Concepts, the Nike Air Max 1 SP Concepts Mellow pays homage to '60s and '70s youth culture with its fabrication and palette. It is constructed with a medley of bleached denim, ripstop canvas, red velour, and bandana materials, each contrasting one another. The embroidered "flower power" Swoosh nods to common clothing design themes of the 1970s. At the base, a speckled Air Max sole completes the design.

The Nike Air Max 1 SP Concepts Mellow released in March of 2022 and retailed for $170.

name: Wheat (2023)
title: Jordan 13 Retro Wheat (2023)
description:
Relive the glory of an icon with the Jordan 13 Retro "Wheat". This 2023 rendition pays homage to the silhouette's storied past, bringing back the famed wheat colorway first introduced in 2004. Tumbled leather uppers, crisply dressed in white, are accented by nubuck overlays in a workwear-associated wheat tone, delivering a striking contrast and undeniable style.

The Jordan 13 Retro "Wheat" stays true to its roots, featuring signature holograms at the heel and the Jumpman logo on the tongue. These authentic details are a nod to the original, celebrated specifications that have made the Jordan 13 a beloved staple in sneaker history. The upcoming release mirrors its nearly two-decade-old predecessor while ensuring a fresh look.

Mark your calendar for November 21, 2023, as the iconic Jordan 13 Retro "Wheat" hits the shelves. Retailing at $200, this sneaker is a piece of Jordan Brand heritage reimagined for the modern connoisseur. Don't miss out on the chance to own a part of sneaker legend.

name: Racer Blue White
title: Nike Dunk Low Racer Blue White
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Racer Blue White features a smooth Racer Blue leather upper with contrasting white leather overlays and Swooshes. A woven Nike tongue tag and heel embroidery nod to the original stylings of the 1985 Nike Dunk. At the base, a matching EVA foam sole completes the design.

The Nike Dunk Low Racer Blue White released in 2022 and retailed for $100.

name: Black Silver White
title: Nike Air Max Plus Black Silver White
description:
The Nike Air Max Plus Black Silver White comes in black, metallic silver, and white colorway.

Constructed with honeycomb-shaped underlays and palm tree-inspired TPU overlays, this Air Max Plus sneaker features a Tuned Air (Tn) cushioning unit. A whale tail-shaped mid-foot shank sits between the heel and forefoot. Branding details include white Swooshes on the laterals and medials, Swoosh Air branding on the tongue tags, and Tn Air branding on the insole and heel counter. A foam midsole and a rubber outsole complement the design.

The Nike Air Max Plus Black Silver White was made available on July 1st, 2022, retailing at $175.

name: Slate Onyx
title: adidas Yeezy 350 V2 CMPCT Slate Onyx
description:
The adidas Yeezy 350 V2 CMPCT Slate Onyx features a PrimeKnit canvas characterized by a combination of black and gray tones, all of which sit atop a black sole equipped with cushioning Boost technology.

The Slate Onyx adidas Yeezy 350 V2 CMPCT showcases a neutral colorway with an upper woven from black and gray threads, boasting an engineered 3D knit construction that offers lightweight support and a snug fit. Moreover, it boasts a flexible sock-like collar and easy-to-wear no-tie elastic laces for added convenience. The sneaker's foundation consists of a full-length Boost midsole, enclosed within a semi-translucent TPU cage, and reinforced by a robust rubber outsole – delivering both durability and comfort for a satisfying footwear experience.

What our experts love about the adidas Yeezy 350 V2 CMPCT Slate Onyx is its 3D knit upper, which not only provides a unique and eye-catching aesthetic, but also offers a lightweight and supportive fit. The sneaker was released on August 4th, 2023, for $230.

name: With Love
title: adidas AE 1 With Love
description:
The adidas AE 1 With Love, born out of a collaboration with basketball sensation Anthony Edwards, marks the inaugural colorway for Edwards' debut signature shoe.

Crafted with black knit textile, the upper of the adidas AE 1 With Love is reinforced by an Acid Orange TPU support cage, which incorporates breathable perforations arranged in a unique honeycomb pattern. The woven tongue tag proudly displays Anthony Edwards' initials, and the back heel features the iconic adidas 3-Stripes logo. The midsole integrates Boost and LightStrike technologies, delivering both lightweight cushioning and energy return. With a rubber outsole, the shoe guarantees exceptional traction and grip on diverse surfaces.

The standout attribute of the adidas AE 1 With Love is its prominent TPU overlay, seamlessly integrated with perforations extending to the sole unit. This design element, paired with the Georgia peach-inspired upper, imparts a unique and distinctive aesthetic to the shoe. The sneaker debuted for $120 on December 16th, 2023.

name: Raging Bull Red (2021)
title: Jordan 5 Retro Raging Bull Red (2021)
description:
2021 marked 12 years since the Air Jordan 5 Defining Moments pack dropped, and in the same year, one-half of that pack resurfaced on the SNKRS app.

The Air Jordan 5 Raging Bulls is a suede lover’s dream, bringing back the same look and feel from the 2009 version. The upper is composed entirely out of red suede, celebrating MJ’s tenure with the Chicago Bulls. From there, a red and black embroidered "23" appears on the lateral side of each shoe’s heel, highlighting Jordan’s quintessential jersey number. In usual Jordan 5 fashion, the upper part of the tongue is made of reflective materials with a contrasting black Jumpman logo. Lastly, the model’s World War II fighter jet inspiration is made apparent from the white and red shark tooth details that lay atop a black midsole.

The Air Jordan 5 Raging Bulls released in April of 2021 for $190.

name: Supreme Wheat
title: Nike Air Force 1 Low SP Supreme Wheat
description:
Drawing inspiration from classic work boots, the Nike Air Force 1 Low SP Supreme Wheat features a Flax Durabuck upper with Supreme Box Logo insignias on the lateral heels. At the base, a matching Flax Air sole completes the design. This model was exclusively sold through Supreme stores and their online shops.

The Nike Air Force 1 Low SP Supreme Wheat released in November of 2021 and retailed for $150.

name: Covellite
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Covellite
description:
Yeezy added a new colorway to its 380 line with the adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Covellite. The Covellite has one of the most interesting arrangements of color in its product line.

The Yeezy Boost 380 Covellite features a marbled navy blue, grey, and black Primeknit upper that is reminiscent of a digital camo pattern. A gum brown Boost sole with tubular black laces wraps up the design.
The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Covellite released in March of 2021 and retailed for $230.

name: Triple Black
title: Nike Air Max 97 Triple Black
description:
Crafted from recycled materials, the Nike Air Max 97 Triple Black is covered in a black mesh and leather combination for a monochromatic look. The Nike Air Max 97 Triple Black is back, this time crafted from a combination of mesh and leather on a water ripple–inspired silhouette. Everything on the shoe gets the black-on-black treatment, including the laces, tongue, and Swoosh. 3M Scotchlite strips supply reflective flair to the monochromatic upper. A multi-window Nike Air midsole and scuff-resistant outsole round off the design.

The Nike Air Max 97 Triple Black was released in December of 2018 and retailed for $160.

name: Sail Light Orewood Brown (Women's)
title: Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Sail Light Orewood Brown (Women's)
description:
The Nike Vomero 5 Sail Light Orewood Brown (Women's) takes on the running shoe silhouette, constructed with a blend of lightweight materials in elegant neutral tones for performance and style.

The Nike Vomero 5 in Sail Light Orewood Brown for women exhibits a dual-tone color palette. This sneaker combines a foundational mesh structure with strategically placed leather and TPU overlays. The Light Orewood Brown shade gracefully adorns the leather elements, including the vamp, toebox, mudguard, eyestays, and specific sections of the midfoot. Adding to the shoe's visual appeal, a TPU cage and Swoosh in the same color make a distinct presence, while reflective 3M accents on the nylon straps of the tongue provide a reflective touch. The overall package is beautifully completed with the inclusion of Zoom Air technology within the soles, enhancing both comfort and performance.

What our experts say stands out in the Nike Vomero 5 Sail Light Orewood Brown (Women's) is its blend of retro style and modern comfort. The vintage-inspired silhouette, combined with Zoom Air cushioning technology, offers a unique combination of fashion and functionality. The sneaker debuted on December 1st, 2023, for $160.

name: Fire Red (2020)
title: Jordan 4 Retro Fire Red (2020)
description:
Jordan Brand revisited an iconic colorway with the Air Jordan 4 Fire Red (2020), now available on StockX. This release returns in its original form with "Nike Air" branded heels, making it the first time this colorway has retroed in this variation since its debut in 1989.

This Jordan 4 consists of a white leather upper with black and Fire Red detailing. Rubber netted underlays, black heel tabs with "Nike Air" branding, and black with fire red midsoles completes this design. These sneakers released in November of 2020 and retailed for $200.

name: Shadow Brown (Women's)
title: adidas Gazelle Shadow Brown (Women's)
description:
The adidas Gazelle Shadow Brown (Women's) is an elegant lifestyle shoe that takes advantage of an iconic silhouette that has been turning heads for over 50 years. The sneaker has been specifically sized for women.

The Women's Shadow Brown adidas Gazelle features a luxurious upper crafted from warm brown suede. The T-toe and eyestay overlays are also made from this same brown suede, while the iconic serrated side panel three stripes are white leather. The tongue is brown leather and matches the rope laces, and gold Gazelle branding graces the lateral side panel. The sole unit is crafted from gum rubber, which sneaks up the sidewalls to form a translucent mudguard. The outsole is patterned for multi-surface grip.

Our favorite aspect of this women's sneaker is the hit of pink. The leather heel tab sports a debossed cream-colored trefoil, as it adds a pop of color to this shoe. The adidas Gazelle Shadow Brown (Women's) was released on November 1, 2023, for $100 retail.

name: Flint Grey
title: Jordan 14 Retro Flint Grey
description:
The Jordan 14 Retro Flint Gray applies a Flint Gray colorway and premium materials to the recognizable Jordan 14 Retro silhouette.

The upper is made of soft suede with shaggy suede overlays on the forefoot and heel. The choice of materials combined with the Flint Gray colorway gives the sneaker a soft, smokey appearance. The tongue is made of suede and mesh with perforations that allow the foot to breathe. Like other Jordan 14 models, the "Retro Flint Gray" iteration was inspired by Tinker Hatfield’s favorite sports car, the Ferrari. For example, the Jumpman logo on the heel overlays mimics the design of the Ferrari logo. The panels on the midsole also create the illusion of movement, which pays tribute to race cars.

Our StockX experts like the ‘JORDAN’ branding on the tongue. It can only be seen upon close inspection. The Jordan 14 Retro Flint Gray was released on March 20th, 2024, and retailed at $210.

name: LeBron James Fruity Pebbles
title: Nike Dunk Low QS LeBron James Fruity Pebbles
description:
The Nike Dunk Low QS LeBron James Fruity Pebbles come in Habanero Red mixed with Laser Blue and White colorway.

This Dunk Low sneaker by Nike features a smooth white leather base contrasted with habanero red overlays and a laser blue dressed side Swoosh. The shoe’s white tongue is decorated with the woven Fruity Pebbles tags, while the heel tab is embroidered with LeBron’s LJ logo. The interior part of the sneaker is a Nike-branded sock liner revealing another Fruity Pebble graphic print. Concluding the design is the treaded milky translucent rubber outsole.

The Nike Dunk Low QS LeBron James Fruity Pebbles was released in November 2022 and retailed at $120.

name: Orca
title: Nike Kyrie 8 Orca
description:
The Nike Kyrie 8 Orca is known for its lightweight property and superior traction, enabled by a commendable forefoot Zoom Strobel.

The vamp of the Nike Kyrie 8 is constructed from leather and protrudes from a black rubber outsole. It shimmers in a mercury-grey hue and features a ribbed pattern. As it meets a padded tongue that enhances wearing comfort, it meets punched eyelets encased by a pair of webbing eyelets. Both sides have the signature Nike Swoosh – the left side shows a white logo encircles the mustache, and the right displays a smaller black graphic extending to the heel notch.

We like the detailed design of the Nike Kyrie 8 Orca sole. It starts at the toe tip in black, to a laser blue outsole, and a thick white midsole near the heel. A padded lining also adds to an already stylish design. Released in the Kyrie lineup on November 11th 2022, this shoe retails at $140.

name: Paris YMCA
title: Jordan 1 Mid SE Paris YMCA
description:
The Jordan 1 Mid SE Paris YMCA is a special-edition sneaker that finds inspiration in the oldest basketball court in Paris. This basketball court can be found in the basement of the Paris YMCA and was opened in 1893.

The sneaker features an earthy colorway that matches tones found on the basketball court, including the hardwood floors and off-white walls. The upper is made of leather in Sand Drift, while the leather and suede overlays feature Earth and Velvet Brown. The leather heel counter displays a woven pattern, which resembles the basketball court’s parquet floors. This woven pattern can also be found behind the Jumpman logo, on the tongue’s logo tag. Other branding details include the Jordan Wings logo on the heel and the leather Swoosh logos across the side panels.

Our experts at StockX like the way this sneaker artfully pays tribute to an important place in basketball history. The Jordan 1 Mid SE Paris YMCA was released on February 1st, 2024, and retailed at $135.

name: After Hours
title: adidas Harden Vol. 8 After Hours
description:
The adidas Harden Vol. 8 After Hours represents a departure from the bold color blocking displayed on other Harden Vol. 8 iterations. Instead, it features Core Black and Cloud White on the upper and midsole, and a splash of Cobalt Blue on the outsole.

Created by NBA player James Harden and adidas, this basketball shoe boasts a sleek silhouette with a sock-like cuff and breathable textile upper. The oversized EVA cage provides lateral support, while the BOOST midsole comes equipped with Lightstrike cushioning. However, the standout feature is the patent leather toe box in Cloud White. Its shiny surface reflects the light and draws attention to the sneaker’s molded design.

Our experts at StockX like that both the textile base and other EVA cage come in Core Black, minimizing the color-blocking effect and reducing the spotlight usually shone on the side panels. The adidas Harden Vol. 8 After Hours was released on July 1, 2024, and sold for $160.

name: New Wave
title: adidas AE 1 New Wave
description:
The adidas AE 1 New Wave represents a collaboration between the iconic German sneaker company and NBA star shooting guard Anthony Edwards. This basketball shoe fuses a resting style with high-octane performance capability on the court.

The New Wave iteration of the adidas AE 1 features an Arctic Fusion / Core Black / Cloud White colorway. The upper Cor Black textile overlaps with Arctic Fusion synthetics that blend into the sole unit. The lattice-work overlays on the upper reveal Arctic Fusion mesh beneath. The Boost midsole provides lightweight support, cushioning, and energy return, while the rubber outsole offers impact absorption and multidirectional traction in an undulating herringbone pattern. The heel sports a black pull tab for ease of on/off.

What our sneaker experts enjoy most about these basketball kicks are the subtle hits of branding: a white AE on the tongue tag and three white stripes on the heel. The Adidas AE 1 New Wave was released on January 25, 2024, for a retail price of $120.

name: Collegiate Green Gum
title: adidas Samba OG Collegiate Green Gum
description:
The adidas Samba OG Collegiate Green Gum comes in a Collegiate Green colorway with Core White accents.

The Samba OG Collegiate Green Gum has a suede upper that is soft and durable, and the leather detailing on the heel tab and 3-Stripes on the side. It has a gum rubber outsole that provides traction and durability. The shoe has a cushy insole that provides support for the foot, making it comfortable to wear for extended periods of time. The tongue and collar add a more comfortable feel to the ankle. The tongue also features an adidas logo.

We think that one of the key features of the adidas Samba OG Collegiate Green Gum is its classic design. The low-profile design of the shoe improves stability, agility, and responsiveness, making it perfect for sports and other activities. The shoe was first released on October 20th, 2022 at a retail price set at $100.

name: April Skateboards
title: Nike SB Dunk Low April Skateboards
description:
Strap in for a ride with the Nike SB Dunk Low April Skateboards, a sneaker that’s as much about performance as it is about making a statement. The Turbo Green/Metallic Silver/Turbo Green colorway is a nod to the fearless energy of the skate parks.

The design stays true to the SB Dunk Low's heritage, blending functionality with street-ready aesthetics. This sneaker brings a bold twist to the classic design, incorporating a color pop that stands out against the concrete playgrounds. It's built to withstand the scrapes and scratches of skate life, all while keeping your style on point.

Priced at a cool $120, the April Skateboards edition is an affordable piece of skateboarding's rich culture. Set to drop on November 27, 2023. It's a colorway that represents more than just style. It's a testament to the skate scene's vibrant personality and a must-have for those who live to ride.

name: Reverse Laney (Women's)
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Reverse Laney (Women's)
description:
Jordan Brands popular Air Jordan 1 model is getting Michael Jordan's Emsley A. Laney High School treatment with the release of the Women’s Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG Reverse Laney.

The Women’s Air Jordan 1 High OG Reverse Laney is the second iteration of the Air Jordan 1 to receive the Laney treatment, after Nike previously released the sneakers in men’s sizing in 2013. This version of the Laney features a leather upper, with blue and yellow color blocking, and a black and red Nike Air logo on the tongue.

The Air Jordan 1 Retro high OG Reverse Laney (W) released February 17, 2023, with a retail price of $180.

name: Bob Marley One Love
title: adidas SL 72 RS Bob Marley One Love
description:
The adidas SL 72 RS Bob Marley One Love is a sneaker with a vintage running shoe silhouette, featuring a Core Black fabric and suede upper, accented by Core White leather for the adidas signature 3-Stripes, lace panel, and heel tab. The midsole is done in green and Off-White with adidas branding embossed near the heel, contrasted by a maroon outsole. Bob Marley’s signature in gold appears on the rear heel.

German athletic shoe and apparel brands are known worldwide for their century-long heritage, and the label pays homage to a fellow global entity, Jamaican singer Bob Marley, with the SL 72 RS. The shoe’s color palette, signature, and throwback aesthetic are a tribute to the beloved artist, who passed on at 36 in 1981.

In our opinion, the best feature of the SL 72 RS is its Marley's autograph, which is the perfect subtle complement to the shoe’s referential aesthetic. The adidas SL 72 RS Bob Marley One Love was released on October 15, 2024, and retailed at $120.

name: One Piece Red-Haired Shanks
title: Puma Suede One Piece Red-Haired Shanks
description:
The Puma Suede One Piece Red-Haired Shanks is part of a collaboration between Puma and One Piece, a pirate-themed manga series created by Eiichiro Oda.​
​​
​The sneaker pays tribute to Red Haired Shanks, the chief of the Red Haired Pirates, through its colorway. Team Regal Red matches the character’s vibrant red hair, while Puma Silver can be found on the Red Haired Pirates’ flag. The suede upper features a debossed Puma Cat logo on one side panel and a metallic silver skull and swords on the heel. The side panels feature a wavy leather line in silver with a teal outline. The tongue displays co-branding, including a skull and Puma lettering. In addition, three black lines that resemble claw marks can be found on the lateral side panel.​
​​
​Our StockX experts like the flat lace closure and the inclusion of Team Regal red laces. The Puma Suede One Piece Red-Haired Shanks was released on March 23rd, 2024, and retailed at $85.

name: Stone Grey
title: adidas Yeezy 450 Stone Grey
description:
The adidas Yeezy 450 Stone Grey is another sneaker released as part of the long-standing collaboration between adidas and singer/fashion designer Kanye West’s Yeezy brand.

The Yeezy 450 is a modern lifestyle sneaker featuring a seamless one-piece knit textile upper. It has a monochromatic color palette featuring a light grey hue and an avant-garde design aesthetic with a sock-like fit, elastic collar, and traditional lacing system. The shoes also have a molded rubber sole that extends to the sides of the shoe, creating a cage-like structure that not only adds aesthetic value, but also has functional importance.

What we love most about the adidas Yeezy 450 Stone Grey is the added support provided by the cage-like structure on the shoe. This makes them sturdier while also supporting your feet, allowing for better balance. The shoes were first released for retail on the 15th of August, 2023, priced at $210.

name: Hidden NY
title: ASICS Gel-NYC Hidden NY
description:
The ASICS Gel-NYC Hidden NY is a running shoe that blends technologies from different eras to create a modern and functional sneaker.

This version of the ASICS Gel-NYC features an upper that combines elements of the early 2000s GEL-NIMBUS 3 and the more modern GEL-MC PLUS V. The upper is constructed mostly with white mesh for breathability. Silver, white, and green synthetic overlays appear across the upper in ASICS’ signature design. The ASICS logo can be found on one side of the heel in green, while "GEL" appears on the back of the heel also in green. The circular Hidden logo also appears on the midsole and the tongue in green. The shoe also contains a combination of lightweight foam and GEL technology in the insole for extra comfort and functionality.

What we like best about this shoe is the white and green colorway, which gives this comfortable shoe a clean, yet exciting look. The ASICS Gel-NYC Hidden NY was released on March 23, 2024, for a retail price of $170.

name: Blue Tint (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Next Nature Blue Tint (Women's)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Next Nature Blue Tint (Women's) is a low-top sneaker that is part of Nike’s "Next Nature" line. All "Next Nature" shoes are crafted with at least 20 percent recycled material and are part of Nike’s effort to minimize carbon emissions.

This two-toned sneaker for women features a Blue Tint, Cobalt Bliss, Summit White, Volt, and Black colorway that is reminiscent of the sky. The bright Summit White base allows the blue hues on the Swoosh, overlays, lace cage, and outsole to pop. In terms of branding details, the tongue boasts a ‘Nike’ label while ‘NIKE’ is also stitched across the heel.

Something our experts love is the incorporation of the Nike Grind midsole. This speckled midsole is made from recycled shoes from Nike’s Reuse-A-Shoe program and pre-consumer scraps created during manufacturing. The women’s size Nike Dunk Low Next Nature Blue Tint (Women's) was released on September 8, 2023, and retailed at $115.

name: Stone Salt
title: adidas Yeezy Foam RNR Stone Salt
description:
The adidas Yeezy Foam RNR Stone Salt takes on the slip-on silhouette with a low-top design, emphasizing comfort and ease of wear.

The Stone Salt adidas Yeezy Foam RNR showcases a predominantly neutral colorway, with a Stone Salt upper – a blend of gray and beige. The shoe is constructed with a one-piece foam upper, promoting a sock-like fit and lightweight feel. It lacks traditional laces and relies on elastic bands for a secure fit. Carefully positioned vents of different sizes enhance breathability and simultaneously enhance the eye-catching visual appeal of the slip-on design. On the underside, the outsole boasts a wavy traction pattern, ensuring dependable grip.

The standout feature of the adidas Yeezy Foam RNR Stone Salt is the unconventional yet highly comfortable one-piece foam construction. This design not only sets it apart visually, but also ensures a snug and effortless fit, making it a practical choice for those seeking comfort and style in a casual sneaker. The shoe was released on August 11th, 2023, for $90.

name: White University Red
title: Nike Kyrie 8 White University Red
description:
The Nike Kyrie 8 White University Red is the 8th release of the signature line of shoes released by Nike in collaboration with NBA superstar Kyrie Irving.

The shoes have a lightweight upper made from a combination of materials that include mesh and synthetic textile. These materials are also flexible and breathable to allow easy movement while also keeping your feet cool. The Nike Kyrie 8 has a black and white color scheme with red accents adding a touch of color. The red accents are most notably seen on the branding details, which include Kyrie’s signature logo on the tongue plus Nike’s iconic Swoosh on the side panels.

One thing that stands out on the Nike Kyrie 8 White University Red is the sole unit, which incorporates advanced cushioning technologies to absorb impact and cushion your foot with every step, keeping you as comfortable as possible. The shoes were first released for retail at the price of $140 on 24th November 2022.

name: Chicago (2023)
title: Jordan 1 Low TD Cleat Chicago (2023)
description:
The Jordan 1 Low TD Cleat Chicago (2023) is an updated version of the Jordan 1 basketball sneaker.

The upper of the Air Jordan 1 Low TD Cleat Chicago (2023) comes in a white and University Red colorway with black accents. The shoe features a low-cut design, which allows for a full range of motion for the ankle, allowing players to make quick and agile movements on the field. The toe box is reinforced with additional leather and has perforations, which provides extra protection and breathability.

We think that the standout feature of the Jordan 1 Low TD Cleat Chicago (2023) is its sole. The sole is made from a hard rubber material, which provides traction on the field and features a cleat pattern that allows for multidirectional movement and stability, ensuring that players can maintain control and grip on various surfaces. The shoe was released on June 1st, 2023, at a retail price of $140.

name: Midnight Navy (GS)
title: Jordan 4 Retro Midnight Navy (GS)
description:
The Air Jordan 4 Retro Midnight Navy GS applies color blocking in light smoke grey and midnight navy to dress the sneaker.
​
​This Retro Air Jordan 4 for grade-schoolers is available in a white/​midnight navy/​light smoke grey/​fire colorway. The upper is made of white leather with light grey support Wings, a matching light grey heel tab with Jumpman branding imprinted on top, and navy molded eyelets. The woven tongue tag has an additional Jumpman graphic in navy. The sneaker has a two-tone polyurethane midsole with encapsulated AIR in the forefoot and an exposed unit in the heel.
​
​The Air Jordan 4 Retro Midnight Navy GS was released on the 29th of October 2022, retailing for $160.

name: Mambacita (GS)
title: Nike Kobe 8 Protro Mambacita (GS)
description:
The Nike Kobe 8 Protro Mambacita (GS) honors Kobe Bryant’s late daughter Gianna Bryant and was released on what would have been the rising basketball player's 18th birthday.

The white and black butterfly pattern that graces the durable mesh upper represents Gianna’s transformational impact on basketball. In addition, the white, metallic gold, and black colorway draws inspiration from Gianna’s basketball team colors. The Swoosh logos embroidered on the outer side panels and along the heels come in metallic gold thread, which complements the gold detailing on the tongue and the sockliner. Technical features include a carbon fiber shank plate and React foam cushioning in the midsole.

Our StockX experts like that the right heel bears "GIGI," Gianna’s nickname, and the left heel displays "2," her jersey number. The grade school-sized Nike Kobe 8 Protro Mambacita (GS) was released on May 1, 2024, and retailed at $120.

name: Pioneer
title: adidas Harden Vol. 8 Pioneer
description:
The adidas Harden Vol. 8 Pioneer is a futuristic basketball shoe that’s part of a collaboration between adidas Basketball and NBA player James Harden.

This performance basketball shoe features a supportive EVA frame that looks like an off-white teardrop. It provides structure around the sock-like inner cuff, which allows the cuff to fit securely from toe to ankle. The EVA frame wraps around the arch and extends into a Boost midsole in the same Cloud White hue. The upper is made of black textile that wraps around the foot, while a panel of black leather wraps around the toe area. There are no branding details on the upper, which contributes to the sneaker’s futuristic aesthetic.

Our StockX experts like the ‘JH’ traction pattern and herringbone tread on the rubber outsole. The adidas Harden Vol. 8 Pioneer was released on March 1st, 2024, and retailed at $160.

name: Black Gunmetal
title: New Balance 2002R Black Gunmetal
description:
The New Balance 2002R Black Gunmetal is a performance running shoe with interior technical features inspired by the MR2002.

The sneaker boasts a breathable mesh upper with cut-out suede and leather overlays. Suede detailing can also be found on the heel and forming the mudguard. Although the shoe features ABZORB SBS pods in the heel for increased energy return and an ABZORB midsole for added cushioning, it appears light. Another element that makes the sneaker stand out is the black-on-grey colorway of Gunmetal, Phantom, and Black, which creates a stealthy look. In terms of branding, the New Balance "N" graces the lateral side panel, and "2002R" can be found on the mesh upper.

Our experts like how the white midsole contrasts the dark tones of the upper. The New Balance 2002R Black Gunmetal was released on October 21st, 2022, and retailed for a price of $140.

name: Black Dark Powder Blue
title: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG Black Dark Powder Blue
description:
The Air Jordan 1 Retro Low OG UNC arrives with a white leather upper with contrasting black overlays and a University blue Swoosh. This sneaker comes in a combination of white, dark powder blue, and black hues.

This Retro Low OG UNC model also features a black Wings Nike logo on its heel. Lastly, there is a black woven tongue and a blue outer sole that completes its design.

The Air Jordan 1 Retro Low OG UNC was first released on 29th July 2022. At the time, this sneaker had a suggested retail price set at $130.

name: Sandy Pink (Women's)
title: adidas Gazelle Indoor Sandy Pink (Women's)
description:
The adidas Gazelle Indoor Sandy Pink (Women's) gives the Gazelle Indoor a pastel makeover with a Sandy Pink base and accents in Cloud White.

Originally designed as an indoor training shoe, this women's-sized adidas Gazelle model in Sandy Pink stays true to its sporty roots with a grippy outsole made of durable gum rubber. The retro-inspired design includes pops of Cloud White on smooth leather accents, including the heel mustache and the 3-Stripes logo on the side panels. The suede upper and toebox overlay come in Sandy Pink and give the sneaker a luxe, velvety finish. A front lace closure secures the fit and houses Sandy Pink laces.

Our experts like the metallic gold branding details, including the "adidas" and "GAZELLE" lettering because they contribute to the sneaker’s premium aesthetic and set the shoe apart from more sporty models. The adidas Gazelle Indoor Sandy Pink (Women's) was released on June 1, 2024, and sold for $120.

name: Big Bubble Sport Red
title: Nike Air Max 1 '86 OG Big Bubble Sport Red
description:
Nike is celebrating Air Max Day in 2023 by bringing back an original Air Max design, with the release of the Nike Air Max 1 ‘86 Big Bubble Sport Red. The Big Bubble pays homage to the original design of the Nike Air Max 1, which featured a bigger air unit.

The Air Max 1 ‘86 Big Bubble released as Nikes premier Air Max Day release in 2023. The sneakers are constructed using grey synthetic nubuck, white mesh and red synthetic suede across the uppers and a large air unit on the midsole. Nike used Sport Red branding on the tongue and heel of the sneaker.

The Nike Air Max 1 ‘86 Big Bubble Sport Red released March 26, 2023, with a retail price of $150.

name: Athletic Department University Blue
title: Nike Dunk Low Athletic Department University Blue
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Athletic Department University Blue arrives in a predominantly Light Smoke Gray upper, with accents of University Blue in the classic low-top silhouette.

The Light Smoke Gray University Blue Nike Dunk Low Athletic Department is constructed with a combination of leather and suede for a premium look and feel. The leather overlays provide durability and support, while the suede panels add texture and style. The shoe features a traditional low-top silhouette with a padded collar for comfort. Nike has incorporated its time-tested technology, including a cushioned insole and a rubber outsole with a classic pivot point tread pattern to ensure both comfort and grip. The sneaker adopts a Light Iron Ore EVA foam midsole to provide cushioning and impact protection. Nike's iconic Swoosh logo is prominently displayed on both sides of the shoe, along with Nike branding on the tongue and heel tab.

Our experts say the Nike Dunk Low Athletic Department University Blue’s standout feature is its retro-inspired design, paying homage to the Dunk's rich history in the sneaker world. The sneaker was released on July 25th, 2023, for $110.

name: Honey Flux
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Honey Flux
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Honey Flux features a bright yellow neoprene upper with reflective "700" quarter detailing and black reinforced trimming. A black, sculptural Boost sole brings the maximized cushioning that Yeezy has been recognized for since their start in 2015.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Honey Flux released in September of 2021 and retailed for $220.

name: Lucid Pink (Women's)
title: adidas Samba OG Lucid Pink (Women's)
description:
The adidas Samba OG Lucid Pink (Women's) is a modern take on the classic indoor soccer shoe from the 1950s and features a Cloud White base with bright Lucid Pink and slightly off-white Wonder White accents.

Inspired by past generations of Samba sneakers, this version of the Lucid Pink (Women's) adidas Samba OG includes a breathable textile lining and an upper crafted from soft leather. Cloud White serves as a backdrop to the Wonder White toebox overlay and heel mustache. Lucid Pink adds splashes of color to the serrated 3-Stripes logos running along the side panels. In addition, the insole displays repeating Lucid Pink "adidas" lettering and trefoil logos. Cloud White laces wind through eyelets in the lace cage and secure the sneaker’s fit.

Our experts like the dark-gray-brown color of the rubber outsole. It’s a cooler hue than traditional gum rubber and provides contrast to the Lucid Pink 3-Stripes. The women’s size adidas Samba OG Lucid Pink (Women's) was released on May 8, 2024, and sold for $100.

name: White Pure Platinum
title: Nike Dunk Low Retro White Pure Platinum
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Retro White Pure Platinum is a low-top counterpart to the classic Dunk High silhouette. 

The Nike Dunk Low Retro has an all-leather construction leaving the Swoosh logos, outsole, and branded heel tabs in a Platinum grey tone. The shoe has a low-cut padded collar and a perforated toe box with Nike branding in the woven tongue tag, sock liner, and heel tab. It has a rubber cupsole for traction with stitched sidewall construction and an interior foam wedge for comfort. 

The Nike Dunk Low Retro White Pure Platinum was released on 19th November 2022. Upon its launch, its retail price was $110.

name: TIGHTBOOTH
title: Nike SB Dunk Low TIGHTBOOTH
description:
The TIGHTBOOTH x Nike SB Dunk Low is where the heartbeat of the city meets the soul of skate culture. Releasing on November 14, 2023, this sneaker is a celebration of the skateboarding scene and the urban landscape it thrives in. The White/Black-Safety Orange colorway mirrors the street lights and city nights, serving as a beacon for skaters everywhere.

This collaboration is about more than just looks—it's about the feel of the board underfoot and the grip on the pavement. The reflective elements and textural contrasts are inspired by the very streets that skaters call home. It’s a sneaker that doesn't just stand out visually; it's built to perform under the cover of darkness, embodying the essence of nocturnal sessions.

At $135, the TIGHTBOOTH Nike SB Sunk Low collaboration is an investment into the legacy of street skating. It's a bold statement piece for those who make the city their playground after sundown.

name: Summit White Malachite
title: Nike Dunk Low Retro Summit White Malachite
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Retro Summit White Malachite is a low-top basketball shoe with a vintage-inspired colorway of Summit White and Malachite.

This colorway is similar to the ones first seen in 1985 and gives the sneaker a retro varsity athletics aesthetic. The upper is made of Summit White leather with leather forefoot and heel overlays in grayish white. Perforations decorate the vamp, allowing the foot to breathe, while the lace cage houses Summit White aces. The signature Swoosh logo comes in Malachite and checks across the side panels. It matches the Malachite on the rubber outsole and lettering across the woven tongue tag. In addition, the ‘NIKE’ lettering embroidered on the heel tab also comes in Malachite.

Our experts at StockX like the incorporation of a cupsole, which grips the ground and provides additional traction. The Nike Dunk Low Retro Summit White Malachite was released on January 5th, 2024, and retailed at $115.

name: True Blue
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG True Blue
description:
The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG True Blue was a special release that marks the 35th anniversary of the Air Jordan 3 line.

The upper section of this Retro High shoe is constructed of smooth leather. The base is white, the Swoosh is true blue, and the overlays are true blue and cement gray. True blue is also used for the Wings logo on the collar, tongue tag, laces, Nike Air branding on the white insole, and sock liner. Soles with encapsulated AIR units complete the design.

The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG True Blue debuted on January 14th, 2023 for $180 retail.

name: Light Iron Ore
title: Nike P-6000 Light Iron Ore
description:
Taking its inspiration from the Nike Air Pegasus from 2006, the Nike P-6000 Light Iron Ore is a sneaker with an early 2000s aesthetic that delivers updated comfort and durability.

The Light Iron Ore colorway of the Nike P-6000 features an upper with a base of loosely woven white mesh with darker textiles showing through. This is overlaid with real and synthetic leather and suede in hues of gray. A gray molded leather Nike swoosh outlined in black courses across the side panel, an embroidered gray Nike swoosh adorns the heel counter, an embossed Nike swoosh rests below and on the brown-gray mudguard, and Nike branding graces the tongue tag. A Nike swoosh appears on the toe box and insole.  A durable rubber outsole in shades of dark to light gray and a white foam midsole for cushioning round out this shoe.

Our favorite feature of this shoe is the dark gray tongue webbing with Bowerman Series branding, a nod to Nike co-founder Bill Bowerman. The Nike P-6000 Light Iron Ore was released on July 8, 2023, for $120 retail.

name: Spider-Man Across the Spider-Verse (GS)
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Spider-Man Across the Spider-Verse (GS)
description:
The Air Jordan 1 High OG Spider-Man Across the Spider-Verse GS showcases a visual composition incorporating three primary colors: white, black, and University Red, which collectively shape its overall look.

This High OG Spider-Man Across the Spider-Verse Air Jordan 1 in grade-school sizing features a white leather upper with black patent-leather on the collar and Nike Swoosh. The overlays in scarlet color are made of a combination of different textures and prints, creating a patchwork-like design that pays homage to the diverse Spider-Man universe. On the side of the shoe, you'll find a classic Wings logo, and the nylon tongue is adorned with a woven Nike tag. The high-top sneaker is completed with a rubber cup sole that combines worn sidewalls with a semi-translucent crimson outsole.

We discovered that the design of this sneaker was inspired by the original Spider-Man, which featured in the movie "Across the Spider-Verse." During its launch on May20, 2023, the Air Jordan 1 High OG Spider-Man Across the Spider-Verse GS retailed for $150.

name: Travis Scott University Red
title: Jordan Jumpman Jack TR Travis Scott University Red
description:
The release of the Air Jordan Jumpman Jack TR Travis Scott University Red marks a momentous occasion: the first wide public launch of a brand-new, original colorway from the collaborative genius of Jordan Brand and Travis Scott. This sneaker is a homage to the past and a forward leap in design, drawing inspiration from classic basketball sneakers of the '80s and the rugged aesthetic of '90s skate shoes. It’s a perfect blend for enthusiasts who appreciate a retro vibe with a modern twist.

Travis Scott's first entirely original silhouette comes to life with the iconic, signature reversed Nike Swoosh in a bold university red, contrasting strikingly against the timeless sail & black upper. The carefully pre-yellowed midsole adds a touch of vintage appeal, invoking a sense of nostalgia while remaining at the pinnacle of style.
