Complete with a special co-branded shoe box and dust bag, the Jordan Jumpman Jack TR is as much a collector's piece as it is a testament to sneaker innovation.

Released on April 26, 2024, the Air Jordan Jumpman Jack TR Travis Scott University Red retailed for $200. This sneaker is the inception of Travis Scott's original design legacy, offering a unique take on sneaker culture. With its rich 80s and 90s influences and the unmatched Travis Scott brand power, this sneaker is ready to conquer the streets and capture the essence of both basketball and skateboarding heritage.

name: Off Noir (Women's)
title: Jordan 3 Retro Off Noir
description:
The Jordan 3 Retro Off Noir (Women's) takes a classic silhouette and dresses it in a fusion of different colors and textures and sizes it for women. This sneaker offers elite style and high-performance capabilities.

The Women's Off Noir Jordan 3 Retro sports a base of black nubuck suede overlaid with black leather. The black leather of the tongue, eye stays, and collar is perforated, adding both style and breathability. Elephant print leather overlays the heel and toe. A tonal embossed Jumpman logo adorns the heel tab while a tonal debossed Jumpman graces the tongue. The eyelets provide the one hit of coconut milk on the upper.

What we enjoy most about this singular shoe is its tried-and-true sole unit. Coconut milk-colored foam in the midsole houses visible Air for both cushioning and spring. The gray rubber outsole absorbs impact and provides multidirectional traction. The Jordan 3 Retro Off Noir (Women's) was released on November 15, 2023, for a retail price of $200.

name: Sandy Bodecker
title: Nike SB Dunk Low Sandy Bodecker
description:
The Nike SB Dunk Low Sandy Bodecker was inspired by the original 2003 eBay Charity Auction Nike SB Dunk Low.

It has a white base with overlays in the company's trademark red, green, blue, and yellow colors. The sneaker features clear stripes on its vamp, on the heel, and on the middle part. In addition, the shoe features a blue Nike Swoosh on both sides with an SB emblem on its heel panel. Its tongue panel is constructed with a padded cushion with a Nike Swoosh printed on it.

The Nike SB Dunk Low Sandy Bodecker debuted on December 17th, 2022, and retailed at $130.

name: University Blue
title: Jordan 4 Retro University Blue
description:
Jordan Brand paid homage to MJ’s alma mater with the Air Jordan 4 University Blue. The University Blue colorway draws a close resemblance to the extremely rare Air Jordan 4 UNC PE that was given to Tarheel student-athletes in 2019.

The Air Jordan 4 University Blue features a University Blue suede upper with mesh netting on the quarter panel and tongue. Similar to OG Jordan 4 colorways of the past, the eyelets, heel tab, and sections of the midsole are a speckled Cement Grey. Hits of black appear on the wing eyelets, sole, and Jumpman logo on the heel tab. Two woven labels are stitched to the tongue; one being the classic Jumpman woven label; the other being a Team Jordan jock tag. A black, white, and Tech Grey sole with a clear Air unit completes the design.

The Air Jordan 4 University Blue released in April of 2021 and retailed for $200.

name: White Cement Reimagined (GS)
title: Jordan 3 Retro White Cement Reimagined (GS)
description:
The Air Jordan 3 Retro White Cement Reimagined GS was released to celebrate the 35th anniversary of the Air Jordan 3 designed by Tinker Hatfield.

The Air Jordan 3 Retro White Cement Reimagined in grade-school sizing features a white leather upper adorned with elephant print overlays on the heel and toe, accents of Varsity Red on the lace loops, and a Jumpman logo on the tongue. Its vintage polyurethane midsole is accompanied by an exposed unit in the heel and an encapsulated Air-sole unit in the forefoot. Additionally, a crimson Jumpman logo is stitched onto the white leather tongue, while the back tab has a pre-yellowed appearance with an embossed Nike Air logo.

The Air Jordan 3 Retro White Cement Reimagined GS was released on 11th March 2023 with its retail price set at $150.

name: One Piece Blackbeard Teech
title: Puma Suede One Piece Blackbeard Teech
description:
The Puma Suede One Piece Blackbeard Teech sneaker is a daring fusion of Puma's classic style with the dark allure of one of the most formidable characters from the beloved anime series, One Piece. Decked in puma black and dark chocolate, this edition captures the essence of Marshall D. Teach, aka Blackbeard, with its bold and brooding color scheme. Designed for fans who appreciate the depth of storytelling and the complexity of character development in One Piece, this sneaker is a tribute to the series' iconic antagonist.

Crafted with the legendary Puma Suede silhouette, this sneaker offers timeless style coupled with modern design elements inspired by the One Piece universe. The choice of colors represents Blackbeard's menacing presence and his pivotal role in the series, providing fans with a piece of wearable art that's both stylish and symbolic. It's a perfect blend of streetwear fashion and anime culture, appealing to those who live at the intersection of comfort, style, and fandom.

Released on March 23, 2024, for $85, the Puma Suede One Piece Blackbeard Teech quickly became a coveted item among both sneaker enthusiasts and anime fans. Its launch is celebrated as a moment when Puma seamlessly integrated the spirit of One Piece into their classic suede design, offering a sneaker that's statement of allegiance to one of anime's most compelling narratives. This sneaker is a declaration of style and a nod to the enduring legacy of One Piece.

name: Heritage
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Heritage
description:
The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG Heritage flips the original Chicago colorway for a bold, unique look. It features a white and University Red smooth leather upper with black leather collars and red Swooshes. From there, a black and red woven Nike tongue label and an Air sole at the base completes the design.

The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG Heritage released in 2022 and retailed for $170.

name: Lil Yachty Concrete Boys It's Us
title: Nike Air Force 1 Low Lil Yachty Concrete Boys It's Us
description:
The Nike Air Force 1 Low Lil Yachty Concrete Boys It's Us updates the Air Force 1 Low’s familiar silhouette with details inspired by American rapper Lil Yachty’s Concrete Boys collective.

The all-white base of the Lil Yachty Concrete Boys It's Us version of the Air Force 1 Low serves as an ideal backdrop for Concrete Boys’ branding. The collective’s logo—a stickman wielding a sledgehammer—is embroidered on the outer side panel in Midnight Navy thread. The heel tab displays additional Concrete Boys’ branding, including construction equipment, "CONCRETE BOYS" lettering, and another stickman. The tongue’s logo tag showcases a Swoosh and the words "IT’S US," a reference to the collective’s 2024 compilation titled "It's Us, Vol. 1."

Our experts at StockX like that the collar lining and the rubber outsole come in Midnight Navy because the dark hue sets off the all-white upper. The Nike Air Force 1 Low Lil Yachty Concrete Boys It's Us was released on December 2, 2024, and sold for $130.

name: Pale Coral (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Next Nature Pale Coral (Women's)
description:
Constructed of 50% recycled materials, the women's Nike Dunk Low Next Nature Pale Coral (W) features a white Flyleather upper with Pale Coral overlays and Swooshes. From there, matching soles and woven tongue labels complete the design.

The women's Nike Dunk Low Next Nature Pale Coral (W) released in November of 2021 and retailed for $100.

name: White Aqua (GS)
title: ASICS Gel-1130 White Aqua (GS)
description:
The ASICS Gel-1130 White Aqua (GS) presents the Gel-1130 in a kids’ size. This technical running shoe boasts performance-enhancing technologies and a colorway of crisp white and aqua.

The upper construction features breathable mesh in white with a slightly loose weave. Aqua accents add splashes of color on the tongue branding, plastic pieces on the midsole, and along the upper. Like running sneakers in the ASICS catalog from the early 2000s, this shoe displays synthetic overlays with black and metallic silver stripes. In terms of technology, gel units in the midsole provide supportive cushioning and protect against impact stress. Padding around the collar and in the tongue contributes to the sneaker’s bulky, Y2K aesthetic.

Our StockX experts like the metallic silver mudguard that protects the toe area and carries a hint of aqua. The grade school–sized ASICS Gel-1130 White Aqua (GS) was originally released on March 3, 2024, and sold for $85.

name: Triple Black
title: adidas NMD R1 Primeblue Triple Black
description:
The adidas NMD R1 Primeblue Triple Black is made from recycled material made in part with Parley Ocean Plastic.

The sneaker is purely black in color, from the laces to the sole, the tongue, and even the decorative highlights. The adidas trefoil logo is displayed on the top of the tongue, on the heel, and on the front end of the sole. The adidas NMD R1 Primeblue Triple Black also has three stripes on each side of the shoe and is completed with a stretchy knit upper.

The adidas NMD R1 Primeblue Triple Black was released in June of 2021 at the retail price of $140.

name: Collegiate Green Gum Grey Toe
title: adidas Samba OG Collegiate Green Gum Grey Toe
description:
The adidas Samba OG Collegiate Green Gum Grey Toe is a modern take on the adidas Samba sneaker.

The Samba OG Collegiate in Green Gum Grey Toe features a Collegiate Green color scheme with white accents on the branding elements and a grey overlay on the toe. The shoe is made with premium materials, including a suede upper and leather accents, making it both comfortable and durable. The 3-Stripes are displayed prominently on the sides, adding to the shoe's recognizable design. The sneaker also features a low-top silhouette and a soft lining for a comfortable fit. It comes with flat Collegiate Green laces for a secure fit.

We believe that one of the most noteworthy features of the adidas Samba OG Collegiate Green Gum Grey Toe is its distinctive gum sole. This sole offers superior grip and traction, making it a fantastic option for both athletic use and everyday wear. The sneaker debuted on May 8th, 2023, and retailed for $100.

name: Shadow 2.0
title: Jordan 1 Retro High Shadow 2.0
description:
The upper of the Air Jordan 1 Shadow 2.0 is made of a black leather base with Light Smoke Grey overlays. A classic Wings logo appears on the lateral ankle wrap while a woven Nike Air label is stitched atop the tongue to complete the look.

The Air Jordan 1 Shadow 2.0 released in May of 2021 and retailed for $170.

name: Court Purple White
title: Jordan 1 Retro High Court Purple White
description:
Jordan Brand added a new colorway to the silhouette that started it all with the Jordan 1 Retro High Court Purple White, now available on StockX. This release follows similar design elements as the Chicago 1, only this time replacing red with Court Purple.

This Jordan 1 consists of a white leather upper with Court Purple overlays and black detailing. A black Swoosh and Wings logo, white midsole, and Court Purple outsole completes the design. These sneakers released in April of 2020 and retailed for $170.

name: Stone Island Light Green
title: New Balance 574 Legacy Stone Island Light Green
description:
The New Balance 574 Legacy Stone Island Light Green was released as part of Stone Island's Summer/Fall 2024 collection and represents a collaboration with New Balance. It reinterprets New Balance's iconic 574 silhouette and incorporates premium yet practical materials.

Stone Island is an Italian menswear label known for researching fabrics and innovative designs. The Stone Island Light Green New Balance 574 Legacy embodies this ethos by crafting the upper with ripstop fabric in Mustard Gold and nubuck in Light Green. The overlays display the iconic New Balance "N," which uses a rubberized material. A panel on the medial side displays "STONE ISLAND PRODUCT RESEARCH," which pays tribute to the label's design process.

Our experts at StockX like the dual branding, including the Stone Island compass logo on the tongue and "NEW BALANCE" on the heel tab. The New Balance 574 Legacy Stone Island Light Green was released on June 14, 2024, and sold for $140.

name: Triple White
title: New Balance 550 Triple White
description:
The New Balance 550 Triple White is a reimagined design of the original 1989 New Balance 550, worn by pro ballers in the 80s and 90s.

Everything about this shoe is white, from its branding to its laces to its midsole. Its upper consists primarily of leather and slightly breathable mesh underlays. The upper sits on a cushioned midsole and a rubber outsole with patterns underneath for improved underground grip. Like the original, it features distinct stitching throughout its body, 550 branding and "N" logos on its sides, and NB branding on its outsole.

The New Balance 550 Triple White debuted on 10th October 2022 with an original retail price of $110.

name: Granite Pink
title: New Balance 9060 Granite Pink
description:
The New Balance 9060 Granite Pink finds inspiration in the visible tech aesthetic found in running shoes from the early 2000s.

The upper is crafted from breathable mesh in Pink Granite with pig suede and leather overlays in Granite. The New Balance "N" on the outer side panel is made of synthetic leather in metallic silver, while the "N" on the inner side panel is made up of reflective tape lines. The sculpted midsole houses ABZORB and SBS cushioning, which protects against impact and adds a bulky aesthetic to this 2000s-inspired sneaker. The front lace-up closure is adjustable and houses off-white laces that match the technical midsole pods.

Our experts at StockX like the subtle branding details, including the tongue’s logo tag and the "new balance" lettering on the synthetic insole. The New Balance 9060 Granite Pink was released on February 15, 2024, and retailed at $150.

name: Court Vision (Women's)
title: Nike Sabrina 2 Tunnel Vision (Women's)
description:
The Nike Sabrina 2 Court Vision (Women's) updates the Sabrina 1 created by WNBA player Sabrina Ionescu with performance-enhancing features.

The Sabrina 2 replaces the React foam midsole with a Cushlon 3.0 foam midsole. Combined with the Zoom Air unit in the forefoot, this upgrade allows for increased impact protection without reducing agility. The mesh upper helps the foot breathe, while the locked-in feel comes in part from the containment fit bands that wrap around the midfoot. In addition, the "S" herringbone pattern on the rubber outsole supports multi-directional traction and quick movements.

Our experts at StockX like the shattered glass embroidery patterns on the upper that symbolize Ionescu’s ability to shatter the proverbial glass ceiling in the world of women’s sports and beyond. The sneaker also displays an ‘i’ on the heel that represents Ionescu’s last name. The women’s size Nike Sabrina 2 Court Vision (Women's) was released on June 25, 2024, and sold for $130.

name: Black Elephant
title: Jordan 1 Low SE Black Elephant
description:
The Jordan 1 Low SE Black Elephant dresses an iconic silhouette in a black-on-black colorway accented with the signature elephant print that was introduced by designer Tinker Hatfield on the Air Jordan 3 in 1988.

The Black Elephant Special Edition Jordan 1 Low-Top sports a stealthy black upper relieved only by the white embroidered Wings logo on the heel. The base is smooth black leather with smooth black leather overlays adorning the toe, eye stays, and vamp. The collar, heel overlay, and quarter panel Nike are in a black leather elephant print. The sock liner is black mesh, and the black mesh tongue has an embroidered black Jumpman.

What our sneaker experts appreciate most about this sports shoe is the sole unit that firmly locks in this shoe as a tried-and-true AJ1. The white foam midsole with an encapsulated Air unit for maximum cushioning rests on a black rubber outsole grooved for traction on many surfaces. The Jordan 1 Low SE Black Elephant was released on October 20, 2023, for $125 retail.

name: Brotherhood
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Brotherhood
description:
Jordan Brand honored Michael Jordan's time as a member of one of the most historic African American college fraternities with the Air Jordan 1 High Brotherhood.

Drawing inspiration from the Omega Psi Phi crest, the Air Jordan 1 High Brotherhood arrives with a vibrant University Gold, purple, and white leather construction. Its color blocking is simple and bold, similar to past Jordan 1 releases like the Shattered Backboards and Bred Toes. In retro fashion, a woven Nike tongue label and Wings logo at the collar complete the design.

The Air Jordan 1 High Brotherhood released in February of 2022 and retailed for $170.

name: Cream
title: ASICS Gel-NYC Cream
description:
The ASICS Gel-NYC Cream draws inspiration from contemporary and heritage models in the ASICS catalog. It boasts a neutral colorway with hits of metallic silver and earthy-brown accents.

The mixed-material upper borrows details from two retro sneakers from the 2000s: the Gel-Nimbus 3 and the Gel-MC Plus V. The mesh base comes in Cream with layers of overlays in Cream and metallic silver. The signature Formstripes also display Cream and create a web across the quarter panels. One of the most eye-catching design elements is the suede mudguard wrapping around the shoe. It features "ASICS" lettering and complements the beige tones on the midsole. Adding a modern element to the retro design, the tooling system comes from the Gel-Cumulus 16. Providing advanced cushioning, the midsole includes Gel inserts and soft foam.

Our experts like the inclusion of Gel inserts in the heel and forefoot for maximum comfort. The ASICS Gel-NYC Cream was released on June 21, 2024, and sold for $130.

name: City of Cinema
title: Nike SB Dunk Low City of Cinema
description:
The Nike SB Dunk Low City of Cinema is a low-top athletic shoe featuring a Celestial Gold leather upper with a mottled finish, accented by the Nike Swoosh in black on the sides. The tongue and heel collar are done in Dark Team Red crushed velvet, accented by coordinating laces and Nike branding in Baroque Brown and Gold. An Armory Navy heel tab displays embroidered Nike branding, while the Baroque Brown outsole coordinates the aesthetic.

The Nike Dunk has evolved from a university sports shoe into a staple within Nike SB, the American sneaker brand’s skateboarding collection. In honor of the Olympic Games 2024, held in Paris, France, Nike released the City of Cinema Dunk Low, which features an aesthetic that recalls the decor of classic Parisian theaters.

In our opinion, the best feature of these shoes is their velvet accents, which are not a common fabrication in sneakers. The Nike SB Dunk Low City of Cinema was released on October 10, 2024, and retailed for $125.

name: University Blue
title: Jordan 1 Mule Golf University Blue
description:
The Jordan 1 Mule Golf University Blue is a slip-on golf shoe whose design was inspired by a 2021 version of the AJ 1 Retro High OG sneaker.

This iteration of the Jordan 1 Mule Golf has a white leather base that is perforated at the toebox for breathability. UNC blue suede overlays round out the toebox, heel, and run up the sides of where the laces would be on a traditional sneaker. The Nike Swoosh appears in black on the midsoles. There is a patch with the Jumpman logo and the word "GOLF" in black on the tongue. Memory foam is used as cushioning on the inside for extra comfort, while a white and blue rubber outsole provides grip and traction.

Our favorite feature of these shoes is the clean UNC colorway formed by suede overlays. It gives the shoe a classic look. The Jordan 1 Mule Golf University Blue was released on March 1, 2024, for a retail price of $110.

name: Tiempo Pack Black
title: Nike Killshot 2 LTR PRM Tiempo Pack Black
description:
The Nike Killshot 2 LTR PRM Tiempo Pack Black updates the Killshot 2 with premium materials and a soccer-inspired design.

Although the original Killshot from 1979 was created for the tennis court, the Tiempo Pack Black Nike Killshot 2 LTR PRM includes a fold-over "tongue," mimicking 1980s soccer cleats. Although it looks like a tongue, this piece of black leather is actually a removable attachment. The upper is crafted from smooth, black leather with exposed stitching in clean white. The stitching highlights the mudguard, the Swoosh logos, the eyelets, the heel counter, and the collar. Branding details grace the fold-over "tongue," the functional tongue, and the smooth heel tab.

Our experts at StockX like that the grippy rubber outsole comes in Baroque Brown. This hue complements the black upper and gives the sneaker an earthy finish. The Nike Killshot 2 LTR PRM Tiempo Pack Black was released on September 18, 2024, and sold for $90.

name: Team Red
title: Nike Dunk Low Team Red
description:
Constructed of white and Team Red smooth leather, the Nike Dunk Low Team Red is an ode to the original look of the 1985 Nike Dunk Low. Nike embroideries on the heel tab and a woven tongue label arrive in a classic fashion. From there, a white and Team Red sole completes the design.

The Nike Dunk Low Team Red released in May of 2022 and retailed for $100. It was also re-released in 2023.

name: Panda Elephant
title: Jordan 1 Mid SE Panda Elephant
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Panda was first released in 2021, and since then, it has helped influence many of the other sneakers that Nike has put out. The Air Jordan 1 Mid SE Panda Elephant was one of the examples of this.

The upper on this Air Jordan 1 was made entirely out of leather with a white base complemented by black overlays that gave it the signature "Panda" look. These colors also continued throughout the rest of the shoe thanks to its two-tone white midsole and its black outsole.

But the best part about this particular Air Jordan 1 was the suede elephant print that was utilized to create both the Swooshes and the collars on the sneakers. It helped make this more than just another black-and-white Nike sneaker. The Jordan 1 Mid SE Panda Elephant was released on October 20, 2023, for an original retail price of $135.

name: Stash (2024)
title: Nike Air Max 95 Stash (2024)
description:
The Nike Air Max 95 Stash (2024) is a striking collaboration that brings together the iconic silhouette of the Air Max 95 with the artistic vision of graffiti legend Stash. This men's sneaker features a captivating Obsidian, Black, and Harbor Blue colorway that pays homage to Stash's signature palette. The upper showcases a gradient effect, reminiscent of the original Air Max 95 design, while incorporating unique textures and materials that reflect Stash's urban-inspired aesthetic.

Functionality meets style in this reimagined classic. The shoe retains the Air Max 95's renowned comfort with its visible Air units in the heel and forefoot, providing responsive cushioning for all-day wear. Premium materials adorn the upper, including durable synthetics and plush textiles, ensuring both longevity and a luxurious feel. The distinctive lacing system and subtle branding elements add to the shoe's appeal, making it a standout piece for sneaker enthusiasts and collectors alike.

Us at StockX believe this product is great for those seeking a perfect blend of street-style edge and athletic performance, offering a unique twist on a beloved Nike silhouette.

name: Court Purple (GS)
title: Nike Kobe 8 Protro Court Purple (GS)
description:
The Nike Kobe 8 Protro Court Purple (GS) celebrates NBA player Kobe Bryant and the 20 years he spent playing for the Los Angeles Lakers through symbols and signature colors.

Like the adult-sized version, the GS Kobe 8 Protro Court Purple displays the numbers ‘8’ and ‘24’ across the upper in a repeating pattern. ‘8’ represents Kobe Bryant’s first jersey number and ‘24’ is the jersey number he switched to in order to celebrate his growth. The numbers come in Court Purple and stand out against the sneaker’s white mesh base. Other details also come in Court Purple, including the laces, stripes on the heel, the signature, and the Swooshes.

Our StockX experts like the semi-translucent outsole that supports the carbon fiber shank plank beneath the arch. The grade school-sized Nike Kobe 8 Protro Court Purple (GS) was released on February 8th, 2024, and retailed at $120.

name: Blue Tint
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Blue Tint
description:
In a similar pattern to the renowned adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Zebra, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Blue Tint features a marbled grey Primeknit upper with a light grey side stripe that is decorated with bright red SPLY-350 text. At the base, a Blue Tint semi-translucent Boost sole adds cushioning and support.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Blue Tint originally released in December of 2017, and restocked in January of 2022 at a retail price of $220.

name: Silver Metallic Sea Salt
title: New Balance 1906R Silver Metallic Sea Salt
description:
The New Balance 1906R Silver Metallic Sea Salt adds a neutral colorway with metallic accents to the recognizable 1906R silhouette.

Featuring a bulky construction and crisscrossing overlays, the New Balance 1906R Silver Metallic Sea Salt draws inspiration from early 2000s technical running shoes. However, the gentle colorway is a contemporary addition. The base features lightweight mesh in Sea Salt and synthetic leather overlays in Silver Metallic with reflective detailing. The ABZORB midsole and N-ergy cushioning provide stability and protect against impact. In addition, the Stability Web technology creates a supportive base for the runner. The laces come in Sea Salt and can be adjusted for a customizable fit.

Our experts at StockX like the splash of black beneath the heel that breaks up the Sea Salt and tan tones on the midsole. The New Balance 1906R Silver Metallic Sea Salt was released on November 24, 2023, and retailed at $155.

name: Colorado Away White Black
title: Nike Air DT Max '96 Colorado Away White Black
description:
The Nike Air DT Max '96 Colorado Away White Black is an updated relaunch of Deion Sanders’ iconic Air DT Max ’96.

The Colorado Away White Black Nike Air DT Max '96 returns with a colorway inspired by the University of Colorado at Boulder’s Colorado Buffaloes. As head coach of the college football team, Sanders dresses the retro-inspired sneaker in a color palette that matches the road uniforms. The top half displays white leather, while the black leather underlays feature a claw mark-like design. This pattern seamlessly blends into the black polyurethane midsole, highlighting the visible Air Max units in the heel. Securing the fit, an adjustable midfoot strap crosses the lace cage with a black Swoosh logo.

Our experts at StockX like the flashy gold details, including the Swoosh logos on the upper and the components on the rubber outsole. The Nike Air DT Max '96 Colorado Away White Black was released on September 16, 2024, and sold for $170.

name: Blue Bird Gum
title: adidas Gazelle Indoor Blue Bird Gum
description:
The adidas Gazelle Indoor Blue Bird Gum has a vintage-inspired design that features a Blue Bird upper and a gum rubber sole.

The Gazelle Indoor Blue Bird Gum has a suede upper that is soft and durable. The shoe also features a classic lace-up closure that ensures a secure, comfortable fit. The adidas logo features on the tongue, heel, and sole, while the word gazelle is seen right above the adidas 3-Stripes. The shoe boasts a low-profile design that promotes better stability and balance. The shoe's slim profile and low-to-the-ground construction make it easier for you to maintain proper posture and alignment while you move. The tongue and collar are both padded with soft materials that provide additional comfort and support around ankle area.

We simply love the adidas Gazelle Indoor Blue Bird Gum for its translucent sole that is visible throughout . The sneaker was released on July 15th, 2022 at a retail price of $150.

name: Glow Green (2022/2023 Restock)
title: adidas Yeezy Slide Glow Green (2022/2023 Restock)
description:
DISCLAIMER: US and UK sizing is the same and does not require any conversion.
The Yeezy Slide Glow (2022 Restock) arrives as a more vibrant variation of the 2021 Yeezy Slide Glow. It is constructed with a Glow EVA foam for comfort and responsiveness. A grooved outsole adds proper traction for daily wear.

The Yeezy Slide Glow (2022 Restock) released in May of 2022 and retailed for $60.

name: Neutral Grey Sail
title: Jordan 1 Mid SE Neutral Grey Sail
description:
Premium, versatile, and with a timeless design, the Air Jordan 1 Mid SE Neutral Grey Sail effortlessly elevates a sneakerhead’s game – and offers comfort and durability to boot.

Pumped full of the legendary Nike Air cushioning for the bounciest, most comfortable step, these Air Jordan Mid’s bring a sophisticated touch of the legendary silhouette while popping with a crisp color combo. The uppers are a combination of greys, including ‘neutral,’ ‘sail,’ and ‘smoke grey.’ White base coloring on the laces, toe box, and sides, the suede and textile help the Wings and Jumpman logos pop. A Nike Swoosh sits on both inners of the shoe. This show boasts great rubber soles for traction, and a breathable toe box delivers comfort.

We love the sophisticated color palette of these Nike Air Jordans. A legendary shoe, street cred comes standard with the Air Jordan 1 Mid SE Neutral Grey Sail, released on 1 July 2024, priced at $135.

name: Jade Smoke (Women's)
title: Jordan 1 Low Jade Smoke (Women's)
description:
The Jordan 1 Low Jade Smoke (Women's) is a low-top sneaker that features bold color blocking in Jade Smoke, Anthracite, and Sail.

The upper is constructed primarily from smooth leather with Anthracite as the base and Sail on the forefoot overlays, the mudguard, the heel counter, and around the collar. The flat, black tongue is made from a synthetic textile, which makes the sneaker stand out from other Jordan 1 Low models. Jade Smoke can only be found on the Swoosh logos, which check across the side panels. Other branding details include the Air Jordan Wings logo on the heel and a white Jumpman on the tongue.

Something our StockX experts like is the choice of Legend Sand for the midsole. The slightly off-white hue gives the sneaker a retro, worn-in appearance. The women’s size Jordan 1 Low Jade Smoke (Women's) was released on April 1, 2024, and retailed at $115.

name: White Black
title: Nike Blazer Mid 77 Jumbo White Black
description:
The Nike Blazer Mid 77 Jumbo White Black is a remodeled edition of the classic Nike Blazer, which was styled in the 70s, a staple shoe in the 80s, and a classic in the 90s.

Although it harnesses the old-school look of the original sneaker, this rethought sneaker features an elastic heel with large pull tabs. It also features oversized Nike swooshes on its sides, jumbo laces, raised herringbone pattern on the rubber outsole, a soft suede accent on the toe, and red stitching around its toe and heel.

The Nike Blazer Mid 77 Jumbo White Black was released on 4th November 2021. During its release, this sneaker had a retail price of $110.

name: Wheat
title: Nike SB Dunk Low Wheat
description:
The Nike SB Dunk Low Wheat comes in a Wheat and Wheat-Baroque Brown-Gum color scheme.

This SB Dunk model by Nike features a wheat suede base with matching shades of tan on the shoe’s lining, mesh tongues, and laces. Dark Brown branding appears on the sneaker’s tongue and the heels. The midsole matches the sneaker’s upper color scheme. Its boxing toe features perforations meant for aeration. The design further boasts a gum rubber outsole. The outsole is parted patterned for traction.

The Nike SB Dunk Low Wheat was first launched in February 2021 with a retail price set at $110.

name: Bred Reimagined (PS)
title: Jordan 4 Retro Bred Reimagined (PS)
description:
The Jordan 4 Retro Bred Reimagined (PS) takes the Air Jordan 4 Retro’s signature silhouette and reinvents it for kids.

Like the adult-sized model, the (PS) Jordan 4 Retro "Bred Reimagined" is part of Jordan Brand’s Reimagined series. Unlike previous models, this sneaker boasts an upper made of leather instead of velvety nubuck. It creates a smoother finish and allows light the bounce off the upper. Mesh netting can be found on the quarter panels and allows the foot to breathe. While the construction is mostly black, Cement Gray, and Varsity Red elements add contrast. For example, the Jumpman logo on the tongue, the tongue’s inner lining, and patches of tread on the rubber outsole come in Varsity Red.

Our StockX experts like the Nike branding in Cement Gray on the heel counter because it offers a throwback to the original sneaker. The pre-school-sized Jordan 4 Retro Bred Reimagined (PS) was released on February 17th, 2024, and retailed at $100.

name: A Ma Maniére Dusk
title: Jordan 5 Retro A Ma Maniére Dusk
description:
The Jordan 5 Retro A Ma Maniére Dusk takes center stage in a collaboration between A Ma Maniére and the Air Jordan Brand. It is part of a dynamic two-sneaker pack and is dressed in black and burgundy crush with additional black and pale ivory accents.

This high-top silhouette features a black suede upper. Pale-ivory mesh netting made out of A Ma Maniére’s distinctive ‘A’ logo is found on the quarter and part of the tongue. The sleek design is complemented by black-on-black ‘Nike Air’ embroidery on the heel and a silver reflective tongue that displays black Jumpman branding. The black polyurethane midsole, embellished with shark-tooth detailing in a deep burgundy hue, provides a striking contrast, while the pre-aged translucent rubber outsole gives it some added flair. Black laces can be held tightly in place with a translucent Nike-branded lace lock.

A standout feature is the visible Air pack in the heel that sports A Ma Maniére branding on the lateral side of the shoe. The Jordan 5 Retro A Ma Maniére Dusk sneaker sold for $225 during its retail debut on November 24, 2023.

name: Cream Pure Silver (Women's)
title: ASICS Gel-1130 Cream Pure Silver (Women's)
description: The ASICS Gel 1130 Cream Pure Silver W is a sleek and stylish running shoe that offers both comfort and performance. The shoe features a cream-colored upper with silver accents, giving it a clean and modern look. The Gel cushioning system provides excellent shock absorption, while the durable rubber outsole offers traction and stability on a variety of surfaces. The ASICS Gel 1130 Cream Pure Silver W is made with high-quality materials, including a breathable mesh upper and synthetic overlays for added support. The shoe also features a padded collar and tongue for added comfort, as well as a removable sockliner that can be replaced with custom orthotics. Released on September 1st, 2021, the ASICS Gel 1130 Cream Pure Silver W is priced at $70, making it an affordable option for runners of all levels. Whether you're a seasoned athlete or just starting out, this shoe is sure to provide the support and comfort you need to reach your goals. Something we love about the ASICS Gel 1130 Cream Pure Silver W is its versatile design, which makes it a great choice for both running and everyday wear. Our experts think the best features of this shoe are its Gel cushioning system and durable rubber outsole, which provide excellent support and traction. Overall, we think the standout feature of the ASICS Gel 1130 Cream Pure Silver W is its combination of style and performance, making it a must-have for any runner's shoe collection.

name: White Cement
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG White Cement
description:
The Air Jordan 1 is getting the cement print treatment, with the release of the Jordan 1 Retro High OG White Cement. Jordan is drawing inspiration from the popular Air Jordan 3 silhouette with its elephant inspired cement print.

The Jordan 1 Retro High OG White Cement is constructed with high quality white leather uppers, with a contrasting black nike swoosh and leather accents. The sneakers are highlighted with gray cement print, and are tied together with black laces and sit on top of a muslin midsole, giving the sneaker a vintage look.

The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG White Cement released February 25, 2023, with a retail price of $180.

name: Sand
title: adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Sand
description:
DISCLAIMER: US and UK sizing is the same and does not require any conversion.

The adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Sand arrives in a Sand monochromatic color scheme. Its one-piece sculpted upper with oval cut-outs provide a futuristic aesthetic to complete the design.

The adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Sand released in May of 2021 and retailed for $75.

name: Concord (2018)
title: Jordan 11 Retro Concord (2018)
description: Jordan Brand is reaching harder than MJ on Space Jam for the sneaker of the year crown by releasing the Jordan 11 Retro Concord (2018). This Iconic Jordan 11 colorway is showcasing a white upper with black accents, white midsole, and a freezing cold translucent sole. These sneakers released in December 2018 and retailed for $220. Revisit the dominant legacy MJ left behind and grab a pair on StockX today.

name: White Pure Platinum
title: Nike Air Force 1 Flyknit 2 White Pure Platinum
description:
The Nike Air Force 1 Flyknit 2 White Pure Platinum features a white and Pure Platinum Flyknit and nubuck upper. From there, nubuck on the eyestays and logo and "Ultra" construction on the white midsole complete the design.

The Nike Air Force 1 Flyknit 2 White Pure Platinum released in May of 2019 and retailed for $110.

name: Preloved Purple
title: adidas AE 1 Preloved Purple
description:
The adidas AE 1 Preloved Purple redefines street-inspired footwear with a bold purple aesthetic. This shoe's unique color-blocking and premium materials highlight how innovative adidas is as a fitness and lifestyle brand. These kicks give you an ideal blend of performance and fashion.

The Preloved Purple AE 1 by adidas features a soft suede upper in black, with a rich purple-tone rubber outsole that almost covers the whole shoe, paired with contrasting white overlays for added depth. Adidas branding on the tongue and heel complements the color and style. These shoes were designed with versatility in mind and aim to bridge the gap between fashionable footwear and the athletic heritage of the German company´s shoes.

One thing we, the experts, love about the adidas AE 1 Preloved Purple is its semi-translucent, purple outsole, which adds elegant visual detail. Another standout feature is the suede upper. It retailed at $120 when it was released on 5th October 2024.

name: Tweed Midnight Navy Corduroy
title: Nike Dunk Low Tweed Midnight Navy Corduroy
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Tweed Midnight Navy Corduroy takes an iconic sports shoe silhouette and dresses it in elegance worthy of an English country estate.

The Tweed Midnight Navy Corduroy iteration of the Nike Dunk Low-Top features an upper with a base of navy corduroy. It is overlaid on the toe and eye stays with woolen-speckled brown tweed. The collar and heel are overlaid with brown plaid tweed. The side panel Nike swoosh is caramel-colored corduroy that matches the tumbled leather heel tab. The tongue and sock liner are also navy corduroy and match the insole with crisp white Nike branding. Blue Nike branding appears on the crisp white tongue tag. The outsole is gum rubber with a pattern for traction and absorbing impact.

What our experts love most about this sneaker is the way the cream-colored aspects of the shoe tie the aesthetic together. The Nike embroidery on the heel tab and the laces complement the cream-colored EVA foam midsole and lock in the look of the shoe. The Nike Dunk Low Tweed Midnight Navy Corduroy was released on November 8, 2023, for a retail price of $125.

name: Wales Bonner Desert White
title: adidas Samba Nylon Wales Bonner Desert White
description:
The adidas Samba Nylon Wales Bonner Desert White reimagines the Samba using the house codes of Wales Bonner. This London-based label combines preppy and athletic styles with Afro-Atlantic inspiration.

The smooth upper is made from leather in Desert White, while the 3-Stripes logo is a texturized leather in Wonder White. Like other versions of the adidas Samba, this iteration features a T-shaped overlay crafted from suede and a low-top silhouette. The textile inner lining displays a vibrant Ash Blue, complementing the Ash Blue and brown laces. Exaggerated stitching on the heel and tongue adds a touch of espadrille-inspired detailing, which the gold-tone metal eyelets contribute to the sneaker’s premium feel.

Our StockX experts like the dual Wales Bonner and adidas branding across the tongue and on the Ash Blue insole. The adidas Samba Nylon Wales Bonner Desert White was released on May 21, 2024, and sold for $160.

name: Cloud White Core Black (GS)
title: adidas Samba OG Cloud White Core Black (GS)
description:
The adidas Samba OG Cloud White Core Black (GS) is a grade school-sized version of the classic adidas Samba OG and comes in a neutral colorway of Cloud White, Core Black, and Gum.

The sneaker boasts a full-grain leather upper in Cloud White with grey suede overlays. Like other Samba OG models, the Cloud White Core Black (GS) iteration features a prominent T-shaped overlay across the toe and the 3-stripes on the side panel. Metallic gold letters spell out "SAMBA" along the 3-stripes and add a pop of shimmer to the lateral side panel. In contrast, the simple adidas Trefoil can be found on the tongue tag.

Our experts like the gum rubber outsole, which comes in a dark hue instead of the yellow tone more commonly associated with gum materials. The adidas Samba OG Cloud White Core Black (GS)was released on August 10th, 2023, and retailed at $80.

name: Halloween Skull
title: Nike Dunk Low Retro QS Halloween Skull
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Retro QS Halloween Skull is here to celebrate Halloween in style, offering a spooky twist on the classic Dunk silhouette. This limited-edition sneaker features a cracked leather upper, with vibrant green hues emerging from beneath the black exterior, creating a dramatic contrast. An embossed black skull decorates the toe box, adding to the eerie theme, while the custom insole showcases a series of skull graphics for a chilling effect.

Designed with the same iconic Dunk Low shape, the Halloween Skull edition stands out for its bold design and attention to detail. The textured cracked leather gives the shoe a unique look, and the bright cactus and green curry accents make it a real eye-catcher. Whether you’re hitting the streets or attending a Halloween event, this sneaker is sure to turn heads with its striking visuals and Halloween-themed aesthetics.

Released on October 24, 2024, the Nike Dunk Low Retro QS Halloween Skull retailed for $140. With its vibrant colorway and limited-edition design, this sneaker is a must-have for sneakerheads looking to celebrate Halloween in style.

name: Riot Skateshop
title: Nike SB Dunk Low Riot Skateshop
description:
The Nike SB Dunk Low Riot Skateshop is a striking collaboration that pays homage to the vibrant skateboarding culture. This men's sneaker features a rich mahogany base, complemented by dark beetroot, team red, sail, and night maroon accents, creating a visually captivating design. The premium materials and expert craftsmanship ensure both style and durability, making it an ideal choice for skaters and sneaker enthusiasts alike.

Designed with skateboarding in mind, these shoes offer superior comfort and performance. The low-top silhouette provides flexibility and freedom of movement, while the padded collar and tongue offer enhanced support. The shoe comes with both red and black laces, allowing for customization to suit individual preferences. With its unique colorway and attention to detail, the Nike SB Dunk Low Riot Skateshop is set to become a coveted addition to any sneaker collection.

Us at StockX believe this product is great for both skateboarding enthusiasts and fashion-forward individuals looking for a versatile, eye-catching sneaker that stands out from the crowd.

name: Sea Salt
title: New Balance 9060 Sea Salt
description:
The New Balance 9060 Sea Salt, which has remained the silhouette with the highest number of sales to date since its release, took inspiration from the 990 series.

The shoe arrives in the sea salt colorway and has suede leather, mesh, and rubber as the materials making up its main components. Mesh and premium pig suede leather makes the upper of New Balance 9060 Sea Salt. The midsole and outsole are all made of rubber of different colorways. The midsole is white, while its outsole is of the "seat water" colorway.

The New Balance 9060 Sea Salt first debuted in the early 2000s at a release price of $170.

name: Halloween Zombie
title: Nike Ja 1 Halloween Zombie
description:
Step into the eerie season with the Nike Ja 1 "Halloween" a sneaker that beautifully marries innovative design with a spooky aesthetic. This edition, wrapped in a Lime Blast/Oil Green-Black-Hemp-Cacao Wow colorway, brings a fresh and spooky vibe to the courts. The upper, crafted with synthetic materials and mesh ensures a comfortable and breathable fit. The design is a salute to the Halloween spirit, echoing haunting stories with every stride you take.

The innovative tech in the sneaker doesn't take a backseat to aesthetics. The colorway is more than just a visual treat; it's a representation of Nike's commitment to evolving sneaker culture. The zombie scratches across the iconic Swooshes, the eerie hands rising from graves, and the blood-red embroidered number "12" are a tale of spooky elegance blended with sporty functionality. This is where the tradition of Halloween meets the futuristic design of Nike, creating a sneaker that's as visually appealing as it is performance-ready.

With the Nike Ja 1 "Halloween" you're stepping into a narrative crafted meticulously by Nike and Ja Morant. The eerie yet exciting colorway, coupled with the innovative design, makes it a coveted possession for any sneakerhead. Dropping on October 28, 2023, at a retail price of $120, the Nike Ja 1 "Halloween" is a sweet deal for those ready to make a statement on and off the court.

name: Blue Fusion Gum (Women's)
title: adidas Gazelle Indoor Blue Fusion Gum (Women's)
description:
The adidas Gazelle Indoor Blue Fusion Gum W upper is adorned with premium suede while showcasing the titular Blue Fusion. This women’s-sizing silhouette arrives in a Blue Fusion/Footwear White/Gold Metallic colorway.

The adidas Gazelle Indoor Blue Fusion Gum W features a textured tongue with white branding. The signature minimizes its branding features. Other significant features of this low-top sneaker include white lace, Cloud White sock liners, and unbranded heel tabs. Meanwhile, the lateral and medial panels reveal sawtooth-edged Cloud White 3-Stripes. The lateral sides of the shoe, above the 3-Stripes, display the "Gazelle" branding. The gum sole unit is designed in caramel color to round out the sneaker's design.

What we think stands out in the adidas Gazelle Indoor Blue Fusion Gum W is its archival design that brings out a brilliant and vibrant colorway. The adidas Gazelle Indoor Blue Fusion Gum W was released at a retail price of $90 on December 15th, 2022.

name: Jackie Robinson
title: Nike Air Max 1 '86 OG Jackie Robinson
description:
Step into a legacy of greatness with the Nike Air Max 1 '86 OG Jackie Robinson, an exquisite sneaker that celebrates the trailblazing spirit of the iconic baseball legend. Drenched in the dignified midnight navy, obsidian-sail, metallic gold, and gum medium brown colorway, this design pays homage to Robinson's monumental journey with the Brooklyn Dodgers. Designed for those who not only chase dreams but also honor the pathbreakers who paved the way, this sneaker transcends sport to become a symbol of history and perseverance.​
​​
​Echoing Robinson's monumental impact on the MLB, the sneaker features a 42 patch on the tongue and an emblem on the shoelaces, representing his iconic jersey number and indelible mark on the game. The luxurious touches of metallic gold reflect the excellence and honor of Robinson's legacy, while the gum medium brown sole grounds the design in timeless style. This sneaker not only speaks to Jackie Robinson's impact in sports but also his role as a catalyst for change and inspiration in society.​
​​
​The Nike Air Max 1 '86 OG Jackie Robinson dropped on April 15, 2024, for $150. With its profound backstory and thoughtful design, it promises to be more than just a collector's item but a wearable testament to courage and change. Whether you're a sneakerhead, a history buff, or a sports enthusiast, these shoes invite you to walk in the footsteps of greatness, embodying the enduring legacy of Jackie Robinson with every step.

name: Light Orewood Brown (Women's)
title: Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Light Orewood Brown (Women's)
description:
The Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Light Orewood Brown (Women's) features a layered design that combines subtle shades and different textures. This running and lifestyle sneaker is specifically sized for women.

The Light Orewood Brown colorway of the Women's Nike Zoom Vomero 5 has an upper base of loosely woven Creamy White mesh with a tonal underlay. Synthetic leather overlays bolster the toecap, collar, and heel, while suede overlays in Creamy White accent the lateral forefoot and eye stays. A plastic midfoot cage provides support and singular styling and the plastic cage at the heel offers increased ventilation. The Sail-colored foam midsole houses Zoom Air for an off-the-ground sensation of lightness under foot. A brown rubber outsole with waffle lugs for traction completes this shoe.

The detail of this women's sneaker that we find most delightful is the 3M reflective striping on the tongue, toecap, and collar that make this shoe pop in the dark. The Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Light Orewood Brown (Women's) was released on February 7, 2024, for retail price of $160.

name: Black (Women's)
title: UGG Tazz Slipper Black (Women's)
description:
The UGG Tazz Slipper Black W takes on the slip-in silhouette, and retains most of the classics of the shoe brand, including the suede upper, wool lining, and the Treadlite rubber outsole.

The Tazz Slipper Black for women has a black suede upper, with a patterned multicolor collar providing the only contrast. On the inside, it features plush UGG sheepskin wool throughout the lining. The foam footbed is present in the rest of the underfoot. UGG maintains its signature Treadlite rubber outsole for traction under a 1.5-inch platform sole.

The UGG Tazz Slipper Black W was originally released on the 1st of November 2021 for an initial retail price of $120.

name: Triple Pink (PS)
title: Nike Dunk Low Triple Pink (PS)
description:
Since its first release, the Nike Dunk Low Triple Pink (Preschool)remains one of the high-selling variants of the Nike Dunk Low series.
​
The upper of Nike Dunk Low Triple Pink (Preschool) is constructed with light pink-layered leather featuring darker pink overlays of synthetic leather made from recycled polyester material. The toe box is made of pink perforated leather. Its pull tab, which is embroidered with the symbol of "NIKE," is also constructed using pink synthetic leather. The midsole and outsole of the Nike Dunk Low Triple Pink (Preschool) are made of pink and white rubber.
​
Nike Dunk Low Triple Pink (Preschool) was first released on September 13, 2022, at a price of $85.

name: Reverse
title: 361 Degrees BIG3 4.0 Quick Reverse
description:
The 361 Degrees BIG3 4.0 Quick Reverse is a performance basketball shoe created by the Chinese sportswear brand 361 Degrees. It features a mismatched colorway, with blue dominating the left shoe and pink covering the right shoe.

The 4.0 version features several upgrades, including a full-length ENRG-X+ midsole for a springy feel underfoot. TPU panels reinforce the lightweight mesh upper at the heel and toe box and reduce rollover motions. Another important technical feature is the nylon anti-torsion piece beneath the midfoot, which provides rigid support. The Reverse 361 Degrees BIG3 4.0 Quick displays several design details that reinforce its reputation for speed, including a lightning bolt motif down the side panels in an off-white hue.

Our experts at StockX like the grippy rubber outsole because it provides superior traction on indoor and outdoor basketball courts. The 361 Degrees BIG3 4.0 Quick Reverse was released on July 15, 2023, and sold for $130.

name: Chicago (2022)
title: Jordan 2 Retro OG Chicago (2022)
description:
2022 was unofficially dubbed the Year of the Jordan 2, as Jordan Brand brought back the classic Air Jordan 2 Chicago in its true OG form. The Air Jordan 2 Chicago reps the same historic colorway worn by Michael Jordan during his 1986-1987 season with the Bulls. The sneaker features white reptile-embossed leather uppers, Varsity Red reptile spine design on the heel, and Varsity Red signature Wings logo on the tongue. A black midsole and "NIKE" debossed branding on the heel tab ties up this signature silhouette.

The Air Jordan 2 Chicago retro released in December of 2022 for $200.

name: Albino & Preto
title: Nike SB Dunk Low Albino & Preto
description:
Step into a blend of cultures with the Nike SB Dunk Low Albino & Preto. The Fossil/Black/Sail colorway is a style statement as well as a reflection of a unique collaboration between the skate and Jiu-Jitsu cultures.

The upper is adorned with heavy gauge canvas, replicating the texture and the grace of Jiu-Jitsu kimonos, while the sail-colored body wrapped in fossil & black accents add a stylish contrast. The black swoosh is a standout feature, epitomizing the duality of Albino & Preto's name and the collaborative essence of this pair. With every step, feel the essence of Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu meeting the skate world. The textile upper features a pearl weave construction traditionally used on jiu-jitsu uniforms, offering not just a visual appeal but a story woven into the fabric of the sneaker. This pair of Dunks are a narrative of tradition meeting modernity. It's about the sail-colored boxes of Nike SB meeting the modern take on Jiu-Jitsu kimonos by Albino & Preto.

Released on September 23, 2023, for a retail price of $130, this pair is not just a purchase but an investment in a legacy of cool. Grab your pair and step into the story.

name: Think Pink
title: Nike GT Cut Cross Think Pink
description:
The Nike GT Cut Cross Think Pink is a performance basketball shoe designed for play on indoor and outdoor courts. It features a pastel color gradient, ranging from pink to light purple.

This low-top sneaker is part of the Greater Than Series' low-budget expansion. Despite its initial lower price point, the Think Pink Nike GT Cut Cross is still engineered to improve on-court performance—specifically speed and agility. The Zoom Air unit in the forefoot absorbs impact and increases energy return, while the herringbone traction pattern provides a grippy feel. In addition, the sneaker boasts two types of foam in the midsole for maximum comfort. The design showcases light purple that fades to pink from the toe, along the midsole, to the heel.

Our experts at StockX like the stylized Swoosh logo cutting across the side panel because it reveals the mesh construction. The Nike GT Cut Cross Think Pink was released on August 23, 2024, and sold for $110.

name: Union White Canvas
title: Jordan 1 Retro AJKO Low SP Union White Canvas
description:
Union LA and Jordan are starting off 2023 with the release of the Air Jordan Retro AJKO Low SP Union. This marks the seventh silhouette Union and Jordan Brand have partnered on.

The collaboration between Union and Jordan brand comes with a white and neutral grey canvas upper, sail midsoles, and yellow stitching accents. The Jordan x Union AJKO Low SP features removable blue and grey swoosh patches with Union LA branding placed below.

The Air Jordan 1 Retro AJKO Low SP Union released January 27, 2023, with a retail price of $150.

name: Sea Salt Brown
title: New Balance 9060 Sea Salt Brown
description:
The New Balance 9060 Sea Salt Brown takes aspects from many New Balance running silhouettes, combines them, and infuses them with cutting-edge sneaker technology and an early 2000s running aesthetic.

This creamy-colored shoe features an upper of pale tan mesh that offers breathability and a lightweight stride. Leather and suede overlays in shades of tan and mocha course across the shoe offering a layered look, as well as extra support. The pale side-panel N outlined in a darker mocha complements the translucent CR device that helps lock in heel stability. The ABZORB midsole provides cushioning with every step, as well as springy energy return to propel your stride. Branding hits the heel tab and the tongue tag to complete the look of this immediately recognizable runner.

The aspect of this sneaker that we most enjoy is inspired by the New Balance 860. The diamond-patterned outsole that absorbs shock and provides grip enhances this sneaker's colorway with shades of cream, tan, and mocha. The New Balance 9060 Sea Salt Brown was released on April 1, 2024, for $150 retail.

name: MX Oat
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 MX Oat
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 MX Oat features a yellow, orange, and blue swirl-patterned Primeknit upper with a mesh side stripe and yellow heel tab. From there, a semi-translucent Boost midsole and pale yellow rope laces complete the design.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 MX Oat released in October of 2021 and retailed for $220.

name: Two-Toned Grey (GS)
title: Nike Dunk Low Two-Toned Grey (GS)
description:
Nike Sportswear added to their Dunk Low lineup with this Nike Dunk Low Two Toned Grey with grade school sizing (GS) colorway, arriving in a mix of gray tones. The Nike Dunk Low Two Toned Grey (GS) comes constructed in a full leather build featuring light and dark shades of gray. The clean two-toned Grey colorway sees the slightly darker shade of neutral overlaying the base layer, while the white Swoosh logo, laces, and midsole complete the two-tone look. A gray rubber outsole completes the design.

The Nike Dunk Low Two Toned Grey (GS) was released in March of 2022 at a retail price of $85.

name: Comme des Garcons PLAY White
title: Converse Chuck Taylor All Star 70 Hi Comme des Garcons PLAY White
description:
With a look inspired by the Converse Chuck Taylors of the ‘70s, the Converse Chuck Taylor All Star 70s Hi Comme des Garcons PLAY White has a high-top that blends the collab branding and collaboration. Converse Chuck Taylor All Star 70s Hi Comme des Garcons PLAY White has a white canvas upper with double stitching and shiny metal eyelets. It also features heart icons on the sidewall. The lower part of the shoe mostly features a vulcanized rubber midsole and outsole.

Converse Chuck Taylor All-Star 70s Hi Commes des Garcons PLAY White was released in January 2019 and retailed at a price of $125.
model: Converse Chuck Taylor All Star 70 Hi

name: Copper (2024)
title: Nike Air Foamposite One Copper (2024)
description:
The Nike Air Foamposite One Copper (2024) redefines boldness with its head-turning metallic copper upper contrasted by black accents. Originally launched in the late 90s, the Foamposite One was ahead of its time in both design and technology. This 2024 re-release is a nostalgic nod to the silhouette's history for today’s sneaker lovers.

The innovative molded Foamposite upper ensures durability and a futuristic aesthetic, while a carbon fiber midfoot shank offers unparalleled stability. Its sleek, glossy finish and performance-driven design make it an easy favorite for both collectors and athletes. Off-court, the sneaker's bold colorway guarantees it as a standout piece in any wardrobe.

Retailing at $230 and released on December 4, 2024, the Nike Air Foamposite One Copper (2024) is an essential addition to any sneaker collection. Its metallic copper, black, and off noir tones symbolize a seamless blend of heritage and regal aesthetics.

name: Dark Smoke Grey
title: Nike SB Dunk Low Dark Smoke Grey
description:
The Nike SB Dunk Low Dark Smoke Grey is a low-cut sneaker whose design follows the classic color blocking of previous Dunk Lows, with this iteration presenting in a dark smoke grey and black color palette.

The SB Dunk by Nike is a low top sneaker that has a solid following thanks to its relaxed, casual aesthetic and comfortable fit. Fresh colorways are always appearing, and this iteration boasts a tonal dark smoke grey and black combination. The entire upper is all suede. The dark smoke grey envelopes the toe cap, forefoot, eyelet, and heel overlay. While black fills in the remaining areas. The white midsole adds balance, while the gum outsole is a classic choice that provides well-needed traction.

According to our experts, the black leather Swoosh is a premium design element and gives this shoe a touch of elegance. The Nike SB Dunk Low Dark Smoke Grey was released on December 3, 2024, with a $115 recommended retail price.

name: Light Orewood Brown Sashiko
title: Nike Dunk Low Light Orewood Brown Sashiko
description:
Nike is reintroducing Japanese Sashiko stitching into the popular Nike Dunk Low model, after it was last seen used on the Air Force One silhouette in 2022.

The Nike Dunk Low Orewood Brown Sashiko is constructed with a Pale Ivory denim upper that features Orewood Brown contrast stitching throughout. Nike used red Sashiko style stitching across the toe box, heel tab and eyelets. Red Nike branding is placed subtly on the tongue and insoles.

The Nike Dunk Low Light Orewood Brown Sashiko released March 9, 2023, with a retail price of $120.

name: Desert Sand
title: adidas Yeezy Foam RNR Desert Sand
description:
The adidas Yeezy Foam RNR Desert Sand arrives with a Desert Sand, oval-cut foam construction made of part EVA and algae. From there, a cushioned footbed offers comfort and support, while a sculptural sole with deep treads provides traction.

The adidas Yeezy Foam RNR Desert Sand released in June of 2022 and retailed for $80.

name: White Particle Grey
title: Nike ZoomX Vaporfly 3 White Particle Grey
description:
The Nike ZoomX Vaporfly 3 White Particle Grey was released two years after Nike unveiled the second version of the Vaporfly shoe. This running sneaker boasts a slew of new features not found in the previous Vaporfly models.

For starters, the Nike ZoomX Vaporfly 3 has a full-length carbon fiber flyplate to provide it with stability. It also has Nike's patented ZoomX foam to make it extra responsive. It includes a breathable upper constructed out of Flyknit yarn and is available in a variety of colors.

The thing that our experts love most about the Nike ZoomX Vaporfly 3 White Particle Grey is the bulge near the heel. In addition to giving the Vaporfly 3 a more unique appearance than previous Vaporfly sneakers, the bulge near the heel prevents people from putting too much weight on the insides of their feet. The Vaporfly 3 was released on 1st April 2023 for $250.

name: Bordeaux
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Bordeaux
description: The Air Jordan 1 High Bordeaux released in November of 2021 and retailed for $170.

name: Black Cement
title: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG Black Cement
description:
Redefining the low-cut silhouette game, the Jordan 1 Retro Low OG Black Cement made a splash in the sneaker world on June 24, 2023. This classic model from Jordan Brand got a striking makeover with the brand’s renowned elephant print, showcasing an undeniable combo of quality and style.

Sporting an impressive black upper, with iconic elephant print overlays on the heel and toe box these kicks are crafted from a mix of high-grade leather and suede, boasting durability and sophistication. Complementing the uppers is a clean white midsole, offering a stark contrast and enhancing the sneaker's visual appeal. A Nike Air logo resides on the tongue, adding a dash of bold color to the muted palette. The Jordan 1 Retro Low OG Black Cement promises a fitting tribute to the legacy of Jordan Brand.

These Jordan 1 Retro Low OG Black Cements hit the streets on June 24, 2023, with a retail price tag of $140.

name: Craft Ivory
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Craft Ivory
description:
The Jordan 1 Retro High OG Craft Ivory updates the classic Air Jordan 1 Retro silhouette with subtle color-blocking and canvas material. This sneaker is also part of Jordan Brand’s Craft series.

The base construction features premium suede in Sea Glass, which gives the sneaker a luxury appearance. Something that makes this shoe stand out is the overlays and heel panel. The forefoot overlays are made of suede in Sea Glass, while the heel panel comes in Ivory canvas. This creamy tone and durable textile can also be found around the heel and on the Swoosh logos. The Jordan Wings logo is displayed near the ankle, on a canvas patch, in Sea Glass-colored embroidery.

Our StockX experts like the nude-pink finish of the mesh tongue. It adds a third color-blocking tone, but doesn’t distract from the design or dominant colors. The Jordan 1 Retro High OG Craft Ivory was released on March 30th, 2024, and retailed at $180.

name: Circle Of Life
title: Nike Kyrie 8 Circle Of Life
description:
The Nike Kyrie 8 Circle of Life flaunts a galactic multicolor mesh upper fused with a performance-oriented midsole and outsole. Cosigned by Kyrie Irving, these sneakers pay homage to the basketball legend with a matching performance.

The Circle of Life induces the best with its light bone, yellow strike, malachite, orange trance, vivid purple, and hyper pink colorway. The colors blend on the breathable mesh with the vivid purple cropped Swoosh. The eyestays and laces take on a white hue to balance things up, while the liner draped in malachite reverts to the multicolor motif. A white midsole bearing Kyrie Irving's signature on the heel sits between the upper and a vivid purple outsole, which ends in an orange trance around the toecaps. Contoured serrations on the rubber outsole complete the Circle of Life design.

What is the standout feature of the Kyrie Circle of Life sneakers? As our experts expound, it is the enhanced responsiveness of the midsole fused to the court-ready outsole. The combination allows you to accelerate and decelerate on demand. The Nike Kyrie 8 Circle of Life was released on November 14, 2022, retailing for $140.

name: Black White Swoosh
title: Nike Air Max 1 Black White Swoosh
description:
The Nike Air Max 1 Black White Swoosh presents a classic silhouette originally launched in 1987 and dresses it in a stealthy colorway that pops with hits of bright white.

The Black iteration of the Nike Air Max 1 with a White Swoosh features an upper that starts with a base made from black mesh. Black synthetic overlays adorn the mud guard, toe cap, and eyestays, while tumbled black synthetic leather forms the heel counter. A white synthetic leather Nike Swoosh courses across the side panel and matches the embroidered Nike Air branding on the heel. White Nike Air branding also adorns the tongue tag and black insole, providing a few more hits of contrast.

What we enjoy most about this classic sneaker is the sole. The black foam midsole houses a visible Max Air unit that offers cushioning and spring. The outsole, made of black rubber, is patterned with heritage waffle lugs in order to absorb impact and provide traction. The Nike Air Max 1 Black White Swoosh was released on January 4, 2024, for a retail price of $140.

name: Yellow Ochre
title: Jordan 1 Low Yellow Ochre
description:
The Jordan 1 Low Yellow Ochre is a low-top basketball sneaker whose design was inspired by the classic version that came out in 1985.

This iteration of the Jordan 1 Low comes with an upper made completely of smooth leather. The midsole is black, while the heel and toebox appear in Yellow Ochre. The toebox is also perforated to allow for better air flow. The Nike Swoosh also appears in Yellow Ochre on the midsoles, and the Air Jordan logo is stamped onto the yellow heel in black. The black cushioned tongue also contains a Simple Yellow Jumpman logo. A white and yellow outsole patterned for traction completes the look.

What we like most about this sneaker is its bold color scheme, reminiscent of the colors of Pittsburgh. The Jordan 1 Low Yellow Ochre was first introduced on December 18, 2023, for a retail price of $115.

name: UNC White
title: Jordan 6 Retro UNC White
description:
Jordan Brand drew inspiration from Michael Jordan's alma mater, the University of North Carolina, for the Air Jordan 6 Retro UNC White.

Constructed with University Blue Durabuck and white leather, the Air Jordan 6 Retro UNC White utilizes color blocking reminiscent of the renowned Jordan 6 Carmine. Hits of navy blue on the tongue and midsole integrate UNC's lesser known school color. At the heel, a Jordan Team patch nod to the jock tags that are stitched to the bottom of UNC's uniforms. From there, an icy semi-translucent Air sole completes the design.

The Air Jordan 6 Retro UNC White released in March of 2022 and retailed for $210.

name: Triple Black
title: Jordan 1 Mid Triple Black
description:
Inspired by the original Air Jordan 1 from 1985, the Jordan 1 Mid Triple Black is a mid-cut Air Jordan 1 sneaker in a "Triple Black" colorway.

This sneaker features traditional detailing on the monochromatic upper section, including a matching retro "Wings" emblem etched on the collar flap, Swooshes on the lateral and medial, perforated detailing on the toebox, nylon tongue, laces, and a tonal Jumpman logo on a matching tongue tag. Rounding out the design of this shoe is the traditional Air Jordan 1 sole unit in a Triple Black tone matching the upper. 

What our experts love about this sneaker is its design and colorway. The design, inspired by the OG 1985 release, and the Triple Black colorway throughout the genuine leather upper and sole unit make this offering sleek and versatile. The Jordan 1 Mid Triple Black was originally made available on September 27th, 2022, retailing at $115.

name: White Oreo (2021)
title: Jordan 4 Retro White Oreo (2021)
description:
The Air Jordan 4 Retro White Oreo features a white leather and mesh upper with hits of Tech Grey on its eyelets and midsole. From there, a red Jumpman logo is embroidered on the tongue, adding a pop of color to the neutral-toned design.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro White Oreo released on Saturday, July 3rd and retailed for $190.

name: Cardinal Red
title: Jordan 3 Retro Cardinal Red
description:
Jordan Brand brought an OG Air Jordan 7 colorway to the Air Jordan 3 for the Air Jordan 3 Cardinal Red.

Constructed with white tumbled leather and signature Elephant Print overlays, the Air Jordan 3 Cardinal Red takes a traditional approach in its color blocking and fabrication, similar to the iconic Black Cement 3s. Spicing up the design, sharp Cardinal Red midsoles and detailing pop against the neutral toned upper. Bright orange Jumpman logo embroidery on the tongue adds the finishing touch.

The Air Jordan 3 Cardinal Red released in February of 2022 and retailed for $200.

name: Burgundy (2023)
title: Jordan 5 Retro Burgundy (2023)
description:
The Jordan 5 Retro Burgundy (2023) arrives featuring an identical color palette of Deep Burgundy, Light Graphite, and Metallic Silver that adorned the original release back in 2006.

The (2023) Burgundy Jordan 5 Retro incorporates a burgundy suede upper, complemented by contrasting stitching and transparent netting on the quarter panel for enhanced breathability. The heel overlay and tongue are adorned with embroidered Jumpman branding, featuring a reflective silver finish to enhance visibility in low-light situations. A polyurethane midsole in a matching color showcases speckled shark-tooth accents, and houses a visible Air-Sole unit in the heel for cushioning. The outsole, featuring a translucent herringbone traction pattern, ensures dependable grip on various surfaces.

What our experts love about the Jordan 5 Retro Burgundy (2023) is the rich burgundy suede upper, which gives the shoe a luxurious and premium look. This suede material, along with the contrasting details and reflective accents, sets this sneaker apart and adds to its overall appeal. The sneaker debuted on August 29th, 2023, for $225.

name: Leather Triple Black
title: Nike Air Max 90 Leather Triple Black
description:
The Nike Air Max 90 Leather Triple Black 2020 was released as an addition to the Nike Air Max 90 collection. 

The Leather Triple Nike Air Max 90 Black 2020 has a midsole that is equipped with Nike's patented Air Max technology, providing maximum comfort and cushioning with each step. The air unit is visible through the outsole of the shoe. The outsole of the sneaker features a waffle pattern that provides excellent traction and grip on various surfaces. 

We think that one outstanding feature of the Nike Air Max 90 Leather Triple Black 2020 is its colorway. The upper of the Nike Air Max 90 Leather Triple Black 2020 sneaker is made with multiple leather panels, which are all black. The panels are textured, giving the shoe a unique design that stands out from other sneakers. The Nike Air Max 90 Leather Triple Black 2020 was released on July 28th, 2020 at a retail price of $130.

name: Semi Lucid Blue Cloud White
title: adidas Campus 00s Semi Lucid Blue Cloud White
description:
Inspired by the nostalgia of the 2000s, the adidas Campus 00s Semi Lucid Blue Cloud White shoes made their iconic debut. The release saw the classic silhouette rejuvenated with a fresh take on a favored colorway

Adidas sticks to its roots with premium suede on the uppers, detailed with classic Adidas stripes in Cloud White. The off white midsole and Lucid Blue outsole complete this visually appealing colorway. It's a nod to the past, designed for the present. Bringing back the vintage vibes with a modern twist, these shoes capture the true essence of 00's style and Adidas' timeless design language. Whether you're out and about or chilling with your friends, these kicks will ensure your style game is always on point.

adidas Campus 00s Semi Lucid Blue Cloud White dropped with a retail price of $110.

name: Tai Chi Yellow
title: ASICS GEL-Kayano 14 Tai Chi Yellow
description:
The ASICS GEL-Kayano 14 Tai Chi Yellow incorporates innovative Gel technology and eye-catching Tai Chi Yellow accents to create a technical running shoe with strong early 2000s roots.

Designed by Kiko Kostadinov, this sneaker takes elements from original Gel-Kayano models created by Toshikazu Kayano. A web of overlays crisscrosses over the side panels, giving the sneaker the early 2000s version of a futuristic look. While the shoe keeps its original tooling, it features updated components and materials. The airy mesh upper in white allows the foot to breathe, while synthetic leather replaces genuine leather on the metallic-silver overlays. Pops of bright Tai Chi Yellow can be found on parts of the midsole, and ASICS branding on the heel, tongue, and lateral side panel.

Our experts at StockX like the supportive padding in the tongue and around the collar, which contributes to the sneaker’s technical silhouette. The ASICS GEL-Kayano 14 Tai Chi Yellow was released on May 1, 2024, and sold for $150.

name: Red Swoosh Panda
title: Nike Dunk Low Retro Red Swoosh Panda
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Retro Red Swoosh Panda is dressed in a mix of three major colors: white, university red, and black.
​
​The white accents on the tongue tags and leather overlays contrast with the black leather foundation of this Retro Nike Dunk model. Red heels, Swooshes, as well as a rubber outsole with cushioning technology, are visible in the shoe's design. The white lace closure system, lining, black outsole, and white midsole complete the look.
​
​The Nike Dunk Low Retro Red Swoosh Panda made its debut on October 1st, 2022, for a recommended retail price of $110.

name: Sand (Kids)
title: UGG Tazz Slipper Sand (Kids)
description:
The UGG Tazz Slipper Sand (Kids) is a kids’-sized slip-on shoe with a chunkier sole for extra cushioning and height.

This iteration of the UGG Tazz Slipper is constructed with a fully suede upper in a Sand tan color. There is a single seam in the middle of the upper to hold the two sides together, while the UGG brand name appears embossed into the lateral side of the shoe. Decorative stitching in white and very light blue lines the opening and the heel features a pull tab. The lining is made of UGGplush wool for comfort and warmth. The slipper sits on top of a chunky Sand rubber sole.

What we like most about this shoe are the subtle colors of the decorative stitching, which add a touch of visual interest to the otherwise simple shoe. The UGG Tazz Slipper Sand (Kids) was released on January 1, 2024, for a price of $90.

name: Military Blue (2024) (PS)
title: Jordan 4 Retro Military Blue (2024) (PS)
description:
The Jordan 4 Retro Military Blue (2024) (PS) adds "Military Blue," an OG Jordan 4 Retro colorway, to this kids' size sneaker.

The upper is constructed from Off-White leather with tonal, reinforced stitching, and quarter panel cutouts revealing mesh layered over Military Blue material. This bright-blue color can also be found on the TPU support wings, the heel tab, the molded eyelets, and the midsole. A leather mudguard in Neutral Gray protects the toe area and complements the color of the rubber outsole. The sneaker displays minimal branding, but includes NIKE in white lettering on the heel and the Jumpman logo on the tongue.

Our StockX experts like the inclusion of Off-White laces because the tone is softer than Core White and doesn't distract from the design. The preschool-sized Jordan 4 Retro Military Blue (2024) (PS) was released on May 4, 2024, and retailed at $100.

name: Cream Black
title: New Balance 550 Cream Black
description:
The New Balance 550 Cream Black features a smooth white leather upper with perforated overlays, black piping, mesh collars, and cracked leather New Balance logos. At the tongue, a New Balance Basketball woven label adds a vintage feel. From there, a matching sole with court grip completes the design.

The New Balance 550 Cream Black released in March of 2022 and retailed for $100.

name: Philly
title: Nike Dunk Low Retro Premium Philly
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Retro Premium Philly celebrates "the City of Brotherly Love" through details and colors that represent this storied city.

Boasting a low-top silhouette with padding around the collar and in the tongue, this Nike Dunk Low Retro Premium features an upper crafted from tumbled leather in white with a combination of leather and suede overlays. The heel overlay comes in grey shaggy suede, while the leather forefoot overlay displays a grey, mottled pattern. In addition, the Swoosh logo is made from grey cracked leather with a multicolor mark on the medial side panel. The various greyscale tones remind the wearer of the color of concrete and other materials that make up Philadelphia’s urban landscape. Instead of "NIKE," the heel tab displays "PHILLY" in multicolor lettering, which matches the collar lining and the tongue’s logo tag.

Our StockX experts like that the Kelly Green laces reveal Philadelphia’s geographical coordinates. The Nike Dunk Low Retro Premium Philly was released on May 30, 2024, and retailed at $135.

name: Hike
title: Nike Book 1 Premium Hike
description:
