Hit the court or the town in style with the Nike Book 1 Premium Hike, a sneaker that echoes Devin Booker's passion for exploring the great outdoors. Featuring a color palette of dark stucco, light silver, and clay orange, this shoe captures the essence of a rugged adventure, merged with the sophistication of premium materials. It's a shoe crafted for individuals who seek the thrill of the hike and the rush of the game – a perfect blend for the active and the stylish.

Booker's signature sneaker comes loaded with features designed for the trail-blazing spirit. The Hike edition is more than just its earthy, rich tones; the sneaker's advanced traction pattern, responsive Cushlon cushioning, Nike Zoom air bag in the heel and lockdown fit reflect Booker’s dynamic gameplay, offering you the support and performance needed to dominate the game. Whether you're making quick cuts or going for the jump shot, the Nike Book 1 Premium Hike is built for those who play with passion and style.

Dropped on April 6, 2024, for $150, the Nike Book 1 Premium Hike is your invitation to step into a world of adventure. These sneakers are a salute to Devin Booker's multifaceted life, balancing the demands of an athlete with the call of the wild. Don your pair and be ready to tackle any challenge with confidence and flair, just as Booker takes to the court or the trails.

name: Coconut Milk
title: Jordan Spizike Low Coconut Milk
description:
The Jordan Spizike Low Coconut Milk, inspired by cultural icon and film director Spike Lee, combines a number of elements from different Air Jordans in one eye-catching sneaker.

The Coconut Milk colorway of the Jordan Spizike Low-Top starts with a base of soft leather in a Pale Creamy shade. This same leather forms a mudguard that is overlaid with iconic elephant print at the toe and heel. Jordan 4 TPU wings in a creamy beige support the collar and integrate into the eyestays, while off-white netting from the Jordan 5 appears in the side-panel window. The Jordan 3 sole unit features a midsole of Sail-colored foam that encases a cassette of visible Air under the heel and rests atop a matching rubber outsole with traction grooves and Jordan branding.

The most notable and enjoyable features of this hybrid sneaker are the hits of red that make the upper pop with contrast. These include Spike Lee branding at the heel, an embroidered Jumpman on the tongue, and a lace lock with a white Jumpman. The Jordan Spizike Low Coconut Milk debuted on March 20, 2024, for $160 retail.

name: Deep Royal Blue
title: Nike SB Dunk Low Deep Royal Blue
description:
The Nike SB Dunk Low Deep Royal Blue is a skateboarding sneaker dressed in rich suede that offers a distinctive look of elegance to this highly functional sports shoe.

The Deep Royal Blue iteration of the Nike SB Dunk Low-Top features an upper with a base of forest green suede with deep royal blue suede overlays that match the laces. The padded mesh tongue is also deep green, with a royal blue lining that matches the sock liner with padding at the collar. The Nike swoosh is a creamy white suede that matches the embroidered branding on the heel tab and the woven branding on the tongue tag. The deep green insole also features Nike branding.

The aspect of this shoe we enjoy the most is the sole unit, for its functionality and style. Sail-colored foam with deep green stitching composes a midsole with an encapsulated Zoom Air unit. The deep green rubber outsole with a royal blue pod at the midfoot has circles and grooves for grip. The Nike SB Dunk Low Deep Royal Blue was released on January 12, 2024, for a retail price of $115.

name: Fragment x Travis Scott
title: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG SP Fragment x Travis Scott
description:
The Air Jordan 1 Low Fragment Design x Travis Scott nods to the original 2016 Air Jordan 1 Fragment with its simple color blocking. It features a smooth white leather upper with black and royal blue leather overlays. From there, a signature reversed Swoosh and yellowed soles add a Cactus Jack flair to the classic silhouette.

The Air Jordan 1 Low Fragment Design x Travis Scott released in August of 2021 and retailed for $150.

name: Grey
title: New Balance 990v5 Grey
description:
The New Balance 990v5 Grey is the fifth iteration of New Balance's iconic 990 series that originated in 1982. The 990v5 Grey arrives in NB's signature grey color scheme. Its upper is constructed of a grey mesh with matching suede overlays and translucent TPU side panels. Reflective detailing on the New Balance logo and piping shine when exposed to light. At the base, an ENCAP midsole offers utmost cushioning and support. This model is made in the United States of America.

The New Balance 990v5 released in February of 2019 and retailed for $175.

name: Triple Black (2021)
title: Nike Air Huarache Triple Black (2021)
description:
The Nike Air Huarache Triple Black 2021 falls under the gap of Nike sneakers. This sneaker features a midsole forefoot flex ridges that are deeply and highly sculpted.

The Nike Air Huarache Triple Black 2021 is entirely made up of synthetic leather and a nylon combo that is paired to the neoprene bootie. The sneaker also features a flexible molded heel structure. This sneaker’s entire upper part is made up of an encapsulated Air unit. The entire sneaker is black colored.

The Nike Air Huarache Triple Black 2021 was made available at the retail price of $120 on August 5th, 2021.

name: Protection Pack Black Leather
title: New Balance 1906D Protection Pack Black Leather
description:
The New Balance 1906D Protection Pack Black Leather arrives in a retro-inspired look and gets a black colorway, a low-cut, and a mix of leather and airy mesh for its construction.

The Protection Pack Black Leather New Balance 1906D black mesh base layer serves as a backdrop for a combination of leather and suede overlays, introducing a tactile contrast to the overall design. These overlays sport a distressed, well-worn appearance. The N logo, situated at the midfoot, smoothly blends into the NLOCK lacing system, both in a sleek black hue. This design approach continues with the toe and midfoot overlays, which seamlessly match the all-black heel counter. Minimalistic branding elements in white include 1906D on the heel and New Balance on the tongue. To complete the overall aesthetic, the sneaker is finished with a black foam midsole, featuring red NERGY branding and a black outsole.

What our experts love about the New Balance 1906D Protection Pack Black Leather its captivating textural appearance. The combination of various materials, including leather and suede overlays, creates a visually dynamic and tactile experience. The sneaker was released on July 22nd, 2023, for $170.

name: Black Metallic Silver
title: New Balance 1906R Black Metallic Silver
description:
The New Balance 1906R Black Metallic Silver is a running shoe with an upper inspired by the 2000s runner style era.

This version of the New Balance 1906R comes with a black mesh upper, featuring shiny black leather overlays running from the toe, up to the laces, and all the way around the heel. The New Balance N is featured on the midsoles in black, outlined in metallic silver with "NLock" branding in the middle. The N-Lock system stabilizes the sides of the shoe, while a shiny black TPU cage supports the heel. The NB logo can be found in silver on the heel and "1906R" appears in silver on the lateral side under the ankle. The outsole is also predominantly black, with just a few sections appearing in silver.

Our favorite thing about this shoe is the mostly blacked-out design. The all-black colorway with just a few hints of silver gives the shoe an air of mystery and style. The New Balance 1906R Black Metallic Silver was released on April 3, 2023, for a price of $155.

name: Bliss Pink Dark Blue
title: adidas Gazelle Bliss Pink Dark Blue
description:
The adidas Gazelle Bliss Pink Dark Blue is an indoor soccer shoe that stays true to the design of the original Gazelle, which debuted in the 1960s.

This iteration of the adidas Gazelle features a Bliss Pink suede upper. This color makes up almost the full body of the shoe, including the midsole, the laces, and the overlays. The three stripes logo appears in dark blue leather across the midsole on both sides of the shoe, with the word "GAZELLE" appearing in metallic gold next to the first stripe. The heel collar is also dark blue leather. The adidas logo appears in pink on the heel collar and again on the tongue. The gum rubber outsole provides grip and traction.

Our favorite thing about this shoe is the Bliss Pink colorway, as the bold color helps the shoe stand out. The adidas Gazelle Bliss Pink Dark Blue was released on January 10, 2024, for a retail price of $115.

name: Mater
title: Crocs Classic Clog Mater
description:
The Crocs Classic Clog Mater steps into the scene with a playful spirit, mirroring the whimsy of Disney Pixar’s Cars. This funky edition is no ordinary pair; it’s a tribute to Mater, the beloved tow truck from Radiator Springs. From the front, a glossy TPU overlay showcases Mater’s grin, while the back flaunts a tow hook detail on the heel strap, making every step a statement of fun and comfort.

Mater's unique charm doesn't end there; these clogs feature an exposed engine design on the toe, a quirky touch that is bound to turn heads. The Crocs Classic Clog Mater isn’t just about looks; it’s about celebrating youthful exuberance with a comfy, snug fit that’s ready for adventure. The blend of iconic Crocs comfort with Mater's playful persona makes this pair a must-have for those looking to add a touch of whimsy to their footwear collection.

Dropped on October 17, 2023, at a retail price of $60, this pair is a ride into the playful world of Radiator Springs.

name: Alternate Bred (2022)
title: Jordan 1 Mid Alternate Bred (2022)
description: The Air Jordan 1 Mid Alternate Bred 2022 is a highly anticipated release from the iconic sneaker brand. This shoe features a sleek black and red colorway, with premium leather upper for a luxurious feel. The mid-top design offers both style and support, while the Air-Sole unit in the heel provides cushioning for all-day comfort. The release date for this shoe is December 14th, 2022, and with a retail price of $125. Whether you're a die-hard sneakerhead or just looking for a stylish and comfortable shoe, the Air Jordan 1 Mid Alternate Bred 2022 is a must-have addition to your collection.

name: Craft Photon Dust (GS)
title: Jordan 4 Retro SE Craft Photon Dust (GS)
description:
The Air Jordan 4 Retro SE Craft Photon Dust GS is a reimagination of Tinker Hatfield’s original 1989 design. 

The Air Jordan 4 Retro SE Craft Photon Dust for grade schoolers is designed with an all-leather upper in a subtle pale grey finish, with a shaggy suede forefoot overlay in a matching color. It features molded eyelets with pale vanilla accents, and Jumpman branding on the tongue tag and heel tab. The suede quarter panels also have grid-embossed detailing. The shoe's cushioning is provided by an exposed Air-sole unit in the white foam midsole. Additionally, its two-tone herringbone-traction rubber outsole ensures superior grip.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro SE Craft Photon Dust GS was released on 11th February 2023 with its retail price set at $150.

name: Georgetown
title: Jordan 5 Retro Georgetown
description:
The Jordan 5 Retro Georgetown is a stunning iteration that breathes new excitement into the iconic Jordan 5 model, seamlessly blending tradition with a fresh new colorway of Midnight Navy, Black, and Football Grey. The uppers boast a blend of Midnight Navy and Black, showcasing a timeless yet bold look that's both sporty and sophisticated.

The midsole is adorned with speckles on the AJ5's iconic shark teeth, a design element that's been a hallmark of the Jordan 5. The monochromatic Jumpman logo and eyestays adds a sophisticated touch to the already eye-catching design. Additionally, the white midsole accompanied by Midnight Navy accents on the shark teeth pairs beautifully with a semi-translucent icy blue and Midnight Navy rubber outsole, adding that extra flair and functionality to the design​.

Released on November 10, 2023, and retailing at $210, these sneakers are a blend of history, comfort, and contemporary style, encapsulating the essence of the Jordan brand while offering a fresh, modern aesthetic. Get ready to up your sneaker game with this iconic Jordan 5 Retro Georgetown!

name: Iceman
title: Rigorer AR1 Iceman
description:
The Rigorer AR1 Iceman is a stylish and high-performance soccer cleat designed with the demands of competitive players in mind.

This shoe boasts a sleek and modern design with clean lines and bold accents. The upper is constructed from premium mesh, providing durability, flexibility, and breathability even during intense gameplay. It features a padded collar and cushioned insole to provide support and comfort, while a soft lining helps to reduce friction and irritation. A lightweight and responsive soleplate with strategically placed studs delivers top-notch traction and agility, and a low-profile design promotes quick acceleration and agile movements.

What our experts especially appreciate about the Rigorer AR1 Iceman, however, is its white and gray colorway against which thoughtfully placed blue accents pop for a modern and elegant aesthetic. This soccer shoe originally retailed with a price tag of $100 when it was first released on December 25, 2023.

name: Galaxy (2024)
title: Nike KD 4 Galaxy (2024)
description:
The Nike KD 4 Galaxy recaptures the essence of its 2012 counterpart, which was a highlight of the NBA All-Star Weekend. Its Metallic Silver/Total Orange/Dark Grey colorway is a nod to the original's space-themed design, making it a standout piece in any sneaker collection. The KD 4 Galaxy is not just a shoe; it's a piece of basketball history, embodying the spirit of one of the most memorable All-Star events.

The 2024 version of the KD 4 Galaxy preserves the iconic design while integrating modern technology for enhanced performance. It's a perfect amalgamation of nostalgia and innovation, appealing to both long-time fans of the silhouette and new enthusiasts alike. The distinct colorway and star-studded design elements pay tribute to Kevin Durant's stellar performance and the sneaker's astronomical theme.

Set to launch on February 15, 2024, with a retail price of $130, the Nike KD 4 Galaxy is more than just a re-release; it's a celebration of basketball heritage and sneaker culture. Its arrival is eagerly anticipated by fans around the world, ready to experience a piece of sneaker history.

name: Seattle Supersonics
title: Nike SB Dunk Low Pro PRM Seattle Supersonics
description:
The Nike SB Dunk Low Pro PRM Seattle Supersonics is a shoe whose color scheme was inspired by the basketball team's colors.

The Seattle Supersonics Nike SB Dunk Low Pro PRM has a leather, mesh, and suede upper. Bright Fire Red forms the perforated toe box, the sides, the ankle area, and the thick tongue. Fir green overlays round out the toe cap and form the eyestays, ankle strap, and heel tab. The Nike swoosh appears in white across each side and is outlined in University gold, while the tongue has a fir green and gold logo patch. The Nike brand name is also embroidered on the University Gold heel tab. The shoe sits on a white midsole and gum rubber outsole.

What stands out about this shoe are the hits of University Gold, which add even more contrast. The Nike SB Dunk Low Pro PRM Seattle Supersonics was released on December 7, 2024, for $125.
model: Nike SB Dunk Low Pro PRM

name: Fruity Pebbles (2024)
title: Nike LeBron 4 Fruity Pebbles (2024)
description:
Introducing the Nike LeBron 4 Fruity Pebbles 2024, a vibrant and playful addition to the LeBron sneaker lineage. This edition bursts onto the scene with a colorway inspired by the iconic cereal, featuring white, true red, mean green, varsity purple, and splashes of color that mimic the look of Fruity Pebbles. It's a design that pays homage to LeBron James' childhood favorite and brings a fun, nostalgic vibe to the basketball court.

The Nike LeBron 4 Fruity Pebbles 2024 features advanced cushioning and a foamposite shell upper to ensure optimal comfort. Its distinctive design, from the bold color palette to the intricate detailing, showcases Nike's commitment to innovative aesthetics. If you're a sneakerhead or LeBron fan in search of a unique addition to your collection, this sneaker hits all the right notes.

Released on March 7, 2024, and retailing at $250, the Nike LeBron 4 Fruity Pebbles 2024 has made a splash in the sneaker community. Its playful design, coupled with the sneaker's history, has garnered attention from fans and collectors alike. As a celebration of LeBron's legacy and a nod to the simple joys of childhood, the Nike LeBron 4 Fruity Pebbles 2024 stands out as a memorable and desirable release in the world of basketball sneakers.

name: Patta Waves Rush Maroon (with Bracelet)
title: Nike Air Max 1 Patta Waves Rush Maroon (with Bracelet)
description:
The Nike Air Max 1 Patta Waves Noise Rush Maroon features a grey mesh upper with smooth maroon leather overlays and wave-shaped mudguards. A yellowed Air sole with a brown outsole adds the finishing touches.

The Nike Air Max 1 Patta Waves Noise Rush Maroon released in November of 2021 and retailed for $160.

name: White Light Orewood Brown (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Next Nature White Light Orewood Brown (Women's)
description:
Constructed of FlyLeather, a leather-like material made up of at least 50% recycled materials, the women's Nike Dunk Low Next Nature White Light Orewood Brown (W) features simple color blocking similar to the original 1985 Nike Dunk. It features a white base with Orewood Brown overlays and Swooshes. From there, a white and grey Air sole completes the design.

The women's Nike Dunk Low Next Nature White Light Orewood Brown (W) released in March of 2022 and retailed for $105.

name: White
title: Common Projects Original Achilles White
description:
With its subtle details and simple structure, the Common Projects Original Achilles White is designed with casual walking in mind, rather than intense exercise or hitting the basketball court.

This Common Projects Original Achilles White features a crisp white sole, with the rest of the upper being in the same shade. The majority of the shoe is composed of leather, and a serial number is stamped in gold towards the heel. White laces lay on top of the simple white tongue that is free of any logo.

First released in January 2004, the Common Projects Original Achilles White had a starting retail price of $415.

name: Triple Black Patent
title: New Balance 9060 Triple Black Patent
description:
The New Balance 9060 Triple Black Patent is a performance shoe with a sleek colorway and shiny, elegant accents.

This version of the New Balance 9060 is constructed with a black textile base for the upper. Shiny black patent leather overlays connect the toe box to the laces and the midsole, and also stretch back from the top of the laces to form the heel support. Black suede overlays form the toe cap and run over the midsoles, while the New Balance N logo appears on the lateral side in black patent leather and on the other side in a dashed design. An NB logo adorns the heel, and the tongue also contains branding elements. A shiny black TPU counter supports the heel, and the whole shoe sits on top of a chunky and wavy black rubber outsole.

Our favorite thing about this NB shoe is the sleek black colorway with patent accents. It gives the shoe an elegant look. The New Balance 9060 Triple Black Patent was released on February 15, 2024, for $150.

name: Halo
title: Nike Kobe 9 Elite Protro Halo
description:
The Nike Kobe 9 Elite Protro Halo is an angelic tribute to the late NBA legend Kobe Bryant released on his August 24th birthday.

White dominates the sneaker’s construction and symbolizes Kobe’s transition to the heavens. The Halo colorway was first seen on the Nike Kobe 8 Protro, which was released on the athlete’s birthday in 2023. The sneaker boasts an eye-catching high-top design with a lightweight Flyknit upper instead of traditional leather. The Flyknit provides a locked-in feel and is durable yet flexible. The addition of Nike React tech in the midsole allows for greater responsiveness, while the outsole is designed to mimic the natural movements of the foot.

Our experts at StockX like the sneaker’s commitment to maintaining its white aesthetic—even the Swoosh logo and the Kobe Bryant branding on the tongue come in clean white. The Nike Kobe 9 Elite Protro Halo was released on August 23, 2024, and sold for $240.

name: Travis Scott British Khaki
title: Jordan 6 Retro Travis Scott British Khaki
description:
Travis Scott and Jordan Brand teamed up to deliver the Air Jordan 6 Retro Travis Scott British Khaki. The British Khaki marks the second time that Travis has added his touch to the Jordan 6 silhouette, the first being the 2019 Air Jordan 6 Travis Scott.

The upper of the Air Jordan 6 Retro Travis Scott British Khaki is made of British Khaki suede. From there, hits of Bright Crimson appear on the heel and tongue embroidered logos. The upper also has two cargo pockets: one with a snap enclosure on the lateral ankle and one with a zip enclosure on the medial ankle. A translucent tongue, heel tab, and outsole that glows in the dark adds the finishing touches to this latest Travis Scott Jordan.

The Air Jordan 6 Retro Travis Scott British Khaki released in April of 2021 and retailed for $250.

name: Argon (2022)
title: Nike Dunk Low Retro QS Argon (2022)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Retro QS Flash White Argon Blue Flash features a smooth leather upper that combines a marine blue foundation with powder blue overlays and a crisp white Swoosh.

This Low Retro QS Nike Dunk has a woven Nike tag on the breathable nylon tongue, while the white leather back tab displays a Nike wordmark in slanted block lettering. The sneaker rests on a standard rubber cupsole, featuring white sidewalls and a pastel blue outsole.

The Nike Dunk Low Retro QS Flash White Argon Blue Flash was released on the 23rd of September 2022 for a retail price of $130.

name: Mocha (GS)
title: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG Mocha (GS)
description:
The Jordan 1 Retro Low OG Mocha (GS) borrows the classic "Oreo" color-blocking and adds a chocolatey touch of Mocha on the heel.

Sticking to its retro roots, the Mocha (GS) Jordan 1 Retro Low OG boasts an all-leather construction with a white base and black accents on the forefoot overlay, the eyelets, the Swoosh, the mudguard, the collar lining, the rubber outsole, and the durable laces. The smooth leather heel counter and heel tab display Mocha, breaking up the black and white color-blocking. In addition, the heritage Air Jordan Wings logo embroidered on the heel tab comes in black, while the tongue tag features a black base with "NIKE AIR" lettering in Mocha.

Our experts at StockX like that this shoe is a high-top rendition of the AJ1 High Mocha from 2020. The grade school-sized Jordan 1 Retro Low OG Mocha (GS) was released on September 21, 2024, and was priced at $140.

name: Dusty Cactus
title: Nike P-6000 Dusty Cactus
description:
The Nike P-6000 Dusty Cactus draws its striking design from 2000s Pegasus models, including the Nike Pegasus 25.

Evocative of early 2000s runners, the Dusty Cactus Nike P-6000 features vertical and horizontal overlays streaking across the airy mesh upper. The overlays are crafted from leather and synthetic leather in metallic silver and Dusty Cactus, a bright aqua hue. The foam midsole provides soft cushioning, while the full rubber outsole provides no-slip grip on indoor and outdoor surfaces. The padded, mesh tongue displays a combination of ‘NIKE’ and "BOWERMAN SERIES’ branding, and the insole features an exaggerated Swoosh.

                             Our StockX experts like the molded, synthetic leather Swoosh logos on the side panels. The metallic silver embroidery around the edges makes the Swoosh shape stand out and allows the vivid Dusty Cactus tone to pop. The Nike P-6000 Dusty Cactus was released on January 5, 2024, and sold for $110.

name: Flamingo Pink
title: adidas Harden Vol. 8 Flamingo Pink
description:
The adidas Harden Vol. 8 Flamingo Pink is one of six adidas Harden Vol. 8 sneakers released during the spring of 2024. This sneaker stands out in the lineup due to its vibrant colorway of Lucid Pink, Solar Red, and Impact Orange.

The upper is made of knit textile with EVA support panels on the sides. The panels come in Lucid Pink and boast a curved design, which gives the sneaker a futuristic appearance. A closure system with Impact Orange laces cinches the front; however, the inner bootie completes the snug fit. In addition, pull tabs on the heel and front allow for easy removal. A full-length Boost midsole is visible through cutouts in the outsole and supports the Lightning Strike technology underfoot.

Our experts at StockX like the series of engraved lines on the molded heel panel because they add to the shoe’s futuristic aesthetic. The adidas Harden Vol. 8 Flamingo Pink was released on April 15, 2024, and retailed at $160.

name: Skyline
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Skyline
description:
Jordan Brand is paying homage to the original Michael Jordan Skyline photograph, with the release of the Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG Skyline.
​
​The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG Skyline is designed with gradient prints of oranges, pinks, and blues to represent the iconic Micheal Jordan photo of him dunking in front of the Chicago skyline. Jordan brand used canvas uppers and a sail midsole to help give the sneaker a vintage inspired look. The sneakers come with specially designed packaging to look like the Michael Jordan Skyline photograph.​
​
​The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG Skyline released April 8, 2023, with a retail price of $180.

name: Rebellionaire
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Rebellionaire
description:
The Air Jordan 1 Retro High Rebellionaire draws inspiration from the original Air Jordan 1 Shadow with its simple black and grey color blocked upper. Printed on the leather construction, graffiti style text covers the upper. At the base, a white and grey Air sole completes the design.

The Air Jordan 1 Retro High Rebellionaire released in March of 2022 and retailed for $170.

name: Moonbeam Classic Burgundy (Women's)
title: New Balance 327 Moonbeam Classic Burgundy (Women's)
description:
The New Balance 327 Moonbeam Classic Burgundy W arrives in a white, burgundy, and light gray color scheme.
​
​The New Balance 327 Moonbeam Classic Burgundy W has on the upper as a base white leather with light grey suede overlays on the front and back of the shoe for an elevated appearance. In addition, on the side it features a burgundy N logo on the medial side. There is New Balance branding on the sneaker’s tongue, in a matching burgundy base. The shoe's lightweight foam midsole and rubber outsole provide comfort and grip.
​
​The women’s rendition of the New Balance 327 Moonbeam Classic Burgundy was released on September 24th, 2020, and retailed at a price of $90.

name: Mono Clay
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Mono Clay
description:
The adidas Yeezy 350 V2 Mono Clay is apart of 2021's Mono pack. The upper of the sneaker introduces a new monofilament mesh to the signature 350 V2 model. A pull tab is stitched to the heel, bringing back the fan-favorite design addition. Lastly, a Boost sole is added to the sole for comfort.

The adidas Yeezy 350 V2 Mono Clay released in June of 2021 for $220, exclusively in Asia.

name: Yuto Horigome
title: Nike SB Dunk Low Yuto Horigome
description:
The Nike SB Dunk Low Yuto Horigome features a classic low-top silhouette with a sleek and streamlined design adorned in a blend of the neutral tones of Wolf Gray, Iron Gray, and Sail.

The Yuto Horigome Nike SB Dunk Low features a Sail leather upper, strengthened with Wolf Gray suede overlays on both the front and rear portions. It includes a leather Swoosh in a unique Iron Gray shade, and the branding elements consist of a double-feather graphic on the lateral heel. Additionally, 'Y uto Horigome' is prominently displayed on the tongue tag, denoting his association with Nike SB. The pink suede back tab is adorned with an embroidered Nike wordmark, creating a striking contrast with the low-cut padded collar made from brown suede. The sneaker's foundation is firmly supported by a sturdy cup sole.

What our experts say about the Nike SB Dunk Low Yuto Horigome is that Yuto's influence and style are reflected in the shoe's design, making it an appealing choice for not only for skateboarders but others as well. The clean and classic colorway adds to the shoe’s desirability for both skateboarding and everyday wear. The sneaker was released on August 29th, 2023, for $130.

name: Di'orr Greenwood Navajo Arts
title: Nike SB Dunk High Di'orr Greenwood Navajo Arts
description:
The Nike SB Dunk High Di'orr Greenwood Navajo Arts is a skateboarding shoe inspired by iconic basketball shoe designs and Navajo culture.

This sneaker was designed by Di'Orr Greenwood, an artist and member of the Navajo Nation. It includes elements that pay tribute to Greenwood’s heritage. For example, the Big Dipper constellation, known as Nahookos Bika, is stitched across the Swoosh logo on the lateral side panels. Small white stars decorate the Swoosh on the medial side and the panels that form the lace cage. In addition, while some perforations across the vamp are regular holes, others are star-shaped cutouts. The upper comes in leather and features contrasting panels in Turquoise Blue, Rugged Orange, and Black.

Our experts at StockX like the ribbon running the length of the tongue and displaying a gradient of yellow and orange hues. The Nike SB Dunk High Di'orr Greenwood Navajo Arts was released on June 4, 2024, and sold for $145.

name: Sea Salt Moonbeam
title: New Balance 9060 Sea Salt Moonbeam
description:
The New Balance 9060 Sea Salt Moonbeam is a subtle-looking yet fashion-forward sports shoe that you can use for training and casual wear. It's extra comfy, thanks to New Balance's ABZORB cushioning.

New Balance 9060 trainers have always had great-looking, bold, modern styling. It's one of the hallmarks of the range. While this one is lightly colored and somewhat understated, it still gives off a distinctly high-tech air. The colorway combines a silvery upper with slightly grey panels, the Moonbeam shade. These alternate between breathable textiles and plush suede.

We like the fluid lines of this shoe, as well as its high-tech credentials. A sculpted midsole pod well protects the foot. Underneath are six cushioning platforms that combine to provide flexibility and high grip levels. We can't fault this shoe regarding foot support when running. The New Balance 9060 Sea Salt Moonbeam was released on 31 July 2024, priced at $150.

name: Protection Pack Navy Grey
title: New Balance 2002R Protection Pack Navy Grey
description:
The New Balance 2002R Protection Pack Navy Grey is a reimagined iteration of the iconic New Balance 2002R sneakers.

Designed by Yue Wu, this sneaker features an upper with a mesh base, overlayed by jagged suede overlays along its mudguard, midfoot, heel, and toebox. Most overlays are navy blue, while the overlays on the bottom portion of the heel and toebox are grey. Rounding out the shoe’s design is a white and earth-tone midsole paired with a black rubber outsole.

The New Balance 2002R Protection Pack Navy Grey first hit the market on Valentine’s Day 2023. At the time of its release, this shoe had a retail price of $170.

name: Cactus Plant Flea Market Black (2024)
title: Nike Air Force 1 Low Cactus Plant Flea Market Black (2024)
description:
The Nike Air Force 1 Low Cactus Plant Flea Market Black (2024) is part of a collaboration between Nike and Cactus Plant Flea Market, a streetwear label defined by its DIY aesthetic and playful designs.

This sneaker represents one of the first times Cactus Plant Flea Market reimagined the classic Air Force 1. Although the shoe doesn’t display bold Cactus Planet Flea Market design elements, it has several key details. The left shoe features ‘AIR,’ while the right shoe displays ‘FLEA’ in black bubble letters outlined in white. The all-black upper is made of leather and boasts tonal leather overlays, a Swoosh on the medial side panel, and perforations across the vamp for breathability.

Our StockX experts like the black rubber outsole, which completes the black-on-black aesthetic. The Nike Air Force 1 Low Cactus Plant Flea Market Black (2024) was launched on May 7, 2024, and sold for $150.

name: Travis Scott Cactus Jack Saturn Gold
title: Nike Air Max 1 Travis Scott Cactus Jack Saturn Gold
description:
In collaboration with Travis Scott's record label Cactus Jack, the Nike Air Max 1 Travis Scott Cactus Jack Saturn Gold pays homage to outdoor exploration and the Nike ACG Pocket Knife hiking shoe. It boasts a light yellow layered mesh upper with matching Durabuck overlays and reversed Swoosh logos. A drawstring Gillie lacing system nods to common features on trail runners. At the base, a yellowed sole with a cloudy Air unit adds the finishing touch.

The Nike Air Max 1 Travis Scott Cactus Jack Saturn Gold released in May of 2022 and retailed for $150.

name: Light Bone Bicoastal Green
title: Nike P-6000 Premium Light Bone Bicoastal Green
description:
The Nike P-6000 Premium Light Bone Bicoastal Green is a running shoe turned lifestyle sneaker that draws inspiration from Pegasus sneakers in the Nike catalog.

The upper is airy white mesh with textile and synthetic overlays in Light Bone, Metallic Silver, and Bicoastal, a green hue with hints of blue. The Pegasus 2006 and Pegasus 25 inform the sneaker's design, including the overlay pattern and the slightly chunky silhouette. Padding around the tongue and collar provides protective cushioning, while the foam midsole adds a responsive feel. Swoosh logos are on the side panels, the toebox, the heel, and the toe. Finally, the off-white color applied to the midsole adds a vintage touch and a worn-in aesthetic.

Our StockX experts like how the materials upgrade the classic 2000s technical silhouette. The Nike P-6000 Premium Light Bone Bicoastal Green was released on March 26, 2024, and retailed at $120.

name: Houston Oilers
title: Jordan Spizike Low Houston Oilers
description:
The Jordan Spizike Low Houston Oilers pays tribute to the Houston Oilers, an American football team that called Houston home from 1960 to 1996.

This low-top sneaker takes elements from four iconic shoes in the Jordan catalog. For example, the lacing Wings provide a secure fit and are a throwback to the Air Jordan 4, while the mesh details on the quarter panel pay homage to the Air Jordan 5. The sneaker boasts a Football Blue base with University Red details, which represent the Houston Oilers’ team colors. The upper is made of velvety nubuck with overlays displaying an elephant print pattern. This Jordan signature pattern also comes in Football Blue and slightly darker Fountain Blue. A visible Nike Air unit can be found in the heel, which provides responsive cushioning.

Our StockX experts like the University Red details, including the toggle on the laces and the Jumpman logo. The Jordan Spizike Low Houston Oilers was released on February 21st, 2024, and retailed at $160.

name: Black
title: adidas Ultra Boost 1.0 DNA Black
description:
The adidas Ultra Boost 1.0 DNA Black is a striking dual-chromatic sneaker. This running and lifestyle shoe is partially made of recycled Parley Ocean Plastic, signifying the adidas commitment to the environment.

The adidas Ultra Boost 1.0 DNA in a Core Black colorway features an upper in black adidas Primeknit designed to hug your foot and provide comfort and energy-enhancing support. The black adidas three stripes on the side panel and a black Fitcounter molded heel counter have a sheen that sets them apart from the Primeknit. The tongue, laces, pull tab on the heel, sock liner, and insoles are also unrelieved black.

The feature we most enjoy about this shoe is the high-performance sole unit. Hundreds of Boost capsules are fused to cushion and return energy with every step. The adidas Ultra Boost 1.0 DNA Black was released on January 1, 2023, for a retail price of $200.

name: CLOT Halo Ivory
title: adidas Gazelle CLOT Halo Ivory
description:
The adidas Gazelle CLOT Halo Ivory reimagines the Gazelle silhouette as an espadrille-like shoe. It’s also part of a collaboration between adidas and CLOT, a Hong Kong-based streetwear label known for combining Eastern and Western aesthetics.

The upper is crafted from a knit textile in Halo Ivory instead of leather or suede. This material makes the sneaker look handmade and almost like thick linen or woven hemp fabric. Paying tribute to the classic adidas Gazelle silhouette, the toebox boasts a suede overlay in tan. The heel tab and the panels around the laces also come in tan. However, this sneaker stands out because of the adidas 3-Stripes logo, embroidered with seed beads in Cloud White.

Our StockX experts like the espadrille-inspired midsole with oversized stitching and a neutral tan color. The adidas Gazelle CLOT Halo Ivory was released on June 14, 2024, and retailed at $160.

name: Comme des Garcons PLAY Black
title: Converse Chuck Taylor All Star 70 Ox Comme des Garcons PLAY Black
description:
Converse Chuck Taylor All Star 70s Ox Comme des Garcons PLAY Black is a model of the iconic collaboration between Comme des Garcons, a Japanese Brand, and Converse. Converse Chuck Taylor All Star 70s Ox Comme des Garcons PLAY Black features a canvas upper. It also features contrasting lace colorways and white seams. On the side, it features the famous red heart and a silhouette that ends on the cream-colored sole.

Converse Chuck Taylor All Star 70s Ox Comme des Garcons PLAY Black was released in July 2017 and had a retail price of $120.
model: Converse Chuck Taylor All Star 70 Ox

name: Cream Cloud Grey
title: ASICS Gel-NYC Cream Cloud Grey
description:
Inspired by the people, culture, and lifestyle of New York City, the ASICS Gel-NYC Cream Cloud Grey dresses the innovative silhouette in a neutral colorway of Cloud Grey and cream.

Originally designed by Angelo Baque, the Cream Cloud Grey ASICS Gel-NYC is a mashup of retro and contemporary influences. For example, the Gel-Nimbus 3 and the Gel-MC Plus V inform the upper, while the tooling system borrows from the Gel Cumulus 16. This gives the sneaker upgraded Gel cushioning in the heel and forefoot but also celebrates running shoes from the early 2000s through the bulky, layered upper. Breathable mesh in Cream makes up the base, while leather and synthetic overlays in Cloud Grey create a supportive, crisscross pattern on the side panels.

Our experts at StockX like the padding around the collar and in the tongue because it adds comfort and contributes to the bulky aesthetic. The ASICS Gel-NYC Cream Cloud Grey was released on July 13, 2024, and sold for $130.

name: Paw Print Pink Foam (Women's)
title: Jordan 1 Low SE Paw Print Pink Foam (Women's)
description:
The Jordan 1 Low SE Paw Print Pink Foam (Women's) adds paw print motifs to the outsole for an updated take on the OG sneaker.

While the silhouette hearkens back to the original shoe from 1985, the fuzzy white laces and Foam Pink paw prints give the Paw Print Pink Foam (Women's) Jordan 1 Low SE a modern yet cute upgrade. However, the sneaker still maintains its premium leather construction with a white base and Pink Foam on the mudguard, eyestays, and heel detailing. The Glacial Blue Swoosh logo adds a pop of color and tonally matches the embroidered Air Jordan Wings logo on the heel. An encapsulated Air-Sole unit cushions against impact, while the rubber outsole provides durable traction.

Our experts like the metallic silver Jumpman logo on the leather tongue because the shiny metal gives the sneaker a premium feel. The women’s size Jordan 1 Low SE Paw Print Pink Foam (Women's) was released on September 1, 2024, and sold for $115.

name: Bad Bunny Triple Black
title: adidas Response CL Bad Bunny Triple Black
description:
The adidas Response CL Bad Bunny Triple Black is a limited-edition sneaker that was designed in collaboration with Puerto Rican artist Bad Bunny.

The upper of the Response CL Bad Bunny Triple Black is made from breathable mesh. The shoe also features reflective details on the 3-Stripes and upper that provide visibility in low-light conditions. The midsole is designed with adidas' BOOST technology, which provides cushioning and energy return. The outsole is made from high-quality rubber that provides traction on any surface.

We think that the notable feature of the adidas Response CL Bad Bunny Triple Black is the eye graphic on the heel tab. The eye graphic is a black-and-white illustration with a bold outline that contrasts with the all-black design of the shoe. It is intentionally placed on the heel tab, which is visible from behind, making it a unique and eye-catching detail. The shoe was released on June 24th, 2023, at a retail price of $160.

name: Orange Rush Gum
title: adidas Samba OG Orange Rush Gum
description:
First designed back in the late 1940s, the adidas Samba has been released in so many different colorways since then. The adidas Samba OG Orange Rush Gum helps add to the mix by presenting the Samba in a different light .

This adidas Samba OG has a leather upper that is almost entirely orange except for some white on the tongue tag and heel and the white that was used for adidas’ Three Stripes logo. The sneaker also comes with a set of laces that are a slightly lighter shade of orange and a gum rubber sole that contrasts the colors found on the rest of the shoe nicely.

What we love most about this sneaker, though, is that it showcases adidas' desire to continue to push boundaries with the Samba silhouette. Even though it has been around for decades, adidas keeps on finding new ways to make it look modern without sacrificing any of the features that have turned it into a classic shoe for the brand. The adidas Samba OG Orange Rush Gum was released on September 15, 2022, for $100.

name: Castlerock Rain Cloud
title: New Balance 480 Castlerock Rain Cloud
description:
The New Balance 480 Castlerock Rain Cloud is a stylish lifestyle shoe inspired by basketball sneakers of the 1980s.

The upper of this elegantly dressed low-top is fashioned from light gray suede overlaid with darker gray suede at the toe cap, midfoot, side panel, eye stays, and heel counter. The toe box is perforated to facilitate breathability and enhance comfort. Flat white laces that ensure a snug closure echo the white lining of the medium gray leather side panel " N." New Balance branding also hits the tongue tag and the heel tab. A white foam midsole offers cushioning and support and rests atop a dark gray rubber outsole that sports grooves and circles for traction in multiple directions when you’re on the move.

The eye-catching standout feature of this pair of kicks is the gray tumbled leather collar padded for comfort. It features the only hit of leather on the upper aside from the side-panel " N." The New Balance 480 Castlerock Rain Cloud was released on January 9, 2024, for a retail price of $90.

name: Royal Toe
title: Jordan 1 Retro High Royal Toe
description:
Jordan Brand adds a twist to a classic with the Jordan 1 Retro High Royal Toe, now available on StockX. Releases like the Shattered Backboard 1 and Bred Toe have shifted all eyes on Jordan’s "Black Toe" inspired colorways. The Royal Toe takes inspiration from the original Jordan 1 Royal colorway (which released in 1985) and adds design elements of the Black Toe 1 to create a familiar, but new dialogue.

This AJ 1 features a white and royal leather upper with black leather overlays and detailing. A white midsole, royal outsole, and branded leather tongue tag completes this design. These sneakers released in May of 2020 and retailed for $170 USD.

name: University Red Gum
title: Nike SB Dunk Low University Red Gum
description:
The Nike SB Dunk Low University Red Gum is a skateboarding sneaker that features an all-red colorway with an outsole in Gum Light Brown.

Released as part of the "Support Your Local Skateshop" initiative, this low-top sneaker features a bulky construction with padding around the collar and tongue. The upper is crafted entirely from leather in University Red, with overlays of the same color. In addition, lines of reinforced stitching also come in University Red. Perforations across the vamp allow the foot to breathe, while thick laces wind through the eyelets. White details can be found on the signature Swoosh reaching across the side panels and the NIKE logo embroidered on the heel tab. The tongue displays a University Red logo tag with a Swoosh in Gym Red.

Our StockX experts like the thick gum rubber outsole, which provides traction on pavement. The Nike SB Dunk Low University Red Gum was released on May 1, 2024, and retailed at $115.

name: Mirage (Translucent Outsole)
title: Nike Book 1 Mirage (Translucent Outsole)
description:
Introducing the Nike Book 1 Mirage (Translucent Outsole)n, a sneaker that seamlessly blends traditional craftsmanship with contemporary style. Its unique color palette of light orewood brown, sesame, baroque brown, and sail is inspired by earthy tones and natural landscapes, making it a standout choice for those who appreciate footwear that makes a statement without shouting. The Mirage translucent outsole adds a touch of intrigue, elevating the sneaker's overall aesthetic and ensuring that it catches the eye of passersby. ​
​​
​Nike's dedication to innovation and style is evident in every detail of the Nike Book 1. From the choice of materials to the sleek design lines, this sneaker is built for those who demand both form and function. Whether you're hitting the court or heading to a casual outing, the Nike Book 1 Light Orewood Brown is designed to complement a wide range of styles and personalities, making it a versatile addition to any sneaker collection.​
​​
​Having made its debut on February 17, 2024, the Nike Book 1 Mirage (Translucent Outsole), retailing at $140, has already left a significant mark on sneaker culture. Its thoughtful design and impeccable craftsmanship have garnered attention from basketball players and casual wearers alike. If you're looking for a sneaker that combines timeless elegance with modern performance, the Nike Book 1 Mirage (Translucent Outsole) is a choice that you won't regret.

name: Falcons
title: Nike Air DT Max '96 Falcons
description:
The Nike Air DT Max '96 Falcons is a premium sneaker that pays homage to coach and former NFL player Deion Sanders’s early career with the Atlanta Falcons.

The Falcons Nike Air DT Max '96 upper is crafted from ultra-soft, black nubuck with accents in Team Anthracite, Fire Red, and white. This color scheme represents the Falcons’ team colors and celebrates one of Georgia’s top NFL teams. Embroidered in Fire Red and white thread, "21" appears on the heel—a nod to Sanders’s Falcons jersey number. Other Fire Red details include the collar lining, the heel pull tabs, the miniature Swoosh logos near the ankle, and the tongue pull tab. In terms of technology, visible Air Max cushioning provides comfort underfoot.

Our experts at StockX like that this sneaker is the first DT Max to display Sanders’s jersey number. The Nike Air DT Max '96 Falcons was released on November 15, 2024, and sold for $170.

name: Fresh White
title: Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 Fresh White
description:
The Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 Fresh is composed of an all-white leather construction with vamp perforations, Swoosh overlays, and a thick Air sole in a signature style. Instead of traditionally embroidered detailing at the tongue and heel, this model adds its own twist with subtle, debossed detailing for an elevated look.

The Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 Fresh released in July of 2022 and retailed for $140.

name: Cyber Reflective (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Cyber Reflective (Women's)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Cyber Reflective (Women's) presents a sports shoe dressed in unrelieved shades of black. This sneaker designed and specifically sized for women features reflective details inspired by cyberpunk culture.

The Women's Cyber Reflective Nike Dunk Low-Top features an upper with a base of black nubuck with classic perforations in the toe box. The black laces, the black tongue, and the black sock liner add to the obsidian look of this upper. The foam midsole is also black and sits on top of a black rubber outsole grooved for traction on many different surfaces. The one hit of color on this sneaker is on the racer blue insole that sports black Nike branding.

The aspect of this shoe that is most compelling is the reflective surface of the smooth black leather overlays on the upper. The overlays glow silver in the dark, making this stealthy shoe stand out. The Nike Dunk Low Cyber Reflective (Women's) was released on January 12, 2024, for a retail price of $135.

name: Vintage Panda (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Vintage Panda (Women's)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Vintage Panda (Women's) takes the signature two-tone "Panda" colorway and applies it to a vintage-inspired Dunk. The standard Black and White Panda colorway sees the addition of Coconut, an off-white hue.

This off-white, slightly yellow color can be found on the midsole and laces, which gives the Vintage Panda a worn-in appearance. Unlike the classic Panda Dunk, this variant features a glossy coating over the black leather overlays that adds to the sneaker’s retro appeal. In addition, the Swoosh on the side panel matches the overlays and contrasts the bright, white base. The sneaker features a padded, low collar and a soft textile lining to maximize comfort.

What do our experts love about this sneaker? The branding is minimal, including a Nike tag on the tongue and ‘NIKE’ stitched across the back tab in white thread. The women’s size Nike Dunk Low Vintage Panda (Women's) was released on October 18, 2023, and retailed at $125.

name: Tom Sachs Archive Dark Sulfur
title: NikeCraft General Purpose Shoe Tom Sachs Archive Dark Sulfur
description:
The NikeCraft General Purpose Shoe Tom Sachs Yellow is the result of a collaboration between Nike and Tom Sachs.

The Tom Sachs Yellow NikeCraft takes on a functional design with a yellow mesh upper with tonal suede overlays and a contrasting white Swoosh on the lateral and medial sides. Orange tabs on the heel and tongue allow an easy on and off. The shoe sits a top a cream midsole packed with EVA for cushioning, while a black waffle-traction rubber outsole is for grip.

The NikeCraft General Purpose Shoe Tom Sachs Yellow was released on the 2nd of September 2022, and originally retailed for $110.

name: Stargazer
title: Nike Ja 2 Stargazer
description:
The Nike Ja 2 Stargazer is a glitzy trainer that will immediately catch everyone's eyes when you wear it. It has one of the most unusual colorways you'll likely encounter. Plus, you're also getting all the advanced Nike athletic tech.

This is an updated version of the hugely popular Nike Ja 1. It benefits from additional padding around the ankle cuff and a new waterfall collar. The colorway features magenta ripple panels with a pastel blue swoosh. The lower heel and side soles have contoured gray segments that evoke stars in the Milky Way. A suede toe box completes the look.

Our experts were very taken by the visual styling of this shoe. There's a fluidity that's designed to reflect Ja Morant's smooth playing style. The grippy undersole feels secure and solid during fast direction changes. This innovative trainer strikes a good balance between fashion, ability, and on-court ruggedness. The Nike Ja 2 Stargazer was released on 3 October 2024 and retailed at $120.

name: White Black Medium Olive
title: Nike Air Max 1 White Black Medium Olive
description:
The Nike Air Max 1 White Black Medium Olive pays homage to the original Air Max 1, introduced in 1987, but with a modern twist in a color combination of white, black, Pure Platinum, and Medium Olive.

The upper of the White Black Medium Olive Nike Air Max 1 is predominantly crafted from Crisp White mesh, accentuated by Pure Platinum overlays and a black Swoosh logo. Synthetic suede overlays in Pure Platinum adorn the white mesh base. Touches of olive green can be observed in the textile lining and synthetic suede mudguard, in addition to the stitched Nike Air logo located on the rear heel. The white PU midsole contains a visible Air-sole unit in the heel, guaranteeing a comfy stride. Additionally, the shoe features a two-toned black and white rubber outsole.

The standout element of the Nike Air Max 1 White Black Medium Olive is the exposed Air-sole unit in the heel, providing enduring comfort and making the shoe an excellent choice for both athletic activities and casual wear. The sneaker debuted for $140 on October 12th, 2023.

name: Roses
title: Nike Giannis Zoom Freak 6 Roses
description:
The Nike Giannis Zoom Freak 6 Roses has everything the modern B-ball player could want in a shoe. The latest technology is used in its construction and material blends to specifically enhance stability, speed and stamina.

The Nike Zoom technology comprises the standard high-performance Air Zoom unit in the toe to provide impact absorption and improve comfort. Upgraded rubber soles provide enhanced traction over previous models. This particular collab with Giannis Antetokounmpo has a colorway to commemorate the Bucks star's father. It has a pink Swoosh overlaid with roses on a white background.

The big thing we prize about this basketball shoe is its sentimental factor; the other colorways in the range don't have the familial connection. We also like its updated silhouette, based on the Giannis Immortality 4 series. The Air Zoom cushioning has an energy return effect, along with a Cushion 2.0 foam midsole. The Nike Giannis Zoom Freak 6 Roses was released on 16 August 2024 at a retail price of $150.

name: Vintage Green (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Vintage Green (Women's)
description:
Constructed with a smooth white and Pro Green leather upper, the women's Nike Dunk Low Vintage Green (W) explores the same two-tone color blocking featured on the first line of Nike Dunks in 1985. From there, vintage-styled, yellowed soles and laces add the finishing touches to this retro design.

The women's Nike Dunk Low Vintage Green (W) released in March of 2022 and retailed for $110.

name: Bred Toe (GS)
title: Jordan 1 Low Bred Toe (GS)
description:
The grade school Air Jordan 1 Low Bred Toe GS mimics the color scheme of its predecessor, the Air Jordan 1 Bred Toe. It features amazing details like a puffy black nylon tongue, a large Air Jordan Wings logo embroidered on the heel, and a white Jumpman logo. Additionally, it features an enhanced red outsole and a cushioned white midsole.

The grade school Air Jordan 1 Low Bred Toe GS was released on 8th December 2021. It retailed at $75.

name: Run The Jewels
title: Nike SB Dunk Low Run The Jewels
description:
Run The Jewels released their first ever sneaker with Nike, with the release of the Nike SB Dunk Low Run The Jewels. The sneakers are inspired from the Run The Jewels 3 album cover artwork.

The Nike SB Dunk Low Run The Jewels are constructed with blue suede uppers that sit on top of a translucent blue outsole. Nike used pink suede on the Swoosh, and gold branded accents on the heel and tongue. The limited edition sneakers feature RTJ branding on the insoles, and come with three different blue lace sets.

The Nike SB Dunk Low Run The Jewels released April 20, 2023, with a retail price of $110.

name: Orange Emerald Rise
title: Nike SB Dunk Low Orange Emerald Rise
description:
The Nike SB Dunk Low Orange Emerald Rise takes on the classic Dunk Low silhouette, and showcases a vibrant colorway that combines orange and Emerald Rise tones, creating a bold and eye-catching aesthetic.​
​​
​The Orange Emerald Rise Nike SB Dunk Low highlights a textured suede upper, with the base color in Emerald Rise and distinct orange overlays at both the forefoot and heel sections. The sneaker is constructed almost entirely from fluffy suede, which gives it a retro appeal. The iconic Swoosh is crafted from Noise Aqua suede, harmonizing with the Nike logo details on the tongue tag and rear tab. Inside, the midsole incorporates a Zoom Air unit in the heel to provide cushioning for impact protection. The foundation of the sneaker is reinforced by a rubber cup sole in a Lemon Chiffon hue.​
​​
​What we love about the Nike SB Dunk Low Orange Emerald Rise is its unique and eye-catching fluffy appearance. The shoe's upper incorporates a "hairy" or "fluffy" suede material, giving it a distinctive and textured look that mimics the appearance of fur. The low top was released on August 25th, 2023, for $110.​
​​
​

name: Hello Kitty (2022)
title: Nike Air Presto Hello Kitty (2022)
description:
Originally produced as a gift for Nike's friends and family in 2004, the Nike Air Presto Hello Kitty returned in 2022 for its first-ever official release.

The Nike Air Presto Hello Kitty nods to Sanrio's Hello Kitty, a fictional character created by Yuko Shimizu in 1974. The upper is constructed of a light blue neoprene upper with Hello Kitty graphics and a semi translucent TPU lace cage. At the heel, a Hello Kitty styled heel wrap adds further detailing. From there, a white and black Air sole with Swoosh detailing completes the design.

The Nike Air Presto Hello Kitty released in May of 2022 and retailed for $140.

name: Grey Lilac
title: New Balance 9060 Grey Lilac
description:
The New Balance 9060 Gray Lilac introduces refined details to a lifestyle runner that draws inspiration from design elements found in New Balance’s iconic 99X series.

Taking cues from celebrated 99X models and embracing futuristic aesthetics reminiscent of the Y2K era, the Gray Lilac New Balance 9060 showcases a gray ‘N’ logo on the quarter panel. The tongue patch on the NB 9060 is inspired by the lace jewel of the original 991, and its design seamlessly integrates sway bars from the 990 into the upper. The sculpted pod midsole, equipped with ABZORB, ENCAP, and SBS technologies, provides underfoot comfort. The upper, secured with drawcord lacing, features gray mesh and suede overlays in a subtle pale gray hue, ensuring a snug and well-ventilated fit.

The notable highlight of the New Balance 9060 Gray Lilac resides in its sculpted pod midsole, delivering an unparalleled level of comfort through the integration of ABZORB, SBS cushioning, and ENCAP technologies. The runner debuted for $150 on November 22nd, 2023.

name: Bright Cyan
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Bright Cyan
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Bright Cyan features a Bright Cyan nylon upper with reflect "700" graphics on the lateral side. A sculptural black Boost sole completes the design.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Bright Cyan released in June of 2021 and retailed for $220.

name: Fade Salt
title: adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Fade Salt
description:
The adidas Yeezy 700 v3 Fade Salt features the silhouette’s signature glow-in-the-dark cage over a Fade Salt colorway.

The upper section of this collaborative V3 sneaker is made of Primeknit, with the RPU cage open at the forefoot to expose the tongue and laces. The inner section is constructed for a snug fit and the insole features both Yeezy and adidas branding. The thick, polyurethane midsole features full-length EVA cushioning and boasts adidas branding on its heel. The rubber outsole sports herringbone traction interspersed with pods. 

The adidas Yeezy 700 v3 Fade Salt originally debuted on September 22, 2022 for $210 retail.

name: Black Metallic Gold (2020)
title: Jordan 1 Retro High Black Metallic Gold (2020)
description:
Jordan Brand is no stranger to patent leather. Since the Air Jordan 11 debuted the material for the brand back in 1996, it’s found its way onto various models such as the Jordan 1, Jordan 4, and Jordan 7. 2020 marks the third issue of the patent-clad Air Jordan 1 Black Metallic Gold, with the first releasing back in 2001, and again in 2013.

The Air Jordan 1 Black Metallic Gold’s 2020 retro delivers slight cosmetic changes from its 2013 predecessor. The upper black and metallic gold patent leather upper. From there, a full translucent black sole with gold speckles completes the Jordan 1 classic.

The Air Jordan 1 Black Metallic Gold released in November of 2020 and retailed for $170.

name: KoRn 30th Anniversary
title: adidas Superstar KoRn 30th Anniversary
description:
The adidas Superstar KoRn 30th Anniversary blends music and fashion in a design that celebrates the influential band's legacy. This collaboration merges adidas' iconic Superstar silhouette with elements that pay homage to American rock group KoRn's 30-year history.

The KoRn 30th Anniversary Superstar by adidas features a leather upper in white, black, and gold with embossed patterns inspired by the band’s aesthetic. The design incorporates the KoRn logo on the heel, the Adidas logo on the tongue, "Superstar" written in gold above the 3-Stripes that each say "Est. 1994". The classic shell-toe structure gives you extra durability, and the rubber outsole provides traction.

One aspect we, the experts, admire about the adidas Superstar KoRn 30th Anniversary is the intricate embossing, which adds depth to the leather upper. Another standout is the collaboration-specific branding, uniquely combining the brand's iconic elements with KoRn’s visual identity. Retailing at $140 when it was released on October 31, 2024, as a fitting tribute.

name: Rattlesnake
title: Nike Book 1 Rattlesnake
description:
The Nike Book 1 Rattlesnake is a premium sneaker that’s part of a collaboration between NBA player Devin Booker and Nike. It features a primarily white upper with rattlesnake skin details.

The upper is crafted from smooth leather and a canvas-like textile with white stitching. The combination of these two materials creates a gentle textural contrast that allows the rattlesnake elements to stand out. The Swoosh logos on the side panels display a rattlesnake pattern with brown, tan, and black tones. Embroidery around the Swoosh logos creates a white border and makes the print stand out. Hits of red can be found on the BOOK logo tag on the tongue and CHAPTER ONE running up the heel. Other noteworthy details include the number 96 on the heel pull tab, which represents the year Booker was born.

Our StockX experts like the addition of a lightweight midsole with a Zoom Air unit in the heel. The Nike Book 1 Rattlesnake was released on May 11, 2024, and retailed at $140.

name: Triple Red
title: Nike Air Force 1 Low Triple Red
description:
If you are a lover of red athletic shoes then the Nike Air Force 1 Low Triple Red is just for you. Every single part of the shoe is red, from the sole to the uppers, the tongue, the laces, and even the signature Nike swoosh. Embossed on the sole of the shoe you will find the word "Air," which you will also find on the back of the shoe underneath the Nike name and logo.

Released in February 2020, the Nike Air Force 1 Low Triple Red retailed for $110.

name: DreamWorks Shrek
title: Crocs Classic Clog DreamWorks Shrek
description:
The Crocs Classic Clog took an adventurous turn with the DreamWorks Shrek collaboration, released on September 13, 2023. This iconic footwear got a fairytale twist, boasting details inspired by our favorite ogre.

Coming in a swamp-inspired color scheme, this clog captures the essence of Shrek, merging greens and browns harmoniously. But what truly sets it apart? The toe box showcases the unmistakable Shrek nose and ear details, injecting a playful vibe and bringing out the magic of the animated classic.

What's really cool about this Crocs x Shrek design is the signature comfort of the Classic Clog combined with the enchanting allure of DreamWorks. Whether you're headed on an adventure around town or Far Far Away, these are the perfect fit. The Crocs Classic Clog DreamWorks Shrek collab dropped on September 13, 2023, and was initially priced at a magical $60.

name: Brown Putty Grey
title: adidas Samba OG Brown Putty Grey
description:
The adidas Samba OG Brown Putty Grey covers the classic Samba construction in a warm yet neutral colorway of brown, Putty Grey, and Gold Metallic.

Although the silhouette maintains its original form, the color blocking gives the brown putty grey adidas Samba OG a contemporary upgrade. For instance, the base, eyelets, and thin tongue come in a rich brown hue, while off-white covers the heel mustache, the signature 3-Stripes logo, and the collar lining. Adding a third color contrast, the suede T-shaped toe box overlay is gray. The shoe features several branding details, including "SAMBA" in gold lettering on the outer side panel and an off-white adidas logo on the tongue. Like other Samba models, this version boasts a gum rubber outsole underfoot.

Our experts at StockX like that the use of gray on the toe box overlay brings out the suede’s velvety texture. The adidas Samba OG Brown Putty Grey was released on September 30, 2024, and sold for $100.

name: Smokey Mauve (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Smokey Mauve (Women's)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Smokey Mauve (Women's) adds a white base with overlays in Smokey Mauve to the classic Nike Dunk Low silhouette.

This low-top sneaker features an upper made of leather with color-blocking leather overlays. Like other versions of the Nike Dunk Low, the "Smokey Mauve" edition boasts prominent Nike branding. However, each branding detail on the exterior comes in Playful Pink, including the Swooshes on the side panel, ‘NIKE’ stitched across the heel counter, and the logo tag on the tongue. The sneaker has perforations across the vamp, which allow the foot to breathe, as well as a front lace-up system with prominent Smokey Mauve laces weaving through the eyelets.

Our StockX experts like the pivot hoop design on the rubber outsole because provides both traction and durability. The women’s size Nike Dunk Low Smokey Mauve (Women's) was released on January 29th, 2024, and retailed at $115.

name: Burnt Sunrise
title: Nike SB Dunk Low Burnt Sunrise
description:
The Nike SB Dunk Low Burnt Sunrise adds a warm colorway of Burnt Orange and Light Gum Brown with Vintage Green accents to the SB Dunk Low silhouette.

Released ahead of the Fall/Winter season, this low-top skateboarding sneaker boasts an all-suede upper that lends itself well as a backdrop for the fiery Burnt Orange. The forefoot and heel overlays, the tongue, the cotton laces, and the back tab come in Burnt Orange, while the midsole and rubber outsole display complementary Light Gum Brown. The Burnt Sunrise Nike SB Dunk Low features several elements that enhance comfort, including padding around the collar and in the tongue as well as Air Zoom cushioning in the midsole.

Our experts at StockX like that the branding details come in Vintage Green. For instance, the suede Swoosh logo, the ‘NIKE’ lettering embroidered on the back tab, and the Nike branding on the tongue feature Vintage Green. The Nike SB Dunk Low Burnt Sunrise was released on July 30, 2024, and sold for $115.

name: Travis Scott Cactus Jack Baroque Brown
title: Nike Air Max 1 Travis Scott Cactus Jack Baroque Brown
description:
In collaboration with Travis Scott's record label Cactus Jack, the Nike Air Max 1 Travis Scott Cactus Jack Brown draws inspiration from the Nike ACG Pocket Knife hiking shoe. It features a layered mesh upper with tonal-brown Durabuck overlays and reversed Swoosh logos. A drawstring Gillie lacing system nods to common features on trail runners. At the base, a yellowed sole with a cloudy Air unit completes the design.

The Nike Air Max 1 Travis Scott Cactus Jack Brown released in May of 2022 and retailed for $150.

name: White Black (Women's)
title: Nike Blazer Mid 77 White Black (Women's)
description:
Drawing inspiration from the original 1973 Nike Blazer, the Nike Blazer Mid 77 White Black (Women's) utilizes simple color blocking to deliver a throwback look. It features a white leather upper with black Swoosh overlays and grey suede mudguards. At the base, a white Sole completes the design.

The Nike Blazer Mid 77 White Black (Women's) was released in April of 2020 for $100.

To shop all Nike Blazer shoes, click here.

name: Induction
title: Nike Ja 2 Induction
description:
The Nike Ja 2 Induction is a low-top basketball shoe featuring an upper in Taupe Grey animal print, overlaid with sheer Cobalt Bliss fabric with a scratched lines print. The lace panel and vamp are also Taupe Grey, accented by Ja 2 branding. The midsole in Cobalt Bliss coordinates with the upper, accented by the Swoosh. Midnight Series and 12:AM branding appear on the rear and inner heel.

Nike, the world’s largest athletic shoe producer, has been a significant entity in outfitting NBA players and collaborating with them to create signature shoes since the 1980s. To celebrate Memphis Grizzlies’ point guard Ja Morant’s induction into the Murray State Hall of Fame, Nike made the Ja 2 Induction, which features a color palette and patterns in honor of his achievements.

In our opinion, the shoe's best feature is its dual-patterned upper, which highlights its uncommon colorway. The Nike Ja 2 Induction was released on September 26, 2024, and retailed for $120.

name: Driftwood Castlerock
title: New Balance 9060 Driftwood Castlerock
description:
The New Balance 9060 Driftwood Castlerock is a sneaker with a look inspired by Y2K fashion.

This iteration of the New Balance 9060 features a paneled upper with breathable mesh and suede overlays. The mesh comes in a light brown color, while the suede overlays appear in various shades of a darker brown across the entire upper. The New Balance N adorns both midsoles, on one side made up of small white dashes and on the other side in solid white. The heel collar appears in dark gray with "NB" branding, while the tongue bears the 9060 logo. The shoe is supported by a chunky and curvy rubber outsole in shades of off-white and brown. The shoe is also equipped with ABZORB cushioning for extra comfort.

What we like most about this shoe is the muted color scheme, allowing it to blend in with any outfit. The New Balance 9060 Driftwood Castlerock was released on November 14, 2022, for a retail price of $150.

name: Bad Bunny Last Forum
title: adidas Forum Buckle Low Bad Bunny Last Forum
description:
The adidas Forum Buckle Low White is a collaborative sneaker between the German lifestyle brand and artist Bad Bunny.

The shoe has an off-white leather upper with matching suede overlays, and the signature 3-Stripes are made of grey suede. An adjustable ankle strap and toggle lacing that wraps around the collar is added to the laces for a secure fit. The "third eye" logo of Bad Bunny is displayed on two sets of overlapping tongues. The shoe has clear rubber sidewalls on a rubber cup sole.

The adidas Forum Buckle Low White debuted on the market on December 10th, 2022, retailing at $160.

name: Royal Blue Gum
title: adidas Samba OG Royal Blue Gum
description:
The adidas Samba OG Royal Blue Gum takes the classic, soccer-inspired Samba silhouette and applies a saturated colorway of Royal Blue, Gum, and Core White.

The sneaker features a soft suede upper in Royal Blue with signature Samba toe overlays in the same blue hue. The Royal Blue contrasts the Core White serrated 3-Stripes on the side panel, the heel, and the adidas Trefoil logo tag on the tongue. ‘SAMBA’ is printed along the 3-Stripes in metallic gold ink. Like other Sambas, the "OG Royal Blue Gum" comes with a gum rubber outsole that provides traction and contributes to the shoe’s iconic look.

What do our StockX experts love about this sneaker? The EVA insole provides additional cushioning and is one of the main differences between this model and the OG Samba. The adidas Samba OG Royal Blue Gum was released on October 21, 2022, and retailed at $100.

name: Static
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 V2 Static
description: adidas and Kanye are teaming up to release the adidas Yeezy 700 V2 Static. This Yeezy 700 comes with a grey upper with white accents, white midsole, and a black sole. These sneakers released in December 2018 and retailed for $300. The 700’s have been one of the hottest adidas silhouette this year so place a Bid on these today.

name: Silver Cream
title: New Balance 530 Silver Cream
description:
The New Balance 530 Silver Cream was released in celebration of the brand’s 30th anniversary.

This model has a cream-toned mesh base with silver and grey synthetic overlays. The "N" logos on the shoe quarters also comes in a silver hue with a black outline. Further branding includes the "NB" text on its padded tongue, also in a silver tone, and a 530 text on the shoe collar. The base is equipped with an ABZORB midsole that provides light cushioning, and completes its design. 

The New Balance 530 Silver Cream was released on the market on January 7th, 2023. It retailed at a price of $100.

name: Black Black White
title: Nike P-6000 Black Black White
description:
The Nike P-6000 Black Black White dresses the P-6000 in all-black with a white Swoosh stitched onto the side panel to add contrast.

The running shoe Black Black White Nike P-6000 takes elements from heritage Pegasus models in the Nike catalog, including models from the early 2000s. Foam cushioning underfoot gives the sneaker an athletics-inspired look and protects the foot against impact stress. Sporty line overlays streak across the upper and is one of the P-6000’s noteworthy design elements. The overlays replace genuine leather with synthetic leather, which is durable and gives the sneaker a modern upgrade. Finally, the durable rubber outsole also comes in black and features a traction pattern with grooves.

Our experts like the ‘NIKE’ branding on the tongue’s logo tag because it’s one of the only pops of white on the black sneaker. The Nike P-6000 Black Black White was released on March 31, 2023, and sold for $120.

name: B.A.D.
title: Nike KD 16 B.A.D.
description:
The Nike KD 16 B.A.D. pays homage to Kevin Durant's grandmother, Barbara A. Davis, with her initials B.A.D. proudly displayed on the left tongue.

Dominated by a lush Field Purple color, a beloved choice of Barbara A. Davis, the B.A.D. Nike KD 16 is accented with Rush Fuchsia details, infusing a vibrant touch. A mesh base in the design creates a subtle and refined contrast. Deeper purple tones grace the tongue, eyestays, sock liner, vamp, and lace set, adding layers of depth and opulence to the overall aesthetic. Combining both meaning and functionality, the shoe incorporates a purple foam midsole matched with a coordinating rubber outsole for comfort and traction. KD's logo graces the right tongue, while the left tongue bears the B.A.D. inscription. This same acronym is prominently featured on the purple insoles, reinforcing the heartfelt tribute to his grandmother.

The notable feature of the Nike KD 16 B.A.D. is its sincere tribute to Barbara A. Davis, as the design and color scheme are crafted to honor and celebrate her lasting legacy. The sneaker debuted for $160 on October 27th, 2023.

name: Jacquemus Black (Women's)
title: Nike J Force 1 Low LX Jacquemus Black (Women's)
description:
Nike made waves this summer in collaboration with Jacquemus with the drop of the J Force 1 Low LX in the pristine black colorway on June 21, 2023. This fresh silhouette brought a high-end spin to the beloved Air Force 1, flexing a blend of luxe materials and avant-garde aesthetics.

The sneaker’s upper in black offers a sleek leather upper, with a clean, black outsole. Subtle accents play across the shoe, with an interesting sole woven together to the upper. while a pop of metallic silver hits, flaunting that iconic Nike logo.

This wasn't just another release, it was a game-changer. The Nike J Force 1 Low LX black hit the streets on June 21, 2023. With a retail price of $170.

name: Athletic Department Deep Jungle
title: Nike Dunk Low Athletic Department Deep Jungle
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Athletic Department Deep Jungle launched as part of the Nike Athletic Department Pack, which brings old-school styling to fan-favorite Nike models. This sneaker follows the Nike Dunk Low Athletic Department University Blue; however, it includes a different nostalgic colorway inspired by varsity sports.

The "Deep Jungle" colorway includes Sail, Deep Jungle, Coconut Milk, and White, which presents as a white base with dark green details. The smooth leather upper comes in Coconut Milk, which contrasts the Deep Jungle found on the suede Swooshes, inner liner, heel tab, and rubber outsole. The sneaker boasts minimal branding, including ‘NIKE’ stitched across the heel tab and the Nike label on the tongue.

Something our experts love is the off-white color of the midsole, which gives the sneaker a worn-in, vintage appearance. The Nike Dunk Low Athletic Department Deep Jungle was released on October 1, 2023, and retailed at $110.

name: Sporty & Rich Brown
title: adidas Handball Spezial Sporty & Rich Brown
description:
The adidas Handball Spezial Sporty & Rich Brown upgrades the original Handball Spezial from 1979 with a primarily suede upper and a brown and gum colorway.

The base is brown suede with tonal suede overlays that give the sneaker a premium feel. White leather on the 3-Stripes logo and the heel tab breaks up the brown base and provides a contrast in texture. Brown laces wind through the eyelets and offer a secure front closure. Unlike other Handball Spezial models, the "Sporty & Rich Brown" version doesn’t display the traditional woven logo tag on the tongue. Instead, the tag is a thin, rectangular box with "sporty & rich" spelled in white letters.

Our StockX experts like the gum rubber sole, which adds traction and reminds the wearer of the Handball Spezial’s retro roots. The adidas Handball Spezial Sporty & Rich Brown was released on May 23, 2024, and sold for $100.

name: Blue Tint
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Blue Tint
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Blue Tint features a Blue Tint nylon upper with reflective graphics and details throughout the design. A thick black Boost sole and tongue adds the finishing touches to the hiking-inspired design.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Blue Tint released in July of 2021 and retailed for $220.

name: I Promise
title: Nike Zoom LeBron NXXT Gen I Promise
description:
The Nike Zoom LeBron NXXT Gen I Promise is a collaboration between Nike and Lebron James.

The Gen I Promise Nike Zoom LeBron NXXT arrives in a multi-color, multi-color color scheme. The shoe has an upper constructed with a lightweight, breathable mesh material and synthetic overlays for support and durability. The midsole is cushioned with Nike's Zoom Air system, which offers responsiveness and impact protection and ensures comfort. The outsole is made of a durable rubber compound with multidirectional traction patterns. In addition, the shoe features a lacing system that permits a customized fit and support. The sneaker features a Nike Swoosh on either side and a "NIKE Swoosh LBJ" inscription on the tongue.

The Nike Zoom LeBron NXXT Gen I Promise was released on February 10, 2023, and retailed for $160.

name: Bode Black Coconut Milk
title: Nike Astro Grabber SP Bode Black Coconut Milk
description:
