The Nike Astro Grabber SP Bode Black Coconut Milk is part of a collaboration between Nike and Bode, a New York City–based label known for its fine craftsmanship and sentimental connection to the past.

The sneaker updates the original football shoe from 1974 with premium materials and a retro colorway of black and Coconut. Although this version of the Astro Grabber replaces the original upper with suede and full-grain leather, the sneaker doesn’t lose its vintage aesthetic. For example, the outsole boasts a classic waffle-like pattern, designed for gripping the turf on slippery football fields. Like other collaborations between Bode and Nike, this sneaker hangs heritage charms from the laces. One charm is a silver baseball, while the other is a gold football.

Our experts like the Coconut Milk details on the Swoosh, the laces, the woven tongue tag, and the lining. The Nike Astro Grabber SP Bode Black Coconut Milk, a special project sneaker, was launched on May 1, 2024, and retailed for $160.

name: Light Carbon Monarch
title: Nike SB Dunk Low Light Carbon Monarch
description:
The Nike SB Dunk Low Light Carbon Monarch is a low-top sneaker featuring an all-suede fabrication. The upper features Light Carbon overlays on top of Monarch’s deep orange base, accented by the Swoosh in Sesame. Nike branding adorns the tongue and heel tab, while the Summit White and Dark Stucco mid- and outsole combination complete the color palette.

The Dunk Low is one of the American athletic wear brand Nike’s most iconic and recognized styles, which was first introduced as a canvas for college sports team colors. The Dunk found fans in skateboarders, and it is now frequently released as part of Nike SB, Nike’s skateboarding offshoot. The Light Carbon Monarch colorway is a limited edition release for the 2024 holiday season.

Our experts feel that the best feature of this design is its all-suede upper, which coordinates well with its unique colorway. The Nike SB Dunk Low Light Carbon Monarch was released on October 3, 2024, and retailed for $115.

name: Protection Pack Harbor Grey
title: New Balance 1906D Protection Pack Harbor Grey
description:
The New Balance 1906D Protection Pack Harbor Grey upper is made crafted with a mesh base in Castle Rock and Harbor Grey colorway. 

The sneaker features layers of TPU detailing and hacked suede materials at the heel. The tongue features stitched hacked leather accents with an embossed New Balance logo. The rubber outsole supports the ABZORB midsole and SBS heel insert. Additionally, its overlays are made of hairy ripstop, while its midsole is constructed of N-Ergy technology. The "N" logo is embroidered on both lateral sides of the sneaker, completing its appearance.

The New Balance 1906D Protection Pack Harbor Grey debuted on January 6th, 2023, and retailed at $160.

name: Black Pink Ribbon Laces (Women's)
title: adidas Samba OG Black Pink Ribbon Laces (Women's)
description:
The adidas Samba OG Black Pink Ribbon Laces (Women's) adds Satin Pink ribbons that give the sneaker’s black leather upper a luxurious feel.

Although the Samba OG has soccer roots, the "Black Pink Ribbon Laces (Women’s)" version goes beyond its sports heritage. The all-leather upper comes in black and features tonal overlays at the toebox and tonal stitching. The signature 3-Stripes and the leather heel mustache display a warm beige that complements the pink ribbon laces. Threading through eyelets in the leather upper, the pink ribbons resemble ballet shoe laces and have a silky feel.

Our experts like the metallic silver adidas branding on the leather tongue because it adds to the sneaker’s luxurious feel and matches the crisp ‘SAMBA’ lettering in gold foil. The women's size adidas Samba OG Black Pink Ribbon Laces (Women's) was originally launched on May 1, 2024, and were offered for $100.

name: Salt
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Salt
description: Keep those haters salty by copping the adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Salt. This Yeezy Boost 700 comes with a salt upper, salt midsole, and a salt sole. These sneakers released in February 2019 and retailed for $300. Don't be salty if you missed the general release, just buy them now on StockX.

name: Beef and Broccoli
title: Nike Air Max 1 Beef and Broccoli
description:
The Nike Air Max 1 Beef and Broccoli is a sneaker whose colorway takes its name from the popular Chinese take-out dish.

This iteration of the Nike Air Max 1 is made with an Outdoor Green mesh base on the upper. Suede in different shades of brown provides overlays around the entire bottom of the shoe, above the sole, across the midsole, and running up to the laces. The Nike Swoosh appears in Outdoor Green on the midsole, while the heel is a darker shade of brown and also contains a Nike Swoosh. There is also a brown logo patch on the tongue, and a visible Air Max unit under the heel embedded in the black rubber outsole.

Our favorite feature of these shoes is the two-tone cable laces, which add to the outdoor aesthetic of these shoes. The Nike Air Max 1 Beef and Broccoli was released on February 20, 2024, for a retail price of $140.

name: Neon Nights
title: New Balance 1906R Neon Nights
description:
The New Balance 1906R Neon Nights sneakers are not the norm for New Balance shoe design. While New Balance tends to stick to a more subtle color palette for its sneaker designs, they decided to go in a radically different direction for this colorful release.

Unlike many of the other New Balance sneakers, the 1906R Neon Nights feature a mesh and leather upper with a black base that includes several bright pops of color. Some of the other colors used to bring this New Balance shoe together are blue, pink, purple, green, orange, and yellow.

What our experts love most about New Balance 1906R Neon Nights sits just below the surface of this colorful shoe. It has an ABZORB midsole for added comfort along with a Stability Web outsole that delivers plenty of support. The New Balance 1906R Neon Nights was released on 17th December 2022 for $155.

name: Collegiate Navy Clear Sky Gum (GS)
title: adidas Handball Spezial Collegiate Navy Clear Sky Gum (GS)
description:
The adidas Handball Spezial Collegiate Navy Clear Sky Gum (GS) updates the classic Handball Spezial silhouette with an all-suede upper and a blue-on-blue colorway.

Originally designed as an indoor handball shoe, this low-top sneaker takes elements from its sporty heritage and gives them a modern twist. For instance, the sneaker boasts a gum rubber outsole that provides superior traction on indoor surfaces like hardwood. When compared to the Samba, the Handball Spezial has a thicker sole that provides extra cushioning. However, dark Collegiate Navy suede replaces traditional nubuck on the upper for a soft feel. Pops of Clear Sky decorate the serrated 3-Stripes logo, the tongue’s retro-inspired adidas branding, and the leather heel mustache.

Our experts like the gentle contrast between the Collegiate Navy and the Clear Sky. These hues bring out the texture of both the leather and suede, giving the sneaker a luxe appearance. The grade school–sized adidas Handball Spezial Collegiate Navy Clear Sky Gum (GS) was released on July 10, 2024, and retailed at $90.

name: Black White
title: New Balance Numeric 480 Black White
description:
A simple, classic, and lightweight unisex skateboarding shoe, the New Balance Numeric 480 Black White brings a clean look to life on and off your board. 

Inspired by skaters from the 80s, these sneakers are designed for hard use. Tough and durable, although extremely lightweight at only 480 grams, they are made with FuelCell foam to add propulsion to every step. The round toe cap is reinforced and ventilated with tiny holes. Made with a black and white color combination, the rubber outsoles pop in the brown signature NB style. A lightweight, breathable upper with a black lace enclosure gives you a comfortable shoe for leisure or sport.

We love the versatility of these classic 480s. In an evergreen color palette that matches your whole wardrobe, sporty never looked this good. The New Balance Numeric 480 Black White was released on 1 July 2024, priced at $100.

name: White Black Gum
title: adidas Samba XLG White Black Gum
description:
The adidas Samba XLG White Black Gum is a version of the iconic football-turned-streetwear shoe with extra-large detailing for a stylish look.

This iteration of the adidas Samba XLG is made with a leather upper. The upper is white and features a beige suede overlay covering the toebox and running up through the center to the laces. The iconic three stripes are formed on the midsoles in black leather, and the heel collar is also black leather. "SAMBA" appears in gold lettering on the lateral midsole above the first black stripe. The cushioned tongue also features a black adidas logo patch. The traditional chunky gum rubber outsole is flat.

Our favorite feature of this shoe is the extra-large detailing on the tongue and the large outsole. These elements give the shoe a bolder look, so they stand out with any outfit. The adidas Samba XLG White Black Gum was released on August 16, 2023, for a retail price of $110.

name: Light Orewood Brown
title: Nike Dunk Low Premium Light Orewood Brown
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Premium Light Orewood Brown dons the classic Dunk Low low-top silhouette and features a Light Orewood Brown colorway, creating a warm and earthy aesthetic.

The Light Orewood Brown Nike Dunk Low Premium boasts a subtle ivory tone on its upper, which is crafted from breathable canvas and accented with leather overlays at the forefoot and heel. Nike's branding is tastefully incorporated, adorning both the woven tongue tag and the rear tab. The low-top Dunk Low is set atop a cream-colored cup sole, complete with an internal foam wedge for added comfort, and a rubber outsole providing traction and grip.

Our experts say the Nike Dunk Low Premium Light Orewood Brown colorway is the best feature, with a rich and sophisticated appearance. The Light Orewood Brown hue adds a touch of elegance to the classic Dunk Low silhouette, making it a stylish and versatile choice for people who appreciate a classic design with a contemporary twist. The shoe was released on August 30th, 2023, for $120.

name: Core Blue Cream White Gum
title: adidas Handball Spezial Core Blue Cream White Gum
description:
The adidas Handball Spezial Core Blue Cream White Gum adds a soft colorway that highlights the sneaker’s athletic heritage.

Although the silhouette was originally released in the 1970s, this version of the Spezial features contemporary upgrades. For example, the Core Blue upper is made of durable synthetic material instead of suede. This material is more breathable and lighter than traditional suede. However, the sneaker still displays the signature serrated 3-Stripes logo in Cream White and the metallic SPEZIAL lettering. In addition, the collar comes in Cream White; however, the retro-inspired woven tongue tag boasts a Crystal White background. The tag reads "adidas HANDBALL SPEZIAL" and comes with a trefoil logo.

Our experts at StockX like the inclusion of the natural gum rubber outsole because it hearkens back to the sneaker’s design roots. The adidas Handball Spezial Core Blue Cream White Gum was released on March 15, 2024, and retailed at $110.

name: Active Pink Blue Burst (Women's)
title: adidas Gazelle Bold Active Pink Blue Burst (Women's)
description:
The adidas Gazelle Bold Active Pink Blue Burst (Women's) adds an Active Pink base and Semi Blue Burst accents to the platformed Gazelle Bold silhouette.

Like other Gazelle Bold models, the Active Pink Blue Burst version features three layers of stacked gum rubber underfoot. The top two layers come in light gum, while the bottom layer is darker. Beneath the heel, "adidas" is debossed on each layer. Sticking to OG Gazelle roots, the upper is crafted from suede in Active Pink, with tonal suede on the T-shaped toebox overlay. The serrated 3-Stripes and the heel tab come in Semi Blue Burst, which contrasts the base. The front lace closure provides an adjustable fit, while the laces are dyed Active Pink.

Our experts at StockX like the heritage adidas branding on the tongue logo tag. The women’s size adidas Gazelle Bold Active Pink Blue Burst (Women's) was released on December 15, 2023, and sold for $100.

name: Supreme Sail
title: Nike SB Darwin Low Supreme Sail
description:
The Nike SB Darwin Low Supreme Sail is part of a collaboration between Nike Skateboarding and Supreme, a New York City–based luxury streetwear label known for its connection to skater culture.

This sneaker is a revival of the Nike Darwin, a basketball shoe designed by Tinker Hatfield that features a low-top silhouette and skater upgrades. The upper is made from durable canvas in Sail, allowing the foot to breathe while providing flexibility. Boarder Blue accents on the Swoosh, the "SUPREME" logo tag, the secured webbing eyelets, and the dual branding on the tongue add splashes of color to the upper. The shoe sits on a black polyurethane midsole but doesn’t display visible Air technology in the heel.

Our StockX experts like that the leather Swoosh on the heel is reversed. The Nike SB Darwin Low Supreme Sail was released on May 2, 2024, and sold for $118.

name: Bone Sparrow
title: New Balance 9060 Bone Sparrow
description:
The New Balance 9060 Bone Sparrow shoe, presenting in a natural inspired color scheme of bone and sparrow, boasts a chunky and bold silhouette and is designed for casual wear and light athletic activity.

When the New Balance 9060 was being designed, it sparked a new word: retrofuturism. And the evidence of that word is present in this low-top shoe that is packed with New Balance’s sneaker tech while ebbing and flowing "retro" and "futurism" styles. The primarily bone colored upper is made out of suede, mesh, and synthetic materials which all work together to ensure it looks and feels great. Two different tilted Ns, sporting sparrow colored accents, adorn the sides, while additional branding is on the heel and tongue.

We particularly like sneaker tech designed with comfort in mind, such as the brand’s ABZORB midsole, ABZORB SBS heel, and the translucent CR device on the heel. The New Balance 9060 Bone Sparrow retailed for $150 when it was released on October 28, 2024.

name: Jewell Loyd Dusty Cactus Lilac Bloom
title: Nike Air Zoom GT Cut 3 Jewell Loyd Dusty Cactus Lilac Bloom
description:
The Nike Air Zoom GT Cut 3 Jewell Loyd Dusty Cactus Lilac Bloom is an updated version of the Nike Air Zoom Greater Than (GT) Cut, originally seen in 2021. It features a vibrant colorway of Dusty Cactus and Lilac Bloom, plus a smiley face pattern.

This sneaker is part of a collaboration between Nike and WNBA player Jewell Loyd and finds inspiration in Justice, the son of the athlete’s best friend. The upper is made of soft, Dusty Cactus suede with textile overlays in Lilac Bloom. The overlays display a vibrant smiley face pattern with the signature Swoosh replacing the smile line. The upper sits on a full-length Zoom Air midsole, while Flywire cables in the lace closure system create a secure fit.

Our StockX experts like the motivational quote on the midsole: "ready, set, go!" The Nike Air Zoom GT Cut 3 Jewell Loyd Dusty Cactus Lilac Bloom was released on May 14, 2024, and retailed at $190.

name: Green Lucid Pink (Women's)
title: adidas Gazelle Bold Green Lucid Pink (Women's)
description:
The adidas Gazelle Bold Green Lucid Pink Womens is a women’s model that provides a new take on the original Gazelle shoe, which was initially launched in 1968. It features bright colors and the classic 3-Stripes on the side.

This adidas Gazelle model is made from a mixture of rubber, leather, and suede. It has a Dark Forest Green suede body, with bright pink suede and leather appearing on the back of the shoe. The sole and midsole are composed of three thick layers of white rubber that are meant to provide support. These shoes also come with Forest Green laces that are crisscrossed.

A feature of the adidas Gazelle Bold Green Lucid Pink Womens that our group of experts particularly likes is the white textured tongue that helps to make this model especially unique. This pair of shoes first was released for sale on June 1st, 2023, and its starting retail price began at $120.

name: Light Bone Dark Stucco (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Light Bone Dark Stucco (Women's)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Light Bone Dark Stucco (Women’s) is a low-top shoe with a retro design paying homage to the 80s.

This iteration of the Nike Dunk Low comes with a leather upper. The base at the midsole is an olive green color, while the perforated toebox sports a beige color. Light gray hemp overlays round out the toebox and stretch from the top of the laces around the heel. A hairy suede Nike Swoosh appears in a tan color on the midsoles, while the heel collar is a darker green. We find another smaller Nike Swoosh on the heel on the lateral side, and the Nike brand name in red on the heel. The tongue also sports a Nike branding patch. The gray and olive-toned rubber outsole completes the look.

What we like most about this shoe is the combination of materials used. The hemp, leather, and suede all give the shoe texture. The Nike Dunk Low Light Bone Dark Stucco (Women’s) was released on March 5, 2024, for a retail price of $135.

name: Black Gum
title: adidas Handball Spezial Black Gum
description:
The adidas Handball Spezial Black Gum takes on an original 1979 silhouette.​
​​
​The upper of this Spezial sneaker is made of black suede with a white heel tab in smooth leather. Metallic gold Spezial branding appears next to the 3-Stripes on the lateral side and metallic gold adidas branding adorns the white tongue patch. The sockliner is also smooth black leather and the insole is black with white adidas branding. A gum rubber outsole is for traction on hard courts.​
​​
​The adidas Handball Spezial Black Gum was first released on August 26th, 2020 for a retail price of $100.

name: Urawa (2023)
title: Nike Air Max 1 Urawa (2023)
description:
The Nike Air Max 1 Urawa (2023) is an updated version of the original Nike Air Max 1 Urawa. The OG model was launched in 2004 as part of a collaboration between Nike and one of the biggest football clubs in Japan, the Urawa Dragons.

While the original Urawa only retailed in Japan, the 2023 version was sold in the US. The 2023 Air Max Urawa variation features a mostly white colorway of Pure Platinum, White, Black, Sport Red, and Summit White, unlike its predecessor which came in a bright Jersey Red, White, Silver, and Deep Red. Other elements mirror the 2004 Urawa, including the placement of the overlays, the use of mesh in the upper, and the visible Air Sole unit in the midsole.

Our experts love the addition of bright red details on the eyelets near the collar and on the Air Sole unit to honor the original Urawa. The Nike Air Max 1 Urawa (2023) was released on October 3, 2023, and retailed at $160.

name: Bone White (2023)
title: adidas Yeezy 500 Bone White (2023)
description:
The adidas Yeezy 500 Bone White (2023) is part of the collaboration between adidas and Kanye West under his Yeezy brand. This collaboration ended in October 2022, making these products difficult to get a hold of.

This sneaker is part of the Yeezy 500 line, the only adidas shoes to contain adiPRENE technology for comfort and added bounce. The Yeezy 500 in Bone White (2023) arrives in a Bone White colorway, giving them a clean look. The upper is constructed of nylon mesh with suede and leather overlays. A crisscross lacing system completes the sneaker´s design.

What our StockX experts love most about this shoe is the uniquely shaped rubber sole. As this colorway is muted, the shape of the sole adds personality to the shoe, in addition to its performance-enhancing features. The adidas Yeezy 500 in Bone White (2023) was first released on August 7th, 2023, for a retail price of $210.

name: Tech Explosion
title: New Balance 1906A Tech Explosion
description:
The New Balance 1906A Tech Explosion gives the 1906A an exaggerated technical makeover with overlapping, deconstructed overlays in a variety of metallic and matte hues.

As New Balance digs into its retro catalog, the 1906A Tech Explosion joins the ranks of reimagined technical running shoes with early 2000s roots. It features a classic, white mesh base with exaggerated synthetic and genuine leather overlays in Silver Metallic, Gold Metallic, and Castlerock. Each overlay stands out against the base, highlighting the individual design details. Nylon ribbons in Castlerock thread through the New Balance "N" and hang over the midsole, giving the sneaker an unfinished look.

Our StockX experts like the yellow-orange stains on the white midsole. They elevate the sneaker beyond models with an entirely off-white midsole, and pay homage to the shoe’s retro design elements. The New Balance 1906A Tech Explosion was released on July 24, 2024, and sold for $170.

name: Oil Green Olive Aura
title: Nike Dunk Low Retro Premium Oil Green Olive Aura
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Retro Premium Oil Green Olive Aura is a sneaker that radiates a natural allure with its olive tones.

Constructed with a breathable textile base and smooth nubuck overlays, the Oil Green Olive Aura Nike Dunk Low Retro Premium upper boasts a distinctive texture. The entire upper is bathed in an Oil Green shade, while subtle pale green accents highlight branding elements, including the iconic Swoosh and the woven Nike tongue tag. Crafted with meticulous attention to detail, the shoe features a denim/canvas twill base with leather on the Swooshes and heel, complemented by suede overlays. Uniform tonal branding is present on the embroidered heel tab, tongue tag, and insoles. The design is finished with a sturdy rubber cupsole that showcases stitched sidewall construction, an interior foam wedge, and a light-colored rubber outsole.

The noteworthy characteristic of the Nike Dunk Low Retro Premium Oil Green Olive Aura lies in its distinctive color scheme and the harmonious blend of materials. This combination of colors and materials gives the shoe a unique and appealing aesthetic. The sneaker debuted for $120 on November 2nd, 2023.

name: Tom Sachs Field Brown
title: NikeCraft General Purpose Shoe Tom Sachs Field Brown
description:
Tom Sachs is continuing his partnership with Nike into 2023 with a new release of the NikeCraft General Purpose Shoe Tom Sachs in a Field Brown colorway. The Tom Sachs NikeCraft GPS silhouette was regarded as one of the best new models to release in 2022.

The NikeCraft Tom Sachs General Purpose Shoe is made up of a rich suede and breathable mesh and comes in a Field Brown colorway. A white Nike branded tag sits on top of the brown tongue with a black pull loop located on the tongue and heel of the sneaker.

The NikeCraft General Purpose Shoe Tom Sachs Field Brown released February 5, 2023, with a retail price of $110.

name: Maroon Almost Yellow
title: adidas Gazelle Indoor Maroon Almost Yellow
description:
The adidas Gazelle Indoor Maroon Almost Yellow evokes the shades of leaves changing color in the fall. It retains the classic profile of the original. This joins a long line of imaginative athleisure trainers offering strong visual appeal and everyday wearability.

Few shoes have enjoyed the enduring appeal of adidas Gazelle sneakers. This version has all its hallmark features. The low-profile suede upper is there, along with the almost translucent rubber sole containing foam cushioning. The colorway mixes the maroon of fall oak leaves with chocolate brown and, as promised, an "almost yellow" toe and lace panel.

We really like the sophisticated look of this shoe. There's no need to convince trainer fans of the Gazelle's desirability, and this version will add a luxury touch to one's collection. The trusty slip-resistant sole is still there, and the familiar model name is embroidered in gold next to the adidas 3-Stripes. The adidas Gazelle Indoor Maroon Almost Yellow was released on 27 July 2024, priced at $120.

name: Magnetic (Women's)
title: Nike Sabrina 1 Magnetic (Women's)
description:
The Nike Sabrina 1 Magnetic (Women's) is a women’s athletic shoe featuring a multilayered fabric upper with multiple patterns of embroidery and mesh. A white base is accented by Football Gray and black tones. The Nike Swoosh appears on both rear sides in solid and outline black. Sabrina Ionescu’s branding in black and white adorns the tongue and a black graphic wraps the heel into a lowercase letter i.

Inspired by WNBA player Sabrina Ionescu, the Sabrina 1 Magnetic features technical components like a Zoom Air panel at the forefoot and React foam for energy. As Ionescu’s first signature shoe, the Sabrina 1 Magnetic was inspired by her magnetism on the court, which uplifts her teammates and the game of basketball.

In our opinion, the best features of the Sabrina 1 are its multiple patterns and textures, which play upon each other to recall basketball court imagery. The Nike Sabrina 1 Magnetic (Women's) released on October 1, 2023, and retailed at $125.

name: Zyon
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Zyon
description:
Yeezy adds another colorway of its most well-known design with the adidas Yeezy 350 Zyon, now available on StockX. This 350 V2 dons a similar pattern as the Static colorway, only this time ditching a white side stripe and grey accents for a darker brown stripe and mocha hues.

This Yeezy 350 V2 is composed of a Zyon Primeknit upper with a dark tonal side stripe. A translucent Boost cushioned sole and cream interior completes the design. These sneakers released in March of 2020 and retailed for $220.

name: Black Graphite Grey
title: ASICS Gel-1130 Black Graphite Grey
description:
Celebrating the ninth installment of the GEL-1000 series, the ASICS Gel-1130 Black Graphite Gray sneaker reflects decades of design evolution.

The upper section of the Black Graphite ASICS Gel-1130 is crafted from over 20% recycled material, showcasing ASICS' dedication to sustainability. Its color scheme harmoniously blends black and Graphite Gray, presenting a versatile and modern aesthetic. The shoe has undergone a transformation, incorporating synthetic leather paneling to update its traditional materials and achieve a more contemporary aesthetic. With GEL technology in the heel, the shoe offers cushioning and comfort. The inclusion of a TRUSSIC support arch enhances stability.

The most prominent feature of the ASICS Gel-1130 Black Graphite Gray lies in its GEL technology embedded in the heel. This ensures enduring comfort, making the shoe an exceptional choice for both sports activities and everyday wear. The runner was originally sold for $80 on April 30th, 2022.

name: Hello Kitty (Women's)
title: adidas Gazelle Indoor Hello Kitty (Women's)
description:
In women's sizes, the adidas Gazelle Indoor Hello Kitty (Women's) is an athletic shoe crafted with a debossed bow print leather and suede upper in Core White, accented by a Core Black heel tab. Gazelle branding is printed next to the signature 3-Stripes in Red. Hello Kitty's face and signature Red bow appear on the rear heel and tab. Additional Hello Kitty branding appears on the tongue, accented by laces with three bows. 

adidas, the German athletic shoe brand producing iconic footwear styles since the 1940s, is known worldwide for its timeless footwear, with the Gazelle having been in rotation since 1966. Hello Kitty is an iconic character who is a worldwide phenomenon in her own right, beloved by fans since her introduction in 1975. adidas worked with Sanrio to create a Gazelle infused with Kitty's signature motifs.

In our opinion, the best feature of this shoe is its specialized lacing, which further extends its Hello Kitty aesthetic. The adidas Gazelle Indoor Hello Kitty (Women's) was released on October 1, 2024, and retailed at $120.

name: Dark Grey Black White
title: Nike Zoom Vomero 5 SE SP Dark Grey Black White
description:
The Nike Zoom Vomero 5 SE SP Dark Grey Black White grabs the viewer's attention with swooping lines, geometric patterns and radiating stripes that all come together to focus on the Nike logo in the center. This sneaker offers a combination of white leather and grey mesh that accentuates the chaotic design. "NIKE VOMERO 5" appears in bold text on the tongue.

Nike Zoom Vomero 5 SE SP Dark Grey Black White released in April of 2019 and retailed for $160. This Nike Zoom Vomero 5 SE SP colorway re-released in 2024.

name: Sky Blue
title: Nike Air Max Plus Sky Blue
description:
The Nike Air Max Plus Sky Blue is a sneaker that contains Tuned Air cushioning and stays true to the original design from 1998.

This iteration of the Nike Air Max Plus comes with a Sky Blue textile upper for flexibility and breathability. The blue starts light at the laces and fades to a darker blue at the bottom of the shoe. Energetic white lines snake down from the laces to the base of the upper in an eye-catching wavy pattern. The Nike Swoosh appears on the midsoles in white with a blue outline. White leather rounds out the base and heel, where you can find a yellow Tuned Air logo. There are visible Air Max units under the heel and forefoot.

What we like most about this shoe is the wavy, white lines that run across the entire upper, giving the shoe a unique look. The Nike Air Max Plus Sky Blue was released on March 15, 2024, for a price of $180.

name: Stone Taupe
title: adidas Yeezy 500 Stone Taupe
description:
The adidas Yeezy 500 Stone Taupe adds an all-beige colorway to the sleek Yeezy 500 silhouette. Despite the sneaker’s neutral design, reflective details break up the monotone colorway in low lighting.

This lifestyle Stone Taupe adidas Yeezy 500 fortifies the open cell mesh upper with overlapping leather and suede overlays. These overlays form a mudguard that wraps around the shoe and circular panels that reinforce the eyelets cut into the mesh upper. In terms of branding, the Ortholite sockliner displays dual adidas and Yeezy branding, while the adidas trefoil is also printed into the midsole. Crafted with adiPRENE+, the sculpted midsole and outsole almost resemble a topographical map and draw inspiration from the adidas KB8 3 from 1999.

Our experts at StockX like the oversized pull tab on the tongue, which helps put on and take off the close-fitting sneaker. The adidas Yeezy 500 Stone Taupe was released on March 18, 2024, and sold for $210.

name: Gore-Tex Infrared
title: Nike Air Max 90 Gore-Tex Infrared
description:
The Nike Air Max 90 Gore-Tex Infrared is a sneaker made with Air Max units and waterproof technology.

This iteration of the Nike Air Max 90 features an upper made of Gore-Tex, a waterproof and breathable fabric, and lightweight mesh. The base is white, while leather and synthetic overlays in light gray round out the toebox and run up to the top of the laces. The Nike Swoosh appears in dark gray on the midsoles. Black overlays run up both sides of the shoe above the outsole with small red boxes featuring the Gore-Tex logo. The Nike Air logo appears on the heel, while the tongue contains a red Gore-Tex logo. The thick red and white outsole contains visible Air Max units under the heel.

What we like most about this shoe is the black overlay that runs up each side above the outsole, which gives the shoe a thinner and more streamlined look. The Nike Air Max 90 Gore-Tex Infrared was released on January 11, 2024, for a price of $160.

name: Core Black White (Women's)
title: adidas Gazelle Bold Core Black White (Women's)
description:
The adidas Gazelle Bold Core Black White (Women's) updates the OG Gazelle sneaker that was released in 1996 with a triple-stacked outsole made of gum.

The Gazelle Bold Core Black and White pays homage to the OG shoe through the use of premium suede and the incorporation of the T-toe overlay. Gold lettering spelling out ‘Gazelle’ graces the side panel, following the line of the serrated 3 stripes. The sneaker features a colorway of Core Black, Footwear White and Core White. The front lace-up closure, the 3 stripes, the texturized tongue, and the leather heel tab come in Core white and contrast the black base.

Something our StockX experts love is the way the T-toe overlay matches the hue of the upper, which differs from the OG models. The women’s size adidas Gazelle Bold Core Black White (Women's) was released on January 23, 2023, and retailed at $120.

name: Moonbeam Outerspace (Women's)
title: New Balance 327 Moonbeam Outerspace (Women's)
description:
The New Balance 327 Moonbeam Outerspace (W) arrives in a moonbeam, outerspace colorway.

The New Balance 327 Moonbeam Outerspace for women features a white and gray color scheme. The shoe features an upper that is constructed of a combination of suede and white leather with gray detailing. The shoe's upper has embroidered branding and a distinctive N emblem. The midsole is made of lightweight EVA foam for cushioning and shock absorption, while the rubber outsole delivers traction and grip.

The New Balance 327 Moonbeam Outerspace (W) was released on February 1st, 2021, and sold for a retail price of $90.

name: Footwear White Green
title: adidas Samba OG Footwear White Green
description:
The adidas Samba OG Footwear White Green adorns the classic low-top OG silhouette in a color scheme of footwear white, green, and supplier color.

The ‘Footwear White Green’ adidas Samba OG features an upper constructed from leather material, which offers longevity. The sneaker features branding details including the signature adidas Three Stripes logo on the side panels, the "SAMBA" wordmark on one side panel, and the Trefoil logo on the tongue. The padded collar offers comfort and support. In addition, the shoe's midsole is cushioned to provide impact protection and responsive cushioning. The shoe's sturdy rubber outsole provides traction.

What we love about this sneaker is its striking green accents on the signature three stripes and the heel tab, adding a vibrant pop of color and making it the most notable feature of the shoe. The adidas Samba OG Footwear White Green was released on May 18, 2023, and sold at an initial price of $120.

name: Linen
title: New Balance 2002R Linen
description:
The New Balance 2002R Linen is a reimagined version of the sneakers from the early 2000s with a unique texture.

This iteration of the New Balance 2002R is made with an off-white mesh upper. Mesh dominates the toe box and the sides of the shoe, while the rest of the design is formed by suede overlays. Off-white hairy suede rounds out the toe box and runs under the laces from the top to the sole in several layers. Gray hairy suede appears around the top of the laces, while a wavy strip of off-white suede runs in waves back around the heel. The signature New Balance "N" appears in white on each side outlined in metallic silver, and the heel features an NB logo. The heel is also perforated for breathability. The tongue features a logo patch and 2002R branding can be found on the lateral heel. The shoe sits atop an off-white sole.

What we like best about this shoe are the hairy suede overlays that are reminiscent of the texture of linen, adding a unique touch. The New Balance 2002R Linen was released on December 13, 2023, for a price of $145.

name: Black Anthracite (Women's)
title: Nike Free Metcon 5 Black Anthracite (Women's)
description:
The Nike Free Metcon 5 Black Anthracite (Women's) takes a silhouette designed for the ultimate training workout, dresses it in black and white color blocking, and sizes it specifically for women.

The upper of the Women’s Black Anthracite Nike Free Metcon 5 is constructed of lightweight, breathable black mesh that offers a sock-like feel due to its 7/8-length black inner sleeve. A collar padded with plush foam adds comfort and facilitates entry into this shoe. Synthetic overlays offer foot support during your workouts, while the wide heel offers a solid base for lifting. The white foam midsole provides a soft core of cushioning with a stiff outer layer for stability. Nike free technology in the forefoot allows for agility and flexibility when doing burpees, sprints, and planks. Black and white rubber tread in the outsole delivers durable traction.

The standout feature on this shoe is the internal webbing of the upper that distributes pressure around the midfoot to provide secure comfort during quick cuts and sudden stops. The Nike Free Metcon 5 Black Anthracite (Women's) was released on April 6th, 2023, for $129.00 retail.

name: CO.JP What The (2024)
title: Nike Dunk Low QS CO.JP What The (2024)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low QS COJP What The (2024) is a colorful and stylish low-top sneaker. This retro-style shoe pays homage to Nike's basketball shoe from the 1980s. Some of its style features include a perforated toe and white midsole. It is made of a combination of real and synthetic leather for comfort, breathability, and durability.

A product of Nike, these sneakers are made for action. Whether skateboarding, hooping, or just strolling the boardwalk, their rubber outsole gives you the traction, comfort, and support you'll need to keep having fun.

The Nike Dunk Low QS COJP What The (2024) features the iconic Swoosh symbol associated with the Nike product line. The Nike name is also on the back of the shoe. Our team most appreciates the rainbow of colors in its sneaker design. The palette includes maize/yellow, red, orange, and royal blue. Nike released this shoe on October 18, 2024, for $125.

name: Day One Soft Pink
title: Nike Ja 1 Day One Soft Pink
description:
The Nike Ja 1 Day One Soft Pink is a collaboration between the iconic sneaker company in NBA star Ja Morant. This particular sneaker in the collaboration combines colors and textures in a stylish and comfortable high-performance sports shoe.

The Day One Soft Pink iteration of the Nike Ja 1 has an upper with a base of soft pink mesh overlaid with tonal leather. A red ripstop covers the heel along with a yellow TPU band that connects the two dark gray side panel Nike swooshes. Gray also appears on the mesh sock liner and tongue lining. The insole is pink, the midsole is ice blue foam, and the outsole is translucent rubber patterned for traction and impact absorption.

What our experts enjoy most about this sneaker are all the hits of Ja Morant branding. The heel sports his signature, his number 12, and the words 12 AM—a nod to his round-the-clock training with his dad. The tongue tag and the insoles each feature his logo. The Nike Ja 1 Day One Soft Pink was released on October 1, 2023, for $120 retail.

name: Anthracite
title: Nike Dunk Low Anthracite
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Anthracite dresses this iconic silhouette in a fusion of textures, colors, and fabrics to create an arresting sports shoe with style and dependable construction.

The Anthracite colorway of the Nike Dunk Low-Top sports a cool gray upper, where the side panel, tongue, and collar are constructed of ripstop and the toe box is crafted from nubuck leather with perforations. Black nubuck leather overlays grace the toe box, vamp, eye stays, collar, and heal. The insole and sock liner are black, matching the laces and foam midsole with cupsole construction. The outsole is translucent blue rubber patterned for traction and impact absorption.

What delights us most about this sneaker are the hits of branding. The side panel Nike swoosh is white with a 3M reflective finish. White Nike branding is embroidered on the heel, and white Nike branding with a swoosh adorns the tongue tag and insole. Nike branding with a Swoosh is also embossed on the outsole. The Nike Dunk Low Anthracite was released on November 14, 2023, for a retail price of $125.

name: Collegiate Green Gum
title: adidas Gazelle Indoor Collegiate Green Gum
description:
The adidas Gazelle Indoor Collegiate Green Gum applies a varsity-inspired colorway to the classic Gazelle Indoor silhouette.

Originally designed as an indoor training shoe, the "Collegiate Green Gum" version of the adidas Gazelle Indoor features a soft suede upper in Collegiate Green. A T-shaped toebox protects the toe area and comes in tonal Collegiate Green. The serrated 3-Stripes logo, heel tab, and collar lining feature Footwear White leather. Branding details include ‘Gazelle’ printed along the 3-Stripes logo in Metallic Gold lettering and a trefoil decorating the heel tab. Something that stands out is the semi-transparent gum rubber outsole. It adds softness to the design and reveals the 3-Stripes logo under the outsole.

Our StockX experts like the bold trefoil on the tongue’s logo tag, which speaks to the sneaker’s retro roots. The adidas Gazelle Indoor Collegiate Green Gum was released on April 1st, 2022, and retailed at $100.

name: Pink Fusion (Women's)
title: adidas Campus 00s Pink Fusion (Women's)
description:
The adidas Campus 00s Pink Fusion (Women's) shoes were released for the 2023 summer season. They preserve the classic legacy of the adidas campus in a simple design with a touch of urban culture.

A pink fusion colorway is dominantly featured on the adidas Campus 00s for women. It first appears the suede material present on the suede upper of this shoe. Additionally, it is present on the quarter panels, which are adorned by zigzag-edged three adidas stripes in a cloudy white hue and debossed CAMPUS branding. The eye stay overlays are also pink, as are the laces and the well-padded tongue with an embossed Trefoil logo. The heel uses this primary color, but on the counter is a cloudy white Trefoil.

Our experts adore the two-tone color scheme in the adidas Campus 00s Pink Fusion (Women's). Its plain white outsole with a textured finish makes the shoe stand out. adidas released it on May 1st, 2023 with a price tag of $110.

name: Easter Celebration
title: Nike Air Max 1 Easter Celebration
description:
The Nike Air Max 1 Easter Celebration is a modern iteration of this classic sneaker with an eye-catching colorway.

This iteration of the Nike Air Max 1 is made with a white mesh upper for breathability. The upper is covered by hairy suede overlays in different shades of light and dark green. The dark green suede rounds out the bottom of the shoe above the sole, stretching from the heel down the lateral side and around the toe. The leather midfoot panels in Light Soft Pink contain a light green Nike Swoosh on each side. The Nike Air logo appears on the heel, and the tongue contains a Nike Air Max patch. A visible Air Max unit sits under the heel within the Speckled White outsole.

Our favorite feature on this shoe is the white outsole decorated with black speckles. It adds a nice modern touch to the overall design. The Nike Air Max 1 Easter Celebration was released on March 29, 2024, for a retail price of $160.

name: Hyper Pink
title: Nike Zoom GT Cut 2 Hyper Pink
description:
The Nike Zoom GT Cut 2 Hyper Pink is part of the second edition of Nike’s Greater Than (GT) series with a focus on Air Zoom technology. As the name implies, this high-performance basketball shoe is designed for cutting across the court and changing directions quickly.

The sneaker features a Zoom Air unit in the heel and another layered beneath the upper. When combined with the supportive insole, these cushioning units allow for increased responsiveness. A vibrant pink colorway featuring Hyper Pink, Fierce Pink, Pearl Pink, and Gym Red covers the texturized knit upper while a darker Fireberry color makes the heel and tread stand out.

Something our experts love about this basketball shoe is the contrasting Swooshes on the side panel and the midsole. They face in opposite directions and create the appearance of movement, embodying the rapid "cut" motion that inspired the shoe’s name. The Nike Zoom GT Cut 2 Hyper Pink was released on August 10, 2023, and retailed at $170.

name: Blacktop Dark Moss
title: New Balance 9060 Blacktop Dark Moss
description:
The New Balance 9060 Blacktop Dark Moss fuses updated sneaker technology with aesthetics from the NB sneaker silhouettes from the early 2000s. The result is a retro-futuristic high-performance sports shoe with a Y2K vibe.

The Dark Moss colorway of the New Balance 9060 Blacktop features an upper with gray suede and olive-colored leather overlays undulating across a base of brown mesh. A gray leather N outlined in white adorns the quarter panel, while New Balance branding also appears on the lace locks, tongue tag, and heel. Olive green appears again on the sock liner, tongue lining, and translucent heel counter, which lends both style and support.

Our shoe experts particularly enjoy the high-octane sole unit of this sneaker. The midsole is dual-density ABZORB and SBS for ultimate cushioning and springy bounce. The outsole sports a split pod diamond pattern for impact absorption and traction. The New Balance 9060 Blacktop Dark Moss was released on November 22, 2023, for a retail price of $150.

name: Berlin
title: Nike Dunk Low Berlin
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Berlin is an athletic shoe with a low-top silhouette featuring a dark color palette. Off Noir leather forms the base, accented by Cool Grey for the Swoosh, heel tab and collar, laces, and midsole. Shiny patent overlays in Jade Horizon amp up the impact of the colorway, accented by a neon yellow Nike Swoosh circle overlaid on the heel tab branding. 

The Nike Dunk is one of the brand’s most storied shoes, evolving from outfitting college sports teams in school colors to a bargain shoe appropriated by skateboarders and further to a beloved classic famed for its endless color variations. The Berlin color palette pays homage to the German city’s history and nightlife scene.

In our opinion, the best feature of this iteration is its juxtaposition of leather finishes, which adds nuance to its dark colorway. The Nike Dunk Low Berlin was originally released on October 5, 2024, and retailed for $130.

name: Birch Dark Pewter
title: ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Birch Dark Pewter
description:
The ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Birch Dark Pewter is a reinterpretation of the Gel-Kayano 14, which finds inspiration in technical running shoes from the early 2000s.

Unlike its predecessors, the "Birch Dark Pewter" version features a sustainably dyed sock liner. This dyeing process requires 35 percent less water and reduces carbon emissions by up to 45 percent. The breathable mesh upper comes in Birch, while the synthetic leather overlays feature Dark Pewter with a metallic sheen. Like the original Gel-Kayano, this version includes responsive gel cushioning in the bulky midsole. The sneaker also features ASICS’ signature TRUSSTIC support system and a front lace closure. ASICS branding can be found on the tongue, the heel, and the insole.

Our StockX experts like the padding around the collar and on the tongue that contribute to the sneaker’s retro-inspired aesthetic. The ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Birch Dark Pewter was released on January 1st, 2024, and retailed at $150.

name: Black
title: Nike Air Max Goadome 865031 Black
description:
The trail boot-inspired Nike Air Max Goadome Black made its debut as part of the Nike Sportswear in November 2016.

Nike Air Max Goadome Black has a fully Black colorway. The boot is made of premium leather synthetic materials. Its upper features richly detailed leather and a Nike Air Max cushioning that ensures a clean, classic look with lasting comfort. The design is finished off by a waterproof finish and an aggressive outsole pattern that offers in and outdoor durability.

During its release in November 2016, the triple black colored Nike Air Max Goadome Black retailed at $170.

name: Sashiko
title: Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Sashiko
description:
The Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Sashiko dresses the classic long-distance running shoe silhouette to pay homage to the Japanese textile art of Sashiko—decorative and reinforcement stitching.

The Sashiko Nike Zoom Vomero 5 features an upper of light tan twill on the forefoot and tonal mesh on the side panel. Soft leather overlays in medium brown and orange land on the toe box, quarter panel, and heel, offering both style and support. A pale gray suede overlay adorns the eyestays, while dark brown leather forms the side-panel Nike Swoosh. A tan plastic cage at the midfoot and again at the heel provides stability as well as ventilation. This upper with an artisanal vibe rests atop a sail-colored foam midsole with Zoom Air for durable cushioning and a dark brown rubber outsole lugged for impact absorption and traction.

The most enjoyable and eye-catching aspect of this shoe is the Sashiko stitching on the blue denim collar. This decorative stitching is echoed throughout the upper by the noticeable stitching on the leather overlays. The Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Sashiko was released on December 30, 2023, for $170 retail.

name: Raincloud
title: New Balance 530 Raincloud
description:
The New Balance 530 Raincloud continues the legacy of the original 530 which debuted in 1992. The "Raincloud" takes the performance sneaker’s bulky silhouette and adds a grey-tone color scheme.

The Raincloud, Grey, and White colorway is inspired by the hue of a raincloud just before it pours and is similar to the color scheme found on several New Balance 990s. The sneaker features a breathable mesh upper with soft suede overlays in a complementing grey. The New Balance ‘N’ graces the side panel, while ‘530’ can be found next to the heel overlay. The bulky ABZORB midsole gives the sneaker a ‘90s look and cushions against impact. The rubber outsole provides traction that grips the ground without decreasing flexibility. The "Raincloud" also comes with a padded tongue and collar, which add extra comfort.

Something our StockX experts love is the way the white midsole contrasts the small, black outsole. The New Balance 530 Raincloud was released on June 9, 2023, and retailed at $100.

name: Waffle
title: Nike Dunk Low Waffle
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Waffle applies a warm colorway of Coconut Mile, Sesame, Wheat, and Tonal Orange to the classic Nike Dunk Low silhouette.

Although the upper is made of suede, it’s molded into a grid-like waffle pattern across the quarter panel. This texture contrasts the fuzzy feel of the shaggy suede on the vamp and heel area. Like other models of the Dunk Low, the "Waffle" variation boasts perforations across the toebox. The smooth leather overlays create subtle color-blocking on the upper without distracting from the warm-tone theme. Both the laces and the Swoosh logos on the side panel come in off-white Coconut Milk, which stands out against the shaggy background.

Our StockX experts like the tongue logo tag, which features ‘NIKE’ and an orange Swoosh. It reminds the wearer of the heritage brand without distracting from the design. The Nike Dunk Low Waffle was released on February 17th, 2024, and retailed at $125.

name: Michigan State (GS)
title: Nike Dunk Low Michigan State (GS)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Spartan Green GS has as two dominant hues, the varsity green and white.

The leather upper of this Low Nike Dunk sneaker for grade-schoolers is white-hued. The white leather upper is contrasted by a green hue on the Swoosh logos as well as on the overlays. This same color combination is used on the rest of the shoe, with varsity green appearing on the middle section, laces, and the outsole, whereas a white hue is displayed on the midsole.

The Nike Dunk Low Spartan Green GS was recommended to retail at $100 when it was first released on May 3, 2021.

name: Valentine's Day (2023)
title: Nike Dunk Low Retro PRM Valentine's Day (2023)
description:
Nike is celebrating Valentine’s Day this year with the release of the Nike Dunk Low Retro PRM Valentine’s Day (2023). Nike’s 2023 Valentine’s Day collection consisted of the Dunk Low, Air Trainer 1, Uptempo 96, and Air Force 1 silhouettes.

The Nike Valentine’s Day Dunk Low has a burgundy and sail leather upper with a tumbled pink leather Swoosh. The limited edition sneakers have burgundy outsoles, a mesh sockliner, and is tied off with burgundy shoe laces.

The Nike Dunk Low Retro PRM Valentine’s Day (2023) released February 7, 2023 with a retail price of $120.

name: Cream
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Cream
description:
The luminous colored adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 has a cream white upper, core white midsole, and a camouflaged "SPLY-350" branding across the stripe on the sides.

These originally released in late April of 2017 with a retail price of $220 and restocked in September of 2018.

name: Valentine's Day (2024) (GS)
title: Nike Dunk Low Valentine's Day (2024) (GS)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Valentine's Day (2024) (GS) is a fun, vibrant sneaker specifically sized for grade school kids. With a colorway inspired by Valentine's Day, this shoe offers a warm, cozy style and classic sneaker construction.

The Grade School version of the Valentine's Day 2024 Nike Dunk Low-Top features an upper that is primarily vivid red. A base of rich red corduroy is overlaid with tonal textiles. The slightly oversized Nike swoosh is soft and fuzzy, and the color is a faint pink. We see this soft pink color again in the heel tab with red Nike embroidered branding. The white foam midsole features cup sole construction and deep red stitching that matches the deep red rubber outsole.

The aspect of this sneaker that delights us the most are the Valentine's Day details on the tongue tag and heel tab. The Nike Dunk Low Valentine's Day (2024) (GS) was released on February 4, 2024, for a retail price of $100.

name: Leopard (Women's)
title: adidas Campus 00s Leopard (Women's)
description:
The adidas Campus 00s Leopard (Women’s) is a sneaker whose design was inspired by the skate era of the 2000s, but with a modern shape and updated materials.

This version of the adidas Campus 00s is made with a smooth paneled leather upper. The upper is completely covered in leopard print, including on the overlays seen under the laces and on the tongue. The iconic adidas three stripes appear on the midsoles in a beige color, which is the only departure from the leopard print on the whole shoe. There is an adidas logo in black on the tongue, and another in black on the beige heel collar. The chunky rubber outsole is also beige, fitting nicely into the color scheme.

What we like most about this shoe is the smooth leather upper, which provides flexibility and comfort for the wearer during daily activities. The adidas Campus 00s Leopard (Women’s) was released on September 1, 2023, for a price of $110.

name: UCLA
title: Nike Dunk Low UCLA
description:
The Nike Dunk Low UCLA closely resembles the school colors used by the University of California Los Angeles.

The upper of the Nike Dunk Low UCLA is made of University Gold-colored leather. The sneaker’s upper part also features 'Blue Jay' leather overlays. The tongue of this shoe is golden colored and features blue detailing. The white midsole of this sneaker create an airy break from the combination of a gold-blue color that widely constitutes this shoe.

A matching blue outsole rounds off this sneaker. Nike Dunk Low UCLA will debut on August 9th, 2022 at a retail price of $100.

name: Platinum Tint Dark Obsidian
title: Nike Air Max 1 Platinum Tint Dark Obsidian
description:
The Nike Air Max 1 Platinum Tint Dark Obsidian updates the Air Max 1 silhouette with a gray-tone colorway of Platinum Tint, Wolf Gray, and Dark Obsidian.

The upper is made of breathable mesh with overlapping overlays and panels in Wolf Gray and Platinum Tint. Dark Obsidian can be found on the Swoosh logos, the eyelets, and the rubber outsole. In addition, the tongue’s ‘NIKE AIR MAX’ branding comes in Dark Obsidian. However, ‘NIKE AIR’ is embroidered on the heel in Wolf Gray thread. The sneaker features a slightly bulky silhouette due to padding around the collar and Air Max units in the midsole. The Air Max units provide responsive cushioning and can be seen through transparent windows in the heel.

Our experts at StockX like the color-blocking design on the side panels. The Nike Air Max 1 Platinum Tint Dark Obsidian was released on February 1st, 2024, and retailed for a price of $140.

name: Halloween Skull
title: Nike Air Force 1 Low Retro QS Halloween Skull
description:
The Nike Air Force 1 Low Retro QS Halloween Skull brings a haunting new twist to one of Nike’s most iconic models. Featuring a cracked red & black leather upper, this Halloween-inspired sneaker is both spooky and stylish. The skull theme continues with an embossed black skull on the toe box, while the custom insole showcases a series of skull graphics to enhance the Halloween vibe. This is one of the most unique Air Force 1 designs in recent memory.

The Halloween Skull edition of the Air Force 1 Low Retro retains the timeless shape and comfort the model is known for, but adds a seasonal twist with the eerie cracked leather and crimson accents. The deep red underlay beneath the black cracked leather adds a sinister touch, making this pair perfect for Halloween or any time you want to stand out with a bold look.

Released on October 24, 2024, the Nike Air Force 1 Low Retro QS Halloween Skull retailed for $130. With its sleek color scheme and spooky design, this limited-edition sneaker is a must-have for both Air Force 1 fans and those looking to make a statement this Halloween season.
model: Nike Air Force 1 Low Retro QS

name: Forrest Gump Cortez
title: Nike Book 1 Forrest Gump Cortez
description:
The Nike Book 1 Forrest Gump Cortez is a striking homage to the iconic sneaker worn by Tom Hanks in the beloved film. This men's shoe combines classic design elements with modern performance features, making it a must-have for sneaker enthusiasts and movie buffs alike. The white leather upper is accented with vibrant varsity red and blue details, perfectly capturing the essence of the original Cortez while adding a fresh twist.

Designed with both style and comfort in mind, the Nike Book 1 Forrest Gump Cortez features a cushioned midsole for all-day support and a durable rubber outsole for excellent traction. The sleek silhouette and timeless colorway make this sneaker versatile enough to pair with various outfits, from casual jeans to athletic wear. Whether you're a fan of the film or simply appreciate retro-inspired footwear, these shoes are sure to turn heads and spark conversations.

Us at StockX believe this product is great for those who value nostalgia and want to add a piece of pop culture history to their sneaker collection while enjoying the comfort and quality of modern Nike footwear.

name: Black Total Orange Mini Swoosh
title: Nike Dunk Low Black Total Orange Mini Swoosh
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Black Total Orange Mini Swoosh is a low-top sneaker in the Nike Dunk line.

The Dunk Low Black Total Orange Mini Swoosh features Total Orange accenting against a black and white base. The shoe's upper is constructed from leather, which provides durability and comfort. The toebox includes perforated detailing that improves breathability, allowing air to circulate to keep the feet fresh. The midsole is made of hard foam, providing exceptional comfort, support, and shock absorption. A rubber outsole offers adequate traction and stability, providing support and grip to the wearer.

We believe that the distinctive feature of the Nike Dunk Low Black Total Orange Mini Swoosh is the use of mini-Swoosh logos on the toe and tongue. These miniature Swooshes have a unique placement, making them visible only upon close observation of the shoe. The sneaker was released on July 29th, 2023, at a price of $110.

name: Pink Velvet (GS)
title: Nike Dunk Low Pink Velvet (GS)
description:
The kids Nike Dunk Low Pink Velvet (GS) features a white leather upper with pink leather overlays and metallic pink Swooshes. From there, a velvet Nike branded heel tab, woven tongue label, and pale pink semi translucent outsole completes the design.

The kids Nike Dunk Low Pink Velvet (GS) released in November of 2021 and retailed for $95.

name: Crepe Brown (2022)
title: Nike Air Max 1 Crepe Brown (2022)
description:
The Nike Air Max 1 Crepe Brown, also known as "Crepe Hemp" is re-releasing a classic 2004 three-piece pack colorway designed by Tinker Hatfield.

This Nike Air Max 1 Crepe is made of cream-colored hemp woven on the upper with a brown suede mudguard and tan nubuck overlays. The sneakers by Nike in Medium Brown, Mint Foam, Mushroom, and Muslin have a mint green signature Swoosh hue matching the Nike Air logo embroidered on the heel. Supporting the underfoot is the crepe outsole and off-white polyurethane midsole.

The Nike Air Max 1 Crepe Brown was first made available in September 2022, and retailed at a $180.

name: White Timberwolf
title: New Balance 550 White Timberwolf
description:
The New Balance 550 White Timberwolf updates the New Balance 550, originally launched in 1989, with a neutral color scheme and premium materials.

This understated sneaker taps into vintage New Balance aesthetics with a low-top design and a slightly bulky silhouette. The tri-tone colorway features White, Timberwolf, and Raincloud, making the sneaker stand out from other versions of the New Balance 550 that only showcase two colors. The soft suede upper boasts leather overlays and perforations along the side panel and toe. The padded collar cushions the ankle and complements the foam tongue. Branding details include the signature "N" patch and the 550 logo on the lateral side panel.

Our experts love the visible stitching across the shoe, creating a quilted look and making the overlays stand out against the upper. The New Balance 550 White Timberwolf was released on June 30th, 2023, and retailed at $120.

name: Navy Gum
title: Nike SB Dunk Low Navy Gum
description:
The Nike SB Dunk Low Navy Gum is a low-top skateboarding shoe that creates contrast between the navy upper and the Gum Light Brown outsole.

The navy upper and tonal overlays are made of leather that becomes softer over time, contributing to the sneaker’s retro look. A smattering of perforations across the vamp allows the foot to breathe and provides a design detail on the round toe. While the Swooshes on the side panels and the ‘NIKE’ stitching across the heel counter come in a Crisp White, the tongue houses a navy logo tag with a bright orange Swoosh. This orange tone can also be found on the tag on the underside of the tongue.

Our StockX experts like the use of Gum Light Brown on the rubber outsole. The hue is slightly more yellow than classic gum tones and makes for an unexpected addition. The Nike SB Dunk Low Navy Gum was released on April 6th, 2024, and retailed at $115.

name: White Black (Women's)
title: Nike Air Max 270 White Black (Women's)
description:
Among the variants of Nike Air Max 270, the women’s Nike Air Max 270 White Black is one of those that continues to attract the highest number of sales since its release.

The upper part of the shoe comprises of white and black woven and synthetic fabric. The elongated shoe tongue underneath the white cotton shoelaces is made of smooth white leather. The midsole and outsole of Nike Air Max 270 White Black (women) are both made of white rubber, with the outsole featuring bouncy properties.

The release date of the Nike Air Max 270 White Black (women) was on February 3, 2018. The shoe debuted at a price of $150.

name: Stone Marine
title: adidas Yeezy 450 Stone Marine
description:
The adidas Yeezy 450 Stone Marine dresses the minimalist, sock-like Yeezy 450 in an all-over Stone Marine colorway.

Featuring a one-piece knit build, the upper is crafted from Yeezy Primeknit. This material creates a supportive, locked-in feel while keeping the foot cool and dry. Instead of traditional laces, the Stone Marine adidas Yeezy 450 applies no-tie laces crafted from a stretchy material. They crisscross the upper and complement the ribbed ankle cuff. The polyurethane-injected foam midsole wraps around the upper, featuring indentations and curves that bring to mind stones worn away by water. The midsole supports the foot, while wavy lines on the rubber outsole provide traction.

Something our experts at StockX like is the minimal branding on the exterior. For example, ‘adidas’ lettering can be found on the outsole and the Ortholite sockliner. The adidas Yeezy 450 Stone Marine was released on August 5, 2024, and sold for $210.

name: Black Vegas Gold
title: Nike Air DT Max '96 Black Vegas Gold
description:
The Nike Air DT Max '96 Black Vegas Gold is a relaunch of Deion Sanders’ iconic silhouette from 1996. This time it returns in a flashy black and Vegas Gold colorway with a claw mark pattern covering the premium upper.

At the Black Vegas Gold Nike Air DT Max '96, the eye-catching color palette draws inspiration from the home jerseys worn by the University of Colorado at Boulder’s Colorado Buffalos, a football team coached by Sanders. Vegas Gold accents start from the midsole and claw their way up the upper’s black leather and synthetic leather. A midfoot strap displays a mini Swoosh in Vegas Gold and provides a secure closure over the black laces. Completing the look, visible Air Max units in the heel provide responsive cushioning and pay tribute to designer Tinker Hatfield.

Our experts at StockX like that the branding details, including the Swoosh logos, come in Vegas Gold, contributing to the luxe aesthetic. The Nike Air DT Max '96 Black Vegas Gold was released on September 2, 2024, and sold for $170.

name: Off-White Pine Green
title: Nike Air Force 1 Mid Off-White Pine Green
description:
Off-White and Nike are partnering together again on another Air Force 1 sneaker collaboration, with the release of the Nike Air Force 1 Mid Off-White Pine Green.

Nike’s Air Force 1 Mid Off-White Pine Green is constructed using green premium leather throughout the body of the sneaker. Nike used white accents, the sneakers branding, zip tie, Swooshes, and midsole. The sneakers draw inspiration from Track and Field shoes with a spike like design on the outsoles.

The Nike Air Force 1 Mid Off-White Pine Green released April 28, 2023, with a retail price of $205.

name: Paisley Pack Pink (Women's)
title: Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 Paisley Pack Pink (Women's)
description:
The Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 Paisley Pack Pink (Women's) embraces a soft, delicate pink shade. Designed by Bruce Kilgore, the '07 Paisley Pack Pink is often referred to as "Pink Paisley."

The shoe is adorned with a paisley print that extends across the iconic swoosh logo and the heel counter. It boasts a captivating colorway that is predominantly Pearl Pink, accentuated by touches of white and Coral Chalk. Crafted with a leather upper, this sneaker retains the enduring appeal of the classic Air Force 1 silhouette. Its fusion of style and technology includes Nike Air cushioning to deliver exceptional comfort for a lifestyle-focused design.

What our experts love about the Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 Paisley Pack Pink (Women's) is that it epitomizes a blend of timeless aesthetics and contemporary appeal. This makes it a standout choice for women who appreciate a combination of fashion and comfort in their footwear. The sneaker released 7th February 2023 for $100.

name: Bode Natural
title: Nike Astro Grabber SP Bode Natural
description:
The Nike Astro Grabber SP Bode Natural is part of a collaboration between Nike and Bode, a menswear label recognized for using heritage craftsmanship techniques and contemporary styles.

This sneaker is a reinterpretation of Nike sneakers from the 1970s with a focus on retro-inspired fonts, high-quality materials, and pops of color. The upper is made of a combination of mesh and suede in Light Cream or Natural. These neutral colors are so similar that they look almost the same but give the shoe depth of tone. Black Swoosh logos check across the side panels, while ‘BODE’ adorns the woven tongue tag in a curving font. Plastic charms featuring a red lobster, a pink dog, and a green airplane hang from the thin, cotton laces.

Our StockX experts like the rectangular designs on the rubber waffle outsole. The Nike Astro Grabber SP Bode Natural was released on May 5, 2024, and retailed at $160.

name: Vintage Navy (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low PRM Vintage Navy (Women's)
description:
Introducing a timeless classic with a fresh twist, the Nike Dunk Low PRM Vintage Navy (Women's) dropped and instantly became a must-have on August 24, 2023. This iteration of the beloved Dunk silhouette embraces refined leathers, spotlighting the Vintage Navy colorway.

This sneaker, with its signature Dunk structure, pairs navy contrasts on the heel, toe, outsole, and the renowned Nike Swoosh with the muted white center panels for an unmatched aesthetic. Beyond the visuals, what we absolutely adore is the sneaker's cushioned base, ensuring you step in comfort while turning heads.

Fresh, and fashionable, the Nike Dunk Low PRM Vintage Navy had an initial price tag of $120. Truly, a sneaker that encapsulates the present while nodding to the past.

name: Concord
title: Nike Dunk Low Concord
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Concord updates the classic Dunk Low silhouette with one of Nike’s most beloved colorways, Concord. This color falls somewhere between blue and purple and offers a deep, rich hue.

While the base construction comes in white leather, the color-blocking accents feature Concord. Specifically, the forefoot and heel overlays, the heel tab, the panels around the lace cage, the Swoosh logos, and the rubber outsole come in Concord. In addition, Concord can be found on the collar lining and the laces, although it looks slightly lighter due to the material. Like other versions of the Dunk Low, this sneaker has perforations across the vamp that allow the foot to breathe and a front lace closure that provides a secure fit.

Our StockX experts like the inclusion of insoles in University Red and white. The Nike Dunk Low Concord was released on April 1, 2024, and retailed at $115.

name: Sail Sea Glass
title: Nike Air Max 90 Terrascape Sail Sea Glass
description:
The Nike Air Max 90 Terrascape Sail Sea Glass features a Sail ripstop nylon upper with matching suede mudguards and black canvas Swooshes. At the base, a semi-translucent Air Max sole with recycled Nike Grind treads completes the design.

The Nike Air Max 90 Terrascape Sail Sea Glass released in October of 2021 and retailed for $140.

name: White Better Scarlet
title: adidas Samba OG White Better Scarlet
description:
The adidas Samba OG White Better Scarlet is a modern remake of the original adidas Samba that was first released in 1949. This model is primarily a bright white color and features pops of scarlet red.

This Samba OG White Better Scarlet is a low-top shoe that falls just under the ankle. The upper part of the shoe is made of soft leather in bright white, with tan colored suede overlays on the toe area. The 3-Stripes that are associated with the adidas Samba line appear on the side of the shoe in scarlet red.

A feature that our team particularly enjoys about the adidas Samba OG White Better Scarlet is dark brown gum sole that is made of rubber, as it is designed to provide both comfort and support. This model was originally made available for purchase in May 29th, 2023 and had a starting retail price of $120.

name: White Black
title: Nike Kyrie 8 White Black
description:
The Nike Kyrie 8 White Black is a basketball shoe with a black and white colorway that’s part of NBA player Kyrie Irving’s signature sneaker lineup with Nike.

The mixed-material upper features a marbled pattern with swirls and curving lines. It sits on a lightweight React foam midsole and Zoom Air Strobel. One of the standout details is Kyrie Irving’s signature embossed into the white midsole on the outer side panel. Other details include "Elizabeth Ann Irving" embossed near the toe, which pays tribute to Kyrie Irving’s mother, who passed away in 1996. The sneaker displays two Swoosh logos: a large Swoosh outline on the outer side and a small black Swoosh on the inner side, by the heel.

Our StockX experts like the light pink tone on the forefoot area of the rubber outsole. The Nike Kyrie 8 White Black was released on November 24, 2022, and sold for $140.

name: Dark Brown Tweed
title: adidas Samba OG Dark Brown Tweed
description:
The adidas Samba OG Dark Brown Tweed is an athletic shoe featuring a herringbone Brown Tweed fabric upper, contrasted by the 3-Stripes in Cream White. The heel tab coordinates with the branding, while the lace panel in Dark Brown matches the Tweed upper. The Trefoil logo appears on the tongue, and a textured Gum sole pulls it all together.

The German athletic wear monolith adidas has produced its iconic Samba style since 1949, when founder Adolf Dassler designed it. A well-recognized and classic staple of the adidas footwear roster, the Samba’s signature Gum sole coordinates well with this limited edition menswear-inspired rendition.

In our opinion, the best feature of the Samba OG Tweed is its Tweed upper, which elevates the sneaker into an innovative and versatile lifestyle shoe. The adidas Samba OG Dark Brown Tweed was originally released on September 5, 2024, and retailed at $100.

name: Platinum Varsity Red
title: Nike P-6000 Platinum Varsity Red
description:
The Nike P-6000 Platinum Varsity Red draws inspiration from the Pegasus 2006 and the Nike Air Pegasus 25 in order to create a stylish, comfortable, running shoe that evokes a vibe reminiscent of the early 2000s.

The Platinum Varsity Red colorway of the Nike P-6000 features an upper with a base of Snowy White mesh with a strip of black on the side panel, offering lightweight breathability. Synthetic leather overlays in white and pale gray course across the upper, from the toecap to the heel counter, providing support and a dynamic aesthetic. A molded red synthetic side-panel Nike Swoosh outlined in gold embroidery complements the hits of red in the white foam midsole that offers cushioning and impact absorption. The rubber outsole continues the colorway in black, white, gold, and red.

The aspect of this sneaker that we most enjoy are the nods to Nike co-founder and legendary track coach Bill Bowerman. The webbing on the tongue sports "Bowerman Series" branding and the outsole features a modified waffle traction pattern, an innovation originally designed by Bowerman. The Nike P-6000 Platinum Varsity Red was released on December 10, 2023, for $110 retail.

name: Baroque Brown (Women's)
title: Nike Cortez Baroque Brown (Women's)
description:
The Nike Cortez Baroque Brown (Women's) revamps the classic Cortez runner design with a contemporary colorway of Baroque Brown, Sail, and khaki.

Maintaining its 1972 retro appeal, the Baroque Brown (Women's) Nike Cortez boasts a soft foam midsole in Sail with a khaki-colored wedge beneath the heel. The jagged design on the rubber outsole represents another heritage detail and increases traction. Reinventing the design for contemporary audiences, the sneaker offers a wider toebox than the original for lasting comfort. Baroque Brown covers the shiny textile upper and the suede details on the toebox overlay, the heel counter, and the eyelets. On the other hand, splashes of Sail on the Swoosh logos, the laces, the tongue, the heel tab, and the rubber outsole provide subtle color-blocking and a premium feel.

Our experts like the way khaki balances the color combination and appears on the branding details. The women’s size Nike Cortez Baroque Brown (Women's) was released on April 2, 2024, and sold for $90.

name: Year of the Dragon (2024)
title: Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 Year of the Dragon (2024)
description:
The Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 Year of the Dragon (2024) is an AF1 classic silhouette that celebrates the Chinese New Year and ushers in the Year of the Dragon.

The Year of the Dragon 2024 iteration of the Nike Air Force 1 Low-Top '07 in a sail colorway features an upper of smooth sail leather with perforations in the toe box and along the quarter panel. Smooth sail leather overlays adorn the toe, eye stays, and collar. Patterned sail suede composes the Nike swoosh and heel tab. A vapor green mini swoosh appears on the mud guard and that same vapor green outlines the side panel swoosh. The white foam midsole encapsulates Nike Air and rests on a sail rubber outsole with a traction pattern designed for easy pivots.

The details of this singular sneaker that we appreciate the most are the decorative nods to the Chinese New Year, including a dragon lace charm, a Chinese-themed pattern on the tongue tag, and Chinese-themed graphics on the insoles and heel tab. The Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 Year of the Dragon (2024) was released on February 1, 2024, for $135 retail.

name: Black Dark Smoke Grey
title: Nike Air Max Dn Black Dark Smoke Grey
description:
The Nike Air Max Dn Black Dark Smoke Gray is a sneaker with a new and improved Dynamic Air cushioning system and a futuristic design.

This version of the Nike Air Max Dn comes in a black, Dark Smoke Gray, and Anthracite colorway. The textile upper is mostly black with sleek gray texturing patterns. The midsole is cushioned and supported with black overlays, while the Nike Swoosh appears in the arch of the foot on both sides. The Nike Swoosh also appears at the bottom of the laces. The toecap appears in shiny black, while the shiny black heel also contains a yellow Air Max logo. The same Air Max logo also appears in gray and black on the tongue. The Dynamic Air unit is visible under the heel in four transparent bubbles, while the black chunky rubber outsole completes the look.

What we like best about this shoe is the all-new Dynamic Air unit in the heel, which provides even more energy return during transitions. The Nike Air Max Dn Black Dark Smoke Gray was released on March 26, 2024, for a retail price of $160.

name: Black Grey
title: New Balance 1906R Black Grey
description:
The New Balance 1906R Black Gray finds inspiration in the technical running shoes from the early 2000s and features a black upper with shiny gray details.

One throwback feature is the overlay design on the mesh upper. The crisscrossing overlays create the illusion of movement and remind the wearer that the shoe was create for action. The sneaker boasts three noteworthy technical components: ABZORB SBS cushioning in the heel, an ACTEVA LITE midsole, and an N-ergy outsole. The midsole supports the foot, while the outsole absorbs shock, and the SBS cushioning adds stability. In addition, the stability web technology underfoot supports the arch. The upper is made of breathable mesh in black, while ribbon-like straps wind over the lace cage and form the ‘N’ on the side panel.

Our experts at StockX like the name "1960," which pays tribute to the year New Balance was created. The New Balance 1906R Black Gray was released on August 12th, 2023, and retailed at $150.

name: Knicks
title: Nike Dunk Low Knicks
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Knicks pays homage to Manhattan’s NBA team, the New York Knicks, through a vibrant colorway of Bright Ceramic and Team Royal that represents the team’s colors.

The Knicks Nike Dunk Low is one of several Nike shoes inspired by the Knicks’ team colors that create a connection with basketball culture and the NBA. Boasting an all-leather build, Bright Ceramic acts as the base color, while Team Royal covers the overlays, Swoosh logos, eyestays, heel tab, tongue label, laces, and inner lining. In addition, the rubber outsole also displays Team Royal, while Bright Ceramic letters spell out NIKE on the tongue and heel tab.
