Our experts at StockX like the choice of crisp white instead of off-white on the midsole. It gives the sneaker a clean look and keeps the aesthetic contemporary without retro influences. The Nike Dunk Low Knicks was released on May 1, 2024, and sold for $115.

name: Triple Black
title: New Balance 990v6 Triple Black
description:
The New Balance 990v6 Triple Black decks out the sixth version of the NB 990 in an all-black colorway and a mixed-material upper.

Launched to celebrate the 40th anniversary of the 990, the 990v6 boasts a sculpted midsole with ENCAP and FuelCell foam cushioning underfoot. The inclusion of FuelCell technology represents the latest evolution of the iconic 990 and helps propel the runner forward. The "Triple Black" colorway allows the sneaker’s technical upgrades to take center stage without distracting colors or motifs. In addition, the deep black hue makes the suede mudguard appear even more velvety against the mesh underlays.

Our experts like the reflective accents, which provide visibility in low lighting, and the metallic silver detailing on the heel and insole because they shine when compared to the "Triple Black" colorway. The New Balance 990v6 Triple Black was released on April 16, 2024, and sold for $199.

name: White Shamrock Green
title: ASICS GT-2160 White Shamrock Green
description:
The ASICS GT-2160 White Shamrock Green takes inspiration from the classic silhouette of the GT-2000 running shoe and updates the core elements for enhanced flexibility and cushioning.

The White Shamrock Green Iteration of the ASICS GT-2160 features an upper with a base of white mesh for breathability and a lightweight feel. Synthetic overlays in white, green, black, and silver coarse across the upper in signature ASICS patterning. Silver overlays adorn the toe cap, heel, and eye stays. GT-2160 branding appears in green on a black overlay on the lateral heel, GEL branding graces the heel tab, and ASICS branding adorns the white tongue tag and the white insole. The rubber outsole in gray and green is also segmented into pods on the heel and forefoot.

The feature of this shoe we appreciate most is the dual-segmented midsole that hearkens back to the early 2000s. GEL inserts in the foam under the heel and forefoot add superior cushioning with every step. The ASICS GT-2160 White Shamrock Green was launched on July 8, 2023, for a retail price of $130.

name: Dirty Denim
title: Nike Air Max 1 PRM Dirty Denim
description:
The Nike Air Max 1 PRM Mineral Slate is a sneaker with a Nike premium silhouette.

The Nike Air Max 1 PRM has a combination of mineral slate, deep royal blue, and lemon wash colorways. The upper part is made of suede with a denim overlay with flat cotton laces. The sneaker has a padded collar and TPU eyelets with a Nike Air Max woven patch and two Swoosh details, one on the side panel and the other embroidered on the toe. The visible midsole has been yellowed and complements the gum outsole to display a clear faux-vintage vibe.

The Nike Air Max 1 PRM Mineral Slate was released on the 26th of August retailing at $150.

name: Pale Ivory Black (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Disrupt 2 Pale Ivory Black (Women's)
description:
With a deconstructed aesthetic, the women's Nike Dunk Low Disrupt 2 Pale Ivory features a white mesh upper with light grey suede overlays and dual embroidered Swooshes. Oversized smooth leather heel shanks and woven tongue labels add a unique twist to the classic design. From there, a matching EVA foam sole adds the finishing touch.

The women's Nike Dunk Low Disrupt 2 Pale Ivory released in May of 2022 and retailed for $110.

name: Supreme Rammellzee
title: Nike SB Dunk Low Supreme Rammellzee
description:
Supreme has once again teamed up with Nike for another highly coveted SB Dunk Low. The Nike SB Dunk Low Supreme Rammellzee released on August 31st, 2023, for a retail price of $138. The sneaker sold out quickly at Supreme locations globally.​
​​
​This unique SB Dunk Low features the art of the late Rammellzee, who has collaborated with Supreme numerous times over the years, including way back in 2003. The New York artist lends his iconic style to the upper of this limited edition sneaker, which showcases his unique graffiti style motifs.​
​​
​The Nike SB Dunk Low Supreme Rammellzee dropped on August 31st, 2023, for a retail price of $138. Lock in your pair today on StockX.

name: White Carrier Grey Lilac (Women's)
title: ASICS Gel-1130 White Carrier Grey Lilac (Women's)
description:
The ASICS Gel-1130 White Carrier Grey Lilac (Women's) is a stability running shoe with a white base and crisscrossing overlays in Carrier Grey and white.

This version of the Gel-1130 draws inspiration from classic running shoes in the ASICS catalog, including the Gel-Kayano 14 and sneakers in the Gel-1000 series. The White Carrier Grey Lilac (Women's) ASICS Gel-1130 takes heritage design elements and updates them for a contemporary audience. For instance, synthetic leather replaces genuine leather on the upper, which increases the sneaker’s durability and allows the colors to appear brighter. Aerated mesh keeps the foot cool and provides an airy feel, while Gel technology in the heel gives support and smooth energy return.

Our experts like the subtle splashes of lilac on the midfoot arch because they add a pop of color without distracting from the sneaker’s technical design. The ASICS Gel-1130 White Carrier Grey Lilac (Women's) was released on June 1, 2024, and retailed for $95.

name: Tephra
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 V2 Tephra
description: If you’re looking for a tough sneaker then you need to buy the new adidas Yeezy Boost 700 V2 Tephra. This Yeezy Boost 700 V2 comes with a tephra upper, tephra midsole, and a tephra sole. These sneakers released in June 2019 and retailed for $300. Place a Bid for these Yeezys today on StockX.

name: Analog
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Analog
description: Yeezy is back from his Sunday Service Coachella performance with this new adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Analog. This Yeezy Boost 700 comes with a beige upper plus grey accents, three grey adidas stripes, beige midsole plus grey accents, and a black sole. These sneakers released in April 2019 and retailed for $300. Buy this Yeezy 700 on StockX ASAP.

name: 1 of 1
title: Puma LaMelo Ball LaFrancé Amour 1 of 1
description:
The Puma LaMelo Ball LaFrancé Amour 1 of 1 is an attractive, zany-looking trainer. The latest in the LaFrancé range, it's an upgrade that introduces LaMelo Bali's "Not From Here" NBA style. Its chunky design recalls the late Nineties sneaker trends.

These Puma trainers have a solid, dark pastel blue colorway, with shaded oval segments over the lace holes. They have bouncy, synthetic platform soles with EVA cushioning along the full length. The upper combines leather with a canvas base. For foot protection and stability, there's a full-wrap cup-sole.

We love the appearance of these trainers. They look like great fun to wear, not to mention seemingly indestructible. Little details have been added for convenience, too. The oversize laces are easy and quick to tie, plus there's a little handle at the back of the heel to pull them on and off. The Puma LaMelo Ball LaFrancé Amour 1 of 1 was released on September 12, 2024, priced at $110.

name: Christmas (2024)
title: Nike KD 4 Christmas (2024)
description:
The Nike KD 4 Christmas (2024) returns in time for the winter holiday season with a gleaming Metallic Copper upper and black accents.

First launched in 2011, this iteration stays true to the original Nike KD 4 "Christmas." The innovative basketball from NBA player Kevin Durant boasts a Hyperfuse upper—a lightweight, three-layer composite that supports stability and breathability. A wraparound strap with perforations contains the midfoot, while the front lace closure secures the fit. Although the upper comes in Metallic Copper, black accents decorate the Swoosh logo on the strap, a mini Swoosh on the toe box, "35" on the tongue, and "KD" branding on the heel. In addition, the grippy rubber outsole provides traction and comes in black.

Our experts at StockX like that the 2024 model is almost identical to the version from 2011, making it modern yet timeless. The Nike KD 4 Christmas (2024) was released on November 20, 2024, and sold for $130.

name: White Light Pumice
title: Nike Dunk Low SE White Light Pumice
description:
The Nike Dunk Low SE White Light Pumice is a low-top shoe with a color-blocking design and a subtle colorway.
   
The White Light Pumice Nike Dunk Low SE has a base of white leather. The white toebox features perforations for increased air flow, while the side panels and ankle collar also appear in white. Soft suede overlays in a Light Pumice gray color round out the toe and form the eyestays and the ankle strap. The Nike Swoosh can also be seen crossing each side as a Light Pumice overlay. The heel collar features the Nike brand name embroidered in white, and the tongue bears another Nike logo patch. The shoe sits on a white midsole and a Light Pumice outsole. 

What we like most about this sneaker is the simplistic design with a neutral colorway, which makes the shoe versatile. The Nike Dunk Low SE White Light Pumice was released on July 1, 2024, for $125.

name: Harbor Grey
title: New Balance 1906R Harbor Grey
description:
The New Balance 1906R Harbor Gray is a running shoe with a design inspired by the fashion era of the early 2000s.

This iteration of the New Balance 1906R is made with a mesh upper in dark gray. Synthetic overlays in metallic silver cross the entire upper, rounding out the toebox, crossing the midsole, and running up under the top of the heel. The New Balance N adorns both sides under the laces in a 3D paneled design with N-Lock branding appearing in the middle. 1906R branding can be found on the overlay on the lateral side of the heel. The heel is also supported by a silver TPU cage, which sports the NB logo. Another logo can be found on the tongue, while a patterned gray outsole completes the look.

What we like best about this shoe is the technological enhancements, like N-ergy and ABZORB cushioning, which improve the functionality of the shoe. The New Balance 1906R Harbor Gray was released on January 15, 2024, for a price of $155.

name: Granite
title: adidas Yeezy 500 Granite
description:
Composed of tonal grey mesh, suede, and leather, the adidas Yeezy 500 Granite offers a monochromatic styling similar to the early Yeezy 500s of 2018. Woven lace loops on the tongue nod to the tooling of 1990s hiking boots. From there, a sculptural sole with adiPrene cushioning provides comfort and support.

The adidas Yeezy 500 Granite released in May of 2022 and retailed for $210.

name: Drake NOCTA Champagne
title: Nike Hot Step Air Terra Drake NOCTA Champagne
description:
The Nike Hot Step Air Terra Drake NOCTA Champagne is part of Drake’s NOCTA collaboration with Nike. Like other sneakers in the NOCTA lineup, the NOCTA x Nike Hot Step Air Terra "Champagne" features premium materials, a sleek design, and attention to detail.

This sneaker boasts a leather construction with stitched lines and perforations across the upper. The mini-Swoosh in metallic gold, the gold panels by the heel, and the gold ‘G G-TEK’ logo on the heel break up the light bone base. The sneaker comes with a bulky midsole with a visible Nike Air unit in the heel. An outsole with texturized tread in a translucent grey-blue complements the light bone color of the leather upper.

Our experts at StockX love the lace-up front closure that secures the shoe without distracting from the overall design. The Nike Hot Step Air Terra Drake NOCTA Champagne was released on November 18, 2022, and retailed at $180.

name: Hi-Res Blue
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Hi-Res Blue
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Hi Res Blue has a base that appears in a bright blue color. Throughout the shoe, you will find details in purple, orange, black, and different shades of blue. It is made out of a combination of different materials, like leather, suede, and mesh.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Hi Res Bluehas a chunky sole that is decorated with orange accents. It is made with extra cushioning in order to provide the wearer with extra support and make the shoe durable. 

The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Hi Res Blue were first put onto the market in August of 2022. This shoe’s release price began at $300.

name: Dusted Clay (Women's)
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG SP Dusted Clay (Women's)
description:
The Jordan 1 Retro High OG SP Dusted Clay (Women's) is a Special Project sneaker, which means it’s made with premium suede and leather, and was designed in the NikeLab. This iteration of the Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG features a warm colorway of Dusted Clay, Cacao Wow, and Burnt Sunrise.

Like the original Air Jordan 1, this version boasts a high-top silhouette, perforations across the vamp, and the signature Swoosh logos on the side panels. What sets this sneaker apart is the color-blocked effect created by the Burnt Sunrise and Cacao Wow against the Dusted Clay base. Cacao Wow can be found on the mudguard, lining, collar, eyestays, and Swoosh logos. On the other hand, Burnt Sunrise is displayed around the collar, on the outsole, and across the heel panel.

Our StockX experts like the classic branding, including the Jordan Wings logo embossed on the heel and the woven tongue tag. The women’s size Jordan 1 Retro High OG SP Dusted Clay (Women's) was released on March 6th, 2024, and retailed at $200.

name: Off-White White
title: Nike Air Force 1 Mid Off-White White
description:
The Nike Air Force 1 Mid Off-White White honors the 40th Anniversary of the Nike Air Force 1 by refreshing the classic design with Abloh's signature avante-garde style. It features a white wood grain-textured, lightweight mesh construction with ripstop collar straps, and clear TPU Swooshes. At the base, a warped midsole with multi-colored sections of a track-inspired spiked outsole reference past Nike Off-White designs like the Nike Waffle Racer and Air Zoom Tempo Next%.

The Nike Air Force 1 Mid Off-White White released in June of 2022 and retailed for $185.

name: Gym Red Black Toe
title: Jordan 1 Mid Gym Red Black Toe
description:
The Jordan 1 Mid Gym Red Black Toe is a sneaker variation of the Air Jordan 1 model, which comes in a mid-top design.

The Gym Red Black Toe features a white leather upper that extends from the toebox to the heel with black synthetic layers around the midfoot. The shoe also has Gym Red overlays at the laces, sole, and ankle collar. It has a round toe that has perforations and a cushioned collar and tongue. The sneaker also features the Jordan brand logo on the tongue, with the Wings insignia embossed on the ankle collar. The Nike Swooshes can also be seen on both sides of the shoe. Moreover, the shoe has a soft inner lining with a branded insole.

We especially love the Jordan 1 Mid Gym Red Black Toe for the Gym Red Jumpman logo on the tongue. The sneaker was released on July 20th, 2023, at a retail price of $125.

name: Diamond Shorts
title: Jordan 1 Low Diamond Shorts
description:
The Jordan 1 Low Diamond Shorts features a black Durabuck and white leather upper in a classic color blocked format, similar to legendary Jordan 1s like the Bred and Shadow colorways. At the heel, an Air Jordan Wings logo nods to the origins of the Air Jordan line. A white midsole and semi-translucent outsole add the finishing touch.

The Jordan 1 Low Diamond Shorts released in February of 2022 and retailed for $120.

name: Light Smoke Grey
title: Jordan 1 Retro High Light Smoke Grey
description:
Jordan delivered another new colorway of their most popular silhouette with the Jordan 1 Retro High Light Smoke Grey, now available on StockX. Following a similar reconstructed design language as the Jordan 1 Union LA from 2018, this Jordan 1 utilizes color blocking and different materials to present familiar colors in a unique format.

The Jordan 1 High Light Smoke Grey is composed of a white leather upper with grey suede overlays and a red leather ankle panel. Black suede on the heel paneling and Swoosh, a white midsole, and black outsole completes the design. This Jordan 1 released in July of 2020 and retailed for $170 USD.

name: Wonder White Gum
title: adidas Campus 00s Wonder White Gum
description:
The adidas Campus 00s Wonder White Gum adds a neutral colorway of Wonder White and Cloud White to the bulky Campus 00s silhouette.

Inspired by the original adidas Campus designs, the Wonder White Gum Campus 00s has a bulkier silhouette reminiscent of skateboarding shoes from the early 2000s. Extra padding around the collar and in the tongue creates exaggerated proportions that set this version of the Campus 00s apart from other legacy adidas sneakers. The upper boasts premium leather in Wonder White with hits of Cloud White on the heel mustache and the serrated 3-Stripes logo. Perforations between each stripe in the 3-Stripes logo provide ventilation, while thick cotton laces match the shoe’s oversized proportions and thread through the front closure system.

Our experts like the 2000s-inspired adidas branding on the padded tongue, which features a stylized trefoil without adidas lettering. The adidas Campus 00s Wonder White Gum was released on May 1, 2024, and sold for $110.

name: Reverse Grape
title: Nike Air Max Plus Reverse Grape
description:
The Nike Air Max Plus Reverse Grape updates the iconic sneaker created by Sean McDowell with a purple gradient colorway. The smooth mesh upper fades from Disco Purple to white and back again.

Like other iterations of the Nike Air Max Plus, the "Reverse Grape" version features a black TPU cage that resembles ripples or waves. The TPU cage gives the upper structure and complements the black leather overlays and the shiny leather toecap. Teal Nebula outlines the small Swoosh logos on the side panels and adds a splash of color to the upper. Meanwhile, the visible Air Max units in the heel and forefoot come in Space Purple and Teal Nebula. They provide responsive cushioning and give the midsole a slightly chunky appearance.

Our StockX experts like the way the sneaker stays true to its Air Max Plus roots while introducing a modern color palette . The Nike Air Max Plus Reverse Grape was released on August 29th, 2023, and sold for $175.

name: Kentucky
title: Nike Dunk Low SP Kentucky
description:
Nike celebrated the 35th Anniversary of the Nike Dunk by releasing the Nike Dunk Low SP Syracuse (2020), now available on StockX. The Nike Dunk debuted as part of the 1985 Nike College Color’s program, a program that delivered footwear in the school colors of 12 popular basketball programs allowing fans to support their favorite teams from head to toe. This Kentucky colorway was among the first collegiate colorways Nike released, breaking the mold for colorways used on basketball shoes.

This Nike Dunk Low SP is composed of a white leather upper with varsity royal leather overlays. A white midsole, royal outsole, and classic Nike branding on the tongue completes the design. These sneakers released in March of 2020 and retailed for $100.

name: Black White
title: Jordan 1 Low TD Cleat Black White
description:
The Jordan 1 Low TD Cleat Black White applies the signature AJ 1 Low design to a football cleat.

What makes this cleat stand out is the all-black base, outsole, and liner that contrast the striking white Swoosh. The Swoosh and the Jumpman logo on the tongue are the only elements that break from the black-on-black aesthetic. The outsole features studs that provide a gripping effect, while the lace-up front holds the foot in place. The sneaker features a leather upper with complementing leather overlays. The vamp comes with perforations that allow the foot to breathe, while the reinforced stitching adds durability.

What do our StockX experts love? The sneaker boasts a swoosh on one of the studs beneath the forefoot. This subtle detail speaks to the cleat’s overall sleek, understated appearance. The Jordan 1 Low TD Cleat Black White was released on June 1, 2023, and retailed at $140.

name: Silver Green Gum (Womens)
title: adidas Gazelle Bold Silver Green Gum (Womens)
description:
The adidas Gazelle Bold Silver Green Gum (Women’s) offers a contemporary and sophisticated take on the classic Gazelle design.

The Bold Silver Green Gum adidas Gazelle (Women’s) is characterized by a Pastel Green suede midsole that lends a gentle softness to its overall aesthetic. The rear tab, crafted from Collegiate Green leather, creates an appealing contrast with the shoe's silver green hue. The signature three-stripes logo of adidas, rendered in white, preserves the Gazelle's original charm. The golden 'Gazelle' inscription on the sides further accentuates the shoe's vintage-inspired look. A slim, molded tongue pairs with a padded collar lined in faux leather to ensure a snug fit. The low-top design is set on a stacked platform midsole, constructed from gum rubber with a gradient effect.

The defining feature of the adidas Gazelle Bold Silver Green Gum (Women’s) is its daring reinterpretation of the traditional Gazelle style. The combination of light green calf suede and the platform gum rubber sole enhances the vintage-inspired silhouette, making it a distinctive and fashionable selection. The sneaker debuted for $120 on October 1st, 2023.

name: White Pure Silver Pink (Women's)
title: ASICS Gel-1130 White Pure Silver Pink (Women's)
description:
The ASICS Gel-1130 White Pure Silver Pink (Women's) gives the Gel-1130 a contemporary upgrade with a colorway of Pure Silver and light pink.

Drawing design inspiration from version nine of the Gel-1000 series and the Gel-Kayano 14, the Gel-1130 was initially launched in 2008. The "White Pure Silver Pink" colorway repurposes genuine leather overlays with synthetic leather for a more durable finish. The white mesh upper is lightweight and serves as a backdrop for the Pure Silver and pink overlays. Padding in the collar and the gel technology in the heel contribute to the sneaker’s slightly bulky, technical silhouette, while the front lace closure provides a secure fit.

Our experts like the combination of pink, Pure Silver, black, and white colors on the rubber outsole because they complement the hues on the upper. The women’s size ASICS Gel-1130 White Pure Silver Pink (Women's) was originally released on June 1, 2024, and sold for $95.

name: Black Cement
title: Jordan 2 Retro Black Cement
description:
The Jordan 2 Retro Black Cement was created in honor of the Air Jordan 3’s 35th anniversary. This model has an almost all black body placed next to an off-white midsole with a gray and red sole.

The Retro Air Jordan 2 in Black Cement has a shape that is reminiscent of the original 1987 Air Jordan style. The upper body of the shoe is made from Jet Black leather. There are Cement Gray accents that line the midfoot and are included on the tongue and the heel foxing. The laces are the same Jet Black as the body. The sneaker has a high profile, which helps to achieve fast movement on the basketball court, AIR pods for cushioning, and a round toebox with perforations for breathability.

A feature that our experts particularly love about the Air Jordan 2 Retro Black Cement is the pops of bright red color that appear on the tongue, the back of the shoe, and the sole. The model was originally released for a starting retail price of $175 on September 23rd, 2023.

name: Light Smoke Grey (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Light Smoke Grey (Women's)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Light Smoke Grey (Women's) is part of Nike’s large collection of Dunk sneakers and is designed in the DD1503-117 style.

The sneaker is decorated in the White, Iron Grey & Light Smoke Grey colorway, with the upper fully constructed of leather. The Light Smoke Grey highlighting on the overlays pairs nicely with the shoe’s white base. The Nike's Swooshes, heel tabs, and laces are all Iron Grey, while the heels have grey embroidery. The sneaker’s white midsoles provide contrast to the grey rubber outsoles.

The Nike Dunk Low Light Smoke Grey (Women's) debuted in May of 2022 at a retail price of $100.

name: White Red
title: New Balance 550 White Red
description:
With a similar look as the New Balance 550 Aimé Leon Dore Red, the New Balance 550 White Red features a white leather upper with red mesh collars and accents. At the quarter panel, a puffed New Balance logo nods to designs from New Balance's early basketball collections. From there, a woven New Balance tongue label completes the design.

The New Balance 550 White Red released in 2021 and retailed for $110.

name: Grinch (2020)
title: Nike Kobe 6 Protro Grinch (2020)
description:
Nike opened a new chapter at the end of 2020 and refreshed the Kobe 6 design with the Nike Kobe 6 Protro Grinch. The Kobe 6 Grinch originally debuted in 2010 when Kobe Bryant’s Los Angeles Lakers faced LeBron James’ Miami Heat in a legendary match up on Christmas Day. This is the first Kobe 6 to receive the Kobe Protro treatment, a design process that takes classic Kobe designs and updates them with modern tech for improved performance.

At a first glance, the Nike Kobe 6 Grinch looks identically like the OG pair from 2010: it features a Green Apple and Volt textured, snake-inspired upper as a tribute to Kobe’s Black Mamba moniker. A black Swoosh, red Kobe branding on the tongue, and green translucent outsole accentuate the shoe’s reptile theme. But, because this is a Protro, there are some differences. The updated Kobe 6 Grinch arrives with a more responsive Zoom Air cushioning system and scaled-down traction for an improved court feel. The silhouette shape is even altered to provide a lower, sleeker fit.

The Nike Kobe 6 Grinch released in December of 2020 and retailed for $180.

name: Día de Muertos Pack Off White
title: adidas Samba OG Día de Muertos Pack Off White
description:
The adidas Samba OG Día de Muertos Pack Off White is an athletic shoe featuring an Off White leather upper accented by contrast stitching and a lace panel in Core Black. Samba branding accents the monochrome contrast stitch signature 3-Stripes, while embroidered marigold images in Crew Orange accent the lace panel. A skull image appears on the tongue, and a dark gum rubber outsole finishes the look.

German sneaker adidas has a century-plus of heritage, and many of the brand’s signature styles have remained unchanged for decades. For a unique collection, Pack celebrating Día De Los Muertos, an autumn celebration that reunites the living and dead, adidas reimagined its classic Samba OG with alternate fabrication and imagery that evokes Día De Los Muertos.

Our experts feel that the best feature of the Samba Día De Muertos is its embroidered details, which are subtle yet symbolic. The adidas Samba OG Día de Muertos Pack Off White was released on September 27, 2024, and retailed at $100.

name: Military Black (GS)
title: Jordan 4 Retro Military Black (GS)
description:
The Air Jordan 4 Retro Military Black for Grade Schoolers (GS) first was sold on the market in May of 2022.
​
​This unique shoe model provides a modern spin on the original retro item that was created in 1989. It features a white sole and base with suede and leather overlays in neutral shades of beige and black. The Air Jordan 4 Retro Military Black (GS) for grade schoolers has mesh side panels that were designed not only for style, but also for their breathability. The model provides the feet with plenty of support for walking and exercise.
​
​ The retail price for this item started at $210 for adult sizes.

name: White Black Metallic Silver
title: Nike Air VaporMax 2021 FK White Black Metallic Silver
description:
The Nike Air VaporMax 2021 FK White Black Metallic Silver is a thoughtfully crafted shoe. Notably, 40% of this sneaker is constructed from recycled materials. Its stretchy FlyKnit upper, for example, is made from recycled yarn.

Originally designed for running, this sneaker features a soft collar, webbing eyestays for a modern look, traditional lacing, and heel padding for comfort. It also features Nike Grind rubber details for increased traction and longevity and the VaporMax’s traditional TPU Clip. All these features are set atop its revolutionary VaporMax 2 Air unit.

The Nike Air VaporMax 2021 FK White Black Metallic Silver was released in June 2021 at a retail price of $200.

name: Pure Platinum
title: Nike P-6000 Pure Platinum
description: The Nike P 6000 Pure Platinum is a sleek and stylish sneaker that combines retro design with modern technology. The upper is made of a mix of leather, mesh, and synthetic materials, providing durability and breathability. The colorway is a clean and classic white and platinum, with hits of black and red for contrast. The shoe features a comfortable foam midsole and a rubber outsole for traction. The release date for this shoe was January 27th, 2020, and it retailed for $100. Whether you're hitting the gym or running errands, the Nike P 6000 Pure Platinum is a versatile and fashionable choice.

name: Game Royal Navy
title: Nike Dunk Low Game Royal Navy
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Game Royal Navy adorns the 80s basketball icon with a classic leather upper, featuring a Pristine White base and tonal Swoosh branding.

The Game Royal Navy Nike Dunk Low is crafted from high-quality full leather, strategically perforated on the toebox for improved breathability. The shoes also incorporate mesh tongues and inner lining, ensuring added comfort during wear. The clean white base provides a sleek backdrop for the accents, with Game Royal and Midnight Navy overlays adding a vibrant touch. The iconic Swoosh logos on the sides are elegantly presented in Football Gray, while navy tongue tags, Royal Blue tongues, and embroidered heels contribute to the overall visual appeal. Resting on a white midsole for support and cushioning, the sneakers are grounded by a navy rubber outsole, ensuring reliable traction.

The highlight of the Nike Dunk Low Game Royal Navy is its distinctive color combination, creating a visually appealing design that is both stylish and unique. The sneaker debuted for $115 on November 3rd, 2023.

name: Summit White Metallic Silver (Women's)
title: Nike V2K Run Summit White Metallic Silver (Women's)
description:
The Nike V2K Run Summit White Metallic Silver (Women’s) is a high-performance running shoe with a design that combines both retro and futuristic elements. With a chunky heel, flashy metallic colors, and plastic accents, this unique shoe is the perfect addition to any collection.

This sneaker features an upper made of a mix of material. White mesh provides the base of the forefoot, while Metallic Silver synthetic leather overlays cross over the top of it. These overlays also appear lining the toe box and under the laces. Clear and white plastic overlays adorn the midsole of this Nike V2K Run, and on top of that a Nike Swoosh appears in gray outlined by black.

What we like most about this sneaker is its chunky heel, which adds a unique design element to the shoe, while also serving to improve performance and impact. The Nike V2K Run Summit White Metallic Silver (Women’s) was first released on July 13th, 2023, for a retail price of $110.

name: Silver Bullet (2022)
title: Nike Air Max 97 OG Silver Bullet (2022)
description:
The Nike Air Max 97 OG Silver Bullet 2022 comes in a mixture of four colorways: white, black, university red, and metallic silver.

The top of this Original (OG) Nike Air Max model has a metallic silver finish inspired by the aluminum and titanium components of a mountain bike. Wavy overlays sit on top of the mesh base. The exterior of this sneaker is accented with a crimson Swoosh stitched on the tongue and on the quarter panel. Air units are included in the soles.

The Nike Air Max 97 OG Silver Bullet 2022 was released on November 11th, 2022, retailing at $185.

name: Carbon
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Carbon
description:
Kanye West and adidas keep the ball rolling with the Yeezy 350 V2 Carbon. This release marks the 12th colorway of the favorite 350 V2 model in 2020 and this colorway’s dark-hued upper makes it the perfect piece of footwear for fall.

The Yeezy 350 V2 Carbon holds all of the familiar elements that make the silhouette so popular; breathable Primeknit solid black mesh with its signature side stripe, ribbed patterned off-white midsole, and classic BOOST cushioning make the 350 V2 Carbon easy to love and easy to wear.

The Yeezy 350 V2 Carbon released in October of 2020.

name: Black
title: Nike P-6000 Black
description:
The Nike P-6000 Black features a classic low-top silhouette presented in an all-black colorway.

The Black Nike P-6000 has an upper made from a combination of leather and mesh materials, ensuring durability and breathability. The shoe features a lace-up closure system that allows for a secure and customizable fit. The cushioned midsole provides comfort and shock absorption. Furthermore, the rubber outsole offers traction and grip, ensuring stability and control. The shoe also includes Nike branding details, including the trademark Nike Swoosh logo on the sides and the "NIKE" wordmark on the tongue.

What we love about this shoe is its sleek and modern design. The shoe features a mixture of leather and mesh materials, creating a dynamic and textured upper. The black colorway emphasizes the shoe's bold and statement-making appearance. In addition, the sneaker incorporates a chunky and supportive midsole, which enhances the shoe's overall aesthetic. The Nike P-6000 Black was released on June 28, 2019, at an initial price of $100.

name: Inter Miami CF Messi Black
title: adidas Samba Inter Miami CF Messi Black
description:
The adidas Samba Inter Miami CF Messi Black is an indoor training shoe featuring the away colors of the Inter Miami CF team.

This version of the adidas Samba is constructed with a smooth black leather upper. A T-shaped toe cap appears in black suede. The iconic adidas three stripes logo appears on each side of the shoe in light pink leather, while the word " Samba" appears next to the stripes on the lateral side in gold letters. The shoe also features a light pink heel collar to match the stripes. The tongue features the Inter Miami CF logo in subtle shiny black, blending into the black tongue. The classic gum rubber outsole rounds out the design, and the shoe features an EVA insert for cushioning.

What we love most about this sneaker is the subtle Inter Miami CF present on the tongue, which was a clever way to implement branding. The adidas Samba Inter Miami CF Messi Black will be released on June 22, 2024, for $120.

name: South Park Towelie
title: adidas Campus 80s South Park Towelie
description:
South Park and adidas joined forces to celebrate 4/20 in 2021 with the release of the adidas Campus 80s South Park Towelie. This release references Towelie, a laboratory-made, cannabis-consuming towel character who has made appearances in more than a dozen episodes and three South Park games.

The adidas Campus 80s South Park Towelie features a purple terry cloth upper with white leather overlays and purple leather lining. Towelie’s eyes appear on the tongue and when exposed to sunlight, they transition from white to bright red. A hidden stash pocket in the tongue is big enough to fit the Towelie keychains that are included with the shoes. Quotes from Towelie that read "Don’t Forget To Bring A Towel" and "I Have No Idea What’s Going On" also show up on the tongue’s interior. A white sole and adidas branding on the heel tab complete this South Park release.

The adidas Campus 80s South Park Towelie released in April of 2021 and retailed for $100.

name: Metallic Silver Blue Tint (Women's)
title: Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Metallic Silver Blue Tint (Women's)
description:
The Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Metallic Silver Blue Tint (Women's) is a striking-looking shoe. It has a modern look, with lots to keep the eye entertained. At the same time, it has all the advanced technology one could want in an athletic trainer.

This Nike Air Zoom version has a primarily monochrome colorway that blends shades of cloudy gray with shiny silver detailing. The sole has pastel blue segments that help to emphasize the shoe's sportiness. It has thick grooves and provides superb traction. The textile mesh and synthetic panels are combined with a see-through heel grid. For lateral stability, there's a built-in supportive cage.

We love the combination of a sophisticated color scheme with serious running shoe credentials. It's very lightweight, and the Air Zoom cushioning gives a springy effect that helps with stamina on longer runs. It also provides impact protection, which regular runners will appreciate. The Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Metallic Silver Blue Tint (Women's) was released on 1 August 2023, priced at $160.

name: Space Jam (PS)
title: Jordan 11 Retro Low Space Jam (PS)
description:
The Jordan 11 Retro Low Space Jam (PS) is a low-top, child-sized version of the original Air Jordan 11 Retro Space Jam from 2016.

Although Michael Jordan didn’t wear the low-top shoe in Space Jam, the Space Jam (PS) Jordan 11 Retro Low still boasts the name. The upper is durable ballistic mesh in black with a curvy, patent leather mudguard that circles the shoe. Smooth leather can be found on the heel, while rope laces wind through the web eyelets. The Jumpman logo on the mesh tongue and the stylized "23" on the heel comes in Varsity Blue, adding a pop of color against the all-black upper. Finally, the sneaker offers a full-length Air unit in the Phylon midsole and a supportive carbon fiber plate.

Our StockX experts like the semi-transparent rubber outsole, which features a herringbone pattern and provides additional traction. The preschool-sized Jordan 11 Retro Low Space Jam (PS) was released on May 18, 2024, and sold for $80.

name: Cherry (2022) (GS)
title: Jordan 11 Retro Cherry (2022) (GS)
description:
The Air Jordan 11 Retro Cherry 2022 GS was introduced in the grade schoolers' (GS) catalog with a display of a two-tone colorway.

The sneaker features Varsity Red glossy patent leather mudguards, a tonal leather overlay, and white ballistic mesh. For a tight fit, webbing eyelets on the rope laces are fed. The collar is embellished with a red Jumpman insignia, and the heel tab is decorated with a "23" inscription. An encased Air-sole unit is mounted on a white Phylon midsole, which is aided by a translucent rubber outsole for cushioning.

The Air Jordan 11 Retro Cherry 2022 GS was released on December 10th, 2022. It originally retailed at $185.

name: White Black
title: Nike Zoom Vomero 5 White Black
description:
The Nike Zoom Vomero 5 White Black dresses the Zoom Vomero 5 in a white, black, and gray colorway that allows the sneaker’s technical features to take center stage.

As a modern interpretation of early 2000s running shoes, the White Black Nike Zoom Vomero 5 features a slightly chunky midsole with plush Cushlon foam and Zoom Air cushioning. The combination of these technologies provides supportive comfort with each step without weighing down the foot. Airy mesh combines with plastic components and synthetic leather to create a layered upper with a visually complex design. In addition, plastic caging on the sides supports the sneaker, while ventilation ports at the heel allow the foot to breathe.

Our experts at StockX like the way the white embroidered outline makes the signature Swoosh logos stand out even though all the sneaker's colors lie on the grayscale. The Nike Zoom Vomero 5 White Black was released on March 27, 2024, and sold for $160.

name: Jarritos
title: Nike SB Dunk Low Jarritos
description:
Rumors of a collaboration project between Nike and Mexican beverage company Jarritos started initially in 2022 and now in 2023 we are seeing the collection come to fruition, with the release of the Nike SB Dunk Low Jarritos.

The Nike SB Dunk Low Jarritos is constructed using white leather and tear-away canvas materials across the uppers, while green accents help cover the outsoles and Nike Swoosh. Jarritos branding is seen throughout the insoles, heel tabs, and tongue of the sneakers. The limited edition sneakers come with orange, green, and white laces.

The Nike SB Dunk Low Jarritos released May 10, 2023, with a retail price of $130.

name: Mismatched (GS)
title: Nike Ja 1 Mismatched (GS)
description:
The Nike Ja 1 Mismatched (GS) is whimsical offering by NBA star Ja Morant and Nike. This high-octane sneaker features a right shoe that is primarily Bright Mandarin and a left shoe that is primarily Vapor Green. This head-turning pair of kicks is sized for grade school-aged kids.

The upper of each big kids’ shoe is constructed of loose-weave, breathable, lightweight mesh. A tonal synthetic leather mudguard circles the shoe and rises to form a heel counter. A 3-D gray Nike Swoosh with a pebbled texture hits each side panel and loops around the heel. Speckled gray faux leather heel tabs embroidered with the number 12, speckled gray side-panel overlays, and a tongue tag with mismatched Ja Morant logos adorn each shoe. Each shoe features a tonal Phylon foam midsole that encapsulates a Zoom Air unit in the forefoot for responsive cushioning and a tonal rubber outsole.

Our favorite aspect of this bright pair of mismatched sneakers for kids is Ja’s signature in Mandarin Orange on the Vapor Green shoe and Vapor Green on the Mandarin Orange shoe. The Nike Ja 1 Mismatched (GS) was released on April 19, 2024, for $102 retail.

name: Black White
title: Puma LaMelo Ball MB.01 Lo Black White
description:
The physical appearance of the Puma LaMelo Ball MB.01 Lo Black White is designed with only two main colors: Puma Black and Puma White.

The MB.01 Lo Puma LaMelo Ball in Black White is crafted from high-quality leather. The upper showcases a timeless white and black color scheme, striking a perfect balance between classic and contemporary aesthetics. The lightweight foam midsole ensures comfortable cushioning and support during wear, while the sturdy rubber outsole guarantees excellent traction and grip. Emphasizing the brand identity, the Puma logo is prominently featured on the side of the shoe, adding a subtle branding element to the overall design.

Something that we found interesting with the Puma LaMelo Ball MB.01 Lo Black White is that this sneaker can be worn on the court or on the streets, making it a versatile and fashionable option. At the time of its release on October 15, 2022, the Puma LaMelo Ball MB.01 Lo Black White retailed for about $120.

name: Clay Taupe
title: adidas Yeezy Foam RNR Clay Taupe
description:
The adidas Yeezy Foam RNR Clay Taupe arrives in an all-Clay Taupe color palette, constructed in lightweight foam to add comfort and utility.

The Clay Taupe adidas Yeezy Foam RNR The upper is crafted with a smooth one-piece Primeknit material, which provides comfort, a flexible fit, and breathability. The shoe's midsole is made using adidas' proprietary EVA foam technology, providing cushioning and support. In addition, the midsole features a dynamic design with intricate textures and patterns. The shoe's outsole is crafted of durable rubber, ensuring stability and grip. The shoe also features a sock-like collar for a snug fit around the ankle.

The standout feature of the adidas Yeezy Foam RNR Clay Taupe is its unique colorway. These sneakers feature a distinctive Clay Taupe color that adds a neutral and earthy tone to the design. The shoe was released on May 31st, 2023, and sold for a retail price of $80.

name: Washed Denim
title: Jordan 1 Low Washed Denim
description:
The Jordan 1 Low Washed Denim presents a classic silhouette dressed in colors and materials that give this low-top shoe a unique look.

The Washed Denim iteration of the Jordan 1 Low-Top features an upper made of smooth white leather, with perforations in the toebox. The overlays are made of denim in Midnight Navy Blue and white, giving the denim a washed look. The laces are solid Midnight Navy Blue, as is the rim of the tongue, the sockliner, and the insole with a white Jumpman. The washed denim tongue also has a white Jumpman. The white foam midsole with tonal stitching features encapsulated Air cushioning, and the Midnight Navy Blue rubber outsole offers traction in a pattern of concentric circles.

What our sneaker experts appreciate the most out about this shoe is the clean duality of the colorway. Every aspect of this sneaker is white or Midnight Navy Blue. The Jordan 1 Low Washed Denim was released on August 2nd, 2020, for a retail price of $100.

name: Vintage Stealth Grey
title: Air Jordan 1 Low Vintage Stealth Grey
description:
Since its debut, Air Jordan 1 Low Vintage Grey remains one of the highest-selling variants in the Air Jordan 1 Low series.

Leather, nylon, and fiber are the main materials of the various components of Air Jordan 1 Low Vintage Grey’s heels. Its white leather base is complemented by the nylon tongue and the distressed midsole. The outsole, fabric linings, and laces of the shoe all feature grey overlays. The wings logo is embroidered in white on Air Jordan 1 Low Vintage Grey’s heels.

The Air Jordan 1 Low Vintage Grey is set to release September 2, 2022, at a price of $110.

name: Game Royal
title: Jordan 1 Low TD Cleat Game Royal
description:
The Air Jordan 1 Low TD Cleat Game Royal is a new take on the original Air Jordan 1’s that were originally released in 1985. This model has an upper body that is made of leather and rubber soles.
​
​The Low Air Jordan 1 Cleat in Game Royal features a white leather base that has royal blue leather overlays. The classic Nike Swoosh symbol appears on the side in black leather. This model is a low cut and reaches right below the ankle. The tongue of the shoe also has black accents that match the Nike Swoosh.
​
​One feature that our experts love about the Air Jordan 1 Low TD Cleat Game Royal is the bright white body of the shoe that helps to make the rest of the colors pop. The Air Jordan 1 Low TD Cleat Game Royal were first released on July 1st, 2023, at a starting price of $140.

name: G-Dragon Peaceminusone Panda
title: Nike Kwondo 1 G-Dragon Peaceminusone Panda
description:
The Nike Kwondo 1 G-Dragon Peaceminusone Panda is a collaboration between Nike and G-Dragon.

The Peaceminusone Panda Nike Kwondo 1 G-Dragon comes in a black-and-white color palette. The sneaker features an upper constructed of durable white leather and synthetic materials with black accents. The outsole features a distinct tread pattern for traction and stability. The sneaker's dense midsole provides exceptional padding and support. The shoe features a Nike Swoosh on the lateral sides and a "NIKE Swoosh" inscription on the tongue. The sneaker's design is completed with G-Dragon and Peaceminusone branding on the heel.

The Nike Kwondo 1 G-Dragon Peaceminusone Panda was released on April 18, 2023, and retailed for $190.

name: Gorge Green
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Gorge Green
description:
The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG Gorge Green has become one of the most celebrated colorways in the Jordan catalog.

The white tumbled leather upper of the Retro High OG sneaker has perforations in the toe box and hunter green tumbled leather overlays. The Swoosh is made in silver tumbled leather, the laces and sock liner are green, and the tongue and insole are white with green Nike Air branding. The collar sports a silver Wings logo. The midsole is white and the outsole is green rubber with AIR units.

The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG Gorge Green was released on December 20th, 2022 for a retail price of $180.

name: Starfish (Women's)
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Starfish (Women's)
description:
The leather upper of the Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG Starfish W features a white base, contrasting orange overlays, and a high-cut collar in chocolate brown.

This women's Air Jordan 1 OG Starfish also boasts a woven Nike Air tag embellishing a lightly padded nylon tongue in a vintage off-white finish. The aged aesthetic is repeated on the rubber midsole of the sneaker, fitted with an encapsulated Air-sole unit in the heel and supported underfoot by an orange rubber outsole.

The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG Starfish W was released on the 27th of October 2022, and initially retailed at $180.

name: White Grey Navy Aqua Mini Swoosh
title: Nike Dunk Low White Grey Navy Aqua Mini Swoosh
description:
The Nike Dunk Low White Gray Navy Aqua Mini Swoosh is a standalone colorway of the Nike Dunk Low line. 

The Dunk Low White Gray Navy Aqua Mini Swoosh has an upper that is constructed with durable leather and textile materials. It has a perforated toebox to allow for breathability. The shoe also features a cushioned midsole that provides both support and comfort during movement. The rubber outsole offers a solid grip on various surfaces.

We think that the notable feature of these Low Dunks in White Gray Navy Aqua Mini Swoosh is undoubtedly the vibrant aqua-colored mini Swoosh on the side panel. While the shoe features a classic, understated colorway of white, gray, and navy, the use of this bright aqua color for the mini Swoosh creates a unique and eye-catching contrast that draws attention to the shoe. The Nike Dunk Low White Gray Navy Aqua Mini Swoosh was released on May 1st, 2023 at a retail price of $110.

name: Metallic Silver
title: Jordan 1 Low OG Metallic Silver
description:
The Jordan 1 Low OG Metallic Silver is a low-top sneaker with a Neutral Grey base and Metallic Silver accents.

This sneaker borrows elements from the Air Jordan 1 Retro Japan Grey (2001), including its colorway and the placement of several Metallic Silver details. For example, the vamp, the signature Swoosh logos, the panel around the heel, and the heel tab all display Metallic Silver. On the other hand, Neutral Grey makes up the base and is found on the mudguard and the forefoot overlay. While the Metallic Silver parts are leather, the Neutral Grey pieces are velvety nubuck. The contrast between the nubuck’s almost matte texture and the sheen of the Metallic Silver leather makes this Jordan 1 Low OG model stand out from others.

Our StockX experts like the simple Air Jordan Wings logo on the heel tab. The Jordan 1 Low OG Metallic Silver was released on June 1, 2024, and sold for $140.

name: Mono Ice
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Mono Ice
description:
The adidas Yeezy 350 V2 Mono Ice is one of three from the Mono pack. Each sneaker’s upper is constructed from a new monofilament mesh in Ice blue that exposes the model’s inner cage lining. The Mono pack brings back the heel’s pull tab design on each pair. To finish it out, a familiar Boost sole is added for comfort for the wearer.

The adidas Yeezy 350 V2 Mono Ice released in June of 2021 for $220, exclusively in the US.

name: atmos Pink Denim (Women's)
title: adidas Sambae atmos Pink Denim (Women's)
description:
The adidas Sambae atmos Pink Denim (Women's) adds a contemporary design to the classic Samba silhouette and a tri-toned denim construction.

The upper features faded denim as the base, distressed, dark indigo denim for the 3-Stripes logo, and the oversized T-shaped toe overlay. Another detail that makes this low-top sneaker stand out is the zipper on the heel. Although it’s just for decoration, it appears to zip the heel closed. The heel tab, tongue, and panels around the tongue are made from white denim with frayed edges. Like other Sambae models, the atmos Pink Denim version sits on a thick gum rubber sole that’s larger than the classic Samba’s rubber outsole.

Our experts at StockX like that the outsole comes in traditional gum instead of a faded or orange gum tone. The women’s size adidas Sambae atmos Pink Denim (Women's) was released on April 13, 2024, and retailed at $110.

name: Black White
title: Nike Free Metcon 5 Black White
description:
The Nike Free Metcon 5 Black White is a training sneaker with a sock-like fit and a monochromatic colorway.

The sneaker provides a 7/8-length inner sleeve, which creates an easy entry point. Webbing eyelets for the laces help secure the foot and form a crisscross pattern across the sneaker’s top. In addition, foam padding around the ankle adds comfort and protects this joint. Other technical features include a wide heel, which acts as a base during strength training, and a cushioning foam midsole. The synthetic upper comes in black and has rubber tread in high-wear areas. Finally, a molded heel clip helps the shoe maintain its shape and protects this area from impact stress.

Our StockX experts appreciate the minimal branding, including a vertical Swoosh on the lateral side of the midsole. The Nike Free Metcon 5 Black White was released on April 10th, 2023, and retailed at $130.

name: Midnight Navy (GS)
title: Jordan 3 Retro Midnight Navy (GS)
description:
The Jordan 3 Retro Midnight Navy (GS) pays homage to the iconic Jordan silhouette with a color scheme reminiscent of the timeless 'White Cement' version that gained popularity in 1988.

In grade school sizing, the Midnight Navy Air Jordan 3 Retro features a white leather base adorned with elephant print overlays on the toe and heels. Cement Gray perforations on the eyestays and tongues add a classic touch. The design is accentuated by Midnight Navy contrasting elements on the eyelets, collars, Jumpman branding on the tongues and heels, as well as the midsole and underfoot. The shoe is rounded off with a white midsole housing a visible Air heel unit, all set atop a Cement Gray rubber outsole.

The standout characteristic of the Jordan 3 Retro Midnight Navy (GS) is its iconic elephant print in Cement Gray. This distinctive design element not only enhances the shoe's visual allure but also cements its status in the realm of sneaker history. The sneaker debuted for $150 on December 16th, 2023.

name: Slate Panda
title: adidas Yeezy 350 V2 CMPCT Slate Panda
description:
The adidas Yeezy 350 V2 CMPCT Slate Panda comes with the style, comfort and the distinction of Kanye West's Yeezy line. The Slate White colorway infuses a unique blend of contrasting colors, featuring a compact, knitted upper with a monofilament side stripe.

Staying true to its roots, the shoe showcases the iconic Yeezy Boost technology within a translucent outsole for comfort that's as stellar as its look. The lace-up design, coupled with the minimalist aesthetic, makes these sneakers a trend-setting piece in any sneaker collection.

The adidas Yeezy 350 V2 CMPCT Slate Panda dropped on June 2, 2023, retailing at $230.

name: Chambray (2023)
title: Jordan 7 Retro Chambray (2023)
description:
The Jordan 7 Retro Chambray 2023 was released as a colorway addition to the Air Jordan line of sneakers. This Retro iteration is designed to pay homage to the style and innovation of the original Air Jordan 7.

The Chambray Air Jordan 7 2023 is equipped with a cushioned foam midsole that provides both comfort and support. The outsole of the sneaker is made with durable rubber that provides traction and is designed to withstand the rigors of regular usage. The Jumpman logo appears on the side, and the Air Jordan branding is on the tongue.

We think that the standout feature of the Jordan 7 Retro Chambray 2023 is its sleek and stylish design. The sneaker features a combination of premium-quality leather and suede with Chambray detailing. The shoe is also crafted with intricate detail to create a streamlined and almost aerodynamic silhouette. The shoe was released on July 15th, 2023 at a retail price of $200.

name: Sesame
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Sesame
description: We don’t know if Kanye loves Sesame seeds but we do know that he’s released the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Sesame. This major silhouette comes with a sesame upper, sesame midsole, and a gum sole. These sneakers released in November 2018 and retailed for $220.  While getting your grub on stay fresh and cop these on StockX today.

name: Orange Label Court Purple
title: Nike SB Dunk Low Pro ISO Orange Label Court Purple
description:
The Nike SB Dunk Low Pro ISO Orange Label Court Purple retains the iconic Dunk Low silhouette, characterized by its low-top design in a color scheme that pays homage to the Los Angeles Lakers, with the incorporation of Court Purple overlays and a subtly toned sole.

The Orange Label Court Purple Nike SB Dunk Low Pro ISO comes in the Court Purple shade complemented by a white and gum light brown color palette. The shoe incorporates the customary white leather base, mesh tongues, linings, laces, and midsole. Suede overlays in Court Purple accentuate the design, while the orange label is prominently featured on the tongue, insole, and lace tips branding. The shoe is completed with a gum rubber outsole to add the finishing touch to the overall aesthetic.

What our experts love about the Nike SB Dunk Low Pro ISO Orange Label Court Purple is its bold and distinctive colorway. The combination of Court Purple, white, and gum creates a visually captivating sneaker that serves as a fashion statement. The sneaker debuted for $110 on August 23rd, 2023.
model: Nike SB Dunk Low Pro ISO

name: Brooklyn's Finest (Women's)
title: Nike Sabrina 1 Brooklyn's Finest (Women's)
description:
The Nike Sabrina 1 Brooklyn's Finest (Women's) is a women’s shoe designed in collaboration with American basketball star Sabrina Ionescu.

This iteration of the Nike Sabrina 1 is made with a mesh upper in a unique criss cross pattern across the toe box and around the laces. The pattern appears in black and a light blue-green color. The same light blue-green adorns the sides, which are supported by TPU layers. Black outlines the Nike swoosh on the lateral side, while a black Nike swoosh runs vertically up the heel towards the ankle on the other side. The heel is a lavender color with light pink accents and the tongue contains an S logo for Sabrina. A purple and beige rubber outsole completes the design.

What we like most about this sneaker is the unique patterning on the mesh upper, which makes the shoe stand out. The Nike Sabrina 1 Brooklyn's Finest (Women's) was released on February 4, 2024, for $130.

name: Venice Beach (2024) (PS)
title: Nike Kobe 8 Protro Venice Beach (2024) (PS)
description:
The Nike Kobe 8 Protro Venice Beach (2024) (PS) is an athletic shoe built for preschool-aged children, constructed around a gray base featuring abstractions of yellow, blue, red and green. Complementing the aesthetic are an orange lining, yellow and red laces, an aqua heel and mudguards, and a gray, partially transparent outsole. Kobe Bryant’s signature and the Mamba logo are found on the heel and tongue tab.

Originally released in 2013, the Nike Kobe 8 Protro sneaker was inspired by the colors and atmosphere of Venice Beach, California. Kobe Bryant spent his entire NBA career playing for the Los Angeles Lakers, drawing inspiration from his surroundings. The Protro Venice Beach was originally part of Bryant’s signature line with Nike.

In our opinion, the best feature of the Protro Venice Beach is its brightly colored aesthetic, which looks fresh and energetic. The Nike Kobe 8 Protro Venice Beach (2024) (PS) released on April 13, 2024, and retailed at $90.

name: Cactus Plant Flea Market Moss
title: Nike Air Force 1 Low Cactus Plant Flea Market Moss
description:
The Nike Air Force 1 Low Cactus Plant Flea Market Moss is one of Cactus Plant Flea Market’s first reinventions of the Air Force 1. It features a playful Moss colorway that pays tribute to the label's quirky, DIY aesthetic.

The upper is made of a combination of smooth and pebbled leather in Moss, while the sneaker sits on a tonal rubber outsole. The right shoe displays "AIR" on the lateral side in bubble letters, while the left shoe features "SUNSHINE" stretching from the inner to the outer side panel. Perforations across the vamp allow the foot to breathe and create texture. In terms of branding, "NIKE" is embroidered on the heel and on the woven tongue logo tag in Moss thread.

Our StockX experts like the silver hardware on the laces, which is the only non-Moss hue on the upper. The Nike Air Force 1 Low Cactus Plant Flea Market Moss was released on May 1, 2024, and retailed at $150.

name: Off-White Sail
title: Jordan 5 Retro Off-White Sail
description:
Virgil Abloh added a second colorway to his Jordan 5 collaboration with the Jordan 5 Retro High Off-White Sail, now available on StockX. This release pays homage to the first Jordan that Virgil ever owned, the Air Jordan 5. In signature fashion, Virgil has reimagined this classic silhouette in a way that embraces the importance of Nike Air technology. 

This Jordan 5 is comprised of a sail textile mesh upper with translucent netted panels and circular window inserts throughout the shoe. 3M reflective tongues, fire red Jordan branding, and an aged translucent outsole completes the design. These sneakers released in 2020 and retailed for $225.

name: Black White
title: Nike Air Max 270 Black White
description:
Crafted from a breathable mesh and canvas upper, the Nike Air Max 270 Black White now features 270 degrees of visible Air for extra comfort. Drawing inspiration from the sleek Air Max 180, the Nike Air Max 270 Black White features a slip-in bootie construction to deliver a great fit. The sneaker boasts a Max Air unit with 270 degrees of air encapsulated in the heel. The sneaker utilizes lightweight and soft neoprene across the upper to ensure airflow to the foot.

The Nike Air Max 270 Black White was released in March 2018 at a retail price of $160.

name: Black Cement (2018)
title: Jordan 3 Retro Black Cement (2018)
description: One of the most anticipated releases of 2018, the Air Jordan 3 Retro OG marked the first time original "Nike Air" branding was featured on the "Black Cement" AJ 3 since it's 2001 retro. Jordan stuck to the mantra of "if it aint broke, don’t fix it," on these, staying true to the OG with a black-based leather upper with cement grey, fire red, and white accents, finished off by the iconic elephant print detailing. Their release date was on Michael Jordan's 55th birthday, February 17th, 2018, and went for $200 in mens sizes. The "Black Cement" Air Jordan 3 Retro OG is a must-have, and you don't need us to tell you that. They should be in everyone's collection, multiples if possible. If you're on the hunt for a pair, you can buy them online today. Those with a pair to sell can hit up the StockX marketplace and see what they're currently going for.

name: Carbon
title: adidas Fear of God Athletics I Basketball Carbon
description:
For the adidas Fear of God Athletics I Basketball Carbon, designer Jerry Lorenzo's luxury fashion brand Fear of God and the iconic German sneaker company collaborated to create a basketball shoe with style that pops.

The Carbon iteration of the Fear of God x adidas Basketball sneaker features a base of premium black knit with a tonal neoprene collar on an upper on unrelieved black-on-black. The signature adidas side-panel three stripes appear as a TPU molded cage overlay that adds support to this shoe. A black bungee on the ankle adds flexibility and comfort. The tongue, laces, sock liner, and insole are also black. An embossed adidas logo graces the toe of the upper, while a black bar is adorned with the Fear of God logo at the heel.

One of the most impressive aspects of this sneaker is the sole unit that provides cushioning, support, and grip. A thick, white midsole composed of Lightstrike rests on a white rubber outsole with a herringbone traction pattern. The adidas Fear of God Athletics I Basketball Carbon was launched on December 3, 2023, for $250 retail.
model: adidas Fear of God Athletics I Basketball

name: Craft Vibrations Of Naija
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Craft Vibrations Of Naija
description:
The Jordan 1 Retro High OG has proven once again why it's a classic, with the release of the Craft Vibrations Of Naija edition on May 27, 2023. A unique blend of high-quality leathers defines this model, creating an aesthetic that's both striking and timeless.

The upper of this iteration is draped in a stylish mix of Sail and Pale Vanilla premium leather, making a statement while maintaining that iconic Jordan 1 silhouette. Anchoring the look is a contrast of Black, offering a dynamic visual pop that sets these kicks apart. With an understated pale vanilla outsole complementing the striking upper, this model is designed to stand out in a crowd. The premium finishing touch? The classic Nike Air logo adorning the tongue, rounding off this exquisite design.

The Jordan 1 Retro High OG Craft Vibrations Of Naija was released on May 27, 2023, with a retail price of $180.

name: Bad Bunny Wonder White
title: adidas Response CL Bad Bunny Wonder White
description:
The adidas Response CL Bad Bunny Wonder White is part of a collaboration between adidas and Bad Bunny – a Puerto Rican rapper, producer, and singer.

The CL in the name stands for "classic" and reminds the wearer that this signature shoe draws inspiration from classic 2000s technical running shoes. While the chunky midsole is a throwback to the 2000s, the wavy design of the suede and leather overlays is a modern touch. The overlays add to the sneaker’s off-white base and come in Wonder White and Cream White. The mesh upper allows the foot to breathe, while cushioning in the midsole protects against impact. Other eye-catching details include the 3-stripes on the side panels and an eye motif on the heel.

Our StockX experts like the minimal branding, which allows the shoe’s design to stand out. The adidas Response CL Bad Bunny Wonder White was released on February 17th, 2024, and retailed at $160.

name: Fire Red Silver Tongue (2020)
title: Jordan 5 Retro Fire Red Silver Tongue (2020)
description:
Jordan remastered a 1990s masterpiece with the release of the Jordan 5 Retro Fire Red Silver Tongue (2020), now available on StockX. This is the fourth iteration of the original Fire Red colorway.

This Jordan 5 consists of a white leather upper with netted underlays and Fire Red detailing. A silver 3M reflective tongue with a red Jumpman logo, black and Fire Red midsole, and an icy translucent outsole completes the design. These sneakers released in March of 2020 and retailed for $200.

name: White Blue Red
title: Onitsuka Tiger Mexico 66 White Blue Red
description:
The Onitsuka Tiger Mexico 66 White Blue Red is a heritage running shoe that combines design elements from previous models in Onitsuka Tiger’s catalog.

Noteworthy design features come from the LIMBER-UP training shoe and the Limber shoe – both from the 1960s. For example, the sneaker incorporates the iconic Onitsuka Tiger stripes, originally seen on the Limber shoe, in 1966. The upper is made of premium leather in white, while the leather tiger stripes come in blue and red. However, beige suede can be found on the T-shaped toecap. The sneaker features a thin midsole and outsole in white and beige.

Our StockX experts like the inclusion of heritage Onitsuka Tiger branding on the heel tab and the tongue’s woven tag. The lettering features a retro-inspired blue with the brand’s signature ‘T’ font. The Onitsuka Tiger Mexico 66 White Blue Red was released on January 17th, 2023, and retailed at $120.

name: Safari Mix (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Safari Mix (Women's)
description:
The women's Nike Dunk Low Safari Mix (W) explores exotic patterns and textures with its one-of-a-kind construction. Atop a white leather base, the upper features vibrant overlays constructed of leopard-pattern Durabuck, safari print, faux-horsehair, suede, and smooth leather. Vintage-style Nike woven tongue labels add the finishing touch.

The women's Nike Dunk Low Safari Mix (W) released in March of 2022 and retailed for $120.

name: Setsubun (2022)
title: Nike Dunk Low Setsubun (2022)
description:
Nike is ready for Spring and is drawing inspiration from Japan's annual Setsubun Festival, for a new colorway on the Nike Dunk Low. The Setsubun Festival is held a day prior to the beginning of Spring and is known as the Festival of bean-throwing, whichs brings good fortune.

The Nike Dunk Low Setsubun is designed with shades of brown and tan, honoring the beans thrown at the Setsubun Festival. Nike added splashes of purple across the Swoosh, sockliner, and heel logo. The limited edition sneakers come with purple and white laces with gold aglets.

The Nike Dunk Low Setsubun (2022) released June 1, 2022, with a retail price of $110.

name: Red Panda
title: Nike Dunk Low Red Panda
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Red Panda takes the Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black, also known as the "Panda Dunk," and applies a new colorway. Instead of monochromatic black and white, the Red Panda comes with Velvet Brown, Sanddrift, and Rugged Orange color blocking.

The dark, shaggy suede upper is contrasted by the Rugged Orange of the suede heel overlays, heel tab, and the ‘NIKE’ branding on the texturized tongue. Additional color blocking includes smooth leather details in Sanddrift, including the Swoosh, the toe box, and the lace cage. On the bottom, the sneaker features a dark midsole and a matching rubber outsole.

Something our experts love about this sneaker is how the shaggy suede upper mimics the texture of panda fur and the texturized pattern on the tongue resembles the traditional black and white panda colors. The Nike Dunk Low Red Panda was released on October 27, 2023, and retailed at $120.

name: Split Deep Jungle
title: Nike Dunk Low Retro Split Deep Jungle
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Retro Split Deep Jungle is an alluring sneaker that merges rich green tones with Crisp White and light gray accents, resulting in a visually stunning design.

The Split Deep Jungle Nike Dunk Low Retro distinctive design showcases an all-leather upper divided into deep jungle and silver shades. The deep jungle hue adorns the eyestays, heel overlay, and mudguard, while the quarter panel, collar, and toebox exude a striking silver finish. Classic Dunk details, such as the perforated toebox and padded collar, contribute to its sleek appearance. The laces, matching the overlays in deep jungle, establish a harmonious color scheme. Contrasting with the overall palette, Nike branding on the tongue, Swoosh, and heels is accented in black. The shoe is grounded on a white midsole and gum outsole, completing the thoughtfully designed aesthetic.

The standout element of the Nike Dunk Low Retro Split Deep Jungle lies in its distinctive combination of deep jungle and silver shades on an all-leather upper. This, coupled with the premium textured leather base and 'Deep Jungle' green overlays, delivers a visually appealing and uniquely stylish design. The sneaker debuted for $120 on November 14th, 2023.

name: Tokyo Bio Hack
title: Jordan 1 Retro High Tokyo Bio Hack
description:
Remember back in 2005 when Nike collaborated on a Dunk High with Undefeated? The LA sneaker boutique put their very unique spin on the basketball silhouette, adding bold colors and an unpadded throat of the shoe. Now, the same mismatched color pattern has returned, only this time it on the Air Jordan 1.

The Air Jordan 1 Bio Hack pushes the model to a whole new territory when it comes to color palettes. The upper is made of various suedes and leathers, matched with a hodgepodge of black, Baroque Brown, and Racer Pink. A metallic leather Swoosh is contrasted by a light green midsole to add even further appeal to the traditional model.

The Air Jordan 1 Bio Hack released in September of 2020 for $170.

name: Stone Flax
title: adidas Yeezy 450 Stone Flax
description:
The adidas Yeezy 450 Stone Flax was released as part of a collaboration between American musician Ye, formerly known as Kanye West, and the sneaker brand.

This Stone Flat model dresses the futuristic silhouette in a neutral monochrome finish in stone flax. The dual-layer Primeknit upper features a stretchy sock-like cuff with traditional lace closure. Structural support is provided by tapered polyurethane "fingers" that extend up the sides in an abstract pattern throughout the sneaker. The lightweight PU midsole is reinforced underfoot by a wavy-traction rubber outsole.

The adidas Yeezy 450 Stone Flax was originally released on October 22nd, 2022, at a retail price of $210.

name: Red White
title: Puma Speedcat OG Red White
description:
The Puma Speedcat OG Red White is a bold performance shoe made for speed whose design was inspired by the racetrack.
  
The Red White Puma Speedcat OG has a lightweight paneled leather upper in Puma's bold For All Time Red color. A red leather overlay forms the toe cap, which also bears a white Puma logo on the outer side. White suede Puma Formstrip racing stripes appear on each side of the shoe above the red heel panel, while the Puma brand name and logo appear in metallic-gold letters on the outer side right above it. The tongue and heel also feature metallic-gold Puma branding. The rubber outsole is black and patterned for traction. 
 
What we like best about this sneaker is the slim design that truly supports the speed-enhancing features. The Puma Speedcat OG Red White was first released on June 29, 2024, for an original price of $120.

name: Rose Pink
title: New Balance 9060 Rose Pink
description:
The New Balance 9060 Rose Pink is a sneaker whose design was inspired by New Balance’s 99X models, but with a more futuristic look.

This version of the New Balance 9060 is made with a mesh and suede upper. White mesh makes up the base, while shades of pale, light, and darker pink adorn the suede overlays that cross the midsole, toebox, and heel. The New Balance "N" appears on both midsoles just under the laces, on one side in gray, and on the other side in dashed white lines. The midsole is made of ABZORB cushioning. Other branding elements can be found at the bottom of the laces, on the tongue, on the heel, and stamped onto the toe portion of the rubber outsole. The heel is supported by a silver panel and the chunky outsole appears in white and pink.

What we like most about this shoe are the different shades of pink that make up the overlays. While the design is soft, it gives the shoe more visual appeal. The New Balance 9060 Rose Pink was released on March 15, 2024, for a retail price of $150.

name: Día De Muertos
title: Nike Air Max 1 PRM Día De Muertos
description:
The Nike Air Max 1 PRM Día De Muertos takes the Air Max 1 silhouette and applies Day of the Dead (Día de los Muertos) themed graphics and a vibrant colorway.

The sneaker boasts a colorway of Green Strike, Sail, Opti Yellow, and Hyper Pink. Bright pink tones make up the base. The Swoosh on the side, the flower details on the heel, and the swirling designs across the shoe resemble the intricate patterns painted on sugar skulls during the Day of the Dead festivities. The Opti Yellow matches the color of chrysanthemum flowers, and Hyper Pink-like hues are often found on decorations placed on Day of the Dead altars. The upper is mesh, while the overlays and heel panels are crafted from leather.

Our experts appreciate how the visible Air Max unit in the midsole matches the upper tones. The Nike Air Max 1 PRM Día De Muertos was released on October 21st, 2023, and retailed at $160.

name: Orange Label Wolf Grey Gum
title: Nike SB Dunk Low Pro ISO Orange Label Wolf Grey Gum
description:
Nike continued its Orange Label collection, releasing another Nike SB Dunk Low Pro model in a new Wolf Grey Gum colorway.

The Nike Low Pro ISO Orange Label Wolf Grey Gum is constructed with a premium Wolf Grey upper, white leather Nike Swoosh, and gum outsole. Nike SB’s Orange Label collection features premium materials and special packaging along with Nike’s signature orange branding.

The Nike SB Dunk Low Pro ISO Orange Label Wolf Grey Gum released February 24, 2023, with a retail price of $110.
model: Nike SB Dunk Low Pro ISO

name: Plum Eclipse (Women's)
title: Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Plum Eclipse (Women's)
description:
The Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Plum Eclipse (Women's) is a heavily texturized performance running sneaker with overlapping materials that create a layered look.

The sneaker features a plum-inspired colorway of Plum Eclipse, Black, Earth, Pink Oxford, and Reflective Silver. The upper is made of light mesh in deep Plum Eclipse, while soft suede overlays in Pink Oxford provide gentle contrast. A plastic panel with stripe designs sits behind the Swoosh and helps the shoe keep its shape. The sneaker also houses a honeycomb-like plastic panel wrapping around the heel that adds additional texture as well as structure.

Our experts love the shoe’s reflective detailing. Reflective Silver shoots up the overlays, covers the Swoosh, adds pops of light to the laces, and shines from behind the mesh upper. The women’s size Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Plum Eclipse (Women's) was released on November 6th, 2023, and retailed at $160.

name: Year of the Mamba University Red
title: Nike Kobe 5 Protro Year of the Mamba University Red
description:
The Nike Kobe 5 Protro Year of the Mamba University Red is a vibrant celebration of Kobe Bryant’s legacy and the 2025 Lunar New Year. Inspired by the Year of the Snake, this sneaker features a bold university red base with gold details and intricate snake motifs that pay homage to Kobe’s "Black Mamba" nickname. A golden snake wraps around the sides, while metallic gold accents highlight the toe box, heel, and tongue logo.

The textured snakeskin pattern on the collar gives the sneaker a luxurious edge, complementing the bold design. Black swoosh logos and a durable black rubber outsole ground the shoe with striking contrast, ensuring it’s as functional as it is stylish. Packed with Protro performance updates, this iteration stays true to Kobe’s ethos of innovation and excellence.

Released on January 18, 2025, the Nike Kobe 5 Protro Year of the Mamba University Red retailed for $190. This pair dropped exclusively in China to celebrate Kobe Bryant’s enduring impact and the joy and fortune associated with the Lunar New Year.

name: sacai Undercover Black Bright Citron
title: Nike LD Waffle sacai Undercover Black Bright Citron
description:
The Nike LDWaffle sacai Undercover Black Bright Citron is constructed with a black nylon upper with white and Bright Citron leather, and tonal grey hairy suede overlays. In alignment with other LDWaffles, the tongues, overlays, and soles are doubled, carrying out sacai's reconstructive design aesthetic.

The Nike LDWaffle sacai Undercover Black Bright Citron released in October of 2021 and retailed for $170.

name: Bacon (2021)
title: Nike Air Max 90 NRG Bacon (2021)
description:
The Nike Air Max 90 Bacon is still one of the most highly sought-after Air Max runners of all time. So much so that Nike brought back the 2004 design to celebrate Air Max Day in 2021. It is not often that Nike retros collaborations, while most rarely resurface. But with its continuously growing fan base and pleas from Air Max fans to revive the 16-year-old colorway, Nike brought back the sneaker in its OG form.

The Nike Air Max 90 Bacon returns with all of the design qualities from the 2004 collaboration with Dave’s Quality Meat’s creator, David Ortiz. Mimicking the different shades of colors that appear from raw bacon, the sneaker is composed of various shades of brown, red, pink, and off-white. With a combination of suede, tumbled leather, and mesh, this Air Max 90 brings a luxe feel to the traditional 1990 model.

The Nike Air Max 90 Bacon released in March of 2021 for $140.

name: Dark Stucco
title: Nike Air Max 1 SC Dark Stucco
description:
The Nike Air Max 1 SC Dark Stucco takes the Air Max 1 that was originally released in 1987 and applies a rich colorway of Dark Stucco, black, and Phantom.
