The upper is made of durable mesh in Phantom with suede overlays in Dark Stucco that create a color-blocking effect. The addition of a black leather mudguard creates additional tonal and textural contrast. The black leather Swoosh logos peek out from behind the suede heel counter and check across the side panels. Other branding details include ‘NIKE AIR’ bisected by a Swoosh embroidered across the heel counter in Phantom thread, and a discrete logo tag on the tongue. The midsole houses a visible Air Max unit in the heel that can be seen through transparent windows.

Our StockX experts like the defined tread on the rubber outsole, which adds long-lasting traction. The Nike Air Max 1 SC Dark Stucco was released on January 3rd, 2024, and retailed at $150.

name: Billie Eilish Triple White
title: Nike Air Force 1 Low SP Billie Eilish Triple White
description:
The Nike Air Force 1 Low SP Billie Eilish Triple White is clad in a single-color scheme that define its look – a white hue.

This SP Billie Eilish Triple White Nike Air Force 1 Low sneaker has a clean and pure color scheme. The white fabric upper has been enhanced with a mosaic-style pattern, accentuated by stitching in the same tone and white leather patches that are sewn on. The insoles are made of cork and display Nike x Billie Eilish branding, and the singer's personal logo can be seen on the lace dubrae, which is a molded piece. The low-top sneaker has a matching white rubber cupsole, with an Air-sole heel unit enclosed within a foam wedge.

According to our experts' assessment, the Nike Air Force 1 Low SP Billie Eilish Triple White has become more popular in the market due to its extensive selection of colors. This shoe was introduced on March 23rd, 2023, and it was suggested to be purchased for $130.

name: Red Stardust
title: Nike Dunk Low PRM Red Stardust
description:
The Nike Dunk Low PRM Red Stardust is a low-top sneaker made from premium materials to ensure durability and comfort.

This version of the Nike Dunk Low PRM is made with a light textile upper in a Tan Sand color. The textile base allows for flexibility and extra comfort for the wearer. High-quality suede and leather overlays adorn the toebox, the area under the laces, and down around the heel in a Red Stardust color. The Nike Swoosh adorns the midsole in white. The tongue also has a Nike patch, and the heel contains the Nike brand name on a white tab. The rubber outsole is both white and Red Stardust, sticking to the shoe’s clean and crisp color scheme.

Our favorite feature of this shoe is the smooth textile upper in Tan Sand. The color and texture not only look clean, but also add a sense of comfort and casualness to the shoe. The Nike Dunk Low PRM Red Stardust was released on February 7, 2024, for a price of $125.

name: Stencil Swoosh
title: Nike Dunk Low Stencil Swoosh
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Stencil Swoosh features a double logo with a spray-painted design.

The white tumbled leather upper of this Low Nike Dunk has perforations in the toe box and gray tumbled leather overlays. The side panel boasts a stitched-on dark gray tumbled leather Swoosh and the opposite side panel features a double stenciled-on Swoosh in gray and black. The model also has Nike branding on the tongue, the insole, and the heel. A white midsole with full-length cushioning and a black rubber outsole completes the look.

The Nike Dunk Low Stencil Swoosh was released on December 21st, 2022 for a retail price of $110.

name: Lakers (2022)
title: Jordan 1 Mid Lakers (2022)
description:
The Air Jordan 1 Mid Lakers 2022 is a mid-top sneaker dressed in the NBA Los Angeles Lakers’ trademark colors of yellow and purple.

This shoe features a leather upper with purple overlays, white side panels, a black mesh tongue and laces, and yellow accents on the round perforated toe box and ankle collar. The sneaker sports the white Air Jordan Wings logo on the lateral ankle and Jumpman branding on the tongue and insole. A white midsole and a black rubber outsole with a linear pattern complete the design.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid Lakers 2022 was originally made available on September 17th, 2022, with its retail price set at $125.

name: Praline (Women's)
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Praline (Women's)
description:
The Jordan 1 Retro High OG in Praline (Women´s) is a high-top basketball sneaker that reimagines the original AJ 1 silhouette. The design is inspired by luxury handbags, adding a unique layer to this athletic shoe.

This iteration of the Retro High OG Air Jordan 1 Praline for Women is constructed with a premium white leather base that is perforated on the toebox. Caramel-colored "praline" leather overlays appear lining the toe, beneath the laces, on the heel, and wrapping around the ankle. The Nike Swoosh also appears in Praline on the midsole, while white Air Jordan branding is seen on the ankle strap.

What our StockX experts like most about this sneaker is the lace design. The flat laces are shiny and satin-like, adding an extra touch of luxury to these sneakers. The Jordan 1 Retro High OG Praline (Women´s) was released on September 13th, 2023, at a retail price of $180.

name: Canyon Gold Deep Ocean (Women's)
title: Nike Air Max Sunder Canyon Gold Deep Ocean (Women's)
description:
The Nike Air Max Sunder Canyon Gold Deep Ocean (Women's) is a relaunch of the original sneaker from 1999 that maintains many retro elements.

At the Canyon Gold Deep Ocean (Women's) Nike Air Max Sunder, A zip fastening secures the polyurethane shroud and features a large circular pull tab as well as black-tone hardware. Two pull tabs help you put on or take off the shoe, while the rubber outsole houses responsive, visible Air Max units in the heel. In addition, Nike Air cushioning in the forefoot provides bounce. What makes this sneaker stand out is the ultra-bright colorway of Canyon Gold, Deep Ocean, and Speed Yellow with accents in Light Smoke Gray. The orange and yellow hues fade across the shroud and add pops of color to the outsole.

Our experts like the nod to Nike’s offices around the world – the numbers ‘6453’ that are revealed beneath the zip fastening. The women’s size Nike Air Max Sunder Canyon Gold Deep Ocean (Women's) was released on July 11, 2024, and sold for $180.

name: Diamond Shorts
title: Jordan 1 Mid Diamond Shorts
description:
The Jordan 1 Mid Diamond Shorts arrives with a smooth white leather upper with black Durabuck overlays and Swooshes. At the ankle, a traditional Wings logo nods to the origins of the Air Jordan collection. A Jumpman woven tongue label and semi-translucent outsole add the finishing touch.

The Jordan 1 Mid Diamond Shorts released in February of 2022 and retailed for $120.

name: Union Passport Pack Argon
title: Nike Dunk Low Union Passport Pack Argon
description:
Commemorating Chris Gibbs' rarest Dunk pick-ups from his travels to Japan in the early 2000s, the Nike Dunk Low Union LA Passport Pack Argon takes cues from the 2001 Nike Dunk Low CO.JP Argon. It arrives with a tonal blue smooth leather construction that is wrapped in a tear-away, semi-translucent ripstop nylon covering. From there, a Union LA Frontman logo on the heel and "UN|LA" quarter panel tabs add the finishing touch.

The Nike Dunk Low Union LA Passport Pack Argon released in April of 2022 and retailed for $150.

name: Racer Blue Flat Silver
title: Nike P-6000 Racer Blue Flat Silver
description:
The Nike P-6000 Racer Blue Flat Silver is a running and lifestyle sneaker inspired by Pegasus models from the early 2000s, including the Air Pegasus 2006.

Like its predecessors, the Racer Blue Flat Silver Nike P-6000 features a lightweight design with responsive cushioning in the slightly chunky midsole. The foam midsole sits on a rubber outsole, while a front lace closure system secures the shoe. The upper is a breathable mesh with a web of vertical and horizontal leather overlays on top. While the base comes in Racer Blue, Flat Silver accents can be found on the overlays and the laces. Black adds a third color on the leather mudguard, outlining the Swoosh logos and on the tongue.

Our experts at StockX like the molded design of the synthetic leather Swoosh logos on the side panels. The Nike P-6000 Racer Blue Flat Silver was released on January 15, 2024, and retailed at $110.

name: Pine Green
title: Jordan 1 Retro Low Golf Pine Green
description:
The Jordan 1 Retro Low Golf Pine Green is a low-top golf shoe with a design inspired by the classic Jordan 1 basketball shoe.

This version of the Jordan 1 Retro Low Golf is made with a white leather upper. The toebox is perforated for extra breathability and air flow. Gray suede overlays round out the toebox, come up under the laces, and round out the heel. The Nike Swoosh appears in Pine Green on the midsoles, and the heel collar is the same color. The Air Jordan logo appears in white on the heel collar, and the tongue contains a Jumpman logo patch. The outsole of the shoe is white and green on the bottom, and the bottom has been adapted for golf athletes in its patterning.

Our favorite thing about this shoe is the Pine Green accents, which give the otherwise simple shoe a nice pop of color. The Jordan 1 Retro Low Golf Pine Green was released on March 22, 2024, for a price of $150.

name: Bark
title: adidas Campus 00s Bark
description:
The adidas Campus 00s Bark arrives in a bark, cloud white college-style shade and an off-white midsole.​
​​
​Uppers of the adidas Campus 00s Bark are designed from premium bark brown suede constructing, which renders strength and stability. It features a leather base, with the side panels entailing the 3-Stripes in white. Comfort from its inner cushioning is paramount, preventing joint contact while walking. The underfoot and the off-white midsoles are heightened to promote traction and flexibility while walking and running. Its treads act as an anti-slip feature for this shoe, providing traction. The lace-up reduces shoe movement and adds grip to feet during performances. The shoe’s design concludes atop a chocolate-color tread outsole as an allusion of the Campus brand history.​
​​
​We believe that the standout features of the adidas Campus 00s Bark are its curving shape and its color combination, making a fit for variety attires. The shoe retailed at a price of $90 when released, on December 1st, 2022.​
​​
​

name: Turtledove (2022)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Turtledove (2022)
description:
Seven years following its 2015 debut, the iconic adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Turtle Dove made its return.

While the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Turtle Dove (2022) does arrive with the same brown and grey patterned Primeknit upper, rope laces, and grooved Boost sole as the original release, there are some minor differences. The 2022 iteration is packaged in an updated box and features an upgraded outsole, built for daily wear.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Turtle Dove (2022) released in August of 2022 and retailed for $230.

To shop the original adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Turtle Dove, click here.

name: Royalty Taxi
title: Jordan 12 Retro Royalty Taxi
description:
Drawing a strong resemblance to the original Air Jordan 12 Taxi, the Air Jordan 12 Royalty Taxi elevates the classic design with minor alterations in its detailing.

The design features a white tumbled leather upper with a black toe wrap and gold hook eyelets. A new feature is on the toe wrap, where a gold plaquet is prominent on the lateral side. From there, a woven heel tag and matching sole completes the design.

The Air Jordan 12 Royalty Taxi releases in November of 2021 and retails for $190.

name: Hi-Res Red
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Hi-Res Red
description:
The adidas Yeezy 700 Hi-Res Red arrives with a bright red mesh and suede upper with black and grey suede overlays at the toe. In a different style from the original Yeezy 700s, the design opts for a fully circular lacing system, meaning that the ends of the laces are connected, eliminating a need for a bow on the shoe. This lacing system is similar to recent Yeezy 350s and 380s like the Onyx and Calcite Glow. At the base, a sculptural clay red Boost sole with hits of teal and bright orange provide cushioning and support.

The adidas Yeezy 700 Hi-Res Red released in June of 2022 and retailed for $300.

name: Black White Gum (Women's)
title: New Balance 327 Black White Gum (Women's)
description:
The New Balance 327 Black White Gum W takes on a 70s-style silhouette that became one of the most celebrated in the running catalog for women.

The upper section of this 327 model features a synthetic black base with black suede overlays and an oversized "N" on the side panel in white tumbled leather. New Balance branding appears on the tongue tag, insole, and the medial mudguard. A thick white midsole and a gum outsole with dot-pattern traction that curls up the toe and the heel rounds out the look of this shoe.

The New Balance 327 Black White Gum W was released on July 21, 2022 for $100 retail.

name: Bleached Coral
title: Jordan 1 Low OG Bleached Coral
description:
The Air Jordan 1 Low OG Bleached Coral features a white smooth leather and black cracked leather upper with vibrant Bleached Coral suede vamps and heel wraps. At the heel. A signature Jordan Wings logo nods to the very first Air Jordan logo that predates the Jumpman. From there, a white Air sole completes the design.

The Air Jordan 1 Low OG Bleached Coral Pack released in July of 2022 and retailed for $130.

name: Pink Sand (GS)
title: New Balance 2002R Pink Sand (GS)
description:
The New Balance 2002R Pink Sand (GS) is a grade school-sized version of the New Balance 2002R that comes in a soft pink and off-white colorway of Pink Sand and Quartz Pink.

Like other iterations of the 2002R, the Pink Sand GS version is a performance sneaker with cutout segments and overlapping overlays. The upper features mesh combined with suede and soft leather paneling. The "N" logo stands out against the side panel and comes in a grey tone that matches parts of the rubber outsole and the metallic detailing on the heel. Gel pods in the heel give the sneaker a futuristic aesthetic and propel the foot forward with each step.

Our experts love the line etching across the side of the midsole. It creates the illusion of movement without overwhelming the upper design. The New Balance 2002R Pink Sand (GS) was released on June 27th, 2023, and retailed at $100.

name: Mica Green
title: Nike Dunk Low Mica Green
description:
Nike is adding the recently popular Mica Green colorway to part of its Spring/Summer 2023 collection, with the addition of the Nike Dunk Low Mica Green.

The Nike Dunk Low Mica Green is constructed using a Photon Dust canvas and Mica Green leather uppers. Nike used a sail midsole to help give the sneaker a vintage inspired look, and used Mica Green laces to sit over the matching colored tongue.

The Nike Dunk Low Mica Green released May 16, 2023, with a retail price of $110.

name: Vintage Teal
title: New Balance 550 Vintage Teal
description:
The New Balance 550 Vintage Teal is a low-top model that is designed to embody the spirit of the 80s. It is a remake of the original model that was released by the American sport brand for professional basketball players in 1989.

This New Balance 550 model has a clean upper that has a white base made of leather. This is paired with various leather and suede overlays that are in shades of dark green and light gray. The classic NB logo appears on the side in white and green, and the shoe features bright white shoelaces and a matching white tongue. The toebox has a round design and the footcage includes multiple perforations for breathability.

One feature that our team of experts particularly enjoys about the New Balance 550 Vintage Teal is the rubber gum sole in white and dark green that is designed to provide support and traction. This model was first released on June 21st, 2023, and its starting retail price was $120.

name: Grey Matter Silver Metallic
title: New Balance 530 Grey Matter Silver Metallic
description:
The New Balance 530 Grey Matter Silver Metallic features the look of classic New Balance running shoes with heritage details. This running shoe combines retro style with dependable comfort, support, and durability.

The Grey Matter Silver Metallic iteration of the New Balance 530 running shoe sports an upper of white mesh for a lightweight feel as well as breathability. Silver synthetics course across the upper, adding aesthetic appeal as well as support. A matte gray side panel N is outlined in black and matches the 530 branding on a lateral collar overlay. The pull tab on the heel facilitates the putting on and removal of this pair of kicks and New Balance branding graces the tongue.

What our shoe experts enjoy most about this sneaker is the ABZORB midsole segmented to provide support under the heel and forefoot separately. The outsole, also segmented, is black rubber grooved for traction, durability, and impact absorption. The New Balance 530 Grey Matter Silver Metallic was released on August 28th, 2023, for $120 retail.

name: Patent Bred (GS)
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Patent Bred (GS)
description:
A modified version of Michael Jordan’s first signature sneaker, the grade school Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG Bred Patent GS is an outstanding colorway.

Since its release, the Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG Bred Patent GS has earned a lot of market success primarily because it boasts accented details, including an upper constructed from patent leather, a woven tongue tag, a debossed Air Jordan Wings logo on the ankle, an encapsulated Air-sole cushioning, and an enhanced red rubber outsole.

The gradeschool Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG Bred Patent GS released in December 2021. It retailed at $130.

name: Black Glacier Grey
title: ASICS Gel-1130 Black Glacier Grey
description:
Built on a silhouette originally launched in 2008, the ASICS Gel-1130 Black Glacier Gray is a stability running shoe that exudes retro vibes infused with more modern details.

The Black Glacier Gray ASICS Gel-1130 begins with an upper of black mesh. Leather strips course across the upper, in shades of gray, black, and white. These overlays offer an early 2000’s running shoe aesthetic, as well as support, enhanced at both the toe cap and heel. The black foam midsole features GEL technology in the heel for ultimate comfort cushioning. An incorporated TRUSSTIC support system improves stability with every step. Rounding it out, a black rubber outsole helps provide impact absorption and traction.

Our favorite detail of this sneaker is the reflective detailing that enhances the side panel overlays in order to help make you more visible when you run in low-light conditions. The ASICS Gel-1130 Black Glacier Gray was released on April 15, 2024, for $100 retail.

name: Gorge Green Ostrich (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low LX Gorge Green Ostrich (Women's)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low LX Gorge Green Ostrich (Women's) adds eye-catching Ostrich-print detailing to the Nike Dunk Low’s classic silhouette.

This version of the Dunk Low is an "LX" shoe, which means it’s "Deluxe" and created with high-quality materials. For example, the white upper is made of premium leather, while the faux ostrich print heel and overlays are also made of leather. The vivid Gorge Green tone of the ostrich print stands out against the white background and gives the sneaker a premium feel. The Swoosh on the side panels, the heel tab, and the insole's ‘NIKE’ branding also come in Gorge Green. However, the ‘NIKE’ lettering and Swoosh on the tongue boast metallic gold. Like other versions of the Dunk Low, the "LX Gorge Green Ostrich (Women’s)" features a low-cut design and a durable rubber outsole.

Our experts at StockX like the inclusion of Gorge Green laces that tonally match the shiny overlays. The women’s size Nike Dunk Low LX Gorge Green Ostrich (Women's) was released on February 17th, 2024, and retailed at $135.

name: Travis Scott Mocha
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG SP Travis Scott Mocha
description:
The first release as part of Travis Scott's monumental partnership with Nike, the Air Jordan 1 Travis Scott breaks the conventional rules of the Air Jordan 1 design. For starters, the side Swooshes are reversed, which each tailing facing the toe. Woven tongue tags are shifted and stitched to the side of the tongue instead of the top. Also, in the collar, there is a hidden stash pocket. A one-of-a-kind design fit for a one-of-a-kind artist.

The Air Jordan 1 Travis Scott features a white leather upper with Mocha suede overlays and black leather reversed Swooshes. Hits of red on the tongue slightly contrast the design's earth tones. On the heel, a debossed Cactus Jack logo adds a custom feel. From there, a yellowed midsole and matching Mocha outsole complete the design.

The Jordan 1 Travis Scott Mocha released in May 2019 and retailed for $175.

To shop all Air Jordan 1 shoes, click here.

name: Cherry (2023) (GS)
title: Jordan 12 Retro Cherry (2023) (GS)
description:
The Jordan 12 Retro Cherry (2023) (GS) joins the recognizable Jordan 12 lineup in a grade school size with a vintage-inspired colorway.

This tri-tone colorway of White, Varsity Red, and Black was first seen on an AJ12 during Michael Jordan’s 1996-1997 NBA season. The Jordan 12 Retro Cherry (GS) (2023) finds inspiration in the original shoe, as well as a similar AJ12 model released in 2009. Like others before it, the 2023 iteration features lizard skin-textured overlays in Varsity Red that fortify the white, leather upper. The sneaker boasts a full-length Zoom Air unit as well as a Phylon midsole. The semi-translucent outsole reveals herringbone designs and tread in a similar pattern.

Something our experts love about this sneaker is the minimal branding. The shoe comes with the Jumpman logo on the tongue and outsole, and a Jordan pull tab on the heel, but it does not display the Swoosh. The grade school-sized Jordan 12 Retro Cherry (2023) (GS) was released on October 28, 2023, and retailed at $150.

name: Bred Reimagined (TD)
title: Jordan 4 Retro Bred Reimagined (TD)
description:
The Jordan 4 Retro Bred Reimagined (TD) commemorates 35 years of the Air Jordan 4. This sneaker specifically sized for toddlers reimagines an iconic silhouette and a classic colorway.

The Retro Bred Reimagined Air Jordan 4 for Toddlers features an upper base and overlays constructed of supple black leather with an aged aesthetic. Black mesh windows appear at the bottom of the laces and on the quarter panel. Black laces match a black tongue, and the tongue liner is red to match the insole, which contrasts with the white sock liner. Nike Air branding adorns the heel and insole, and a red Jumpman appears on the tongue.

We find that the most impressive feature of this sneaker is the sole unit. The white foam midsole houses visible Air for ultimate cushioning, and the rubber outsole in gray, red, and white sports a herring bone traction pattern. The Jordan 4 Retro Bred Reimagined (TD) was released on Michael Jordan's 61st birthday, February 17th, 2024. The original retail price was $85.

name: Cream Black
title: ASICS Gel-Nimbus 9 Cream Black
description:
The ASICS Gel-Nimbus 9 Cream Black is an industrial-style sneaker that was originally designed for distance running. It features a Cream base with accents in black and metallic silver.

Unlike other versions of the Y2K-inspired Gel-Nimbus 9, the Cream Black ASICS Gel-Nimbus 9 doesn’t have color blocking or bold contrast. Instead, the tiger stripe overlays streaks across the side panels and crisscross the airy mesh upper. The overlays are crafted from durable leather, while the inner lining is made from a synthetic material. A front lace closure system secures the fit, while padding in the collar protects the ankle.

Something our experts at StockX like is the segmented midsole, which features gel inserts in the heel and forefoot. These gel inserts provide cushioning on a variety of surfaces ranging from pavement to dirt. Plus, the segmented design supports stability and stable steps. The ASICS Gel-Nimbus 9 Cream Black was released on January 1, 2024, and sold for $160.

name: Born X Raised One Block At A Time
title: Nike SB Dunk Low Born X Raised One Block At A Time
description:
Introducing the Born x Raised One Block At A Time Nike SB Dunk Low, showcased in a Deep Royal Blue and White colorway.

This isn't just another Dunk – it's a collaboration with the legendary LA brand, Born x Raised. Representing the culture of LA with a hint of luxury, the upper mixes premium leather with nubuck and silver detailing on the iconic Nike Swoosh & heel tab. "One Block At a Time" is embroidered on the mudguard & featured on the tongue. The heel features "On The Turf" with an extra Nike Swoosh on the back of the midsole. Ensuring you're not only wearing a shoe but a statement. This shoe effortlessly mirrors LA's vibrant and dynamic style. Its design boasts of its heritage while nudging to the future. And of course, the iconic Dunk silhouette ensures a snug fit and ultimate comfort.

In essence, the Born x Raised collab is where street meets sneaker. This masterpiece dropped on shelves at a retail price of $130.

name: Día De Muertos
title: Jordan 1 High Zoom Air CMFT 2 Día De Muertos
description:
The Jordan 1 High Zoom Air CMFT 2 Día De Muertos is a tribute to the rich tradition and the Day of the Dead celebration. Its design encapsulates the vibrant and respectful spirit of Día De Muertos with color schemes that pay homage to the traditional Mexican holiday. The quality construction with classic Jordan 1 detailing makes it a comfortable yet stylish choice.​
​​
​The sneaker's design elements reflect a modern interpretation of a timeless silhouette. The cushioning of the Zoom Air unit ensures a comfy stride while the unique colorway and detailing resonate with the tradition it represents, making it a meaningful and fashionable choice.​
​​
​Step into a legacy of style and cultural richness with the Jordan 1 High Zoom Air CMFT 2 Día De Muertos. Released on October 21, 2023, and retailing at $165, this sneaker is a beautiful blend of tradition, comfort, and modern design that will make a significant addition to your collection.​
​​
​DISCLAIMER: Paint patterns may slightly differ on each pair of the Jordan 1 High Zoom Air CMFT 2 Día De Muertos.

name: Christmas (2023)
title: Nike KD 3 Christmas (2023)
description:
The Nike KD 3 Retro Christmas (2023) stands out as a vibrant and technologically advanced basketball shoe, showcasing a vivid color scheme in Vibrant Yellow, Team Orange, and Photo Blue.

Crafted from smooth, full-grain leather, the Christmas Nike KD 3 Retro (2023) upper exudes a polished and sleek aesthetic. The incorporation of Flywire construction in the forefoot ensures lightweight support and a secure fit. Photo Blue and Team Orange accents embellish various elements, including the tongue tab, profile Swooshes, Flywire branding, and video game controller buttons affixed to the heel. Adding to the comfort, the shoe features a soft nylon inner lining and a Zoom Air cushioning system, providing both cushioning and responsiveness.

The outstanding characteristic of the Nike KD 3 Retro Christmas (2023) is its Zoom Air cushioning system, a technology that delivers exceptional comfort and responsiveness, establishing the shoe as a top choice for performance. The sneaker debuted for $130 on December 19th, 2023.

name: Cream Clay Grey (Women's)
title: ASICS Gel-1130 Cream Clay Grey (Women's)
description:
The ASICS Gel-1130 Cream Clay Grey (Women's) combines modern design with retro running influences, including a neutral tone blend. Its silhouette reimagines classic ASICS design, which has always been focused on sensible athletic wear.

The Cream Clay Grey Gel-1130 by ASICS women's shoe features a breathable mesh upper with overlays in synthetic leather for durability. The color palette includes creamy off-white tones with grey accents for a clean, minimalist finish. ASICS branding appears on the side panels and tongue to add a subtle contrast. The Gel-1130 was first introduced in 2008 and draws inspiration from the Gel-1000 series and highlights ASICS' rich history with performance footwear.

One thing we, the experts, love about the ASICS Gel-1130 Cream Clay Grey (Women's) is its GEL technology for exceptional shock absorption and the stabilizing Trusstic System for added support during movement. Released on August 12, 2024, it retailed at $95, giving you reliable innovation to thrive.

name: Pure (First Release)
title: adidas Yeezy Slide Pure (First Release)
description:
DISCLAIMER: US and UK sizing is the same and does not require any conversion.

The adidas Yeezy Slide Pure is constructed of Pure EVA foam with a soft footbed that offers an immediate step in comfort. An outsole with accentuated grooves for traction and support adds the finishing touches to the design.

The adidas Yeezy Slide Pure released in April of 2021 and retailed for $60.

name: Miami Heat
title: Nike LeBron 20 Miami Heat
description:
The Nike Lebron 20 Miami Heat, available in different hues - including black, university red, university gold, and light smoke gray - is one of the collaborative designs between this iconic American brand and the NBA champion from Akron.

The upper section of the Lebron 20 model is made of black woven textile with a double Swoosh on its right side. The sneaker has an elongated tongue beneath the laces made from cotton. Its midsole and outsole, which are both made from rubber, appears in the black and red colors.

The Nike Lebron 20 Miami Heat was first released on October 24th, 2022 with $200 as the retail price.

name: Moonbeam Sea Salt
title: New Balance 9060 Moonbeam Sea Salt
description:
The New Balance 9060 Moonbeam Sea Salt is designed to capture elements of the preceding 99X, a classic New Balance model, and draws inspiration from Y2K era aesthetics.

Sea salt, rain cloud and moonbeam colors are used for the sneaker. The upper is made from an off-white mesh that is fitted with sea salt pigskin suede overlays. Rain cloud accents are found in the "N" logo on the quarter panels, and the heel tab with the New Balance logo in off-white. The outer sole is made from a grey rubber sole, with the midsole uses Abzorb and SBS cushioning. The heel has a translucent CR fitting, while the tongue logo uses jewels inspired by the 991 sneaker. The shoe’s look is complemented with grey insole and lining, rain cloud laces, and punched eyelets at the throat.

What do our experts like about the New Balance 9060 Moonbeam Sea Salt? Our experts at StockX like the downplayed color gamut selected for the classic sneaker silhouette, and the choice of lightweight materials. New Balance released the sneaker on 26th July 2023 for $160.

name: Dark Blue Pink Spark (Women's)
title: adidas Gazelle Bold Dark Blue Pink Spark (Women's)
description:
The adidas Gazelle Bold Dark Blue Pink Spark (Women's) paints the Gazelle Bold silhouette in a luxurious colorway of dark blue and Pink Spark.

This low-top Dark Blue Pink Spark (Women's) adidas Gazelle Bold updates the original Gazelle from the 1970s with a stacked platform featuring three layers of gum rubber. Each layer ‘showcases adidas’ and the signature trefoil logo. Although the upper is made of woven nylon in dark blue, the suede accents on the toebox overlay and around the laces celebrate the original Gazelle. Another contemporary addition is the shiny Pink Spark satin on the 3-Stripes logo and the heel mustache. Finishing the look, the logo tag on the tongue also comes in Pink Spark.

Our experts appreciate the ‘GAZELLE’ gold foil lettering along the 3-Stripes because it’s a heritage Gazelle design element. The women’s size adidas Gazelle Bold Dark Blue Pink Spark (Women's) was originally released on June 1, 2024, and was priced at $120.

name: Method of Make Perfect Pink (Women's)
title: Jordan 1 Low Method of Make Perfect Pink (Women's)
description:
The Jordan 1 Low Method of Make Perfect Pink (Women's) is part of the Method of Make series, which offers luxurious, elevated versions of classic sneakers.

This sneaker boasts an all-over Perfect Pink construction with metallic gold hardware. For example, a gold tab engraved with AIR JORDAN occupies the place of the woven logo tag on the tongue. Similarly, the Air Jordan Wings logo on the heel and the Swoosh on the side panel are made from metal pieces in gold. Another luxury feature is the oversized leather stitching on the heel and forefoot overlays. Like other Jordan 1 Low models, the Method of Make Perfect Pink version features an air unit in the heel and a rubber outsole underfoot.

Our experts at StockX like the addition of classic laces in Perfect Pink. The women’s-size Jordan 1 Low Method of Make Perfect Pink (Women's) was released on April 18, 2024, and retailed at $135.

name: White Navy
title: New Balance 9060 White Navy
description:
The New Balance 9060 White Navy is a running shoe from the New Balance 9060 silhouette in a white and navy colorway.

This New Balance 9060 sneaker features an upper made of white mesh with matching leather overlays. Navy-colored New Balance hits on the forefoot, the signature "N" logo on the sides, and the heel adds a pop of color to the upper. Other details include a slashed "N" embroidered on the medial, "NB 9060" branding on the tongue, cream laces, and more New Balance branding on the heel, vamp, and insole. Rounding out the design is a dual-color bulky midsole with SBS and ABZORB cushioning atop a navy rubber outsole. 

Something we love about this New Balance running shoe is its luxurious build, technology, and classic colorway, which guarantee comfort and add a premium touch to the design. The New Balance 9060 White Navy was released on June 16th, 2023, for a retail price of $150.

name: Silver Metallic Black Gum (Women's)
title: adidas Samba OG Silver Metallic Black Gum (Women's)
description:
The adidas Samba OG Silver Metallic Black Gum (Women's), in women’s sizes, is a lifestyle shoe featuring a Silver Metallic leather upper, accented by adidas’ signature three stripes in Core Black. Core Black laces and a Core Black heel tab coordinate with the stripes, as does a Gum 5 outsole, which features a deeper shade of gum rubber. Samba branding is imprinted on the side, while adidas branding appears on the tongue.

German athletic wear and sneaker powerhouse adidas’ heritage dates to 1924, and adidas founder Adolf Dassler designed the Samba in 1949. As one of the shoes most closely associated with adidas, the Samba has achieved iconic status. For the Samba OG, adidas has varied the signature black and white color palette to show the stylish range of this classic shoe.

Our experts feel that the best feature of the Samba OG is its Gum 5 outsole, which grounds the Silver Metallic upper. The adidas Samba OG Silver Metallic Black Gum (Women's) released on June 20, 2024, and retailed at $100.

name: Light
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Light
description:
At a glance, the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Light arrives in a clean triple white color palette, but when exposed to light, the white Primeknit upper changes to light pink and its mesh side stripe to dark yellow. An off-white Boost sole and canvas heel tab add the finishing touches.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Light released in August of 2021 and retailed for $220.

name: Triple White (2021) (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Triple White (2021) (Women's)
description:
Everything is white in the monochromatic Nike Dunk Low Triple White 2021 (W).

The women's Nike Dunk Low Triple White 2021 (W) features leather uppers, supple leathers making up the side paneling, and a breathable mesh is used for the tongue. Touches of black are served on the Nike branding atop the tongue and insoles, with everything else clad in a crisp white hue. The midsole and treading below also add to its appeal, with everything served up with colorless finishes. 

The women's Nike Dunk Low Triple White 2021 (W) was released in August 2021 and retailed for $100.

name: Aluminum Gum (Women's)
title: adidas Samba OG Aluminum Gum (Women's)
description:
The adidas Samba OG Aluminum Gum (Women's) includes many elements of the recognizable OG Samba while introducing a neutral tone colorway of Aluminum, Chalk White, and Wonder Beige.

The silhouette stays true to the OG model while adding elements that elevate the sneaker from a football training shoe to a streetwear staple. This sneaker showcases the iconic sidewall stripes with serrated edges against the full-grain upper. In terms of branding, the tongue features the adidas Trefoil, and ‘SAMBA’ is printed alongside the sidewall stripes in gold lettering. Although most of the shoe boasts soft leather, the toe overlays are made of suede. The signature Samba gum rubber midsole increases traction while providing additional cushioning.

Our experts love the sneaker’s overall soft aesthetic, which includes a subtle colorway, silky suede, and a design made for comfort. The women’s size adidas Samba OG Aluminum Gum (Women's) was released on July 25, 2023, and retailed at $100.

name: Wanda
title: Nike KD 16 NRG Wanda
description:
The Nike KD 16 NRG Wanda celebrates the strength and resilience of Kevin Durant's mother, Wanda, with its Mint Foam/Metallic Silver/Emerald Rise/Stadium Green/Pure Platinum/Smoke Grey colorway. This sneaker is a symbol of Durant's gratitude and respect, blending personal storytelling with exceptional performance features.

Equipped with Nike's advanced cushioning and a supportive yet flexible upper, the KD 16 NRG Wanda offers both comfort and stability. Its unique color scheme and meaningful design elements make it a standout piece.

When it was released on November 1, 2023, for $160, the Nike KD 16 NRG Wanda resonated deeply with fans, offering a blend of Durant's personal journey and top-tier basketball technology.

name: Light Orewood Brown
title: Nike Zoom Vomero 5 SE Light Orewood Brown
description:
The Nike Zoom Vomero 5 SE Light Orewood Brown is a special edition sneaker that applies a Light Orewood Brown colorway with hints of white and dark brown to the Zoom Vomero 5 silhouette.

The upper is crafted from loose-weave mesh with leather and synthetic leather overlays, while a honeycomb-like web provides support around the heel, adding a touch of texture. The sneaker features nostalgic elements inspired by early 2000s running shoes, such as the exaggerated midsole pods. Reflective detailing across the upper not only enhances visibility in low lighting but also adds a nostalgic touch, as do the retro motifs of the Swoosh logos on the side panels and heel.

Our StockX experts like Armory Blue on the midsole and outsole, which provides a pop of color against the upper’s neutral tones. The Nike Zoom Vomero 5 SE Light Orewood Brown was released on February 2, 2024, and retailed at $160.

name: Sean Wotherspoon Hemp Green
title: adidas Gazelle Indoor Sean Wotherspoon Hemp Green
description:
The adidas Gazelle Indoor Sean Wotherspoon Hemp Green represents a collaboration between the iconic sneaker company and designer Sean Wotherspoon. This sneaker takes a classic silhouette and dresses it in sustainability.

The Sean Wotherspoon x adidas Gazelle Indoor Hemp Green sports an upper of woven hemp. White and green stitching patterns course across the shoe, interrupted only by the characteristic three stripes along the side panel, in white serrated leather. The heel tab is bright orange, adding a hint of color, while the tongue and laces are both pearly white. The sock liner is white, and the insole is cork. The outsole is translucent gum rubber with a traction pattern of circles and rings. The translucent gum rubber works its way up the upper a bit to form a sort of mudguard.

What our experts enjoy most about this shoe are the hits of dual branding. Sean Wotherspoon branding appears on the heel tab and insole, while adidas branding appears on the tongue, mudguard, and outsole. The adidas Gazelle Indoor Sean Wotherspoon Hemp Green was released on November 16, 2023, for a retail price of $140.

name: Chrome (Women's)
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Chrome (Women's)
description:
The Jordan 1 Retro High OG Chrome (Women's) is known for its combination of classic design and modern flair.

It features a timeless silhouette that pays homage to the original Air Jordan 1 released in 1985. Like other Air Jordan 1 models, the Retro High OG Chrome prioritizes comfort and support. It features a padded collar and tongue for cushioning around the ankle, as well as an encapsulated Air-Sole unit in the heel which offers responsive cushioning even during all-day wear. This shoe boasts a high-top design and is crafted from premium leather to ensure durability. Nike’s iconic branding can be found on the sides of the shoe, as well as in the wings logo on the collar and the tongue.

The standout feature of the Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG Chrome (Women's), however, is its striking metallic "chrome" colorway. This shoe was originally released with a price tag of $180 on April 10, 2024.

name: Vintage Team Red (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low PRM Vintage Team Red (Women's)
description:
Nike is adding another colorway to its Dunk rotation, with the release of the women’s-exclusive Nike Dunk Low PRM Team Red.

​The Nike Dunk Low PRM Team Red is constructed using premium Team Red and white leather uppers. The sneakers are tied together using white laces and have Coconut Milk colored midsoles to help give the sneaker an aged finish. Nike used Team Red on the sockliner, outsoles and heel of the women’s-exclusive sneakers. ​
​
​The women’s-exclusive Nike Dunk Low PRM Team Red released April 21, 2023, with a retail price of $120.

name: Dark Team Red Black
title: Nike Dunk Low Dark Team Red Black
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Dark Team Red Black takes the Dunk Low silhouette and applies color-blocking in Dark Team Red, Summit White, and black.

The base construction features Summit White leather with Dark Team Red overlays in the same material. The Swoosh logos on the side panel, the rubber outsole, and the heel tab come in black, while the laces and Nike branding featured on the tongue boast Dark Team Red. Another branding detail, the word "NIKE" embroidered in Summit White thread, graces the heel tab. Perforations across the vamp and the use of mesh on the tongue allow the foot to breathe.

Our StockX experts like the woven logo tag on the tongue. It features ‘NIKE’ with a small Swoosh in Dark Team Red ink and contributes to the sneaker’s retro appearance. The Nike Dunk Low Dark Team Red Black was released on January 13th, 2024, and retailed at $115.

name: White Metallic Silver
title: Nike Zoom LeBron NXXT Gen White Metallic Silver
description:
The Nike Zoom LeBron NXXT Gen White Metallic Silver comes in a white and metallic silver colorway with black accents.

The upper part of the Zoom LeBron NXXT Gen White Metallic Silver is designed with Flyknit material, which provides a lightweight, supportive, and breathable fit around the foot. Additionally, the Nike logo features on the tongue while the Zoom Air branding is visible on the heel. The midsole features Nike's proprietary Zoom Air technology, which is designed to provide a responsive and comfortable cushioning system. The translucent outsole design provides traction and durability on any surface, while the Lunarlon foam in the midsole offers cushioning and absorbs shock during landings. Similarly, the shoe's padded collar and tongue provide additional cushioning and comfort.

We think that the key feature of the Nike Zoom LeBron NXXT Gen White Metallic Silver is its Flywire lacing technology that locks the foot in place and adds stability. The shoe was released on April 1st, 2023 at a retail price of $160.

name: UNC (2021)
title: Nike Dunk Low UNC (2021)
description:
Nodding to the University of North Carolina Tarheels, the Nike Dunk Low UNC is constructed of a white leather upper with University Blue overlays and Swooshes. From there, a white and University woven Nike tongue label completes the design.

The Nike Dunk Low UNC released in June of 2021 and retailed for $100.

name: White Noise (Women's)
title: Nike Sabrina 2 White Noise (Women's)
description:
The Nike Sabrina 2 White Noise (Women's) revamps WNBA player Sabrina Ionescu’s second signature basketball shoe. It boasts a crisp white colorway with Glacial Blue and Metallic Silver accents.

Although the colorway is reminiscent of the SB Dunk Low Diamond Supply Co. White Diamond from 2018, the women's Nike White Noise Sabrina 2 offers a sleeker silhouette and performance-enhancing tech for the basketball court. An example, the sneaker replaces the Sabrina 1’s React cushioning with a responsive Air Zoom unit on the forefoot and two types of Cushlon foam underfoot. The firmer foam provides a supportive feel, while the softer variety protects against impact. Finally, cables with reinforced stitching and fitted a band contain the midfoot without restricting movement.

Our experts at StockX like the inspiration behind the name "White Noise." It references Ionescu’s ability to ignore negative criticism. The women’s size Nike Sabrina 2 White Noise (Women's) was released on October 1, 2024, and sold for $130.

name: Akoya
title: Nike LeBron 21 Akoya
description:
Drawing inspiration from the beauty of oyster shells, the Nike LeBron 21 Akoya is a low-profile basketball shoe that seamlessly blends style and practicality.

The upper of the Akoya Nike LeBron 21 is crafted from an off-white leather, giving it a refined and fashionable appearance. The design is further enhanced by Lively Orange highlights, visible in the Nike Swoosh's lining and the lace locks. The shoe boasts a semi-translucent white rubber sole that complements its Pristine White midsole. The LeBron 21 Akoya is fitted with a Zoom Turbo unit at the forefoot and a 13-millimeter Zoom unit at the bottom, both designed to aid in propulsion. The shoe also incorporates a full-length Cushlon 2.0 foam carrier for a consistently soft and comfortable feel. A unique feature of the shoe is its 360-degree zonal cabling system, cleverly concealed by a high-quality lightweight fabric, which provides superior containment.

The most remarkable feature of the Nike LeBron 21 Akoya is undoubtedly its 360-degree zonal cabling system. This cutting-edge feature ensures maximum containment, offering the player unparalleled support and stability over the footbed. The sneaker debuted for $200 on September 28th, 2023.

name: Miami Hurricanes
title: Nike Dunk Low Retro Miami Hurricanes
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Retro Miami Hurricanes arrives in orange and green, the colors of the University of Miami.

This Low Nike Dunk is made from 100% leather material. The sneaker has an orange leather base with green overlays. Orange also appears on the matching laces and nylon tongue, and green is featured on the Swoosh, the inner lining, and the branding on the tongue. The models has orange "NIKE" branding on the heels, and the shoe rests on a white midsole and a green rubber outsole.

The Nike Dunk Low Retro Miami Hurricanes was released on the 1st of October 2022 and initially retailed for $110.

name: Field Purple
title: Nike Air Max 1 SC Field Purple
description:
The Nike Air Max 1 SC Field Purple is a performance shoe whose original design was inspired by Parisian architecture.

This iteration of the Nike Air Max 1 SC is made with a white mesh base which makes up the toe box, the sides, and the area around the ankle. Gray leather overlays cross the sides of the shoe from the laces to the arches, and the heel counter is the same shade of gray leather. Field Purple leather forms the mudguard, which runs from the arch on the inside of the shoe all the way around the front to the lateral heel. The Nike swoosh also appears in Field Purple leather on the sides. Both the heel and the tongue feature Nike branding in purple, and a thick white rubber sole with visible Air Max units under the heel completes the look.

What we like most about this shoe are the Field Purple accents, which give the shoe a bold but still clean look. The Nike Air Max 1 SC Field Purple was released on May 1, 2024, for a price of $150.

name: Clay Ash
title: New Balance 9060 Clay Ash
description:
The New Balance 9060 Clay Ash reinterprets the innovative style of the 99X. With a warped and futuristic sensibility, the vibe of this sneaker exudes a dynamic sense of visible motion.

The upper of the Clay Ash New Balance 9060 has a base of breathable, lightweight linen-colored mesh. This is overlaid with wavy strips of leather in light green and light pink that add support as well as a Y2K aesthetic. The silvery-gray side-panel N complements the translucent CR device at the heel that helps lock in support. The dual density midsole in hues of tan and dark vintage rose features both SBS and ABZORB cushioning for ultimate springy bounce. The black rubber outsole encapsulates white diamond-shaped rubber pods to absorb shock and provide grip.

The detail of this sneaker that we most enjoy is the branded tongue tag that takes its inspiration from the lace jewel of the original 991. The New Balance 9060 Clay Ash debuted on March 15, 2024, for $150 retail.

name: Mystic Red Cargo Khaki
title: Nike Dunk Low Mystic Red Cargo Khaki
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Mystic Red Cargo Khaki arrives adorned in a dual-tone leather upper, showcasing a Tomato Red base with dark olive green overlays and a correspondingly colored Swoosh.

Characterized by a vibrant Mystic Red foundation, the Mystic Red Cargo Khaki Nike Dunk Low design is accentuated by Cargo Khaki overlays and a matching Swoosh, all expertly crafted from premium smooth leather. The Mystic Red dominates the upper, aligning with matching tongues, insoles, and embroidered heel branding, contributing to its overall visually striking appeal. Traditional Nike branding details adorn the back tab, sock liner, and the woven tag on the breathable nylon tongue. The rich earth tones on the upper find contrast in a pristine white midsole, featuring stitched sidewall construction and an interior foam wedge. A red rubber outsole rounds off the design, ensuring reliable traction.

The distinctive feature of the Nike Dunk Low Mystic Red Cargo Khaki is its unique and eye-catching color scheme. The harmonious blend of Mystic Red and Cargo Khaki not only captivates, but also offers versatility to the overall aesthetic. The sneaker debuted for $115 on August 12th, 2023.

name: Lucky Shorts
title: Jordan 3 Retro Lucky Shorts
description:
The Jordan 3 Retro Lucky Shorts pays homage to one of Michael Jordan’s most well-known game-day rituals—wearing his UNC practice shorts under his uniform for good luck. This tradition, which began after his iconic 1982 NCAA Championship-winning shot, is now immortalized in sneaker form. The shoe boasts a summit white leather upper, complemented by photon dust grey accents on the toe guard and heel, creating a clean and classic foundation.

A nod to Jordan’s college days, legend blue makes a bold statement on the Jumpman logo and heel, ensuring the heritage is felt throughout the design. One of the standout details is the behind-the-tongue label, designed to mimic the tags found on basketball shorts. It references the years Jordan’s lucky shorts tradition was in full swing, adding a subtle but meaningful touch for die-hard fans. The sail midsole and pure platinum detailing round out the colorway, keeping the design refined yet fresh.

Released on February 22, 2025, the Jordan 3 Retro Lucky Shorts retailed at $200, bringing history and superstition to life through a timeless silhouette. With its mix of summit white, hydrogen blue, legend blue, photon dust, pure platinum, and sail, this pair is a perfect blend of legacy and everyday style.

name: Clay Red
title: adidas Yeezy Foam RNR Clay Red
description:
The adidas Yeezy Foam RNR Clay Red arrives in an all-Clay Red color palette, in a lightweight foam construction.

The Clay Red adidas Yeezy Foam RNR has an upper constructed from a single piece of soft, lightweight foam material. The shoe features a slip-on construction without the incorporation of laces for easy put-on and take-off. The shoe features a distinct textured pattern on the upper. In addition, the shoe features cushioning in the midsole, ensuring comfort and responsiveness. The shoe's outsole unit is built of a durable foam material that provides shock absorption and traction.

What we love about the adidas Yeezy Foam RNR Clay Red is its unique and eye-catching design. These sneakers feature a noticeable Clay Red colorway that adds a bold and vibrant element to the overall look. The shoe was released on May 31st, 2023, and sold for a retail price of $90.

name: Nothing But Net
title: Jordan 1 Mule Golf Nothing But Net
description:
The Jordan 1 Mule Golf Nothing But Net is a mule with a white leather base and a textile pattern inspired by the long-sleeved shirt Michael Jordan wore in a 1993 McDonald’s commercial.

The pattern displays overlapping zigzags resembling lightning bolts in Obsidian, Speed Yellow, University Red, Grape Ice, and Blue Orbit. This pattern is also on the mudguard, the forefoot overlays, the panels where the lace cage would usually be, and around the heel. Perforations across the vamp allow the foot to breathe, while carved tread on the outsole provides traction on various surfaces, including wet grass found on golf courses. Although the shoe has a tongue, it doesn’t have laces or eyelets.

Our experts at StockX like the distinct Jumpman logo on the tongue and the "golf" lettering. The Jordan 1 Mule Golf Nothing But Net was initially released on May 31, 2024, and sold for $110.

name: Michigan (2021/2024) (GS)
title: Nike Dunk Low Michigan (2021/2024) (GS)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Michigan for grade school sizes (GS) brings back one of the original colorways from the 1985 ‘Be True to Your School’ series, reimagined as a low-top and offered in grade school sizing. The Nike Dunk Low Michigan (GS) low-profile silhouette carries an all-leather upper and is built on a Varsity Maize yellow base with Midnight Navy overlays. Perforations on the toe box provide breathability, while a lightly padded nylon tongue that bears the Nike woven brand tag supports the fit. Underfoot, a Midnight Navy rubber outsole atop a White midsole to complete the design.

The Nike Dunk Low Michigan (GS) was released in April 2021 and retailed for $85.

name: Hemp Light British Tan
title: Jordan 1 Low SE Hemp Light British Tan
description:
The Jordan 1 Low SE Hemp Light British Tan is a straightforward version of the Air Jordan 1 that’s crafted with premium materials and covered in various shades of beige and tan.

The Hemp Light British Tan Jordan 1 Low SE’s all-leather upper provides a crisp appearance that elevates the sporty AJ1 to dress-shoe levels. The combination of Hemp, Light British Tan, Sail, and Oatmeal leather creates a clear distinction between the overlays. One of the sneaker’s stand-out details is the leather Swoosh. It checks across the side panels and displays off-white stitching that is a lighter color than the Swoosh’s leather. The Air Jordan Wings logo is embossed onto the heel, which provides another premium addition to this special-edition sneaker.

Our experts like the inclusion of hidden Nike Air cushioning in the heel. It’s another small detail that transforms one of the most iconic sports sneakers of all time into a more formal shoe. The Jordan 1 Low SE Hemp Light British Tan was released on May 15, 2024, and sold for $190.

name: Arizona State
title: Nike Dunk Low Arizona State
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Arizona State takes on the college aesthetics and features an all-leather upper with a bordeaux base and yellow overlays.

This low-profile shoe also has a mesh tongue and sock liner in the same color-blocking design. Other details include yellow Swooshes, a lace-up closure system with bordeaux laces, a perforated toe box, and ‘NIKE’ branding on the heel tab, tongue tab, and insoles. The white midsole sits on a yellow rubber outsole that has a visible linear pattern for traction.

The Nike Dunk Low Arizona State was released on November 25th, 2022, with a retail price set at $100.

name: Flint (2020)
title: Jordan 13 Retro Flint (2020)
description:
Jordan Brand brought back one of the first Air Jordan 13 colorways with the release of the Jordan 13 Retro Flint (2020), now available on StockX. With previous retros in 2005 and 2010, this is the third time that the Jordan 13 Flint has been reintroduced.

This Jordan 13 Retro consists of a navy mesh and white leather upper with flint grey suede underlays. A Jumpman holograph on the ankle, 3M detailing throughout the upper, and Carolina blue branding on the tongue completes the design. These sneakers released in May of 2020 and retailed for $190 USD.

name: Supreme Desert Camo
title: Nike SB Darwin Low Supreme Desert Camo
description:
The Nike SB Darwin Low Supreme Desert Camo is a sneaker with a low-top silhouette that’s part of a collaborative series between Supreme and Nike Skateboarding. This sneaker finds inspiration in the original Darwin sneaker from the 1990s but adds a bold camouflage pattern.

The camouflage pattern features patches of khaki, orange-brown, white, and black, giving it a slightly lighter tone than traditional camo. The upper is made entirely of canvas, which serves as a durable backdrop for the camouflage pattern. Like other versions of the Nike SB Darwin Low, this sneaker features a reverse Swoosh on the heel, a small SUPREME logo tag on the side panel, and dual-branding on the tongue logo tag. The thick sole unit wraps around the shoe and forms ridges that overlap the canvas upper.

Our StockX experts like the way the black lace loops match the outsole. The Nike SB Darwin Low Supreme Desert Camo was initially released on May 2, 2024, and sold for $118.

name: Eagle
title: Nike Kyrie 8 Eagle
description:
The Nike Kyrie 8 Eagle is a high-performance basketball shoe created by Nike and NBA player Kyrie Irving. It boasts a clean Glacier Blue base with accents in Yellow Strike, Orange Trance, and Oxen Brown.

Inspired by Irving’s Native American heritage, this sneaker displays an eagle motif beneath the semi-translucent Glacier Blue upper. The eagle symbolizes power as well as the athlete’s connection to the Wampanoag tribe. The sneaker also displays "ELIZABETH ANN IRVING" embossed into the Strike Yellow midsole, which pays tribute to Irving's late mother.In terms of technology, the midsole houses React foam and Air Zoom Strobel cushioning. The signature Swoosh logo comes in Orange Trance and Yellow Strike and is partially obscured by the midsole.

Our experts at StockX like the inclusion of symbols close to Irving’s heart and the use of bright colors on the upper. The Nike Kyrie 8 Eagle was released on December 8, 2020, and retailed at $140.

name: White Old Royal
title: Nike Air Max 2 CB '94 White Old Royal
description:
Designed for former NBA player Charles Barkley, the Nike Air Max 2 CB 94 White Varsity Purple is a retro-inspired Nike Air Max CB 94 sneaker in a Varsity Purple and white colorway.

This sneaker features a white leather upper with large perforations on the overlays and tiny perforations on the base and Black detailing on the ‘NIKE’ wording branding on the lateral, heel branding, heel pull tab, tongue, and laces. This sneaker utilizes a web-style lacing system supported by a midfoot harness. A black and purple sole unit with a visible Air unit in the heel completes the profile.

The Nike Air Max 2 CB 94 White Varsity Purple was released on February 15, 2021 with a retail price of $160. They were re-released on January 4th, 2024.

name: Purple Rain
title: Nike LeBron 21 Purple Rain
description:
The Nike LeBron 21 Purple Rain pays homage to the greatness of both LeBron James and the legendary artist Prince, fusing the realms of music and basketball in a unique collaboration.

Taking inspiration from the iconic song Purple Rain, the Purple Rain Nike LeBron 21 is draped in a soft Violet Dust hue, extending to the oval laces and tongue construction. Vivid Melon Tint accents accentuate the prominent Swooshes, tongue tab logo, and central lace loops. An iridescent Purple Cosmos finish enhances the Zoom Air cushioned heel. Additionally, the design subtly references the signature colors of the Lakers. The insole features a graphic that directly nods to the late rock and roll legend.

The standout aspect of the Nike LeBron 21 Purple Rain lies in its insole design, featuring a hand adorned with rings, symbolizing LeBron James' four NBA championships. This thoughtful detail adds a personal and meaningful touch to the shoe, commemorating LeBron's remarkable achievements throughout his illustrious career. The sneaker debuted for $200 on October 14th, 2023.

name: Triple White
title: New Balance 530 Triple White
description:
The New Balance 530 Triple White integrates modern technology with heritage design elements from New Balance’s 2000s catalog.

From the midsole to the lace, the Triple White New Balance 530 boasts an entirely white construction. The mesh underlays feature a loose weave that provides an airy feel, while the overlays offer support and represent a throwback to New Balance’s early 2000s running shoes. Other retro details include the heavy padding in the collar and tongue, the segmented pods in the midsole, and the sneaker’s visible tech aesthetic. However, the responsive Gel technology in the midsole keeps the sneaker contemporary and provides advanced energy return. The lace-up closure secures the fit, while the pull tabs ease entry.

Our experts at StockX like the textured grip tread on the rubber outsole, which provides traction on indoor and outdoor surfaces. The New Balance 530 Triple White was released on November 28, 2023, and sold for $100.

name: White Oyster Grey
title: ASICS Gel-NYC White Oyster Grey
description:
The ASICS Gel-NYC White Oyster Grey is an athletic shoe that takes its design inspiration from the early 2000s running era.

The White Oyster Grey ASICS Gel-NYC has a base of white mesh on the upper. Metallic silver overlays cross the upper over the mesh for support, including on the toe box, up the sides, and around the heel. The ASICS design appears on each side in Oyster Grey, while the white mudguard also features Oyster Grey embellishments near the heel. ASICS branding is seen on the lateral heel and tongue, while Gel branding is found on the back of the heel. The shoe rests on a midsole composed of different shades of gray and white and is equipped with Gel technology.

Our favorite thing about this shoe is the crisp, clean colorway, which allows the shoe to be versatile and still neutral. The ASICS Gel-NYC White Oyster Grey was released on October 1, 2024, for $130.

name: Light Armory Blue Photon Dust (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Light Armory Blue Photon Dust (Women's)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Light Armory Blue Photon Dust (Women's) takes the Dunk Low silhouette and adds an upper crafted from shaggy suede that gives the sneaker a furry appearance.

While Photon Dust is the primary color of the upper, the overlays come in Light Armory Blue. A shaggy suede Swoosh checks across the side panel and displays a Light Smoke Gray color that can also be found on the heel tab. The application of these light colors gives the shaggy suede an even softer appearance and makes the color-blocking effect subtle. Like other Nike Dunk Low models, the "Light Armory Blue Photon Dust" variation comes with perforations across the toebox, allowing the foot to breathe.

Our StockX experts like the use of Light Armory Blue on the rubber outsole. The women’s size Nike Dunk Low Light Armory Blue Photon Dust (Women's) was released on January 25th, 2024, and retailed at $135.

name: Gore-Tex JJJJound Charcoal
title: New Balance 2002R Gore-Tex JJJJound Charcoal
description:
The New Balance 2002R Gore-Tex JJJJound Charcoal is part of the second collaboration between New Balance and JJJJound. This sneaker adapts the 2002R’s signature silhouette to a wintery environment with weatherproof design elements.

For example, although the upper is made of leather and mesh, it incorporates a Gore-Tex lining. This lining prevents water from entering the shoe while allowing the foot to breathe and stay warm. The sneaker’s colorway of charcoal and black speaks to its utilitarian roots. In terms of branding, the New Balance ‘N’ in black leather graces the side panel and 2002R branding can be found near the heel. 'GORE-TEX' lettering in white ink is also printed above the 2002R branding.

Something our StockX experts like is the front lace-up system with an adjustable toggle. It allows the wearer to adapt the sneaker to his or her needs. The New Balance 2002R Gore-Tex JJJJound Charcoal was released on February 15th, 2024, and retailed at $190.

name: Maroon Crystal Sand (Women's)
title: adidas Samba OG Maroon Crystal Sand (Women's)
description:
The adidas Samba OG Maroon Crystal Sand (Women's) combines a rich color palette with age-old design elements to bring you a new take on the classic Samba silhouette. With premium materials and refined details, this release offers a fresh perspective.

The women's version of these Maroon Crystal Sand adidas Samba OG by adidas comes with a maroon leather upper with crystal sand suede overlays and gold metallic branding accents. A textured rubber sole provides traction and stability, while tonal laces complete the look. The standard three stripes run down each side of the shoe, with Samba written in gold on the right. The Samba was originally introduced in the 1950s for indoor football and has since evolved into a popular everyday shoe.

One thing we, the experts, love about the adidas Samba OG Maroon Crystal Sand (Women's) is its white metallic detailing, which adds an elegant touch. Another thing that stands out is the long-lasting suede overlays. Released on January 1, 2024, this trainer retailed at $100.

name: White Black Details
title: New Balance 530 White Black Details
description:
The New Balance 530 White Black Details is a colorway part of the New Balance Brand Collection.

These athletic shoes include ABZORB technology with a rubber sole. The top is made of durable synthetic leather and mesh. These New Balance sneakers have traditional laces, a drag strip, and a protective toe cap. They also combine an ENCAP midsole with a suede, leather, and mesh upper. Further, they feature an all-white perforated mesh upper sole with a black padded insole. It displays the black "N" logo on its side with the "530" writing near its heel.

The New Balance 530 White Black Details debuted on March 28, 2022, and retailed at a price of $120.

name: Duck Pecan Yellow Ochre
title: Nike Air Max 1 PRM Duck Pecan Yellow Ochre
description:
The Nike Air Max 1 PRM Duck Pecan, inspired by the "Ugly Duckling" Pack, has become a celebrated model in the catalog.

Dressed in a pecan/yellow ochre color scheme, this sneaker features a premium suede build throughout the upper with a Baroque brown base and pecan hits on the panels and heel overlays. Yellow ochre accents the laces, Swooshes, tongue branding, and the duck motif embroidered on the heel, while the mudguard and sock liner opt for a tonal shade. The design is finished with visible AIR units in the soles for cushioning.

The Nike Air Max 1 PRM Duck Pecan was released on December 20th, 2022, retailing at $160.

name: White Gold Red (Women's)
title: Nike P-6000 White Gold Red (Women's)
description:
Since its debut, the women’s Nike P 6000 White Gold Red (Women) continues to record the highest number of sales in Nike’s P 6000 series.

The upper of Nike P 6000 White Gold Red is made of a mixture of white, black, and metallic gold synthetic materials, premium leather, and textile. The rests on a midsole made from white foam, featuring a cushioned sock liner. The outsole of Nike P 6000 White Gold Red (Women) is made of rubber, red at its heel, and black at the toe-front.

Nike P 6000 White Gold Red (women) was first released on May 20, 2019. At the time of its release, the price of the the shoe was $100.

name: Better Scarlet Clear Pink
title: adidas Campus 00s Better Scarlet Clear Pink
description:
The adidas Campus 00s Better Scarlet Clear Pink updates the classic adidas Campus 80s with a Better Scarlet and Clear Pink colorway while maintaining the OG shoe’s collegiate aesthetic.

The 00s Better Scarlet Clear Pink variation features an upper of premium leather and a soft lining made of terry cloth. The sneaker offers a bulkier silhouette than other adidas shoes inspired by footwear from the 1980s. The tongue and collar are padded, while the fat cotton laces dominate the lace cage. The sneaker comes with two pairs of laces: one in Better Scarlet and the other in Clear Pink. The laces match either the serrated 3-stripes or the leather upper.

What do our experts like most about this shoe? We like the line of perforations that separates each line of the 3-stripes design, allowing the foot to breathe. The adidas Campus 00s Better Scarlet Clear Pink was released on April 5th, 2023, and retailed at $110.

name: Bad Bunny Lionel Messi La Voz De Los Fans
title: adidas Gazelle Indoor Bad Bunny Lionel Messi La Voz De Los Fans
description:
This triple-way collaboration makes the adidas Gazelle Indoor Bad Bunny Lionel Messi La Voz De Los Fans one of the coolest sneaks around. It's a classic street shoe perfect for lovers of popular culture.

These adidas collaboration sneakers bring street cred to life in a premium shoe based on the classic silhouette of the Gazelle. Combining rapper Bad Bunny, footballer Lionel Messi, and fashion brand adidas, the ‘voice of the people’ shoe is made from leather and suede in a tan and cream color blend. The 3-Stripes stay faithful to their usual placement on the sides while the back heel sports a leather X overlay. On the 3-Stripes are the signatures ‘Benito’ and ‘Leo’ in red, handwritten script. The perforated toe box gives breathability, while the rubber outsole provides traction and grip.

Fashion-forward and elevated, these Gazelles effortlessly up your sneaker game. Representing the voice of the fans of music, sport, and fashion in one shoe, the adidas Gazelle Indoor Bad Bunny Lionel Messi La Voz De Los Fans sneakers were released on 26 October 2024, priced at $180.

name: AMBUSH Phantom
title: Nike Air Force 1 Low SP AMBUSH Phantom
description:
Nike is collaborating with AMBUSH to celebrate the 40th anniversary of the Air Force 1, by releasing the Nike Air Force 1 Low SP AMBUSH Phantom.

Ambush and Nike used an off-white Phantom colorway from top to bottom on their Air Force 1 collaboration. Nike used an oversized black swoosh that hangs off the heel, and black AMBUSH branding on the tongue, lace-locks, and insoles.

The Nike Air Force 1 Low SP AMBUSH Phantom released February 28, 2023, with a retail price of $190.

name: Black White
title: Puma Speedcat OG Black White
description:
The Puma Speedcat OG Black White dresses this classic low-top sneaker from the early 2000s in a straightforward colorway of black and white.

Inspired by motorsports and Puma’s apparel partnerships with several F1 teams, this lifestyle shoe boasts a sleek, slim-fitting silhouette. The upper is crafted from premium suede in black with the signature formstrip in white reaching across the side panels. In addition, the Black White Puma Speedcat OG showcases subtle Puma branding, including ‘PUMA’ in metallic gold lettering on the lateral side panel and the tongue, and a white Jumping Cat logo on the toebox. The thin, rubber outsole comes in black and offers traction underfoot, while the black laces secure the closure.

Our experts like the sneaker’s overall premium feel created by the metallic gold accents set against the velvety suede upper. The Puma Speedcat OG Black White was released on June 29, 2024, and sold for $120.

name: Drake NOCTA Black Yellow
title: Nike Hot Step Air Terra Drake NOCTA Black Yellow
description:
The Nike Hot Step Air Terra Drake NOCTA Black University Gold is a collaboration between Nike and Drake’s NOCTA sublevel.

The Nike Hot Step Air Terra has pebbled black leather uppers marked with reflective 3M hits on the side panels and down the tongues. The shoe has contrasting bright accents in the form of mini Swooshes at the lateral heel regions and NOCTA markings on the rears and the tongues. The sneaker has black rope laces, sculpted sole units with large Air units, specially printed insoles, and G-TEK traction rubber outsoles.

The Nike Hot Step Air Terra Drake NOCTA Black University Gold was released on September 16, 2022, with a retail price of $180.

name: White Black Panda (TD)
title: Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black Panda (TD)
description:
A toddler’s shoe (TD), the Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black TD comes in a classic colorway. Crafted from soft leather, the Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black (TD) upper is made from a white base overlaid by contrasting black throughout. The black extends to the iconic Swoosh branding and the lightly padded nylon tongue. The tooling continues the two-toned design to include a white midsole and a black rubber outsole that draws directly from the Air Jordan 1.

The Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black (TD) was released in March 2021 at a retail price of $50.

name: Olympic (2024)
title: Nike Air More Uptempo 96 Olympic (2024)
description:
The Nike Air More Uptempo 96 Olympic (2024) updates the OG sneaker worn by basketball player Scottie Pippen at the 1996 Atlanta Olympics with a patriotic colorway.

The velvety nubuck construction of the Olympic (2024) Nike Air More Uptempo 96 comes in Midnight Navy, while the exaggerated "AIR" lettering wraps around the shoe and comes in crisp white. These colors reach over the midsole, which houses a visible air sole unit. Pops of University Red appear on the dual Swoosh logos on the rubber outsole and the Swoosh embroidered on the leather tongue tag. The heel displays a jewel Swoosh in Midnight Navy, complementing the tonal heel pull tabs.

Something our StockX experts like is the small details that pay tribute to Scottie Pippen. For example, the number 8 in gold on the heel represents the athlete's Olympic jersey number. The Nike Air More Uptempo 96 Olympic (2024) was released on July 26, 2024, and sold for $170.

name: Escape Treeline
title: Nike Air Max 1 PRM Escape Treeline
description:
The Nike Air Max 1 PRM Escape Treeline is a premium edition of the iconic Air Max 1 sneaker that was released as a new addition to Nike's "Escape" collection, which pays homage to outdoor adventures.
​​
​The Air Max 1 PRM Escape Treeline features a premium leather upper with tree graphics on both lateral sides. The color scheme of the upper is predominantly white with Slate Blue, black, and soft gray overlays. The sneaker is equipped with Nike's iconic Air Max technology in the sole, which provides superior cushioning and shock absorption.​
​
​We think that the unique feature of the Nike Air Max 1 PRM Escape Treeline is its premium construction and materials including a mix of suede, leather, and ballistic nylon, which provide durability and a premium feel to the sneaker. The Nike Air Max 1 PRM Escape Treeline was released on May 25th, 2023, at a listing price of $160.

name: Electric Pack Olympic Safari
title: Nike SB PS8 Electric Pack Olympic Safari
description:
The "Nike SB PS8 Electric Pack Olympic Safari" is a performance skateboarding shoe with black and white speckled detailing.

The Electric Pack Olympic Safari Nike SB PS8 was released in honor of the 2024 Paris Olympics and pays tribute to Sandy Bodecker, who made Nike Skateboarding what it is today. Several technical features elevate this version of the Nike SB PS8 to high-performance levels. For example, a durable cage wraps around the lightweight midsole, which is supported by a full-length pylon plate. In addition, the translucent rubber outsole provides traction on cement, pavement, and other surfaces found in urban environments. Leather overlays at the heel and forefoot feature black speckles set against a white background.

Our experts at StockX like the FlyKnit upper, because it’s lightweight but provides lasting support to the overlays. The Nike SB PS8 Electric Pack Olympic Safari was released on July 24, 2024, and sold for $130.

name: Celtics
title: Nike Dunk Low Celtics
description:
Nike prepares the Dunk Low in stadium green, white, and black colors that match the Boston Celtics' home colors. The court-inspired sneaker that is the Nike Dunk Low Celtics employs an all-leather construction with tonal padding and midsole cushioning.

Right away, a white leather base is overlaid with stadium green leather panels on the mudguards, lace panels, and heel counters. Tonal green laces take on the green motif and end at the vamp, where a white-colored mesh tongue creeps underneath up to the ankle liner. The heel tab hints at a battle between black and green, as the former underlies the latter. The Low Celtics all-leather construction sits atop a white-hued rubber midsole with foam cushioning. To wrap up the design is a grippy rubber outsole dressed in black. The final decorative piece is the usual Nike Swoosh on Dunk Low sneakers, but this time it takes on a tonal black hue for the Celtics-inspired kicks.

What our experts find outstanding about the Dunk Low Celtics is the plush padding on the collar, which builds on the sneaker's comfort proposition. The Nike Dunk Low Celtics were released on June 13th, 2023, retailing at $110.

name: Racer Blue Metallic Silver (Women's)
title: Nike Shox R4 Racer Blue Metallic Silver (Women's)
description:
Nike Shox R4 Racer Blue Metallic Silver (Women's) features Nike Shox technology, which provides foot support, comfort, and stability. It is a low-top shoe made of synthetic leather for longevity and durability. They are lightweight and bouncy, which makes them a good choice for either training or competing.

  Along with the extra cushion, its aerodynamic and rubber outer sole gives it an out-of-this-world look. The racer blue and silver color combo and its laser perforations further add to its futuristic design. It comes in women's shoe sizes 5 to 13.5.

The Nike Shox R4Racer Blue Metallic Silver (Women's) is an updated version and remake of an earlier Nike running shoe from the early 2000s. Our team is most excited about the silver accents on this shoe, including a metallic silver Swoosh, which gives it plenty of style. Nike released this on August 6, 2024. It originally sold for $150.

name: Protection Pack Eclipse
title: New Balance 1906D Protection Pack Eclipse
description:
The New Balance 1906D Protection Pack Eclipse presents an edgy, high-octane running shoe in a stealthy colorway.

The Protection Pack Eclipse iteration of the New Balance 1906D sports an upper of lightweight, breathable navy-blue mesh. Navy and dark gray synthetic leather overlays with uneven, jagged edges undulate across the upper to lend this shoe an unfinished, shabby-chic style. The N-Lock lace system offers a comfortable, snugly secure fit, while the TPU heel counter adds stability to the upper. The black midsole composed of ABZORB works in tandem with the black N-ergy to deliver superior shock absorption.

What we enjoy about this sneaker are the hits of branding peppered throughout the shoe. N-Lock branding appears on the crossbar of the side panel N, 1906D peeks out from a lateral collar overlay, N-ergy branding pops in red on the lateral midsole, and NB branding adorns the heel and tongue tag.
