The New Balance 1906D Protection Pack Eclipse was launched on November 22, 2023, for a retail price of $180.

name: Mambacita Gigi
title: Nike Kobe 4 Protro Mambacita Gigi
description:
Nike is honoring Kobe and Gigi Bryant, with the release of the Kobe 4 Protro Mambacita Gigi. The limited edition sneakers come with a specially designed box, white snakeskin textured box that features gold Mambacita branding on top.

The Nike Kobe 4 Protro Mambacita Gigi is designed in a classic two-tone black and white colorway, with added checkerboard accents on the heel. Nike added some color with gold accents on the tongue, and heel of the sneaker, with the number 2, Gigi Bryant's jersey number. The sneakers come with three different lace options and feature specially branded checkerboarded Mambacita insoles.

The Nike Kobe 4 Protro Mambacita Gigi released May 1, 2023, with a retail price of $180.

name: Metro Boomin
title: Nike KD 17 NRG Metro Boomin
description:
The Nike KD 17 NRG Metro Boomin is part of a line produced by Nike, NBA player Kevin Durant, and producer Metro Boomin that honors the artist’s mother.

The Metro Boomin Nike KD 17 NRG comes in a primarily purple colorway of Atomic Violet, black, white, and Hyper Grape that highlights Metro Boomin’s mother’s favorite color. This sneaker features an Air Zoom unit in the forefoot area and was designed for improving gym workout performance. Metro Boomin’s fisheye-like tag on the tongue is the producer’s branding logo, but also represents the struggles of single mothers. In addition, the inside of the padded tongue bears the names of Metro Boomin’s brothers and sisters.

Our experts at StockX like the design details that pay tribute to Metro Boomin’s difficult past. For example, the lightning storm graphics on the side panels represent Metro Boomin’s fight to overcome personal struggles and the power behind his effort. The Nike KD 17 NRG Metro Boomin was released on June 24, 2024, and sold for $160.

name: Bred
title: Nike Air Max 1 Bred
description:
The Nike Air Max 1 Bred takes a classic Tinker Hatfield design that burst onto the sneaker scene in 1987, streamlines the look, and dresses it in a dark colorway with subtle hits of brightness.

This iteration of the Air Max 1 is built upon an upper base of lightweight, tightly woven mesh in an anthracite hue. Rich black suede forms the overlays that course across this upper, while anthracite leather forms the iconic side panel Nike swoosh. Nike Air Max branding embroidered in red hits the heel, while red branding also adorns the black tongue tag. A red embroidered Nike swoosh accents the lateral toe cap. A foam midsole in anthracite provides cushioning and houses a visible Air cassette under the heel. The black rubber outsole sports modified waffle lugs in order to absorb shock and provide grip with every step.

The detail that we enjoy most about this pair of kicks is the red tinting in the Air unit, which ties together the black and red or ‘bred’ look of the shoe. The Nike Air Max 1 Bred was released on December 19, 2023, for a retail price of $150.

name: Luxury Green
title: adidas Harden Vol. 8 Luxury Green
description:
The adidas Harden Vol. 8 Luxury Green is a basketball shoe that came about as a collaboration between the brand and American basketball point guard James Harden.

This iteration of the adidas Harden Vol. 8 features an upper made of fabric and synthetic leather. Black fabric forms the base, which is designed for a personalized fit to the wearer’s foot. An EVA cage appears on each side of the shoe in Luxury Green, running from under the ankle, down the sides of the laces, down around the toes and sole, and back up the heel. This helps support lateral movements on the court. The green rubber sole runs up part of the back of the heel, and adidas iconic three stripes can be seen breaking it up in black.

Our favorite feature of this shoe is the Luxury Green EVA cage and how it contrasts with the black base. The simple design with bright colors makes the shoe stand out. The adidas Harden Vol. 8 Luxury Green was released on March 15, 2024, for a price of $160.

name: Black Silver
title: Nike Air Max Torch 4 Black Silver
description:
The Nike Air Max Torch 4 Black Silver features a silhouette reminiscent of Sean McDowell's classic Air Max Plus. Designed for support and comfort, this sneaker is dressed in a subtle, stylish colorway.

The Black and Silver Nike Air Max Torch 4 features an upper base of loosely woven black mesh with an underlay of silver. Black synthetic textile overlays adorn the toecap, mud guard, eyestays, and heel. A silver TPU cage undulates vertically up the midfoot, providing style as well as structure. A three-dimensional silver Nike Swoosh adorns the side panel, matching a miniature silver Swoosh on the toe. Nike Air branding in silver appears at the lateral heel and on the tongue tag, completing the look of this upper.

The aspect of this sneaker we appreciate the most is the dependable sole unit. A black Phylon midsole with a visible Max Air unit in the heel offers optimal cushioning. The black rubber outsole with hits of silver features heritage waffle lugs for traction, as well as Max Air branding and a Nike Swoosh. The Nike Air Max Torch 4 Black Silver was released on April 26th, 2018, for $140 retail.

name: Reverse Brazil
title: Nike Dunk Low Retro Reverse Brazil
description:
Nike is setting sails towards South America, with the release of their Nike Dunk Low Retro Reverse Brazil. Nike originally debuted the Brazil Dunk Low in 2001, followed by a retro in 2020. This current retro delivers a new take to the iconic colorway.

This Nike Dunk Low pays homage to the Brazilian national flag with yellow and green color blocking across the uppers. The leather sneakers sit on top of a white midsole and green outsole are tied together with yellow laces.

The Nike Dunk Low Retro Reverse Brazil released February 15, 2023 with a retail price of $110.

name: Vintage Michigan
title: Nike Dunk Low Vintage Michigan
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Vintage Michigan is a low-top sneaker that celebrates the University of Michigan Wolverines, the 2023 College Football National Champions. The sneaker pays homage to the university’s colors by applying Midnight Navy and Tour Yellow to the upper.

The leather upper comes in a black base with leather overlays in Midnight Navy and Tour Yellow accents. For example, the vibrant Swoosh on the side panel, the scribbled pattern wrapping around the heel, and ‘NIKE’ stitched across the heel tab all come in Tour Yellow. In addition, the logo tag on the tongue displays Tour Yellow lettering and a Swoosh logo. The sneaker features a round toe with perforations on the toebox and a front lace closure system.
Our StockX experts love this shoe’s connection to the Michigan Wolverines, and how it was released immediately after the Michigan Football Team completed a perfect season with their third consecutive win against Ohio State and winning the National Championship. The Nike Dunk Low Vintage Michigan was released on February 1st, 2024, and retailed at $125.

name: Patta FC Barcelona Culers del Món
title: Nike Air Max Plus Patta FC Barcelona Culers del Món
description:
The Nike Air Max Plus Patta FC Barcelona Culers del Món is a special edition sneaker, released in part of a collaborative effort with Spanish soccer giants FC Barcelona and the Dutch streetwear brand.

The upper is constructed using breathable mesh and other synthetic materials and has TPU overlays wrapped around it. It has a red and blue color scheme with a top-to-bottom gradient effect while the TPU overlays appear in glossy black. The sole unit appears in black with a white case around the midfoot. This Air Max Plus features double Swoosh branding on both sides, Patta branding on the tongue, and the Barcelona badge on the laces.

Our favorite thing about the Nike Air Max Plus Patta FC Barcelona Culers del Món is the Tuned Air cushioning technology which consists of individual pods of hemispheres in the midsole, allowing for targeted support and cushioning in specific areas of the foot. The shoes were released for retail on 17th October 2023 priced at $210.

name: White Better Scarlet Gum (Women's)
title: adidas Sambae White Better Scarlet Gum (Women's)
description:
The adidas Sambae White Better Scarlet Gum (Women's) adds a Cloud White base with vivid Better Scarlet details to the Sambae silhouette. It also features an exaggerated semi-transparent gum rubber outsole that resembles a platform.

The upper is crafted from smooth leather in Cloud White, while the T-shaped toe overlay comes in beige suede. This sneaker stands out due to the 3-Stripes logo on the side panels because it was created with embroidery instead of suede or leather. The embroidery comes in Better Scarlet and gives the sneaker a premium, texturized look. The heel tab, the branding on the tongue, and the ‘SAMBA’ lettering along the 3-Stripes logo also come in Better Scarlet.

Our StockX experts like the vintage-style adidas branding printed across the tongue. It features the trefoil and ‘adidas’ in a rectangular box. The women’s size adidas Sambae White Better Scarlet Gum (Women's) was released on December 1st, 2023, and sold for $110.

name: Needlework Sail Aura (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Needlework Sail Aura (Women's)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Needlework Sail Aura (W) comes in a sail, neutral grey color palette.

The Needlework Sail Aura Nike Dunk Low (W) has an upper constructed entirely of leather with ship-seated overlays and multi-row stitching. The shoe has a lacing system for an adjustable fit and a cushioned tongue for support. The midsole of the shoe is cushioned with EVA foam for lightweight, responsive cushioning and support. The durable rubber outsole of the shoe provides grip and durability. The shoe features a perforated toe box for breathability. The shoe's design is completed with a Nike Swoosh on either side and Nike branding on the heel.

The women’s rendition of the Nike Dunk Low Needlework Sail Aura (W) was released on March 18, 2023, and retailed for $120.

name: Mirrored (Women's)
title: Nike Sabrina 2 Mirrored (Women's)
description:
The Nike Sabrina 2 Mirrored (Womens) gives a bold look and advanced support that's designed for women athletes who value performance but want to look stylish doing it. This innovative sneaker combines Nike’s signature materials with elegant, reflective accents, creating a striking silhouette.

The Mirrored Sabrina 2 (Women's) by Nike is built with a supportive mesh upper that gives you breathability while holding its structure. Reflective detailing on the side panels and midsole adds a unique mirrored effect, improving the shoe’s visual appeal. A deep-silver base with metallic accents complements its streamlined design, while the mirrored Swoosh gives you the branding you're looking for. Inspired by WNBA’s Sabrina Ionescu’s on-court performance, this model features Nike’s responsive Zoom Air cushioning for impact support, all on a durable rubber outsole built for traction.

We love the reflective side panels and the Zoom Air cushioning in the Nike Sabrina 2 Mirrored (Womens), which combine visual appeal with responsive comfort. Released on August 15, 2024, it retailed at $130.

name: Dark Smoke Grey
title: Nike Air Max 1 Premium Dark Smoke Grey
description:
The Nike Air Max 1 Premium Dark Smoke Grey updates the Air Max 1’s traditional color blocking with mixed material overlays and a dark color palette.

This version of Tinker Hatfield’s iconic shoe draws inspiration from the Centre Pompidou’s exposed fixtures and wires. Just like the museum displays exposed pipes and beams, the Dark Smoke Grey Nike Air Max 1 Premium reveals visible Air Max units in the midsole. Combining black and shades of gray, the upper is crafted from premium leather and suede. The contrasting materials create dimension and a layered appearance. Flash Crimson adds pops of color on the Air Max units and the Swoosh logo on the tongue's woven tag. While the side panel Swoosh logos and forefoot overlay come in Dark Smoke Grey, the mudguard uses lighter Smoke Grey.

Our experts like the contemporary upgrades, including the semitranslucent rubber outsole. The Nike Air Max 1 Premium Dark Smoke Grey was released on August 16, 2024, and sold for $160.

name: Cloud White Blue Gum
title: adidas Samba Cloud White Blue Gum
description:
The adidas Samba Cloud White Blue Gum adds a neutral colorway of Cloud White and a dark gum rubber outsole to the recognizable Samba silhouette.

The upper is made of smooth leather in Cloud White with reinforced, tonal stitching. The serrated 3-Stripes logo on the side panels and the laces come in a slightly brighter white than the base, while the T-shaped toe overlay is made of light-gray suede. The flat tongue peeks out from behind the laces and displays a retro-inspired adidas logo tag in blue. Other branding details include SAMBA printed in metallic gold lettering on the lateral side panel. The sneaker features a synthetic lining and a standard fit.

Our experts at StockX like that the gum rubber cupsole comes in a darker shade, which complements the neutral, full-grain leather. The adidas Samba Cloud White Blue Gum was released on January 1, 2024, and retailed at $120.

name: Platinum Tint Black
title: Nike P-6000 Platinum Tint Black
description:
The Nike P-6000 Platinum Tint Black is a running shoe that combines elements from previous Pegasus models in the Nike catalog, including the Pegasus Air from 2006.

At the Platinum tint Black Nike P-6000, the upper is exceptionally lightweight and crafted from airy mesh in light grey. Thin, synthetic leather overlays in Platinum Tint create a web across the upper and mold to the foot's shape. A medium-sized Swoosh logo lays across the overlays and comes in black with an embroidered outline in Platinum Tint. Additional black accents are on the heel, the rubber outsole, and the collar lining. The tongue tag displays "NIKE" lettering and four perforations, while small Swoosh logos are on the toe and heel.

Our experts at StockX like the full rubber outsole, which provides traction on various surfaces. The Nike P-6000 Platinum Tint Black was initially launched on April 23, 2024, and retailed at $120.

name: Mirage (Sail Outsole)
title: Nike Book 1 EP Mirage (Sail Outsole)
description:
The Nike Book 1 EP Mirage (Sail Outsole) is part of NBA player Devin Booker’s first collaboration with Nike. The "EP" in the name stands for "Engineered Performance," which means the sneaker was designed with performance and durability in mind.

The upper is made of leather in Light Orewood Brown and woven textile panels in a similar off-white color. The leather overlays cross the heel and forefoot areas without forming a lace cage. Swoosh logos in tonal Light Orewood Brown check across the side panels and are outlined in off-white stitching. In terms of technology, the midsole boasts a Zoom air unit and Cushion 2.0 Foam, while TPU sidewalls reinforce the shoe.

Our StockX experts like the use of micro-perforated suede on the heel collar. It gives the sneaker subtle texture and makes the slightly warmer tone on the collar stand out. The Nike Book 1 EP Mirage (Sail Outsole) was released on February 17th, 2024, and retailed at $140.

name: Olympic
title: Nike Air Max 1 Olympic
description:
Released ahead of the 2024 Paris Olympics, the Nike Air Max 1 Olympic decks out the Air Max 1 silhouette with details inspired by the Olympic Games.

The Olympic Nike Air Max 1 embodies the spirit of Team USA, with a white base and patriotic accents in obsidian-blue and red. A metallic-gold Swoosh logo graces the side panel and represents the drive to achieve Olympic gold. Classic color blocking on the upper pays homage to the original Air Max 1, while the obsidian mudguard takes notes from the OG Obsidian colorway. The upper construction consists of a mesh base with Light Smoke Grey overlays near the rear and midfoot. Pops of red stand out on the eyelets, the tongue’s logo tag, and the NIKE AIR branding on the heel.

Our experts like how this sneaker subtly celebrates the 2024 Olympics and Team USA through colors instead of motifs or bold lettering. The Nike Air Max 1 Olympic was released on June 17, 2024, and sold for $150.

name: Rock
title: adidas Yeezy Desert Boot Rock
description:
The adidas Yeezy Desert Boot Rock features a beige mesh upper with tonal nubuck and suede overlays. From there, a matching grooved sole provides traction and stability.

The adidas Yeezy Desert Boot Rock released in April of 2019 and retailed for $200.

name: sacai CLOT Kiss of Death Net Orange Blaze
title: Nike LD Waffle sacai CLOT Kiss of Death Net Orange Blaze
description:
Taking cues from the Nike Air Max 1 CLOT Kiss of Death, the Nike LDWaffle sacai CLOT Orange Blaze boasts an off-white translucent and suede upper with Deep Red and Orange Blaze snake-textured Swooshes. From there, a two-toned stacked sole and doubled tongue amplify sacai's unique design aesthetic.

The Nike LDWaffle sacai CLOT Orange Blaze released in September of 2021 and retailed for $170.

name: Summit White
title: Nike Waffle One Summit White
description:
With extra cushioning and support, the Nike Waffle One Summit White can be used for both walking around town or for a bit of more intense exercise.

This pair of shoes has a black sole next to a bright white midsole. The body of the shoe features colors like white, beige, and gray, with different fabrics, including suede and mesh. The iconic Nike symbol known as the Swoosh appears in white. This is a low top model that ends right at the beginning of the ankle.

The Nike Waffle One Summit White was first released in May of 2021. This model had a starting retail price of $100.

name: Wonder White (Women's)
title: adidas Campus 00s Wonder White (Women's)
description:
The adidas Campus 00s Wonder White (Women's) was released as part of adidas' Campus shoe line.

The adidas Campus 00s Wonder White for women is made from suede with smooth leather accents on the heel tab and also on the 3-Stripes. The sneaker has an OrthoLite insole that has been designed to provide superior cushioning and support, allowing you to wear these sneakers for extended periods without experiencing fatigue or discomfort. The outsole is made of rubber and features a tread pattern that provides grip and traction on a wide range of surfaces. The collar and tongue are padded to offer added comfort.

We think that one of the standout features of the adidas Campus 00s Wonder White (Women's) is its unique blend of white shades including Wonder White, Cloud White, and off white. The sneaker was released on July 4th, 2022, at a retail price of $110.

Disclaimer: Please be aware that some of the adidas Campus 00s Wonder White (Women's) have a women's size box label but men's sizing on the inner tag of the shoe.

name: Metallic Red (2023)
title: Nike Air Foamposite One Metallic Red (2023)
description:
The Nike Air Foamposite One Metallic Red (2023) is an additional colorway in Nike's Foamposite line.

The Red Air Foamposite One Metallic Red has a predominantly black upper with white and Varsity Red accents. The outsole is made with translucent rubber, providing grip and traction on any surface. The translucent outsole is designed to showcase the carbon fiber shank plate that helps provide additional support and stability to the wearer's foot.

What we love about the Nike Air Foamposite One Metallic Red (2023) is the Foamposite overlay that runs all around the shoe. This overlay, also in Varsity Red, immediately catches the eye. The metallic sheen reflects light in a unique way, making the shoe appear as though it's shimmering. The Foamposite material itself is highly durable and meant to provide protection and comfort while conforming to the wearer's foot over time. The shoe was released on July 6th, 2023, at a retail price of $230.

name: Dark Glow
title: adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Dark Glow
description:
The adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Dark Glow features a black Primeknit upper with a black TPU cage that glows vivid blue when exposed to the dark. From there, an EVA foam sole adds support for a cushioned fit.

The adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Dark Glow released in August of 2021 and retailed for $200.

name: Onyx (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy Foam RNR Onyx (Infants)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Onyx Infants has a harvested algae construction expressing a sleek black tone and a blended lightweight EVA in a slip-on construction.

The adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Onyx Infants is dynamically sculpted to adopt a design defined by oval and circular perforations, which enhances its breathability. The shoe features a sculpted heel and a soft, textured footbed that provides a snug and comfortable fit. adidas branding appears on the outsole, featuring a wavy traction pattern for optimal grip.
    
  The infants' rendition of the adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Onyx Infants was released in June 2022 and retailed for $40 and in March 2024 and retailed for $45.

name: Smoke Grey
title: Nike Free Metcon 5 Smoke Grey
description:
The Nike Free Metcon 5 Smoke Grey is a high-performance training sneaker designed to improve stability without sacrificing flexibility.

Boasting a lightweight yet durable mesh upper in Smoke Grey, this sneaker has a sleek silhouette without added bulk around the collar or underfoot. The upper includes a 7/8-length inner sleeve that creates a locked-in feeling. The wide heel stabilizes the foot, while a double layer of foam provides supportive cushioning and protects against impact stress. In the forefoot, Nike Free technology allows for flexibility, and the collar’s natural stretch lets the foot move without restriction. The Smoke Grey Nike Free Metcon 5 sneaker features minimal branding details, but the small, white Swoosh logos on the inner side panels add a touch of Nike heritage.

Our experts like the inclusion of rubber tread in high-wear areas, which contributes to the sneaker’s overall longevity. The Nike Free Metcon 5 Smoke Grey was released on April 6, 2023, and sold for $120.

name: White Racer Blue Black
title: Nike Zoom Vomero 5 White Racer Blue Black
description:
The Nike Zoom Vomero 5 White Racer Blue Black features a white, Racer Blue, and black mesh with TecTuff leather upper with the base of white playing host to an electric shade of blue and a neutral yet effective black tone. From there, special Vomero 5 brands the tongue of the silhouette, printed 3-D panels at the heel provide added ventilation, and a thick outsole using Nike's own Zoom cushioning technology complete the design.

The Nike Zoom Vomero 5 White Racer Blue Black released in April of 2019 and retailed for $160.

name: Phantom Cargo Khaki
title: Nike Air Max Plus Phantom Cargo Khaki
description:
The Nike Air Max Plus Phantom Cargo Khaki upgrades the Air Max Plus silhouette with a gentle colorway of Phantom with Neutral Olive accents and splashes of Cargo Khaki.

This sneaker features the iconic wavy design lines across the upper, which are stand-out features of the Air Max Plus lineup. The lines come in Neutral Olive and tonally match the tongue’s mesh base, the collar lining, and the rubber outsole. In addition, the visible Air Max units in the heel and forefoot feature Neutral Olive details. The synthetic upper is constructed from lightweight mesh, which allows the foot to breathe and creates an airy feel. The sneaker displays minimal branding, which includes a small Swoosh on each side panel, a TN Air logo tag on the heel, and Nike Air branding on the tongue.

Our StockX experts like the supportive arch, which also comes in Neutral Olive and was designed to resemble a whale’s tail. The Nike Air Max Plus Phantom Cargo Khaki was released on November 16th, 2023, and retailed at $175.

name: Neckface
title: Nike SB Dunk Low Pro QS Neckface
description:
The Nike Dunk SB Low Pro QS Neckface is a multi-hued sneaker that tones black and white as the dominant colors.

On the black nubuck uppers of this SB Low Pro Nike Dunk shoe, numerous patches bearing Neckface's distinctively expressive visual sense are the focal point. There is also a number of patches on this sneaker that illustrate several depictions of ghouls, tombstones, skulls, demons, as well as snakes. A white midsole that sits on a black sole completes the design.

The Nike Dunk SB Low Pro QS Neckface made its debut in the market on 27th October 2022 with a suggested retail price of $120.
model: Nike SB Dunk Low Pro QS

name: Thunder Blue Cream
title: Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Thunder Blue Cream
description:
Built with an early 2000s aesthetic, the Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Thunder Blue Cream, designed as a running shoe, also works wonderfully as a comfy, cushioning lifestyle shoe that will keep your feet happy for hours.

This versatile shoe has an upper with a base of airy, lightweight white mesh. Synthetic overlays in silver and suede overlays and pale tan adorn this upper, along with a cream-colored TPU heel tab vented for maximum air flow and placed for stability. The synthetic side-panel cage in pale blue and navy adds style and support and matches the side-panel Nike swoosh. This shoe's outsole is designed with pods of navy and cream-colored rubber with a waffle lug to absorb shock and provide traction with each step and stride.

The aspect of this shoe that really makes it stand out is the pale vanilla midsole. The contrasting color makes the shoe pop, and the Zoom Air units provide ultimate cushioning and energy return. The Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Thunder Blue Cream, was released on June 15, 2024, for aretail price of $160.

name: Yellow Pink Gradient
title: Nike Air Max Plus OG Yellow Pink Gradient
description:
Nike Air Max Plus Yellow Pink Gradient is a member of the Air Max Plus line that is revered for its Tuned Air technology, which delivers responsive cushioning and support.

Other noteworthy features of these shoes include an upper crafted from breathable mesh, synthetic overlays for structure and durability, a traditional lacing system for a customizable fit, and a rubber outsole with a tread pattern designed for traction and grip on various surfaces. Air Max branding can be found on the tongue and heel, while the iconic Nike Swoosh is prominently featured on the sides of the shoe.

What our experts like most about the Nike Air Max Plus Yellow Pink Gradient, however, is the color palette that transitions from yellow to pink, creating a vibrant and eye-catching gradient effect across the upper. These shoes retailed with an original price tag of $160 when they first released on December 1, 2022.

name: Drake NOCTA Triple Black
title: Nike Hot Step Air Terra Drake NOCTA Triple Black
description:
The Nike Hot Step Air Terra Drake NOCTA Black features a black perforated tumbled leather reminiscent of the Air Jordan 14. Metallic mini Swoosh emblems at the toe and heel shine against a matte background. In addition to Air Max cushioning, G-TEK is also present in the sole, a technology found in the 1999 ACG Air Terra Humara. From there, NOCTA branding moments on the tongue and insole nod to Drake's Nike sublabel.

The Nike Hot Step Air Terra Drake NOCTA Black released in March of 2022 and retailed for $180.

name: Blue Moonbeam
title: New Balance 1906R Blue Moonbeam
description:
The New Balance 1906R Blue Moonbeam adds a celestial colorway of blue, Moonbeam, and metallic silver to the technical 1906R silhouette.

The Blue Moonbeam New Balance 1906R boasts a mesh construction in off-white with thin overlays in Moonbeam and blue. A panel in metallic silver adorns the toe and complements the silver-tone layered beneath the heel. Designed for comfort, the sneaker boasts an Abzorb midsole and Abzorb SBS heel cushioning. Additional N-rgy cushioning provides support underfoot, while the stability web technology in the rubber outsole increases arch support. The front lace closure system boasts off-white laces that match the mesh upper and thread through small eyelets.

Our experts at StockX like the slanted New Balance ‘N’ on the side panels. It houses a black ribbon that extends beyond the ‘N’ and meets the lace cage. The New Balance 1906R Blue Moonbeam was released on March 30, 2024, and sold for $155.

name: HUF Pear Green (2024)
title: Nike Air Max 1 SP HUF Pear Green (2024)
description:
The Nike Air Max 1 SP HUF Pear Green (2024) is a "Special Project (SP)" sneaker, which means it was crafted in the Nike Lab using premium materials. This sneaker is also part of a collaboration between Nike and HUF, a streetwear label known for using marijuana leaf patterns and a signature green.

As a nod to HUF, this running shoe features a greyscale colorway with pops of Pear on the Swoosh logos, the collar lining, part of the rubber outsole, the tongue's logo tag, and the "NIKE AIR" lettering on the heel. The upper is leather in Medium Grey with leather overlays in Anthracite and Flat Pewter. Visible Air Max units in the heel protect against impact, while the padded collar cushions the ankle.

Our experts at StockX like the dual HUF and Air Max branding on the woven tongue tag. The Nike Air Max 1 SP HUF Pear Green (2024) was launched on June 15, 2024, and sold for $160.

name: Light Orewood Brown (Women's)
title: Nike V2K Run Light Orewood Brown (Women's)
description:
The Nike V2K Run Light Orewood Brown (Women's) is a chic and stylish sneaker designed for the modern person. Featuring a blend of light orewood brown, light bone, khaki, and earth tones, this model offers a sophisticated look that pairs well with any outfit. The V2K Run combines retro charm with modern comfort, making it an ideal choice for both casual wear and athletic activities.

The Nike V2K Run is inspired by the early 2000s running shoe designs, known for their comfort and durability. The Light Orewood Brown colorway adds a contemporary twist to this classic silhouette, with its earthy tones and high-quality construction. Nike's commitment to innovation and style is evident in every detail, from the supportive fit to the intricate design elements.

Released on December 12, 2023, at a retail price of $110, the Nike V2K Run Light Orewood Brown (Women's) is a perfect blend of heritage and modernity. This sneaker offers a unique and fashionable option for women who appreciate both style and comfort. Don’t miss your chance to add this versatile model to your collection.

name: Panda (2021) (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk High Panda (2021) (Women's)
description:
The women's Nike Dunk High Panda (W) features white and black leather upper with a matching sole. From there, hits of red on the woven tongue label add some subtle flair.

The women's Nike Dunk High Black White (W) released in July of 2021 and retailed for $110.

name: Classic Black Grey
title: New Balance 530 Classic Black Grey
description:
The New Balance 530 Classic Black Gray is a technical running shoe that finds inspiration in classic sneaker designs from the New Balance catalog.

One of the first things you notice is the overlapping overlays that come in Classic Black, gray, and Metallic Silver. They’re constructed from leather and suede, and create a sense of movement across the upper due to the line designs. The upper is made of breathable mesh in Classic Black, while the tongue boasts a combination of mesh and synthetic materials. In terms of technology, an ABZORB midsole provides responsive cushioning and gives the sneaker a slightly bulky silhouette. This feature is similar to elements on early 2000s running shoes.

Our StockX experts like the application of Classic Black on the rubber outsole because it contrasts the white midsole. The New Balance 530 Classic Black Gray was released on January 30th, 2023, and retailed at $100.

name: Multi-Corduroy (Women's)
title: Nike Air Max 90 Multi-Corduroy (Women's)
description:
The Nike Air Max 90 Multi-Corduroy (Women's) adds a patchwork of corduroy details to the recognizable Air Max 90 silhouette.

The patchwork features earthy, neutral tones, including Bronzine, Red Stardust, and Cedar. The entire upper is made of corduroy, including the mudguard, the overlays, and the base. Like other versions of the Air Max 90, the Multi-Corduroy iteration was originally designed as a performance running sneaker. Visible Air Max units in the heel provide responsive cushioning, while the padded, low-cut collar and the foam midsole add comfort. The sneaker includes other heritage design elements, including a rubber waffle sole. This design finds inspiration in a waffle iron’s pattern and provides traction.

Our StockX experts like the minimal branding on this shoe. For example, the sides display small Air Max panels, and ‘AIR’ is embroidered across the tongue. The women’s version Nike Air Max 90 Multi-Corduroy (Women's) was released on November 9th, 2023, and was listed at $140.

name: Pink Foam (Women's)
title: Nike Air Vapormax Plus Pink Foam (Women's)
description:
The Nike Air Vapormax Plus Pink Foam (Women's) paints the recognizable Air Vapormax Plus silhouette in a light-pink colorway of Pink Foam and Playful Pink.

Like the OG Air Vapormax Plus that was released in 1998, the Pink Foam iteration features wavy lines that form a floating cage around the synthetic, padded upper. In addition, this sneaker recycles the iconic whale-tail arch, which connects the forefoot and heel underfoot. A pull tab on the heel allows for quick application or removal of the shoe, while an adjustable lace closure provides a secure fit. Finally, rubber pods add durability in high-wear areas and contribute to the sneaker’s technical look.

Our StockX experts like the translucent Vapormax sole unit, which completes the sneaker’s pink-on-pink aesthetic and adds ultra-lightweight cushioning. The women’s size Nike Air Vapormax Plus Pink Foam (Women's) was released on December 18, 2023, and retailed at $210.

name: Neapolitan (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Neapolitan
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Neapolitan (Women's) adds an ice cream-inspired colorway of Cacao Wow, Pink Foam, and Pale Ivory to the Dunk Low silhouette.

This low-top sneaker starts with a chocolatey Cacao Wow base plus strawberry-like Pink Foam on the heel and forefoot overlays, eyelets, and laces. The perforations across the toebox make the Cacao Wow base look like a soft, chocolate cookie. The Pale Ivory Swoosh logo reaches across the side panel, adding a dose of vanilla. Like other versions of the Dunk Low, the "Neapolitan (Women’s)" version features plush padding in the tongue and collar as well as a durable rubber outsole. Rounding on the look, Pink Foam ‘NIKE’ lettering decorates the tongue tag and ‘NIKE’ is embroidered on the heel tab in Pale Ivory thread.

Our experts at StockX like the bright red insole and heel tab because they add an additional berry-like pop of color to the sneaker. The women’s size Nike Dunk Low Neapolitan (Women's) was released on July 31, 2024, and $130.

name: Silver Metallic
title: New Balance 1000 Silver Metallic
description:
The New Balance 1000 Silver Metallic is a performance running sneaker that draws inspiration from the technical running shoes of the early 2000s and features a futuristic colorway of Silver Metallic, Black, and Dawn Glow.

The upper is constructed from breathable Black mesh with supple leather overlays in Metallic Silver. The leather overlays conform to the shape of the shoe and create the illusion of movement. Black highlights can be found on the heel, the collar lining, the outsole, the underside of the tongue, and the sockliner. The signature New Balance "N" comes in Black with a Metallic Silver outline. Like other versions of the New Balance 1000, this sneaker boasts a bulky silhouette with padding around the heel and on the tongue.

Our StockX experts like the addition of Dawn Glow on the midsole because it adds a soft touch to the dark and metallic tones. The New Balance 1000 Silver Metallic was released on April 24, 2024, and retailed at $150.

name: Shima Shima (2023)
title: Nike Air Max 1 Premium Shima Shima (2023)
description:
The Nike Air Max 1 Premium Shima Shima 2023 is part of the Japanese-inspired line of sneakers that arrives in a Summit White/​Plum Eclipse-Wolf Grey-White Siren Red colorway.
​
The Nike Air Max 1 Premium Shima Shima 2023's tongue tag showcases the words ""Shima Shima"" in Japanese, with the inner lining adorned with a distinctive striped pattern. The midsole is white, featuring a visible Air unit in the heel. Meanwhile, Nike matches gray and brown shades on the rubber outsole. The upper is constructed with an all-premium leather with grey quarter panels over a white base, while Swooshes and the mudguard appear in dark brown. The base features Plum Eclipse, while the Nike Air branding appears on the mudguards, Swooshes, and laces.
​
Our experts think the standout features of the Nike Air Max 1 Premium Shima Shima 2023 are the striped liner and the Japanese-themed tongue tags. The The Nike Air Max 1 Premium Shima Shima 2023 was released on March 10th, 2023, at a retail price of $160.

name: Sesame
title: Nike Air Max Plus Sesame
description:
The Nike Air Max Plus Sesame updates the Air Max Plus silhouette with an earthy colorway of Sesame with accents in Smokey Mauve, Hemp, Light Bone, and Red Stardust.

The sneaker boasts several design elements inspired by the original sneaker, including wavy line overlays in leather, plastic detailing, and a base crafted from breathable mesh. The mudguard is also made from mesh, while the toe cap is crafted from a shiny plastic material. Contemporary upgrades include the hiking-inspired lace closure system, which features thin laces and an adjustable toggle. Finally, the inclusion of visible Nike Air units underfoot hearkens back to the sneaker’s performance-running roots and provides responsive cushioning.

Our experts at StockX like the distressed detailing on the midsole, which creates a worn-in, trail-ready feel that matches the sneaker’s outdoorsy aesthetic. The Nike Air Max Plus Sesame was released on February 12, 2024, and retailed at $180.

name: White
title: adidas Samba Classic White
description:
The upper part of the adidas Samba Classic White is constructed entirely of synthetic leather, which increases both its durability and lightness.

The Samba Classic by adidas in white color has a suede overlay that increases its protection for its upper part and resistance to abrasion. Additionally, this shoe has a die-cut EVA cushioning for lightweight comfort and a rubber outsole with non-marking tread for superior traction on all interior surfaces. The sneaker also features a thick outsole that comes in black color.

The adidas Samba Classic White, at the time of its market debut on the 25th of June, 2022, had a suggested retail price of $90.

name: Triple Black
title: Nike Air Max 2 CB '94 Triple Black
description:
Nike added a new spin on Charles Barkley's 1994 pro model with the Nike Air Max 2 CB 94 Triple Black 2020. From top to bottom, the Nike Air Max 2 CB 94 Triple Black 2020 features an all-black color scheme. Different textures like wrinkled leather, Air Max soles, and a thread-stitched Nike logo add variety to the monotone palette. To finalize this design, the Triple Black has a streak of dark blue in the Air unit.

The Nike Air Max 2 CB 94 Triple Black 2020 released in October of 2020 and retailed for $160.

name: Phantom Black
title: Nike Killshot 2 Phantom Black
description:
The Nike Killshot 2 Phantom Black is a lifestyle shoe channeling a timeless design in a Phantom Black color scheme.

Ah, tennis and badminton, those were the days. Even if life is too busy to enjoy a game now, you can still enjoy the old-school style of the Killshot 2. Presenting in a Phantom Black colorway, this shoe has a minimalist aesthetic that complements casual outings with those that are a level up. The upper is smooth leather and forms the background for the white stitching, which adds details. Retro Nike branding in white is seen on the heel. The black outsole is gum rubber and will hide scuffs and scrapes.

Something we think gives this shoe its character are the various overlay stitching lines throughout, including the outline of Nike Swooshes. When it was released to the marketplace on June 1, 2024, the Nike Killshot 2 Phantom Black retailed for $85.

name: Bronzine
title: Nike Dunk Low Retro Bronzine
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Retro Bronzine refreshes a tried and true silhouette and makes it original yet again with an eye-catching colorway that plays with shades reminiscent of bronze.

This low top features a white leather base with a toe box dotted with signature perforations for breathability and comfort. Maize yellow leather forms the overlays that adorn the toe cap, midfoot, and all but the upper eye stays. This maize yellow is reflected in the padded nylon tongue. Bronze leather forms the overlay that stretches from the collar to the heel counter. The white foam midsole with its cupsole construction offers cushioning and support. The rubber outsole with multi-directional traction is in a shade of bronze that hearkens back to the collar overlay, giving this shoe a sense of balance.

The aspect of this sneaker that stands out is the subtle contrast between the pale cream-colored leather of the side panel Nike swoosh and the heel tab. The Nike Dunk Low Retro Bronzine was released on February 21, 2024, for a retail price of $115.

name: Black Wolf Grey
title: Nike Air Max Plus 3 Black Wolf Grey
description:
The Nike Air Max Plus 3 Wolf Grey features a grey plastic TPU, mesh, and leather upper, with the fine mesh base Wolf Grey that transitions slowly into black for the rest of the silhouette.[1] From there, small Nike "Swooshes" in silver at the front of the Air Max Plus 3 combine with the patented cushioning technology in the midsole to complete the design.

The Nike Air Max Plus 3 Wolf Grey released in November of 2019 and retailed for $180.

name: Protection Pack Silver Metallic
title: New Balance 1906D Protection Pack Silver Metallic
description:
New Balance managed to shake things up in 2021 by unveiling its limited-edition New Balance 2002R "Protection Pack." The brand followed up the success of that launch by giving other New Balance sneakers the "Protection Pack" treatment, including the New Balance 1906D. The New Balance 1906D Protection Pack Silver Metallic made its way into the world through this concept.

This New Balance 1906D Silver Metallic sneaker features a breathable upper made of mesh and synthetic leather overlays that have worn edges on them. The upper sits on top of a lightweight ABZORB midsole that has ABZORB SBS heel cushioning for added comfort and support. There is also an N-ergy outsole outfitted with a Stability Web to provide even more support in the arch area.

Our sneaker experts like the outside-the-box thinking that was clearly going on when this New Balance shoe came to life. It delivers another fresh take on the "Protection Pack" idea. The New Balance 1906D Protection Pack Silver Metallic was released on November 22, 2023, and retailed for $180.

name: Faded Azure
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Faded Azure
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Faded Azure features a tonal blue upper constructed with layered mesh, leather, and suede. At the base, a blue BOOST midsole with hits of orange provides cushioning and durability. Reflective detailing in the heel wrap and grey oval laces complete the design.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Faded Azure released in November of 2021 and retailed for $240.

name: Medium Olive Hemp
title: Nike Dunk Low Premium Medium Olive Hemp
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Premium Medium Olive Hemp offers a deluxe version of the beloved silhouette designed by Peter Moore. Enjoy undeniable style and heritage mojo with every step you take and this iconic pair of kicks.

The upper of this low-top features a base of smooth white leather sporting the iconic perforations on the toebox that enhance air flow and overall foot comfort. Olive-colored nubuck forms the overlays at the heel, collar, eyestays, vamp, and toecap. Peach-beige leather is used to construct the branded heel tab and the Nike Swoosh that courses across the side panel. Olive mesh forms the sock liner, while Peach-beige appears once again on the branded tongue tag. This refined sneaker rides on an outsole of olive rubber featuring concentric circles, dynamic grooves, and little stars to form its traction pattern.

The aspect of this sneaker we enjoy the most is the vintage-looking midsole. The off-white side walls with tonal stitching offer comfort as well as retro vibes. The Nike Dunk Low Premium Medium Olive Hemp was released on July 4, 2024, for an original retail price of $125.

name: Bone (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Bone (Kids)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Bone (Kids) introduces the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 in kid-sized proportions and an all-over, off-white colorway of Bone.

Crafted from durable Primeknit, the upper offers a flexible yet snug fit, with distinctive stitching down the vamp that gives the material a sweater-like look. Although the Bone (Kids) adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 boasts a minimalist design, the signature mesh side stripe runs across the lateral side and increases breathability. Another noteworthy feature is the no-tie elastic laces, which complement the pull tabs at the heel. Completing the design, a Boost midsole encapsulated in semi-translucent rubber runs the full length of the shoe and provides lightweight cushioning.

Our experts at StockX appreciate the effort to maintain the sneaker’s tonal look, from the laces to the insole to the outsole. The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Bone (Kids) was released on May 27, 2024, and sold for $160.

name: Patta The Next Wave Dark Russett
title: Nike Air Max 1 Patta The Next Wave Dark Russett
description:
A grey mesh base with brown leather overlays makes up the Nike Air Max 1 Patta The Next Wave Dark Russett colorway. On the lateral side of the shoe, next to the toebox, a small Swoosh can be seen, too.
​
​The inner lining of the Patta Waves sneaker is pink, while its eyelets, insole, and the heel feature a faint blue tint. Co-branding on the tongue, an extra set of laces that match the color of the shoe, and an off-white midsole all combine to complete the design of this Air Max 1 by Nike.
​
​The Nike Air Max 1 Patta The Next Wave Dark Russett debuted in the market on the 25th of June, 2022, at a retail price of $160.

name: The Simpsons Homer Simpson
title: adidas Stan Smith The Simpsons Homer Simpson
description:
Released on August 18, 2023, the adidas Stan Smith took a trip to Springfield and came back with a fresh twist featuring everyone's favorite, slightly clueless dad, Homer Simpson.

Rocking the iconic Stan Smith design, this edition turns up the cool factor with a Homer Simpson colorway. Its clean profile is interrupted by the legendary Homer Simpson as he peeks out from the heel tab, reminiscent of the famous Homer in the bushes meme. A nod to pop culture and one of the internet's favorite memes. The side panel features "Homer Simpson" printed in gold between the iconic dotted 3 stripes logo.

The perfect blend of the timeless Stan Smith design with a touch of Springfield, Whether you're stepping out for a casual day or making a statement, these kicks ensure you do it with unmatched style and a touch of meme magic. The adidas Stan Smith Homer Simpson colorway dropped with a price tag of $130.

name: Sporty & Rich Pink
title: adidas Handball Spezial Sporty & Rich Pink
description:
The adidas Handball Spezial Sporty & Rich Pink adds a primarily pink colorway of Pantone, Cream White, and Gum to the classic Handball Spezial silhouette.

This sneaker is part of a collaboration between adidas and Sporty & Rich, a label founded by Emily Oberg that finds inspiration in vintage sportswear and luxury lifestyles. In keeping with Sporty & Rich's house codes, the Handball Spezial "Sporty & Rich Pink" is crafted from premium, long-lasting materials. The upper construction boasts a suede base in Pantone with tonal suede overlays. The leather 3-Stripes logo and the heel mustache come in Cream White, which gives the sneaker a vintage feel. "SPORTY & RICH" replaces the usual "SPEZIAL" lettering on the side panel, while "adidas" branding decorates the heel mustache.

Our StockX experts like including Pantone-colored laces because they add an extra dose of pink. The adidas Handball Spezial Sporty & Rich Pink was launched on May 23, 2024, and retailed at $100.

name: JJJJound White
title: ASICS GT-2160 JJJJound White
description:
The ASICS GT-2160 JJJJound White is a technical running sneaker with a design informed by running shoes from the early 2010s, including the GT-2000.

First released in 2011, the GT-2160 gained popularity after its re-release in 2023. The JJJJound White ASICS GT-2160 boasts a crisp white colorway with accents in black, variations of gray, and neon yellow. The base is crafted from breathable, white mesh, featuring a loose weave and lightweight feel. Wavy lines across the forefoot hearken back to original GT-2160 designs, while the segmented midsole is rooted in technology from ASICS’s 2010 catalog. In terms of cushioning, gel inserts add to the function-first aesthetic and protect against impact stress.

Our experts at StockX like the eye-catching neon yellow accents on the heel’s JJJJound branding, a stripe across the tongue, and the ASICS logo. The ASICS GT-2160 JJJJound White was released on October 31, 2024, and sold for $190.

name: Black White
title: Nike Air More Uptempo Slide OG Black White
description:
The Nike Air More Uptempo Slide OG Black White is a slide that borrows design inspiration from the Nike Air More Uptempo sneaker.

The Air More Uptempo Slide OG Black White features black synthetic leather upper with white accents. The slide boosts a full-length foam midsole that provides lightweight cushioning and support. In addition, the foam midsole is designed to absorb impact and improve energy return, ensuring that every step feels comfortable and effortless. The sole has a flexible design that allows for natural movement of the foot and the outsole is made of durable rubber that provides grip and traction on various surfaces.

We think the biggest draw of this shoe is the iconic "AIR" branding on the sides, which pays homage to the classic Nike Air Max design. This bold branding gives this sneaker a unique and unmistakable look. The Nike Air More Uptempo Slide OG Black White was released on April 4th, 2023 at a retail price of $85.
model: Nike Air More Uptempo Slide OG

name: Beige Grass Green
title: Onitsuka Tiger Mexico 66 Beige Grass Green
description:
The Onitsuka Tiger Mexico 66 evolved from a sneaker called the Limber-Up training shoe that was first developed in 1966 and designed for Japanese athletes taking part in the 1968 Summer Olympics. Onitsuka Tiger changed the name of this sneaker to the Mexico 66 in the early 2000s and continues to release it in new colorways, including the Onitsuka Tiger Mexico 66 Beige Grass Green.

This version of the Mexico 66 sneaker keeps the same classic shape that the original version had back in the 1960s. It's a slim sneaker with a beige upper made of leather and brown accents on both the front and back of the shoe. It also has an OrthoLite inner sole to provide extra cushioning and overall comfort.

What our experts love most about this sneaker, though, are the green Onitsuka Tiger stripes on it. The Mexico 66 was one of the first Onitsuka Tiger sneakers to feature them, and they're every bit as iconic today as they were 60 years ago. The Onitsuka Tiger Mexico 66 Beige Grass Green sneakers were released on May 19, 2023, for a retail price of $120.

name: Midnight Navy University Blue
title: Nike Dunk Low Midnight Navy University Blue
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Midnight Navy University Blue comes in a Midnight Navy and white colorway with University Blue and Laser Orange accents.

The upper of the Dunk Low Midnight Navy University Blue is made of durable leather, which provides the shoe with both durability. The sneaker sits atop a white midsole and the outsole of the shoe showcases a retro-inspired circular herringbone pattern, perfect for traction and grip. The shoe also features a padded collar and tongue, which ensures that the shoe is comfortable and snug on the feet.

We think that the key feature of the Nike Dunk Low Midnight Navy University Blue is the perforations on the toe box. The perforations are a design element that serves a functional purpose as well. The holes are strategically placed to allow air to circulate through the shoe, which helps to keep the feet cool and dry during intense physical activity. The shoe was released on July 17th, 2023 at a retail price of $110.

name: Los Angeles Dodgers
title: Nike SB Dunk Low Los Angeles Dodgers
description:
The Nike SB Dunk Low Los Angeles Dodgers features a white leather upper with blue overlays and red Swoosh logos. The "Nike" brand name is prevanlent on the heel tab in red.

The Nike SB Dunk Low Los Angeles Dodgers is a low-top sneaker with lace-up closure style. The shoe features a blue and white color scheme that has shades similar to the traditional blue and white worn by the MLB's LA Dodgers. It has a light-brown sole with a pink graphic on the ankle’s right side.

The Nike SB Dunk Low Los Angeles Dodgers was released in June of 2022 at the retail price of $120.

name: New Spruce
title: New Balance 9060 New Spruce
description:
The New Balance 9060 New Spruce is part of the Spruce Pack and adds hits of fresh New Spruce to the 9060’s futuristic silhouette.

Drawing inspiration from classic models in the 99X series, the New Spruce version of the New Balance 9060 showcases the visible tech aesthetic of the early 2000s. For instance, the ABZORB midsole boasts exaggerated sculpted pods that complement the wavy, layered overlays on the upper. The upper is crafted from suede and mesh in Sea Salt, while gray accents stand out on the tongue, heel, and side panels. Although New Spruce saturates the "N" on the outer side panel, stripes of New Spruce cover the "N" on the inner side. The "NB 9060" branding on the tongue and the "NB" stitched on the heel also come in New Spruce.

Our experts at StockX like that this sneaker includes splashes of New Spruce without straying from New Balance’s tonally neutral aesthetic. The New Balance 9060 New Spruce was released on March 29, 2024, and retailed at $150.

name: Space Lavender (GS)
title: ASICS Gel-1130 Space Lavender (GS)
description:
The ASICS Gel-1130 Space Lavender (GS) updates the technical Gel-1130 silhouette with contrasting overlays in Space Lavender and teal. This color combination stands out against the sneaker’s white base and is reminiscent of tonal aesthetics from the late 1990s.

However, this version of the Gel-1130 finds design inspiration in stability running shoes from 2008 and the ninth model in the Gel-1000 series. The Trusstic support system reduces excessive twisting and mimics the natural movement of ligaments in the foot, while Gel cushioning absorbs shock with each step. The Space Lavender (GS) ASICS Gel-1130 sneaker also includes modern upgrades, such as the lightweight mesh upper, which allows the foot to breathe.

Our experts at StockX appreciate the sustainable dyeing techniques applied to the sock liner. Compared to traditional dyeing, this technique reduces carbon emissions by up to 45 percent. The grade school-sized ASICS Gel-1130 Space Lavender (GS) was released on June 1, 2024, and sold for $85.

name: Billie Eilish Sequoia
title: Nike Air Force 1 High '07 SP Billie Eilish Sequoia
description:
The Nike Air Force 1 High '07 SP Billie Eilish Sequoia is a special project collaborative sneaker from the Nike x Billie Eilish Air Force 1 High '07 collection in a Sequoia colorway.

This high-top sneaker is made of synthetic nubuck upper dressed in a monochromatic Dark Green tone. The upper is highlighted by four additional velcro-secured straps that cover the variable-width lacing system. Other details include a tonal Swoosh on the sides, Billie Eilish's logo on the metallic dubrae, and ‘BILLIE EILISH branded insoles. The signature Air Force 1 sole unit in a matching Dark Green tone rounds out the design. 

What our experts love about this collaborative AF1 sneaker is its unique color, materials, and simple design. The monochromatic Dark Green color gives it a unique tone, while the additional straps make the design stand out. The Nike Air Force 1 High '07 SP Billie Eilish Sequoia was released on October 14th, 2022, retailing at $180.

name: Lottery Pack Malachite Green
title: Nike Dunk Low SE Lottery Pack Malachite Green
description:
The Nike Dunk Low SE Lottery arrives in a white smooth leather base with black leather Swooshes on both sides of the shoe, with malachite green heel tabs and the "Nike" in contrasting white.

Malachite green leather material overlays provide the structure for this SE Lottery sneaker´s iconic silhouette and stylized cartoon "Jackpot" Nike logos decorate the tongue tabs and white insoles throughout. Rounding out the footwear design are scratch-off Nike coin hangtags, white midsoles, and malachite green rubber outsoles.

The Nike Dunk Low SE Lottery was first released on the last day of August 2022, and its original retail price was set at $120.

name: Monarch
title: Nike Air Max 1 Monarch
description:
The Nike Air Max 1 Monarch updates the Air Max 1 with a vibrant colorway that mimics the black, white, and orange of a monarch butterfly’s wings.

The base is constructed from breathable, tight-knit white mesh, while leather overlays in gray form the lace cage and protective heel panel. The suede mudguard wraps around the shoe, complementing the Monarch orange of the collar lining and the NIKE AIR MAX embroidery on the heel tab. Black accents can be found on the signature Swoosh logo, the oversized eyelets, the outsole’s tread, and the visible Air Max units in the heel. The midsole comes in white, which offsets the deep black and bold Monarch tones.

Our experts at StockX like the woven NIKE AIR MAX logo tag on the tongue because it pays homage to the sneaker’s retro heritage. The Nike Air Max 1 Monarch was released on April 1, 2024, and retailed at $140.

name: .SWOOSH 404 Error
title: Nike Air Force 1 Low .SWOOSH 404 Error
description:
The Nike Air Force 1 Low .SWOOSH 404 Error is a unique low-top sneaker that incorporates digital language into its design.

This version of the Nike Air Force 1 Low comes with a shiny patent upper. The upper is a Racer Blue color throughout. The only departures from this color are the white laces and the branding seen on the lateral side of the heel. In white text, you can read "404 Error" followed by a period and a small, white Nike Swoosh. The text continues: "The requested upper was not found. Try again." The blue tongue also features a unique patch with more digital language branding. A thick white outsole with a translucent bottom layer completes the look.

Our favorite thing about this sneaker is the shiny patent material used for the upper. This makes the shoe stand out upon first glance. The Nike Air Force 1 Low .SWOOSH 404 Error was released on April 23, 2024, for a retail price of $150.

name: Multi-Swoosh Black Crimson
title: Nike Air Force 1 Low Multi-Swoosh Black Crimson
description:
The Nike Air Force 1 Low Multi Swoosh Black Crimson features a reflective debossed black Swoosh on the side panels. These are filled with overlapping, stenciled-on black orange mini-Swooshes.

Black suede comprises the base and overlays on the upper of this Air Force 1 model. A round tow cap and a crossed lacing system are additional features. Nike Air branding in black-orange appears on the black tongue, insole, lateral midsole, and pull tab. A Nike Air unit for cushioning and a rubber outsole with a circular pivot pattern completes the design.

The Nike Air Force 1 Low Multi Swoosh Black Crimson debuted on October 17th, 2022 for $130 retail.

name: Triple Black
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Triple Black
description:
Yeezy introduced a new variation of their 700 series with the adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Triple Black, now available on StockX. Although the silhouette is similar to previous models, this shoe differs by displaying "700" branding on the upper using compact materials.

This Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN is comprised of a triple black nylon upper paired with reflective detailing. A solid black sole with Boost cushioning completes the design. These sneakers released in February of 2020 and retailed for $220.

name: Preloved Red Gum
title: adidas Handball Spezial Preloved Red Gum
description:
The adidas Handball Spezial Preloved Red Gum is a retro-inspired sneaker with a rich colorway of Preloved Red and clean accents in Cream White and Crystal White.

Originally released in the 1970s as an indoor handball shoe, this version of the Handball Spezial features various throwback details. For example, the sneaker retains its T-shaped toebox overlay, serrated 3-Stripes on the side panels, and gum rubber outsole. However, the upper is crafted from synthetic suede instead of genuine suede, which contributes to the sneaker’s lightweight design. In addition, the textile inner lining allows the foot to breathe and doesn’t weigh down the shoe. While the base comes in Preloved Red, Cream White accents can be found on the heel tab, the 3-Stripes logo, and the collar lining.

Our experts at StockX like the classic logo tag, which comes with crisp Crystal White and Preloved Red lettering. The adidas Handball Spezial Preloved Red Gum was released on February 15, 2024, and sold for $110.

name: Black White
title: Nike Zoom GT Cut 2 Black White
description:
The Nike Zoom GT Cut 2 Black White is a performance basketball shoe that was designed to help athletes accelerate and change directions quickly.

This sneaker boasts an understated appearance while housing a variety of performance technology. For example, Zoom Air units in the heel combined with the foam midsole provide lightweight cushioning and a responsive feel. In addition, a React insole supports the foot. The upper’s inner cage draws inspiration from a butterfly – it’s lightweight and helps the athlete "take off" in a burst of movement. The upper is made of a breathable synthetic material, while the tongue offers a molded design that conforms to the foot. The laces wind through the lateral and medial webbing loops, which creates additional support in the forefoot area.

Something our StockX experts like is the shoe’s black base with Football Gray and white accents. The Nike Zoom GT Cut 2 Black White was released on June 23rd, 2023, and retailed at $170.

name: Great Indoors (Women's)
title: Nike Air Max 1 '87 Great Indoors (Women's)
description:
The Nike Air Max 1 87 Great Indoors W is a limited-edition release sneaker that is available in women's sizing only and was inspired by the Air Max 1 silhouette. 

The Great Indoors Nike Air Max 1 87 W features a rounded toe box, padded collar, and a cushioned midsole for maximum comfort. The shoe also features Air Max 1 details, such as the split heel design and Nike branding on the tongue.

We think that the standout feature of the Nike Air Max 1 87 Great Indoors W is the bold and unique cow print design on the upper. The cow print pattern is made up of Celestine Blue and Sail patterns, which contrast with the tiger stripe swoosh on the side of the shoe to create a striking visual effect. The Nike Air Max 1 87 Great Indoors W was released on March 15th, 2023, at a listing price of $150.

name: Earth Strata Magic Beige
title: adidas Gazelle Indoor Earth Strata Magic Beige
description:
The adidas Gazelle Indoor Earth Strata Magic Beige paints the retro Gazelle silhouette in a warm neutral colorway of Earth Strata, Cloud White, and Magic Beige.

Originally designed as an indoor gym shoe, the Earth Strata Magic Beige adidas Gazelle Indoor features a suede upper, contributing to the retro appearance. The color Earth Strata serves as a backdrop for the Cloud White serrated 3-Stripes logo on the side panel and the heel mustache. The leather lining also comes in Cloud White. In comparison, the suede toe box overlay and the eyelets feature Magic Beige. Tonal laces wind through the eyelets, while adidas Trefoil logos and circles provide traction underfoot. Completing the look, GAZELLE in gold lettering runs along the 3-Stripes and adidas branding decorates the tongue.

Our experts at StockX like the heritage design details, including the grippy gum rubber outsole. The adidas Gazelle Indoor Earth Strata Magic Beige was released on September 1, 2024, and sold for $120.

name: Black (Women's)
title: Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 Black (Women's)
description:
The Nike Air 1 Low Black W features stitched overlays on the upper side. It features air cushioning and Nike Air branding on the tongue and heel of the shoe. Nike Air Force 1 Low Black W also features a low-cut silhouette alongside a padded collar. It also adds a foam midsole and perforations on the toe for breathability. Its rubber outsole has a circular tread pattern for traction and durability.

The Nike Air Force 1 Low Black W was released in January 2019 at a retail price of $170.

name: Cool Grey
title: Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Cool Grey
description:
The Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Cool Grey is a purpose-built running shoe designed for all distances. It has advanced cushioning technology that helps prolong stamina by returning energy through the foot on each stride.

The Nike Zoom tech is combined with a forward-looking design, and the colorway of this model is a premium looking blend of greys and silvers. High visibility cross struts help runners stand out in low light conditions, while providing good lateral support for the wearer. Deeply grooved undersoles are made from sturdy modern synthetics.

Our experts really appreciate the sophisticated layered look of the multiple upper materials in these trainers, and the breathability this creates. They also immediately noted how light they are. The model's athletic credentials are right up there, too. The Air Zoom cushioning literally puts a bounce in the step, while still robustly absorbing surface impact. The Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Cool Grey was released on 20 July 2024, priced at $160.

name: December Sky
title: New Balance 9060 December Sky
description:
The New Balance 9060 December Sky draws its inspiration from the winter sky, featuring a color palette reminiscent of a cool Winter evening.

The upper of the 9060 December Sky sneaker is constructed with a combination of premium suede and breathable mesh materials. This blend allows for a balance of durability, flexibility, and breathability, ensuring a comfortable fit that can withstand daily wear. The midsole features advanced cushioning technology to provide superior support and shock absorption. The outsole is made of durable rubber, engineered to deliver traction and grip on various surfaces. The padded collar and tongue add an extra layer of comfort, reducing friction and preventing any potential discomfort or irritation.

We think that the notable aspect of the New Balance 9060 December Sky is its color combination. The sneaker features a December Sky colorway with Bone accents. The shoe was released on June 15th, 2023 at a retail price of $150.

name: Brown Black
title: New Balance 9060 Brown Black
description:
The New Balance 9060 Brown Black comes in a brown and black colorway with white detailing.

The New Balance 9060 Brown Black includes a mesh upper for breathability and durability with a synthetic overlay for support. The shoe's outsole is constructed of rubber, while the midsole is made of REVlite, which offers responsiveness and cushioning. The sneakers' ABZORB midsole technology provides additional cushioning and protection against impact. The shoe features "NB 9060" on the tongue and "NB" on the heel. The sneaker's design is completed with an "N" logo on the lateral sides.

The New Balance 9060 Brown Black was made available on August 13, 2022, and retailed for $150.

name: Black Grey (GS)
title: New Balance 9060 Black Grey (GS)
description:
The New Balance 9060 Black Gray (GS) is a futuristic sneaker with visible technology that sources elements from heritage 99X models. It comes in a stealthy colorway of black, various shades of gray, and occasional pops of red.

Like other Y2K-inspired sneakers from the New Balance catalog, the Black Gray (GS) New Balance 9060 features padding in the tongue and collar, creating a bulky silhouette. Oversized pods on the sculpted midsole contribute to the sneaker’s bulk while offering a pronounced technical element. The pods highlight the ABZORB and SBS cushioning underfoot. Adding structure without weighing down the shoe, the upper is crafted from breathable mesh in dark gray and white with suede overlays in gray and black.

Our experts at StockX like the diamond-shaped pattern on the rubber outsole because it’s borrowed from the original 860. The grade school-sized New Balance 9060 Black Gray (GS) was released on September 2, 2022, and sold for $110.

name: Recraft Wolf Grey
title: Nike Air Max 90 Recraft Wolf Grey
description:
Originally designed for running, Nike Air Max 90 Recraft Wolf Grey features versatile heritage delivered in style and substance.

The Nike Air Max 90 Recraft Wolf Grey has a thick and full-bodied silhouette. Its midsole has a thick Air Max unit visible in the heel. The toe box's upper, collar, and roof are covered with gray synthetic fabric stitched into a tight grid pattern. Its overlays around the toe box, eyelets, across the side, and on the heel are all in gray leather. The overlays feature a partially obscured Nike Swoosh and an Air Max logo.

The Nike Air Max 90 Recraft Wolf Grey was released on 14th February 2020 at a retail price of $120.

name: Sail Dark Marina Blue
title: Nike Dunk Low SE Sail Dark Marina Blue
description:
The Nike Dunk Low SE Sail Dark Marina Blue is dressed in a color pattern of Dutch blue, white, and dark marina blue.​
​
​Sail, gum light brown, and gum royal make up the shoe's colorway. This sneaker's sail white leather upper is accented by blue mesh tongues and tumbled leather Swooshes. It has a white leather base with white leather overlays, laces, tongue tags, and yellow heel branding. The design is finished with tongues, insoles, and heels that have the Nike branding, a sail midsole, and a gum rubber outsole.
​
​The Nike Dunk Low SE Sail Dark Marina Blue was released on September 1, 2022, and retailed at $110.

name: Travis Scott Wheat
title: Nike Air Trainer 1 SP Travis Scott Wheat
description:
Drawing inspiration from hiking culture and gear, the Nike Air Trainer 1 SP Travis Scott Grey Wheat arrives in a dark brown canvas construction with matching mesh overlays and single stitch Swoosh logos. Canvas shrouds on the upper give wearers options for styling. At the heel and inside of the tongue, concealed zipper pockets provide extra storage. From there, "Cactus Corporation" insignias at the heel and forefoot velcro strap complete the design.

The Nike Air Trainer 1 SP Travis Scott Wheat released in May of 2022 and retailed for $160.

name: Mono Mist
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Mono Mist
description:
The adidas Yeezy 350 V2 Mono Mist's upper delivers monofilament mesh, a new material choice for the sneaker. Lastly, traditional Boost sole is added to the sole.

The adidas Yeezy 350 V2 Mono Mist released in June of 2021 for $220, exclusively in EU.

name: Protection Pack Dark Moss
title: New Balance 2002R Protection Pack Dark Moss
description:
The New Balance 2002R Protection Pack Dark Moss is one of four colorways in the Protection Pack.

Taking inspiration from New Balance’s MR2002 high-end running shoe from 2010, this silhouette is dressed in dark moss, grey, and black while sporting a peek of yellow coming from the back heel. Its innovative ripstop base layer is eye-catching and functional as it is waterproof. Comfort is top of mind as an ABZORB midsole and ABZORB SBS heel provides cushioning with every step. Branding hits can be found on the sides, top, and bottom of the tongue. Giving off an earthy autumn vibe, these sneakers come with toggle laces.

Our experts think that the tech features in this shoe are what make it stand out. The Stability Web in the outsole provides arch support while a proprietary N-ergy outsole absorbs all shocks. The New Balance 2002R Protection Pack Dark Moss debuted on September 21, 2023, and sold at a retail price of $160.

name: White Gum
title: Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 White Gum
description:
The Nike Air Force 1 Low White Gum is a reworked version of the classic Nike Air Force 1 Low. Like the classic Nike Air Force 1 Low, this shoe has a white upper made out of tumbled leather with white laces, Nike swooshes, and tongues. Unlike the original Nike Air Force 1 Low which has a white midsole and outsole, this redefined colorway has a solid gum midsole and outsole.

The Nike Air Force 1 Low White Gum was released on 31st March 2021. During its release, this sneaker commanded a retail price of $120.

name: Black Wonder Leopard (Women's)
title: adidas Handball Spezial Black Wonder Leopard (Women's)
description:
The adidas Handball Spezial Black Wonder Leopard (Women's) is an iconic low-profile silhouette from the adidas Handball Spezial line in a Black Wonder Leopard colorway.

The adidas Handball Spezial originally pulled design inspiration from the handball court. The three stripes feature wonder leopard print in this iteration, and they have the jagged edges which is a staple of this silhouette. The upper is made of black suede, which gives it a premium feel and elevates the aesthetic. Notice the white SPEZIAL branding and trefoil that are imprinted alongside the top stripe on the lateral side. The back heel counter is white without branding, while the gum rubber outsole has adidas branding and perforations around the toe.

According to our experts, the fashionable leopard print stripes are a standout feature and give the shoe some individuality. Originally released on May 1, 2024, the adidas Handball Spezial Black Wonder Leopard (Women's) retailed for $110.

name: Paisley Pack Worn Blue (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Essential Paisley Pack Worn Blue (Women's)
description:
As part of the 2022 Nike Dunk Paisley Pack, the women's exclusive Nike Dunk Low Blue Paisley (W) features a smooth white leather construction with light blue leather overlays, canvas Paisley Swooshes, and matching heel tabs. At the base, a white and light blue sole completes the design.

The Nike Dunk Low Blue Paisley (W) released in March of 2022 and retailed for $120.

To shop all Nike Dunks, click here.

name: For All Time Red
title: Puma LaMelo Ball LaFrancé Amour Red
description:
The Puma LaMelo Ball LaFrancé Amour For All Time Red is part of the Puma x LaFrancé collaboration, which expresses NBA player LaMelo Ball’s personal style through the exaggerated silhouettes LaFrancé is known for.

Like other footwear in the collection, the For All Time Red Puma LaMelo Ball LaFrancé Amour features an all-over red colorway of For All Time Red. Reminiscent of Y2K fashion, thick padding in the collar and side panels gives the sneaker a chunky aesthetic. The upper boasts a durable canvas base with overlays in shiny patent leather. The full-length internal EVA midsole adds cushioning, while the fully wrapped rubber cupsole provides stability. The midsole and outsole display branding specific to LaMelo Ball and ‘LaFrancé’ provides the traction pattern underfoot.

Our StockX experts like the oversized, red laces, which match LaFrancé’s preference for exaggerated proportions. The Puma LaMelo Ball LaFrancé Amour For All Time Red was released on May 17, 2024, and sold for $120.

name: Black Gum
title: adidas Samba Vegan Black Gum
description:
The adidas Samba Vegan Black Gum is part of adidas' vegan collection. adidas is going through its collection of enduring sneakers and updating them with vegan components.
​​
​The Samba Vegan in black shuns conventional leather construction in favor of a novel design that forgoes all animal-based components, including adhesives and dyes. This sneaker uses a vegan leather with a unique light top and a gum rubber bottom. On its sides, you'll find adidas stripes. It also features the adidas logo imprinted on the tongue. Near the stripes on the sides and near to the collar is the Samba branding.
​
​The adidas Samba Vegan Black Gum debuted on June 16, 2021, and retailed at $100.

name: All-Star
title: Nike KD 16 All-Star
description:
The Nike KD 16 All-Star is an athletic shoe featuring a mesh upper with green tiger print, complemented by blocks of magenta.

Designed for the 2024 NBA All-Stars, Nike has created a special colorway for the Nike KD 16 collection, in honor of Phoenix Suns player Kevin Durant. Known as Easy Money because of his ability to effortlessly score points on the basketball court, the KD 16 pays homage to this nickname beneath the orange overlay. A holographic disc appears on the tongue tab, bearing the initials KB in dollar bill print. Kevin Durant branding appears as his name and number visible beneath semi-opaque overlays in Orange TPU, which extend to form the outsole. A yellow midsole and Nike Swooshes in purple at the heel complete the look.

Our experts feel that the best feature of the KD 16 is its vibrant color palette, which is eye-catching and unique. The Nike KD 16 All-Star released on February 16, 2024, and retailed at $160.

name: White Red Dahlia (Women's)
title: ASICS Gel-1130 White Red Dahlia (Women's)
description:
The ASICS Gel-1130 White Red Dahlia (Women's) adds stripes of rich Red Dahlia to the Gel-1130's web of supportive overlays.

Although inspired by the Gel-Kayano 14 and the 9th model released in the Gel-1000 series, this version of the Gel-1130 transcends its early 2000s roots. Soft suede paneling replaces traditional materials like leather, giving the White Red Dahlia (Women's) ASICS Gel-1130 sneaker a more contemporary appearance. While Red Dahlia is the standout color on the overlays, white and metallic silver also catch the eye. The airy mesh upper in white serves as a clean, neutral backdrop for the overlays, while the sole unit comes in an off-white hue that brings out the warmth in the Red Dahlia.

Our experts like the Gel technology in the heel, which provides long-lasting comfort and energy return. The women’s size ASICS Gel-1130 White Red Dahlia (Women's) was released on June 25, 2024, and sold for $100.

name: Collegiate Green
title: adidas Samba OG Collegiate Green
description:
The adidas Samba OG Collegiate Green adds a simple, retro-inspired colorway of Collegiate Green and Cloud White to the Samba OG silhouette.

Originally envisioned as a soccer shoe, this version of the Samba OG features a sleek silhouette with minimal padding. Cloud White covers the full-grain leather upper, while splashes of Collegiate Green decorate the large serrated 3-Stripes logo and the leather heel tab. The Collegiate Green’s rich green is reminiscent of varsity sports colors and gives the shoe a retro appeal. adidas branding decorates the tongue and insole, but, in our opinion, the ‘SAMBA’ lettering in gold foil is the stand-out feature.

Our experts like the light beige hue applied to the suede toebox overlay because it breaks up the purely Collegiate Green and Cloud White upper without distracting from the design. The adidas Samba OG Collegiate Green was released on March 1, 2024, and retailed at $120.

name: CO.JP University Red Obsidian
