title: Nike Dunk Low Retro SE CO.JP University Red Obsidian
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Retro SE CO.JP University Red Obsidian celebrates the 25th anniversary of the exclusive Japanese release of the Nike Dunk Low CO.JP "City Attack." This sneaker pays homage to the original with just a few tweaks.

This Special Edition Nike Dunk low-top features an upper base of University Red leather with perforations scattered across the toebox for breathability and comfort. Obsidian leather forms the upper overlays, as well as the Nike Swoosh that runs across the quarter panel back to the heel. Obsidian flat laces cross over a red mesh tongue and match the obsidian mesh sock liner. This eye-catching sneaker rides on a white foam midsole with tonal lacing and an Obsidian outsole that sports grooves and lugs for impact absorption and traction.

Our favorite details of this sneaker are the ones that are different from the 1999 release. The colors on the tongue tag are flipped and the insole of this iteration is white. The Nike Dunk Low Retro SE CO.JP University Red Obsidian was released on July 5, 2024, for retail price of $115.

name: Recraft Triple White
title: Nike Air Max 90 Recraft Triple White
description:
The Nike Air Max 90 Recraft Triple White was first designed by Tinker Hatfield and was re-released for the celebration of the shoe’s 30th anniversary. It provides plenty of support and cushion.

This model provides a fresh take on the original Air Max 90 Infrared. It has a white sole as well as a white base and is made of a mixture of leather, suede overlays, and mesh. On the shoe, you will also find a white leather mudguard.

The Nike Air Max 90 Recraft Triple White had an initial release date of January 2020. The starting price for this model was $160.

name: 75th Anniversary Pack Black
title: adidas Samba OG 75th Anniversary Pack Black
description:
The world-renowned sneaker company chose the adidas Samba OG 75th Anniversary Pack Black to celebrate its 75th anniversary because the Samba debuted in 1949, the same year the company launched.

For this celebratory shoe, the base is composed of premium tumbled black leather with a black suede T-toe overlay. Smooth white leather is used for the signature serrated side-panel 3-Stripes, as well as the eyestay and heel overlays. The tongue is black leather, while the sock liner is white leather. Gold lettering forms the Samba branding on the outer side panel, as well as the 75 and trefoil branding that hits each heel tab. The textured black foam midsole rides on a black rubber outsole that sports a pattern designed to absorb impact and provide grip.

The detail we love the most about this anniversary pair of sneakers is the dates in gold on the sock liner, 18.08.1949, the company’s debut date, and 18.08.2024, adidas’s 75th birthday. The adidas Samba OG 75th Anniversary Pack Black was released on August 16, 2024, for $110 retail.

name: Athletic Department Light Bone University Gold
title: Nike Air Max 1 Athletic Department Light Bone University Gold
description:
The Nike Air Max 1 Athletic Department Light Bone University Gold is an ode to the original Air Max 1 and is designed to have nostalgic varsity vibes. The body of this model is a Light Bone color, while the sole is a mixture of black and gold.

The Air Max 1 in Athletic Department Light Bone University Gold has a black and gold sole that sits right next to the cream-colored midsole. The body of this Nike Air Max 1 model comes in a Light Bone color that is made of leather and features black, gray, and white overlays. The Nike Swoosh is in black, and the laces are an off-white color.

One component of the Nike Air Max 1 Athletic Department Light Bone University Gold that our team loves is the splashes of gold that make the shoe’s neutral base pop. This model became available for purchase on July 28th, 2023, and was set at a retail price of $150.

name: Luxury Red
title: adidas Harden Vol. 8 Luxury Red
description:
The adidas Harden Vol. 8 Luxury Red is a bold basketball sneaker designed to give you a performance shoe that turns heads. It's designed to meet the demands of on-court action while looking good by combining advanced materials and a striking design.

The Luxury Red adidas Harden Vol. 8 by adidas blends premium suede on the toe cap with breathable jersey mesh on the midfoot. A prominent red upper combined with black accents on the neoprene bootie and lace system gives you a lovely contrast. The red-and-black outsole incorporates JETBOOST cushioning for extra responsiveness. This design reflects adidas’ commitment to innovation that stems from its storied history in performance footwear, dating back to the 1940s.

As the experts, one thing we enjoy about the adidas Harden Vol. 8 Luxury Red is the color combination. Another standout feature is the precise contrast detailing, which amplifies its visual appeal. This model was released on September 1, 2024, at $160.

name: Racer Blue (Women's)
title: Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Racer Blue (Women's)
description:
The Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Racer Blue (Women's) maintains the Zoom Vomero 5’s classic design while adding a vibrant colorway of Racer Blue with metallic silver and black accents.

Reimagining early 2000s running shoes, this iteration of the Zoom Vomero 5 features responsive Zoom Air cushioning in the Cushlon foam midsole. The upper is crafted from durable mesh with supportive synthetic overlays and distinctive plastic caging on the heel – all in Racer Blue. Adding an eye-catching detail, the Swoosh logos come in a mirror-like material that complements the 3M reflective detailing on the overlays. While the midsole and upper come in Racer Blue, the rubber outsole features contrasting black.

Our experts at StockX like the sophistication provided by the suede eyestays to the sneaker’s performance-first design. The women’s size Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Racer Blue (Women's) was released on July 1, 2024, and was orginally priced at $160.

name: Onyx (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Slide Onyx (Kids)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Slide Onyx (Kids) applies an onyx finish to the sandal, featuring a rubberized foam build with a textured surface.

The minimalist design of the adidas Yeezy Slide Onyx (Kids) is free of any exterior branding, save for adidas’ three-stripe logo stamped on the soft top layer of the footbed. Open-toe construction delivers ventilated comfort, while the pair’s footbed includes a soft top layer for comfort. Underfoot, the pair features deep horizontal sawtooth-like grooves that provide traction.

The adidas Yeezy Slide Onyx (Kids) was released in March 2021 and retailed for $50.

name: Mystic Red Rosewood
title: Nike SB Dunk Low Mystic Red Rosewood
description:
The Nike SB Dunk Low Mystic Red Rosewood is crafted predominantly from plush suede, exuding a strong retro vibe while merging Mystic Red, Emerald Rise, Rugged Orange, and Rosewood into a distinctive and harmonious color scheme that combines the finest attributes of each shade.

The Mystic Red Rosewood Nike SB Dunk Low departs from the conventional leather construction, opting for a shaggy suede upper in a vibrant crimson color, while additional touches of Emerald Rise grace the iconic Swoosh and Nike branding found on the cushioned tongue and heel tab. Within the shoe, a foam insole includes a Zoom Air unit to enhance impact absorption. Completing the low-top design is a sturdy rubber cup sole, finished in a solid Rosewood tone, providing durability and style.

What our experts love about the Nike SB Dunk Low Mystic Red Rosewood its suede construction. This luxurious and shaggy suede material not only offers a premium and tactile feel, but also adds a distinctive retro aesthetic to the sneakers. The sneaker was released on August 23, 2023, for $110.

name: White Black Metallic Pewter
title: Nike Air Max Plus White Black Metallic Pewter
description: The Nike Air Max Plus White Black Metallic Pewter is a sleek and stylish sneaker that combines classic design with modern technology. The upper is made of a durable and breathable mesh material, with synthetic overlays for added support and structure. The iconic Air Max cushioning system provides superior comfort and shock absorption, while the rubber outsole offers excellent traction and durability. The colorway features a clean white base with black and metallic pewter accents, giving the shoe a bold and eye-catching look. Released on April 10th, 2020, the Nike Air Max Plus White Black Metallic Pewter retails for $160. Whether you're hitting the gym or hitting the streets, these sneakers are sure to turn heads and keep you comfortable all day long.

name: Black (Non-Reflective)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Black (Non-Reflective)
description: You can never have too much heat, so cop the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Black. This Yeezy Boost 350 V2 comes with a black upper, black midsole, and a black sole. These sneakers released in June 2019 and retailed for $220. Buy these today on StockX.

name: Earth Light Bone
title: Nike P-6000 Earth Light Bone
description:
The Nike P-6000 Earth Light Bone finds inspiration in the Air Pegasus from 2006, but also draws on other technical running shoes in Nike’s early 2000s catalog.

Leather and suede overlays in Sail and Light Bone add structure to the breathable mesh upper. The combination of materials on the upper helps the sneaker remain lightweight, while soft cushioning in the midsole adds comfort. Hits of brown can be found on the rubber outsole and on the thread outlining the Swoosh. Additional branding can be found on the tongue, and "P-6000" is printed near the heel. Padding around the collar and in the tongue contributes to the sneaker’s bulky aesthetic without creating a heavy feel.

Our experts at StockX like the sneaker’s neutral aesthetic, created by overlapping Sail, Phantom, Light Bone, and Earth tones. The Nike P-6000 Earth Light Bone was released on January 30, 2024, and retailed at $120.

name: Carbon Fiber
title: Jordan 1 Mid Carbon Fiber All-Star (2021)
description:
The Air Jordan 1 Mid Carbon Fiber released alongside a pair of Nike Dunks, Air Force 1s, and Air Foamposite Ones to commemorate 2021’s NBA All-Star Game.

Just like each pair within the All-Star pack, the Air Jordan 1 Mid Carbon Fiber also features a black patent leather upper. Under the light, a pattern resembling carbon fiber plating, similar to those found on the outsoles of Jordan 11s, appears on the patent leather upper as well. White leather underlays and a white Wings logo on the ankle add contrast to the shiny material. Lastly, a Jumpman tongue tag is stitched onto a nylon tongue.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid Carbon Fiber released in March of 2021 for $125.

name: Animal Pack Giraffe/Cheetah
title: Nike Dunk Low Retro PRM Animal Pack Giraffe/Cheetah
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Zebra is constructed of a Beach leather upper with Canvas suede overlays decorated with a subtle Cheetah pattern. Baroque Brown Swooshes and heel tabs complete the design.

The Nike Dunk Low Cheetah released in June of 2021 and retailed for $110.

name: White
title: Nike Free RN 2018 White
description:
The Nike Free RN 2018 White is one of Nike’s flexible and lightweight sneakers, dressed in white and black color schemes.

The Nike Free RN 2018 White features a lightweight and breathable mesh upper to allow optimal aeration for comfort during wear. The design also includes a dynamic fit system that utilizes Flywire cables that integrate with the sneaker’s laces to provide a secure and supportive fit. It also includes a rounded heel to promote a natural rolling motion, a lightweight midsole to provide responsive and cushioned comfort, a black Swoosh on the side, and a tri-star patterned outsole with flex grooves to allow for multidirectional flexibility.

The Nike Free RN 2018 White joined Nike’s brands on May 10th, 2018 with a retail price of $100.

name: Ice Blue (2022) (GS)
title: Jordan 1 Mid Ice Blue (2022) (GS)
description:
The Air Jordan 1 Mid Ice Blue GS was manufactured in an ice blue colorway for grade-schoolers.

The accenting blacks fill the dominating vamp, leather panels, and Swooshes, which are established by the quarter overlay, the mudguard, and the collar, as the baby blue colorway combination takes center part. In contrast, the tongue and midfoot design feature a very light Off-White undertone, while the midsole and laces opt for a crisp white finish. It also features the wings logo on its collar. The tongue tag, internal lining, and tread underneath the model's opposing end have an arctic-hued finish.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid Ice Blue GS debuted on 22 October 2022. It retailed at $110.

name: Hand Crafted
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Hand Crafted
description:
The Air Jordan 1 Hand Crafted features a white leather upper with multicolor leather and Durabuck overlays for a unique look. From there, Wings logo collar patches and two-tone laces add a DIY feel.

The Air Jordan 1 Hand Crafted released in December of 2021 and retailed for $170.

name: Travis Scott Neutral Olive
title: Jordan 1 Retro Low Golf Travis Scott Neutral Olive
description:
Indulge in the golf course's lush greens with the Jordan 1 Retro Low Golf Travis Scott Neutral Olive, a stellar collaboration between the iconic Jordan brand and the renowned rapper, Travis Scott. This is the first-ever golf shoe collaboration between Jordan and Travis Scott, making it a rare treasure in the sneaker community.

Reflecting Cactus Jack’s signature earth-toned color palette, this sneaker captivates the crowd with its olive green shade harmoniously blended with sail-tinted leather overlays, a contrasting black reverse Swoosh logo, and subtle touches of bright volt green on the tongue label and heel logo. Crafted for golf enthusiasts, yet with a design that resonates with every sneakerhead, this pair is tailored for the greens with altered traction and hardened rubber. However, the cool and casual vibe it carries makes it suitable for off-the-green casual struts, giving Travis Scott fans a chance to sport these beauties anytime, anywhere.

Dropped on October 13, 2023, at a retail price of $170, the Jordan 1 Retro Low Golf Travis Scott Neutral Olive is not just a pair of sneakers; it's a statement of style, comfort, and unrivaled collaboration between sportswear and music royalty.

name: Tahitian
title: Nike LeBron 21 Tahitian
description:
The Nike LeBron 21 Tahitian is a performance basketball shoe with a low-to-the-ground and lightweight design. It features iridescent details on the heel that resemble a Tahitian pearl and a rope pattern that mimics the patterns on the exterior of a clam’s shell.

The black mesh upper boasts a series of perforations along the side panels that allow the foot to breathe and look like the veining on a clam shell. The quilted tongue also houses perforations and provides plush cushioning. A 360-degree zonal cabling system reinforces the mesh upper without weighing the shoe down. Zoom Air cushioning and foam in the midsole provide responsive cushioning underfoot, while the front lace system secures the fit.

Our StockX experts like the way the iridescent green details on the heel match the green tones of the durable outsole. The Nike LeBron 21 Tahitian was released on November 3rd, 2023, and retailed at $200.

name: Rooted (Women's)
title: Nike Sabrina 1 Rooted (Women's)
description:
The Nike Sabrina 1 Rooted Women's puts a colorful spin on basketball player Sabrina Ionescu’s inaugural collaborative footwear collection.

Designed with the demands of the game in mind, this shoe features a lightweight and breathable mesh upper to provide flexibility and ventilation, as well as a low-cut silhouette for breadth of movement and a padded collar for added comfort. A midfoot band system ensures a secure fit, while a full-length React foam cushion in the midsole and a Zoom Air unit in the forefoot work together to deliver shock absorption and increase stabilization.

What our experts especially appreciate about the Nike Sabrina 1 Rooted Women's, however, is its playful Medium Soft Pink and Total Orange colorway, against which the iconic Nike Swoosh pops in an Oil Green hue on the lateral side. This shoe originally retailed with a price tag of $130 when it was first released on December 6, 2023.

name: Nimbus Cloud
title: New Balance 574 Nimbus Cloud
description:
The New Balance 574 Nimbus Cloud comes in white, grey, and an off-white called nimbus cloud. The shoe has a nimbus cloud leather upper. It also has white leather and mesh sections on the upper part of the shoe. The shoe also features the New Balance logo on both sides of each shoe. Finally, it has a rubber sole with a white mid-section and a black lower finish.

The New Balance 574 Nimbus Cloud was released on March 28th, 2022 and retailed at $85.

name: Patent Elephant Black (Women's)
title: Jordan 1 Low SE Patent Elephant Black (Women's)
description:
The Jordan 1 Low SEPatent Elephant Black (Women's) is a sophisticated, high-fashion sneaker for fun and dressy wear.  It is all-black, made of high-quality leather, and accented with a patterned and textured patent leather material for an elegant touch.

Of course, the shoe is made extra special with various Nike and Jordan logos, such as the Jordan Flight logo on the outer tongue and the Swoosh symbol on the side of the shoe. Perforations on the toe cap and sides give this sneaker enhanced breathability, and Nike Air technology provides the shoe with extra cushioning for better comfort and support throughout the day.

The Jordan 1 Low SEPatent Elephant Black (Women's) is a laced sneaker with black laces for a classic sneaker look. Our team is most impressed with the placement of the white Wings Air Jordan logo on the shoe's heel. Nike released this shoe on July 1, 2024. It originally retailed for $125.

name: White Black Chlorophyll
title: Nike Air Max 1 White Black Chlorophyll
description:
The Nike Air Max 1 White Black Chlorophyll is a sport shoe with Air Max technology that has a bold colorblocked design.

This iteration of the Nike Air Max 1 comes with an upper made of fabric and leather. White fabric makes up the top portion of the shoe, including the toe box, midsoles, and under the laces. There are white fabric overlays that also add visual interest. The Nike swoosh also appears in white on each side. The heel is also sectioned off in white and bears a black Nike Air logo. The entire bottom half of the shoe is black. A thick black mudguard can be seen running around the entire bottom of the shoe, with a wavy pattern near the arch of the foot. The rubber sole and outsole are also black, and clear transparent Air Max units are seen under the heel.

What stands out about this shoe is the thick black mudguard that runs up half of the shoe, giving it a bold design. The Nike Air Max 1 White Black Chlorophyll was released on April 1, 2024, for a price of $150.

name: A Ma Maniére While You Were Sleeping
title: Nike Air Max 95 SP A Ma Maniére While You Were Sleeping
description:
The Nike Air Max 95 SP A Ma Maniére While You Were Sleeping adds a gradient of brown, gray, and pastel-pink hues to the Air Max 95’s iconic wavy overlays.

As a Nike Special Project release, the A Ma Maniére While You Were Sleeping Nike Air Max 95 SP is made with premium materials. It’s also part of a multilabel collaboration, which sees well-known Converse, Jordan Brand, and Nike silhouettes updates with luxury menswear brand Ma Maniere’s timeless, pared-back aesthetic. As one of six Nike models in the collection, this version of the Air Max 95 maintains Virgil Abloh’s preference for sleek lines. The wavy overlays serve as a canvas for an elevated color palette, featuring Dark Violet Ore, Burgundy Ash, light pink, chocolate brown, and gray.

Our experts like the sneaker’s deconstructed aesthetic, including the suede overlays and the leather mudguard. The Nike Air Max 95 SP A Ma Maniére While You Were Sleeping was released on December 7, 2024, and sold for $190.

name: Armory Navy
title: Jordan 1 Mid Armory Navy
description:
The Jordan 1 Mid Armory Navy features a white leather upper with dark navy overlays and Swooshes. At the ankle, black leather collars add a subtle contrast to the overlays. A Jordan Wings logo at the ankle and Jumpman woven label on the tongue complete the design.

The Jordan 1 Mid Armory Navy release in 2022 and retail for $115.

name: Safari Phantom (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Safari Phantom (Women's)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Safari Phantom (Women's) is a low-top silhouette made for women with a design inspired by a safari. 
   
This version of the Nike Dunk Low comes with a leather upper. The base is off-white, making up the side panels, toe box, and ankle area. Leather overlays are seen featuring a wild safari print in shades of gray. These overlays round out the toe box, form the eyestays and ankle strap, and adorn the Swoosh that crosses each side. The toe box is perforated in a radial pattern, channeling the sun's rays. The tongue bears a Nike patch, while the heel collar also contains subtle Nike branding. The shoe sits on a foam midsole and a gray rubber outsole. 

Our favorite thing about this shoe is the classic safari print, which allows the shoe to stand out despite its muted neutral color scheme. The Nike Dunk Low Safari Phantom (Women's) was released on July 1, 2024, for $130.

name: White
title: Nike Air Force 1 Mid '07 White
description:
The Nike Air Force 1 Mid White '07 features a smooth white leather upper with matching overlays and Swooshes. From there, a velcro strap with Nike Swoosh embroidery and a matching Air sole completes the design.

The Nike Air Force 1 Mid White '07 was re-released in December of 2015 and retailed for $95.

name: Blueprint Pack
title: Nike Air Zoom Alphafly Next% 3 FP Blueprint Pack
description:
The Nike Air Zoom Alphafly Next% 3 FP Blueprint Pack is a testament to Nike's dedication to pushing the boundaries of performance running. Featuring a vibrant multi-color palette, this sneaker is designed to catch the eye and deliver top-notch performance. Whether you're training for a marathon or simply enjoy a good run, the Alphafly Next% 3 FP has got you covered.

Equipped with dual Zoom Air units and a full-length carbon plate, this sneaker provides unmatched responsiveness and propulsion. The Flyknit upper ensures a lightweight, breathable fit, adapting to your foot's natural movements for enhanced comfort and support. This combination of advanced technology and striking design makes the Alphafly Next% 3 FP a standout in any runner's collection.

Released on July 3, 2024, the Nike Air Zoom Alphafly Next% 3 FP Blueprint Pack retailed at $285. Its multi-color design underscores Nike's innovative spirit, offering both visual appeal and performance excellence. Step up your running game with this unique and powerful sneaker.
model: Nike Air Zoom Alphafly Next% 3 FP

name: Green Cloud White (Women's)
title: adidas Campus 00s Green Cloud White (Women's)
description:
The adidas Campus 00s Green Cloud White (Women’s) is a shoe inspired by the skate culture of the 90s and the early 2000s. The updated design evokes nostalgia while remaining a modern style icon.

This shoe features a bright green leather upper with white accents. The iconic 3-Stripes of adidas adorn the midsoles of the shoe in white. These Campus 00s iteration for women also feature Cloud White laces and adidas branding in white on the green tongue and heel. The chunky off-white rubber outsole, plus perforation on the side panels for breathability and a round toe, complete the look.

What we at StockX appreciate most about this sneaker is the bold colorway that makes these retro-inspired sneakers stand out. These shoes are truly a statement piece that can be paired with any outfit. The adidas Campus 00s Green Cloud White (Women´s) was released on May 26th, 2023, for a retail price of $110.

name: Protection Pack Grey
title: New Balance 2002R Protection Pack Grey
description:
The New Balance 2002R Protection Pack Grey comes in an all-grey color scheme.

The New Balance 2002R Protection Pack Grey has an upper constructed from a blend of synthetic and breathable mesh materials. The sneaker has a midsole featuring responsive foam for padding and stability. The outsole is made of rubber, making it durable and slip-resistant. The shoes include a sturdy toe cap and a sturdy heel counter for further protection. The shoe features an "N" logo and "2002R" lettering on either side. The sneaker also has "NB" branding on the heel.

The New Balance 2002R Protection Pack Grey was released on February 14, 2023, and retailed for $170.

name: Sail Coconut Milk
title: Nike Air Max Dn Sail Coconut Milk
description:
The Nike Air Max Dn Sail Coconut Milk is an athletic sneaker featuring new Dynamic Air units for increased performance and functionality.

This iteration of the Nike Air Max Dn features a lightweight textile upper in white for breathability. The upper is decorated with a sort of haptic pattern made with dashes in an off-white color across the entire shoe. The upper is supported with white overlays running around the bottom of the whole shoe, and there is a TPU clip under the arch featuring black outlines and a black Nike Swoosh. The heel features an Air Max Dn logo in yellow, while the tongue features this logo again in white. Visible Dynamic Air units sit under the heel, providing a unique visual style and unmatched energy return.

What stands out about this shoe are the Dynamic Air units under the heel in the white outsole. This new technology makes the shoe stand out and allows for even better performance. The Nike Air Max Dn Sail Coconut Milk was released on March 26th, 2024, for a retail price of $160.

name: RTFKT Void (Edition of 11394)
title: Nike Dunk Genesis Low RTFKT Void (Edition of 11394)
description:
The Nike Dunk Genesis Low RTFKT Void (Edition of 11394) is a low-top shoe with a sleek and futuristic design inspired by NFT and gaming.

This iteration of the Nike Dunk Genesis Low features a black textile upper for the toe box, with another black panel separated by raised plastic rounding out the toe. The lateral side of this section features a " +" graphic, nodding to technology. The side panels feature a subtle checked pattern with a Wild Berry pink Nike Swoosh on the lateral side and a Wild Berry RTFKT lightning bolt on the inner side. The black heel area features removable chunky sectioned supports with debossed RTFKT branding and the tongue has a removable void chamber. The shoe features a chunky black branded midsole and black outsole.

What we like best about this sneaker are the removable parts, which allow the wearer to customize the shoe based on their mood. The Nike Dunk Genesis Low RTFKT Void (Edition of 11394) was released on June 21, 2024, for $222.

name: Slime
title: adidas AE 1 Low Lucid Lime
description:
The adidas AE 1 Low Lucid Slime merges cutting-edge basketball performance with striking visual appeal. This beautiful design balances innovation with comfort and features bold green accents on a black base. It's tailored for dynamic on-court play and everyday use.

The Slime AE 1 Low by adidas features a black mesh upper enhanced by generative support wings in fluorescent-green coloring, creating a honeycomb structure for improved breathability. TPU sidewalls bolster stability, while a responsive Boost midsole ensures cushioning while walking or running. The shoe has Anthony Edwards' logo on the tongue and the adidas 3-Stripes visible on the heel counter.

One thing we love about the adidas AE 1 Low Lucid Slime is its generative support wings that give you optimal airflow and support during high-intensity movement. The full-length Boost midsole is another great feature that delivers responsive comfort. Retailing at $110, this model debuted on September 21, 2024​.

name: Slate Grey Raincloud
title: New Balance 9060 Slate Grey Raincloud
description:
The New Balance 9060 Slate Grey Raincloud has a neutral colorway, making it a versatile trainer with practically any clothing. It's also packed full of New Balance athletic technology, giving you an innovative modern running shoe.

The New Balance 9060 line has seen some wonderfully futuristic designs, and while this one has a muted colorway, it still looks very high-tech. The light gray and off-white shades combine well with the wavy slate-colored sole. These panels alternate between suede and textile. Comfort is assured with NB's ABZORB heel and midsole cushioning.

Our reviewers love the fashion-forward styling of this trainer. We also appreciate all the little details, like the sculpted pod in the midsole area and the six separate high-grip cushioning platforms in the undersole. They give this shoe a distinctive silhouette, providing excellent flexibility and foot support. The New Balance 9060 Slate Grey Raincloud was released on 1 September 2024, priced at $150.

name: Turtledove Gold Metallic
title: New Balance 530 Turtledove Gold Metallic
description:
The New Balance 530 Turtledove Gold Metallic adds Metallic Gold accents to the 530’s technical silhouette.

This lifestyle sneaker finds inspiration in the performance running shoes from the early 2000s. It features a lightweight mesh upper in Turtledove with crisscrossing synthetic leather overlays in metallic gold. The New Balance ‘N’ adds an extra pop of gold to the side panels, while ‘530’ can be found on the heel overlay. The mesh tongue also displays ‘NB running’ branding in black lettering, on a synthetic leather panel. The sneaker features heritage technology, including a responsive ABZORB midsole that protects against impact stress. The midsole and the padded collar contribute to the sneaker’s slightly bulky silhouette.

Our experts at StockX like the heel pull tab, which assists with putting on and taking off the sneaker. The New Balance 530 Turtledove Gold Metallic was released on August 28th, 2023, and retailed at $100.

name: Museum Masterpiece
title: Nike Air Max 1 '86 OG Museum Masterpiece
description:
The Nike Air Max 1 '86 OG Museum Masterpiece reinterprets the Air Max 1 as a work of art with museum-themed details.

This retro-inspired sneaker was created to celebrate Nike Air Max Month, a Nike campaign that celebrates the release of the first sneaker with Air Max technology in 1986. It also pays tribute to Tinker Hatfield, the designer behind some of Nike’s most recognizable silhouettes. A marble pattern decorates the entire multi-color leather upper and resembles the floors of many iconic museums. The midsole features a similar marble texture and the exaggerated visible Air Max units originally found in the 1986 model.

Our StockX experts like the details on the insoles, including ‘PLEASE DO NOT STEP ON THE ART’ and information about Tinker Hatfield and the OG Air Max 1. The Nike Air Max 1 '86 OG Museum Masterpiece was launched on March 9th, 2024, and retailed at $170.

name: Ivory Mid Grey
title: ASICS Gel-NYC Ivory Mid Grey
description:
The ASICS Gel-NYC Ivory Mid Gray is a running sneaker with a design that draws inspiration from the early 2000s for a retro look.

This version of the ASICS Gel-NYC features an upper with a base of white mesh. Suede overlays appear in mid-gray across the toe-box and mudguard, while the signature ASICS pattern is formed on the sides of the shoe in white and light gray overlays. The ASICS logo appears on the lateral heel, another one on the tongue, and a GEL logo on the heel. GEL technology is present both in the forefoot and in the rear of the shoe, and the bubbly sole appears in gray and white. A gray outsole completes the look.

What we like most about this sneaker is the monochromatic color scheme, which gives it a clean look. The ASICS Gel-NYC Ivory Mid Grey was released on March 1, 2024, for a price of $140.

name: Crystal White Better Scarlet (Women's)
title: adidas Campus 00s Crystal White Better Scarlet (Women's)
description:
The adidas Campus 00s were originally released right around the turn of the century and were part of a long Campus lineage that dated back to the 1970s. The adidas Campus 00s Crystal White Better Scarlet (Women's) sneakers are a slightly modernized take on the Campus 00s that were unveiled in the 2000s.

These adidas Campus 00s, which were only available in women’s sizes, featured a light grey upper consisting mostly of calf leather. They also had bright pops of red on the tongue and heel, and the Three Stripes on the sides of the sneakers were covered in red as well. A bright-white midsole with a gum rubber outsole completed the appearance of this shoe and helped introduce the Campus 00s to a new audience.

What our experts came to appreciate most about these updated Campus 00s, though, were the thick white laces that made them look like shoes from the early aughts. They also came with a second set of red laces that were designed to make them stand out even more. The adidas Campus 00s Crystal White Better Scarlet (Women's) was released on April 4, 2023, for a $110 retail price.

name: Light Purple Floral (Women's)
title: adidas Samba Light Purple Floral (Women's)
description:
The adidas Samba Light Purple Floral (Women's) is a women’s sized adidas Samba model presenting with a light purple floral design.

The premium leather upper of the Light Purple Floral (Women's) adidas Samba is a white color. Cloud white appears as the toebox color, which gives the sneaker a slight contrast. The adidas 3-Stripes adorn the side panels in Core Black leather and their signature zigzag edging. Black also graces the heel tab, which is slightly ribbed. Embroidered flowers in light purple with a yellow center are scattered throughout the sneaker and add a touch of playfulness. Branding is seen on the tongue and SAMBA is printed above the top stripe. A gum outsole completes the shoe.

We think this sneaker gets its character from the embroidered light purple floral embellishments that are strategically placed around the upper. The adidas Samba Light Purple Floral (Women's) colorway released on August 1, 2024, and had a retail price of $120.

name: Gym Red Flint Grey
title: Jordan 13 Retro Gym Red Flint Grey
description:
Jordan flipped one of the most popular Jordan 13 colorways of all time to create a new colorway with the Air Jordan 13 Red Flint. The Red Flint draws its inspiration from the often re-issued Air Jordan 13 Flint, remixing to the iconic colorway.

The Air Jordan 13 Red Flint features an upper made of red reflective mesh, white leather, and Flint Durabuck. In line with Jordan 13s of the past, a holographic Jumpman emblem is displayed on the lateral ankle. An embroidered Jumpman insignia on the tongue, and a Flint and white sole complete this Jordan 13.

The Jordan 13 Red Flint released in April of 2021 and retailed for $190.

name: Aster Pink (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Next Nature Aster Pink (Women's)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Next Nature Aster Pink (Women's) was part of Nike’s Summer 2024 collection and features bright color-blocking in Aster Pink and a neutral Sail base.

Although this low-top sneaker comes in a familiar colorway, it’s part of Nike’s "Move to Zero" campaign and a "Next Nature" release. Displaying slightly speckled rubber in the outsole, the Aster Pink (Women's) Nike Dunk Low Next Nature includes at least 20 percent recycled or reclaimed materials by weight. The leather construction features Aster Pink on the forefoot and heel overlays, the eyelets, the heel tab, and the signature Swoosh logo. Additionally, the rubber outsole and the lining also come in Aster Pink.

Our experts at StockX appreciate that this sneaker allows individuals to invest in a more sustainable future without sacrificing heritage designs. The women’s size Nike Dunk Low Next Nature Aster Pink (Women's) was released on May 28, 2024, and sold for $115.

name: Real Pink Sandstone
title: New Balance 1000 Real Pink Sandstone
description:
The New Balance 1000 Tan Pink Green is a revival of a classic Nineties trainer with a striking colorway. It has a futuristic look, with high-tech styling to match the advanced materials and construction. It's not OTT though – this is a nicely refined running shoe.

The intricate colorway of this New Balance trainer is highly detailed. The top section of the upper is a light tan, made from top-grade leather. The lower section is baby pink, featuring textile cutouts for breathability. In between runs a wavy line of green ripstop. The thick sole is segmented, with New Balance's ABZORB cushioning at the toe and heel.

We love the fashion-forward design of this trainer. The original look has aged well, and this update has added many extra details and tech to an already very high-performance running shoe. It's extremely grippy, which makes it great for road or trail running. The New Balance 1000 Tan Pink Green was released on 11 September 2024 at a retail price of $150.

name: Sail
title: Nike Air Max 1 SC Sail
description:
The Nike Air Max 1 SC Sail is a "Sports Classic" sneaker, which means it’s designated as a heritage model due to its influence on sports culture.

In this case, this original Nike Air Max started as a running shoe, and this sneaker continues its legacy. It boasts a woven textile upper in white with synthetic leather overlays in Sail and a mudguard in warm Coconut Milk. In addition, a white Swoosh checks across the side panel. The low-cut collar features padding, which works with the thick midsole to provide a slightly bulky silhouette. As is expected of Air Max 1 models, the "SC Sail" version displays visible Air Max units in the heel. These units protect against impact and provide responsive cushioning

Our StockX experts like the combination of warm, off-white colors across the upper, which gives the sneaker a neutral aesthetic. The Nike Air Max 1 SC Sail was released on April 5, 2024, and retailed at $150.

name: Electro Orange
title: Jordan 1 Retro High Electro Orange
description:
The Air Jordan 1 High Electro Orange features a white leather upper with black overlays and a Hyper Orange ankle wrap. From there, a matching woven tongue label and sole complete the design.

The Air Jordan 1 High Electro Orange released in July of 2021 and retailed for $170.

name: Halloween (2023)
title: Nike Air Force 1 Low PRM Halloween (2023)
description:
The Nike Air Force 1 Low PRM Halloween (2023) takes the classic Air Force 1 silhouette and upgrades it with nightmarish details. This sneaker was released alongside the Halloween-themed Nike SB Dunk High Sweet Tooth Candy Corn and the Nike Ja 1 Halloween.

This reimagining of the AF 1 features an all-black upper made of texturized leather and overlays embossed with snakeskin designs. Other details include the Swoosh, the heel panel, and the lace cage, which come with all-black snakeskin patterns. The outsole and tread feature a vibrant color scheme of Campfire Orange, Smoke Grey, and Green. The rubber is almost opaque and makes the Green glow as it creates a snakeskin pattern across the bottom of the shoe.

What do our experts love about this sneaker? The Black midsole blends in with the upper and contrasts the eye-catching outsole. The Nike Air Force 1 Low PRM Halloween (2023) was released on October 30, 2023, and retailed at $145.

name: White Wood Crepe
title: ASICS Gel-1130 White Wood Crepe
description:
The ASICS Gel 1130 White Wood Crepe pays homage to the original ASICS Gel-1130 model by combining innovative technology with a late 2000s aesthetic.

Originally a part of the GEL-1000 series, these shoes are crafted from premium suede and mesh to deliver durability and flexibility. Synthetic overlays further add to the shoe’s durability, ensuring that it maintains its structure even with frequent use. This model features gel cushioning technology in the heel and forefoot areas to minimize shock and absorb impact, allowing for comfortable all-day wear. A durable rubber outsole with a patterned tread provides strong traction on many surfaces, while a standard lacing system offers a secure and customizable fit.

What our experts most appreciate about the ASICS Gel 1130 White Wood Crepe, however, is its neutral color scheme of white and wood crepe which gives it a versatile and timeless aesthetic. This shoe originally retailed for $95 when it was released on January 1, 2024.

name: Nigo White
title: Nike Air Force 3 Low SP Nigo White
description:
The Nike Air Force 3 Low SP Nigo White is an athletic shoe featuring a White fabric upper with multicolored overlays in Tour Yellow, Pink Foam, Blue Void, and Lucky Green. Multicolored Force branding appears on the tongue, and the rear features Nigo Force branding with the Swoosh in silver. Midsole extensions coordinate with the Nike Swoosh in University Red, balanced by a White midsole and Black outsole. The shoe has a rounded toe cap and traction-patterned outsoles.

American athletic wear brand Nike teamed up with Nigo, founder of the Japanese streetwear brand A Bathing Ape, to create a collection of sneakers that expresses both brands' boundless aesthetics and style prowess. The collaboration was rumored for a year before evidence of its existence was exhibited during Paris Fashion Week, an appropriate time and venue for the stylish reaches of this creative alliance.

Our experts feel that the Air Force 3's best feature is its specialized branding, which gives it a trompe l'oeil effect. The Nike Air Force 3 Low SP Nigo White was released on October 4th, 2024, and retailed for $160.

name: Racer Blue
title: Jordan 3 Retro Racer Blue
description:
The Air Jordan 3 Racer Blue features a white tumbled leather upper with grey perforated leather eyestays and Cement overlays. From there, hits of Racer Blue on the Jumpman logos and midsole add vibrance to the classic model.

The Air Jordan 3 Racer Blue released in July of 2021 and retailed for $190.

name: Metallic Black
title: Jordan 1 Retro Low '85 Metallic Black
description:
The Jordan 1 Retro Low '85 Metallic Black brings the iconic 1985 cut of the Air Jordan 1 to a low-top version, providing a fresh take on one of the most beloved models in sneaker history. Featuring a clean white, black, and neutral grey colorway, this low-top version offers the same timeless appeal and cultural significance as the original high-top. The metallic black accents on the swoosh and other detailing add a sleek, modern twist, perfect for those looking to blend classic style with contemporary streetwear.

The Jordan 1 Retro Low '85 retains all the elements that made the original Jordan 1 a cultural phenomenon, from the premium leather construction to the classic Nike Air branding. This low-top version is perfect for sneaker enthusiasts who want a more versatile, easy-to-wear option without sacrificing the boldness of the original design. Its influence on both basketball and streetwear culture remains undeniable, making this release a must-have for any collection.

Released on October 2, 2024, the Jordan 1 Retro Low '85 Metallic Black retailed for $160. This model continues the legacy of the Air Jordan 1, offering both heritage and modern flair in one stylish package.

name: Lilac Bloom (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Premium Lilac Bloom (Women's)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Premium Lilac Bloom (Women's) updates the Dunk Low Premium silhouette with a pastel colorway of Lilac Bloom, Soft Yellow, Coconut Milk, Sail, and Baroque Brown.

Modeled after iconic basketball shoes from the 1980s, the upper of the Lilac Bloom (Women's) Nike Dunk Low Premium features a leather base in Sail with color-blocking leather overlays in Lilac Bloom. Another floral-inspired detail is the small flower outlined with Baroque Brown thread on the lateral side panel. Soft Yellow accents decorate the Swoosh logo, the collar lining, the cotton laces, and the ‘NIKE’ lettering on the back tab, while Baroque Brown can be found on the leather back tab, the rubber outsole, and the Nike logo tag on the tongue.

Our experts at StockX like the midsole’s Coconut Milk hue. It gives the sneaker a worn-in appearance that speaks to the shoe’s retro heritage. The women’s size Nike Dunk Low Premium Lilac Bloom (Women's) was originally released on April 1, 2024, and was priced at $120.

name: Black Off Noir
title: Nike Free Run 5.0 Black Off Noir
description:
The Nike Free Run 5.0 Black Off Noir is a sock-like boot of a sneaker that offers a lightweight design intended to create a comfortable barefoot feeling with each step.

The Black Off Noir Nike Free Run 5.0 is a sneaker dressed in unrelieved black. The upper is lightweight breathable knit fabric with Flywire loops that run from the laces down the side panel to add stability and structure. A thick textile heel counter offers support and a heel pull tab makes on/off easy for this pair of kicks. A black tongue and black insole both feature swoosh-pinwheel branding. The midsole is constructed from soft, lightweight foam with laser-cut grooves that add flexibility. A rubber outsole at the forefoot and heel provides durability.

The detail of these Nike shoes we enjoy the most are the reflective swooshes on the lateral side. The subtle sheen in daylight glows in the dark when the lights go out. The Nike Free Run 5.0 Black Off Noir was released on June 28, 2021, for a retail price of $100.

name: Since 72 Pacific Moss
title: Nike Dunk Low Since 72 Pacific Moss
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Since 72 Pacific Moss, a shoe that pays homage to the year Nike was founded, dresses this classic silhouette in heritage fabric choices.

The "Since 72" Pacific Moss Nike Dunk Low-Top features an upper crafted primarily of canvas. Cream-colored canvas forms the base, while stony, tan-colored canvas forms the overlays at the toecap, midfoot, eyestays, collar, and heel counter. Leather in a Pacific Moss hue forms the signature side panel Swoosh, and the heel tab is adorned with a white embroidered Nike wordmark. The padded nylon tongue in Stony Tan features a white tongue tag with Pacific Moss-colored branding that matches the sock liner, which is padded at the collar. A Sail-colored foam midsole with cupsole construction sits atop a rubber outsole that is grooved for traction and matches the Pacific Moss hits on the upper.

The aspect of this sneaker we most enjoy is the Pacific Moss-colored insole. In a '70s style script, it is branded with the "Since 72" logo. The Nike Dunk Low Since 72 Pacific Moss was released on April 1, 2024, for a retail price of $115.

name: Fade
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Fade
description:
Yeezy unlocked a new 350 V2 colorway as part of their Fall 2020 lineup with the Yeezy 350 V2 Fade. The earthy brown look is primed for the autumnal season, embracing the vibe of newly fallen leaves and their natural surroundings.

The Yeezy 350 V2 Fade features a marbled brown Primeknit upper with a deep blue side stripe across the quarter. A tan translucent midsole around a gum Boost interior completes this standard Yeezy design.

The Yeezy 350 V2 Fade released in November of 2020 and retailed for $220.

name: White Metallic Gold Obsidian
title: Jordan 1 Mid White Metallic Gold Obsidian
description:
The Air Jordan 1 Mid White Metallic Gold Obsidian is a recolored version of the OG Air Jordan 1.

Like the OG Air Jordan 1, this shoe boasts a leather upper, a cushioned midsole, and a roughened rubber outsole. Its upper leather features a white base contrasted by obsidian overlays, a perforated toebox, a grayish nylon tongue, white laces, obsidian swooshes, a white Air Jordan Wings logo on its neck collar, and a metallic gold Jumpman logo on its tongue tag.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid White Metallic Gold Obsidian was first released on 1st August 2019. At the time, its retail price was $110.

name: Cream White Collegiate Green Gum
title: adidas Gazelle Indoor Cream White Collegiate Green Gum
description:
The adidas Gazelle Indoor Cream White Collegiate Green Gum is a revival of the original Gazelle from 1979. It features a retro-inspired colorway of Cream White and Collegiate Green and a low-top silhouette.

At the Cream White Collegiate Green Gum adidas Gazelle Indoor, the slightly yellowed Cream White upper gives the sneaker a worn-in appearance that speaks to its retro aesthetic, while the Collegiate Green matches tones found in varsity athletics uniforms from the 1970s. The upper is crafted from soft suede, while the inner lining uses smooth leather. The leather heel mustache and the 3-Stripes display Collegiate Green, which can also be found on the tongue’s adidas lettering. Finally, metallic gold ‘GAZELLE’ lettering runs along the 3-Stripes logo and completes the vintage look.

Our experts at StockX like the use of gum rubber on the outsole because it creates a semi-translucent effect. The adidas Gazelle Indoor Cream White Collegiate Green Gum was released on March 1, 2024, and sold for $120.

name: Off White Dark Blue (Women's)
title: adidas Samba Off White Dark Blue (Women's)
description:
The adidas Samba Off-White Dark Blue (Women's) sneaker keeps the iconic look of the adidas athletic shoe. It has a low-top design and is made of premium leather for comfort and breathability. A thick rubber outsole gives this shoe added durability and better traction for athletic activities.

  Although it has many features of traditional soccer/football sneakers for women, its comfort and classic style have made them a choice for casual wear. It is off-white with navy accents, including the iconic adidas 3-Stripes on the sides of the shoe. These shoes are available in women's US sizes from 5 to 12.

  Our team is most impressed with the Trefoil adidas logo prominently displayed in a lighter blue shade on the shoe tongue. The Samba collection name is also printed near the heel. The adidas Samba Off-White Dark Blue (Women's) was released on July 18, 2024. It originally retailed for $120.

name: Collegiate Green
title: adidas Gazelle Indoor Collegiate Green
description:
The adidas Gazelle Indoor Collegiate Green comes in a Collegiate Green, Hazy Sky, and Victory Gold color palette.

The Collegiate Green adidas Gazelle Indoor features a low-top classic silhouette with a suede upper, providing durability. The shoe includes a lace-up closure system, offering a secure and adjustable fit. The shoe is constructed with a cushioned midsole, providing comfort and support. In addition, the shoe's rubber outsole offers grip and traction. The shoe features "GAZELLE" lettering on one side. The sneaker's design is completed with the adidas Trefoil logo on the midsole and tongue and the signature Three Stripes branding on the lateral sides.

The standout feature of the adidas Gazelle Indoor Collegiate Green is its classic and timeless design. The shoe features a rich and vibrant Collegiate Green colorway, giving it a bold and eye-catching appearance. The adidas Gazelle sneaker was released on December 20th, 2022, and sold for a retail price of $120.

name: Sand Taupe
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Sand Taupe
description:
The Yeezy 350 V2 continued its reign in 2020 with the release of the Sand Taupe colorway. The sneaker brings back adidas and Yeezy’s love for taupe colors that appear on many of their silhouettes. Drops such as the Yeezy 500 Blush, 350 V2 Flax, and 350 Oxford Tan all feature similar hues. This Yeezy adds to that lightly shaded collection.

The Yeezy 350 V2 Sand Taupe features three colors on the sneaker’s upper. Its Primeknit construction is similar to the other 350 V2 colorways that have released. The midsole is filled with adidas’ signature BOOST cushioning to add comfort with every step, plus another set of laces are included with the sneaker to add versatility.

The adidas Yeezy 350 V2 Sand Taupe released in December 2020 for $220.

name: Cream Metallic Blue
title: ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Cream Metallic Blue
description:
The ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Cream Metallic Blue blends classic running technology with modern aesthetics. This retro-inspired sneaker highlights ASICS' commitment to performance-driven designs by giving you a detailed interplay of Cream mesh, Metallic Blue accents, and chrome overlays in a functional and sporty shoe.

The Cream Metallic Blue Gel-Kayano 14 by ASICS features a Cream mesh base for breathability, complemented by Metallic Blue details on the heel, toe, and branding. Chrome overlays improve the design's look and feel, while the navy-blue accents add contrast. First introduced in 2008, the Gel-Kayano 14 was reimagined in 2021 for lifestyle and performance wear, maintaining ASICS' innovative GEL cushioning for improved comfort.

As experts, we enjoy the ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Cream Metallic Blue because of its GEL cushioning, which provides exceptional shock absorption for a smoother stride. Additionally, the chrome overlays add a layer of structure and style. The sneaker retailed for $150 and was officially released on September 19, 2024.

name: Black Canvas
title: Nike Dunk Low Black Canvas
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Black Canvas arrives in a single-tone black color scheme, characterized by their entirely canvas construction on a low-top silhouette.

The Black Canvas Nike Dunk Low ditches the usual leather build in favor of a black textile upper, incorporating synthetic leather in a matching hue for the iconic Swoosh logo and Nike-branded heel tab. A coordinating Nike tag graces the breathable nylon tongue, preserving the shoe's seamless one-color aesthetic. All of this is set atop a contrasting white midsole, with added durability provided by the black rubber outsole underneath. The foam midsole provides responsive cushioning and impact protection, while the low-top silhouette allows for agility and a comfortable fit.

What our experts love about the Nike Dunk Low Black Canvas is its minimalist monochromatic design, where the entire shoe is elegantly rendered in a sleek and timeless black hue, offering a versatile and stylish look that appeals to those who appreciate understated simplicity. The sneaker was released on May 2nd, 2023, for $110.

name: Chili 2.0
title: Nike Air Max 1 Chili 2.0
description:
The Nike Air Max 1 Chili 2.0 takes on the classic silhouette that pays homage to the original Nike Air Max 1, featuring a low-top, sporty profile with a slightly raised heel counter and a sleek, timeless appearance.

The Chili 2.0 Nike Air Max 1 features a white mesh upper to provide breathability, adorned with a scarlet Swoosh logo that is reinforced by synthetic suede overlays in a subtle Pale Gray shade. Complementary black accents are found on the mudguard and the interior lining crafted from textiles. The midsole, made of lightweight white polyurethane and adopting the classic wedge design, delivers comfortable cushioning. It is further enhanced with a Max Air unit in the heel, featuring a touch of red for added visual intrigue. The iconic Swoosh logo is featured on both sides of the shoe, while the Nike Air Max branding can be found on the tongue tag, heel, and on the insole.

Our experts report that the coolest feature of the Nike Air Max 1 Chili 2.0 is its ability to seamlessly blend the classic appeal of the original Air Max 1 design with a modern twist through the vivid "Chili Red" colorway. The sneaker debuted for $140 on July 20th, 2023.

name: Blue Fusion
title: adidas Harden Vol. 8 Blue Fusion
description:
The adidas Harden Vol. 8 Blue Fusion is a basketball shoe designed in collaboration with American basketball star James Harden.

This version of the adidas Harden Vol. 8 is constructed with a Lucid Blue knit upper. The upper is enclosed in an off-white EVA cage from heel to forefoot on each side, providing a unique design and unrivaled support. The heel is reinforced with TPU and the toe box is also hardened. The heel also features a blue pull tab, and the off-white outsole runs up the back of the heel, bearing the iconic Adidas 3-Stripes logo in blue. The tongue also features a pull tab and a sock-like lining around the ankle. A blue and white outsole completes this design.

Our favorite element of this shoe is the minimal branding, which lets the unique design of the EVA cages stand out. The adidas Harden Vol. 8 Blue Fusion was released on May 1, 2024, for $160.

name: Sunrise
title: Nike Book 1 Sunrise
description:
The Nike Book 1 Sunrise introduces a bold design and imaginative materials in a dynamic color palette inspired by the shades of dawn with oranges, pinks, and purples. This modern silhouette reflects Nike's forward-thinking craftsmanship and offers a fresh approach to modern sneaker design.

The Sunrise Book 1 by Nike features a knit upper in gradient tones transitioning from orange to light yellow, mimicking the colors of the sunrise. Structured overlays add durability, while the midsole uses lightweight foam for extra responsiveness. Subtle branding on the tongue and heel complements the futuristic look and feel. The Nike Book line reflects the brand’s evolution since it was founded in 1971 and combines visually appealing designs with the cutting-edge technological approach for which Nike is famous.

What we love about the Nike Book 1 Sunrise is its seamless gradient knit upper, which highlights a new take on color blending in sports shoes, and its lightweight foam midsole. Released on 10th October 2024, it retailed at $140.

name: Wales Bonner Cream White
title: adidas Samba Nylon Tonal Wales Bonner Cream White
description:
The adidas Samba Pony Tonal Wales Bonner Cream White is part of a collaboration between adidas Originals and Wales Bonner, a London-based luxury label known for its reinvention of preppy apparel.

This football training shoe takes the recognizable Samba construction and updates it with shaggy mohair across the upper. The colorway of Cream White and Mystery Brown is reminiscent of the 1970s varsity sports aesthetic, but the mohair gives the sneaker a more luxurious feel. Like other Samba models, this iteration boasts serrated 3-stripes down the side panel that tonally match the fold-over tongue, laces, and heel details. The lace cage, toe overlays, and collar are made of leather in Cream White. A gum rubber outsole completes the look and provides traction.

Our experts love the subtle, tonal stitching, which allows other design features to stand out. The adidas Samba Pony Tonal Wales Bonner Cream White was released on November 8th, 2023, and retailed at $160.

name: White Piquant Orange
title: ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 White Piquant Orange
description:
The ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 White Piquant Orange takes a classic silhouette from the late 2000s and updates it with a better fit and superior cushioning and shock absorption.

The White Piquant Orange colorway of the ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 features an upper of breathable white mesh for a lightweight ride. Black, silver, and shiny orange leather strips overlay this upper, lending style and snug-fitting support. Hits of branding appear throughout the upper, with Gel branding on the heel, Gel-Kayano 14 branding on the orange collar overlay, and ASICS branding on the tongue tag. The black sockliner matches the black insole and sports white ASICS branding.

The aspect of this shoe we appreciate the most is its white foam midsole that incorporates Gel technology in the heel and forefoot for a smooth stride, with a cushioned take-off and landing. This sits atop a black and orange rubber outsole with the TRUSSTIC support system at the midfoot. The ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 White Piquant Orange was released on July 2, 2023, for a retail price of $150.

name: Panda (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Next Nature Panda (Women's)
description:
DISCLAIMER: The Nike Dunk Low Next Nature Panda (Women's) come in 3 variations. All 3 variations share the same style ID, DD1873-102. The 3 variations are as follows; white inner lining/white tongue tag (as pictured), black inner lining/white tongue tag, and black inner lining/black tongue tag. All variations are passable under this product page, as long as the Style ID printed on the box label and size tag is DD1873-102.

The women's Nike Dunk Low Next Nature Panda is constructed of 50% recycled materials. Two-tone black and white Flyleather composes the upper in a simple, color blocked look similar to some of the most popular Dunks to release. From there, matching soles and woven tongue labels add a finishing touch.

The women's Nike Dunk Low Next Nature Panda released in November of 2021 and retailed for $100. As of December 2023 the retail price is $120.

name: Green Bean (2022)
title: Jordan 5 Retro Green Bean (2022)
description:
Having debuted in 2006, the Air Jordan 5 Green Bean (2022) marks the first time the colorway has ever been reissued. It arrives in its original grey reflective construction with hits of Green Bean on the tongue and midsole. At the base, an icy blue semi translucent outsole completes the design.

The Air Jordan 5 Green Bean (2022) released in May of 2022 and retailed for $210.

name: Hyper Pink Laser Orange (Women's)
title: Nike Air Zoom Alphafly Next% 2 Hyper Pink Laser Orange (Women's)
description:
The Nike Air Zoom Alphafly Next 2 Hyper Pink Laser Orange Women's is a cutting-edge running shoe that builds upon the success of its predecessor, the Air Zoom Alphafly Next%, to deliver innovative technology and improved design features that enhance speed, comfort, and efficiency.

This shoe in women's sizing comes equipped with ZoomX foam, Nike's most responsive and lightweight cushioning material, which is strategically placed in the midsole to ensure a plush and responsive feel underfoot. Air Zoom Pods in the forefoot and heel further enhance cushioning and responsiveness. A Flyknit upper wraps around the foot to provide a snug and supportive fit while maintaining breathability and flexibility. Similar to its predecessor, the Air Zoom Alphafly Next 2 features a full-length carbon fiber plate in the midsole which is designed to maximize energy return.

What our experts love most about the Nike Air Zoom Alphafly Next 2 Hyper Pink Laser Orange Women's, however, is its Hyper Pink upper, Laser Orange outsole, and contrasting black accents. This shoe originally retailed for $275 on February 14, 2023.

name: Legend Pink (PS)
title: Jordan 11 Retro Low Legend Pink (PS)
description:
The Jordan 11 Retro Low Legend Pink (PS) updates one of Jordan Brand’s most beloved silhouettes with a soft colorway of white and Legend Pink.

At the Legend Pink (PS) Jordan 11 Retro Low, the signature patent leather mudguard in Legend Pink wraps around the shoe, protecting the white, textile upper. A full-length Air unit provides cushioning underfoot, while the translucent rubber outsole in Legend Pink is one of the sneaker’s heritage design elements. Crisp White laces wind through the lace loops and secure the sneaker’s front closure system. A mini Jumpman logo decorates the heel, while a large Jumpman logo embroidered in Legend Pink thread takes center stage on the oversized, textile tongue.

Our experts like the way the Legend Pink colorway softens the sneaker’s overall design especially when compared to bold Air Jordan 11 colorways preferred by Michael Jordan, including "Bred" and "Concord." The preschool-sized Jordan 11 Retro Low Legend Pink (PS) was released on June 22, 2024, and sold for $80.

name: Grey Matter Harbor Grey
title: New Balance 530 Grey Matter Harbor Grey
description:
The New Balance 530 Grey Matter Harbor Grey is a sneaker inspired by the '90s with modern twists to the classic running shoe.

The New Balance 530 Grey Matter comes with an upper that is primarily mesh. It has leather overlays in a Grey Matter and Harbor Grey colorway that has white and black accents. The shoe features the "N" logo on the quarter panels in Grey Matter with a white outline. Harbor Grey and Grey Matter leather overlays form a cage on the shoe, which uses grey laces for closure. A black heel loop tab contrasts the grey padded collar and features two grey vertical stripes. The shoe also features a "530" logo overlay on the lateral heel in Harbor Grey with white outlining. The outer sole is made of black rubber and contrasts the grey foam midsole.

What do our experts love about the New Balance 530 Grey Matter Harbor Grey? StockX experts like the retro design combined with Abzorb technology in the sole for comfort. The 530 Grey Matter Harbor was released on 1st February 2023 for $100.

name: Taupe Haze
title: Jordan 4 Retro Taupe Haze
description:
Hype for the new Air Jordan 4 Taupe Haze started brewing when the teasers of the sneakers surfaced, with sneakerheads noting their similarities to Travis Scott’s unreleased Air Jordan 4 Olive. Despite being compared to such a hyped sneaker, the Air Jordan 4 Taupe Haze has characteristics that allow it to stand out on its own.

The Air Jordan 4 Taupe Haze features a unique design that elevates the popular Jordan model. The upper holds cracked textures on the forefoot, midfoot, and tongue, with lighter shades of Taupe Haze under the top coat. From there, hits of black appear on the outsole, midsole, and eyelets. An Infrared Jumpman logo on the tongue brightens up the tonal sneaker and completes its overall design.

The Air Jordan 4 Taupe Haze dropped in February of 2021 for $200.

name: Miami Nights
title: adidas Harden Vol. 8 Miami Nights
description:
The adidas Harden Vol. 8 Miami Nights is a basketball shoe featuring a Core Black mesh lace up upper defined by abstract ellipse shaped synthetic Pulse Magenta structural elements, which transition to the mid- and outsole as one unit. Lucid Cyan inserts at the mudguard point coordinate with adidas’ signature three stripes at the rear heel.

The Harden Vol. 8 is an unabashed tribute to the Miami, Florida, aesthetic, designed as a signature sneaker for NBA player James Harden. While Harden plays for the Los Angeles Clippers, German athletic shoe brand adidas knows their signature athletes well. The Vol. 8 Miami Nights pays tribute to Harden’s affinity for frequenting Miami’s nightclub scene during his time off the court.

In our opinion, the best feature of the Harden Vol. 8 is its unique structure, which is accentuated by the Miami Nights colorway. The adidas Harden Vol. 8 Miami Nights released on November 15, 2024, and retailed at $160.

name: Protection Pack Driftwood
title: New Balance 2002R Protection Pack Driftwood
description:
The New Balance 2002R Protection Pack Driftwood design comes with worn-in hairy suede uppers that go well with the base's breathable mesh. 

The stable N-Ergy technology and web underfoot provide comfort. The upper is decorated with 3M reflective details as well as several New Balance-related motifs, most notably the distinctive N logo. Featuring mesh below, the sneaker has a beige-colored fabric. The shoe is made of calf suede and has a comfortable, cushioned sole. Other details include a red NB logo on its insole, a logo patch on its side, front lace-up fastening, and a round toe.

The New Balance 2002R Protection Pack Driftwood was released in March 2023. The sneaker retailed at $170.

name: Black (Women's)
title: Nike Air VaporMax Plus SE Black (Women's)
description:
The Nike Air VaporMax Plus SE Black W is a blacked-out running shoe modeled after the Air Max Plus of 1998.

This running shoe in women sizing features a bootie construction which provides a wearer with a snug and secure fit and an upper crafted out of leather, textile, and suede. Its upper is detailed with shiny overlays that hold in place the laces, VaporMax initials branding on the heel, a lettered VaporMax Air Plus branding on its tongue tag, and Nike Swooshes towards the heel and on the overlays holding the laces in places. The upper sits atop an innovative VaporMax Air sole which provides the sensation of air for soft and lightweight responsiveness, a rubber outsole with rubber pods on high-intensity wear areas for enhanced durability, and lugs to improve its tractions. 

The Nike Air VaporMax Plus SE Black W was released on 12th November 2020. Initially, it retailed at $200.

name: Tom Sachs
title: NikeCraft General Purpose Shoe Tom Sachs
description:
After a brief hiatus following the renowned Mars Yard series, Nike and Tom Sachs joined forces once again in 2022 for the NikeCraft General Purpose Shoe.

The NikeCraft General Purpose Shoe (GPS) is a minimalist, do-everything shoe that will thrive in any possible scenario thrown your way. In a clean styling, the GPS boasts a three-piece molded cup sole, suede mudguards, microfiber collar, and an ultra-breathable knit that is open enough to breathe but tight enough to fend off rain and snow. Touching on Sachs' previous designs, a waffle tread outsole similar to that of the first Nike Moon Shoe and a tongue with exposed foam edges adds a vintage appeal.

The NikeCraft General Purpose Shoe released in June of 2022 and retailed for $110.

name: Sashiko Denim
title: Jordan 1 Low SE WRMK Sashiko Denim
description:
The Jordan 1 Low SE WRMK in Sashiko Denim is a version of the Air Jordan 1 basketball shoe that has become iconic ever since its debut in the 1980s. This version comes in a mostly white and blue colorway.

This basketball shoe was inspired by Wabi Sabi, the Japanese concept that emphasizes finding beauty, even in imperfections. The Jordan 1 Low SE WRMK in Sashiko Denim is constructed of a white canvas base with blue denim overlays with white stitching. The Nike Swoosh appears in black on the midsole and is constructed of leather. The rubber outsole appears yellowed, purposely dirtied to embrace the concept of Wabi Sabi.

What our StockX experts like most about this shoe is its commitment to the Wabi Sabi concept. The construction of the shoe embodies beautiful imperfections perfectly, giving it a relaxed and worn-in look. The Jordan 1 Low SE WRMK in Sashiko Denim was released on August 26th, 2023, for a price of $130.

name: Sculpt
title: adidas Harden Vol. 8 Sculpt
description:
The adidas Harden Vol. 8 Sculpt is part of NBA player James Harden’s 8th lineup of signature sneakers with adidas. This basketball shoe boasts a futuristic look and technical elements designed to improve on-court performance.

The sneaker features an inner cuff with a sock-like fit. Teardrop-shaped EVA panels can be found on the sides and protect the inner cuff. The EVA panels come in a vibrant Hazy Copper and stand out against the Core Black mesh construction. Something that makes this sneaker stand out is the way the EVA panels extend past the upper and into the full-length Jet Boost midsole. A leather toecap protects the toe area, while a ‘JH’ traction pattern underfoot grips the ground.

Our StockX experts like the pull tabs on the heel and above the front lace system. They help the wearer put on and take off the snug-fitting shoe. The adidas Harden Vol. 8 Sculpt was released on February 23rd, 2024, and retailed at $160.

name: Black University Blue
title: Jordan 13 Retro Black University Blue
description:
The Air Jordan 13 Retro University Blue takes on the "Black Cat" silhouette that debuted in 1998.

The upper of this Retro Air Jordan 13 sneaker features black mesh and leather with blue suede overlays. The black tongue and black insole each feature a blue Jumpman and the toe box sports Jordan branding at the bottom of the laces. The panther eye on the lateral-side collar has a holographic finish. The blue midsole has black curving up onto it from the outsole. The outsole, designed to look like a panther paw, features Jumpman and AIR units.

The Air Jordan 13 Retro University Blue was released on December 23rd, 2022 at $200 retail.

name: Pink Foam Red White (GS)
title: Nike Dunk Low Pink Foam Red White (GS)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Pink Red White GS features a white leather upper complemented by pink overlays and a deep red, purple-like shade marking the Swoosh. The pink continues to the mudguard, lacing system, and heel, while underneath, the Nike Dunk keeps its classic color blocking with a white midsole and a pink outsole and treading. 

The grade school-sized Nike Dunk Low Pink Red White GS was released in August 2021 and retailed for $85.

name: Focus Olive (Women's)
title: adidas Gazelle Indoor Focus Olive (Women's)
description:
The adidas Gazelle Indoor Focus Olive (Women’s) is one of many colorways of the popular adidas Gazelle Indoor silhouette, presenting in a Focus Olive, pink, and gum color combination.

Sporting a retro 1960s design, this low top lifestyle sneaker has a Focus Olive colored upper made out of suede. The signature adidas three stripes are seen on both sides of the shoe in pink with a bit of personality: tonal stitching and jagged edges. Subtle gold colored Gazelle branding is imprinted alongside the top stripe on the lateral side. The gum mudguard helps keep these sneakers looking like new and has adidas branding to boot. Underfoot, adidas has managed to squeeze in more branding as the gum rubber outsole has adidas trefoil lugs.

In our opinion, a standout feature of these shoes in women's sizing is the textured tongue that is perforated throughout the throat and displays a branding hit. The adidas Gazelle Indoor Focus Olive (Women’s) was originally released on June 1, 2024, with a retail price of $120.

name: Black Metallic Silver (2018/2024)
title: Nike Shox R4 Black Metallic Silver (2018/2024)
description:
The Nike Shox R4 Black Metallic Silver 2018/2024 features a mix of numerous colors, with Max Orange, Metallic Silver, and black coming being the main colors.

The upper part of this Black Metallic Silver Nike Shox R4 is dressed in black leather and Metallic Silver. Along with the classic Shox heel unit, this sneaker also has a few bursts of red on its tongue. A black lacing system that completes the aesthetic is also included in this sneaker.

The Nike Shox R4 Black Metallic Silver retailed for $140 during its launch on November 24th, 2018. The Nike Shox R4 Black Metallic Silver re-released in 2024 for a retail price of $150.

name: Slate Bone
title: adidas Yeezy 350 V2 CMPCT Slate Bone
description:
The adidas Yeezy 350 V2 CMPCT Slate Bone was a collaborative sneaker added to both of the brands' catalogs.

This sneaker features an all-gray Primeknit upper with the trademark stretchy sock-like ankle collar. The upper is highlighted by a cream shade that runs throughout the exterior. Branding in this Yeezy Boost version, which only features the signature Yeezy on the insoles. Gray laces and a full-length Boost cushion used on the off-white sole finish off the design. 

The adidas Yeezy 350 V2 CMPCT Slate Bone was made available on September 23rd, 2022. Initially, it retailed at $230.

name: Lottery Pack Grey Fog
title: Nike Dunk Low SE Lottery Pack Grey Fog
description:
The Nike Dunk Low SE Jackpot was a special edition added to brand´s catalog that is draped in neutral tones, highlighted by an all-leather material upper in a white and gray mix of colors.

The Low SE Nike Dunk sneaker mimics a scratch-off lottery ticket, and the signature black Swoosh is coated in a wear-away top layer that reveals a hidden pop of color. The shoe is mounted on a sturdy rubber cupsole, featuring an interior foam wedge for cushioning.

The Nike Dunk Low SE Jackpot was originally released on the 31st of August 2022 for an initial retail price of $120.

DISCLAIMER: The wear-away top layer of the Swoosh logos may be partially rubbed off.

name: Dark Smoke Grey
title: Nike Air Max 2 CB '94 Dark Smoke Grey
description:
The Nike Air Max 2 CB '94 Dark Smoke Grey is the second colorway of NBA player Charles Barkley’s signature sneaker that was released in early 2024.

The original Air Max 2 CB debuted in 1994, but this sneaker pays tribute to Tinker Hatfield’s design and adds contemporary updates. Although the basketball shoe’s silhouette remains the same, the grayscale colorway is a new touch. The overlapping panels on the leather upper feature Light Smoke Grey, Dark Smoke Grey, and Light Silver. Barely Green on the visible Air Max units in the heel provides pops of color against the neutral backdrop. The sneaker boasts a reinforced lace closure system with an additional strap at the top. A pull tab on the heel helps the wearer remove the sneaker, while perforations on the side panels and vamp add breathability.

Our experts at StockX like the overlapping AIR branding on the heel. The Nike Air Max 2 CB '94 Dark Smoke Grey was released on February 22, 2024, and retailed at $170.

name: Patta Waves Noise Aqua (with Bracelet)
title: Nike Air Max 1 Patta Waves Noise Aqua (with Bracelet)
description:
In collaboration with Patta, the Nike Air Max 1 Patta Waves Noise Aqua (with Bracelet) features a grey mesh upper with white overlays with Aqua Swooshes and a wave-shaped mudguard. From there, classic Nike branding on the heel pays homage to the original line of Air Max 1s. A white midsole, multicolor outsole, and custom Patta woven tongue tags completes the design.

The Nike Air Max 1 Patta Waves Noise Aqua (with Bracelet) released in October of 2021 and retailed for $160.

name: Aluminum (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk High Aluminum (Women's)
description:
Arriving with a smooth white leather upper with Aluminum overlays, the women's Nike Dunk High Aluminum (W) offers a comparable color-blocked look to the UNC in a high-cut silhouette. Like all Nike Dunks, signature star traction is featured on the sole beneath the toe.

The women's Nike Dunk High Aluminum (W) released in September of 2021 and retailed for $110.

name: Sweet Tooth Candy Corn
title: Nike SB Dunk High Sweet Tooth Candy Corn
description:
The Nike SB Dunk High Sweet Tooth Candy Corn boasts that recognizable Nike SB Dunk silhouette with a Halloween-inspired colorway and candy details.

A gradient of Amarillo and Orange covers the smooth leather upper and overlays before fading to white across the vamp. It appears almost spraypainted across the sneaker. This high-top skateboarding shoe features overlapping Swoosh logos in Orange and Amarillo on the left and right sides that connect around the heel. In addition, the Orange swoosh complements the laces and the stitching along the midsole. The rubber outsole provides traction and a burst of black that contrasts the bright colors on the upper.

Our experts at StockX love the Trick-or-Treat-inspired insole. It features graphics of candy corn with pennies, a nod to candy corn's status as the original "penny candy." The Nike SB Dunk High Sweet Tooth Candy Corn was released on October 18, 2023, and retailed at $125.

name: MiUSA Grey Silver
title: New Balance 990v4 MiUSA Grey Silver
description:
The New Balance 990v4 Made in USA Grey Silver is a part of the 990 series, which is well-known for its quality, comfort, and timeless aesthetic.

The New Balance 990v4 Grey Silver comes with an upper in different tones of Grey. With an upper crafted from a combination of premium pigskin suede and breathable mesh, it is durable, ventilated, and flexible, allowing for a wide range of movement. The mesh and suede parts come in a light grey colorway, and details of darker grey outline the mesh parts. The iconic " N" logo on the side of the shoe follows the same grey colorway. And ENCAP midsole technology provides a superior level of support and cushioning with its dual-density foam system.

But what our experts love most about the New Balance 990v4 Made in USA Grey Silver is the ABZORB technology set in the midsole to absorb shocks and reduce the impact of your steps. These shoes have been keeping feet stylish and comfortable since their release on June 2, 2023, for a price of $185.

name: Black
title: Nike Air Max Plus 3 Leather Black
description:
The Nike Air Max plus 3 Leather Black accents this high-octane silhouette with traditional materials and dresses it and as stealthy colorway.
