The Black Leather Nike Air Max Plus 3 sports a black mesh upper for lightweight breathability and encases it in a black TPU cage of wavy lines in order to give the shoe structure and support. Accents of black leather encircle the shoe along the mud guard and toe cap and the tongue is also black leather, along with the miniature Nike swoosh on the quarter panel just above the mud guard. The iconic midfoot plate in the shape of a whale tail is present and accounted for, as is the Phylon midsole encapsulating Tuned Air all along the forefoot and heel. The black rubber outsole with traction completes the monochromatic look of this shoe.

The detail we really appreciate about this sneaker are the three hits of colorful Tuned Air branding that grace the heel, tongue, and outsole. The Nike Air Max plus 3 Leather Black debuted on May 26, 2022 for a retail price of $190.

name: Recraft Triple Black
title: Nike Air Max 90 Recraft Triple Black
description:
The Nike Air Max 90 Recraft Triple Black features a black sole, midsole, and body. It'ss made from a variety of materials, including plastic and suede, which give it a matte appearance. Part of the midsole is transparent and hollow to help keep it lightweight.

The Air Max 90 Recraft in Triple Black by Nike was an original 1990 design of Tinker Hatfield. The sneaker also features a breathable mesh lining and a padded tongue.

The Nike Air Max 90 Recraft Triple Black first became available for purchase in January of 2020. This model had a retail price of $120.

name: The World Is Your Oyster
title: Nike LeBron 21 The World Is Your Oyster
description:
The Nike LeBron 21 The World Is Your Oyster is a low-top sneaker with a swirly, pastel pink design. Bright pink athletic shoelaces and a pink decorative heel complete the stylish look. Marine life, namely oysters, inspires the aesthetics. This sneaker is available in sizes for both men and women.

It is a basketball shoe with performance features such as lightweight comfort, breathability, superior traction, heel support, and a cushy foam midsole to give you added bounce to boost your jumper shot. This shoe is designed by Nike and has the Nike name on the back heel and the Swoosh sign in silver on the side of the shoe.

Nike LeBron 21 The World Is Your Oyster is part of the Nike Lebron James collection. Our team is touched because the shoe collection was spurred by James' daughter and her passion for basketball and other sports. Nike released this shoe on July 1, 2024. It originally retailed for $200.

name: Travis Scott Grey Haze
title: Nike Air Trainer 1 SP Travis Scott Grey Haze
description:
Pulling inspiration from backpacking gear, the Nike Air Trainer 1 SP Travis Scott Grey Haze features a light grey canvas upper with darker grey mesh overlays and single stitch Swoosh logos. Canvas shrouds on the upper give wearers options for styling. At the heel and inside of the tongue, concealed zipper pockets provide extra storage. From there, "Cactus Corporation" insignias at the heel and forefoot velcro strap add a custom feel.

The Nike Air Trainer 1 SP Travis Scott Grey released in May of 2022 and retailed for $160.

name: Rebellious Air Fireberry
title: Nike Air Max Plus Rebellious Air Fireberry
description:
The Nike Air Max Plus Rebellious Air Fireberry dresses the Air Max Plus with an electric colorway of Pure Purple and Fireberry with black and white accents.

At the Rebellious Air Fireberry Nike Air Max Plus, The TPU overlays display a fade from Pure Purple to Fireberry, which matches the gradient of color across the mesh upper. The TPU overlays act as a cage and resemble palms swaying in the breeze or waves. Other nature-inspired accents include the TPU arch beneath the midfoot that looks like a whale tale and features Pure Purple and Fireberry. The sneaker offers visible Air Max cushioning underfoot, which provides support without weighing the foot down, while Air Max branding decorates the cushioned tongue's logo tag. The rubber outsole contains a surprising feature – pops of neon green.

Our experts at StockX like the reflective detailing because it provides visibility in low lighting and gives the sneaker a sporty feel. The Nike Air Max Plus Rebellious Air Fireberry was released on July 12, 2024, and sold for $180.

name: Black White
title: Jordan 14 Retro Black White
description:
The Jordan 14 Retro Black White represents a recent inclusion in Michael Jordan's 14th signature footwear line, showcasing a timeless two-tone color palette.

Inspired by Michael Jordan's passion for luxurious motor sports and high-performance vehicles, the Black White Jordan 14 Retro showcases an elegant design. Built on an all-black foundation, the shoe integrates suede underlays and nubuck overlays, creating a distinct texture. Jordan branding takes center stage on the prominently featured tongue, while white accents highlight the collar and toe. A subtle touch of red enriches the Jumpman logo within the crest, adding a burst of color amid the dominant black and white palette. The Jordan 14 midsole displays a striking black-and-white contrast, and the design is completed with a sturdy black rubber outsole.

The noteworthy characteristic of the Jordan 14 Retro Black White is its elegant design lines coupled with high-performance technology. Taking inspiration from one of MJ's favorite cars, the Ferrari 550, the AJ14 incorporates a Jumpman logo reminiscent of the Ferrari crest and heel panels inspired by the car's high-performance tires. The sneaker debuted for $210 on December 20th, 2023.

name: Pathway Royalties
title: Nike KD 16 Pathway Royalties
description:
The Nike KD 16 Pathway Royalties is a masterpiece of modern sneaker design, appealing to the young basketball aficionados. Its Black, Vivid Purple, Bright Crimson, and Metallic Silver colorway is bold and striking, representing Kevin Durant's path to greatness.

This sneaker is engineered for top-tier performance, featuring cutting-edge technology for enhanced stability and support. The responsive cushioning system and breathable upper material make it ideal for intense basketball games. The Pathway Royalties edition symbolizes Durant's journey, resonating with the ambition and drive of its wearers.

Released on September 8, 2023, and priced at $150, the Nike KD 16 Pathway Royalties has become a symbol of hard work and success, making it a popular choice among basketball players and sneaker collectors.

name: Grey Magic Beige Gum (Women's)
title: adidas Gazelle Bold Grey Magic Beige Gum (Women's)
description:
The adidas Gazelle Bold Grey Magic Beige Gum Women's sneaker is part of the iconic Gazelle line from adidas and offers a blend of heritage design and contemporary performance in women sizing.

This shoe features a classic design inspired by the original Gazelle silhouette from the 1960s. Its upper is crafted from premium suede and leather and prominently displays the renowned 3-Stripes branding on the sides. A low-top profile and streamlined shape give the shoe a sleek and timeless aesthetic while offering a breadth of movement. A classic gum rubber outsole adds a touch of vintage flair and ensures traction on many surface types.

What our experts most enjoy about the adidas Gazelle Bold Grey Magic Beige Gum Women's sneaker, however, is its Earth tone colorway, which employs Grey Six, Magic Beige, and Cream White hues. It originally retailed for $120 when it was released on February 1, 2024.

name: White Black Volt University Gold
title: Jordan 1 Retro High White Black Volt University Gold
description:
Jordan Brand started 2021 on a high note with the Jordan 1 High Volt Gold. The Volt Gold offers a new take on the renowned Black Toe theme by implementing new materials and features that contribute to a reconstructed design aesthetic.

In familiar Black Toe color blocking, the upper of the Jordan 1 Volt Gold is composed of white, black, and yellow leather. A Volt yellow-tinted panel donning the Jordan Wings logo wraps the ankle. Unlike OG Jordan 1 designs that feature double stitch reinforcement, the Volt Gold utilizes single stitch reinforcement on its overlays, creating dimensionality with exposed edges. A nylon tongue with exposed foam edges and reverse transparent tongue label emphasize Jordan’s reconstructed design approach. A yellowed midsole and black outsole offer an aged look.

The Jordan 1 High Volt Gold released in January of 2021 and retailed for $170.

name: Aunt Pearl
title: Nike KD 3 Aunt Pearl
description:
The Nike KD 3 Aunt Pearl is a variation of Kevin Durant’s Nike KD 3 with a pink, pearlescent color scheme first seen in the Nike KD 4 edition. This vibrant colorway pays tribute to Kevin Durant’s aunt who played a significant role in his life and passed away in 2000 from lung cancer.

The KD 3 Aunt Pearl features retro upgrades without retooling the interior of the shoe. It includes ballistic mesh sidewalls that provide support without sacrificing breathability. The upper also boasts smooth leather and flexible synthetic materials, which are covered in soft pink colors. The leather overlays and tongue display a pearly sheen that compliments the translucent tread on the bottom of the shoe.

Something our experts love is the mismatched branding details on the tongues. The right shoe’s tongue features KD branding, while the left shoe’s tongue showcases the Kay Yow Cancer Fund logo. The Nike KD 3 Aunt Pearl was released on October 15, 2023, and retailed at $130.

name: Cloud White
title: adidas Yeezy 450 Cloud White
description:
In early 2020, images of the adidas Yeezy 450 began to circulate when Kanye was spotted outside of the Yeezy Season 8 fashion show during Paris Fashion Week. This otherworldly design captured the attention of Yeezy fans, mostly because it is unlike anything Yeezy has ever made. Then, one year later, Yeezy finally released its brand new 450 silhouette with the adidas Yeezy 450 Cloud White.

The adidas Yeezy 450 Cloud White is one of Yeezy’s most unique designs yet. Its simplified two-piece construction appears complex due to its extreme, molded foam sole. The sole clasps the mesh upper, acting as an exoskeleton to provide structure. Similar to the Yeezy 700 V3, this release does not feature Boost or adiPRENE technology. Instead, Yeezy utilizes EVA foam to deliver comfort.

The adidas Yeezy 450 Cloud White released in March of 2021 and retailed for $200.

name: Black Metallic Gold (GS)
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Black Metallic Gold (GS)
description:
Fresh and bold, the Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG Black Metallic Gold sneaker comes with a hot color combo of black and gold. A sophisticated look to a heritage sneaker, this modern spin on the all-time favorite is the perfect tribute to the legendary baller.

Black, gold, and more striking than ever, these Air Jordan Retro sneakers bring the familiar feel of the high-top game-changing sneaker back with a premium finish. The black leather base of the shoe helps gold accents pop in genuine leather. A Wings stamped logo sits on the collar while a stitched-down Nike swoosh claims the sides. The shoe has lace enclosures and a perforated toe bank. A gold Jumpman hangtag comes with every pair. Rubber traction keeps your feet in the game when you hit the court for a bit of one-on-one.

We love the color pairing on this iconic shoe reimagined by the Air Jordan designers. Keeping it classy while remembering its roots, this high-top brings street cred and sportsmanship together in one slick reminder of a legacy player. The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG Black Metallic Gold sneakers were released on 08 October 2024, priced at $240.

name: Active Fuchsia (GS)
title: Nike Dunk Low Active Fuchsia (GS)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Active Fuchsia (GS) is an iconic low-profile basketball sneaker by Nike.

The Nike Dunk Low Active Fuchsia for grade-schoolers is available in a two-toned color scheme with white and Active Fuchsia. The sneaker features an all-leather upper with overlays in a bold hot pink shade that creates a striking contrast against the clean white foundation. Its breathable toe box has perforations, and the low-cut collar is padded to ensure comfort. The sneaker is supported by a sturdy cupsole that merges white sidewalls with a fuchsia rubber outsole, delivering traction.

The Nike Dunk Low Active Fuchsia (GS) was released on 1st March 2023 with its retail price set at $90.

name: Ember Glow
title: Nike KD 16 Ember Glow
description:
The Nike KD 16 Ember Glow exemplifies Kevin Durant's exceptional on-court skills and distinctive style, presenting a captivating fusion of Ember Glow, University Red, and Light Fusion Red tones for a visually striking appearance.

Crafted with a multi-layered textured mesh upper, the Ember Glow Nike KD 16 elegantly incorporates synthetic mudguards that gracefully envelop the entire model. A 3M reflective upper with a translucent outsole/midsole combination reveals the intricate mechanics behind KD's prowess. Compared to previous iterations, the KD 16 is lighter with a lower upper, sitting atop a rubber sole featuring Zoom Air cushioning for heightened comfort and traction. A novel TPU caging system introduces ventilation on both the lateral and medial sides, seamlessly blending onto the split midsole of the forefoot. The design is completed with KD branding on the tongue tabs and a Swoosh on the lateral ankle.

The standout characteristic of the Nike KD 16 Ember Glow lies in its 3M reflective upper, enhancing not only the visual appeal of the shoe but also offering a glimpse into the intricate, machine-like workings of KD's extraordinary abilities. The sneaker debuted for $160 on September 25th, 2023.

name: Golden Bullet (2023)
title: Nike Air Max 97 OG Golden Bullet (2023)
description:
Nike is bringing back a fan favorite just in time for Air Max Day, with the return of the Air Max 97 OG Golden Bullet (2023).

The Air Max 97 OG Golden Bullet uses the same color blocking pattern as the Air Max 97 OG Silver Bullet, but with golden counterparts. Nike used red Swooshes on the mesh uppers, and tongue. The gold sneakers sit on top of a clear air bubble unit that wraps around the midsole.

The Nike Air Max 97 OG Gold Bullet (2023) released March 7, 2023, with a retail price of $185.

name: Craft White Cement Grey Black
title: Jordan 1 Mid SE Craft White Cement Grey Black
description:
The Jordan 1 Mid SE Craft White Cement Gray Black combines subtly different colors, textures, and fabrics to lend singular elegance to a classic silhouette.

The White Cement Gray Black colorway of the Jordan 1 Mid-Top Special Edition Craft uses plush suede in different shades of gray to form the heel, the collar overlay, the vamp overlay, the eye says, and the toe underlay. White hemp canvas is used to construct the side panel, the perforated toe box that’s sewn on, and the padded collar with distinct edging. Black suede is used for the Nike swoosh with stitching, heel overlay, and tongue. The sock liner is white while the insole is black. The midsole is constructed of foam with a cup sole design and Nike Air. The black rubber outsole provides impact absorption and traction.

What we love most about this shoe are the hits of branding. A tonal Wings logo is debossed on the black heel, while a white Jumpman logo adorns both the insole and tongue. The Jordan 1 Mid SE Craft White Cement Gray Black was released on August 29, 2023, for a retail price of $135.

name: Wolf Grey
title: Jordan 13 Retro Wolf Grey
description:
The Jordan 13 Retro in Wolf Gray is a men’s basketball shoe that provides comfort and protective padding both on and off the court. The sleek look of the shoe makes it appropriate for wear both during the game and during the after-party.

The Retro Jordan 13 in Wolf Gray has a clean white leather base with small perforations in the shape of a circle for a unique look. Wolf Gray overlays adorn the heel and the midsole just above the sole of the shoe. It features a vibrant red color underfoot, and the Jordan Jumpman logo appears in the same red shade on the tongue. Branding details are completed with the signature Jordan hologram on the back.

What we at StockX think makes this shoe stand out is its unique, perforated, white leather base. This element gives the shoe a spotless look that can be paired with any outfit, both on and off the court. The Jordan 13 Retro in Wolf Gray was released on August 5th, 2023, for an initial price of $210.

name: Slate Grey (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Slide Slate Grey (Kids)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Slide Slate Grey (Kids), in kids sizes, is an athletic slide shoe featuring a chunky, singular silhouette. Fabricated from injected EVA foam, the Yeezy slide offers the comfort of a wide strap aesthetic with a seamless construction that highlights the monochrome Slate Grey palette. adidas three stripes branding appears on the footbed, and the grooved outsole offers traction.

Launching in 2015 with a fashion show, American rapper and producer Kanye West collaborated with German sportswear giant adidas to create the Yeezy collection of shoes. With Yeezy, Kanye West presided over the designs with full creative control of the product design. The result was a series of functional sneakers and lifestyle shoes with an aesthetic that is a marked departure from adidas’ heritage styles, showcasing the power of innovation within collaboration.

Our experts feel that the best feature of the Yeezy Slide is its simplicity, which makes the shoe both stylish and wearable. The adidas Yeezy Slide Slate Grey (Kids) released on June 10, 2024, and retailed at $50.

name: Fearless UNC Chicago
title: Jordan 1 Retro High Fearless UNC Chicago
description:
Please Note: Extra laces are not guaranteed. Jordan Brand sheds light on Michael’s transition from the college hoops scene to the NBA with the Jordan 1 Retro High Fearless UNC Chicago, now available on StockX. 1984 marked the year MJ entered the league and changed the game as we know it. This shoe is an embodiment of staying true to your roots as you face adversity and adapt to perform at the highest level.
This AJ 1 is composed of a white patent leather upper with red and university blue overlays, black Nike "Swoosh", white midsole, and a red outsole. These sneakers released in November of 2019 and retailed for $160.

name: Moonlight (2021)
title: Jordan 5 Retro Moonlight (2021)
description:
The Air Jordan 5 Moonlight arrives looking identical to the original 2013 Jordan 5 Oreo. It features a black Durabuck upper with translucent netted inserts and grey embroidered Jumpman logos on the tongue. From there, a white midsole with black speckled shark teeth and an icy translucent sole brings a contrast to the monotone upper.

The Air Jordan 5 Moonlight released in September of 2021 and retailed for $190.

name: Rattan Gorge Green
title: Nike Dunk Low Retro Rattan Gorge Green
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Retro Rattan Gorge Green has a full leather upper and combines a Rattan, Gorge Green, Sail and Dark Driftwood color scheme.

The sneaker also features a Gorge Green on its Swooshes, tongue labeling, inner liner, rubber outsoles, and heel tabs. At the rear end of the shoe is the Nike branding printed in white. Other details include the perforations at the forefoot, and a crossed lacing system in white. The outsole boasts a linear pattern for traction and stitching throughout.

The Nike Dunk Low Retro Rattan Gorge Green made its debut on November 23rd, 2022, with a retail price set at $110.

name: Lilac Bloom
title: Nike Book 1 Lilac Bloom
description:
The Nike Book 1 Lilac Bloom decks out NBA player Devin Booker’s first collaboration with Nike in an all-over pastel-purple colorway and a mixed-material upper.

Unlike previous editions of the Book 1, the Lilac Bloom version is colorful and moves away from grayscale and neutral colors. The upper is crafted from suede, genuine leather, and a twill-like material in Barley Grape, giving the sneaker a smooth appearance. The shiny material on the Swoosh logo and the collar has a pearlescent sheen and comes in Daybreak. Additional splashes of Daybreak decorate the top of the tongue and the soft lining. A Zoom-Air unit in the heel provides a springy feel, while the rubber outsole features a herringbone pattern for multidirectional traction.

Our experts like the full-length foam in the midsole because it provides soft cushioning underfoot. The Nike Book 1 Lilac Bloom was released on July 18, 2024, and sold for $140.

name: Clay Brown
title: adidas Yeezy 500 Clay Brown
description:
The adidas Yeezy 500 Clay Brown presents an array of materials commonly found in hiking shoes designed to withstand the great outdoors. It is constructed of a Clay Brown mesh upper with leather and suede overlays that wrap the silhouette. A sturdy adiPRENE sole adds a responsive feel to the trail-ready design.

The adidas Yeezy 500 Clay Brown released in September of 2021 and retailed for $200.

name: Semi Blue Burst Almost Yellow (Women's)
title: adidas Gazelle Indoor Semi Blue Burst Almost Yellow (Women's)
description:
The adidas Gazelle Indoor Semi Blue Burst Almost Yellow (Women's) is a women’s indoor training shoe with a bright colorway.

This version of the adidas Gazelle Indoor is constructed with a nylon upper in a Semi Blue Burst color. A T-shaped suede toe cap appears in the same color, and the same material runs under the laces. The traditional adidas three stripes are formed on the sides of the shoe in a pale, light yellow color. The heel collar, void of branding, is almost the same yellow color. The blue padded tongue features a white and blue adidas logo patch, while a semi-transparent gum rubber outsole completes the design.

Our favorite thing about this indoor training shoe is how the pale yellow accents complement the light blue color, reminiscent of the summer sky. The adidas Gazelle Indoor Semi Blue Burst Almost Yellow (Women's) was released on March 1, 2024, for $120.

name: Black Dark Grey
title: New Balance 2002R Black Dark Grey
description:
The New Balance 2002R Black Dark Grey blends urban looks with technical capabilities that offer a smart, quieted sneaker for versatile use. This edition leverages New Balance’s expertise in ergonomic design and long-lasting construction with refined, contemporary fashion.

The Black Dark Grey 2002R by New Balance features a suede and mesh upper in dark tones for breathability and structure. The ABZORB midsole technology offers shock absorption and comfort, while the N-ergy outsole gives you extra stability. Released as part of New Balance’s 2000 series, which originally debuted in 2010, this model maintains classic running-shoe elements with modern updates to give you a shoe that highlights the brand’s renowned craftsmanship and futuristic design.

What we love about the New Balance 2002R Black Dark Grey are its ABZORB cushioning for lasting comfort and the sturdy N-ergy outsole for added stability. Released at $145 on July 3, 2024, these features combine seamlessly for an everyday sneaker.

name: Charcoal
title: New Balance 9060 Charcoal
description:
The New Balance 9060 Charcoal is a performance shoe whose design was inspired by the original 99X series and has some updated elements.

This version of the New Balance 9060 has a Charcoal gray mesh as its base. Charcoal suede overlays cross the upper for support, notably on the sides, toe box, and heel. The New Balance N appears on both sides – on the inner side, it is adorned with white dashes, while on the lateral side, it appears in gray. An NB logo is on the heel tab, while the tongue bears 9060 branding. The shoe sits on a chunky midsole in white and cream. It’s equipped with Abzorb cushioning for comfort and energy return.

Our favorite thing about this sneaker is the contrast in colors between the upper and the midsole, which gives the shoe a sleek, modern look. The New Balance 9060 Charcoal was released on July 31, 2024, for $150.

name: Metallic Silver
title: New Balance 1906L Metallic Silver
description:
The New Balance 1906L Metallic Silver reimagines the 1906 as a slip-on loafer. This hybrid sneaker showcases a futuristic color palette of metallic silver and grey.

Seamlessly blending New Balance’s technical specs with the design requirements of a loafer, the Metallic Silver New Balance 1906L is lace-free. With N-ergy cushioning underfoot for shock absorption, the sneaker offers long-lasting comfort. The upper is crafted from a loose weave mesh that ensures durability, while the metallic silver accents draw attention to the supportive overlays. Although the sneaker doesn’t need laces, a traditional loafer apron crosses the tongue. It features a silver metallic sheen that matches the collar.

While many loafers include a tassel hanging over the vamp, this version doesn’t include a tassel. Our experts appreciate this exclusion because it maintains the sneaker’s sporty aesthetic. The New Balance 1906L Metallic Silver was released on September 19, 2024, and sold for $150.

name: CO.JP Reverse Curry (2024)
title: Nike Dunk Low QS CO.JP Reverse Curry (2024)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low QS CO.JP Reverse Curry (2024) was designed and released by Nike as a highly exclusive sneaker. This Quick Strike release of a Concept Japan silhouette was released by Nike only in Japan.

The Reverse Curry 2024 CO.JP Nike Dunk Low-Top Quick Strike uses a colorway that first debuted in 1999. The base of this sneaker is curry-colored smooth leather that matches the laces and the mesh tongue. The overlays are smooth white leather and the heel tab features curry-colored Nike branding. White Nike branding adorns the curry-colored tongue tag.

The aspect of this arresting-looking sneaker that our shoe experts appreciate the most is its dependable soul unit. The white foam midsole uses cupsole construction with a foam wedge for support and cushioning. This rests on top of a curry-colored rubber outsole that is grooved with traction designed for multiple surfaces and embossed with Nike branding at the midfoot. The Nike Dunk Low QS CO.JP Reverse Curry (2024) was released on January 12, 2024, for a retail price of $135.

name: Travis Scott
title: Jordan 6 Retro Travis Scott
description:
Trailing the buzz of their recent collaborations, Travis Scott and Jordan Brand team up once again for the Jordan 6 Retro Travis Scott, now available on StockX. This is the fourth Air Jordan silhouette that Cactus Jack has touched. This sneaker made its mainstream debut when Travis rocked them on stage during his Super Bowl LIII performance and the rest is history.

This AJ 6 features an olive upper with black detailing and red contrasting accents on the tongue and lace locks. A side cargo pocket is displayed on the collar, giving this sneaker a design modification that makes it the first of its kind. A sail midsole, glow-in-the-dark translucent outsole, 3M detailing and both Nike Air and Cactus Jack branding on the heel completes the design. These sneakers released in October of 2019 for $250.

name: Panda
title: Nike Air Max 90 Panda
description:
The Nike Air Max 90 Panda applies the iconic black and white colorway made famous by the Nike Dunk Low Panda. However, it also features the Air Max 90’s recognizable silhouette and visible Air Max units.

Originally designed as a running shoe, this sneaker features a low-top design with a padded collar and waffle sole. The base is made of white mesh with leather overlays in black or white on the forefoot, midfoot, toe, and collar. Like other Air Max 90 models, the "Panda" variant features TPU details near the lace cage and midsole. In terms of branding, the tongue displays a logo tag with ‘NIKE AIR MAX’ lettering and a TPU detail on the side panel reads ‘AIR MAX.’ A TPU patch on the heel also displays ‘NIKE AIR.’

Our experts at StockX like the way this sneaker pays tribute to the panda colorway without forgetting its design heritage. The Nike Air Max 90 Panda was released on June 26th, 2023, and retailed at $130.

name: Alien Blue
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Alien Blue
description:
The adidas Yeezy 380 Alien Blue arrives in a light grey and white reflective Primeknit upper with a Glow Green side stripe. From there, a faint Alien Blue translucent BOOST sole provides a supportive base.

The adidas Yeezy 380 Alien Blue released in May of 2021 and retailed for $230.

name: Cardinal (2022)
title: Jordan 7 Retro Cardinal (2022)
description:
The Air Jordan 7 Retro Cardinal 2022 has become part of the sports collection of the brand and is dressed in a white, cardinal red, black, and chutney color scheme.

This high Air Jordan 7 sneaker features a white leather upper with hints of chutney on the heel pull tab and the Jumpman logo on the lateral ankle. Black and cardinal red are featured on the heel tab, midsole decoration, lining, and insole. The signature "23" branding on the heel counter, a black "Air Jordan" embroidery on the tongue, a black outsole, and a round toe box complete the design.

The Air Jordan 7 Retro Cardinal 2022 was released on December 17th, 2022, retailing at $210.

name: Year of the Dragon (2024) (Women's)
title: Jordan 1 Low Year of the Dragon (2024) (Women's)
description:
The Jordan 1 Low Year of the Dragon (2024) (Women's) fuses style with tradition in a sneaker design that celebrates the Chinese New Year in the Year of the Dragon. These sneakers, specifically sized for women, exude eye-catching elegance.

The Year of the Dragon 2024 Jordan 1 Low-Top for Women features an upper with a base of white leather overlaid with rich, dark red tumbled leather. The white laces match the tongue and the foam midsole with tonal stitching. A dark gray translucent rubber outsole matches the sock liner and tongue lining to lock in the look of this shoe.

The aspect of this sneaker we enjoy the most is the elegant branding. The side panel Nike Swoosh features rich gold embroidery that echoes the wings logo on the heel and the Jumpman on the insole. There is also an embroidered tonal Jumpman on the tongue tag and embossed Nike branding on the midfoot of the outsole. The Jordan 1 Low Year of the Dragon (2024) (Women's) was released on January 24, 2024, for a retail price of $125.

name: Military Blue (2024) (TD)
title: Jordan 4 Retro Military Blue (2024) (TD)
description:
The Jordan 4 Retro Military Blue (2024) (TD) is a toddler-sized shoe featuring Military Blue accents on the classic design.

This iteration of the Air Jordan 4 Retro is constructed with a white leather upper. The shoe has a sectioned design, with white leather forming the base above the sole and the area around the ankle. Military Blue leather at the midsole and at the bottom of the laces is covered with white mesh. A gray mudguard rounds out the toe. The tongue features a blue Jumpman logo, while the heel features a blue pull tab with a white Nike logo. A Military Blue and white rubber outsole completes the look.

What stands out about this small shoe is the blue leather patch at the midsole paired with white mesh. The Jordan 4 Retro Military Blue (2024) (TD) was released on May 4, 2024, for a price of $85.

name: Black White
title: Nike Air Max 97 Black White
description: This Nike Air Max 97 "OG" edition comes in a clean black and white colorway. Made to commemorate the 30th Anniversary of the classic Air Max silhouette. This pair sports a black-based upper with a white sole, black Max Air unit and white branding throughout. They were one of three colorways that dropped alongside each other. The release date was August 1st, 2017 where they retailed for $160 in men's sizes. Fans of the Air Max 97 were very pleased with this colorway and it quickly became a must-have. Perfect for everyday use, you can never go wrong with a black and white colored sneaker. If you're in need of a pair, hit up the marketplace to buy them. Those looking to sell can do so online today.

name: Wales Bonner Navy Croc
title: adidas Samba Wales Bonner Navy Croc
description:
The adidas Samba Wales Bonner Navy Croc combines timeless design with premium craftsmanship. This limited-edition sneaker features a deep navy faux Croc-textured leather upper, accented by cream 3-Stripes and brown tones. Its co-branded tongue adds a signature touch, combining Wales Bonner's modern aesthetic and adidas's classic styling.

The Wales Bonner Navy Croc Samba by adidas stands out with its debossed Croc material iteration. The tonal accents are complemented by a cushioned gum sole that gives you an aesthetic appeal and comfort. Released as part of the Fall/Winter 2024 collection, this sneaker builds on the iconic Samba's legacy while showing off a distinct take on trendy footwear design.

As the experts, one thing we enjoy about the adidas Samba Wales Bonner Navy Croc is the co-branded details on the tongue and the patchy detailing on the upper to add depth. Retailing at $300, this exclusive sneaker originally debuted on October 24, 2024.

name: Wonder White
title: adidas Handball Spezial Wonder White
description:
The adidas Handball Spezial Wonder White paints the Handball Spezial in a neutral colorway of Wonder White with Cloud White accents.

Although the original indoor training shoe debuted in 1979, this version of the Handball Spezial maintains its retro roots. The upper is made of smooth suede with a tonal suede heel tab and a T-shaped overlay over the toebox. Cloud White accents can be found on the heel tab and the serrated 3-Stripes logo. The oversized tongue displays a Cloud White adidas logo tag with Wonder White lettering. "SPEZIAL" in boxy, metallic gold letters and a trefoil decorate the outer side panel. Completing the look, a rubber outsole in a traditional gum rubber hue adds traction underfoot and a dose of retro appeal.

Our experts at StockX like the Wonder White "adidas" lettering on the heel tab. The adidas Handball Spezial Wonder White was released on January 28, 2024, and retailed at $110.

name: Silver Surfer (2024)
title: Nike Dunk Low Silver Surfer (2024)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Silver Surfer (2024) reintroduces the Marvel-inspired sneaker from 2004 that drew inspiration from the metallic silver character who skates through the universe on a surfboard.

With color-blocking that’s nearly identical to the original, the Silver Surfer (2024) Nike Dunk Low boasts Neutral Grey, Metallic Silver, Aegean Storm, Flat Silver, and Gym Red. The upper is crafted from mesh and leather in Silver, which allows the Aegean Storm and Gym Red accents to pop. For example, the leather Swoosh logo and the " NIKE" lettering on the tongue tag come in Aegean Storm. However, the leather heel tab and the woven tongue tag display Gym Red.

Our StockX experts like how closely the relaunch matches the OG version. For example, the 2024 shoe even displays a motif of the Silver Surfer on the insole. The Nike Dunk Low Silver Surfer (2024) was released on September 5, 2024, and sold for $135.

name: Cream
title: adidas Yeezy 450 Slide Cream
description:
Unveiled on August 3, 2023, the adidas Yeezy 450 Slide is the next evolution of the iconic Yeezy line, taking strides into new design territories.

Defying traditional aesthetics, the Yeezy 450 Slide presents an unorthodox, avant-garde silhouette that instantly captures attention. Its meticulously engineered, one-piece design showcases an extraordinary visual dynamic. Crafted for comfort, the slides provide a snug, tailored fit for those who live life on the move.

The adidas Yeezy 450 Slide dares to defy norms and set new trends. This model was released to the world on August 3, 2023, with an attainable retail price of $110.

name: PSG Paris Saint-Germain
title: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG PSG Paris Saint-Germain
description:
Celebrate one of Europe's iconic football clubs with the Jordan 1 Retro Low OG PSG Paris Saint-Germain model. It's a highly desirable model in this famous Jordan range. The construction is immaculate, offering both style and excellent durability.

This special Air Jordan 1 version has an all-leather upper sail with a white basic shell color, creating a foundation for an off-noir black layer and Swoosh. It has a pink toe box with dimples and a gradient finish. The Paris tongue tag is embroidered in red, with a red Jordan wings logo at the back of the heel.

Our experts love this collab and the resulting colorway. The contrasting black and pink patterning creates a dynamic, eye-catching effect, adding an unusual touch. It's a low-profile trainer with a grippy black outsole that contrasts with the off-white rubber midsole. The Jordan 1 Retro Low OG PSG Paris Saint-Germain was released on 1 October 2024 at a retail price of $150.

name: White Sky Blue
title: adidas Samba OG White Sky Blue
description:
The adidas Samba OG White Sky Blue is a Crisp Footwear White, Clear Sky Blue colorway from the adidas Samba OG line.

The full grain leather upper of this silhouette is primarily Crisp Footwear White and is the base for Clear Sky and blue accents to pop off. The toebox features the signature t-style design and presents in a beige suede. Three Clear Sky adidas stripes adorn the side panels and boast their zigzag edges. This same Clear Sky Blue is seen on the ribbed heel tab that is flanked with delicate stitching. As for branding there is gold foil SAMBA lettering on the side panel and a blue and white square graphic on the tongue.

Our experts think the standout feature of the adidas Samba OG White Sky Blue is its understated timeless aesthetic and versatility. Its crisp, clean combination of colors means it pairs well with khakis, shorts or jeans. This sneaker released on April 21st, 2024, at a retail price of $100.

name: Powder Blue (2024) (GS)
title: Jordan 9 Retro Powder Blue (2024) (GS)
description:
The Jordan 9 Retro Powder Blue (2024) (GS) is a grade schoolers-sized version of the Jordan 9 Retro that comes in a delicate colorway of Dark Powder Blue, Summit White, and black. Dark Powder Blue is a version of Carolina Blue and pays tribute to Michael Jordan's alma mater – the University of North Carolina.

This basketball shoe celebrates the 30th anniversary of the Jordan 9 and reintroduces one of its most iconic colorways. The upper is crafted from white leather with stitched details along the side panels. The speed lacing system keeps the sneaker secure, while the black mesh tongue contrasts the base color. A patch with the Jumpman logo secures the heel pull tab, which helps with putting on and taking off the sneaker. Dark Powder Blue details decorate the midsole and the interior sleeve.

Our StockX experts like the inclusion of responsive Air-sole cushioning in the midsole. The grade school-sized Jordan 9 Retro Powder Blue (2024) (GS) was released on March 23rd, 2024, and retailed at $160.

name: Lucky Green
title: Jordan 2 Retro Lucky Green
description:
Jordan Brand is continuing their run of the Jordan 2 Silhouette into 2023, with the Air Jordan 2 Retro Lucky Green.

Jordan Brand traditionally stays away from green sneakers, but highlighted it in this model with Lucky Green accents, heel, outsoles and sockliner. The Retro Jordan 2 Lucky Green features white leather uppers, and vintage inspired cream colored midsoles, mudguard and lace eyelets.

The Air Jordan 2 Retro Lucky Green released February 3, 2023, with a retail price of $175.

name: Mystic Navy
title: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG Mystic Navy
description:
The Air Jordan 1 Low Mystic Navy arrives in a black and Mystic Blue smooth leather construction with identical color blocking and detailing to the original line of 1985 Air Jordan 1s. At the heel, a classic Jordan Wings logo nods to the silhouette's origins. From there, a white and Mystic Navy Air sole completes the design.

The Air Jordan 1 Low Mystic Navy released in June of 2022 and retailed for $130.

name: Summit White
title: Nike P-6000 Premium Summit White
description:
The Nike P-6000 Premium Summit White is a shoe with a Summit White mesh upper, accented by linear leather overlays in Light Bone and Phantom, creating a multi-tonal, multi-textured white aesthetic. The Nike Swoosh appears on the sides, accented by a black outline. The linear textured midsole continues the multi-White aesthetic, while a gum outsole completes the look. An additional Nike Swoosh appears on the rear heel, accented by P-6000 branding.

Nike, based in Beaverton, Oregon, is the world’s largest sneaker producer, and as such the brand has always been on the forefront of sneaker trends and technology. With the P-6000, Nike’s designers reinterpreted the Air Pegasus from 2006, creating an early 2000s retro aesthetic that is lightweight and comfortable for all-day wear.

Our experts feel that the best feature of the P-6000 Summit White is its intricate overlay construction, which highlights the multi-tonal Summit White colorway. The Nike P-6000 Premium Summit White released on January 5, 2024, and retailed for $120.

name: Black White (2023)
title: Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 Black White (2023)
description:
The Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 Black White (2023) gives the AF 1 Low a stealthy makeover with a black base and branding details in white.

At the Black White (2023) Nike Air Force 1 Low '07, The leather upper, midsole, outsole, laces, and lining come in black, while the branding on the tongue and the heel tab features white. The leather heel tab showcases ‘NIKE AIR’ and a Swoosh, while the tongue displays ‘NIKE AIR FORCE 1’ and the insole reveals ‘NIKE.’ In addition, the classic leather Swoosh also comes in bright white. Perforations on the toebox and the side panels allow the foot to breathe, while the laces provide a secure front closure.

Our experts at StockX like the encapsulated Air unit in the heel because it’s a heritage design element and provides responsive cushioning. The Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 Black White (2023) was released on September 18, 2023, and sold for $110.

name: Tekken 8 Jin Kazama
title: Nike Air Foamposite One Tekken 8 Jin Kazama
description:
The Nike Air Foamposite One Tekken 8 Jin Kazama brings space-age technology to your feet. It has futuristic contours and is ultra-comfortable, hugging your feet like a second skin. At the same time, it's unmistakably a very advanced sports trainer.

This was a highly anticipated new version of the collab between Tekken 8 and the Nike Air trainer line. Its colorway blends a matte black top upper with a metallic proton dust body, featuring a subtle dark grey lightning pattern. A tiny Swoosh appears near the top of the toe. Look underneath the rubber sole, and you'll see the word "FIST," representing the Jin Kazama character.

We also looked forward to this release, and it didn't disappoint. It's hard to get past the visual styling and the hyper-contoured look. It's something every trainer collector and Tekken fan is going to want to get their hands on. It comes in exclusive Jin Kazama packaging to make it even more special. The Nike Air Foamposite One Tekken 8 Jin Kazama was released on 25 October 2024, priced at $250.

name: Triple Black
title: Nike Air Kukini Triple Black
description:
The Nike Air Kukini Triple Black is a unique colorway of the Air Kukini silhouette featuring a monochromatic color scheme covering the entire shoe.

The Triple Black Nike Air Kukini model has a unique upper which is constructed with a web-like pattern of synthetic overlays that wrap around the shoe in a cage-like design. This not only gives the shoe a distinctive look, but also provides a combination of breathability and support. The shoe also has a chunky sole made of rubber which features a transparent air unit on the heel.

One of the stand-out features on the Nike Air Kukini Triple Black is the midsole, which has a visible AIR unit around the heel area. The unit is helpful in providing responsive cushioning to the foot during walking and other activities, as well as impact absorption for a comfortable feel. The shoe was released for retail priced at $140 on the 9th of September, 2022.

name: Mambacita Sweet 16
title: Nike Kobe 6 Protro Mambacita Sweet 16
description:
The Nike Kobe 6 Protro Mabacita Sweet 16 pays tribute to the late Gigi Bryant and the Mamba & Mambacita Sports Foundation.

The Nike Kobe 6 debuted in 2011 and was the sixth signature sneaker between Nike and the late Laker legend, Kobe Bryant. In 2018, Nike would retro some of Kobe’s older and most memorable sneakers under their Protro program as a means to better equip each pair for the demands and needs of current athletes.

The Nike Kobe 6 Protro Mabacita Sweet 16 features a black snakeskin-inspired upper as a tribute to Kobe’s Black Mamba on-court moniker. From there, Gigi’s AAU basketball jersey number, 2, is stamped on both lateral sides of the ankle. The Mamba & Mambacita Sports Foundation crest is printed on the heel of each shoe followed by both Kobe and Gigi’s names underneath. Lastly, a neoprene and mesh tongue and signature Zoom midsole provide comfort and stability on and off the court.

The Nike Kobe 6 Protro Mabacita Sweet 16 released on May 1st, 2022.

name: Craft Light Olive
title: Jordan 1 Low SE Craft Light Olive
description:
The Jordan 1 Low SE Craft Light Olive gives an artisan vibe to an iconic sports shoe silhouette. Dressed in subtly complementary earthy tones, this shoe fuses trendy style with tried-and-true comfort.

The Light Olive colorway of the Jordan 1 Low-Top Special Edition Craft features an upper of light olive-green smooth leather with lighter greenish-tan suede overlays with distressed edging. The black side-panel Nike swoosh features contrasting white stitching. The creamy white textile tongue with exposed foam matches the sock liner and foam midsole that encapsulates Air. The white laces match the white insole, and the olive-green rubber outsole with stars and circles for traction matches the leather on the upper.

What we enjoy most about this sneaker are the hits of bright Mandarin orange. Orange stitching appears on the lateral side of the Nike swoosh, and a Wings logo is embroidered in orange beneath an orange suede heel patch. An orange tab on the laces matches the Jumpman on the tongue tag as well as the Jumpman on the insole. The Jordan 1 Low SE Craft Light Olive was released on September 16, 2023, for a retail price of $125.

name: Airbrush Swoosh Black
title: Nike Dunk Low Airbrush Swoosh Black
description:
Nike has released its Dunk model in a cornucopia of colorways over the years. The Nike Dunk Low Airbrush Swoosh Black is one of the many additions to the Dunk collection.

The upper part of this Nike Dunk Low sneaker features black leather with black suede overlays. This Dunk Low also has a white midsole made out of rubber, a black rubber outsole, and Nike Basketball logos included on the insoles.

But in our expert opinion, the thing that separates this Nike Dunk Low from other Nike Dunk releases is the design of the Swooshes on the sides of it. At first glance, they may look like ordinary white Swooshes, but they’ve been given the airbrush treatment to help make this particular Dunk more unique than it would be otherwise. The Nike Dunk Low Airbrush Swoosh Black first hit stores on July 26, 2023, when it originally retailed for $110.

name: Obsidian
title: Jordan 1 Retro High Obsidian
description:
Jordan Brand adds a new colorway to its hot streak of Jordan 1 releases with the Air Jordan 1 "Obsidian / University Blue", now available on StockX. Since its debut in 1985, the Air Jordan 1 has been a cultural monument, breaking barriers between the court and the streets. Jordan Brand has continued to shed new light on this timeless silhouette and does so with this release.

This AJ 1 features a similar design to the "UNC Patent" 1s that released in February of 2019, only this time the colorway receives a full leather treatment. This sneaker released in August of 2019 and retails for $160.

name: Pine Green
title: Jordan 3 Retro Pine Green
description:
The Air Jordan 3 Pine Green features a black Durabuck upper with signature elephant print overlays and green perforated collars. Hits of Pine Green on the midsole and Jumpman tongue embroidery stand out against their neutral backdrops. From there, a Jumpman heel tab and Air sole adds the finishing touches to this retro design.

The Air Jordan 3 Pine Green released in October of 2021 and retailed for $190.

name: Baby Lavender Pure Silver (Women's)
title: ASICS Gel-1130 Baby Lavender Pure Silver (Women's)
description:
The ASICS Gel-1130 in baby lavender and pure silver (women’s) offers a fresh look for modern style. They feature a soft baby lavender hue with pure silver accents, blending vibrant colors with retro running aesthetics. These shoes are the way to go if you want something reliable and stylish.

The baby lavender and pure silver Gel-1130 by ASICS combines a lightweight mesh upper with synthetic overlays for breathable support. The metallic silver details along the side and heel complement its soft lavender color. Known for its retro appeal, the Gel-1130 draws inspiration from ASICS’ popular running shoe designs of the 2000s. The women's shoe includes an advanced GEL™ cushioning system to add extra comfort and ease transitions.

One thing we love about the ASICS Gel-1130 in baby lavender and pure silver is its breathable mesh construction, which helps with airflow during movement. Another highlight is the GEL™ technology cushioning to absorb impact. This ASICS Gel-1130Baby Lavender Pure Silver (Women's) was released at a retail price of $110 on 26 September 2024.

name: White Blue Haze Rain Cloud
title: New Balance 550 White Blue Haze Rain Cloud
description:
The New Balance 550 White Blue Haze Rain Cloud comes in a white, blue haze, rain cloud color scheme.

The White Blue Haze Rain Cloud New Balance 550 showcases a white leather and mesh upper. It incorporates a REVlite midsole, ensuring lightweight cushioning for added comfort. With a rubber outsole, the shoe offers both grip and durability. The iconic "N" logo is present on each side, while the tongue displays "new balance 550 NB" branding. The heel features the "NB" logo. Completing the design, there is a "550" inscription on one side and "NB new balance" lettering on the midsole.

The New Balance 550 White Blue Haze Rain Cloud was released at a retail price of $120 on January 24, 2023.

name: Midnight Navy (2022)
title: Jordan 6 Retro Midnight Navy (2022)
description:
For the first time in over 20 years, Jordan Brand brought back the Air Jordan 6 Midnight Navy in its original form.

The Air Jordan 6 Midnight Navy arrives in a white tumbled leather construction with perforated panels and a mesh and black rubber tongue. Being that this colorway debuted as a retro, a Jumpman logo embroidery is featured on the heel instead of the OG Nike Air logo. At the base, a Midnight Navy and white Air midsole atop an icy semi-translucent outsole complete the design.

The Air Jordan 6 Midnight Navy released in May of 2022 and retailed for $200.

name: White Pure Platinum
title: Nike Air Max Terrascape Plus White Pure Platinum
description:
The upper of the Nike Air Max Terrascape Plus White Pure Platinum is constructed from durable materials designed to withstand rugged terrain. The combination of synthetic overlays and mesh provides a balance of durability and breathability. The padded collar and tongue provide extra comfort and support around the ankle, reducing the risk of discomfort during outdoor activities.

The outsole of the Nike Air Max Terrascape Plus White Pure Platinum is designed with a multidirectional tread pattern and deep grooves to provide excellent traction on various surfaces. Synthetic overlays are strategically placed on high-wear areas of the shoe, offering added protection against abrasion and rugged terrain.

Our team of experts especially love the Nike's Max Air cushioning technology in the heel, which provides superior impact protection and comfort during hikes and outdoor adventures. It helps absorb shock and reduce fatigue during extended wear. The Nike Air Max Terrascape Plus White Pure Platinum hit the market on November 17th, 2022, with a price tag of $185.

name: Night Sky
title: Nike Dunk Low Night Sky
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Night Sky presents a mesmerizing iteration of a classic Nike silhouette.

The Night Sky version of the Nike Dunk Low-Top features an upper with a base of white leather with its signature perforations in its toe box. Deep orange tumbled leather overlays appear across the upper. This rich orange color is echoed in the laces and the embroidered Nike branding on the heel tab. The black leather heel tab and the black leather Nike swoosh are printed with whitish-colored star-like graphics reminiscent of a night sky. Black Nike branding appears on the white tongue tag and the white insole.

The feature of the shoe we find most fascinating is the way the outsole works sustainability into the style of the shoe. Beneath the white foam midsole, a black outsole is made of recycled Nike grind rubber, which has a speckled appearance that echoes the stars on the upper. The Nike Dunk Low Night Sky was released on December 23, 2023, for a retail price of $120.

name: Triple Black (Women's)
title: Nike Air Rift Triple Black (Women's)
description:
The Nike Air Rift Triple Black (Women's) offers a versatile, comfortable, and casual yet rugged shoe designed for all sorts of fun, whether it's in the city, at the beach, or on the trail. The sneaker has been specifically sized for women.

This low-to-the-ground sneaker is comprised of black textile panels that overlap. The toebox panel sports a tonal embroidered Nike Swoosh, while the midfoot and heel panels feature black leather and webbing straps to help secure an overall foot fit. A lighter black foam midsole in an undulating pod design encapsulates Air for ultimate cushioning and features debossed Air branding. The outsole is lugged rubber that matches the midsole, providing rugged traction for any adventure.

The feature of this women's shoe that we most appreciate is the tongue area, which has been left open, offering this shoe and easy sandal vibe. The Nike Air Rift Triple Black (Women's) was released on May 18, 2024, for retail price of $120.

name: Black White (GS)
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Black White (GS)
description:
The Jordan 1 Retro High OG Black White (GS) is a grade school-sized shoe with a high-top silhouette and a sleek colorway.

This iteration of the Jordan 1 Retro High OG features a black and white leather upper. Black dominates the side panels of the shoe and rounds out the toebox. The toebox itself is white, perforated for breathability, and white also appears on the heel counter and ankle strap. The Nike Swoosh appears in white across the sides. A black Air Jordan logo can be seen on the ankle strap on the lateral side, and a Nike Air logo appears on the tongue in white. A white sole and black outsole complete the look.

Our favorite aspect of this shoe is the black and white colorway, which makes the sports shoe a little more elegant. The Jordan 1 Retro High OG Black White (GS) was released on February 24, 2024, for a list price of $140.

name: Alternate Bel-Air
title: Jordan 5 Retro Alternate Bel-Air
description:
Jumpman paid tribute to Will Smith’s electrifying 90s outfits in The Fresh Prince of Bel-Air with the Jordan 5 Alternate Bel-Air, now available on StockX. Drawing inspiration from the 2013 Jordan 5 Bel-Air, the Alternate Bel-Air arrives with a brighter take on Smith’s favorite Jordans.

Also known as the Jordan 5 Poison Green, the Alternate Bel-Air consists of the same 90s style colors and patterns as its predecessor, only this time the grey upper is replaced with white leather. A multi-color midsole, icy translucent outsole, and mismatched green and pink Jumpman logos on the tongues complete this retro-style masterpiece. These sneakers released in August of 2020 and retailed for $200.

name: White Ice Blue (Women's)
title: Jordan 1 Low White Ice Blue (Women's)
description:
The Air Jordan 1 Low White Ice Blue W is crafted from a bi-material leather and suede upper, with a pastel color palette.​
​​
​This Low Air Jordan 1 for women comes in white and ice blue colorway. The sneaker has a white leather base featuring sky blue leather overlays. The sneaker has a white midsole and a light blue outsole with a repeat color of the upper, and the Wings logo on the heel. The shoe has an AIR-encapsule technology unit on its sole for cushioning.​
​​
​The Air Jordan 1 Low White Ice Blue W was released on the 24th of March 2022, and retailed for an initial price of $100.

name: Core Black Lucid Blue
title: adidas Campus 00s Core Black Lucid Blue
description:
The adidas Campus 00s Core Black Lucid Blue combines elements from heritage adidas shoe styles of the 1980s with catalog favorites from the early 2000s.

This low-top sneaker has a slightly bulky appearance due to padding around the collar and in the tongue. Specifically, the padding causes the tongue to push up and slightly out of the lace cage. This retro feature is a throwback to skate shoes from the 2000s. While the upper is made of suede, the tongue boasts a mesh material. The entire sneaker is painted in Core Black with a smattering of Lucid Blue details. For example, the trefoil logos on the tongue and heel come in Lucid Blue. ‘CAMPUS’ is also printed along the serrated 3-Stripes in Lucid Blue ink.

Our StockX experts like the incorporation of reflective detailing on the 3-Stripes, the tongue, and along the heel. The adidas Campus 00s Core Black Lucid Blue was released on September 20th, 2023, and retailed at $115.

name: Wonder White Clear Sky (Kids)
title: adidas Gazelle Bold Wonder White Clear Sky (Kids)
description:
The adidas Gazelle Bold Wonder White Clear Sky (Kids) reimagines the original Gazelle from the 1970s with a triple-stacked platform and a soft, pastel colorway of Wonder White, Cloud White, and Clear Sky.

Unlike the OG Gazelle, this version of the Gazelle Bold features three layers of gum rubber underfoot, which adds height and a contemporary feel. The layers form a gradient of gum hues from light to dark. In addition, each layer displays its own "adidas" branding and a small trefoil. The smooth leather upper in Wonder White provides durability, while a tonal suede overlay forms a "T" over the toe box. Heritage elements include the serrated 3-Stripes logo in Cloud White and the front lace closure system.

Our experts like the Clear Sky accents on the heel mustache and the adidas label printed on the tongue. They add just a touch of color to the Wonder White base. The kid-sized adidas Gazelle Bold Wonder White Clear Sky (Kids) was released on April 12, 2024, and sold for $100.

name: Hangul Day
title: Nike P-6000 Hangul Day
description:
The Nike P-6000 Hangul Day is a special iteration of the Nike P-6000 running sneaker with a unique color scheme that pays tribute to the Korean national holiday Hangul Day.

The shoes have a retro-inspired chunky silhouette featuring a mesh base layered with nubuck and suede materials. The three materials contribute significantly to the shoe’s lightweight and breathable characteristics. As for the color scheme, they display a Photon Dust base with khaki overlays creating the contrast effect. Apart from the Nike Swoosh, branding details on the shoe include a Nike logo on the tongue and tiny P-6000 branding on the lateral ankle.

One thing we love about the Nike P-6000 Hangul Day, apart from the connection to Korean culture, is the use of a foam midsole. This makes the shoe better suited for running as it adds a track-inspired stance and unbelievable cushioning. The shoes were released on the 6th of October, 2023, at the retail price of $120.

name: Mineral Green Crystal Sand (Women's)
title: adidas Samba OG Mineral Green Crystal Sand (Women's)
description:
The adidas Samba OG Mineral Green Crystal Sand (Women's) upgrades the Samba with a retro-inspired colorway of Mineral Green and Shadow Green with Crystal Sand accents. The combination of deep-green and off-white hues brings a varsity sports aesthetic to the classic silhouette with a contemporary twist.

The upper of the Mineral Green Crystal Sand (Women's) adidas Samba OG is made from velvety nubuck with tonal shaggy suede on the T-shaped toe box overlay and the heel mustache. Creating a premium feel, slightly darker Shadow Green accents can be found on the leather collar and tongue. The serrated 3-Stripes logo, the adidas branding printed on the tongue, and the exaggerated stitching on the side panels and heel tab feature Crystal Sand.

Our experts at StockX like the rubber outsole’s dark hue because it complements the Mineral Green and Shadow Green’s rich tones. The adidas Samba OG Mineral Green Crystal Sand (Women's) was released on July 18, 2024, and sold for $100.

name: Syracuse
title: Nike Dunk Low SP Syracuse
description:
Nike celebrated the 35th Anniversary of the Nike Dunk by releasing the Nike Dunk Low SP Syracuse (2020), now available on StockX. The Nike Dunk debuted as part of the 1985 Nike College Color’s program, a program that delivered footwear in the school colors of 12 popular basketball programs allowing fans to support their favorite teams from head to toe. This Syracuse colorway was among the first collegiate colorways Nike released, breaking the mold for colorways used on basketball shoes.

This Nike Dunk Low SP is composed of a white leather upper with orange blaze leather overlays. A white midsole, orange outsole, and classic Nike branding on the tongue complete the design. These sneakers released in March of 2020 and retailed for $100.

name: Light Smoke Grey
title: Nike Mac Attack QS SP Light Smoke Grey
description:
The Nike Mac Attack QS SP Light Smoke Grey is a retro-inspired sneaker released to celebrate Nike's iconic basketball heritage, featuring a clean colorway of light smoke grey, black, and white.

The Nike Mac Attack QS SP pays homage to its original design with a retro style combining a Light Smoke Grey mesh base and leather paneling. The sneaker features a sleek black Swoosh on the lateral and medial sidewalls, with additional accents on the toebox, ankle, and heel. A classic blue and black checkerboard tongue tag with a fiery red "Nike" logo stitched in the center adds a nostalgic touch. The sneaker is elevated by an all-white midsole, complemented by a star-spangled rubber outsole, delivering a complete throwback aesthetic.

As StockX specialists, we are particularly enamored with the classic blue and black checkerboard tongue tag featured on the Nike Mac Attack QS SP Light. The Nike Mac Attack QS SP Light Smoke Grey was released on 23rd June 2023, retailing at $120.

name: Día De Muertos (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Día De Muertos (Women's)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Día De Muertos (Women's) is part of a collection released to celebrate the Day of the Dead in honor of eternal connections.

Arriving in women’s sizing, this Nike Dunk Low has leather underlay in a Metallic Gold colorway with a brushstroke pattern. It is visible on the perforated vamp, midfoot on the quarter panels, and parts of the heel. Several overlays cover this leather base, including scaly Sailor-colored leather on the mudguard and gill-patterned leather on the eyestays. The quarter panels introduce a suede material on the black Swoosh. The heel returns the leather overlays in a black, molded panel that forms the collar flaps.

Our experts think the vibrant hues on the branding of these sneakers deliver a unique pop and make them outstanding. The Nike tongue logo is pink, matching the embroidery on the heel counter. A traditionally significant hummingbird site on the lateral heel and comes in a Light Jade tint with Sail accents. The Nike Dunk Low Día De Muertos (Women's) was released on October 21st, 2023, for 125.

name: Italian Camo (2024) (GS)
title: Nike Kobe 6 Protro Italian Camo (2024) (GS)
description:
The Nike Kobe 6 Protro Italian Camo (2024) (GS) represents an installment of the continued Nike Kobe line that honors the legacy of NBA star Kobe Bryant. This colorway pays homage to his time spent in Italy, where his father played pro basketball. This sneaker is sized for grade-school-aged kids.

The big kids’ Italian Camo colorway of the Kobe 6 Protro 2024 features a synthetic upper with a faux reptile texture. The camo pattern takes inspiration from the Italian military uniform. Black laces close over a black tongue to ensure a snug closure. An olive green TPU heel counter completes the look of this upper. The Protro midsole in black rests atop a rubber outsole in olive green and black.

What we enjoy most about this sneaker are the hits of crimson that add pops of contrast throughout the sneaker. Bright red Kobe logos hit the tongue tag and outsole, while the tongue lining and side panel Nike swoosh are also bright red. The Nike Kobe 6 Protro Italian Camo (2024) (GS) was released on April 13, 2024, for $120 retail.

name: Concord (GS)
title: Jordan 1 Low SE Concord (GS)
description:
The Air Jordan 1 Low SE Concord (GS) comes in a white and black color palette.

The Jordan 1 Low SE Concord has a leather upper, and the Jumpman emblem is embroidered on the tongue. The sneaker features a lightweight midsole for padding and a sturdy rubber outsole for grip and stability. The shoe also features a padded collar and perforations in the toe box for ankle support and ventilation, respectively. The sneaker's design is completed with a Nike Swoosh on the lateral sides and an Air Jordan logo on the heel.

The grade schoolers’ sizing of the Air Jordan 1 Low SE Concord (GS) was released at a retail price of $95 on January 17, 2023.

name: Kasina Won-Ang Orange
title: Nike Air Max 1 Kasina Won-Ang Orange
description:
South Korean boutique Kasina celebrated its 25th Anniversary with the Nike Air Max 1 Kasina Wong-Ang Orange.

Pulling inspiration from Wong-Ang Ducks, a style of carved wooden ducks traditionally gifted to newlywed couples, the Nike Air Max 1 Kasina Wong-Ang Orange incorporates colors and materials that are said to bring good fortune in Korean culture. It boast a premium brown tumbled leather upper with dark green faux horsehair overlays and brown and orange suede mudguards. At the heel, small Wong-Ang Duck embroidery nods to the Korean wedding custom. At the base, an icy, semi-translucent outsole revealing a geometric pattern on the bottom of the midsole adds the finishing touch.

The Nike Air Max 1 Kasina Wong-Ang Orange released in June of 2022 and retailed for $160.

name: Big Bubble Obsidian
title: Nike Air Max 1 '86 Big Bubble Obsidian
description:
The Nike Air Max 1 ‘86 Big Bubble Obsidian is a reproduction of the original design from 1986. Designed by Tinker Hatfield, this was the first sneaker to have a visible Nike Air unit in the heel. Obsidian is also the original colorway that these sneakers were released with in 80’s, making these sneakers timeless.
​
​This Air Max 1 ´86 sneaker’s upper is constructed from a mix of textile materials and suede, with a lining of textile material and a rubber sole for traction. The mesh inserts around the toe and the midsole appear in white, while beige suede overlays can be found on the side and the heel. The Swoosh appears on the side, and obsidian rounds out the design above the white rubber outsole. Red accents appear on the heel and on the tongue, giving this shoe a pop of color.
​
​What our StockX experts love about this shoe is the visible Air unit in the heel. The Nike Air Max 1 ‘86 Big Bubble Obsidian was released on September 9th, 2023, at a price of $150.

name: Fat Tongue Black Orange
title: Jordan 1 Mid Fat Tongue Black Orange
description:
The Jordan 1 Mid Fat Tongue Black Orange is a mid-top basketball silhouette featuring classic Air Jordan branding and a modern design. 

This version of the Jordan 1 Mid features a black leather upper with orange leather overlays. The orange overlays round out the ankle strap and the heel. The perforated toe box also comes in orange leather. The iconic Nike swoosh appears in orange on the midsole outlined in red, and it wraps around the heel. Classic Air Jordan branding is found on the orange ankle strap. A white rubber outsole with orange on the bottom rounds out this sleek design. 

What our experts like best about this sneaker is the extra cushioning in the ankle and tongue areas, providing extra support and comfort. The Jordan 1 Mid Fat Tongue Black Orange was originally released on May 13th, 2023, for a retail price of $110.

name: White Light Armory Blue
title: Nike Dunk Low White Light Armory Blue
description:
The Nike Dunk Low White Light Armory Blue pays tribute to the University of North Carolina through its collegiate colorway of Summit White, white, and Light Armory Blue. However, what sets this sneaker apart from other UNC-inspired variations is the choice of Light Armory Blue instead of classic Carolina Blue.

The white, all-leather upper of the White Light Armory Blue Nike Dunk Low serves as a simple backdrop for the pops of Light Armory Blue brought to the Swoosh logos and the rubber outsole. The NIKE lettering on the heel and the branding on the woven tongue tag are also in this unique blue. Another subtle detail is the suede overlays in Summit White, accentuating the sneaker’s heritage construction. White cotton laces thread through the lace cage and allow for an adjustable fit.

Our experts at StockX like the mesh tongue and perforations on the toe box because they provide breathability and an airy feel. The Nike Dunk Low White Light Armory Blue was released on May 1, 2024, and sold for $115.

name: Blush
title: adidas Yeezy 500 Blush
description:
With a pale pink monochromatic palette, the adidas Yeezy 500 Blush features a hiking-inspired suede and mesh construction are durable enough for the trails and also versatile enough for daily wear. From there, a sculptural adiPRENE sole adds the finishing touch.

The adidas Yeezy 500 Blush debuted in February of 2018, and restocked in February of 2022 for a retail price of $200.

name: Fresh Coconut Milk
title: Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 Fresh Coconut Milk
description:
The Nike Air Force 1 Low ’07 Fresh Coconut Milk covers the Air Force 1 Low ’07 silhouette in a creamy, off-white colorway of Fresh Coconut Milk.

From the rubber outsole to the inner lining to the branding details, every part of this sneaker comes in Fresh Coconut Milk. The upper is crafted from durable leather, with forefoot and heel overlays in the same material. Leather Swoosh logos reach across the side panels, while the front lace closure provides a secure, adjustable fit. Inspired by the OG Air Force 1 released in 1982, this basketball sneaker houses Nike Air cushioning in the foam midsole and boasts a grippy, rubber outsole.

Our experts like the way the perforations across the toebox match the perforations on the insoles. The Nike Air Force 1 Low ’07 Fresh Coconut Milk was originally launched on October 11, 2023, and sold for $140.

name: Fade Onyx
title: adidas Yeezy Knit RNR Fade Onyx
description:
Pushing the boundaries of innovation and style, the adidas Yeezy Knit RNR Fade Onyx dropped a shadowy masterpiece on August 10, 2023. This Yeezy model takes sneaker aesthetics to a whole new dimension, blending simplicity with avant-garde design.

The Yeezy Knit RNR Fade Onyx became the talk of the town with its unique sock-like silhouette, making it the sneaker of choice for those who crave comfort and a stand out look. With a neutral grey gradient, it showcases an uninterrupted flow from its ankle collar to its toe box. But it doesn't just stop there. The sneaker's grey rubber outsole complements the design, while its EVA midsole ensures lightweight comfort with every step. Plus, with its PU toe reinforcement, this Yeezy promises not just style, but also durability.

Making its grand entry on August 10, 2023, the adidas Yeezy Knit RNR Fade Onyx was priced at a cool $210 for those looking to elevate their sneaker game.

name: Iridescent
title: Puma LaMelo Ball MB.01 Iridescent
description:
The Puma LaMelo Ball MB.01 Iridescent is a basketball shoe created by Puma in partnership with NBA player LaMelo Ball.

This sneaker features an all-pink construction in Light Chiffon with iridescent accents on the midsole and splashed across the upper. In addition, thin line designs on the tongue and vamp come in Light Aqua. Featuring a seamless design, the lightweight upper is made of mesh and conforms to the foot’s natural shape without feeling snug. NITRO-injected foam adds responsive cushioning to the midsole, while the TPU heel counter stabilizes the foot and ankle. In terms of traction, high-abrasion tread on the outsole grips the ground.

Our StockX experts like that this sneaker finds inspiration in the galaxy and space exploration. Embroidered designs around the collar mimic flames and details on the vamp look like rocket ship wings. The Puma LaMelo Ball MB.01 Iridescent was released on February 2nd, 2024, and retailed at $140.

name: Night Indigo Wonder Taupe
title: adidas Gazelle Night Indigo Wonder Taupe
description:
The adidas Gazelle Night Indigo Wonder Taupe takes a silhouette that was retooled as an indoor handball shoe in 1979 and gives it an iconic street style that's still defining fashion today.

The Night Indigo Wonder Taupe colorway of the adidas Gazelle features a deluxe upper crafted from night indigo suede that forms the base, as well as T-toe and eyestay overlays that enhance the structure of the shoe. The collar is padded, and the indigo-blue synthetic tongue is molded to enhance comfort as you slide into the shoe. Taupe leather is used for the sock liner, the heel tab, and the signature serrated three stripes coursing down the side panel. The gum rubber sole unit sneaks onto the upper to form a thin, translucent mudguard. The outsole is patterned for traction with every step.

What we enjoy most about this fashion and comfort icon is the simplicity of its branding. A blue trefoil hits the heel tab, a taupe trefoil is debossed the tongue, and Gazelle branding in gold graces the side panel. The adidas Gazelle Night Indigo Wonder Taupe was released on January 1, 2024, for a retail price of $100.

name: Vintage Floral (GS)
title: Jordan 3 Retro Vintage Floral (GS)
description:
The Jordan 3 Retro Vintage Floral (GS) is a grade school-sized sneaker with a design inspired by the wallpaper in Michael Jordan’s childhood home.

This version of the Jordan 3 Retro is made with a premium textured leather upper in white. Overlays around the toebox and heel sport a leopard print with tan and soft pink colors. Part of the lace cage sticks to the white and soft pink color scheme, while the top part appears in black and yellow. The heel of the shoe is also black with a large white Jumpman logo. The heel collar has a subtle floral pattern on it, paying homage to Jordan’s childhood home. The tongue features a black Jumpman logo, while there’s a visible Air unit under the heel.

Our favorite feature of this shoe is the surprising pop of black present on the heel and lace cage. This departure from the soft pink and white hues adds some welcome contrast to the design. The Jordan 3 Retro Vintage Floral (GS) was released on January 19, 2024, for a retail price of $160.

name: CLOT Jade
title: Jordan 5 Retro Low CLOT Jade
description:
The Air Jordan 5 Low CLOT Jade celebrates China's appreciation for jade, as its heritage and tradition is infused with greatness. The design features a black satin-like upper with semi-translucent TPU netted inserts and light grey heel embroideries. Attached to the red woven laces, clear jade beads add further decoration. At the base, a midsole similar to the Jordan 5 Metallic and a jade semi-translucent outsole complete the design.

The Air Jordan 5 Low CLOT Jade released in May of 2022 and retailed for $200.

name: Sulfur
title: adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Sulfur
description:
Constructed with a blend of EVA foam and recycled materials, adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Sulfur arrives in an identical build to prior Foam RNNRs. Oval cut openings throughout the neutral-toned design create a sculptural look while providing ventilation. At the base, a cushioned footbed offers comfort and support.

The adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Sulfur released in April of 2022 and retailed for $90.

name: MiUSA Black Grey White
title: New Balance 990v6 MiUSA Black Grey White
description:
The New Balance 990v6 MiUSA Black Grey White continues to deliver the original New Balance 990 goal of a perfect running shoe by combining FuelCell technology on the midsole and a fabric lining in grey tones.

The body of the New Balance 990v6 has a mesh underlay in a black hue. A dark suede overlay starts on the mudguard and proceeds to cover the circumference of the border between the shoe and the sole. On the quarter panels, a mix of mesh base, black suede, grey synthetic strips, and the "N" New Balance branding in light grey are present. A similar overlay design appears on the heel.

StockX experts think the colorful logos distributed on this shoe’s surface make it stand out and give it an identity. A red V6 branding appears on the tongue alongside New Balance 990 embossed writing. Additionally, the NB logo with a Made in USA tag adorns the heel counter. Released on April 7th, 2023, the New Balance 990v6 MiUSA Black Grey White had a retail price of $200.

name: Core White Magic Beige
title: adidas Samba OG Core White Magic Beige
description:
The adidas Samba OG Core White Magic Beige finds inspiration in the original football shoe from the 1950s. However, it boasts upgrades, including premium materials and a minimalist colorway of Core White, Wonder White, and Magic Beige.

This low-top sneaker has a leather construction in Core White with Magic Beige accents on the serrated 3-Stripes logo, the heel, and the collar. The lining is also made of leather, which adds a premium touch to the design. Another standout feature is the collection of perforations across the vamp. The signature T-shaped toe overlay is constructed from leather and divides the perforations into two groups. The sneaker offers a gum rubber outsole with a less-orange tone than traditional gum.

Our StockX experts like the additional perforations on the leather tongue, which allow the foot to breathe. The adidas Samba OG Core White Magic Beige was released on March 24, 2024, and retailed at $100.

name: White Clay Canyon (GS)
title: ASICS Gel-1130 White Clay Canyon (GS)
description:
The ASICS Gel-1130 White Clay Canyon (GS) takes a running silhouette with a late 2000s aesthetic, dresses it in an understated, stylish colorway, and sizes it for grade-school-aged kids.

This running shoe sized for kids and designed for all-day comfort builds upon an upper base of loose weave white mesh that offers lightweight breathability. Synthetic leather overlays in dark blue and silver streak vertically and horizontally over the upper, adding iconic style and all-over foot support. The off-white foam midsole is infused with Gel technology for ultimate springy cushioning. A silver midfoot plate offers the stability of the TRUSSTIC support system. Pods of black and brown rubber form the outsole, designed to absorb impact and provide multi-surface traction.

The aspect of this kids’ running shoe that we enjoy the most is the conscientiously crafted dope-dyed black sock liner that is specifically constructed to reduce water usage and carbon emissions. The ASICS Gel-1130 White Clay Canyon (GS) was released on March 3, 2024, for a retail price of $85.

name: White Cement (2016)
title: Jordan 4 Retro White Cement (2016)
description:
