The Air Jordan 4 Retro White Cement 2016 features the classic 1989 colorway White/Fire Red/Black/Tech Gray. Black waffle eyestays and white mesh enhance the white leather upper. "Cement" refers to the black-speckled gray accents on the midsole, wings, and heel. A black Nike Air logo and Swoosh appear just below a cement-pattern heel tab. The white tongue features a red Jumpman above "Flight" printed in black. The black insole has a red Nike Air logo and Swoosh. The white midsole has visible Air. The rubber outsole includes every color in the colorway.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro White Cement 2016 was released on February 12, 2016, at a retail price of $220.

name: White Varsity Red
title: Jordan 2/3 White Varsity Red
description:
The Jordan 2/3 White Varsity Red is a hybrid basketball shoe that combines elements from heritage sneakers in the Jordan catalog.

The base is made of white leather with Varsity Red accents and leather overlays with a lizard-skin texture. The overlays wrap around the back of the sneaker and feature a Varsity Red line that transforms into the collar lining. Other Varsity Red details can be found on the retro-inspired Air Jordan Wings logo printed on the tongue and a panel on the heel. Both the padded tongue and the mudguard are crafted from premium leather and come in white. Perforations form a line that wraps around the upper and allows the foot to breathe.

Our StockX experts like the visible air units in the heel and the choice of Cement Grey on the rubber outsole because these elements pay homage to previous Jordan Brand sneakers. The Jordan 2/3 White Varsity Red was released on July 6, 2024, and retailed at $160.

name: Black White
title: New Balance 574 Black White
description:
The New Balance 574 Black White is a sneaker released through the collaboration of BEAMS and New Balance brands. 

The sneaker arrives in a blend of black, light grey, and white colorway dubbed "Black White." At the same time, black makes the most of the shoe; grey hints appear on the inner lining, padded collars, and the heel unit. The upper comprises long-lasting suede and breathable mesh vamp, while an EVA chunk underfoot provides lightweight cushioning beneath. Branding detailing is enhanced by the logo patch to the sides and tongue, the heel tab, and the horizontally patterned stabilizer. Adding to the shoe’s design are a rounded toe and a flat rubber outsole.  

The New Balance 574 Black White 2022 was released on December 30th, 2021. It retailed at a price of $95.

name: Lionel Messi
title: adidas Samba Indoor Lionel Messi
description:
The adidas Samba Indoor Lionel Messi is an indoor soccer shoe, paying homage to the colors of soccer star Lionel Messi’s national team: Argentina.

This iteration of the adidas Samba Indoor is made with a white leather upper. It also features a gray suede toe cap, consistent with the shoe’s classic design. The iconic three stripes logo adorns the midsoles in light blue. Messi’s name appears in gold on the lateral side above the first stripe. The tongue and laces come in royal blue, while Messi’s logo is featured in light blue on the tongue and is embossed into the leather on the lateral heel. The heel collar is metallic gold, and a translucent white rubber outsole completes the look.

What we like most about this shoe is its subtle design paying homage to Argentina. The adidas Samba Indoor Lionel Messi was first released on February 20, 2024, for a retail price of $100.

name: White Black Red (2022)
title: Jordan 1 Mid White Black Red (2022)
description:
The Air Jordan 1 Mid White Black Red 2022 is a Jordan Brand’s launch that looks like the 2018’s Air Jordan 1 Bred Toe.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid White Black Red 2022 has a white leather upper. Red accents are present in the collars, tongue, toe perforated toe box, and Swooshes. It also features black overlays, insole, lining, laces, rubber outsole, and Jumpman logo on the tongue. A winged logo on the collar and a white midsole complete the look.

This Air Jordan 1 Mid White Black Red 2022 debuted on 1st June 2022, retailing at $120.

name: Sea Salt Black
title: New Balance 327 Sea Salt Black
description:
The New Balance 327 Sea Salt Black arrives sporting a heritage running silhouette inspired by the '70s.

The New Balance 327 Sea Salt Black is crafted from a breathable, lightweight nylon and suede upper, padded insole, and shock-absorbing rubber sole for unmatched comfort. New Balance's hard-to-miss "N" logo graces the sides in black in addition to the NB hits on the tongue and insoles alike. Finally, its design is rounded off with a midsole lined in a durable black rubber outsole that runs from the top heel to the toe.

The New Balance 327 Sea Salt Black was released in March 2021 and retailed for $90.

name: Sunrise
title: Nike KD 17 Sunrise
description:
The Nike KD 17 Sunrise showcases a vibrant, sunrise-inspired colorway with splashes of Safety Orange and University Gold. Created by NBA player Kevin Durant and Nike Basketball, this sneaker represents a bold addition to the KD 17 lineup.

The wavy TPU overlays on the Sunrise Nike KD 17 draw inspiration from Sean McDowell’s Nike Air Max Plus and extend from the midsole to the eyelets. Each overlay displays a color gradient that fades from University Gold to Safety Orange. In contrast, the underlays fade from white to University Gold. Hits of black can be found on the Swoosh logos and a line delineating the midsole and upper. As for contemporary upgrades, the Cushlon midsole houses a strong TPU shank, while Zoom cushioning provides superior energy return.

Our StockX experts like Kevin Durant’s personal branding details, including his signature on the Safety Orange heel counter. The Nike KD 17 Sunrise was released on May 17, 2024, and sold for $150.

name: Vintage UNC Grey
title: Jordan 1 Low Vintage UNC Grey
description:
Inspired by the 2018 Union Jordan 1s, the Air Jordan 1 Low Vintage UNC Grey sneaker arrives in a White/​Varsity Blue/​Grey/​Sail color scheme.​
​
​The upper is made of a white suede base with blue overlays on the forefoot and front eyestays, while grey overlays highlight a section of the eyestays, heels, and Swooshes. Tumbled leather is used on the Swooshes. Other details include a padded Nike Sail tongue, an orange ‘Wings’ logo on the heel, Jumpman branding on the tongue, and a perforated toebox. A Nike Sail midsole and University Blue rubber outsole complete the design.​
​
​The Air Jordan 1 Low Vintage UNC Grey was released on October 1, 2022 for a retail price of $110.

name: Night Stadium
title: Jordan 1 Mid SE Night Stadium
description:
The Jordan 1 Mid SE Night Stadium showcases a unique blend of light and dark gray tones on the upper, utilizing smooth suede and cracked nubuck for an unconventional appearance.

The Night Stadium Jordan 1 Mid SE introduces a palette featuring Night Stadium, Neutral Gray, black, Total Orange, and Flat Pewter shades. The shoe's construction incorporates diverse textures, combining smooth suede and cracked nubuck with mesh tongues and inner lining. While the primary color theme revolves around various shades of grey, the clever addition of Total Orange accents, particularly on the Jumpman logo and stitched trim, imparts a noticeable Halloween-inspired vibe. Completing the design is a white midsole resting on a black rubber outsole, creating a cohesive and balanced aesthetic.

The standout characteristic of the Jordan 1 Mid SE Night Stadium lies in the Night Stadium hue, enhanced by subtle accents, resulting in a shoe with a distinctive visual appeal. The sneaker was originally sold for $135 on October 1st, 2023.

name: Black
title: Nike Air Force 1 Mid '07 Black
description:
The Nike Air Force 1 Mid '07 Triple Black (2021) features a smooth black-on-black upper made of genuine and synthetic leather with a black swoosh and overlays on the heel and toe cap.

The Nike Air Force 1 Mid '07 Triple Black's black laces feature a silver AF1 tag. The black heel tab has black Nike Air branding and swoosh, and the strap at the top of the collar sports a mini swoosh. The black insole of the right shoe has a white patch with branding, the black midsole has a hidden Air Sole unit, and the black rubber outsole features an iconic concentric circles pattern.

The Nike Air Force 1 Mid '07 Triple Black (2021) was released in 2021 at a retail price of $100.

name: Patta Waves Monarch (with Bracelet)
title: Nike Air Max 1 Patta Waves Monarch (with Bracelet)
description:
In collaboration with Patta, the Nike Air Max 1 Patta Waves Monarch (with Bracelet) features a grey mesh upper with white overlays with Monarch Swooshes and a wave-shaped mudguard. From there, retro Nike branding on the heel nods to the original line of Air Max 1s. A cream Air midsole, multicolor outsole, and signature Patta woven tongue tags add the finishing touch.

The Nike Air Max 1 Patta Waves Monarch released in October of 2021 and retailed for $160.

name: White Mica Green
title: Nike Air Max 1 White Mica Green
description:
The Nike Air Max 1 White Mica Green is a special colorway of the iconic Air Max 1 silhouette featuring a color combination of white, gray, Mica Green and accents of black.

The shoe’s upper is made from mesh material and has suede overlays around the midfoot and heel. The base is covered in white while the overlays appear in gray with Mica green, covering the mudguard around the toe box and heel as well as the Swoosh. It also has an Air unit in the midsole for added cushioning, while the outsole is black and white.

What we love about the Nike Air Max 1 White Mica Green is its minimalist design with tone down color shades that make it an appealing option for every outfit, regardless of the season. The Air Max 1 White Mica Green was released on April 14, 2023 priced at $150.

name: Moonbeam True Red (Women's)
title: New Balance 327 Moonbeam True Red (Women's)
description:
The New Balance 327 Moonbeam True Red (Women's) takes inspiration from '70s NB running shoe design and combines it with aspects of several New Balance silhouettes in order to come up with comfortable running and lifestyle shoe. This sneaker is specifically sized for women.

The Moonbeam True Red (Women's) New Balance 327 with a wedge silhouette begins with a base of moonbeam-colored nylon with a collar padded for enhanced comfort. Tonal suede overlays inspired by the NB 320, 355, and Supercomp adorn the toebox, eyestays, and heel. Red New Balance branding hits the medial heel overlay and complements the red tongue tag with a moonbeam flying NB. The flared midsole of moonbeam foam rests atop a lugged gum rubber outsole that wraps up the toe and heel, a feature that is also a nod to the NB 320, 355, and Supercomp.

The stand-out feature that makes this pair of women’s sneakers pop is the oversized side-panel N in textured red leather that will turn heads with every step you take. The New Balance 327 Moonbeam True Red (Women's) was released on April 3, 2024, for $100 retail.

name: Black Croc
title: Jordan 1 Retro Low Golf Black Croc
description:
The Jordan 1 Retro Low Golf Black Croc was released in 2023 as part of the Jordan Brand's golf collection.

The Black Jordan 1 Retro Low Golf Croc has a durable rubber outsole with a unique outsole pattern that maximizes traction and stability on the course. The shoe's midsole features Nike's proprietary Air technology, providing ample cushioning and support for the golfer's feet. The shoe is also equipped with a removable and interchangeable spikes system, which allows golfers to adjust their traction depending on course conditions. The spikes are made with durable TPU materials that provide ample grip on the course's grass or terrain, ensuring that golfers can take a precise swing without slipping or losing balance.

What we like the most about the Jordan 1 Retro Low Golf Black Croc? It's without a doubt its premium black crocodile leather upper, which gives the shoe a bold, luxurious look. The leather is water-resistant and provides ample protection to the foot during damp weather conditions. The shoe was released on January 7th, 2023 at a retail price of $140.

name: Sail Iridescent Swoosh (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Sail Iridescent Swoosh (Women's)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Sail Iridescent Swoosh (Women's) is a women’s shoe with a simple colorway featuring unique iridescent elements.

This iteration of the Nike Dunk Low has an upper made of leather. The dominant color is Sail off-white, which forms the perforated toe box, the midsole, and part of the heel. Suede overlays in a darker shade of off-white forms the toe cap and runs from the ankle around the heel. The Nike swoosh appears across each side of the shoe in a multi-colored iridescent tone that changes when the light hits it in different ways. The word Nike is also stitched into the heel collar in an iridescent thread, and a subtle Nike logo patch can be found on the tongue. An off-white rubber outsole forms the bottom of the shoe.

What we think stands out about this sneaker is the simple colorway with iridescent accents. The off-white colorway truly allows these unique elements to shine. The Nike Dunk Low Sail Iridescent Swoosh (Women's) was released on April 1, 2024, for $115.

name: What The
title: Jordan 5 Retro What The
description:
To honor the 30th Anniversary of the Jordan 5, Jordan Brand added a "What The?" treatment to its catalog with the Jordan 5 What The. This design boasts a mix of materials and details from Jumpman’s best Non-OG Jordan 5 colorways, including the Tokyo, Shanghai, Raging Bull, Bel-Air, Laser, Green Bean, Olive, and Quai 54 colorways.

In true mismatched fashion, each foot of the Jordan 5 What The showcases a different look. On the right, yellow suede from the Tokyo 5 smothers the upper atop a purple and blue speckled Belair 5 midsole with a patterned interior pulled from the Jordan 5 Olive. On the left, red suede tributing the Raging Bull Jordan 5 covers the upper atop a black, grey, and lime green sole that references the Quai 54 iteration. Heel embroidery nodding to the Shanghai and Tokyo models, icy translucent outsoles, and 3M reflective tongues complete this scrambled iteration.

The Jordan 5 What The released in November of 2020 and retailed for $220.

name: Stealth
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Stealth
description:
The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG Stealth, featuring a stealth and white color scheme, is one of the Air Jordan 1’s celebrated versions.

These Retro High OG Stealth sneakers feature a stealth grey hue on the laces, overlays, leather tongue labels, Swooshes, and on the outsole too. The white colorway is dominant on the shoe’s goat leather base. This Air Jordan 1 has a perforated toe box to allow aeration. Also, its outsole is patterned to increase traction.

The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG Stealth were originally made available on August 2022, at the retail price of $180.

name: White Midnight Navy
title: Nike Dunk Low Retro White Midnight Navy
description:
The White Midnight Navy Nike Dunk Low Retro pairs classic design with fresh detailing to highlight Nike's legacy in basketball-inspired kicks. Its crisp white base and navy overlays give you a clean, versatile look that suits a wide range of styles.

The White Midnight Navy Dunk Low Retro by Nike features a smooth leather upper with a white foundation accented by deep navy overlays. A perforated toe box improves breathability, while the durable rubber outsole guarantees long-lasting traction. The iconic Swoosh logo appears in navy on both sides, complemented by white laces for a balanced aesthetic. First introduced in 1985, the Dunk line remains one of the most popular in Nike’s rich history.

Something we enjoy about the White Midnight Navy Nike Dunk Low Retro is its supportive rubber outsole that gives you a more reliable grip and the padded collar for added comfort while you wear them. Released on 11th June 2024, it retailed at $115.

name: Sunset (2024)
title: Nike Air Max Plus Sunset (2024)
description:
The Nike Air Max Plus Sunset (2024) is a special-edition of the "Sunset" colorway, which has been released numerous times over the years throughout the history of the Nike Air Max Plus.

The wave-like upper has TPU overlays that resembles waves in the sea as the sun sets. Aiming to mimic and capture all phases of a sunset, you’ll notice how the colors gradient from a bright Ceramic Yellow in the toe area all the way to a deep dark pimento in the heel area. Together with other colors such as black, resin, and white, the effect is nothing less than spectacular. On the quarter side panels, you’ll spot small red Nike Swooshes, while iconic Tuned Air (TN) logos sit on the heel, on the insole, and underfoot in the middle of the outsole.

What our experts love about this shoe is how the Air Units complement the idea of a sunset, the orange color peeking through adds to the overall aesthetic. When it was released on July 3, 2024, the Nike Air Max Plus Sunset (2024) had a $180 price tag.

name: Racer Blue
title: Jordan 5 Retro Racer Blue
description:
In a style similar to classic Jordan 5s of the past, the Air Jordan 5 Racer Blue features a black Durabuck upper with signature TPU netted inserts and a reflective padded tongue. At the base, Racer Blue accents pop against a black midsole and icy translucent sole.

The Air Jordan 5 Racer Blue released in February of 2022 and retailed for $200.

name: CLOT By Edison Chen Black
title: adidas Superstar CLOT By Edison Chen Black
description:
The adidas Superstar CLOT By Edison Chen Black is part of the second drop brought to you by adidas and Edison Chen, a Hong Kong–based streetwear label founded by the actor of the same name.

Finding inspiration in Chen’s creative journey, the sneaker was first seen during Shanghai Fashion Week and is a mature take on the classic Superstar silhouette. The signature shell toe is crafted from premium leather with carefully stitched ridges. The upper is made of premium leather in Core Black, while Cloud White details are visible on the 3-striped logo and a line running through the midsole. In addition, the retro-inspired adidas logo tag on the tongue comes in Core White. The sneaker boasts tassels on the laces, which speaks to its premium aesthetic.

Our experts like the perforation details around the collar and between the 3-Stripes. The adidas Superstar CLOT By Edison Chen Black was first released on April 12, 2024, and sold for $200.

name: Driftwood Stone Pink Sea Salt
title: New Balance 9060 Driftwood Stone Pink Sea Salt
description:
The New Balance 9060 Driftwood Stone Pink Sea Salt showcases an appealing combination of contrasting materials and colors, combining classic elements from the iconic 99X silhouette with a futuristic twist.

The Driftwood Stone Pink Sea Salt New Balance 9060 kicks off with a clean white mesh foundation, forming the base layer for the sneaker. Complementing this are soft and elegant Pale Pink suede panels that grace the mudguards, toeboxes, medial sides, and heel portions. Creamy leather accents make their presence felt, notably on the signature N insignia along the sides and the branded rear tabs. Leather trims outline the toeboxes and ankle regions, while brown highlights incorporate New Balance branding beneath the laces. The tongue badges, outsole tips, and insoles feature distinct markings, all resting atop chunky midsoles adorned with a mix of white, cream, and beige accents.

What our experts love about the New Balance 9060 Driftwood Stone Pink Sea Salt is its distinctive fuzzy appearance, thanks to the use of Pale Pink suede panels on various parts of the shoe. The sneaker debuted for $150 on May 16th, 2023.

name: Purple Burst
title: adidas D.O.N. Issue #6 Purple Burst
description:
The adidas D.O.N. Issue #6 Purple Burst is an ultra-sleek basketball shoe, with an extremely forward-looking design. Its kaleidoscopic color scheme immediately stands out from the rest.

Part of the Donovan Mitchell signature collection, it has all the hallmarks of top-class adidas basketball shoes. A key feature is the adidas Lightstrike technology, which creates an exceptionally lightweight midsole that's also extremely responsive to sudden changes of direction. Combined with a comfortable padded upper, this puts these shoes in the same realm as other adidas basketball icons.

Our experts rate these shoes very highly for their performance on court. They provide superior lateral support without the need for a high side wall. This gives a low-profile basketball shoe that provides a high degree of flexibility while still imparting stability. An accentuated midsole gives excellent arch support too. The adidas D.O.N. Issue #6 Purple Burst retailed at $120 upon its release on 5 July 2024.

name: Icons Yellow Strike
title: Nike Air Max 95 Icons Yellow Strike
description:
The Nike Air Max 95 Icons Yellow Strike arrives sporting a color scheme of white, Yellow Strike, Wolf Gray, and Cool Gray, crafted using a combination of materials, including mesh, suede, and nubuck.

The Yellow Strike Nike Air Max 95 Icons maintains its signature gray gradient on the suede overlays. It gradually transitions to a clean white palette, covering the nylon tongue construction and the mesh shroud surrounding it against a deep black backdrop. Vibrant pops of yellow emerge on the heel's embroidered Swoosh and the matching tongue tabs, while faded brown lace loops add a touch of contrast to the predominantly grayscale design. The sole unit is finished in sleek black for the former version, while the latter brown option extends its tone to the Air Max bubble underfoot, with insoles featuring "ICONS" branding.

What our experts love about the Nike Air Max 95 Icons Yellow Strike is the visible Air sole technology that offers responsive cushioning and impact protection underfoot. The technology consists of pressurized air pockets within the midsole, providing superior impact absorption and comfort for wearers. The sneaker debuted for $175 on May 9th, 2023.

name: WNBA Desert Camo (Women's)
title: Jordan 3 Retro WNBA Desert Camo (Women's)
description:
The Jordan 3 Retro WNBA Desert Camo (Women's) removes the signature elephant print and adds a colorway inspired by desert camouflage.

The camouflage pattern covers the entire upper and features splotches of Dark Driftwood, Sail, Hemp, and Velvet Brown. Satin and synthetic leather make up the upper, giving the WNBA Desert Camo (Women's) Jordan 3 Retro a slightly shiny finish without sacrificing durability. Like the OG sneaker from 1988, this version boasts visible air units in the heel that work with the foam cushioning to provide a responsive, supportive feel. Another notable feature is the soft textile lining the padded collar. It adds comfort and comes in a light-hemp hue.

Something our experts at StockX like is the addition of Brilliant Orange "JORDAN" lettering underfoot. It provides of pop of color and tonally matches the Jordan branding on the insole. The Jordan 3 Retro WNBA Desert Camo (Women's) was released on July 19, 2024, and sold for $200.

name: Brown Elephant
title: Jordan 1 Low SE Brown Elephant
description:
The Jordan 1 Low SE Brown Elephant comes in a subtle light beige and white color combination. The sneakers are defined by a color-blocked leather upper adorned with Jordan's unmistakable Jumpman and Wings logos, as well as Nike's iconic Swoosh on the side panels.

The Brown Elephant Jordan 1 Low SE upper begins with a classic white leather foundation and rugged brown suede overlays, extending from the mudguard to the heel section. The Swooshes feature a brown-on-brown elephant print, introducing the distinctive "Brown Elephant" element to the footwear. Additionally, black accents are found in the lining, rubber outsole, and Wings embroidery at the heel, finalizing the overall appearance of this fresh design.

What our experts find most appealing about the Jordan 1 Low SE Brown Elephant is its elephant print texture overlay on the upper. This distinctive pattern not only adds a touch of urban style, but also pays homage to the iconic design elements seen on classic Air Jordan models. The sneaker debuted on July 21st, 2023, for $120.

name: Hazy Green (Women's)
title: adidas Samba OG Hazy Green (Women's)
description:
The adidas Samba OG Hazy Green (Women's) is a modern take on the classic indoor soccer shoe, complete with an airy colorway of Cloud White, Wonder White, and Hazy Green.

Honoring its soccer roots, the Hazy Green (Women's) adidas Samba OG maintains several heritage design elements, including a low-to-the-ground silhouette and the iconic 3-Stripes logo on the side panels. The upper is crafted from leather and suede, with a Cloud White base and Wonder White accents on the toebox overlay and the heel mustache. The Hazy Green 3-Stripes logo matches the "adidas" branding and trefoils on the insole, while a metallic silver adidas logo graces the leather tongue and "SAMBA" decorates the outer side panel.

Our experts like the grippy gum rubber outsole. Not only does it provide traction, it also comes in a darker tone than traditional gum, giving the sneaker a contemporary upgrade. The women’s size adidas Samba OG Hazy Green (Women's) was released on June 1, 2024, and sold for $100.

name: White Black
title: adidas Adizero Evo SL White Black
description:
The adidas Adizero Evo SL White Black is a super-light (SL) running shoe boasting a sleek, racing-inspired look in a cloud white and core black color combo.

The Adizero Evo SL brings speed-inspired design into everyday life. The crisp white based is made of lightweight synthetic and textile materials. Large core black adidas stripes are emblazoned on the side panels and meld down into the chunky cloud white midsole. Adizero branding adorns the middle of the tongue in the form of a long tag while the adidas mountain emblem is on the heel in black. With a nod to environmentally friendly design practices, this shoe has a construction that includes at least 20% recycled materials.

In our opinion, the full-length Lightstrike Pro foam midsole would have to be the adidas Adizero Evo SL White Black’s best design feature. It offers responsive cushioning and energy return for all-day comfort. When it was released on October 25, 2024, this sneaker sold for $150 retail.

name: Pacific Moss
title: Nike Dunk Low Retro Pacific Moss
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Retro Pacific Moss dresses the legendary silhouette designed by Peter Moore in crisp, contrasting dual color blocking with a pop.

The upper of the Pacific Moss version of the Nike Dunk Low-Top Retro features a smooth white leather base with the classic perforations scattered across the toebox to enhance ventilation for comfort. Coppery brown leather overlays adorn the heel tab, heel counter, padded collar, midfoot, toecap, and eyestays. This leather also forms the side panel Nike Swoosh and matches the flat laces that offer a snug closure. The white mesh tongue has a coppery brown lining that matches the mesh sock liner. Nike branding hits the tongue tag and heel tab. The white foam midsole rests on a coppery brown rubber outsole with a pivotal traction pattern under the forefoot.

The stand out feature that we most enjoy on this pair of Nike Dunks is the subtle texture on the upper overlays that gives this sneaker an air of distinction. The Nike Dunk Low Retro Pacific Moss was released on May 7, 2024, for a retail price of $115.

name: Lunar New Year Pink
title: New Balance 1906R Lunar New Year Pink
description:
The New Balance 1906R Lunar New Year Pink was released ahead of Chinese Lunar New Year to celebrate the Year of the Dragon and the attributes associated with this zodiac sign.

The light pink colorway of Rosewood, Filament Pink, and Shell Pink represents one of the lucky colors of the dragon zodiac. The upper is made of nylon Ripstop mesh with crisscrossing shiny synthetic overlays. Like other models of the New Balance 1906R, the "Lunar New Year Pink" version finds inspiration in technical running shoes from the early 2000s. The ACTEVA LITE midsole provides responsive cushioning and contributes to the sneaker’s bulky silhouette. Other technical elements include an N-ergy outsole for absorbing shock and ABZORB SBS cushioning in the heel for stability.

Our experts like the inclusion of silver accents to break up the all-pink construction. The New Balance 1906R Lunar New Year Pink was released on January 1st, 2024, and retailed at $175.

name: Triple White (Women's)
title: Nike Air Force 1 Low Shadow Triple White (Women's)
description:
The women's Nike Air Force 1 Shadow Triple White (W) features a reconstructed white leather upper with monotone Swooshes and overlays. At the base, a thick white Air sole completes the design.

The women's Nike Air Force 1 Shadow Triple White (W) released in October of 2019 and retailed for $120.

name: Lilac (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Next Nature Lilac (Women's)
description:
Next Nature Lilac is a Dunk Low retro release. It is made of 20% recycled materials. 

The women’s Nike Dunk Low has a white leather upper with a perforated toe box. It also has lilac overlays, Swooshes, and laces. A purple Nike label appears on its white tongue. It also features a volt insole with a black Nike pinwheel logo. The purple heel cap includes an embroidered white Nike logo. A white rubber midsole matching its purple Grind rubber outsole completes the design.

The women’s Next Nature Lilac Dunk Low was released on July 1, 2022, retailing at $100.

name: Stealth (Women's)
title: Jordan 1 Mid Stealth (Women's)
description:
The Air Jordan 1 Mid Stealth W comes in a mixture of three main hues; stealth, white, as well as sail.

This Mid Air Jordan 1 for women is made of leather. Contrast is created between the sail foundation and the panels of stealthy grey which wrap all around heel, toe box, and ankle. The winged basketball image is debossed on this sneaker's collar. This shoe also has a Nike's Swoosh logo that boasts on medial and on the lateral sides. A solid grey rubber outsole and a white Air-cushioned midsole complete the design.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid Stealth W debuted on April 16th, 2021, with a suggested reatil price of $125.

name: Miami Hurricanes (GS)
title: Jordan 5 Retro Low Miami Hurricanes (GS)
description:
The Jordan 5 Retro Low Miami Hurricanes (GS) celebrates the University of Miami’s Miami Hurricanes with a colorway that matches the NCAA Division I football team’s colors.

Featuring the iconic 1990s silhouette designed by Tinker Hatfield, this version of the Air Jordan 5 boasts a leather and patent leather upper construction in Football Gray. The mesh on the quarter panels allows the foot to breathe, while plush padding around the collar protects the ankle. Inspired by fighter planes from WWII, this low-top sneaker boasts a shark tooth pattern on the two-tone polyurethane midsole. Visible Air-sole units provide cushioning, while the Jumpman logos come in Brilliant Orange and Football Gray.

Our experts at StockX like the placement of the Brilliant Orange and Pine Green accents. They are visible enough to celebrate the Miami Hurricanes without distracting from the sneaker’s heritage design. The grade school-sized Jordan 5 Retro Low Miami Hurricanes (GS) was released on June 6, 2024, and sold for $140.

name: Peach Cream (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Peach Cream (Women's)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Peach Cream W was made available as part of Nike’s 2022 fall collection.

The Peach Cream Nike Dunk Low for women has a two-toned design featuring a combination of peach cream and white in its colorway. The base of the shoe is all white while the Swooshes, shoelaces, front and rear panels, and durable outsole also have a peach-cream hue. It has an all-leather upper with a Swoosh logo on the medial and lateral sides, perforated toe boxes for breathability, a cushioned midsole, and tongue and heel branded with the Nike logo.

The Nike Dunk Low Peach Cream W was released on September 17, 2022, with its retail price at $100.

name: Phantom Volt
title: Jordan 1 Retro Low Golf Phantom Volt
description:
The "Jordan 1 Retro Low Golf" in Phantom Volt is a low-top golf shoe with a spikeless outsole that’s perfectly suited for a day on the golf course.

This version of the Air Jordan 1 Retro Low Golf comes in a black, white, Phantom, and Volt colorway. The white leather base with a perforated toebox features black leather overlays around the toe and laces. The Nike Swoosh appears on the midsole in black leather, while a light beige overlay appears on the heel. The Jordan logo appears on the heel in Phantom Volt, while the Jumpman logo appears on the tongue in the same color.

What we appreciate most about this sneaker is the simple colorway with the bright Phantom Volt accents. This shoe is just muted enough to go with any outfit while the bright accents add a touch of flair. The Jordan 1 Retro Low Golf in Phantom Volt was originally released on April 30th, 2023, for a price of $140.

name: Athletic Department Coconut Milk Medium Blue
title: Nike P-6000 Athletic Department Coconut Milk Medium Blue
description:
The Nike P-6000 Athletic Department Coconut Milk Medium Blue is part of Nike’s retro-inspired "Athletic Department." This technical shoe pays homage to the sneakers of the early 2000s, particularly the Nike Pegasus 25.

Unlike previous versions, the Athletic Department Coconut Milk Medium Blue boasts a neutral Sail and Coconut Milk base across the lightweight mesh upper. These light tones complement the bulky midsole and crisp laces. The sneaker features suede and leather details, including the Swoosh on the side panel and Photon Dust accents on the heel and toe. The lace cage connects to overlays stripping across the upper in six lines.

Our experts love the Electric Algae branding, including the "NIKE" lettering down the tongue, the tiny Swoosh on the heel, and the "P-6000" on the overlay. The Nike P-6000 Athletic Department Coconut Milk Medium Blue was released on March 20th, 2023, and retailed for $120

name: Verdy Visty
title: Nike SB Air Max Ishod Wair Verdy Visty
description:
The Nike SB Air Max Ishod Wair Verdy Visty is Japanese graphic artist Verdy’s take on American skateboarder Ishod Wair’s second signature shoe for Nike.

The Verdy Visty Nike SB Air Max Ishod Wair draws inspiration from Visty, a cute monster character created by Verdy. Specifically, the colorway pays homage to the character, including pastel color-blocking panels in Blue Gaze, Bicycle Yellow, and Light Arctic Pink. The mixed-material upper is crafted from suede, leather, and thin mesh, displaying layers of overlapping overlays. The suede increases the soft aesthetic and serves as a velvety base for the pastel hues. Adding comfort, Air Max units are housed in the heel and a layer of foam in the midsole protects against impact stress.

Our experts like the attention to detail, including Ishod Wair’s name embroidered along the eyelets. The Nike SB Air Max Ishod Wair Verdy Visty was released on September 20, 2024, and sold for $110.
model: Nike SB Air Max Ishod Wair

name: Banned (2020) (GS)
title: Jordan 1 Mid Banned (2020) (GS)
description:
The Kids Air Jordan 1 Mid Banned 2020 offers a mid-top take on Michael Jordan’s first signature shoe, the controversial Jordan 1 High Banned.

On the upper of the Kids Air Jordan 1 Mid Banned 2020’s ankle flaps, Swoosh, heel counters, and toe boxes are all constructed with red leather. Black laces, leather medial side and toe panels, and tongue create a contrasted look to the design. A white midsole and red outsole complete the design.

The Kids Air Jordan 1 Mid Banned 2020 released in November of 2020 and retailed for $90.

name: Black Cat (2020)
title: Jordan 4 Retro Black Cat (2020)
description:
Jordan Brand brings back a mid-2000’s classic with the Jordan 4 Black Cat (2020), now available on StockX. Originally debuting in 2006, this is the first time the Black Cat colorway has seen a retro. The fourteen year Black Cat drought has officially ended.

This Jordan 4 is composed of a black nubuck suede upper with matching detailing. Black hardware, netting, and outsoles complete the design. These sneakers released in January of 2020 and retailed for $190.

name: Black Opti Yellow
title: Nike Air Max Plus Black Opti Yellow
description:
The Nike Air Max Plus Black Opti Yellow is a performance shoe whose design was inspired by flames and beaches.

The Black Opti Yellow Nike Air Max Plus has a mesh upper that fades from a lighter Wolf Grey around the toe box and laces to a Black color around the bottom and heel. Curved shiny black TPU supports run vertically down the upper, resembling flames. A small Nike swoosh appears on each side in Opti Yellow, while a black mudguard and shiny black toe cap support the front half of the shoe. The heel counter is also black leather and features a Tuned Air logo. The design of the arch was inspired by the shape of a whale’s tail, and it also fades into Opty Yellow near the bottom. Air Max units are seen under the heel and forefoot.

Our favorite thing about this shoe is the whale’s tail arch design incorporating Opti Yellow, making it stand out. The Nike Air Max Plus Black Opti Yellow was released on October 22, 2024, for $170.

name: Metallic Silver Aegean Storm
title: Nike P-6000 Metallic Silver Aegean Storm
description:
Inspired by the 2006 Air Pegasus sneaker, the Nike P-6000 Metallic Silver Aegean Storm brings fresh color palettes to a breathable, comfortable shoe made for sport and street.

This ultra-comfy Nike P-6000 boasts an iconic design evocative of early 2000’s sneaker styles. With a mesh and textile outer, fabric lining, and rubber sole, this shoe has a white, blue, and silver color palette with faux leather detailing. The mesh panels keep feet cool, while the bold, rubberized Nike logo sits in blue with yellow stitching on the outer panels. The shoe's base is white with silver panelwork and blue stitching. With a midsole split between blue and off-white, the outsoles come with high-traction black rubber. The shoes have a front lace enclosure and are finished with a Nike logo emblazoned on the tongue.

We love the Greek-inspired coloring of these sneakers, which bring a breezy, fresh look to streetwear. The perfect blend of comfort and style delivers a shoe ideal for training and leisurewear alike. The Nike P-6000 Metallic Silver Aegean Storm was released on 6 November 2024, priced at $120 retail.

name: White Night Indigo Gum
title: adidas Samba OG White Night Indigo Gum
description:
The adidas Samba OG White Night Indigo Gum was originally designed as a soccer shoe, but has become a lifestyle staple. It features a preppy colorway of Core White with accents in Night Indigo and tan.

This sneaker boasts a retro-inspired design, with a T-shaped overlay across the toebox and heritage design elements, for example, the signature leather 3-Stripes logo in Night Indigo that graces the side panels. Other Night Indigo accents can be found on the leather heel tab, while the T-shaped overlays are crafted from tan suede. The base features Core White, which complements the Core White cotton laces. Paying homage to its retro roots, the sneaker has a gum rubber outsole with a waffle pattern on the forefoot area.

Our StockX experts like the adidas logo stamped on the leather tongue and SAMBA branding on the outer side panel because they give the sneaker a contemporary upgrade. The adidas Samba OG White Night Indigo Gum was originally released on March 5, 2024, and sold for $100.

name: MiUSA Grey
title: New Balance 993 MiUSA Grey
description:
The New Balance 993 MIU Grey features a gray suede upper with mesh underlays and white-on-gray New Balance logos. From there, cushioning pockets at the base of the heel and high-performance woven mesh on the forefoot complete the design.

The New Balance 993 MIU Grey released in November of 2019 and retailed for $175.

name: Fear Pack (2023) (GS)
title: Jordan 3 Retro Fear Pack (2023) (GS)
description:
A decade after its initial release, the Jordan 3 Retro Fear Pack (2023) (GS) makes a comeback, this time tailored for grade school kids.

A decade after its initial release, the design of the Fear Pack Jordan 3 Retro (2023) (GS) effortlessly merges tonal elephant print overlays with dark gray nubuck. The collar and tongue are adorned with black suede, highlighted by a Total Orange embroidered Jumpman logo Noteworthy Total Orange eyelets seamlessly merge with a Jumpman icon positioned on the back heel. Crafted for optimal comfort and longevity, the shoe incorporates an Air-sole unit tinged with orange and a polyurethane midsole that seamlessly blends three colors, presenting a fusion of performance and style.

The standout characteristic of the Jordan 3 Retro Fear Pack (2023) (GS) lies in its vibrant Total Orange highlights across the Air Unit, eyelets, and Jumpman branding. This daring color choice serves as a tribute to Jordan's bold and audacious spirit. The sneaker was originally sold for $150 on November 25th, 2023.

name: sacai Fragment Grey
title: Nike LD Waffle SF sacai Fragment Grey
description:
The Nike LDWaffle sacai Fragment Grey features a grey mesh upper with layered suede overlays and white leather doubled Swooshes. On the side of the doubled sole, both sacai and Fragment branding is printed in black. From there, a doubled tongue with woven labels completes the design.

The Nike LDWaffle sacai Fragment Grey released in August of 2021 and retailed for $170.

name: Legend Pink (TD)
title: Jordan 11 Retro Low Legend Pink (TD)
description:
The Jordan 11 Retro Low Legend Pink (TD) is a child-sized version of the Air Jordan 11 Retro Legend Pink that features a white base with light pink accents.

Although the Legend Pink (TD) Jordan 11 Retro Low is tiny, it boasts an upper crafted from ballistic mesh in white and a wavy patent leather mudguard in Legend Pink. White rope laces wind thread through the web eyelets, providing a secure fit. Like the adult-sized version, this iteration features a semi-translucent rubber outsole in Legend Pink. The outsole has grooves that provide additional traction. The heel and mesh tongue display Jumpman logos in Legend Pink, while a white Jumpman logo is on the insole.

Our StockX experts like incorporating tonal stitching, including the Legend Pink thread against the Legend Pink mudguard. The toddler-sized Jordan 11 Retro Low Legend Pink (TD) was released on June 22, 2024, and sold for $60.

name: Hunger
title: Nike Ja 1 Hunger
description:
The Nike Ja 1 Hunger is presented in various color combinations incorporating leather and ballistic mesh on its upper. The mesh covers its vamp and side panel, while leather material is featured on the majority of its upper.​
​
​This sneaker comes in game royal, university red, black, bright crimson, photo blue, and vivid orange color schemes. The mismatched design highlights the right foot's top in the game royal color scheme while emphasizing the left foot with a vivid crimson hue. The features a characteristic "Ja" marking with his number "12" on the heels as well as the hunger logo printed on its tongue in orange, with black letter scribbles on its heel counter completing the overall appearance.​
​​
​What we love about the Ja Hunger sneaker design is the foam midsole with speckles mirroring the mismatched color tones on the outsoles, a black wraparound TPU Swoosh, and the springy Zoom Air Unit on the forefoot, providing cushioning. The Nike Ja 1 Hunger was released on 25th May 2023. The sneaker initially retailed at $110.

name: Vanta
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 V2 Vanta
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 V2 Vanta features a muted, all-black mesh, leather, and suede construction in a styling influenced by 1990s running shoes. At the base, a Boost-cushioned sole adds comfort and support.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 V2 Vanta originally released in June of 2019 and retailed for $300.

name: Shadow Brown Alumina
title: adidas Handball Spezial Shadow Brown Alumina
description:
The adidas Handball Spezial Shadow Brown Alumina is a version of the shoe that was originally designed for handball courts in 1979.

This version of the adidas Handball Spezial features a paneled white leather upper. A white suede overlay rounds out the toebox and moves up the center toward the laces, while the adidas three stripes appear in light blue leather across both midsoles. SPEZIAL and the adidas trefoil logo can be seen in gold above the first stripe on the lateral side. The heel collar is also light blue leather, while there is another gold adidas logo on the tongue. A slim gum rubber outsole completes the look.

What we like most about this shoe is the slim and streamlined design, which allows for effortless street style and functionality. The adidas Handball Spezial Shadow Brown Alumina was initially released on February 10, 2024, for a price of $100.

name: Día de Muertos Pack Black
title: adidas Samba OG Día de Muertos Pack Black
description:
The adidas Samba OG Día de Muertos Pack Black is a low-top shoe with a rubber outsole for good traction, stability, and durability. These shoes are suitable for playing sports and casual wear. Their design is inspired by the Day of the Dead Holiday, which celebrates the memory of loved ones who have passed. In keeping with the theme, they are black-and-white with a dark brown sole.

These leather shoes are smooth and soft, giving them a high-quality look and feel. The signature 3-Stripes complete the look and give a nod to the adidas brand. adidas is a world leader in manufacturing athletic shoes and apparel.  

Our team is most impressed with the fancy stitching on the top and back of the adidas Samba OG Dia de Muertos Pack Black. In contrast, the white shoelaces complete the look. When released on September 27th, 2024, it originally retailed for $100.

name: Cool Grey (2021) (GS)
title: Jordan 11 Retro Cool Grey (2021) (GS)
description:
Like the original 2001 design, the gradeschool Air Jordan 11 Retro Cool Grey 2021 GS boasts a mid-top with a grey nubuck upper. This amazing colorway also boasts a white pylon cushioning boosted with a compact Air sole unit and strengthened with a translucent rubber outsole, an elegant "23" on its textile heel tab, and an embroidered white Jumpman logo on its lateral ankle.

The gradeschool Air Jordan 11 Retro Cool Grey 2021 GS was released on 12th November 2021. It retails at $185.

name: Dragon Red
title: Nike Dunk Low Retro Dragon Red
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Retro Dragon Red adds a twist to the Panda Dunk design with a tri-hue colorway of white, black, and Dragon Red.

Inspired by basketball shoes from the 1980s, the Dragon Red Nike Dunk Low Retro features a durable leather construction with a white base and a synthetic lining. The leather overlays, eyelets, and heel tab come in black, while the Swoosh logo, the ‘NIKE’ embroidery on the heel, the Nike branding on the tongue tag, and the rubber outsole come in Dragon Red. Perforations on the toebox increase airflow, while the rubber outsole features a pivot circle traction pattern for a grippy feel.

Our experts like the way the Dragon Red hue stands out against the black and white Panda color-blocking, adding contemporary elements to a heritage Nike design. The Nike Dunk Low Retro Dragon Red was released on August 1, 2024, and was priced at $115.

name: Parris Goebel (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low QS Parris Goebel (Women's)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low QS Parris Goebel (Women's) is a singular sneaker that represents a collaboration between the classic sports shoe company and the New Zealand dancer, artist, and choreographer Parris Goebel.

The Parris Goebel x Nike Dunk Low-Top Quick Strike Limited Release for Women sports an upper of matte bronze tumbled leather with overlays crafted from glossy pink leather. The side panel Nike swoosh is iridescent green leather with a metallic sheen. The sock liner is bright pink, contrasting with the green insole and yellow tongue tag. The midsole with its cup sole construction is made of sail-colored foam and rests atop a vibrant pink rubber outsole patterned for traction.

What we love most about this sneaker are the hits of branding. Upside-down Nike branding appears in green on the heel tab, pink on the tongue tag, and embossed on the outsole. Parris Goebel branding adorns the insole and a jeweled Nike swoosh functions as both a lace dubrae and a removable charm. The Nike Dunk Low QS Parris Goebel (Women's) was released on October 9, 2023, for retail price of $125.

name: White Mint (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Next Nature White Mint (Women's)
description:
Composed of 50% recycled materials, the women's Nike Dunk Low Next Nature White Mint (W) offers a more sustainable way to wear Dunks. The upper arrives in a simple white and Mint two-tone, color blocked look similar to some of the most popular Dunks to ever release. From there, matching soles and woven tongue labels complete the design.

The women's Nike Dunk Low Next Nature White Mint (W) released in the Spring of 2022 and retailed for $100.

name: Dark Iris
title: Jordan 3 Retro Dark Iris
description:
The Air Jordan 3 Retro Dark Iris is a high-top sneaker and comes in a white/black/Cement Grey/purple colorway.

The leather base is primarily white with purple highlights around the heel and on the ankle. The shoe also has a black interior, plus a black-and-gray elephant print overlay. The Air Jordan 3 Retro Dark Iris is completed with a white midsole and Cement Grey outsole. The shoe features the Jumpman logo on the tongue and heel, with the 'AIR' brand logo below the Jumpman.

The Air Jordan 3 Retro Dark Iris is set for release in August, 2022, at the retail price of $200.

name: Drake NOCTA Violet Haze
title: Nike Hot Step Air Terra Drake NOCTA Violet Haze
description:
The Nike Hot Step Air Terra Drake NOCTA Violet Haze draws its inspiration from streetwear and performance aesthetics.

Born from a collaboration between Nike and NOCTA, the sub-label co-founded by Canadian artist Drake, the shoe features an upper crafted from premium leather and synthetic materials. The midsole employs Nike’s Air technology for responsive cushioning, while a durable rubber outsole with a treaded pattern offers strong traction on a variety of surface types. NOCTA branding can be found on the tongue and heel, while Nike’s iconic Swoosh logo makes a subtle appearance on the shoe’s lateral side. Perforations along the sides allow for air flow for added comfort.

What our experts find to be a standout feature of the Nike Hot Step Air Terra Drake NOCTA Violet Haze is its solid Violet Haze colorway. This shoe originally retailed with a price tag of $180 when it was first released on November 18th, 2022.

name: Pure Platinum
title: Nike Air VaporMax 2023 Flyknit Pure Platinum
description:
The Nike Air VaporMax 2023 FlyKnit Pure Platinum sneakers are a part of Nike's VaporMax series. They are a neutral-colored model that are designed to provide support and comfort.

This Nike Air VaporMax model has a triple white body, with the Nike ‘Swoosh’ symbol appearing on the side with hints of platinum. Most of the shoe’s body is made from knit fabric that makes it sock-like and accommodates wide feet. The sole is one single unit. There is a gray and white heel tab at the back that helps the wearer to take the shoe on and off.

A feature that our group of experts love about the Nike Air VaporMax 2023 FlyKnit Pure Platinum is the plush cushioning of the Air-Sole that provides support and absorbs shock. This pair of shoes became available on May 18, 2023, for an initial starting retail price of $210.

name: Dark Green White (Kids)
title: adidas Campus 00s Dark Green White (Kids)
description:
The adidas Campus 00s Dark Green White (Kids) takes an iconic 80s silhouette, fashions it with a Y2K retro vibe, dresses it in collegiate colors, then sizes it specifically for kids.

The Kids’ version of the Dark Green White adidas Campus 00s features an upper constructed of deep green suede. The signature side-panel serrated three stripes in white leather match the wide flat laces to give the shoe bold color blocking. A white trefoil hits the green heel tab and the tongue, while adidas branding accents the dark green insole. The comfortable textile tongue lining and sock liner are also in white. The off-white foam midsole offers support and cushioning, while the gun rubber outsole sports of herringbone traction pattern. Campus branding in white hits the side panel, giving this shoe a distinct look.

Our favorite detail of this kids’ sneaker is the white stitching that courses across the green upper. This contrast pops and sets this sneaker apart. The adidas Campus 00s Dark Green White (Kids) was released on February 10, 2024, for $90 retail.

name: Better Scarlet (Women's)
title: adidas Samba OG Better Scarlet (Women's)
description:
The adidas Samba OG Better Scarlet (Women's) boldly reinterprets an iconic shoe with rich red colors that provide a subtle nod to its retro roots. This classic shoe combines age-old design with modern updates that blend into various settings.

The Better Scarlet Samba OG for women's by adidas gives you a smart design built with premium leather uppers, complemented by suede overlays for texture and longevity. Its vibrant scarlet hue dominates the design, paired with tonal accents and signature 3-Stripes branding in white for contrast. The gum rubber outsole provides a grip and a vintage aesthetic. This shoe was initially launched in the 1950s as a football trainer.

Something we, the experts, enjoy about the adidas Samba OG Better Scarlet (Women's) is its gum outsole, which gives you traction. Another standout detail is premium leather uppers, sweetening the shoe's longevity. It retailed at $100 when it was released on the 1st of September 2024.

name: Wonder Beige Tweed
title: adidas Samba OG Wonder Beige Tweed
description:
The adidas Samba OG Wonder Beige Tweed is a complete original. It takes the classic adidas Samba and gives it a look that would be most at home on a British country estate.

The adidas Samba has a well-deserved place in the pantheon of iconic shoes. This model takes one of the most popular casual trainers on the planet and gives it an English countryside colorway. The upper is made from authentic Harris Tweed and the usual Samba combination of leather and nubuck. If you look closely, you'll see that it's made up of forest green, mauve, brown, and off-white strands to create the classic tweed color.

This is one of the classiest Samba models we've seen. Our experts raved about its "English country gentry" look. If you're a fan of the model, this one is a definite collectible. It's a fine addition to the range and stands out among the many other colorways. The adidas Samba OG Wonder Beige Tweed was released on 5 September 2024 at a retail price of $100.

name: Sand
title: adidas Yeezy 500 High Tactical Boot Sand
description:
The adidas Yeezy 500 High Tactical Boot Sand is a heavy-duty, high-top boot whose design was inspired by the military. 
   
The Sand-colored adidas Yeezy 500 High Tactical Boot is made with a mix of neoprene-like mesh and premium suede. The padded ankle area alternates between these two materials, while suede forms the toe box, eyestays, and heel collar. adidas branding can be seen on the tip of the toe on a piece of the tan midsole that comes up onto the upper, and again on the inner side of the heel of the midsole. The midsole is enhanced with adiPRENE cushioning and has a chunky and curvy textured design. The outsole is a darker tan color. 

The most interesting thing about this shoe is the complete lack of branding on the upper, which is a refreshing take on this model. The adidas Yeezy 500 High Tactical Boot Sand was released on May 27, 2024, for $300.

name: Wings
title: Jordan 3 Retro Wings
description:
The Jordan 3 Retro Wings is an expansion of Jordan Brand’s Wings Scholarship Program, which provides educational opportunities for underprivileged youths. The proceeds from this limited-edition sneaker support Jordan Brand’s initiatives.

The Wings Jordan 3 Retro design features a classic elephant print on the heel and toe, as well as an upper crafted from denim twill and smooth leather in white. The denim twill displays a repeating pattern of roses, leaves, and stems that complements the delicate rose motif on the heel. The rose features pink petals with yellow-orange leaves and a thin stem. The rubber outsole in Rose provides traction underfoot and matches the floral theme, while air cushioning in the off-white midsole provides a responsive feel.

Our experts like the bold pops of University Red on the eyestays, the large Jumpman logo on the tongue, the outsole, and the insole. This hue unifies the colorway and breaks up the white base. The Jordan 3 Retro Wings was released on July 30, 2024, and sold for $210.

name: UNC White Dusk Blue (Women's)
title: New Balance 550 UNC White Dusk Blue (Women's)
description: The New Balance 550 UNC White Dusk Blue W is a sleek and stylish sneaker that combines classic design with modern materials. The upper is made from premium leather and features a clean white colorway with accents of dusk blue on the heel and branding. The midsole is crafted from durable rubber and provides excellent cushioning and support for all-day comfort. This sneaker is perfect for casual wear or for adding a touch of sophistication to any outfit. The release date for this shoe is January 8th, 2023, and with a retail price of $110. With its timeless design and high-quality construction, the New Balance 550 UNC White Dusk Blue W is a must-have for any sneaker enthusiast.

name: Ionic Photon Dust (Women's)
title: Nike Sabrina 1 Ionic Photon Dust (Women's)
description:
The Nike Sabrina 1 Ionic Photon Dust (Women's) is the first colorway featured on a signature basketball shoe created by Sabrina Ionescu, a WNBA all-star.

The sneaker pays tribute to the player’s Romanian-American heritage by including embroidered accents on the eyestays and forefoot. Although subdued, the stitched patterns resemble traditional Romanian architectural elements. While the upper is constructed from breathable mesh, the heel and tongue feature suede details. The quarter panel displays the recognizable Nike Swoosh stitched in an outline over translucent mesh. In addition, the sneaker houses a Zoom Air Unit in the forefoot and a Nike React midsole that stretches the full length of the shoe.

Something our experts love is the lowercase ‘i’ shape on the heel, which represents the first letter of the athlete’s last name. The women’s size Nike Sabrina 1 Ionic Photon Dust (Women's) was released on September 1, 2023, and retailed at $130.

name: MiUSA Grey
title: New Balance 990v3 MiUSA Grey
description:
The New Balance 990v3 Grey 2019 is one of the 2019 releases by shoe manufacturer New Balance.

The New Balance 990v3 Grey 2019 comes in grey and features a leather upper section. The upper part is also made of mesh patches in grey. In addition, the shoe has an ENCAP midsole cushioning with a lightweight foam combined with a rim made of durable polyurethane. The shoe also has white laces for a secure fit and the New Balance logo on both sides.

The New Balance 990v3 Grey 2019 was released on 1st October 2019 to retail at $165.

name: Winterized Black (2023)
title: Jordan 6 Rings Winterized Black (2023)
description:
The Jordan 6 Rings Winterized Black (2023) offers an all-weather version of the iconic silhouette that fuses elements from different Air Jordans in order to pay homage to MJ's 6 NBA championships.

The Winterized Black iteration of the Jordan 6 Rings features an upper crafted from black ballistic mesh. This is overlaid with water-resistant black leather at the toebox, mudguard, and heel. Black rope laces thread through sturdy metal eyelets that stem from long metal eyestays to provide a secure fit across the entire foot. The black foam midsole encapsulates Air for cushioning, while the black rubber outsole is deeply grooved for all-weather, all-terrain traction.

The aspect of this sturdy sneaker that we most enjoy is the one hit of non-black on the upper, a light brown Jumpman logo and Air branding that hits the heel. The Jordan 6 Rings Winterized Black (2023) was released on September 30, 2023, for $185 retail.

name: University Gold
title: Nike Dunk Low University Gold
description:
The Nike Dunk Low University Gold combines tradition and innovation in this iteration of the iconic silhouette designed by Peter Moore and launched in 1985.

The University Gold Coconut Milk colorway of the Nike Dunk Low-Top features traditional color blocking on the upper. The signature overlays from the heel to the toecap and the side-panel Nike Swoosh are crafted from tumbled leather in a rich University Gold. This eye-catching hue is echoed in the laces, tongue lining, and sock liner. The embroidered Nike branding on the heel tab matches the foam midsole that provides both cushioning and support. This stylish and comfortable sneaker rests atop a light brown gum rubber outsole that offers shock absorption and grip with every step.

The aspect of this sneaker that we most enjoy is the upper base, which is made of a Coconut Milk-colored hemp textile instead of the more traditional leather. This twist makes this Dunk Low stand out. The Nike Dunk Low University Gold was released on June 8, 2024, for $125 retail.

name: Seafoam (Women's)
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Seafoam (Women's)
description:
The women's Air Jordan 1 High Seafoam (W) arrives in a smooth white leather construction with Seafoam Durabuck overlays and Swooshes. On the laces, crisp bronze trimming stands out against the design's subtle coloration.

The women's Air Jordan 1 High Seafoam (W) released in August of 2021 and retailed for $170.

name: Oatmeal (Women's)
title: Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Oatmeal (Women's)
description:
The Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Oatmeal W has become a celebrated addition to the women´s catalog.

This Vomero Nike Zoom model comes dressed in an Oatmeal, Sail, Pale Ivory, and Light Chocolate color scheme. The shoe features a tonal upper constructed of an open mesh base paired with leather overlays and Swooshes. Other design details include the plastic side panels and heel counter, 3M reflective hits, and the Bill Bowerman motif stamped onto the insoles, all in while atop Zoom Air cushioning.

The Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Oatmeal W was made available on December 7th, 2022, retailing at $160.

name: Ivory
title: New Balance 530 Ivory
description:
Since its launch in 1992, New Balance 530 Ivory has become a popular unisex sneaker due to its performance running shoe design.

New Balance 530 Ivory's upper is made of synthetic leather, while the midsole is produced through a cold cement process. New Balance 530 Ivory's design is ivory, white, and black, with a style code of MR530SH. The sneaker weighs 339 grams (12 oz.) and features a lace-up closure. New Balance 530 Ivory also features the New Balance "N" logo on its quarter panel.

New Balance 530 Ivory became available on July 5, 2022, at a retail price of $80.

name: LA
title: Nike Dunk Low SE LA
description:
The Nike Dunk Low SE LA is a special edition sneaker that captures the relaxed yet elevated aesthetic of one of the West Coast’s most iconic cities.

The LA Nike Dunk Low SE boasts a mixed-material upper with a canvas-like base painted in a color gradient, fading from Baltic Blue to creamy Sail. These refreshing hues are reminiscent of the sandy shores, blue skies, and ocean waters of LA’s Venice Beach and Manhattan Beach. Providing a complementary touch, the suede overlays come in Sail and match the eyelets, heel, and laces. The Baltic Blue heel tab displays"NIKE" in cloud-like lettering, while a cloud pattern also decorates the tongue. Adding a splash of Pale Ivory, the Swoosh logo checks across the side panel.

Our experts at StockX appreciate that the tongue and the side panels feature the same color gradient pattern. The Nike Dunk Low SE LA was released on October 26, 2024, and sold for $125.

name: Indigo
title: ASICS Gel-NYC Indigo
description:
The ASICS Gel-NYC Indigo is a low-top performance shoe with an upper supported by layers of colorful overlays. 
   
The Indigo ASICS Gel-NYC has an upper made of white mesh for breathability. Hairy suede overlays in different shades of blue cross almost the entire upper, providing durable support. Indigo and Navy overlays form the toecap, mudguard, and eyestays, and also cross the sides in the classic ASICS stripes pattern. The heel is also supported by these overlays, and Gel branding can be seen at the back. ASICS branding is seen in white under the lateral ankle and again on the tongue. The white midsole is enhanced with Gel technology for comfort and energy return, and the look is completed by a black outsole.

What we love most about this shoe are the way the overlays truly support the foot where it’s needed most: around the side panels and ankle area. The ASICS Gel-NYC Indigo was released on May 16, 2024, for $140.

name: Union Sail Leather
title: Jordan 1 Retro AJKO Low SP Union Sail Leather
description:
The Air Jordan 1 Retro AJKO Low SP Union Sail Leather is a sneaker that came as a result of a collaboration between Jordan Brand and Union LA.

The Air Jordan 1 Retro AJKO Low SP comes in a color scheme featuring a blend of Sail, black, and Muslin-Neutral Grey. The upper is made of Sail canvas and is complemented by tone-on-tone overlays, as well as a suede Nike Swoosh in black. Additionally, the shoe is adorned with a UN/LA tag, with the Union LA monogram located behind the comma, and finished off with yellow stitching on the forefoot.

The Air Jordan 1 Retro AJKO Low SP Union Sail Leather was released on 2nd February 2023 with its retail price set at $150.

name: White Dusty Blue
title: New Balance 550 White Dusty Blue
description:
The New Balance 550 White Dusty Blue is an iteration of the original New Balance P550 that focused on performance on the basketball court. These retro sneakers provide an air of nostalgia while adding modern technology to this classic design.

This sneaker is constructed with a white leather upper that is perforated on the toebox and the lower part of the midsole. Gray suede overlays appear on the toebox and near the ankle. Dusty Blue lines the ankle and heel and appears on the rubber outsole. New Balance branding is visible in Dusty Blue on this New Balance 550’s white heel, on the midsole, and on the tongue.

What we like most about this sneaker is the advanced technology combined with a vintage design. Extra cushioning and support enhance performance, while the design itself reflects a basketball era of the past. The New Balance 550 White Dusty Blue was released on June 21st, 2023, for a retail price of $120.

name: Black (Women's)
title: Nike Air Rift Breathe Black (Women's)
description:
The Nike Air Rift Breathe Black W is a stylish and comfortable athletic shoe featuring a sleek black and cool grey design with white accents.

Women's Black Air Rift Shoes are crafted with breathable materials to ensure maximum comfort during intense workouts or casual wear. It has a black and cool grey color scheme and white accents that add a touch of contrast. Its distinctive split-toe design and hook-and-loop strap details ensure a secure and personalized fit for every step. Emphasizing style and comfort, the shoe features Nike Air cushioning in the heel, providing impact absorption, while the plush foam midsole offers a soft feel.

At StockX, we can't get enough of the shoe’s innovative split-toe design! It's not just a style statement; it optimizes foot flexibility and enhances natural movement, making it a favorite among our experts. Coupled with the hook-and-loop strap details and plush foam midsole, it delivers unparalleled comfort and support. The Nike Air Rift Breath Black W was released on 25th February 2019 and retailed at $100.

name: Graffiti (2023)
title: Nike Zoom LeBron 4 Graffiti (2023)
description:
The Nike Zoom LeBron 4 Graffiti (2023) is a limited-edition sneaker that was created by Nike in collaboration with LeBron James and was initially released in 2006.

The sneaker features a University Red, Black, and White colorway with bold graffiti graphics that dominate the side. The graphics feature black and white lettering inspired by the graffiti written across the walls of New York City. A black and red ankle collar secures the foot and features a white mini-Swoosh outlined in red, while an exaggerated pull tab adorns the heel. The sneaker also comes with a responsive Zoom Air unit in the midsole and a plastic casing that adds stability.

Our StockX experts love the translucent red detailing on the outsole. It provides traction while allowing you to see the graffiti designs on the midsole. The Nike Zoom LeBron 4 Graffiti (2023) was released on September 19, 2023, and retailed at $240.

name: Bubblegum
title: Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 Bubblegum
description:
The Nike Air Force 1 Low ’07 Bubblegum updates the Air Force 1 Low ’07 silhouette with a bubblegum-inspired colorway of Pink Rise and white.

Although the sneaker maintains its classic ’80s construction, the use of premium materials and candy-inspired colors offers a contemporary upgrade. The upper is crafted from white leather with durable, tonal stitching on the overlays. Pink Rise accents grace the Swoosh logos, the rubber outsole, the heel tab, and the "NIKE AIR" lettering on the woven tongue tag. Like the OG model, the Bubblegum iteration features a collection of perforations on the vamp and two holes on each side panel. These perforations allow the foot to breathe and are a heritage design element.

Our experts at StockX like the inclusion of lightweight Nike Air cushioning in the foam midsole. The Nike Air Force 1 Low ’07 Bubblegum was released on January 20, 2024, and sold for $115.

name: Joe Freshgoods When Things Were Pure Black Ice
title: New Balance 1000 Joe Freshgoods When Things Were Pure Black Ice
description:
The New Balance 1000 Joe Freshgoods When Things Were Pure Black Ice is part of a collaboration between New Balance and Chicago-based designer Joe Freshgoods.

Like other items in the collection, this sneaker celebrates the nostalgia of the Y2K era while looking to the future. The sneaker boasts a technical silhouette with ABZORB cushioning in the bulky midsole. One of the sneaker’s contemporary updates is a loose weave mesh across the upper, instead of mesh with small, tight holes. While the midsole, leather details, and mesh come in black, the fortifying leather overlays feature an iridescent brown that appears to change color depending on the lighting. Branding details include a small leather "N" on the side panel, "JFG" embroidered on the overlays, and dual branding on the tongue.

Our StockX experts love the vivid green color of the sockliner. The New Balance 1000 Joe Freshgoods When Things Were Pure Black Ice was released on April 11, 2024, and retailed at $170.

name: Wales Bonner Core Black
title: adidas Samba Pony Tonal Wales Bonner Core Black
description:
The adidas Samba Pony Tonal Wales Bonner Core Black is a collaboration between the iconic German sneaker company and the London-based luxury fashion house.

The Wales Bonner X adidas Samba Pony Tonal Core Black features an upper with a base made of black faux pony hair. The overlays are luxe black leather with cream-colored leather at the heel tab and the side panel three stripes. The cream color appears again on the tongue that folds over the laces. Dual branding for adidas and Wales Bonner appears on the insoles and the tongue tag. The laces are also cream, providing further contrast to the black-on-black of the upper.

What our shoe experts enjoy most about this sneaker Is its sole unit, which is characteristic of the adidas Samba. The die-cut Eva foam of the midsole provides cushioning and impact absorption while the gum rubber outsole provides traction. The adidas Samba Pony Tonal Wales Bonner Core Black was released on November 8, 2023, for a retail price of $160.

name: Conchiolin
title: Nike LeBron 21 Conchiolin
description:
The Nike LeBron 21 Conchiolin is a performance basketball shoe with signature Nike technologies that support high-energy movements and cushion against impact stress.

In fact, support is one of the main themes of this sneaker. It finds inspiration in conchiolin, a protein secreted by clams and other mollusks that helps them build their strong shells and assists in the process of forming pearls. Other pearl-inspired elements include the durable leather upper, which comes in an iridescent white that mimics the inside of a clamshell or a pearl. In addition, crease lines look like the veining inside a clamshell, and the perforations are similar to holes found on some shells. In terms of technology, this sneaker boasts mesh details with 360-degree zonal cabling and responsive Zoom Air units in the heel.

Our StockX experts like the extra-strong rubber outsole, which provides traction on various surfaces. The Nike LeBron 21 Conchiolin was released on December 19, 2023, and sold for $200.

name: Strawberry Waffle
title: Nike Dunk Low Retro SE Strawberry Waffle
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Retro SE Strawberry Waffle takes an iconic silhouette and embellishes the design in order to pay homage to Bill Bowerman, the Nike co-founder who came up with the heritage waffle outsole pattern when he was coaching track. This sneaker is then dressed in a playful colorway.

The upper base of this low-top is crafted from wheat-colored suede that sports perforations at the toebox and padding at the collar. Pale Vanilla leather overlays reinforce the toe and heel and add support to the midfoot and eyestays. Tumbled red leather is used to create the Nike Swoosh on the quarter panel, as well as the heel tab with a white embroidered Nike word mark. The wheat-colored suede tongue sports a waffle-patterned tongue tag with Nike branding. Flat red laces and a red mesh sock liner match the rubber outsole that underlies a Sail foam midsole.

The standout detail of this sneaker that we most appreciate is the stylized side panel. Pale Vanilla leather is overlaid with a waffle-pattern cage fashioned from wheat-colored suede. The Nike Dunk Low Retro SE Strawberry Waffle was released on August 20, 2024, for a retail price of $125.

name: CO.JP Neutral Grey (2020)
title: Jordan 1 Retro High CO.JP Neutral Grey (2020)
description:
For the first time since 2001, Jordan Brand has brought back the Air Jordan 1 Retro High CO Japan Neutral Grey, now available on StockX. The Air Jordan 1 CO.JP originally released as a Japanese exclusive in very limited quantities. Only 2,001 pairs were released in the Neutral Grey colorway while other colorways were produced as an edition of 3,000. After 20 years, the CO.JP was reborn and finally released globally.

The Air Jordan 1 CO Japan Neutral Grey features a grey suede and silver leather upper with a bubble "Wings" stamp just like the 2001 version. The main difference between the 2020 iteration and its predecessor is in the tongue, where the updated pair features "Nike Air" embroidered on the tongue instead of the 2001s’ Jumpman tag.

The Air Jordan 1 CO Japan Neutral Grey released in August of 2020 and retailed for $170.

name: Hello Kitty (GS)
title: adidas Gazelle Hello Kitty (GS)
description:
The adidas Gazelle Hello Kitty (GS) decks out the familiar Gazelle silhouette with motifs and colors inspired by the Japanese cat character.

As part of a collaboration between adidas and Sanrio, this grade-school version of the Gazelle celebrates Hello Kitty’s 50th anniversary. The white leather upper displays debossed hair bows, inspired by one of Hello Kitty’s favorite accessories. Hello Kitty’s face graces the heel, while a small, red bow decorates the leather heel mustache. The serrated 3-Stripes logo comes in bright red, complementing the exposed stitching on the heel mustache. Other noteworthy features include the Hello Kitty branding on the tongue and tiny white bows along the laces. Completing the look, a suede toe box overlay in beige protects the toe, while the dark rubber outsole matches the black accents.

Our experts at StockX like the dual adidas and Hello Kitty branding printed in metallic gold on the insole. The adidas Gazelle Hello Kitty (GS) was released on October 1, 2024, and sold for $85.

name: Wheat
title: Nike Air Max 90 Premium Wheat
description:
The Nike Air Max 90 Premium Wheat is a sneaker with a design was inspired by the 90s, featuring a simple look and a waffle outsole.

This style of the Nike Air Max 90 Premium is made with a suede base on the upper in a Wheat Brown colorway. Suede overlays of the same color create a paneled look, while pleated rubber accents appear under the laces and just above the arch. The rubber above the arch also contains the Air Max logo. The Nike Swoosh appears on both sides of the shoe, while the heel also contains rubber accents with the Nike air logo. The tongue is cushioned and contains a Nike patch. Visible Air Max units sit under the heel within the rubber outsole.

Our favorite thing about this sneaker is the monochromatic look. The mix of materials all in the same colors gives the shoe unique visual appeal. The Nike Air Max 90 Premium Wheat was released on October 23, 2022, for a price of $150.

name: Wet Putty 2.0
title: Nike Air Force 1 Low Wet Putty 2.0
description:
The Nike Air Force 1 Low Wet Putty 2.0 is an ideal street shoe. It's a real looker, and it's extremely comfortable. If you want an unusual colorway in one of the world's most sought-after trainers, this is one to go for.

This model in the iconic Nike Air Force 1 range lives up to its unusual name. You instantly recognize the look of wet putty. The oily green upper is made from shiny patent leather, with a neon orange swoosh and a translucent carrot-colored sole. It has the classic low Air Force silhouette.

We like the wet putty look and the striking contrast of the vivid orange shades. The patent leather look adds even more flair, making the trainer come alive. Of course, there's all the comfortable cushioning that comes with all shoes in the Air Force 1 range. The Nike Air Force 1 Low Wet Putty 2.0 was released on 1 September 2024, priced at $135.

name: Oreo
title: Puma LaMelo Ball MB.02 Oreo
description:
The Puma LaMelo Ball MB.02 Oreo is part of the second collaboration between NBA player LaMelo Ball and Puma. What makes the sneaker stand out is the recognizable "Oreo" colorway, which features black and white details on the upper with Oreo speckling along the midsole.

Shiny TPU overlays catch the light and complement the side panel wings, inner lining, and synthetic laces. Boasting a sleek silhouette, the sneaker houses Nitro foam in the midsole that is both lightweight and responsive for performance. In terms of branding, LaMelo Ball’s "1" wings and halo logo are on the tongue and up the heel. "M.E.L.O" and a small Puma insignia also grace the back of the shoe.

Our experts love how the etched tread overlaps the midsole, creating a wrapping effect. The Puma LaMelo Ball MB.02 Oreo was released on August 11, 2023, and retailed for a price of $130.

name: Bite
title: Nike Ja 1 Bite
description:
The Nike Ja 1 Bite is a dynamic basketball shoe created through the collaboration of NBA star Ja Morant and Nike. This stylish shoe delivers high-octane capabilities on the court.

The upper of the Ja Morant x Nike Bite sneaker features a mesh upper in shades of red stardust.
