This lightweight, breathable, flexible feel is supported by midfoot lockdown in the form of a tonal synthetic overlay that integrates into the lacing system. A black side panel Nike Swoosh adds a hit of dark contrast. A guardrail above the midsole helps ensure foot stability during landings and takeoffs. The foam midsole in blocks of white and speckled brown encapsulates Zoom Air under the forefoot for springy propulsion. A black rubber outsole hearkens back to the Nike Swoosh to tie together the look of this shoe.

What we enjoy most about this pair of kicks are all the hits of Ja Morant branding, including his number 12 on the heel tab, his signature on the lateral heel, and his initials on the tongue tag. The Nike Ja 1 Bite was released on February 1, 2024, for a retail price of $120.

name: Kith Cream Scarab (2024)
title: ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Kith Cream Scarab (2024)
description:
The ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Kith Cream Scarab (2024) is New York–based fashion house Kith’s take on the iconic Gel-Kayano 14. Bringing a toned-down look, this sneaker features an off-white Cream base with overlays in Scarab and shiny metallic silver.

The upper of the Kith Cream Scarab (2024) ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 is crafted from lightweight mesh with synthetic leather overlays that streak across the side panels. The sneaker boasts heritage Kayano features, including extra padding around the collar and ASICS form stripes on the side panels. The visible EVA Gel midsole provides cushioning, while the rubber outsole increases traction on a variety of surfaces.

Our experts at StockX like the contrast between the dark Scarab on the overlays and midsole and the metallic silver accents. While metallic silver is a throwback to early 2000s running sneakers, the application of Scarab is a contemporary addition. The ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Kith Cream Scarab (2024) was released on March 28, 2024, and sold for $160.

name: Dark Slate
title: adidas Yeezy 450 Dark Slate
description:
With a simplified two-piece construction, the adidas Yeezy 450 Dark Slate features Dark Slate foam sole that clasps a monochromatic sock-like Primeknit upper. From there, thick rope laces add the finishing touches.

The adidas Yeezy 450 Dark Slate released in June of 2021 and retailed for $200.

name: Dark Beetroot
title: Nike Air Max 95 Dark Beetroot
description:
While originally designed for more powerful runners, the Nike Air Max 95 Dark Beetroot sneaker, and brainchild of Sergio Lozano.

The Nike Air Max 95 Dark Beetroot silhouette boasts a black-to-grey gradient on the upper, black and white mesh panel eye stays, and burgundy-colored lace loops. To complete the anatomy-inspired aesthetic are mini Swoosh embroideries on the heel, "Air Max" labeling on the tongue, and an air bubble on the midsoles. It has dark burgundy hit with cutting-edge, anatomy-inspired aesthetics.

The Nike Air Max 95 Dark Beetroot sneaker was released in September 2022, retailing at $185.

name: Chicago Lost and Found (TD)
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Chicago Lost and Found (TD)
description:
The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG Lost and Found TD features a mixture of four dominant colors: muslin, varsity red, sail, and black.

The upper part of this sneaker for toddlers (TD) is made of a white leather material that has a cracked finish, which is also visible on the black leather collar. There are red leather overlays on the shoe's upper part and a white midsole atop a red outsole finish its look. The signature Air Jordan's Wings emblem is found on the right upper side, with a similar emblem featuring on the left upper side of the left. AIR units are included in the soles.

The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG Lost and Found TD had a suggested retail price of $70 during its launch on 19th December 2022.

name: Brown Pink (Women's)
title: adidas Gazelle Indoor Brown Pink (Women's)
description:
The adidas Gazelle Indoor Brown Pink (Women's) comes in a soft colorway of brown and pink with off-white accents, bringing to mind Neapolitan ice cream.

Harking back to its indoor training roots, the Brown Pink (Women's) adidas Gazelle Indoor features a low-top design and a sleek silhouette. The upper boasts a velvety soft suede build, with a tonal overlay across the toebox in the same material. While the leather heel mustache comes in pastel pink, the iconic serrated 3-Stripes logo is made from off-white leather. The brown tongue reveals "ADIDAS" lettering and trefoil in metallic gold, which complements the " GAZELLE" lettering printed along the 3-Stripes. Adding a final touch, brown laces thread through the front closure system.

Our experts like the small perforations on the tongue because they provide an airy feel and keep the foot cool. The women’s size adidas Gazelle Indoor Brown Pink (Women's) was released on June 1, 2024, and retailed at $120.

name: Protection Pack Black
title: New Balance 1906D Protection Pack Black
description:
The New Balance 1906D Protection Pack Black comes in an all-black color scheme.

The New Balance 1906D Protection Pack Black features a black colorway with white detailing. The upper is constructed from a mixture of mesh and durable leather for lightweight sturdiness and breathability. The shoe's midsole features both ABZORB and C-CAP technologies for comfort and protection against impact. The shoe also has a rubber outsole for grip and wear resistance. The sneaker features an "N" logo on either side and "NB" branding on both the tongue and heel.

The New Balance 1906D Protection Pack Black was released on January 6th, 2023, and retailed for $165.

name: Spring Green
title: Nike P-6000 Spring Green
description:
The Nike P-6000 Spring Green finds inspiration in the Nike Air Pegasus from 2006 but gives this retro-inspired sneaker a contemporary upgrade with a white base and electric Spring Green and metallic silver accents.

On the Spring Green Nike P-6000, the breathable mesh upper features real and synthetic overlays in Springs Green and metallic silver that reinforce the sneaker’s 2000s look. However, the signature tiger stripe overlays also provide the function of supporting the shoe’s lightweight construction and lace system. The front lace closure houses strong black and white laces that thread through loops and perforations. In addition, the full rubber outsole provides a no-slip grip on a variety of surfaces.

Our experts at StockX like the way the Spring Green stitching around the black Swoosh logo complements the panel of tonal mesh on the sides and the splashes of Spring Green on the foam midsole. The Nike P-6000 Spring Green was released on March 20, 2024, and sold for $110.

name: Light Smoke Grey
title: Nike Ja 1 Light Smoke Grey
description:
Unveiled on August 11, 2023, the Nike Ja 1 Light Smoke Grey is where dominance on the court meets modern design and style. This signature sneaker’s design is inspired the dynamism of NBA's rising star, Ja Morant, this sneaker is a fresh fusion of cutting-edge design and athletic prowess.

Sporting a fresh Light Smoke Grey, the Nike Ja 1's design pushes boundaries. The upper combines breathable mesh with dynamic leather overlays, ensuring agility and support on every jump and pivot. The sleek design is punctuated by a bold Nike Swoosh. While both sneakers boast the same base hue, there’s a twist: the left and right shoes subtly mismatch in their color schemes, giving a unique edge to those quick on-court turns and off-court flexes. The embroidered "12" on the heel? That’s not just any number. It signifies the jersey number Ja rocks on the court, symbolizing the spirit of a new basketball generation.

But this shoe isn’t all about aesthetics. Fused with cutting-edge cushion tech and an advanced grip pattern on the sole, it's the future of basketball footwear. These dropped on August 11, 2023, for an attainable retail of $110.

name: Hyperspace
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Hyperspace
description: Try not to dress like a hypebeast after copping the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Hyperspace. This Yeezy Boost 350 comes with a grey upper, grey translucent stripe, grey midsole, and a Grey sole. These sneakers released in March 2019 and retailed $220. Make some space for some new Yeezys and Buy these now on StockX.

name: Bred Sail (Women's)
title: Jordan 1 Low Bred Sail (Women's)
description:
The Jordan 1 Low Bred Sail (Women's) takes the recognizable Jordan 1 Low from 1985 and applies a bold color-blocking pattern with Black, Gym Red, and Sail.

The shoe features a Black and Gym Red calf leather construction, but Black is the dominant hue. Gym Red leather accents include the Swoosh across the side panels and the perforated vamp. In addition, the Air Jordan branding details on the heel and the Jumpman motif on the tongue come in Gym Red. Like other Jordan 1 Low models, this iteration boasts a low-top design, a round toe, and a laced-up fastening on the front.

What do our experts like about this women’s-sized sneaker? While the midsole comes in subdued Sail, the rubber outsole comes in Gym Red. This detail adds cohesion to the shoe and a pop of color underfoot. The Jordan 1 Low Bred Sail (Women's) was released on May 5th, 2023, and retailed at $90.

name: Silver Toe (Women's)
title: Jordan 1 Elevate Low SE Silver Toe (Women's)
description:
The Air Jordan 1 Elevate Low SE Silver Toe W has become a celebrated addition to the women's catalog.

This low-top sneaker features a black leather upper with semi-reflective silver accents in the area around the Nike Swoosh and toe. The shoe also boasts a Jordan Wings logo stamped behind the ankle and a classic Jumpman emblem stamped on top of the tongue. Nike Air technology in the non-slip white rubber sole along with stitching details around the top of the midsole complete the design.

The Air Jordan 1 Elevate Low SE Silver Toe W was released on October 19th, 2022, at a retail price of $130.

name: Red Stardust (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Red Stardust (Women's)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Red Stardust (Women's) is a women’s exclusive Dunk Low in a Red Stardust colorway.

This Dunk Low features an all-leather upper with a white base and Red Stardust overlays on the mudguard, eyestays, heel, and tongue tab. Rugged Orange hues on the Swooshes, sock liner, and tongue lining contrast the upper. Other details include an embroidered ‘NIKE’ wordmark on the heel tab, white laces, a perforated toebox, and more Nike branding on the tongue tag and insoles. Underfoot, a clean white midsole rests on a Rugged Orange rubber outsole. 

What our experts particularly love about this Nike Dunk Low is its unique color scheme and construction. The color blocking gives it a distinctive and eye-catching appearance, while the quality materials used in its build guarantee comfort and durability. The Nike Dunk Low Red Stardust (Women's) was released on November 18th, 2023, for a retail price of $115.

name: Wash Orange
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Wash Orange
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Wash Orange features a grey leather, suede, and mesh upper with teal panels and reflective underlays. At the base, a thick Wash Orange Boost midsole contrasts cool tones found in the upper.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Wash Orange released in October of 2021 and retailed for $250.

name: Limestone Black
title: Nike ACG Rufus Limestone Black
description:
The Nike ACG Rufus Limestone Black is a unique slipper that has now made a comeback after about a decade.

This model of the Nike ACG Rufus is made with a seamless suede upper in a Limestone tan color. The only design seen on the upper is a small Nike Swoosh embossed into the lateral side. The midsole is black rubber that dons a wavy texture near the bottom, and speckled Limestone tan forms the thick outsole, fully enclosing the black midsole. A small black Nike swoosh appears on the front tip of the outsole. The midsole has foam cushioning for extra comfort.

Our favorite thing about this shoe is the unique black midsole unit that contrasts nicely with the Limestone color of the rest of the shoe. The Nike ACG Rufus Limestone Black was first released on May 10, 2024, for an initial retail price of $110.

name: Blue Glaze Total Orange (Women's)
title: Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Blue Glaze Total Orange (Women's)
description:
The Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Blue Glaze Total Orange (Women's) combines different materials to create a layered look reminiscent of early 2000s running shoe aesthetics. This colorful, sporty shoe is specifically sized for women.

The Blue Glaze Total Orange color scheme of the Women's Nike Zoom Vomero 5 has an upper that sports a base of tightly woven black mesh. Overlays in textile and synthetic leather in shades of black and white course over the upper, providing foot support as well as a vintage aesthetic. A side-panel Nike Swoosh in white and orange stretches across a light blue TPU cage. A white foam midsole offers Zoom Air cushioning and rests atop the black rubber pods of the grippy outsole. Orange and reflective hits pepper this upper, giving it bright accents both day and night.

The aspect of this sneaker that we most enjoy is the black plastic heel counter that features ventilation ports in its lattice work, providing comfort and structure. The Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Blue Glaze Total Orange (Women's) was released on March 8th, 2024, for a retail price of $180.

name: Paisley Pack Pink (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Essential Paisley Pack Pink (Women's)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Essential Paisley Pack Pink W is a variation of the classic Nike Dunk Low.

The Nike Dunk Low has a low-profile silhouette with its upper combining a stark white leather base with soft pink overlays at the toe cap, the foxing, the mudguard, and the eye stay panel. The signature profile Swooshes in Paisley print glide across both the lateral and medial mid-panels as well as the heel tabs. To top it off, it has a white midsole and a pink rubber outsole.

The Nike Dunk Low Essential Paisley Pack Pink for women was released on 7th February 2023 with its retail price set at $110.

name: White Football Grey
title: Nike Free Metcon 5 White Football Grey
description:
The Nike Free Metcon 5 White Football Gray is a workout shoe designed for mobility, lifting, or high-intensity cardio exercises. It features a light colorway of white, Football Gray, and Ashen Slate with accents in Sundial – a warm, yellow hue.

At the White Football Gray Nike Free Metcon 5, the wide heel provides support during lifting, while the internal webbing in the midfoot adds comfort and stability during sudden, lateral movement. The 7/8 inner sleeve provides a sock-like fit and locks the foot in place. In addition, the upper is crafted from breathable mesh, and soft foam around the collar supports the ankle without restricting movement. While white and Football Gray dominate the upper, splashes of Sundial can be found on the Swoosh logo embedded beneath the heel and the lace loops.

Our experts at StockX like the Nike Free technology in the forefoot because it supports natural movement. The Nike Free Metcon 5 White Football Gray was released on April 1, 2024, and sold for $120.

name: Vintage Indigo
title: New Balance 9060 Vintage Indigo
description:
The New Balance 9060 Vintage Indigo is a technical running shoe with a bulky, exaggerated midsole that gives it a futuristic aesthetic inspired by sneakers from the 2000s.

The 9060 model takes elements from the iconic 990 series, including visible technology and wavy etchings on the midsole. The sneaker boasts a grey-tone colorway of Arctic Grey, Steel, and Vintage Indigo. The upper is made from mesh with soft suede overlays overlapping and fusing to the midsole. To create effective cushioning and energy return, the midsole houses both ABZORB and SBS technology. The sneaker has minimal branding, including the New Balance "N" on both side panels, "NB 9060" printed on the tongue tag, and a small "N" below the laces.

Our experts love the semi-translucent plastic heel counter that separates the suede from the midsole. The New Balance 9060 Vintage Indigo was released on September 23rd, 2023, and retailed at $150.

name: Electric Green Black
title: Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Electric Green Black
description:
The Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Electric Green Black is a limited edition sneaker, which is a part of Nike's Zoom Vomero 5 series.

The Electric Green Black Nike Zoom Vomero 5 features a black and green colorway and an upper that is made of a combination of soft textile and breathable mesh materials. The shoe also features a supportive midfoot cage and the midsole is designed to provide cushioning and shock absorption, boasting Nike's Zoom Air technology. The outsole is made of rubber to provide traction on a range of surfaces.

The Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Electric Green Black was released on April 17, 2019 at a retail price of $160. They were re-released on June, 7th 2024.

name: What The
title: Nike KD 15 What The
description: DISCLAIMER: There is variance amongst this product.  Buyers may receive the shoes as shown in our images otherwise they will receive a pair where the right and left shoes are swapped. In the latter case, the right shoe will have a pink toe and the left toe will be purple.

name: White Picante Red
title: Nike Air Zoom GT Cut 3 White Picante Red
description:
The Nike Air Zoom GT Cut 3 White Picante Red is designed for creating space for step back jumpers, back door cuts, and all the game-changing plays you strive for throughout all four quarters.

The upper of the White Picante Red Nike Air Zoom GT Cut 3 features a stretchy white breathable material meant to move with your foot across the court. Red deco stitching covers the forefoot and matches the tint of the side-panel Nike Swoosh. White synthetic overlays are perforated to provide ventilation, even as they offer lockdown foot support. A full-length the ZoomX foam midsole offers cushioning and springy energy return, and includes a plate at the pinky toe for stability. The rubber outsole has a modified herringbone traction pattern specifically designed for stopping on a dime and making lateral cuts on the court.

The stand-out feature of this shoe that catches our eye is the dual-color blocking on the sole unit. The forefoot of the sole unit is bright red, while from the midfoot to the heel, the midsole and outsole are Snowy White. The Nike Air Zoom GT Cut 3 White Picante Red was released on January 13, 2024, for $190 retail.

name: Beige Sail (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Next Nature Beige Sail (Women's)
description:
Nike applies a Sail and Hemp color scheme to its beloved '80s basketball silhouette, offering a more environmentally friendly reinterpretation of Peter Moore's iconic 1985 design in the Nike Dunk Low Next Nature Beige Sail (Women's).​
​​
​The Next Nature Beige Sail Nike Dunk Low for women features a Hemp-colored base with airy toe perforations, accompanied by overlays in the Sail colorway that beautifully complements the backdrop. The upper is completed with flat laces and a lightweight tongue. Following the tradition of its predecessors, the Nike Dunk Low Next Nature incorporates synthetic leather made from recycled polyester. To top it off, this release is finished with a two-toned rubber outsole that provides full-length cushioning.​
​​
​What our experts love about the Nike Dunk Low Next Nature Beige Sail (Women's) is its strong commitment to eco-conscious design. This sneaker is a shining example of Nike's dedication to sustainability and responsible manufacturing. It embraces a more environmentally friendly approach by using materials that prioritize ecological impact reduction. The sneaker debuted for $110 on August 30th, 2023.​
​​
​

name: Triple Black
title: New Balance 1906U Triple Black
description:
If you're a black-only person when it comes to shoes, the New Balance 1906U Triple Black will be ideal. Its monochrome colorway looks slick, giving it a designer edge that many multi-colored trainers out there can't quite match.

The triple black colorway of this New Balance trainer has a sleek, stealthy look, with only slight variations in its shades. It has a tough ripstop base with leather overlays. The heels have protective TPU cushioning. This cousin of the New Balance 1906R is all about utility. A further plus is that the outsoles are purportedly made from recycled materials.

We're thrilled that New Balance has released such a minimalist trainer. All the high-tech we expect from the brand is there in a lightweight package that's entirely focused on functionality. Its chunky sole has high grip capabilities, and its uppers are breathable. The New Balance 1906U Triple Black was released on 18 July 2024, priced at $155.

name: Duck Honey Dew
title: Nike Air Max 1 PRM Duck Honey Dew
description:
The Nike Air Max 1 PRM Duck Anthracite was a special edition sneaker from the Ugly Duckling collection.

Dressed in a mix of honeydew, anthracite, kumquat, and black color scheme, this shoe features an upper constructed with premium suede materials. Supple black highlights the base, with anthracite hits covering most of the center panel and heel. The mudguard and lining opt for a tonal kumquat, while honeydew accents the Swooshes, laces, and the embroidered duck motif on the heel. A white midsole with AIR units atop a honeydew-speckled outsole rounds out the design.

The Nike Air Max 1 PRM Duck Anthracite made its debut on December 20th, 2022, retailing at $160.

name: Atlanta
title: Nike Air Max 95 Premium Atlanta
description:
The Nike Air Max 95 Premium Atlanta was designed in collaboration with four different Atlanta-based retailers: Walter's, SolePlay, A Ma Maniere, and Wish ATL. This vibrant shoe pops with contrast and a few subtle surprises.

The Premium Atlanta iteration of the Nike Air Max 95 sports an upper base of lightweight and breathable gray mesh. This is overlaid with undulating strips of suede in gradient shades of orange to red. A gray leather overlay on the toecap adds support and protection, matching the webbing eye stays that feature reflective detailing. A black Nike Swoosh at the collar matches the foam midsole, which holds visible units of orange-tinted Air for ultimate cushioning. This sneaker rests atop a dark orange rubber outsole with deep lugs that provide traction and shock absorption.

Our favorite aspect of this Atlanta sneaker is the gray leather heel tab. It sets this shoe apart with its detailed graphic of a phoenix above ATL branding. The Nike Air Max 95 Premium Atlanta was released on April 4, 2024, for $185 retail.

name: Chrome
title: Jordan 6 Retro Chrome
description:
The Air Jordan 6 Retro Chrome is crafted from a tumbled leather, synthetic nubuck and synthetic textiles, with a color palette of black and metallic silver.

This Retro Air Jordan 6 comes in a black/metallic silver-chrome colorway. The sneaker has a mid-top mounted on a black polyurethane midsole, highlighted with metallic silver accents and supported by a translucent rubber outsole. The shoe has a branding of silver Jumpman on the lace guard. It also has a windowed tongue, lace locks, and a spoiler-like heel tag.

The Air Jordan 6 Retro Chrome was released on the 26th of November 2022 and retailed for an price of $200.

name: JJJJound Tobacco
title: adidas Samba OG JJJJound Tobacco
description:
The adidas Samba OG JJJJound Tobacco represents a collaboration between adidas Originals and the Montreal design studio JJJJound. The result is an elegant iteration of a classic silhouette originally designed for the football pitch.

The upper of this classic-silhouette JJJJound Tobacco adidas Samba OG features a base crafted from tan-gold hairy suede. This same luxe suede is used for the T-toe and eyestays overlay. Nubuck in a warm brown shade forms the signature serrated 3-stripes on the side panel as well as the heel tab. Flat warm brown laces cross over a suede tongue, locking in the complementary colorway. JJJJound branding hits the insole. A gum rubber sole unit features a textured sidewall and a grippy outsole.

Our favorite aspect of this posh lifestyle shoe is the JJJJound gold foil branding on the outer side panel that takes the place of the usual Samba branding. The adidas Samba OG JJJJound Tobacco was released on June 27th, 2024, for $160 retail.

name: Black Metallic Gold
title: Nike LeBron 20 Black Metallic Gold
description:
The Nike LeBron 20 Black Metallic Gold showcases gold accents thoughtfully incorporated into its design. These refined gold details grace the "XX" dubrae (lace aglets), the "XX" branding on the tongue, and the uppermost eyelets. At the heel of the shoe, you'll find LeBron James' signature patch, which signifies his endorsement and personal touch on the design.

The upper of the Nike LeBron 20 Black Metallic Gold is crafted from a black knit material, providing a lightweight and breathable feel. The upper offers flexibility and comfort, making it suitable for intense on-court action. The Nike Swoosh logos on each side of the shoe are presented in a striking Metallic Gold finish. The outsole is constructed from a translucent material.

What truly captivates our experts is the midsole of the Nike LeBron 20 Black Metallic Gold, which is predominantly in white with black specks. It incorporates advanced cushioning technology, ensuring responsiveness and impact protection during gameplay. The Nike LeBron 20 Black Metallic Gold was released on April 6th, 2023, available for purchase for $200.

name: Shadow Purple
title: New Balance 9060 Shadow Purple
description:
The New Balance 9060 Shadow Purple upgrades the New Balance 9060 silhouette with a smokey colorway of Shadow and Purple with an off-white midsole.

The upper is breathable mesh in Shadow with overlapping pigskin overlays in Purple. The overlays create a mudguard and a lace cage housing thick, off-white laces. The sneaker features a bulky, retro design augmented by the ABZORB midsole and SBS cushioning, which protect against impact. The side panels display the signature New Balance "N" in silver and a jewel New Balance logo on the tongue’s logo tag. Other branding features include the "NB" lettering on the heel and the "N" on the durable rubber outsole.

Our StockX experts like how this sneaker pays tribute to the New Balance 860 while adding contemporary upgrades. The New Balance 9060 Shadow Purple was released on July 9, 2022, and retailed for a price of $150.

name: Moment (GS)
title: Puma LaMelo Ball LaFrancé Amour Moment (GS)
description:
In grade school sizes, the Puma LaMelo Ball LaFrancé Amour Moment (GS) is an athletic shoe featuring a chunky silhouette paired with a monochrome aesthetic in Alpine Snow’s cream shade. A canvas heel collar accents the leather upper and insets on the side. An oversized midsole features embossed branding, as does the heel pull tab. The sole features inlaid Puma LaFrancé branding, which also appears on the tongue.

German brand Puma is the third largest sneaker brand in the world, founded in 1948. LaMelo LaFrance Ball is an NBA player for the Charlotte Hornets. Puma tapped Ball to collaborate on a series of lifestyle sneakers evocative of his eccentric style yet varied from his signature performance line with the brand.

In our opinion, the best features of the shoes are their oversized styling and abrasion-resistant soles. The Puma LaMelo Ball LaFrancé Amour Moment (GS) was released on July 19, 2024, and retailed for $95.

name: Panda
title: Jordan 1 Mid TD Cleat Panda
description:
The Jordan 1 Mid-TD Cleat Panda is a high-top performance shoe engineered for speed, with the classic monochrome "Panda" color blocking.​
​​
​The Jordan 1 Mid-TD Cleat Panda elevates its design by incorporating key elements from the AJ1, including the synthetic leather details in the upper and Jet Black overlays that enhance durability against abrasion. The sneaker has football-inspired elements, including specific gridiron aesthetics underfoot, wide stud placement ensuring traction on the field, and an external midsole that provides long-lasting cushioning. These contrasting details serve as a finishing touch to the overall design and cater to the demands of football.​
​​
​A notable feature our shoe experts highlight about the Panda Air Jordan 1 mid-sneaker is the white tread on the outsole that distinguishes it from the low tops. The Jordan 1 Mid-TD Cleat Panda was released on June 9th, 2023. Upon its release, its retail price was set at $150.​
​​
​

name: Black
title: New Balance 1906A Black
description:
The New Balance 1906A Black deconstructs the iconic sneaker from the early 2000s and adds a monochromatic colorway.

At first glance, the silhouette looks like the 1906R; however, the similarities end there. The black New Balance 1906A boasts an asymmetrical design with quality mesh and textile materials. While the loose weave mesh comes in black, the leather overlays feature a combination of black and Dark Silver Metallic. Displaying cut-off ends, two black ribbons form the signature New Balance "N" logo on the side panel. These ribbons and the exposed stitching on the upper give the sneaker a DYI look. The ACTIVA LITE midsole houses ABZORB SBS and N-ergy cushioning, providing comfort and advanced energy return.

Our experts at StockX like the tongue tag because it draws attention from the branding and is different from traditional labels. The New Balance 1906A Black was released on October 5, 2024, and sold for $170.

name: Ambient Sky
title: adidas Campus 00s Ambient Sky
description:
The adidas Campus 00s Ambient Sky arrives in an Ambient Sky, Footwear White, and Off-White color palette.

The Ambient Sky adidas Campus 00s features an upper that is constructed from a combination of materials, including leather overlays and suede panels. The shoe's midsole is made of lightweight EVA foam, providing cushioning and responsiveness. The shoe's outsole is crafted from durable rubber, offering traction and grip. The shoe features the signature adidas 3-Stripes branding on the lateral sides. The sneaker features the "CAMPUS" inscription on one side, and the adidas Trefoil logo on the heel and tongue.

The unique feature of the adidas Campus 00s Ambient Sky is its nostalgic 2000s-inspired design. These sneakers pay homage to the retro aesthetics of the 2000s era, featuring a vibrant and bold colorway with a mix of sky blue and pink accents. The adidas Campus 00s Ambient Sky was released on July 16th, 2022, and sold for a retail price of $100.

name: Chicago Lost and Found (PS)
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Chicago Lost and Found (PS)
description:
The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG Lost and Found PS comes in a mix of different tones, with varsity red, black, sail, and muslin being the dominant color schemes.

The leather top of the Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG Lost and Found for pre-schoolers (PS) features scarlet overlays at its forefoot as well as on the heel, and it also has a white foundation on the heel with a black signature Swoosh. This sneaker also has a white lacing system and the Wings logo on the sides, as well as Air unit soles.

The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG Lost and Found PS was released on November 19th, 2022 with a retail price of $85.

name: Brown Blue Grey
title: Jordan 1 Retro Low SE Brown Blue Grey
description:
The Jordan 1 Retro Low SE Brown Blue Gray dresses the iconic silhouette designed by Peter Moore in an elegant colorway that pops with understated contrast.

The upper of the Brown Blue Gray Jordan 1 Retro Low-Top Special Edition features a base of smooth white leather overlaid with glossy smooth brown leather at the heel, eyestays, vamp, and toecap. For comfort enhancement, this upper is padded at the collar and perforated at the toebox. An off-white foam midsole houses Air in the heel for support and cushioning. The black rubber outsole that provides multi-directional grip calls back to the black laces and black sock liner to tie the look of this shoe together.

The feature of this classic sneaker we appreciate the most are the hits of steel blue that adorn the upper. A Wings logo is embroidered on the heel, a Jumpman logo is embroidered on the tongue, and the classic side-panel Nike Swoosh is crafted in a steel blue knit. The Jordan 1 Retro Low SE Brown Blue Grey was released on February 14, 2024, for $125 retail.

name: Phantom Metallic Gold (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Phantom Metallic Gold (Women's)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Phantom Metallic Gold W has become a celebrated addition to the brand's women´s catalog.

The upper section of this Low Phantom Nike Dunk model features a cream-colored leather base with perforations in the toe box and light grayish-tan leather overlays. The midsole matches the base and the grayish-tan outsole matches the overlays. The color metallic gold appears on the Nike Swoosh as well as the Nike branding on the heel and tongue. The grayish-tan insole features cream-colored Nike branding.

The Nike Dunk Low Phantom Metallic Gold W was released on November 1st, 2022 for a retail price of $110.

name: N7 (2024)
title: Nike Air Max 1 '87 N7 (2024)
description:
The Nike Air Max 1 '87 N7 (2024) incorporates heritage motifs and prints celebrating Indigenous American culture and history across North America into the Air Max 1’s signature design.

The N7 (2024) Nike Air Max 1 '87 showcases a combination of light, almost pastel hues with vibrant splashes of Bright Mandarin and Dusty Cactus underfoot. The canvas upper features suede overlays in Light Bone and a black suede mudguard with traditional-style stitching in an off-white thread. The prominent stitching speaks to the long history of threadwork and textile craftsmanship across North American Indigenous communities. The sneaker boasts visible Air Max units in the heel, and signature 'AIR MAX' branding in black thread on the heel counter.

Our experts at StockX like the way the touches of Bright Mandarin and Dusty Cactus on the rubber outsole provide a visual enhancement to the durable, waffle traction pattern. The Nike Air Max 1 '87 N7 (2024) was released on June 21, 2024, and sold for $160.

name: Black Flint
title: Jordan 13 Retro Black Flint
description:
The Jordan 13 Retro Flint is making its return in 2023, with the release of the Air Jordan 13 Retro Black Flint. ​
​
​The Jordan 13 Retro Black Flint is dressed in black, white, red, and Flint Grey. The Jordan 13 is constructed using leather, suede, and reflective mesh across the uppers. The sneakers are tied together with white laces, while a red Jumpman logo sits on top of the tongue. A holographic eye sits on the outer heel.
​​
​The Jordan 13 Retro Black Flint released April 22, 2023, with a retail price of $200.

name: Clay Brown
title: adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Clay Brown
description:
Yeezy returned to the Earth-toned palette with the Yeezy 700 V3 Clay Brown. The Clay Brown slightly resembles the Alvah with its primarily black look. But instead of a completely muted upper, it dons lighter earth tones, adding contrast throughout the silhouette.

The Yeezy 700 V3 Clay Brown features a black engineered mesh upper with light brown streaks running along the side encompassed by a signature translucent cage unit. A thick EVA foam midsole, reinforced toe cap, and 3M detailing on the forefoot complete this futuristic look.

The Yeezy 700 V3 Clay Brown released in December of 2020 and retailed for $200.

name: Wales Bonner Leopard
title: adidas Samba Nylon Wales Bonner Dark Brown
description:
The adidas Samba Pony Wales Bonner Leopard represents a collaboration between the iconic German sneaker company and the luxury fashion brand. The resulting shoe combines a singular style with a classic silhouette.

The upper base and overlays of the adidas Samba Pony Wales Bonner Leopard are luxe leather in a caramel and dark brown marbled pattern reminiscent of a leopard. The heel tab and tongue that fold over the laces are both creamy white leather that matches the signature three stripes along the side panel. The heel tab and tongue sport exaggerated looped stitching and the three stripes feature dark brown stitching. The textile sockliner is light blue while the insole is creamy white. This distinctive-looking upper rests upon a gum rubber sole unit patterned for traction and impact absorption.

What our experts enjoy most about this sneaker is the refined dual branding. But the insole and the tongue have "adidas" with the trefoil logo and "Wales Bonner" underneath in a clean, linear presentation that emphasizes the elegance of this shoe. The adidas Samba Pony Wales Bonner Leopard was released on November 8, 2023, for $160.

name: NBA 75th Anniversary Chicago
title: Nike Dunk Low EMB NBA 75th Anniversary Chicago
description:
In celebration of the 75th Anniversary of the NBA, Nike teamed up with the NBA to release a Chicago Bulls-themed Nike Dunk Low.

The Nike Dunk Low EMB 75th Anniversary Chicago features a Sail leather upper with a red toe wrap and black overlays. From there, a commemorative NBA logo woven tongue tags and matching sole completes the design.

The Nike Dunk Low EMB 75th Anniversary Chicago released in October of 2021 and retailed for $110.

name: Summit White Concord
title: Nike Air Max 180 Summit White Concord
description:
The Nike Air Max 180 Summit White Concord is a reissue of the iconic Air Max 180 designed by Tinker Hatfield in 1991. In comparison to other reissues, this shoe more closely resembles the OG sneaker with its understated design and retro-inspired colorway.

The Summit White Concord Nike Air Max 180 is outfitted with a Summit White base and accents in metallic gold and Bright Concord. Grape-purple Concord appears on the midsole wedge, the outsole, the collar, and the flat tongue, while metallic gold stands out on the Swoosh logos and the "NIKE AIR" embroidery on the heel. The upper construction combines suede and mesh, drawing inspiration from the original shoe. However, the sneaker includes several modern upgrades, including a larger 180-degree Air unit underfoot.

Our experts like the way the gold Swoosh pays tribute to Team USA’s men’s basketball victory at the 1992 Barcelona Olympics. The Nike Air Max 180 Summit White Concord was released on August 7, 2024, and sold for $150.

name: Be True Hyperflat
title: Nike Dunk Low Be True Hyperflat
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Be True Hyperflat is a low-top basketball shoe featuring a metallic multicolor look.

This iteration of the Nike Dunk Low is made with a matte silver upper as the base. Matte silver dominates the midsole and the toebox, which is perforated for breathability. Iridescent overlays adorn the shoe around the toebox, under the laces, and around the heel. These overlays appear in shiny purple, red, pink, and yellow, with the ones around the toebox having a square pattern. The Nike Swoosh appears on the midsoles in an Iridescent Yellow color. The heel features a multicolored heel tab with the Nike brand name written across in purple wavy lettering, reminiscent of the hippie era. The tongue features a Nike branding patch and a pull tab with the words "BE TRUE TO YOUR DNA."

What we like most about this shoe is its iridescent nature, because even though different colors are present, the look of the shoe can change depending on how the light hits. The Nike Dunk Low Be True Hyperflat was released on September 9, 2023, for a retail price of $115.

name: sacai Fragment Blue Void
title: Nike LD Waffle SF sacai Fragment Blue Void
description:
The Nike LDWaffle sacai Fragment Blue Void combines the best of both sacai and Fragment's aesthetics. The mesh, leather, and suede construction of the LDWaffle represents sacai's experimental outlook, while the black and Blue Void palette is more reserved, similar to the utilitarian look that many of Fragment's collaborations have.

The Nike LDWaffle sacai Fragment Blue Void released in August of 2021 and retailed for $170.

name: Magic Beige (Women's)
title: adidas Gazelle Indoor Magic Beige (Women's)
description:
The adidas Gazelle Indoor Magic Beige (Women's) continues the Gazelle legacy with a neutral colorway of Magic Beige, Cloud White, and Gum.

Originally imagined as an indoor soccer shoe, the Gazelle Indoor in beige and white has transformed into a lifestyle shoe known for its premium construction. The upper boasts soft suede in Magic Beige with Cloud White accents on the leather details. For instance, the signature serrated 3-Stripes logo and the heel mustache come in Cloud White. Heritage elements, including the grippy gum rubber cupsole and the 3-Stripes, pay tribute to the Gazelle legacy. Finally, branding details in metallic gold round out the look on the outer side panel and the tongue.

Our experts like the color switch-up on the laces and tongue—they feature Magic Beige instead of Cloud White. The women-sized adidas Gazelle Indoor Magic Beige (Women's) was released on May 11, 2024, and sold for $120.

name: Coconut Mauve (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Next Nature Coconut Mauve (Women's)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Next Nature Coconut Mauve (Women’s) is a low-top women’s basketball shoe made with sustainable practices in mind.

This iteration of the Nike Dunk Low is made with a white synthetic leather upper, while the toebox has been perforated for breathability. Synthetic leather overlays in Coconut Milk round out the toebox, run up under the laces, and down around the heel. The Nike Swoosh appears on the midsoles in a Smokey Mauve color. The heel also contains a Coconut Milk heel tab with the embroidered Nike brand name also in Smokey Mauve, while the tongue contains a Nike branding patch. The white outsole with Smokey Mauve on the bottom completes the look.

What we like best about this women's shoe is the sustainable practices that were used to make it out of synthetic material. The Nike Dunk Low Next Nature Coconut Mauve (Women’s) was released on February 20, 2024, for a list price of $115.

name: Neutral Olive
title: Nike Air Max 90 Neutral Olive
description:
The Nike Air Max 90 Neutral Olive dresses the Air Max 90 with mixed-material panels in neutral, earthy tones. Originally made for performance running, this sneaker maintains its classic 1990s silhouette and boasts exposed Air Max units in the heel.

Although leather dominates the upper, soft suede and plastic accents create a texture contrast in the Neutral Olive Nike Air Max 90. In addition, the Light Bone, Medium Olive, and Neutral Olive hues add an extra dimension to the sneaker’s silhouette. In terms of branding, the signature Swoosh logo and rubberized ‘NIKE AIR’ branding on the heel come in black, while the ‘AIR MAX’ branding on the side panel’s ribbed plastic piece comes in Neutral Olive. A leather 'NIKE AIR MAX' label brings additional branding to the padded tongue.

Our experts at StockX like the low-cut collar, which features thick yet sleek padding that protects the ankle. The Nike Air Max 90 Neutral Olive was released on January 20, 2024, and sold for $130.

name: Lakeside
title: Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Lakeside
description:
Nike introduced the original Zoom Vomero running sneaker to the world all the way back in 2006, and the company has continued to put out new versions of it ever since. The brand first unveiled the Zoom Vomero 5 in 2010 as part of its "Bowerman Series," and it makes its return more than a decade later in the form of the Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Lakeside. It's one of the many new Zoom Vomero 5 colorways that Nike released in 2024.

This Nike Zoom Vomero 5 has a mesh and leather upper that is covered in a Lakeside colorway along with TPU overlays situated on its sides and heels. This same bright blue color also covers everything from the tongue and laces to the inner lining and even the rubber outsole on the shoe.

Our experts like the Lakeside colorway on this sneaker, but they also love the 3M reflective accents scattered all over it. It makes them shine in low-light situations and adds another cool decorative touch to them. The Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Lakeside was released on January 1, 2024, for a $160 retail price.

name: Safari Summit White Phantom (Women's)
title: Nike Air Max 1 '87 Safari Summit White Phantom (Women's)
description:
The Nike Air Max 1 '87 Safari Summit White Phantom W is a sneaker design in women sizing that draws inspiration from the original Air Max 1, released in 1987.

  The upper of the Safari Summit White Phantom Nike Air Max 1 '87 W is made using a combination of leather, suede, and textile. The sneaker features a supportive heel cup, reinforced toe box, and the visible Air unit that provides cushioning and comfort with every step.

We think that the standout feature of the Nike Air Max 1 '87 Safari Summit White Phantom W is the iconic speckled Safari print on the mudguard and heel, which is inspired by the original Air Max 1 released in 1987. The Summit White and Phantom colorway of the shoe, combined with the Safari print, creates a unique and eye-catching design. The Nike Air Max 1 '87 Safari Summit White Phantom W was released on March 3rd, 2023 at a retail price of $150.

name: Dark Earth Mushroom
title: New Balance 327 Dark Earth Mushroom
description:
The New Balance 327 Dark Earth Mushroom paints the 327 in an earthy colorway of Mushroom and Dark Earth. This sneaker boasts a low-top design with minimal padding around the collar and a flat tongue.

This simple running sneaker finds inspiration in heritage running shoes in the New Balance Catalog from the 1970s. Like the OG version, it features a classic wedge silhouette and premium materials. Contemporary upgrades include the oversized New Balance N on the side panels, which comes in white and disappears beneath the midsole and the laces. Using a lightweight, slightly shiny material, the upper is inspired by the 320 and the 355 styles. Like the 355, this New Balance sneaker boasts a rubber outsole that completely wraps over the heel. The rubber outsole comes in black and offers trail-inspired lugs.

Our experts at StockX like the contrast between the synthetic base in Dark Earth and the suede overlays in Mushroom. The New Balance 327 Dark Earth Mushroom was released on October 1, 2023, and retailed at $100.

name: Seasonal
title: Nike Ja 1 Seasonal
description:
The Nike Ja 1 Seasonal is a shoe designed in collaboration with Memphis Grizzlies basketball star Ja Morant with a springtime colorway.

This version of the Nike Ja 1 features an upper made of mesh in an off-white Coconut Milk color. This mesh material forms the toe box and sides of the shoe up to the ankle. Coconut Milk leather overlays form the mudguard and connect the forefoot to the laces. These overlays are also perforated for breathability on the inside of the shoe. The Nike swoosh wraps around the heel and appears on both sides in white. The heel is brown, with perforations on one side revealing a Coconut Milk color underneath, while the other side is solid and features red stitching for Ja Morant’s branding. The number 12 appears in black on the top of the heel, and Ja’s logo appears on the tongue. A Coconut Milk and light blue sole and outsole complete the look.

What we love most about this shoe is the handwritten elements on the heel, adding a personal touch. The Nike Ja 1 Seasonal was released on April 1, 2024, for $140.

name: Gore-Tex JJJJound Pine
title: New Balance 2002R Gore-Tex JJJJound Pine
description:
The New Balance 2002R Gore-Tex JJJJound Pine is a collaboration between the iconic sneaker company and the menswear design collective founded in Montreal by Justin R. Saunders.

The New Balance x JJJJound 2002R Gore-Tex Pine features an upper with a rugged base of tightly woven black mesh. This is overlaid with thick mottled green suede strips that bolster the upper at the toe cap, eyestays, quarter panel, collar, and heel. The signature side panel N puffs out in black leather and features reflective detailing. Black rope laces with a black lace lock add to the rugged look of this upper. Dual branding adorns the black heel counter, and Gore-Tex branding appears above 2002R debossed branding at the outer collar. This durable upper rests on a black ABZORB midsole with an SBS ABZORB unit in the heel for ultimate cushioning over rugged terrain. The black rubber outsole is deeply lugged for multi-surface traction.

What we appreciate most about this rugged pair of kicks is the Gore-Tex inner bootie designed to keep your foot dry. The New Balance 2002R Gore-Tex JJJJound Pine was released on February 15, 2024, for $190 retail.

name: Glow Green
title: adidas Yeezy Slide Glow Green
description:
Constructed of bright Glow Green EVA foam, the adidas Yeezy Slide Glow Green provides lightweight durability with a luminous look. From there, strategic groove placement on the underfoot enhances traction and comfort.

The adidas Yeezy Slide Glow Green released in September of 2021 and retailed for $60.

name: Green Gecko
title: Puma LaMelo Ball MB.01 Lo Green Gecko
description:
The Puma LaMelo Ball MB01 Lo Green Gecko has become a part of the brand´s catalog. The basketball sneaker appears in a Green Gecko or Castlerock colorway.

The upper of this collaborative shoe is made from synthetic materials featuring a 3D printed design throughout. The laces are made of green cotton with an underlying tongue made of mesh. This upper displays a circular leaves motif, near the collar, forming a crown and the rubber outsole has a thin linear pattern for traction.

The Puma LaMelo Ball MB01 Lo Green Gecko was originally released on October 21, 2022. The retail price was $120.

name: Mid Grey Sheet Rock
title: ASICS Gel-NYC Mid Grey Sheet Rock
description:
The ASICS Gel-NYC Mid Grey Sheet Rock is a performance running shoe that adds a grayscale colorway to the ASICS Gel-NYC silhouette.

This sneaker draws inspiration from heritage running sneakers in the ASICS catalog, including the GEL-NIMBUS 3 and the GEL-MC PLUS V. Specifically, the upper features crisscrossing overlays inspired by the GEL-MC PLUS V and a mesh upper similar to the one found on the GEL-NIMBUS 3. While the mesh comes in Mid Grey, the overlays display metallic silver. In terms of technology, the bulky midsole houses a combination of lightweight foam and gel technology in the forefoot and rear. These additions provide responsive cushioning and support for the foot.

Our StockX experts like the color contrast between the Mid Grey, Sheet Rock, and metallic silver upper and the all-black rubber outsole. The ASICS Gel-NYC Mid Grey Sheet Rock was released on December 1, 2023, and retailed at $130.

name: Maroon
title: adidas Gazelle Maroon
description:
The adidas Gazelle Maroon applies a Rich Maroon base with Chalk White accents to the Gazelle’s classic silhouette.

Like the original model released in 1966, the updated "Maroon" version features an upper crafted from soft suede instead of leather. This low-top sneaker was originally designed as an indoor soccer shoe, but is no longer defined by its sports designation. The entire upper comes in maroon suede with a tonal toe overlay and maroon laces winding through the punctured eyelets. Chalk White accents include the heel tab and the serrated 3-Stripes running up the side panel. In terms of branding, trefoil logos can be found on the tongue and across the heel tab. ‘Gazelle’ is also printed along the 3-Stripes in Metallic Gold lettering.

Our experts at StockX like the gum rubber outsole, which provides traction and comes in a dark tone. The adidas Gazelle Maroon was released on August 9th, 2023, and retailed at $110.

name: Cream Pure Silver Champagne
title: ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Cream Pure Silver Champagne
description:
The ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Cream Pure Silver Champagne is a running shoe designed with the aesthetics of 2000s running in mind.

This iteration of the ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 is made with a white breathable textile mesh upper. Shiny Pure Silver overlays form the toe cap and run from the bottom of the laces to the sole at the forefoot. The traditional ASICS design crosses both sides of the shoe in gray overlays, accented with navy blue. Metallic champagne overlays run from the back of the ankle to the sole, while the heel also contains more silver overlays with GEL branding. The tongue features an ASICS logo while the shoe sits on top of a white rubber sole. The sole is infused with GEL technology for extra cushioning in a dark blue color visible on the lateral side.

What we like best about this sneaker are the blue GEL materials visible in the sole, adding a pop of color. The ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Cream Pure Silver Champagne was released on December 3, 2021, retailed for $140.

name: Ivory Pink Fusion (Women's)
title: adidas Sambae Ivory Pink Fusion (Women's)
description:
The adidas Sambae Ivory Pink Fusion (Women's) is a reimagining of the adidas Samba with a soft colorway of ivory and Pink Fusion.

Unlike traditional Samba models, this version of the Sambae features a smooth leather upper and a translucent gum rubber outsole. The use of translucent gum rubber gives the sneaker a softer appearance and allows light to illuminate the outsole. Instead of applying leather, the 3-Stripes logo is embroidered onto the side panels using premium ivory thread. Although the dominant color is ivory, Pink Fusion details can be found on two heart-shaped eyelets, hearts on the insole, and the tongue’s trefoil logo. Another noteworthy feature is the premium nubuck used on the T-shaped toebox.

Our StockX experts like that the side panel branding reads ‘SAMBA,’ reminding the wearer of the shoe’s origin. The women’s size adidas Sambae Ivory Pink Fusion (Women's) was released on January 15th, 2024, and retailed at $110.

name: Off-White Black Electro Green
title: Nike Blazer Low Off-White Black Electro Green
description:
The Nike Blazer Low Off-White Black Electro Green boasts a multi-disciplinary, multi-sport aesthetic - a central motif in Virgil Abloh's body of work. Encompassing aspects of basketball, skateboarding, and trail running silhouettes, the Off-White Blazer Low fuses an Air Terra Humara TPU heel piece with a classic vulcanized sole for a unique base. On the black leather upper, punched-out holes are scattered, similar to the Air Jordan 5 Off-White. An accented Electro Green over-lacing system, exposed foam tongue, zip tie tag, and Swoosh tab all add Off-White's signature detailing to complete the design.

The Nike Blazer Low Off-White Black Electro Green released in April of 2022 and retailed for $140.

name: Kith Cream Scarab (2024)
title: ASICS Gel-1130 Kith Cream Scarab (2024)
description:
The ASICS Gel-1130 Kith Cream Scarab (2024) gives Ronnie Fieg’s Gel-1130 a contemporary upgrade with a Cream base and dark Scarab-green accents.

Inspired by retro running shoes from the 2000s, the Kith Cream Scarab (2024) ASICS Gel-1130 is part of a collaboration between ASICS and the streetwear label KITH. The upper is crafted from breathable mesh in Cream, while the synthetic leather overlays in metallic silver and the signature ASICS formstripe in Scarab provide contrast. The lifestyle running shoe boasts visible gel technology in the SpEVA and AHARPLUS midsole, offering a cushioned, responsive feel. Padding around the collar gives the sneaker a bulky silhouette, while the mesh lining allows the foot to breathe.

Our experts at StockX like the subtle branding in metallic silver and Scarab, including "GEL" on the heel and "ASICS GEL-1130" on the padded tongue. The ASICS Gel-1130 Kith Cream Scarab (2024) was released on March 28, 2024, and sold for $110.

name: White Pink Sugar
title: New Balance 530 White Pink Sugar
description:
The New Balance 530 White Pink Sugar dresses the 530 in a spring-inspired colorway of Pink Sugar and bright white.

Inspired by running shoes from New Balance’s early 2000s running catalog, the White Pink Sugar New Balance 530 features an airy mesh base in white with synthetic leather overlays in Pink Sugar, Silver Metallic, and white. The Pink Sugar and Silver Metallic overlays boast a metallic sheen with tonal, reinforced stitching. "NB" branding appears on the padded tongue, while the signature New Balance "N" decorates the mid-panel, and "530" is printed on the overlays. Responsive ABZORB cushioning adds a modern touch to the sneaker’s retro silhouette, while the rubber outsole provides increased traction.

Our experts at StockX like the padding in the collar and tongue, which protects the ankle and pays tribute to classic New Balance running shoes. The New Balance 530 White Pink Sugar was released on March 29, 2024, and sold for $100.

name: White Dark Grape (Women's)
title: ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 White Dark Grape (Women's)
description:
The ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 White Dark Grape (Women's) adds Dark Grape and metallic silver accents to the Gel-Kayano 14’s clean white base.

Inspired by technical running shoes from the early 2000s, the White Dark Grape (Women's) ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 features a bulky silhouette. The tooling system is borrowed directly from the OG model and houses responsive Gel cushioning. Although this sneaker wasn’t designed by Toshikazu Kayano, it pays tribute to his creative legacy through details on the upper. A web of metallic silver, black, and Dark Grape overlays crisscross the side panels. These overlays support the mesh base and give the sneaker a futuristic look.

Our experts like the gradient of Dark Grape sprayed across the midfoot area, on the rubber outsole. It adds a detail that’s only noticeable upon close inspection and complements Dark Grape accents on the side panel, the tongue, and the lining. The women’s size ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 White Dark Grape (Women's) was released on July 2, 2023, and sold for $150.

name: Black Fjord Grey
title: ASICS Gel-NYC Black Fjord Grey
description:
The ASICS Gel-NYC Black Fjord Grey debuts with retro vibes as it pays homage to the original model that was released in the 2000s.

Dressed in a black and fjord grey, the upper of this is sneaker boasts mixed materials that mimic leather. Mesh and synthetic seamlessly glide together to present an aesthetic that is sporty and luxurious with various textures. The iconic ASICS stripes add a boost of energy on the sides in fjord grey while black is present in the toe box, tongue, laces, and accents in the heel. The beloved GEL technology is seen in the forefoot and the heel, while the Space Trusstic bridge is under the arch.

We think that the mix of retro influences with athleticism is this sneaker’s unique design element. An ASICS logo on the tongue and GEL logo on the heel, both in red, add a bit of pop to the otherwise tonal shoe. The ASICS Gel-NYC Black Fjord Grey was released on September 13, 2024, with a retail price of $130.

name: Wales Bonner Fox Brown
title: adidas Samba Nylon Wales Bonner Fox Brown
description:
The adidas Samba Nylon Wales Bonner Fox Brown represents a captivating fusion of sportswear heritage and high-fashion aesthetics, born from the collaborative efforts of adidas and the British-Jamaican designer Grace Wales Bonner.

The Wales Bonner Fox Brown adidas Samba Nylon showcases the British brand's contemporary interpretation of a classic. The low-profile silhouette boasts a Fox Brown nylon upper with a matching forefoot overlay in textured suede. Tan leather accents adorn the iconic 3-Stripes and rear tab. Adding a touch of contrasting color, blue nylon lines the collar. The lateral heel proudly displays 'Wales Bonner,' while dual branding graces the sock liner and fold-over tongue. A robust gum rubber cupsole forms the foundation of the sneaker.

The most notable characteristic of the adidas Samba Nylon Wales Bonner Fox Brown is the meticulously stitched detailing at the heel. This distinctive feature, a signature element found throughout Bonner's work, contributes a unique touch to the overall design of the shoe. The shoe debuted for $160 on November 8th, 2023.

name: White Black Gum
title: adidas Samba Decon White Black Gum
description:
The adidas Samba Decon White Black Gum updates the original Samba released in the 1950s with a deconstructed aesthetic and a minimalist colorway of Cloud White, Core Black, and Grey One.

Cloud White leather makes up the upper, while the signature T-shaped overlay crossing the upper is crafted from velvety suede in Grey One. Highlights of black can be found on the heel tab and the 3-Stripes logos on the sides. Metallic gold SAMBA lettering runs next to the 3-Stripes on the outer side panel and matches the gold branding on the tongue. It reads "adidas" and displays an oversized trefoil. Keeping to the sneaker’s roots, the outsole is made of gum rubber that provides traction on multiple surfaces.

Our experts like the tonal stitching on the upper because it doesn’t stand out, keeping with the minimalist design. The adidas Samba Decon White Black Gum was launched first on August 25, 2023, and sold for $150.

name: Israfil
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Israfil
description:
Please note: Extra laces required Yeezy added to their already extensive catalog with the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Israfil, now available on StockX.

The Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Israfil features the same elements that fans of the sneaker love. The upper features multi-colored threads that add a variety of looks to the wearer’s feet from different angles. From there, the upper is matched with a translucent midsole that showcases the sneaker’s BOOST cushioned tech.

The Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Israfil released in August of 2020 for $220.

name: Crepe Soft Grey
title: Nike Air Max 1 Crepe Soft Grey
description:
The Nike Air Max 1 Crepe Soft Grey has been one of the most recognizable colorways in the Nike Air Max series since its release.

The Nike Air Max 1 Crepe Soft Grey lands in soft grey, neutral grey, and thunder colorways that complete its style. The upper part is made out of synthetic leather with suede at the toe and swoosh, the soles are made of rubber material. It has a brown outer sole and a thick white midsole.
     
The Nike Air Max 1 Crepe Soft Grey became available February 24th, 2023 with a retail price of $160.

name: Off-White University Red
title: Nike Blazer Low Off-White University Red
description:
The Nike Blazer Low Off-White White University Red boasts a multi-disciplinary, multi-sport aesthetic - a central motif in Virgil Abloh's body of work. Encompassing aspects of basketball, skateboarding, and trail running silhouettes, the Off-White Blazer Low fuses an Air Terra Humara TPU heel piece with a classic vulcanized sole for a unique base. On the white leather upper, punched-out holes are scattered, similar to the Air Jordan 5 Off-White. An accented over-lacing system, exposed foam tongue, zip tie tag, and Swoosh tab all add Off-White's signature detailing to this modified classic.

The Nike Blazer Low Off-White White University Red released in April of 2022 and retailed for $140.

name: Hyper Pink Laser Orange
title: Nike Air Zoom Alphafly Next% 2 Hyper Pink Laser Orange
description:
The Nike Air Zoom Alphafly Next% 2 Hyper Pink Laser Orange is a revolutionary racing sneaker designed to help you shave seconds off your best time while enjoying ultimate comfort.

The Hyper Pink Laser Orange colorway of the Nike Air Zoom Alphafly Next% 2 features an upper of bright pink Atomknit that's both lightweight and breathable. An outline of a black Nike Swoosh is worked into this knit and courses from the toe box to the outer side panel. Notched pink laces help secure a snug fit, while the pink integrated knit tongue helps ease lace pressure. Pink pull tabs at the heel and tongue facilitate on/off, and lofted pods of Flyknit provide lightweight lockdown at the heel.

The most impressive part of this sneaker is the bright orange midsole. It has full-length ZoomX foam and two forefoot Zoom Air units for cushioning and springy energy return. A full-length carbon fiber plate offers a propulsive sensation with every stride, and a thin black rubber outsole has vents to allow for ZoomX expansion. The Nike Air Zoom Alphafly Next% 2 Hyper Pink Laser Orange was released on April 4, 2023, for $275 retail.

name: Kasina Won-Ang Grey
title: Nike Air Max 1 Kasina Won-Ang Grey
description:
South Korean boutique Kasina honored its 25th Anniversary with the Nike Air Max 1 Kasina Wong-Ang Grey.

Referencing Wong-Ang Ducks, a style of carved wooden ducks traditionally gifted to newlywed couples, the Nike Air Max 1 Kasina Wong-Ang Grey incorporates colors and materials that are said to bring good fortune in Korean culture. It features a premium teal tumbled leather upper with dark grey faux horsehair overlays and light grey suede mudguards. At the heel, small Wong-Ang Duck embroidery nods to the Korean wedding custom. From there, an icy, semi-translucent outsole revealing a geometric pattern on the bottom of the midsole completes the design.

The Nike Air Max 1 Kasina Wong-Ang Grey released in June of 2022 and retailed for $160.

name: Parra Abstract Art (2021)
title: Nike SB Dunk Low Pro Parra Abstract Art (2021)
description:
Nike and Dutch artist and sneaker collab veteran Parra teamed up for an Olympic inspired Nike SB Dunk Low with the Nike SB Dunk Low Parra Abstract Art.

The Nike SB Dunk Low Parra Abstract Art highlights Parra's surreal take on pop art. Off-white leather on the upper creates a blank canvas so that overlays smothered in vibrant, retro Parra patterns rise to prominence. Additional details like the embroidered mini-Swoosh on the toe box and gum outsole offer nostalgic appeal.

The Nike SB Dunk Low Parra Abstract Art released in July of 2021 and retailed for $110.

name: Anatomy of Air GID
title: Nike Air Max 95 Anatomy of Air GID
description:
Nike paid homage to what inspired the Air Max 95's ideation with the Nike Air Max 95 Anatomy of Air.​
​​
​Designed by celebrated designer Sergio Lozano, it is documented that the Air Max 95 design was inspired by the human anatomy and sedimentary rock. The Nike Air Max 95 Anatomy of Air features color blocking reminiscent of muscular tissue, with leather layered overlays in shades of red atop a bone white mesh base. Visible Air Max units in the sole add the finishing touch.​
​​
​The Nike Air Max 95 Anatomy of Air released in July of 2022 and retailed for $180.

name: White Black
title: Nike Blazer Low 77 Vintage White Black
description:
The Nike Blazer Low 77 Vintage White Black returns with its low-profile style, and heritage basketball looks.

The nearly 1-to-1 remake of the Nike Blazer Low 77 Vintage White Black features crisp leather on the upper with soft suede and synthetic details for added durability and throwback styling. The ultra-clean colors, simple lines, and low-cut, padded collar continue the look, which is wrapped up by an outsole fused with the midsole. The solid rubber outsole with herringbone pattern adds traction, durability, and heritage styling.

The Nike Blazer Low 77 Vintage White Black was released in December 2020 and originally retailed for $85.

name: Pulse Mint Pink (Women's)
title: adidas Gazelle Bold Pulse Mint Pink (Women's)
description:
The adidas Gazelle Bold Pulse Mint Pink (Women's) arrives in a Pulse Mint, Screaming Pink, and Gum color palette.

The Pulse Mint Pink adidas Gazelle Bold adopts the timeless low-top silhouette and adds on a suede upper for a classic look. The lace-up closure ensures a secure and customizable fit, while the padded collar provides added comfort. With a cushioned midsole for enhanced comfort and impact absorption, the shoe offers a durable rubber outsole for reliable traction. The signature 3-Stripes branding and adidas Trefoil logos adorn the sides, while the "GAZELLE" inscription adds a distinctive touch to the side panel.

The standout feature of the adidas Gazelle Bold Pulse Mint Pink (Women's) is its vibrant color scheme, combining bold pulses of mint and pink. This eye-catching design adds a stylish and playful element to the classic Gazelle silhouette. The women’s rendition of the adidas Gazelle was released on December 6th, 2022, and sold for a retail price of $120.

name: Rose Pink (Wide) (GS)
title: New Balance 9060 Rose Pink (Wide) (GS)
description:
The New Balance 9060 Rose Pink (Wide) (GS) Is a colorful sneaker that takes inspiration from several New Balance silhouettes to provide a fun, secure, stable sneaker for grade school-aged kids in a wide foot fit.

The Rose Pink colorway of the grade schoolers’ Wide New Balance 9060 features a white mesh upper that offers breathability and enhanced comfort. Synthetic leather and suede overlays and shades of pink add all-over foot support, as well as whimsical style, to this shoe. The white N embroidered on the side panel complements the translucent Pearly White heel clip that offers a locked-down feel. The ABZORB midsole in white, cream, and pink offers cushioning and impact absorption with every step. The diamond traction pattern on the brown rubber outsole takes its tried-and-true design from the NB 860.

The aspect of this sneaker that we enjoy the most is the white and blue NB branding on the cutout window of the tongue, which takes its inspiration from the lace jewel of the NB OG 991 for a vintage feel. The New Balance 9060 Rose Pink (Wide) (GS) was released on February 15, 2024, for $110 retail.

name: Abalone
title: Nike LeBron 21 Abalone
description:
The Nike LeBron 21 Abalone takes the recognizable Lebron 21 silhouette and adds a vibrant pattern that mimics the inside of an abalone shell.

The lightweight mesh upper features abalone shell patterns that include whirling patterns in tones ranging from aqua to dark green. The Swoosh on the lateral side comes in abalone print with an embroidered white line, while the Swoosh on the medial side panel features rows of stitches. These stitched lines look like the pattern on the outside of an abalone shell and correspond to the exposed construction on the heel. This low-to-the-ground basketball shoe boasts Zoom Air technology in the midsole and ventilation ports on both sides of the shoes.

Our StockX experts like the symbolism behind the shoe. To Lebron James, the shell protecting the pearl within symbolizes the way he protects his daughter. The Nike LeBron 21 Abalone was released on December 1st, 2023, and retailed at $210.

name: Tan Lines (Women's)
title: Nike Air Max 1 Tan Lines (Women's)
description:
The Nike Air Max 1 Tan Lines (Women's) features multi-color panels across the upper, giving the sneaker a patchwork appearance.

Overlapping panels of suede stand out against the white mesh base. The suede overlays come in a variety of rich colors, including Plum Fog, Burnt Sunrise, Grain, violet, Deep Royal Blue, and Dust. Like the original Air Max 1 from 1987, this updated version boasts visible Air Max technology in the heel. However, the Nike branding is a change of pace from the usual fonts and logos. For example, the heel tab is embossed with stylized ‘Nike’ lettering, while the suede tongue displays ‘Nike’ in the same font.

Our StockX experts like the inclusion of a black rubber outsole, which contrasts the upper's vibrant colors and provides traction. The women’s size Nike Air Max 1 Tan Lines (Women's) was released on December 5th, 2023, and retailed at $180.

name: Black Carbon
title: ASICS Gel-1130 Black Carbon
description:
The ASICS Gel-1130 Black Carbon is a running shoe made with Gel technology to support enhanced performance and comfort.

This iteration of the ASICS Gel-1130 is made with a base of black mesh. This black mesh dominates the toe box, the sides, and the heel of the shoe. Gray suede overlays round out the toe box and appear on the sides in the typical ASICS pattern, while some of the overlays sport white lines in the middle. The heel has a curved design formed by the gray overlays, and the word GEL is placed here. The tongue features a Gel-1130 logo patch, and the shoe sits on top of an off-white rubber sole and outsole.

Our favorite feature of this sneaker is the black mesh base, which provides both functionality and an elegant dark look. The ASICS Gel-1130 Black Carbon was released on January 10, 2024, for an initial retail price of $100.

name: Crystal White Preloved Red
title: adidas Samba OG Crystal White Preloved Red
description:
The adidas Samba OG Crystal White Preloved Red is a lifestyle sneaker with an ultra-airy mesh upper plus leather and suede details.

Drawing from the 1970s adidas archives, this low-top sneaker was originally designed for the soccer pitch. However, it includes a variety of elements that provide a contemporary upgrade. The upper is crafted from a loose-weave mesh in Crystal White that keeps the foot cool on hot days. The suede T-shaped toebox overlay comes in the same color, while the leather heel tab and serrated 3-Stripes logo display bright Preloved Red. The Crystal White leather lining adds a premium feel, while the gum rubber outsole is a classic touch.

Our experts at StockX like the minimalist branding, including the rectangular logo printed on the tongue that reads "adidas." The adidas Samba OG Crystal White Preloved Red was released on March 8, 2024, and retailed at $100.

name: White Burgundy Gum
title: adidas Samba OG White Burgundy Gum
description:
The adidas Samba OG White Burgundy Gum is a training shoe with a classic design made with premium materials.

This colorway of the adidas Samba OG is constructed with a soft white leather upper dominating most of the shoe. A suede T-shaped toe cap appears in beige. The classic adidas three stripes logo appears across the sides of the shoe in Burgundy Red overlays, and the heel collar is also Burgundy Red. The word Samba is featured on the lateral side next to the stripes in gold letters. A blue adidas logo patch is featured on the tongue, while a classic gum rubber outsole rounds out the iconic design.

What we like best about the shoe is that it stays true to the traditional design but adds Burgundy Red accents. The adidas Samba OG White Burgundy Gum was introduced on March 8, 2024, and retailed for $100.

name: Putty Mauve Wonder Taupe (Women's)
title: adidas Campus 00s Putty Mauve Wonder Taupe (Women's)
description:
The adidas Campus 00s Putty Mauve Wonder Taupe Women's sneaker is a modern take on a classic silhouette from the 1970s that offers both style and comfort for everyday wear in women's sizing.

This sneaker features a sleek and minimalist design with clean lines and a low-profile silhouette. The upper is crafted from premium suede and leather, offering a luxurious look and feel. Its understated design is complemented by subtle adidas branding, including the signature three-stripes on the sides and a trefoil logo on the tongue and heel tab. With comfort as a top priority, this shoe employs a cushioned midsole for support and shock absorption, as well as a padded collar and tongue for all-day wearability.

What our experts especially enjoy about the adidas Campus 00s Putty Mauve Wonder Taupe Women's, however, is its soft, neutral color scheme in Putty Mauve and Wonder Taupe against which a white rubber outsole and small white details at the heel and tongue pop. This shoe originally retailed for $120 when it was released on January 8, 2024.

name: Coconut Milk Hot Punch
title: Nike Giannis Immortality 2 Coconut Milk Hot Punch
description:
The Nike Giannis Immortality 2 Coconut Milk Hot Punch is a basketball shoe inspired by Giannis Antetokounmpo, an NBA player of Greek and Nigerian heritage.

The Coconut Milk Hot Punch Nike Giannis Immortality 2 pays homage to his Greek heritage through conceptual maps of Athens and Lagos and hieroglyphic-like details. For example, the medial side displays a circle bisected by a zigzagging arrow. The upper is made from airy mesh in two distinct patterns, while cutouts in the foam midsole reduce the shoe’s overall weight. While the base comes in Coconut Milk, University Blue takes over the rubber outsole, the collar lining, and the tongue. Hot Punch accents are on the Swoosh logos and the oversized heel pull tab.

Our experts at StockX like the internal midfoot strap, which provides stability. The Nike Giannis Immortality 2 Coconut Milk Hot Punch was released on May 8, 2023, and retailed at $85.

name: Green (Women's)
title: adidas Gazelle Bold Green (Women's)
description:
The adidas Gazelle Bold Green (Women's) gives the platformed Gazelle Bold silhouette a premium upgrade with rich green suede and white leather on the upper.

For a new take on the classic silhouette from the 1970s, the Green (Women's) adidas Gazelle Bold features a triple-stacked gum rubber outsole underfoot. Ranging from medium to light gum, the outsoles form a gradient and feature triple ‘adidas’ lettering and trefoils. The base construction, the T-toe overlay, the eyelets, and the laces come in velvety green, while the heritage 3-Stripes logo, the heel mustache, the lining, and the texturized tongue add elegant contrast in white. Completing the look, a circular keychain with silver hardware and adidas branding hangs from the laces.

Our experts at StockX like the metallic gold ‘GAZELLE’ lettering and the adidas branding on the tongue because they contribute to the sneaker’s premium look. The women’s size adidas Gazelle Bold Green (Women's) was released on April 7, 2024, and sold for $130.

name: Amber Tint
title: adidas Yeezy QNTM Amber Tint
description:
The adidas Yeezy QNTM Amber Tint features a marbled Amber Tint Primeknit upper with grey heel wraps and black collars. From there, a light grey suede toe wrap and semi-translucent sole completes the design.

The adidas Yeezy QNTM Amber Tint released in December of 2021 and retailed for $250.

name: Sea Salt Black (Women's)
title: New Balance 327 Sea Salt Black (Women's)
description:
The New Balance 327 Sea Salt Black (W) comes in a sea salt, white, and black color palette.

The New Balance 327 Sea Salt Black (W) features an upper that is made of lightweight, breathable mesh material with suede overlays for sturdiness and comfort. The shoe's outsole is composed of a rubber compound for grip and stability, while the midsole is made with REVlite foam for padding and support. The shoe features "NB" branding on the tongue, and it also has New Balance's iconic "N" emblem on the side panels.

The women’s rendition of the New Balance 327 Sea Salt Black (W) was released on August 19, 2022, and retailed for $95.

name: Resin
title: adidas Yeezy 450 Resin
description:
With a minimalist two-piece construction, the adidas Yeezy 450 Resin features a Resin foam sole that encompasses a matching sock-like Primeknit upper. Thick rope laces and sock-like collars add finishing touches.

The adidas Yeezy 450 Resin released in December of 2021 and retailed for $200.

name: Mexico
title: adidas Gazelle Mexico
description:
The adidas Gazelle Mexico is a sports shoe with a color scheme designed to show support for Mexico’s sports teams.

This iteration of the adidas Gazelle comes with a suede upper in a Green Oxide color. This color scheme dominates, including on the overlay at the toebox that runs up to the laces. The iconic three stripes appear on the midsoles in light beige leather, and the word "GAZELLE" appears on the lateral side in gold lettering. The heel collar is also beige leather with the adidas trefoil logo stamped onto it in dark green. The tongue of the shoe contains a Mexican seal to show support for the country, and a dark brown gum rubber outsole completes the look.

What we like best about this shoe is the streamlined and sleek design that still pays homage to Mexico. The adidas Gazelle Mexico was released on December 2, 2023, for a retail price of $100.

name: Analog
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Laceless Analog
description:
