In a similar fashion to Nike basketball shoes that carry the renowned "What The?" moniker, the Puma MB.01 LaMelo Ball Be You boasts a vibrant, asymmetrical look that borrows elements from colorways in the MB.01 collection. Galaxy-print areas of the upper nod to the MB.01 Galaxy, while hits of lime green and hot pink celebrate the popular MB.01 Rock & Morty. LaMelo's signature "1 of 1" insignia on the tongue and insole adds the finishing touch.

The Puma MB.01 LaMelo Ball Be You released in July of 2022 and retailed for $120.

name: Beach Glass Pink
title: New Balance 9060 Beach Glass Pink
description:
The New Balance 9060 Beach Glass Pink is a casual athleisure sneaker released by New Balance as part of the 9060 line. It has a unique Beach Glass Pink which features a vivid color palette with different hues.

The shoe‘s upper is made from a combination of genuine leather, suede, and mesh materials. it has a light blue and white mesh base with multicolored, layered overlays made from leather and suede. The New Balance 9060 also has a chunky sole unit featuring ABZORB technology which helps with cushioning the foot and shock absorption while walking or doing sports.

One of the things our experts love about the New Balance 9060 Beach Glass Pink is the color palette. The white base is complemented by subtle accents of light blue and black plus vibrant hues of red and green which give the shoe a beautiful and colorful aesthetic making it stand out regardless of the outfit. The shoe was released for retail priced at $150 in July 2023.

name: Protection Pack Vintage Orange
title: New Balance 2002R Protection Pack Vintage Orange
description:
The New Balance 2002R Protection Pack Vintage Orange remains the best-selling variant of the original 2002 Luxury Kick since its debut.

The vintage yellow upper of the shoe is created using suede, premium mesh, and leather as the main materials. The foam tongue topping the classic abzorb midsole with cotton laces rounds up the design of New Balance 2002R Protection Pack Vintage Orange. The N-energy outsole of the shoe is made of salt water white rubber.

New Balance 2002R Protection Pack Vintage Orange was first released in August 2022 at select retailers in Europe and Asia at a price of $150.

name: Mist (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Mist (Kids)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Mist (Kids) in kids’ sizes features a slip-on design. This shoe is known for its alien-like design that is created through open fabrication. The material of the shoe consists of algae and EVA foam as part of Kanye West's commitment toward more sustainable product endeavors.

RNNR Mist attracts attention for its futuristic silhouette that is crafted as a single piece of Foam RNNR. The chunky, elliptical shape is balanced by its wearable all over tan color and slip on functionality. Ellipse-shaped openings allow for breathability, ease of wear, and lightness. Paired with or without socks, the Foam RNNR is an all-season shoe and an expression of style.

In our expert opinion, the forward leaning design balanced by Mist’s neutral color is the best feature of Foam RNNR. The adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Mist (Kids) released on 11th March 2022 for $60.

name: x Pleasures AC Milan 2023/24 Light Version Authentic
title: Puma x Pleasures AC Milan 2023/24 Light Version Authentic Jersey Multicolor
description:
The Puma x Pleasures AC Milan 2023/24 Light Version Authentic Jersey Multicolor is an Associazione Calcio Milan football jersey for the 2023/24 season. The shirt's body is cream-colored with a tan print, accented by dark brown printed trim on the collar and sleeves. The Puma cat logo and AC Milan crest branding appear on the chest, alongside sponsorship branding on the front and back.

For the AC Milan Jersey geometric patterns, contemporary brand Pleasures drew inspiration from the aesthetics and energy of the masonry patterns seen on the streets of Milan. Beyond that, the AC Milan Jersey is crafted from 100% recycled fabric, excluding the trims.

Our experts feel that the best feature of the AC Milan Jersey is its moisture-wicking fabrication, which keeps you cool while you watch the match. The Puma x Pleasures AC Milan 2023/24 Light Version Authentic Jersey Multicolor was released on February 11, 2024, and retailed at $175.

name: Ochre (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Slide Ochre (Kids)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Slide Ochre (Kids) applies an uneven light brown finish to the sandal, featuring a rubberized foam build with a textured surface.

The minimalist design of the adidas Yeezy Slide Ochre (Kids) is free of any exterior branding, save for adidas’ three-stripe logo stamped on the soft top layer of the footbed. Open-toe construction delivers ventilated comfort, while the pair’s footbed includes a soft top layer for comfort. Underfoot, the pair features deep horizontal sawtooth-like grooves that provide traction.

The adidas Yeezy Slide Ochre (Kids) was released in December 2021 and retailed for $45.

name: Bright Lime Midnight (Women's)
title: ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Bright Lime Midnight (Women's)
description:
The ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Bright Lime Midnight (Women's) is a women’s exclusive running shoe from ASICS’ GEL-KAYANO™ 14 series in a "Bright Lime Midnight" colorway.

This GEL-KAYANO™ 14 sneaker features a mixed-material upper made of a Bright Lime mesh base with Metallic Silver and black leather overlays. Contrasting hits of white feature on the overlays, laces, the "ASICS Tiger" brand logo on the tongue, and "GEL" lettering on the heel tab. Other details include "GEL-KAYANO 14" wording printed on the lateral heel, black insoles with the "ASICS Tiger" brand logo, and a black padded mesh lining. Underfoot, a white and Bright Lime GEL-cushioned midsole rests on a treaded multicolor rubber outsole. 

Something we love about this running shoe is its vibrant colorway and design elements, which makes it a bold and stylish choice for individuals seeking a distinctive and energetic aesthetic in their footwear. The ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Bright Lime Midnight (Women's) was made available on July 31st, 2023. Initially, it retailed at $150.

name: Cream Kale
title: ASICS Gel-1130 Cream Kale
description:
The ASICS Gel-1130 Cream Kale is part of GEL-1000’s ninth iteration and is an updated version of the 2008 sneaker. Although this stability running sneaker resembles running shoes from the 2000s, it incorporates new technologies and design features.

Unlike its predecessor, the Cream Kale variant features an all-mesh base and mesh detailing throughout the shoe. Even the inserts are made of mesh. This material allows the foot to breathe and keeps the shoe lightweight. GEL technology in the heel reduces shock from impact, while ASICS’ signature Trusstic support system provides stability and prevents the shoe from twisting. In terms of branding, ‘ASICS’ can be found across the tongue.

Our experts love the contrast between the silver and green overlays. Dark green can also be found along the padded color and splashed across the outsole. The ASICS Gel-1130 Cream Kale was released on September 23, 2023, and retailed at $95.

name: Ronnie Fieg Super Yellow
title: ASICS Gel-Lyte III Remastered Ronnie Fieg Super Yellow
description:
The ASICS Gel Lyte III Remastered Ronnie Fieg Super Yellow showcases a thoughtfully designed aesthetic, predominantly cloaked in a refined shade of grey. At the same time, its distinctive character is accentuated by the vibrant yellow stripes gracefully adorning the sides.

The Remastered Ronnie Fieg "Super Yellow" boasts a fusion of style and technology. Its upper showcases premium materials, combining suede and leather for a luxurious touch. The iconic split tongue design offers a unique look, while the yellow stripes on the sides provide a pop of contrast. The Gel cushioning technology in the sole ensures exceptional comfort, while the set of laces allows for customizable styling, making it a standout choice in form and function.

Our team is captivated by the shoe, and one feature that truly stands out is the iconic split tongue design. Our experts admire how it encapsulates the essence of the Gel Lyte III silhouette, offering a unique visual flair that has become synonymous with the sneaker. The ASICS Gel Lyte III Remastered Ronnie Fieg Super Yellow was released on the 27th of February, 2023, and retailed for $195.

name: Above The Clouds
title: ASICS GT-2160 Above The Clouds
description:
The Asics GT-2160 Above The Clouds represents a collaboration between the renowned sneaker company and the Australian boutique retailer. The result is a sleek running shoe inspired by the GT-2000s circa 2010.

The Above The Clouds x Asics GT-2160 features a lightweight upper with a base of translucent NEXKIN on the vamp and forefoot and white mesh on the midfoot and collar. Synthetic leather overlays course across the upper in shades of dark green, foam green, and silver. A synthetic brown heel counter adds support and sits just below the GEL branding. The green mesh sock liner is padded at the heel for comfort. Aqua blue insoles feature dual branding. GT-2160 branding appears on a pale green overlay on the lateral heel.

We particularly enjoy the segmented sole unit of this running shoe. Gel inserts in the foam midsole under the forefoot and heel provide ultimate cushioning while a rubber outsole provides a multi-surface grip. The Asics GT-2160 Above The Clouds was released on October 13, 2023, for $150 retail.

name: Core Black Red (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Core Black Red (Infants)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Core Black Red (Infants), a soft sneaker specifically sized for babies, offer a snug, comfortable, lightweight pull-on fit.

The upper of the Infants' version of the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 in a Core Black / Red / Core Black colorway is fashioned from black PRIMEKNIT speckled with red. A woven-in red stripe courses across the lateral side of the upper sporting the cryptic SPLY-350 branding the right way about on one shoe, and in a backwards mirror image on the other shoe. Black no-tie laces make this baby sneaker easy to slip on and off.

What our sneaker experts appreciate most about this shoe is the dependable sole unit that will support and protect a baby's foot. A black Boost midsole covered by a TPU cage sits atop a black rubber outsole with the lattice weave pattern that allows the Boost to expand and react. The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Core Black Red (Infants) was released on February 8, 2022 for a retail price of $140.

name: Sumac
title: adidas Yeezy 500 High Sumac
description:
The adidas Yeezy 500 High Sumac features a Sumac mesh and suede upper with navy and red leather overlays. A Sumac adiprene sole and neoprene tongue complete the design.

The adidas Yeezy 500 High Sumac released in May of 2021 and retailed for $220.

name: Magnet
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Magnet
description:
Yeezy expands its 700 color pallette once again with the adidas Yeezy Boost 700 "Magnet", now available on StockX. Despite an existing line of Yeezy 700s assorted in six colorways, the Magnet is the first time this colorway has been used.

This 700 features a grey upper with suede overlays and orange accents on the midsole. Its chunky midsole is inspired by the Adidas KB3 atop a gum outsole completes the design. These sneakers released in September of 2019 and retailed for $300.

name: Yeezreel (Reflective)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Yeezreel (Reflective)
description:
Following its non-reflective counterpart, Yeezy released the adidas Yeezy 350 Yeezreel Reflective, now available on StockX. This 350 V2 is reminiscent of the Glow colorway that released in early 2019, but sets itself apart with the addition of new tones woven in the Primeknit upper. This model was released in both reflective and non-reflective variations.

This Yeezy 350 V2 is composed of a Yeezreel upper and with black and grey accents ingrained in the upper. A translucent Yeezreel Boost cushioned sole that glows-in-the-dark and side stripe completes the design. These sneakers released in December of 2019 and retailed for $250.

name: Carbon Blue
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Carbon Blue
description:
Yeezy adds to its ever growing 700 line with the adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Carbon Blue, now available on StockX. Trailing the releases of the Magnet and Teal Blue colorways, this shoe stays true to the Yeezy aesthetic with a new tonal variation that stays in the same ballpark of other 700 releases.

This 700 is composed of a mix of grey and carbon blue tones that are assorted amongst a mix of suede and mesh. A grey rubber midsole and gum outsole completes the design. These sneakers released in December of 2019 for $300.

name: Frosted Blue
title: adidas Yeezy 500 High Frosted Blue
description:
The adidas Yeezy 500 High Frosted Blue arrives with a molded upper composed of tonal blue suede, premium leather, and elastane. Off-white suede overlays cover the toe wrap and eyestay while elastane padding makes up the collar of the shoe for additional comfort. An off-white adiprene sole provides traction and stability, a fitting way to wrap up this hiking-inspired silhouette.

The adidas Yeezy 500 High Frosted Blue released in April of 2021 and retailed for $200.

name: Kith Cream Scarab (2023)
title: ASICS Gel-1130 Kith Cream Scarab (2023)
description:
The ASICS Gel-1130 Kith Cream Scarab (2023) features a white mesh and synthetic leather upper, a reinforced collar, and mesh lining. The ASICS form stripe signature motif appears on the side panels in silver with black and white detailing. Gel branding appears on the rear, and ASICS Gel-1130 branding appears on the tongue, grounded by Cream and black midsoles and outsoles.

Kith is an American fashion and lifestyle brand, founded in New York City in 2011 by Ronnie Fieg. Kith is known for their retail locations in major cities around the world, focused on streetwear and athletic brands in dynamic settings. It’s only natural that Kith would team up with performance-focused ASICS, which has operated by their credo "Sound Mind, Sound Body" since their founding in 1949.

Our experts feel that the best features of the Gel-1130 Kith are its performance details, including SpEVA and AHARPLUS midsoles and its visible Gel midsole, which enable maximum endurance. The ASICS Gel-1130 Kith Cream Scarab (2023) released on June 23, 2023, and retailed for $110.

name: Sand (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy Foam RNR Sand (Infants)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Foam RNR Sand Infants is one of the products from the Kanye West-designed Yeezy Foam Runner line. This product comes in a sand color and has a detailed structure molded in a single piece.

Cut-outs on the Yeezy Foam RNR by adidas complete the design for little children while also providing airflow. This shoe, which is constructed entirely of algae-based foam. The sole's wave-like traction design offers durability and grip for everyday movement activities.

The adidas Yeezy Foam RNR Sand Infants model was first made available on the 11th of June, 2022, with a suggested retail price of $45.

name: Unaffected Infinite Wonders Pack Black Silver
title: ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Unaffected Infinite Wonders Pack Black Silver
description:
The ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Unaffected Infinite Wonders Pack Black Silver is a retro-inspired running shoe produced in collaboration with South Korean streetwear label Unaffected.

As part of the Infinite Wonders pack, the Unaffected Infinite Wonders Pack Black Silver ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 embodies streetwear aesthetics with metallic silver streaking across the toe box and overlays. Crafted from durable synthetic leather, the overlays stand out against the black mesh base. Although the sneaker isn’t designed by Toshikazu Kayano, it keeps the original midsole tooling. The Gel midsole reduces impact stress and adds stability without weighing down the shoe. A quick-lacing system with an adjustable toggle replaces traditional laces, while padding around the ankle adds comfort.

Our experts at StockX like the elements that celebrate heritage ASICS models. For instance, the mesh upper is a throwback detail to the original shoe from 2008. The ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Unaffected Infinite Wonders Pack Black Silver was released on November 24, 2023, and sold for $200.

name: White Blue Atoll
title: Puma Clyde All-Pro White Blue Atoll
description:
The Puma Clyde All-Pro White Blue Atoll is a modern version of the classic Puma Clyde basketball shoe which was named after basketball legend Walt "Clyde" Frazier, who played a significant role in popularizing the model.

The shoe has a simple and minimalist design featuring a neutral upper with suede overlays on the heel area. The neutral upper is complemented by multicolored stripes that run all over the upper, even crisscrossing each other, although they leave a huge space in the shape of the iconic Puma formstrip. The sole unit is fully white and has some decorative lines running across it with the name ‘Clyde’ engraved on the heel area.

A standout feature on these Puma Clyde All-Pro White Blue Atoll is the midsole which has ProFoam+ technology to provide cushioning on your feet, keeping them comfortable even with all-day wear. The shoes were initially released on 11th November 2020 and retailed at $130.

name: Yecheil (Reflective)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Yecheil (Reflective)
description:
Yeezy adds a flare to one of its most well-known designs with the adidas Yeezy 350 Yecheil Reflective, now available on StockX. This 350 V2 strays away from the usual earth tones with a colorful palette, making it stand out from previous releases. This model was released in both reflective and non-reflective variations.

This Yeezy 350 V2 is composed of a black upper with white, red, yellow, and blue accents. A black Boost cushioned sole and black side stripe completes the design. These sneakers released in December of 2019 and retailed for $220.

name: Bone (2022) (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy Slide Bone (2022) (Infants)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Slide Bone 2022 Infants is a re-release of the 2019 original version.

Made from injected EVA foam, this slip-on shoe comes in a beige colorway. The adidas logo is debossed into the foam and appears on the footbed. A wraparound strap is available on the heel to ensure the Slide doesn't slip off the foot. This Slide features a coarse sole to provide grip and a molded footbed for comfort. An abstract stripe is engraved into the midsole on the heel.

The adidas Yeezy Slide Bone 2022 Infants for kids was made available on the 31st of May, 2022. Originally, it retailed at $50.

name: Ronnie Fieg Super Orange
title: ASICS Gel-Lyte III Remastered Ronnie Fieg Super Orange
description:
The ASICS Gel Lyte III Remastered Ronnie Fieg Super Orange was released in honor of the inauguration of Kith's Beverly Hills flagship store.

The Orange ASICS Gel Lyte III Remastered Ronnie Fieg boasts an exquisite blend of materials, combining premium suede and breathable mesh in its construction. The upper is beautifully designed with a harmonious contrast between Pumice Stone and Orange Tiger, creating a captivating visual appeal reminiscent of the city's eclectic charm. The colorway encapsulates a sense of boldness and nostalgia, making it versatile for various casual outfits.

What we love about the shoe is its signature split tongue design that the Gel Lyte III is renowned for. This distinctive feature adds an element of uniqueness to the shoe and contributes to an exceptional fit, ensuring maximum comfort during extended wear. The split tongue provides a snug yet flexible feel, preventing the discomfort often associated with traditional tongue constructions. The ASICS Gel Lyte III Remastered Ronnie Fieg Super Orange was released on the 6th of June, 2023, and sold at $195.

name: MX Rock (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 MX Rock (Kids)
description:
The Yeezy Boost 350 V2, designed by Kanye West, has become a cultural icon since its debut. The MX Rock colorway offers a muted, dark, and earthy palette that pairs well with any outfit. The signature stripe running along the side adds a touch of distinction, while the ribbed midsole showcases the innovative Boost technology. These design elements highlight the model's unique blend of fashion and function, making it a must-have for young sneakerheads.

Priced at $160, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 MX Rock (Kids) was released on February 23, 2022. This sneaker not only delivers on style but also ensures maximum comfort. Add a touch of Yeezy flair to your child's footwear collection with this versatile and trendy model.

name: Kith Leatherback
title: ASICS Gel-Lyte V Kith Leatherback
description: The ASICS Gel Lyte V Kith Leatherback is a sleek and stylish sneaker that combines premium materials with cutting-edge technology. The upper is crafted from high-quality leather, which provides durability and a luxurious feel. The colorway features a black and white base with pops of vibrant green on the branding and outsole. The Gel Lyte V technology in the midsole offers superior cushioning and support, making these sneakers perfect for both casual wear and athletic activities. Released on November 24th, 2021, the ASICS Gel Lyte V Kith Leatherback retails for $165. This price point is in line with other premium sneakers on the market and is a testament to the quality of materials and technology used in the construction of the shoe. Something we love about ASICS Gel Lyte V Kith Leatherback is the attention to detail in the design. The combination of premium leather and vibrant green accents creates a unique and eye-catching look. Our experts think the standout feature of the ASICS Gel Lyte V Kith Leatherback is the Gel Lyte V technology in the midsole, which provides superior cushioning and support. Overall, we love the combination of style and performance that the ASICS Gel Lyte V Kith Leatherback offers.

name: Rhuigi B-Boy
title: Puma Suede Rhuigi B-Boy
description:
The Puma Suede Rhuigi B Boy is a low-top sneaker released in part of a collaborative effort between Puma and Rhuigi Villaseñor, the founder of Los Angeles-based luxury streetwear brand, RHUDE.

The shoe features a predominantly pink upper, white accents on the laces, and the classic Puma lines that run across the sides. It also has metallic gold accents on the branding details which help to add a touch of luxury to the shoes. The upper is made from suede material while the sole unit features a rubber construction to enhance durability. As for branding, the Puma Suede Rhuigi has Puma text branding on the sides and heel area as well as another logo on the tongue and the number 91 on the heel tab.

One thing we love about the Puma Suede Rhuigi B Boy is that it comes with a padded insole to provide a soft cushion for your feet. The shoes were released for retail in April 2023 priced at $120.

name: Core Black Copper
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Core Black Copper
description: Hope you're ready to smash open that piggy bank and spend some pennies on the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Copper. Displaying a rich look, these have a core black upper and sole. There's also core black "SPLY-350" branding across the core copper stripe on both sides. These dropped in November 2016 and retailed at $220, Add more sauce to your sneaker collection on StockX.

name: Yeezy
title: Nike Air Foamposite Pro Yeezy
description:
After being inspired by the Air Yeezy 2 colorway silhouette, Nike released the Nike Air Foamposite Pro Yeezy with a laser crimson colorway to give it a unique spin. The black/laser crimson colorway signature features carbon fiber prints on its upper.

The Air Foamposite Pro Yeezy is adorned with neon red accents with a black upper and a glow-in-the-dark outsole. It features crimson at the heel, liner, and tongue, with eyestays displaying a faux snakeskin pattern. Inspired by Kanye West's 2012 model, a black Foamposite shell and Swoosh team with a black mesh/nubuck upper to design the sneaker.

The Nike Air Foamposite Pro Yeezy was released at a retail price of $250 on April 19, 2014.

name: Slate Blue
title: adidas Yeezy BSKTBL Knit Slate Blue
description:
The adidas Yeezy BSKTBL Slate Blue borrows design features from the Yeezy QNTM and 350 V2 CMPCT designs to create a responsive court shoe. The sole of the Yeezy BSKTBL is reminiscent of the QNTM, while its sock-like Primeknit upper arrives as a high-top form of the 350 V2 CMPCT.

The adidas Yeezy BSKTBL Slate Blue released in December of 2021 and retailed for $300.

name: Sand (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Foam RNR Sand (Kids)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Foam RNR Sand Kids was designed by performing artist Ye, the artist formerly known as Kanye West, and made its debut on his daughter, North West, in 2019.​
​
​The Yeezy Foam is a slip-on, lace-free shoe that comes in a beige/​desert sand hue designed for kids. The shoe has a durable and lightweight EVA foam midsole, made partly from harvested algae. For ventilation, the shoe has strategically mapped vents giving an aesthetic cut-out detailing. It has a branded insole while the outsole has a wavy traction pattern for a strong grip on kids’ feet.
​
​The adidas Yeezy Foam RNR Sand Kids was released on March 26, 2021, with its retail price set at $65.

name: UFO
title: Puma LaMelo Ball MB.01 Lo UFO
description:
Continuing the storyline that LaMelo's on-court skills and swagger are not of this planet, the Puma MB.01 Lo LaMelo Ball UFO draws inspiration from UFOs (Unidentified Flying Objects) and their radiant tractor beams. It is constructed with a light grey mesh and ripstop upper with reinforced seams and embroidered bird wing detailing similar to that of the high-top iteration. Geared for an explosive style of play, a Puma Hoops Nitro Foam midsole delivers maximum responsiveness and stability. Bright blue semi-translucent outsoles and sock lining add the finishing touch.

The Puma MB.01 Lo LaMelo Ball UFO released in June of 2022 and retailed for $120.

name: Core Black Green
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Core Black Green
description: While soldiers rave about the seven core Army values, the sneaker community can go off about the adidas Yeezy Boost V2 350 Core Green. Setting a battlefield tone, this silhouette comes with a core black upper and sole. They also feature core black "SPLY-350" branding across a core green stripe on both sides. These dropped in November 2016 and retailed at $220. Dont be afraid to break rank and place a Bid on StockX.

name: Pure (Restock Pair) (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy Slide Pure (Restock Pair) (Infants)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Slide Pure Restock Pair Infants provide enough comfort and support to stay on the feet for an average amount of walking throughout the day.

This sleek and smooth model is made from two pieces of injected EVA foam. The design was created with comfort and utility in mind. Rather than having laces, the shoes use a certain material that allows them to easily stay on the feet.

The adidas Yeezy Slide Pure Restock Pair Infants was first introduced to the market in November of 2021. The starting retail price for this product was $70 for children’s sizing.

name: Chocolate
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 750 Chocolate
description: The adidas Yeezy Boost 750 Light Brown/Gum (Chocolate) was initially rumored to be a Brown/Glow In The Dark version but as the release details became clearer, adidas Originals calls this Kanye West design Light Brown and Gum with a semi-translucent outsole. While previous Yeezy Boost 750 releases shared the colors, this version became affectionately known as the Chocolate Yeezy Boost 750. This Yeezy Boost colorway initially hit "the internets" months before the actual October 15th, 2016 release date and has a color palette from previous "Yeezy Season" apparel collections. Although many of the sneaker blogs showcased a version with a glow in the dark outsole. The shoes carried an initial retail price of $350 but as is the case with most of Kanye West's collaborations with adidas, the pre-release buzz pushed resell prices significantly higher. Time will tell if the "Chocolate" Yeezy Boost 750 Light Brown/Gum will be as popular as other Kanye West designs but as of now, this Yeezy Boost looks promising.

name: Azure Reflective
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Azure Reflective
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Azure Reflective is an athletic sneaker created by adidas in collaboration with rapper Kanye West’s fashion line Yeezy. 

This iteration of the adidas Yeezy Boost 380 features a knit upper, allowing for breathability and flexibility in movement. The upper is mostly shades of brown, with an Azure patch running across the midsoles. This patch is perforated to keep your feet cool during extended wear. Aside from the colorful and straightforward upper with round laces, the chunky outsole completes the look. This oversized outsole starts near the top in a somewhat transparent darker shade of brown and fades to a lighter brown at the bottom. 

What we like most about this shoe is the subtle branding that can only be found on the insole. The lack of prominent branding on the shoe's upper allows the unique design and color scheme to take center stage. The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Azure Reflective was released on December 12, 2020, for a price of $250.

name: Desert Sand
title: adidas Yeezy Slide Desert Sand
description: DISCLAIMER: US and UK sizing is the same and does not require any conversion.

name: Dark Slate (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy 450 Dark Slate (Kids)
description:
The adidas Yeezy 450 Dark Slate (Kids) is a kids' iteration of the avant-garde design of the Yeezy 450. Crafted from knit, these Dark Slate sneakers feature a black colorway from top to bottom.

The Yeezy 450 for kids takes on a dark slate colorway in comparison to the popular Cloud White Yeezys. A heavily knit upper class in Dark Slate lines up the 40 Dark Slate Kids cagey design. The ankle entry features a sock-like construction for a snug fit around your foot. Rope laces, still taking on the black color, secure the fit while an EVA midsole creeps up from the underfoot to deliver cushioning. An adidas logo under the wavy outsole signs off the subdued aesthetic of these Kanye West-inspired kicks.

What is the standout feature of the sneaker? As our experts state, it is the quirky design that takes on a dark slate colorway for a subdued yet eye-catching aesthetic. These kicks are a must-have for kids foraying into the world of high fashion. The adidas Yeezy 450 Dark Slate (Kids) was released on June 26, 2021, retailing for $140.

name: AFEW Beauty of Imperfection
title: ASICS Gel-Lyte III AFEW Beauty of Imperfection
description: The ASICS Gel Lyte III Afew Beauty of Imperfection is a highly anticipated release that showcases the brand's commitment to quality and innovation. The shoe features a unique design that celebrates the beauty of imperfection, with a mix of materials and textures that create a one-of-a-kind look. The upper is made of premium suede and leather, with a mix of colors that include beige, brown, and blue. The shoe also features a speckled midsole and a gum outsole, adding to its overall aesthetic appeal. The ASICS Gel Lyte III Afew Beauty of Imperfection is set to release on February 26th, 2022, with a retail price of $170. This shoe is sure to be a hit among sneaker enthusiasts and collectors alike, thanks to its unique design and high-quality construction. Something we love about ASICS Gel Lyte III Afew Beauty of Imperfection is the way it celebrates imperfection and individuality. Our experts think the standout feature of this shoe is its mix of materials and colors, which create a truly unique look. We also love the attention to detail and quality that ASICS is known for, making this shoe a must-have for any sneakerhead.

name: White Classic Red
title: ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 White Classic Red
description:
The ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 White Classic Red was released as part of the long-running Gel Kayano series, a collection of running shoes designed for stability and support by ASICS.

The shoes have a predominantly silver upper, complemented by red and black accented lines running across the upper. It is made from a combination of mesh and other synthetic materials which help to keep the shoes lightweight and breathable, allowing for optimal air ventilation during intense running activities. The sole unit, on the other hand, utilizes the Trusstic System to reduce the weight of the sole unit while maintaining structural integrity.

The ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 White Classic Red has a few standout features that our experts love, including Gel cushioning, Dynamic DuoMax Support System and an Impact Guidance System (IGS). They all work together to help improve comfort and performance during running activities. The shoes were initially released at the retail price of $130 on December 29th, 2020.

name: BAIT Misfits
title: ASICS Gel-Lyte V BAIT Misfits
description:
The ASICS Gel Lyte V BAIT Misfits features a striking BLACK/DEEP ORANGE colorway, embodying a bold and energetic fusion of hues inspired by the iconic Misfits punk rock band.

The ASICS Gel Lyte V "Misfits" showcases a dynamic design with a black base and vibrant orange accents on the toe, heel, and midsole. Crafted with premium materials, it offers both style and durability. The Gel Lyte V technology ensures exceptional cushioning and comfort while paying homage to the Misfits punk rock band's iconic aesthetic. This sneaker seamlessly merges bold color contrast and performance for an unforgettable footwear experience.

At StockX, we're captivated by the sneaker’s distinctive colorway, seamlessly blending BLACK/DEEP ORANGE hues inspired by the legendary Misfits punk rock band. This striking fusion captures attention and pays homage to an iconic era. The ASICS Gel Lyte V BAIT Misfits was released on the 25th of April, 2015, and sold for $150.

name: Mono Carbon
title: adidas Yeezy QNTM Mono Carbon
description:
The adidas Yeezy QNTM Mono Carbon nods to the original Yeezy QNTM that debuted in 2020. It features a marbled grey Primeknit construction with a suede toe wrap and semi-translucent sole that seamlessly meshes into the upper. The main differentiator in this pair is that it has a slightly more yellowed sole and subtle hits of a greenish grey on the upper.

The adidas Yeezy QNTM Mono Carbon released in April of 2022 and retailed for $250.

name: Pink Glo
title: ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Pink Glo
description:
The ASICS Gel Kayano 14 Pink Glo is a retro-styled running shoe that was designed to have a late 2000s aesthetic. The athletic brand released it as a nod to its original Gel Kayano series, and it was the first pair of shoes in the collection to be designed by someone other than Toshikazu Kayano.

This ASICS Gel Kayano model has a midsole that features gel technology cushioning, which is meant to provide support and help absorb shock. The upper part of the shoe is made from a mixture of mesh and leather that are in various colors, including pink, black, and gray.

A feature that our experts like about the ASICS Gel Kayano 14 Pink Glo is the sock liner, as it was made with a process that helps to decrease water usage and carbon emissions. This pair of shoes was released on July 1st, 2023, and had a retail price of $150.

name: Desert Sand (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Foam RNR Desert Sand (Kids)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Foam RNR Desert Sand Kids is a result of a collaboration between adidas and Yeezy. The shoes were designed by popular musician Kanye West, who owns the Yeezy brand. This is not the first project the two brands have collaborated on.

The adidas Yeezy Foam RNR Desert Sand Kids was released in adult, kids' and infant sizing in the 'desert sand' colour scheme. They have been constructed using harvested algae and EVA, which gives the shoe its futuristic design and makes it lightweight.

The adidas Yeezy Foam RNR Desert Sand Kids was released on 11th June 2022 at a retail price of $208.

name: White Grand Shark
title: ASICS EX89 White Grand Shark
description:
The ASICS EX89 White Grand Shark was designed by Toshikazu Kayano to pay homage to basketball shoes from the late 1980s.

The White/Grand Shark colorway of the ASICS EX89 features an upper that begins with a base of white leather. White leather overlays adorn the toe cap, vamp, eyestays, mudguard, collar, and heel. Dark blue leather overlays course both horizontally and vertically across the side panel in the iconic ASICS pattern. White laces crisscross over a white mesh tongue that sports tonal ASICS branding. The padded sock liner in white mesh matches the insole, which sports blue ASICS branding. ASICS branding embroidered in blue hits the heel in a window between the leather overlays.

What we appreciate most about this sneaker is the sole. The midsole has enhanced cushioning thanks to FF BLAST technology, and the sail and gray rubber outsole features a traction pattern inspired by a city skyline. The ASICS EX89 White Grand Shark was released on February 1, 2023, for a retail price of $110.

name: Turtledove
title: adidas Yeezy 350 Cleat Turtledove
description:
The adidas Yeezy 350 Cleat Turtledove was a part of the adidas Yeezy collection created in collaboration with rapper Kanye West.

The 350 Cleat Turtledove features an upper design that is made from a breathable and flexible material, while the studded sole is designed to offer traction and stability. The studded sole is made from durable black rubber, with 12 studs for maximum grip. The Turtledove colorway is a nod to the original Yeezy Boost 350 sneaker, with a combination of gray and off-white hues.

The adidas Yeezy 350 Cleat Turtledove was released on September 15, 2016, at a retail price of $250.

name: French Blue Pure Silver
title: ASICS Gel-1130 French Blue Pure Silver
description:
The ASICS Gel-1130 French Blue Pure Silver features an upper crafted from synthetic leather paneling on top of mesh fabric in French Blue’s deep navy hue.

Japanese athletic wear brand ASICS is known for the comfort and durability of their running shoes. Evolving over decades, the GEL-1130 sneaker offers a tribute to the ninth iteration of the GEL-1000 series. Updates include the synthetic leather paneling, which modernizes the shoe’s aesthetic. The heel’s GEL technology offers ASICS’ signature cushioning. A white curvilinear midsole pops against the Pure Silver and navy upper, balanced by a black and French Blue outsole, with GEL technology in the heel. ASICS branding accents the tongue.

In our opinion, the best feature of the Gel-1130 is its Pure Silver overlays, which give the shoe versatility for street or sports wear. The ASICS Gel-1130 French Blue Pure Silver released on March 10, 2022, and retailed for $85.

name: Triple Black
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 750 Triple Black
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 750 Triple Black is the outcome of the collaboration between adidas and Kanye West's fashion brand - Yeezy.

The Triple Black adidas Yeezy Boost 750 sneaker features an all-black colorway with a suede upper. The suede upper also features a mid-foot strap, offering additional lockdown support for a secure fit. At the same time, its Boost midsole, made of adidas' Boost technology ensures cushioning and comfort. The design is completed by the treaded rubber outsole for traction.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 750 Triple Black was released on December 19th, 2015 and it retailed at $350.

name: Oyster Grey (Gallery Dept. Edition)
title: ASICS Gel-1130 Oyster Grey (Gallery Dept. Edition)
description:
DISCLAIMER: The ASICS Gel-1130 Oyster Grey (Gallery Dept. Edition) is a custom sneaker that shares the same style ID as the base sneaker used. The ASICS Gel-1130 Oyster Grey colorway will not pass the verification process under this product page, if you would like to buy or sell the ASICS Gel-1130 Oyster Grey, please click here.

Please Note, The ASICS Gel-1130 Oyster Grey (Gallery Dept. Edition) are hand painted, therefore each painted pattern may vary by shoe.

name: Synth (Non-Reflective)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Synth (Non-Reflective)
description:
The summer of 2019 started with yet another regional Yeezy release, featuring the Synth Yeezy Boost 350 V2. Following successful regional releases of the Clay, Trfrm, and Hyperspace colorways, the Synth released exclusively in Africa, Asia, the Middle East, and Australia alongside the Antlia 350s in Europe.

This V2 sports more muted, neutral tones than previous colorways, features a nude Primeknit upper, a gum sole, the removal of the traditional heel tab, and the signature translucent side stripe. This particular adidas Yeezy sneaker retailed for $220.

name: Energy Glow
title: adidas Yeezy BSKTBL Knit Energy Glow
description:
The adidas Yeezy BSKTBL Knit Energy Glow is a basketball shoe that was released as part of a collaboration between adidas and Kanye West.

The Energy Glow Yeezy BSKTBL Knit iteration has an upper that is made from PrimeKnit and a heel that is made from molded polyurethane material. The sneaker comes in an Energy Glow color scheme with black accents. The shoe also features a Boost midsole and has a 3D-printed shank plate. The outsole is translucent and is constructed from rubber. It also features a lug pattern with the adidas logo at the center. The tongue is integrated to form a single unit with the collar and is completed with black round laces.

Our experts say that one of the notable features of the adidas Yeezy BSKTBL Knit Energy Glow is its extended knit collar. The collar is made from stretchy material and extends up past the ankle. The shoe was released on February 18th, 2022, at a retail price of $300.

name: Oxford Tan
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Oxford Tan
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Oxford Tan was released as a collaborative design by adidas and Kanye West as part of their Yeezy series of sneakers. The release of this sneaker features a Light Stone/Oxford Tan-Light Stone colorway.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Oxford Tan features a Light/Oxford Stone Primeknit upper with monochromatic Oxford laces, a tan Boost outsole, and suede stripes on the medial sides. Furthermore, this sneaker includes ribbed rubber midsole to prevent you from slipping and falling.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Oxford Tan was released on December 29th, 2015, at a retail price of $200.

name: Buzz City
title: Puma LaMelo Ball MB.01 Buzz City
description:
Taking its name and palette from the Charlotte Hornet's City Edition uniforms, the Puma MB.01 Buzz City arrives in a black knit upper with turquoise wings embroidery surrounding the collar. On the tongue, a decorative "1" illustration is stylized identically like Ball's distinctive chest tattoo. At the base, a sculptural black sole with Nitro Foam technology is a perfect match for hoopers with explosive play styles.

The Puma MB.01 Buzz City released in February of 2022 and retailed for $125.

name: MX Sand Grey (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR MX Sand Grey (Kids)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR MX Sand Grey (Kids) feature injected EVA foam and part-harvested algae for a lightweight build on the slip-on. The silhouette is dressed in a swirl of earth-toned colors for this iteration.

The flexible Yeezy slides flaunt ventilation ports on the sides as well as the vamp on the forefoot. Coral accents decorate the MX Sand Grey colorway on the silhouette. Underfoot is a wavy pattern with treads like on the Stone Sage hpr. The threads deliver traction across various surfaces, while the ports are designed for breathability around your foot. A soft top layer on the foot bed further aids in the slip-ons' comfort proposition.

What our experts like about the Yeezy Foam Sand Greys is their resulting colorway, which has earthy tones with playful coral and pink accents, ideal for kids. The adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR MX Sand Grey (Kids) was released on December 11, 2021, retailing for $60.

name: Bone (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy Slide Bone (Infants)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Slide Bone (I) is a footwear option for infants that was released as part of the Yeezy brand by Kanye West.

The Infants Yeezy Slide Bone are made of foam material and have a bone color. The Yeezy branding is printed on the insole of the slides which have a slip-on design. The slide also features a wide strap across the top with a ribbed texture. The outsole of the Yeezy Slide Bone Infants is made of the same foam material as the rest of the slide, with a series of grooves strategically placed for added grip and stability.

The adidas Yeezy Slide Bone (I) was released on December 6th, 2019 at a retail price of $35.

name: Oil (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy Desert Boot Oil (Infants)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Desert Boot Oil (Infants) brings the classic Desert Boot to little feet. Born from a collaboration between adidas and Kanye West, these shoes juxtapose high fashion against rugged workwear.

The Desert Boots are crafted with premium materials, including a suede upper and mesh lower layers for breathability and durability. Their solid black "Oil" colorway is representative of the Yeezy brand's affinity for natural and neutral color schemes. Their boot silhouette provides ankle support while a lace closure system provides an adjustable fit. Their outsole is made of durable rubber to guarantee traction, and a pull tab on the tongue allows parents to assist with easy on-and-off wear.

What our experts love most about the adidas Yeezy Desert Boot Oil (Infants) is the unique stitching patterns that add to their overall aesthetic. These shoes originally retailed at a price of $100 when they initially released on September 14, 2019.

name: Stone Sage (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Stone Sage (Infants)
description:
First released in March of 2022, the adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Stone Sage Infants are durable, yet made out of EVA foam to be as lightweight as possible while still protecting the wearer’s feet.

Made in the USA, the adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Stone Sage Infants is composed of natural algae that have been harvested from lakes for the purpose of keeping these bodies of water clean. Mapped vents are strategically placed around the shoe to provide breathability, particularly on the upper part of the foot. The shoe is designed with warmer weather in mind.

The adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Infants originally retailed at $45.

name: Concrete Teal Pink (Women's)
title: ASICS Gel-1130 Concrete Teal Pink (Women's)
description:
Originally released in 2008, the ASICS Gel-1130 Concrete Teal Pink (Women's) is a women's-exclusive sneaker inspired by the brand's Gel-Kayano lineup. It features many of the same elements as the sneakers that were included in this collection.

The upper on this sneaker has synthetic leather overlays paired with mesh underlays and is constructed out of about 20% recycled materials. It also has ASICS' patented TRUSSTIC technology incorporated into it to provide extra support and stability, along with GEL technology cushioning designed to set you up with more than enough shock absorption.

The thing our experts like the most about this sneaker, though, is that it manages to maintain an old-school look and feel while also providing new-age technological touches that turn it into a modern running shoe that can provide superior performance. The ASICS Gel-1130 Concrete Teal Pink (Women's) was released on July 1, 2023, for a retail price of $95.

name: Cinder Reflective
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Cinder Reflective
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Cinder Reflective features a Cinder Primeknit upper, with almost the entirety of the construction featuring a dark grey color that evokes tones of charcoal, and it is broken up only by a deeper black stripe running through the center of the Primeknit. From there, a full midsole that features the patented Boost technology and a gum-colored outsole and bright yellow pad at the heel complete the design.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Cinder Reflective released in April of 2020 and retailed for $220.

name: Moonrock
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Moonrock
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Moonrock is a part of the adidas Yeezy Boost line, which is a series of sneakers created by adidas in collaboration with rapper and fashion designer Kanye West.

The Yeezy Boost 350 Moonrock has outsoles that are made from rubber material and insoles that are designed using adidas' Boost technology, which uses a foam sole to provide cushioning. The upper and laces are made of a single-piece Primeknit material. The Yeezy Boost 350 Moonrock is available in a grayish-brown "moonrock" colorway, which features contrasting dark gray stitching and a translucent outsole.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Moonrock was released on November 14, 2015 at a retail price of $200.

name: Cecilie Bahnsen Mary Jane Pure Silver
title: ASICS GT-2160 Cecilie Bahnsen Mary Jane Pure Silver
description:
The ASICS GT 2160 Cecilie Bahnsen Mary Jane Pure Silver delivers the Danish designer's couture-inspired take on the lifestyle running shoe, reimagined as a Mary Jane hybrid featuring a transparent upper adorned with illustrated floral lines and gleaming metallic silver overlays.

The Cecilie Bahnsen x ASICS GT 2160 'Pure Silver' combines transparent paneling with intricate floral prints. The design cleverly shifts focus from the typical ASICS branding on the medial and lateral walls. The distinctive two-eyelet lace setup functions as a graceful bow on the toe, accompanied by a subtle ASICS branding detail. The result is a harmonious fusion of innovative design elements, transcending conventional tropes while maintaining ASICS's legacy of quality and comfort.

At StockX, we're captivated by the shoe's unique transparent paneling with delicate floral prints. Handpicked by our experts, this feature adds an artistic touch that diverges from the norm, distinguishing it from typical lifestyle running shoes. The ASICS GT 2160 Cecilie Bahnsen Mary Jane Pure Silver was released on the 19th of July, 2023, and sold for $200.

name: Static (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 V2 Static (Kids)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 V2 Static (Kids) is a lifestyle sneaker designed for children that incorporates the same technologies found in the original Yeezy Boost 700 model.

The gray upper is made of a woven material with a loose weave, while the overlays come in velvety nubuck leather in off-white. The overlays create a curve along the side panel that matches wavy line details. The sneaker features a lace closure that combines eyelets and loops. Something that makes the sneaker stand out is the mudguard design. It doesn’t wrap around the full front of the sneaker. Instead, it leaves a small part exposed, revealing the mesh beneath. In terms of technology, the shoe has a full-length Boost unit in the midsole and herringbone designs on the outsole.

Our StockX experts like the reflective detailing on the eyelets, laces, and lines along the quarter-panel. The kid-sized adidas Yeezy Boost 700 V2 Static (Kids) was released on August 2nd, 2022, and retailed at $180.

name: Orange
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Orange
description:
Yeezy introduced a new colorway to their 700 MNVN series with the adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Orange, now available on StockX. Although the silhouette is similar to previous models, this shoe differs by displaying "700" branding on the upper using compact materials.

This Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN is comprised of an orange nylon upper paired with reflective detailing. A solid black sole with Boost cushioning completes the design. These sneakers released in February of 2020 and retailed for $220.

name: Pirate Black (2016)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Pirate Black (2016)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Pirate Black (2016) comes in a pirate black, pirate black-pirate black color palette.

The Pirate Black adidas Yeezy Boost 350 (2016) features a design that incorporates a Primeknit upper for breathability and flexibility. The shoe's midsole features adidas' proprietary Boost technology, which provides energy return and recovery, cushioning, and responsiveness, ensuring comfort. The shoe features reinforced suede for durability and protection. The sneaker has a rubber wrap around the ankle, providing stability and arch support.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Pirate Black (2016) was released on February 19, 2016, and sold for a retail price of $200.

name: Black Red (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Black Red (Infants)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Core Black Red 2017 I was part of the Yeezy and adidas collaborative collection.

The sneaker has an all-black colorway throughout the lace-up, and a black Primeknit upper with a stitched red SPLY-350 logo on the medial quarter panel and center seam. The crimson stitched pattern is also displayed on the pull tab at the heel. The structure is supported by a full-length boost midsole that is covered in semi-transparent chunky black rubber with a vertical linear pattern. 

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Core Black Red 2017 I debuted on February 11th, 2017 and retailed at $140.

name: Light Grey Glow In the Dark
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 750 Light Grey Glow In the Dark
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 750 Light Grey Glow In the Dark is a high-level glowing-in-the-dark sneaker. The glowing sneakers detail a light grey patent leather elevated with a flexible mid-foot band.

Since its release in the market, the adidas Yeezy Boost 750 has gained a lot of profit because of its flexible, absorbent, comfortable, and athletic quality. The glowing sneakers have round rope shoe laces, come in light grey, and are made from a foam material.

The Yeezy Boost 750 Light Grey Glow In the Dark released on November 6, 2016 at a price of $350.

name: Teal Blue
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Teal Blue
description:
In continuation of its ever growing 700 line, Yeezy brand keeps it simple with the Adidas Yeezy Boost 700 "Teal Blue", now available on StockX. Trailing the releases of the Magnet and Inertia colorways, this shoe stays true to the Yeezy aesthetic with a new tonal variation that stays in the same ballpark of other 700 releases.
This 700 is composed of a mix of grey and teal tones that are assorted amongst a mix of suede and mesh. A grey rubber midsole and gum outsole completes the design. These sneakers released in October of 2019 for $300.

name: Beluga Reflective (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Beluga Reflective (Kids)
description:
The three main colors that are used to dress the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Beluga Reflective Kids are Reflective, Steeple Grey, as well as Solar Red.

This V2 Beluga Reflective adidas Yeezy Boost 350 for kids showcases a mostly gray Primeknit upper accompanied by an orange side stripe bearing SPLY-350 branding. The knitted construction incorporates reflective fibers throughout, providing improved visibility when it's dark. The design of this shoe also features a full-length Boost midsole that is encased in a partially transparent rubber cage. This version of adidas Yeezy Boost 350 comes with a Steeple Grey lacing system that completes its design.

The Primeknit upper of this sneaker is one feature that our experts found to be attractive, more so among enthusiasts of outdoor activities due to its improved breathability. The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Beluga Reflective Kids hit the market for the first time on December 18, 2021, and retailed at $160.

name: Phosphor
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Phosphor
description:
The upper of the adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Phosphor pair is Neon Yellow with its pull tabs and toe featuring a black colorway.

The volt-based mesh upper of the sneaker was made available without shoelaces. Along with matching black sock liner and tongue, black overlay panels can also be seen at the heel counters and forefoot. The shiny silver "700" logo on the medial and lateral midfoot of the shoe by adidas and Yeezy is also featured. A black rubber outsole and white Boost-cushioned midsole complete the design.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Phosphor was launched on the 24th of April 2020, and retailed at $220.

name: J. Cole Black
title: Puma RS-Dreamer J. Cole Black
description:
The Puma RS Dreamer J Cole Black has become a celebrated version in the German sport and lifestyle brand catalog.
​
​This RS Dreamer sneaker by Puma features a mix of the dominant black and a multi-colorway throughout. Its upper design has a breathable mesh, and the suede overlays around the sneaker's ankle and the forefoot. The upper is in the black color scheme. The RS foam midsole is in contrasting red, mint, yellow, and purple accents.
​
​The Puma RS Dreamer J Cole Black originally was launched in July 2020, and its retail price was set at $125.

name: Bone
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Bone
description:
Yeezy added a new colorway to their 700 MNVN series with the adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Bone, now available on StockX. Although the silhouette dons a familiar Boost 700 sole, this shoe differs by displaying "700" branding on the upper using compact materials. 

This Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN is comprised of a Bone nylon upper paired with reflective detailing. A solid black sole with Boost cushioning completes the design. These sneakers released in April of 2020 and retailed for $220.

name: Ochre (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy Slide Ochre (Infants)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Slide Ochre Infants is crafted from rubberized foam with textured surfaces. The slides are rendered in an uneven finish, and a light brown color floods the minimalist build. The footbed offers step-in comfort, highlighted by a soft top layer marked with adidas’ three-stripe branding. Underfoot, the outsole features horizontal grooves that yield enhanced cushioning and traction.

The infant’s rendition of the adidas Yeezy Slide Ochre Infants was released in December 2021 and retailed for $35.

name: J Cole Ebony and Ivory
title: Puma RS-Dreamer J Cole Ebony and Ivory
description:
The Puma RS Dreamer J Cole Ebony and Ivory is a collaboration between Puma and J. Cole.

The Ebony and Ivory Puma RS-Dreamer J Cole comes in a Puma white and Puma black color palette. The shoe features a black and white textile upper, providing breathability and support. The midsole is equipped with Puma's innovative RS cushioning technology, which offers comfort, responsiveness, and energy return. The outsole is constructed from a durable rubber compound with multidirectional traction patterns to ensure retention and stability. Additionally, the shoe features subtle branding details, including J. Cole's "Dreamer" logo on the heel and Puma's RS insignia on the tongue.

One notable feature of the Puma RS Dreamer J Cole Ebony and Ivory is its color scheme. The shoe showcases a combination of ebony black and ivory white tones, creating a sleek and contrasting look. This color palette adds a sense of sophistication and versatility to the shoe. The Puma RS-Dreamer J Cole Ebony and Ivory was released on December 4, 2020, and sold for a retail price of $125.

name: Desert Sand (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy Foam RNR Desert Sand (Infants)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Foam RNR Desert Sand Infants is one of the offerings from the Yeezy Foam Runner collection designed by rapper Kanye West.

The shoe comes in a neutral beige color, with a detailed structure molded in one piece. The adidas Yeezy Foam RNR Desert Sand Infants has cut-outs that offer ventilation and complete the design. Completely made of an algae-based foam, this shoe springs when you take a step. The wave-like traction pattern on the sole provides grip and durability for regular life activities.

The adidas Yeezy Foam RNR Desert Sand Infant version was made available on 11 June 2022, retailing at $45.

name: Carbon (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Carbon (Kids)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Carbon (Kids) features a Primeknit upper with a mix of black and gray threads, creating a subtle look. The post-dyed monofilament side stripe on the kid's shoe's lateral side adds a black accent to the side that divides the upper, light gray weave from the lower, largely black construction.

It also comes with a second set of regular and no-tie stretch laces for easy wear and removal. The sneaker is equipped with adidas' signature Boost cushioning technology in the midsole, providing exceptional comfort and responsiveness. Its outsole is made of durable rubber, offering excellent traction and stability. A pull tab is included on the heel for easy on-and-off wear.

Something we find notable about the shoe is its iconic "SPLY-350" branding is integrated into the shoe's side stripe, adding a distinctive touch to its appearance. This adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Carbon (Kids) was released on October 2nd, 2020. The pair retailed at $160.

name: Enflame Orange (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy Slide Enflame Orange (Infants)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Slide Enflame Orange (Infants) designed for infants, is a comfortable sandal created in collaboration between Adidas and Kanye West's Yeezy brand. These infant sized Yeezy Slides come in a striking Enflame Orange colorway. The Yeezy branding is discreetly featured on the footbed.

These Yeezy Slides are designed as open-toed sandals, providing breathability and ease of wear. The backstrap ensures a secure fit, allowing infants to wear them comfortably without the risk of the sandals slipping off. These infant Yeezy Slides feature a convenient slip-on design. They are easy to put on and take off for parents who are on the move. The outsole of the adidas Yeezy Slide Enflame Orange (Infants) is made of durable rubber material that provides traction and grip, even on smooth surfaces.

What our experts at StockX truly appreciate about these sandals is the thoughtful, ergonomic footbed design. This footbed is made from EVA foam, which offers cushioning and support. The adidas Yeezy Slide Enflame Orange (Infants) was available at a retail price of $35 when it was released on June 21st, 2021.

name: Citrin (Reflective)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Citrin (Reflective)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Citrin (Reflective) features a reflective Citrin Primeknit upper with a mesh side stripe and textile heel tab. At the base, a Boost cushioned sole adds the finishing touch.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Citrin (Reflective) released in September of 2019 and retailed for $220.

name: Glow Green (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy Slide Glow Green (Infants)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Slide Glow Green (Infants) comes in a glow green color scheme.

The Glow Green adidas Yeezy Slide (Infants) showcases an upper made from a resilient synthetic fabric, for its softness and durability, ensuring a secure and cozy fit. The design of the slide facilitates effortless slipping on and off. With a contoured footbed, the slide offers both arch support and cushioning, promoting comfort and providing necessary assistance. The outsole is equipped with a textured pattern, enhancing stability and delivering reliable traction.

The infants’ sizing of the adidas Yeezy Slide Glow Green was released for $35 on September 6, 2021.

name: Cloud White (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy 450 Cloud White (Kids)
description: The adidas Yeezy 450 Cloud White Kids is a highly sought-after sneaker that was released on March 6, 2021. This shoe features a unique design that is sure to turn heads, with a white knit upper that is both breathable and comfortable. The shoe also features a unique lacing system that provides a secure fit, as well as a durable rubber outsole that provides excellent traction. The adidas Yeezy 450 Cloud White Kids is made from high-quality materials, ensuring that it will last for years to come. This sneaker is available at a retail price of $140, making it an affordable option for parents looking for a stylish and comfortable shoe for their kids. Don't miss out on this must-have sneaker for your little ones!

name: Turtledove (2015)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Turtledove (2015)
description:
Released in 2015, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Turtle Dove is the first colorway to kick off Yeezy's expansive 350 line. Composed of a grey and brown patterned Primeknit, the design was one of the most comfort focus Yeezy designs at the time and still is to this day. At the base, a grooved Boost outsole delivers adidas' renowned cushioning.

To shop the latest 2022 re-issue, click here.

name: Glow Green (2022) (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy Slide Glow Green (2022) (Infants)
description:
adidas Yeezy Slide Glow Green is a slide for infants. It features no stylistic change from the previous releases.

The adidas Yeezy Slide Glow Green has a light luminous green color. It is made from a comfortable and responsive molded Glow EVA foam. The foam is also lightweight and durable. The slide features groove placement on the underfoot to enhance traction and comfort. This kids' slide also has a strap to hold the heels firmly.

The kids adidas Yeezy Slide Glow Green debuted on 31st May 2022. During this release, it had a retail price of $50.

name: Pirate Black (2015)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Pirate Black (2015)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Pirate Black 2015 comes dressed primarily in a Pirate Black color scheme with small accents of dark gray and red.

This Pirate Black 2015 adidas Yeezy Boost 350 has a black Boost midsole, a Pirate Black/dark gray speckled Primeknit upper that features branded suede accents on its medial sides and red-accentuated heel tabs. This shoe also features patterned dark gray rope laces. A herringbone-patterned rubber outsole and an EVA midsole complete the design of this sneaker.

When making its debut on August 22nd, 2015, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Pirate Black 2015 had $200 as its retail price.

name: Cecilie Bahnsen Mary Jane Black
title: ASICS GT-2160 Cecilie Bahnsen Mary Jane Black
description:
The ASICS GT-2160 Cecilie Bahnsen Mary Jane Black gets a fresh twist courtesy of Danish fashion designer Cecilie Bahnsen. This Mary Jane-style running shoe arrives in an elegant black design and is expertly crafted from mesh. The shoe is adorned with meticulous detailing that is complemented by a convenient side touch strap.

The Cecilie Bahnsen Mary Jane Black ASICS GT-2160 upper u ndergoes a stylish transformation into an entirely black design, skillfully crafted from light mesh material. It is adorned with floral motifs and enhanced with glossy patent leather embellishments. Drawing inspiration from the Mary Jane footwear style, this reimagined structure replaces the traditional tongue with a cut-out portion secured by a floral strap and decorative laces. To provide a comfortable ride, the sneaker gets a black foam midsole encapsulating visible gel cushioning in the heel.

What our experts love about the ASICS GT-2160 Cecilie Bahnsen Mary Jane Black is the intricate floral patterns, which are a remarkable contribution from the renowned fashion designer, Cecilie Bahnsen. The shoe released on 19th July 2023 for $200.

name: Nice Kicks Spumoni
title: ASICS Gel-Lyte III Nice Kicks Spumoni
description:
The ASICS Gel Lyte III Nice Kicks Spumoni features a delectable colorway of ivory, chocolate, and pink, reminiscent of a delightful Spumoni ice cream treat, all wrapped up in the iconic Gel Lyte III silhouette.

The Nice Kicks Spumoni boasts a distinctive style, harmonizing ivory, chocolate, and pink hues reminiscent of Spumoni ice cream. Crafted with premium materials, its suede and leather upper exude quality and comfort. The sneaker is equipped with ASICS' renowned Gel cushioning technology and ensures a supportive stride. The split tongue design and signature ASICS branding on the heel complete the visually appealing and meticulously detailed ensemble.

As the StockX team, we're captivated by the sneaker's exceptional fusion of style and creativity. The delectable ivory, chocolate, and pink colorway pays homage to the iconic Spumoni ice cream, while the premium suede and leather materials emphasize luxury and comfort. The ASICS Gel Lyte III Nice Kicks Spumoni was released on the 11th of June, 2021, and sold for $130.

name: Rihanna Fenty Black
title: Puma Avanti VL Rihanna Fenty Black
description:
FENTY x PUMA presents the Avanti, worn by legends and reborn by Rihanna. This classic silhouette was taken from the PUMA archives and reimaged by Rihanna through her own personal design language and creative treatment. This new sport-fashion icon features a premium leather upper and a gum sole, and appears in two bespoke versions: classic black and white, and allover silver chrome.

Buttery soft leather upper ; Leather piping around formstrip ; Attached fold over tongue in soft leather ; Debossed Fenty logo on tongue, quarter, and heel with gold foil finish ; Brown leather lining ; EVA foam wedge midsole ; Gum outsole.

name: Blue Oat Reflective
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Blue Oat Reflective
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Blue Oat Reflective arrives in an all-blue oat color scheme.

The Blue Oat Reflective adidas Yeezy Boost 380 has an upper that is made with a PrimeKnit material that offers flexibility and breathability. The shoe features a sock-like construction for a snug and secure fit. The sneaker's lacing system ensures a customizable fit. The shoe's midsole features adidas' signature Boost technology, which provides cushioning and energy return while offering responsiveness and comfort. The sneaker has an outsole crafted with a durable rubber compound, providing grip and traction.

The standout feature of the adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Blue Oat Reflective is its reflective elements. These sneakers feature reflective detailing on the upper, which illuminates when exposed to light. This unique characteristic adds a captivating and futuristic touch to the design. The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 was released on July 24th, 2020, and sold for a retail price of $250.

name: Sneaker Freaker atmos Alley Cats
title: ASICS Gel-Lyte III OG Sneaker Freaker atmos Alley Cats
description:
The ASICS Gel Lyte III OG Sneaker Freaker Atmos Alley Cats release draws inspiration from the stray cats often found in the urban backstreets of Tokyo and Melbourne.

The GEL LYTE™ III OG features a captivating color scheme that evokes vibrant neon lights synonymous with bustling cityscapes. The striking purple tones adorning the upper and midsole are a fusion of Atmos' signature blue and SNEAKER FREAKER's defining red. This collaboration is exemplified by asymmetrical logos embellishing the tongue, heel, and sock liner, adding a distinctive touch to the sneaker's design ethos.

What we love about the design is its attention to detail in uniting Atmos' blue and red hues within the purple palette, demonstrating an exceptional design curation level. This remarkable interplay of colors and logos celebrates the spirit of collaboration and captures the essence of urban aesthetics and individual expression. The ASICS Gel Lyte III OG Sneaker Freaker Atmos Alley Cats was released on the 4th of July, 2022, and was sold at $160.

name: Nickelodeon Slime (GS)
title: Puma LaMelo Ball MB.02 Nickelodeon Slime (GS)
description: The Puma LaMelo Ball MB02 Nickelodeon Slime GS is a vibrant and playful sneaker that is sure to turn heads. The shoe features a bright green Nickelodeon slime-inspired upper, with black and white accents throughout. The Puma logo is prominently displayed on the side of the shoe, while the LaMelo Ball logo can be found on the tongue. The shoe is made with high-quality materials, including a durable rubber outsole and a comfortable cushioned midsole. The upper is made with a combination of synthetic and textile materials, providing both breathability and support. The Puma LaMelo Ball MB02 Nickelodeon Slime GS is set to release on December 21, 2022, with a retail price of $110. This shoe is sure to be a hit with fans of both Puma and LaMelo Ball, as well as anyone looking for a fun and unique sneaker to add to their collection. Something we love about the Puma LaMelo Ball MB02 Nickelodeon Slime GS is the bold and playful design, which is sure to make a statement wherever you go. Our experts think the standout feature of this shoe is the Nickelodeon slime-inspired upper, which is both eye-catching and fun. Overall, we love the combination of style and quality that Puma has brought to this collaboration with LaMelo Ball.

name: Rihanna Fenty Aged Silver
title: Puma Avanti C Rihanna Fenty Aged Silver
description:
FENTY x PUMA presents the Avanti, worn by legends and reborn by Rihanna. This classic silhouette was taken from the PUMA archives and reimaged by Rihanna through her own personal design language and creative treatment. This new sport-fashion icon features a premium leather upper and a gum sole, and appears in two bespoke versions: classic black and white, and allover silver chrome.

Leather based chrome upper and formstrip ; Attached fold over tongue in leather based chrome material ; Laser etched Fenty logos on tongue, quarter, and heel FOT ; EVA foam wedge midsole ; Gum outsole ; Fenty branded footbed.

name: Back Streets of Japan Pack Aqua Angel
title: ASICS Gel-Lyte III OG Back Streets of Japan Pack Aqua Angel
description:
The ASICS Gel Lyte III OG Back Streets Of Japan Pack Aqua Angel takes a bold step with its iconic split tongue design, arriving in two captivating colorways, Aqua Angel / Mako Blue and Ivory Black, where the dynamic interplay of vibrant hues through energizing color blocking reflects the lively ambiance of Japan's nocturnal streets.

The GEL LYTE III Backstreets of Japan pack boasts textile uppers combined with leather overlays, achieving a harmonious blend of durability and style. Enhanced by GEL cushioning technology, the sneaker offers unparalleled comfort and shock absorption, making every step a delight. Complemented by a rugged rubber outsole, it ensures exceptional traction and longevity, making this sneaker a testament to ASICS' commitment to quality and innovation.

What truly stands out to our team about this sneaker is the incorporation of GEL cushioning technology. This ingenious feature enhances comfort and provides unparalleled shock absorption, creating a smooth and supportive stride. The ASICS Gel Lyte III OG Back Streets Of Japan Pack Aqua Angel was released on the 19th of March, 2021, and sold for $110.

name: Calabasas Core White
title: adidas Yeezy Powerphase Calabasas Core White
description:
The adidas Yeezy Powerphase Calabasas Core White was part of a collaboration between rapper Kanye West and adidas. It draws its inspiration from the 80s with an Off-White buttery leather design throughout.

The Yeezy Powerphase features a premium off-white leather upper with perforated 3-Stripes, gold foil Calabasas branding on the lateral side, and an adidas wordmark on the eye stay logo window. The sneaker arrives in an all white colorway with a matching rubber sole and matching laces.

The adidas Yeezy Powerphase Calabasas Core White was originally released on the 28th of March 2017 for an initial retail price of $120.

name: Slate Azure
title: adidas Yeezy BSKTBL Knit Slate Azure
description:
The adidas Yeezy BSKTBL Knit Slate Azure is Kanye West’s second basketball shoe, made in collaboration with adidas. Unlike other versions, this sneaker features a bold colorway of Slate Azure and black.

The sneaker’s sock-like silhouette makes it stand out from other basketball shoes and identifies it as part of the Yeezy BSKTBL Knit family. The upper is made of PrimeKnit, which conforms to the foot’s shape and adds breathability. This knit material features a texturized weave that fades from Slate to Azure. A black ankle collar fits securely over the ankle and contributes to the shoe’s sock-like appearance. The semi-translucent midsole houses adidas Boost technology, which decreases impact stress and adds subtle detailing.

Something our experts at StockX like is the way the black laces match the back ankle collar. The adidas Yeezy BSKTBL Knit Slate Azure was released on June 10th, 2022, and retailed at $300.

name: Team Colors White Bluemazing
title: Puma LaMelo Ball MB.01 Lo Team Colors White Bluemazing
description:
The Puma LaMelo Ball MB01 White Blue has a NITRO foam sole and midsole, as well as breathable mono-mesh uppers that provide airflow. This model also has non-slip rubber outsoles that gives extra traction. 

This LaMelo MB01 by Puma in White Blue has a white body with bright royal blue details. This pair of shoes also has white laces with a white tongue, and a winged image that appears in the middle of the tongue in the same royal blue color. The lining of the shoe is black.

The Puma LaMelo Ball MB01 White Blue model first became available for purchase in July of 2022. This pair of shoes started at a retail price of $120.

name: Yeshaya (Reflective)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Yeshaya (Reflective)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Yeshaya (Reflective) features a reflective Yeshaya Primeknit upper with a translucent mesh side stripe. From there, a cushioned Boost sole completes the design.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Yeshaya (Reflective) released in January of 2020 and retailed for $250.

name: Stone Sage (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Stone Sage (Kids)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Foam Sage Kids shoe model is water-resistant and was made to be worn for everyday activities.

This model is a brown slip-on shoe that was designed with comfort and utility in mind. While it covers the entire foot, it has holes to help provide breathability and airflow. The sole of the shoe has extra padding to help make the wearer’s feet as comfortable and supported as possible.

The adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Stone Sage Kids first were released on the market in March of 2022. The starting retail price for this pair of shoes was $60.

name: Rick and Morty
title: Puma RS-X Rick and Morty
description:
Puma teams up with Justin Roiland and Dan Harmon to create this Puma RS-X Rick and Morty, which commemorates the adventures of the cartoon grandson-grandfather duo.

Resting on the green midsole of the Puma RS-X is an EVA midsole adorned with electric green patterns. The upper features a breathable textile in safety yellow, with leather overlays covering the mudguard area. On the quarters, the safety yellow flow on leather overlays continues. However, slanted green stripes cover the entire length of these panels, and an "RS RUNNING SYSTEM" tagline appears on the lateral side. The heel has a leather underlay, a deeply ribbed counter in rubber, and a mustache that brings back the mesh material of the vamp.

What stand-out features are present on the Puma RS-X Rick and Morty? The shoe’s references to the fan-approved Ricky and Morty animation are outstanding. These include the green patterned midsole recalling intergalactic experiences and Rick’s and Morty’s faces in the inner tongue. The shoe has a May 26th, 2022 release date, and initially retailed at $120.

name: Cream
title: ASICS Gel-1090 V2 Cream
description:
The Asics Gel-1090 V2 in the luxe Cream colorway broke onto the scene on June 22, 2023, offering sneaker enthusiasts a fresh blend of heritage and innovation.

Encased in a creamy, smooth finish, this Gel-1090 V2 showcases a synergy between soft suede and adaptive mesh across its facade. Dominating the sneaker’s anatomy is the breathable mesh, while the supple suede elevates the design and creates a luxe feel, encompassing the mudguard and heel.

The distinctive Asics branding combined with the iconic Gel cushioning make this sneaker pop.
