Revel in the Gel's comfort tech, which promises an unparalleled ride, and the sole's dynamic traction pattern ensuring grip. The Asics Gel-1090 V2 Cream, a harmony of style and function, made its debut on June 22, 2023. This gem was priced at a cool $140 on release day.

name: Team Colors White High Risk Red
title: Puma LaMelo Ball MB.01 Lo Team Colors White High Risk Red
description:
The Puma LaMelo Ball MB.01 Lo Team Colors White High Risk Red has a white sole, midsole, and body. This model also features white laces and a variety of bright red details.
​​
​The shoes are primarily composed of a mixture of leather and breathable mesh. This model has a black interior lining, as well as the PUMA logo on the toe and the "1 of 1" inscription in red on the tongue. There are also red accents right on the ankle and a plastic criss-cross pattern near the sole.
​​
​Puma LaMelo Ball MB.01 Lo Team Colors White High Risk Red was first made available for purchase in July of 2022. The model's starting retail price was $120.

name: Shale Warm
title: adidas Yeezy 500 High Shale Warm
description:
adidas and Yeezy introduced the Yeezy 500 High Shale Warm in 2021. Even though there are a lot of 500 low colorways, this upcoming Shale Warm release is only the fourth high silhouette to release from Kanye West and the Three Stripes.

The adidas Yeezy 500 Shale Warm brings back the high cut silhouette with earthy tones. The upper shows off a mix of materials like neoprene, leather, and suede in earth tones. The sneaker is equipped with a rugged, non-marking outsole and a mudguard to help withstand any terrain. Tumbled leather detailing adds a more luxe feel to the boot-like silhouette.

The adidas Yeezy 500 Shale Warm released in February of 2021 for $220.

name: Pokémon Charmander
title: Puma Slipstream Lo PokÃ©mon Charmander
description: The Puma Slipstream Lo Pokemon Charmander is a highly anticipated release for sneaker enthusiasts and Pokemon fans alike. This shoe features a vibrant orange and yellow colorway inspired by the popular fire-type Pokemon, Charmander. The upper is constructed with a mix of suede and leather materials, providing durability and a premium feel. The Puma logo is embroidered on the side, while the Pokemon logo is featured on the tongue and heel. The Slipstream Lo silhouette offers a comfortable fit with a padded collar and tongue. This shoe was released on November 12, 2022, with a retail price of $100. Don't miss out on this unique and stylish collaboration between Puma and Pokemon.

name: NES
title: Puma Future Rider NES
description:
Inspired by the Nintendo Entertainment System (NES) console, the Puma Future Rider NES is a collaborative sneaker between Puma and Nintendo featuring the Puma Future Rider silhouette. 

The upper is made of a neutral Grey textile base with Light Grey Suede overlays on the forefoot, quarter panel, and heel. Black accents on the branded leather heel tab and Formstrip, ‘Puma branding on the quarter panel, and the tongue tag contrast the upper. Hits of Red appear on the 8-bit Super Mario Bros. graphic on the tongue tag, velcro straps on the sides, and midsole lining. Rounding out the design is a White midsole with Grey TPU inserts on the heels and a Black studded rubber outsole. Each pair comes with a hang tag branded with Nintendo controller buttons. 

What our experts love about this sneaker are the colorway and details. The unique details and Cream/Grey colorway set it apart from other Puma Future Rider models. The Puma Future Rider NES was made available on December 4th, 2020, for a retail price of $90.

name: Dazzling Blue (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Dazzling Blue (Infants)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Dazzling Blue Infants arrives in a Core Black and Dazzling Blue color scheme.

The Dazzling Blue adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 for infants features a classic silhouette that is built with a PrimeKnit upper, offering lightweight feel and breathability. The shoe features Boost technology in the midsole, ensuring cushioning and responsiveness. The shoe's outsole is made of durable rubber, providing traction and stability. The shoe features "SPLY-350" lettering on the dazzling blue stripe displayed on the side. The sneaker's design is completed with a lace-up closure and a pull tab at the heel for easy on and off.

Something we highlight about the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Dazzling Blue Infants is their eye-catching and vibrant color scheme. These sneakers feature a Dazzling Blue upper, which adds a bold and playful element to the design. The shoe was released on February 27th, 2022, and sold for a retail price of $140.

name: Zyon (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Zyon (Kids)
description:
The "adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Zyon (Kids)" was launched as part of the kids’ sports collection of the adidas Brand.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Zyon Kids is made from Primeknit/ knitted fabric material at the upper part and synthetic yarn at the soles. The sneaker comes with a Zyon color at the upper and white at the soles. The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Zyon Kids features elastic shoelaces placed on the non-metallic eyelets.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Zyon (Kids) became available on July 18th, 2020 at a retail price of $160.

name: Cloud White (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy 450 Cloud White (Infants)
description:
The adidas Yeezy 450 Cloud White (Infants) is an adidas Yeezy model intended to be worn by infants. With an all-cloud white colorway and an adidas Yeezy’s ultramodern design, the sneakers are an innovative piece of footwear that provides maximum comfort for your infant.

The adidas Yeezy 450 Cloud White (Infants) is built to fit like a sock with a knit upper which provides a cozy fit, along with an Ortholite sockliner and elastic cuff. The oversized outsole features a wavy traction pattern that almost reaches the cuff. It also features white laces, but the shoe itself is tieless and can be pulled over a baby’s foot with ease.

What our experts like most about the adidas Yeezy 450 Cloud White (Infants) is its fun build for a performance baby shoe. They’re the perfect wardrobe addition for any active infants and future sports stars. These sneakers were originally released on March 6, 2021, and sold at a retail price of $140.

name: Day-Lyte
title: ASICS Gel-Lyte III OG Day-Lyte
description: The ASICS Gel Lyte III OG Day Lyte is a classic sneaker that has been updated with modern materials and technology. The upper is made of a combination of suede and mesh, which provides both durability and breathability. The colorway is a mix of white, blue, and orange, which gives the shoe a fresh and vibrant look. One of the standout features of the ASICS Gel Lyte III OG Day Lyte is the Gel technology in the sole. This technology provides excellent cushioning and shock absorption, making the shoe comfortable to wear for extended periods of time. The outsole is made of rubber, which provides excellent traction on a variety of surfaces. The ASICS Gel Lyte III OG Day Lyte was released on June 11, 2021, and has a retail price of $120. This shoe is a great choice for anyone who wants a comfortable and stylish sneaker that can be worn for a variety of activities. Something we love about ASICS Gel Lyte III OG Day Lyte is the combination of classic design and modern technology. Our experts think the best features are the Gel technology in the sole and the durable yet breathable upper. What we love about the ASICS Gel Lyte III OG Day Lyte is the fresh and vibrant colorway. The standout feature of the ASICS Gel Lyte III OG Day Lyte is the excellent cushioning and shock absorption provided by the Gel technology. Our experts especially love the rubber outsole, which provides excellent traction on a variety of surfaces.

name: Inertia
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 V2 Inertia
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 V2 Inertia's upper contains an array of textures like soft nubuck, grained leather and mesh fabric. This sneaker starts with pale gray at the heel and then slowly graduates to lighter shades of blue like a gradient. A hard gray midsole with a ridged, cream-colored sole offsets the soft fabric and neutralizes the pale blue. The dash of peach offers the perfect counterbalance to the blues and grays, turning the adidas Yeezy Boost 700 V2 Inertia into a cheerful sneaker that was made for a spring release.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 V2 Inertia released in September of 2019 and retailed for $300.

name: Beluga Reflective (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Beluga Reflective (Infants)
description:
This adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Beluga Reflective (Infants) is building upon the success of the original Beluga colorway, which was first introduced back in September 2016. This version incorporates reflective elements that add a distinctive flair to the shoe. 

This infant's sneaker features reflective 3M parts that are very visible. The shoe's upper is made of gray Primeknit and has a vivid "Solar Red" side stripe with contrast "SPLY-350" marks. The Three Stripes logos are used on the insoles and sock liner as additional branding. The medial side's suede midfoot panel has been removed, and a new elastic fit has taken its place in place of the pull tab. Full-length BOOST sole components that are enclosed and express a transparent gray tone complete the shoe's appearance.

Our experts love this infant’s sneaker upper which features a mix of gray and orange hues with a subtle reflective yarn woven throughout, creating an eye-catching effect when exposed to light. The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Beluga Reflective (Infants) was released on December 18th, 2021, and retailed at $140.

name: LaMelo Ball Galaxy
title: Puma RS-X LaMelo Ball Galaxy
description: The Puma RS LaMelo Ball Galaxy is a highly anticipated sneaker release that boasts a unique and eye-catching design. The upper is made of a black mesh material with galaxy-inspired accents in shades of blue, purple, and pink. The Puma logo is prominently displayed on the side in white, while the RS technology adds a touch of retro flair to the overall look. The midsole is made of lightweight foam and features a rubber outsole for added durability and traction. The sock liner is also cushioned for added comfort during wear. The Puma RS LaMelo Ball Galaxy is set to release on May 27th, 2022, with a retail price of $120. Something we love about the Puma RS LaMelo Ball Galaxy is the unique and bold design that sets it apart from other sneakers on the market. Our experts think the standout feature of this sneaker is the galaxy-inspired accents that add a pop of color and personality to the overall look. We also love the combination of retro and modern elements, making it a versatile sneaker that can be worn for both casual and athletic occasions.

name: Bright Cyan (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Bright Cyan (Kids)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Bright Cyan (Kids) is a vibrant and eye-catching sneaker that brings the bold Yeezy design to younger fans. Featuring a bright cyan upper with black accents, this model offers a striking and modern look. The lightweight nylon construction ensures durability and comfort, while the reflective detailing adds a touch of flair. The Boost cushioning technology provides superior comfort and support.

The Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN, designed by Kanye West, is known for its futuristic design and exceptional performance. The Bright Cyan colorway stands out with its bold and vibrant palette, perfect for making a statement. The black overlays and reflective detailing enhance the overall look, while the chunky midsole showcases the innovative Boost technology. These design elements highlight the model's unique blend of style and function.

Priced at $220, the adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Bright Cyan (Kids) was released on June 7, 2021. This sneaker not only delivers on style but also ensures maximum comfort for kids. Add a touch of Yeezy flair to your child's footwear collection with this vibrant sneaker.

name: Pirate Black (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Pirate Black (Infants)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Pirate Black (Infant) is a Yeezy Boost 350 model sneaker that was designed for infants.

The Yeezy Boost 350 Pirate Black (Infant) comes in a blend of colors, including Pirate Black, Blue Gray, and Core Black. The midsole is designed with adidas' exclusive Boost technology, which is known for its responsiveness and cushioning properties. The outsole is made from a durable rubber material that provides excellent traction, ensuring that your infant has a firm grip on the ground when walking or running. The sole is lightweight, which makes it comfortable for your little one to wear for extended periods. The stretchy laces also ensure that the shoe fits snugly around your infant's foot.

We think that the standout feature of the shoe is the prime-knit upper construction, which provides excellent breathability and a snug fit around the infant's foot. The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Pirate Black (Infant) was released on August 27th, 2016, at a retail price of $130.

name: Not From Here Red Blast (GS)
title: Puma LaMelo Ball MB.01 Not From Here Red Blast (GS)
description:
The midsole of the Puma MB01 LaMelo Ball Red Blast (GS) for grade schoolers is in the same red color as the rest of the shoe. The sneaker is designed to be lightweight, for longer workout sessions in mind.

The body of the shoe is made from a breathable mesh material, coupled with plastic fused overlays. On the middle part of the foot, you will find red win(GS) for grade schoolers that are stitched into the fabric, which wrap around to the back part of the heel.

The Puma MB01 LaMelo Ball Red Blast (GS) for grade schoolers was first released in December of 2021. It had an initial retail price of $125 for men’s sizes.

name: J. Cole Blood, Sweat and Tears
title: Puma RS-Dreamer J. Cole Blood, Sweat and Tears
description:
The Puma RS-Dreamer J. Cole Blood, Sweat and Tears was inspired by the tenacity, determination, and hard work it takes to make it on the court or the microphone. 

They feature a bright palette, cutting-edge performance technology, and the storytelling that has come to be associated with Cole and PUMA Hoops' collaboration. The upper is covered in a Fiery Red foundation that is entirely knitted. The RS foam midsole, dynamic lacing system, tongue, and heel pull tabs are all covered in Fiery Red. The suede overlays, however, opt for a darker shade of Ribbon Red. Cole's "Dreamer" emblem is imprinted in black on the heel, while a white cord lacing system and little forefoot flourish add more contrast. Its outsole, inner lining, and tongue tab RS logo are dressed in grey suede.

What we find remarkable about this shoe is the RS-style running shoe foam and basketball-specific ProFoam combination in the midsoles below to create a hybrid cushioning system. This Puma RS-Dreamer J. Cole Blood, Sweat and Tears released on August 17, 2020 and retailed at $125.

name: Sneaker Politics Always Ready
title: ASICS Gel-Lyte III Sneaker Politics Always Ready
description:
The ASICS Gel Lyte III Sneaker Politics Courtyard design was inspired by Sneaker Politics Founder and CEO Derek Curry’s time in the Army. This pair features rich green/black canvas colorway underlays that mimic military gear, including Neoprene detailing with an American flag pattern at the toe box and an embroidered Politics letter "P" branding at the heel.

The ASICS Gel Lyte III Sneaker Politics Courtyard silhouette retains its signature split-tongue formation and has a comfortable rubber outsole with GEL technology for optimal impact absorption.

ASICS Gel Lyte III Sneaker Politics Courtyard launched in May 2022 and was retailed at $150.

name: Supernova (GS)
title: Puma LaMelo Ball MB.02 Supernova (GS)
description:
The Puma LaMelo Ball MB.02 Supernova (GS) is a kid-sized version of NBA player La Melo Ball’s MB.02 Supernova, a performance basketball shoe with a vibrant colorway.

Like the adult-sized version, the Supernova (GS) features a colorway of Firey Coral and Ultra Orange. Flame motifs decorate the vamp and streak up the heel and along the side panels. Ultra Orange was first seen on the LaMelo Ball MB.01 and made a comeback on this sneaker's woven mesh upper and the NITRO midsole. Regarding branding, the "1 of 1" wings logo and "M.E.L.O" can be found on the heel in bright blue. A TPU clip supports the heel, while the traction pattern on the rubber outsole grips the court.

Our experts at StockX like the "RARE" graphic on the outsole. The grade school-sized Puma LaMelo Ball MB.02 Supernova (GS) was released on October 21, 2022, and retailed at $110.

name: Onyx (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Onyx (Kids)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Onyx (Kids) is a comfortable sneaker that hails from the design collaboration that once existed between Kanye West and adidas, that adidas now controls. This sneaker is specifically sized for kids.

The Kids’ Adidas Yeezy Boost 380 in Onyx features an upper crafted with black and brown fibers of stretchy, breathable Primeknit. Black rope laces feature a black lace lock that matches the heel tab and Prime knit collar. The Boost midsole offers a soft landing and energy return with every step, encased in a thin black rubber cage. A gum rubber outsole features wavy lines of traction and vents through which you can see the white Boost.

Our favorite aspect of this sneaker is the subtle side-panel stripe of all-black that works its way through the upper of this kids’ sneaker. The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Onyx (Kids) was released on November 28, 2020, for an original retail price of $170.

name: Angelo Baque Rebirth of Cool
title: ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Angelo Baque Rebirth of Cool
description:
The ASICS Gel Kayano 14 Angelo Baque Rebirth of Cool showcases a blend of colors, featuring a grey, black, silver, and blue upper, elegantly accented by a vibrant red-orange detail and a touch of yellow tracing the outer edge of the sole.

Crafted with a distinct style, the Kayano 14 Angelo Baque Rebirth of Cool boasts a sleek and contemporary design. The upper, blending shades of grey, black, silver, and blue, exudes an understated yet captivating allure. This collaborative masterpiece showcases meticulous attention to detail, with a vibrant red-orange accent adding a pop of contrast. The integration of advanced Gel cushioning technology ensures optimal comfort and support, while the yellow trim along the outer sole edge adds a playful touch to its overall aesthetic.

Our team is captivated by the Kayano 14 Angelo Baque Rebirth of Cool’s remarkable fusion of artistic expression and performance. The harmonious blend of colors, from the sophisticated greyscale to the striking red-orange accent, creates an eye-catching visual narrative. The ASICS Gel Kayano 14 Angelo Baque Rebirth of Cool was released on the 30th of July, 2021, and retailed at $180.

name: Safflower (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Safflower (Infants)
description:
The adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Safflower (Infants) imagines the signature Yeezy 700 V3 Safflower in a size for babies.

Like the adult-sized version, the infants’ model features an RPU overlay that forms a cage around the mesh upper. RPU is made of rubber as well as other materials often found in molded plastic, so the overlay cage appears stiff, but it has some give. The sneaker gets its name from the safflower-colored mesh with gray stripes that peeks out from behind the cage. On the inside, a contrasting black bootie provides a secure fit and tonally matches the thin laces. The sneaker doesn’t have a tongue, which contributes to its sleek design.

Our experts at StockX like the rounded elements that can be found throughout the shoe, including the rounded toe. The infant-size adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Safflower (Infants) was released on November 14th, 2020, and retailed at $140.

name: Sulfur (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Sulfur (Kids)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Sulfur Kids is a futuristic, one-piece design that comes in a lighter Sulfur colorway and is constructed out of lightweight EVA and harvested algae.

The monochromatic shoe features oval and circular perforations for aeration during the summer heat, including a defined rubber tread for additional stability and in-sole support. The adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Sulfur Kids footwear is slightly brighter than the previous Ochre and Desert Sand colorways.

The adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Sulfur Kids’ earthy tone color palette footwear was released in April 2022, retailing at $65.

name: Galaxy (GS)
title: Puma LaMelo Ball MB.01 Galaxy (GS)
description:
The Puma MB01 LaMelo Ball Galaxy (GS) for grade schoolers for grade schoolers is designed after professional basketball player LaMelo Ball’s playoff shoes. It’s available in full family sizing, so everyone can enjoy a pair.

The Puma MB01 LaMelo Ball Galaxy (GS) for grade schoolers features bright orange accents and thick shoelaces, matched with a vibrant galactic print. The protective sock liner helps to keep both your feet and lower ankle covered from the elements. Around the ankle, you will find embroidered win(GS) for grade schoolers in an electric blue, which stands in contrast against the green gecko-colored rubber outsole and plastic fuse overlaying the heel.

Released in April 2022, the Puma MB01 LaMelo Ball Galaxy (GS) for grade schoolers originally retailed at $125.

name: MX Cream Clay (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR MX Cream Clay (Infants)
description:
With simple designs and a color scheme of two-tone shades, the adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR MX Cream Clay (I) generally emphasizes a minimalist look. 

The top, which is constructed of a combination of lightweight EVA, has a base color of cream with brown and cream splashes that look as if they were painted on with a brush. Flowing lines and numerous punched holes for amphibious wear distinguish the distinctive silhouette. With a slip-on design and an elasticized collar that provides a snug fit and simple on/off functionality, the Yeezy Foam RNNR is intended to be worn without laces.

What we think is the notable feature of this slip-on infant shoe is the use of sustainable materials in its design. The upper is made from an algae-based foam material, contributing to eco-friendly manufacturing practices. The adidas Yeezy foam RNNR MX Cream Clay (I) was released on 2nd August 2021 and retailed at the price of $40.

name: Zyon (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Zyon (Infants)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Zyon Infants comes in a Zyon color scheme.

The Zyon adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 (Infants) adopts a classic silhouette with an upper made of Primeknit, providing comfort and flexibility. The sneaker also features a zig-zag pattern on the Primeknit upper. The midsole incorporates adidas' signature Boost cushioning technology, which provides cushioning and responsiveness and ensures extra comfort and support. The outsole is composed of a durable rubber compound that provides grip and stability.

One notable feature of the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Zyon Infants is its colorway. The shoe showcases a blend of earthy and neutral tones, including shades of grey, beige, and brown. This color palette creates a versatile and fashionable look. The infants’ sizing of the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Zyon was released on July 18, 2020, and originally sold for a retail price of $140.

name: Safflower (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Safflower (Kids)
description:
adidas and Kanye West teamed up to release the boundary-pushing adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Azael in late 2019. They followed it up about a year later by unveiling the adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Safflower (Kids), which was the same shoe with a more kid-friendly design.

This version of the adidas Yeezy 700 V3 had a neutral upper made from monofilament mesh and yellow striations peeking out from behind it. It also had a glow-in-the-dark RPU cage along with a black inner bootie to hold kids’ feet in place when they put these on. It was finished off with a herringbone rubber outsole that delivered superior traction.

In our expert opinion, adidas made the right call by creating the adidas Yeezy 700 V3 in kids' sizes like this. This adidas x Yeezy creation, in particular, had a look and feel that made it a natural fit for the younger crowd. The adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Safflower (Kids) was introduced on November 14, 2020, for a retail price of $160.

name: Flax (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy Slide Flax (Infants)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Slide Flax (Infants) introduces a chic yet functional option for infants, combining Kanye West’s signature minimalist design with practicality for summer. Perfect for beach days, poolside play, or casual outings, this slide offers a blend of style and comfort tailored for little ones. The Flax colorway ensures a sleek and versatile look.

Crafted from durable EVA foam, the Yeezy Slide Flax provides a lightweight yet supportive fit, perfect for tiny, active feet. Its contoured footbed ensures ergonomic comfort, while the soft ridged outsole delivers grip and stability on slippery surfaces. Designed with convenience, the slip-on construction makes for easy on-and-off wear.

Whether splashing by the pool or strolling on the warm sand, the Yeezy Slide Flax combines functionality with Yeezy’s iconic style. This slide is the ultimate summer footwear for your little adventurer, offering all-day comfort and a little flair. The adidas Yeezy Slide Flax (Infants) was released on August 22, 2022, and retailed at $40.

name: Butter Goods Whisper White Prism Violet
title: Puma Slipstream Low Butter Goods Whisper White Prism Violet
description:
The Puma Slipstream Low Butter Goods Whisper White Prism Violet is a sports-turned-street sneaker designed as a collaboration between Puma and Australian skate brand Butter Goods.

This version of the Puma Slipstream Low is made with a paneled smooth white leather upper. The toe box features a single line of perforations just under the laces for breathability, while white leather overlays form the toe cap and mudguard. On the sides of the shoe, two lines of perforations are found. Prism Violet leather overlays also peek through under the perforations on the sides. The word "Butter" appears in purple on the lateral side at the front of the ankle, while the Puma brand name adorns the tongue in large white and red letters. The white heel counter gives way to a shiny purple heel collar, and the shoe sits atop a white branded rubber sole and tan speckled outsole.

Our favorite thing about this shoe is the paneled leather design, which adds visual interest even as the shoe is mostly white. The Puma Slipstream Low Butter Goods Whisper White Prism Violet was released on April 23, 2022, for $130.

name: Resin (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Slide Resin (Kids)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Slide Resin Kids is a kids’-exclusive slip-on shoe from the adidas Yeezy Slide lineup in a Resin colorway.

Constructed with injected EVA foam, this slip-on shoe features a single-strap upper dressed in a monochromatic Resin hue. Plush cushioning is used on the footbed for comfort. Minimal branding details are featured on this Yeezy slide with the adidas Three Stripes debossed on the footbed. Rounding out this shoe’s design is an outsole with a series of strategically placed flex grooves for traction. 

What our experts love about this Yeezy slide is its design and comfort. The injected EVA foam provides lightweight durability, while the footbed cushioning provides comfort. Strategic flex groove placement on the outsole offers optimal traction and comfort. The versatile Light Green Resin colorway gives this slip-on shoe a unique and eye-catching look. The adidas Yeezy Slide Resin Kids was released on December 6th, 2019, for a retail price of $45.

name: Glow Green (2022) (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Slide Glow Green (2022) (Kids)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Slide Glow Green 2022 are made from light-weight injected EVA foam and with a green glow in the dark color. These adidas Slides feature a plain, minimalist design without any branding apart from the small trefoil logo on the footbed. The adidas Yeezy Slide Glow Green 2022 Kids are slip-on shoes with a relatively big upper that covers most of the foot. They also have deep horizontal grooves on the sole.

The adidas Yeezy Slide Glow Green 2022 Kids was first made available for retail in May, 2022, at the price of $60.

name: Resin (2022) (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Slide Resin (2022) (Kids)
description:
Designed for both indoor relaxation and outdoor adventures, the adidas Yeezy Slide Resin 2022 (Kids) is a versatile footwear option. Whether worn poolside, at the beach, or casually around the house, these slides offer a blend of style and functionality.

A neutral, earthy tone serves as the shoes’ sole colorway, creating a sleek look that resonates with the Yeezy brand's commitment to minimalist yet fashion-forward design. These shoes feature a one-piece molded EVA foam construction and discretely embossed adidas and Yeezy logos on the footbed, as well as an open-toe for breathability. Their body incorporates a user-friendly slip-on design, making these slides a convenient choice for youngsters who are learning to manage their footwear independently.

What our experts love most about the adidas Yeezy Slide Resin 2022 (Kids) is the distinct ribbed pattern, which delivers not only a visually appealing texture, but also enhanced traction. These shoes retailed at an original price of $45 when they first released on September 24, 2022.

name: Alvah (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Alvah (Infants)
description:
The adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Alvah (Infant) is part of the Yeezy Boost series created by adidas in collaboration with rapper Kanye West.

The Yeezy 700 V3 Alvah for infants comes in an Alvah colorway. Underfoot, the sneaker features a full-length EVA midsole that provides cushioning and support for little feet. The midsole is designed to absorb shock and reduce impact, reducing the risk of injuries. The outsole is constructed using lightweight rubber that provides additional traction and durability. The lacing system integrates seamlessly with the upper, providing a locked-in feel that is ideal for active children.

We think that the standout feature of the adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Alvah (Infant) is its design. The shoe features a lightweight and breathable upper made of a two-layer mesh material that is both durable and comfortable. The upper also incorporates an RPU cage that wraps around the midfoot, providing additional support and stability. The shoe was released on April 11th, 2020 at a retail price of $140.

name: Rock Ridge Red Blast
title: Puma LaMelo Ball MB.01 Rock Ridge Red Blast
description:
The Puma MB01 LaMelo Ball Grey Red is the first signature shoe designed by Charlotte Hornets’ 20-year-old sensation Lamelo Ball and the German sportswear giant Puma.

Dressed in a two-tone grey and red color scheme, this sneaker features a breathable greyscale upper contrasted by orange branding and design cues. Underfoot, it boasts Nitro-Foam cushioning. This cushioning is held into position with a semi-translucent rubber compound. To offer its wearers protection from sprains, it features heel padding.

The Puma MB01 LaMelo Ball Grey Red was released on the 18th of February, 2022. At the time of its release, this colorway had a retail price of $125.

name: Slate (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Slate (Kids)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Slate (Kids) is a children sized sneaker of the popular adult version of the same name and color, and an updated version of the Yeezy Boost 350.

This Yeezy Boost 350 V2 version has a PrimeKnit upper that provides a snug, comfortable fit that conforms to the shape of foot, which is important when kids are in their shoes all day. The slate-colored upper features a Core Black side stripe detail with the iconic SPLY-350 text in the middle. The sneaker also has a cross lacing system for easy fit.

We think a standout feature of the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Slate (Kids) is the semi-translucent midsole that contains the trademarked polymer Boost foam to keep kids’ feet feeling fresh and ready for whatever comes their way. Released on September 3rd, 2022, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Slate (Kids) sold for a price of $160.

name: Pure (First Release) (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Slide Pure (First Release) (Kids)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Slide Pure (First Release) (Kids) is a slide that was released as part of a collaboration between adidas and Kanye West.

The Yeezy Slide Pure was made specifically for kids and features a pure colorway. It is made from lightweight EVA foam in a sculpted shape. This molded structure is designed to provide a snug, comfortable fit for young feet. It features an adidas logo embossed on the outer edge. The slide also features a contoured footbed to provide additional cushioning and support, which adds to the overall comfort level of this slide.

We think that one of the standout features of the adidas Yeezy Slide Pure (First Release) (Kids) is its construction. This unique material provides both durability and water resistance, which makes it an ideal sandal for summer months or when splashing around in the pool. The slide was released on April 26th, 2021, at a retail price of $50.

name: Ice Studios Blue
title: ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Ice Studios Blue
description:
The ASICS Gel Kayano 14 Ice Studios Blue showcases a striking blue and yellow colorway, fusing vibrant hues for an eye-catching and energetic aesthetic.

The Men's ICE STUDIOS X GEL KAYANO 14 showcases its signature synthetic leather and mesh construction, which ensures durability and breathability. However, this iteration elevates the design with captivating glacier blue tones that exude a sense of coolness, while lemon yellow color pops inject vibrant energy. The shoe features a supportive midsole with ASICS Gel cushioning technology for optimal shock absorption. Its durable outsole ensures reliable traction while coordinating laces complete the sleek and dynamic design.

Our team is thrilled by the shoe’s glacier blue and lemon-yellow colorway. It's a stunning blend of vibrant tones that sets this shoe apart, instantly catching the eyes of our team. This striking design showcases ASICS' commitment to innovation and style, making it a standout choice in the sneaker world. The ASICS Gel Kayano 14 Ice Studios Blue was released on the 12th of August, 2022, and sold for $150.

name: Yecheil (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Yecheil (Infants)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Yecheil (Infant) is part of a collaboration between adidas and Kanye West.

The Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Yecheil was released in infant sizes and features a Yecheil colorway with a patterned upper that has a mixture of different textures and shapes. The upper is made of soft and flexible PrimeKnit material that provides a comfortable and accommodating fit for your little one. This sneaker also comes with a Boost sole that offers unparalleled cushioning and support for your baby's developing feet. This sole technology is designed to provide energy return with every step, making it perfect for active little ones who love to play and explore.

We simply love the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Yecheil (Infant) for its slip-on design that makes it very easy to put on and take off. This is especially useful for restless babies. The sneaker was released on December 20th, 2019, at a retail price of $140.

name: Light (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Light (Infants)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Light (Infant) is a highly sought-after sneaker created through a collaboration between adidas and Kanye West, the American rapper, and fashion designer.

The shoe features a distinctive upper crafted using PrimeKnit material, which is lightweight and breathable, offering a comfortable snug fit. It has cream as the predominant color which also extends to the sole unit. This Yeezy Boost 350 V2 retains some of the signature design elements of the silhouette like the distinctive stripe pattern on the side, and the iconic "SPLY-350" text on the lateral side.

One thing our experts love about the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Light (Infant) is the incorporation of Boost technology into the midsole. This helps with cushioning the foot, while also providing impact absorption which helps to enhance a comfortable experience for everyday wear. The infant-sized shoes were first released for retail in August 2021 for $140 retail.

name: Static (Non-Reflective) (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Static (Non-Reflective) (Kids)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Static (Non-Reflective) (Kids) is a kid-sized version of the recognizable adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2. This iteration of the Boost 350 V2 does not come with reflective detailing or tape.

The sneaker features an upper constructed with white and grey Primeknit. Although the upper is made of the same woven material, the Primeknit is woven into different patterns that create a textured look across the shoe. No-tie elastic laces secure the sock-like sneaker and form a zigzag pattern. On the lateral side, a translucent stripe can be found. This stripe allows the foot to breathe and breaks up the minimalist upper design.
What do our experts love most? The TPU cage wraps around the Boost midsole and contrasts the upper’s stretchy material. The kid-sized adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Static (Non-Reflective) (Kids) was released on August 2, 2022, and retailed at $160.

name: Iridescent Dreams (GS)
title: Puma MB.01 LaMelo Ball Iridescent Dreams (GS)
description: The Puma MB01 LaMelo Ball Iridescent Dreams GS is a stunning sneaker that combines style and performance. The shoe features a sleek black upper with iridescent accents that shimmer in the light. The Puma logo is prominently displayed on the side of the shoe in a bold white font. The midsole is made of lightweight foam that provides cushioning and support, while the outsole is made of durable rubber that offers excellent traction on any surface. The Puma MB01 LaMelo Ball Iridescent Dreams GS is made with high-quality materials that are designed to last. The upper is made of synthetic leather and mesh, while the midsole is made of EVA foam. The outsole is made of rubber and features a herringbone pattern that provides excellent grip. This sneaker was released on August 22, 2022, and has a retail price of $95. It is available in grade school sizes. Something we love about the Puma MB01 LaMelo Ball Iridescent Dreams GS is the unique iridescent accents that give the shoe a futuristic look. Our experts think the best features of this sneaker are its lightweight foam midsole and durable rubber outsole. We also love the sleek black upper and bold Puma logo. The standout feature of the Puma MB01 LaMelo Ball Iridescent Dreams GS is definitely the iridescent accents, which make this shoe a real head-turner. Our experts especially love how comfortable and supportive this sneaker is, making it perfect for both casual wear and athletic activities.

name: Be You (GS)
title: Puma LaMelo Ball MB.01 Be You (GS)
description:
The Puma MB01 LaMelo Ball Be You GS is an addition to the line resulting from a long-running collaboration between German-based footwear company Puma and NBA point guard Lamelo Ball.

Designed for grade-schoolers, this shoe’s upper is constructed from textile mesh. Atop the mesh sit several 3D-printed designs, varying in color. For cushioning, this sneaker utilizes a full-length NITRO foam on its midsole, while for traction and durability it features an outsole made using a nonslip rubber compound.

The Puma MB01 LaMelo Ball Be You GS was released on July 29, 2022. At the time, this basketball shoe’s retail price was $95.

name: Quiet Grey
title: adidas Yeezy Powerphase Quiet Grey
description:
The adidas Yeezy Powerphase Quiet Grey was released in addition to the collaborative line between adidas and Kanye West's Yeezy brand. It takes inspiration from vintage athletic footwear.

The shoe features a fully grey upper constructed from leather with Yeezy branding subtly embossed on the side panel, and "Calabasas" lettering present on the quarter panel. It also has perforated detailing on the side panels, forming the iconic three stripes, and toe box. There is also an additional Adidas logo on the heel of the rubber outsole.

The adidas Yeezy Powerphase Quiet Grey was released at the retail price of $120 on 18th September 2019.

name: Vermillion (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Vermillion (Infants)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Vermilion (I) gives the clog-like design a single-tone vermillion-finish, marking Kanye West's first time using monochromatic hues in his partnership with the adidas brand. 

The slip-on shoe design in infant sizing conveys a tonal brilliant and bold red aspect and serves as Kanye West's ongoing connection to the "Red October" colorway. The slip-on comprises a design accentuated by one piece of EVA foam that was partly constructed with algae developed hydroponically keeping to its trademark. The side panels and vamp have numerous oval-shaped holes punched out throughout the upper acting as vents that provide aeration, and the sculpted heel is made to cushion the back of the foot for a firm fit. At the bottom of the cutting-edge footwear style, treaded soles complete the shoe's design.

The adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Vermilion (I) was released on 29th October 2021. The infant's slip-on retailed at $40.

name: Flax (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Slide Flax (Kids)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Slide Flax (Kids) is a one-piece sandal released by Nike in collaboration with musician and songwriter Kanye West as part of the continued adidas Yeezy partnership.

The slides feature one-piece construction made with injected EVA foam which is lightweight and durable. They have a monochromatic color palette featuring a dark beige hue. The slides also have an open-toe design which allows maximum airflow into the footbed keeping your feet cool and comfortable even during a hot summer’s day. These adidas Yeezy slides feature very minimal branding with only a small adidas logo present.

One thing our experts love about the adidas Yeezy Slide Flax (Kids) is the contoured footbed which conforms to your feet’s shape for a more comfortable fit. They also have a serrated outsole for traction while also adding to the slides’ distinctive look. The kids-sized slides were released for retail in August 2022 for $50.

name: Black (Non-Reflective) (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Black (Non-Reflective) (Kids)
description: You can never have too much heat, so cop the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Black. This Yeezy Boost 350 V2 comes with a black upper, black midsole, and a black sole. These sneakers released in June 2019 and retailed for $220. Buy these today on StockX. Also available in adult sizing.

name: Season 6 Graphite
title: Yeezy Suede Desert Boot Season 6 Graphite
description: The Yeezy Suede Desert Boot Season 6 Graphite is a stylish and comfortable footwear option for those who want to make a statement. The boots are made from high-quality suede material that is both durable and soft to the touch. The graphite colorway is a versatile option that can be paired with a variety of outfits. Released on April 1, 2018, the Yeezy Suede Desert Boot Season 6 Graphite retails for $270. The boots feature a lace-up closure and a rubber sole for added traction and support. The Yeezy branding is subtly embossed on the side of the boot, adding a touch of sophistication to the overall design. One standout feature of the Yeezy Suede Desert Boot Season 6 Graphite is its unique silhouette. The boots have a sleek and streamlined design that is both modern and timeless. The suede material adds a touch of luxury to the overall look, making these boots a must-have for any fashion-forward individual. Something we love about the Yeezy Suede Desert Boot Season 6 Graphite is how versatile they are. They can be dressed up or down, making them a great option for any occasion. Our experts also love the high-quality suede material and the subtle Yeezy branding. Overall, the Yeezy Suede Desert Boot Season 6 Graphite is a great investment for anyone looking for a stylish and comfortable pair of boots.

name: Cloud White (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Cloud White (Infants)
description:
Featuring a Cloud White color scheme, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Cloud White Infant is a specific variation of adidas' Yeezy Boost 350 V2 sneakers appearing in infant sizing.    

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Cloud White Infant is made of a multicolored, re-engineered Primeknit upper. Its upper design also incorporates a woven side stripe made of post-dyed monofilament. Completing the upper design is the shoe's lacing system to ensure a comfortable and adjustable fitting. The sneaker's lower design features a BOOST sole unit that features adidas BOOST technology. BOOST midsole provides comfort through cushioning and impact absorption, while the outer treads optimize traction on various surfaces.

What we love about this adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Cloud White Infant that first appeared on the market on September 21, 2019 with a retail price of $140 is the PrimeKnit upper that makes it light and allows unrestricted airflow during wear.

name: Ronnie Fieg Tokyo Trio 252.1
title: ASICS Gel-Lyte III Ronnie Fieg Tokyo Trio 252.1
description:
Ronnie Fieg returned to his roots to celebrate the recent opening of KITH Tokyo with the release of the ASICS Gel Lyte III Tokyo Trio 252.1, now available on StockX. As part of the Tokyo Trio pack, this Gel Lyte III pays homage to a Japan-exclusive GEL-Lyte III colorway that Fieg wanted to bring to the US in 2007.

While the updated iteration of the ASICS Gel Lyte III 252, it retains most of the original color palette and adds a few design changes that provide a new luxe feeling. Multi-colored suede covers a majority of the silhouette atop a two-tone sole. The ASICS Gel Lyte III 252.1 released in July of 2020 and retailed for $180 USD.

name: Citrin (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Citrin (Infants)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Citrin (Infant) is part of the Yeezy Boost 350 collection that was created in collaboration with Kanye West and adidas. The sneaker comes in a Citrin colorway and was designed specifically for infants.

The upper of this Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Citrin (Infant) has a sock-like construction that provides a snug and comfortable fit for infants. The upper also features a translucent stripe that is made of semi-transparent monofilament yarn, which allows some light to pass through. The midsole is made of adidas’ Boost technology, which provides excellent cushioning and energy return. The sole is made of rubber and provides excellent traction on various surfaces. This ensures that infants can walk and run with ease without the risk of slipping. The shoe also has a lace-up closure that allows for a secure fit.

What we love about the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Citrin (Infant) is undoubtedly its 3D knit upper. The knit material is soft, lightweight, and breathable, ensuring that infant feet stay comfortable throughout the day. The shoe was released on September 23rd, 2019, at a retail price of $140.

name: Kith White
title: ASICS EX89 Kith White
description:
The ASICS EX89 Kith New York Knicks White features three different hues - white, blue, and orange.

The two main materials used in the making of this collaborative pair are leather and rubber. The upper of the shoe is primarily made up of white soft leather. It has a round toe, perforated cap, an Asics logo patch embroidered on tongue, and a padded color. All these rest on a white midsole and outsole, both of which are made of rubber. A linear pattern for traction completes the design.

The ASICS EX89 Kith New York Knicks White hit the market on November 7th, 2022 at a retail price of $130.

name: Ronnie Fieg Tokyo Trio Yoshino Rose
title: ASICS Gel-Lyte III Ronnie Fieg Tokyo Trio Yoshino Rose
description:
Ronnie Fieg returned to his roots to celebrate the recent opening of KITH Tokyo with the release of the ASICS Gel Lyte III Ronnie FiegTokyo Trio Yoshino Rose, now available on StockX. As part of the Tokyo Trio pack, this Gel Lyte III draws inspiration from the Yoshino cherry tree. The Yoshino Rose colorway mimics the tree’s beautiful blossoms with its pink branding and hits of red on the outsole.

The ASICS Gel Lyte III Yoshino Rose features a white mesh upper with grey suede overlays and pink detailing on its classic Tiger stripes. A multi-color outsole and ASICS branding on the heel completes the design. The ASICS Gel Lyte III Yoshino Rose released in July of 2020 and retailed for $180 USD.

name: BAIT Splash City
title: ASICS Gel-Lyte V BAIT Splash City
description: The ASICS Gel Lyte V BAIT Splash City is a limited edition sneaker that was released on April 11, 2015, with a retail price of $150. The shoe features a unique design inspired by the vibrant colors of the Golden Gate Bridge and the Bay Area. The upper is made of premium suede and leather, with a splash pattern that mimics the waves of the ocean. The shoe also features ASICS' signature Gel cushioning technology, providing superior comfort and support for all-day wear. The outsole is made of durable rubber, ensuring long-lasting traction and grip on any surface. The ASICS Gel Lyte V BAIT Splash City comes in a bold colorway of blue, teal, and orange, with accents of black and white. The combination of colors and patterns creates a striking visual effect that is sure to turn heads. Something we love about the ASICS Gel Lyte V BAIT Splash City is the attention to detail in the design, from the unique splash pattern to the Golden Gate Bridge-inspired colorway. Our experts think the standout feature of the shoe is the combination of comfort and style, making it a versatile option for any occasion. Overall, we love the ASICS Gel Lyte V BAIT Splash City for its bold design and superior performance.

name: Concepts Otoro
title: ASICS Gel-Lyte III Concepts Otoro
description:
The ASICS Gel-Lyte III Concepts Otoro features a tonal Coral Cloud plush suede upper with Pure Silver reflective detailing on the toe and heel wrap. A debossed Concepts insignia on the lateral heel and classic Gel-Lyte III split tongue completes the design.

The ASICS Gel-Lyte III Concepts Otoro released in June of 2021 and retailed for $180.

name: MX Sand Grey (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR MX Sand Grey (Infants)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR MX Sand Grey (Infants) is a collaboration between adidas and Kanye West. The shoe was specifically designed for infants and features an MX Sand Gray colorway.

The Yeezy Foam RNNR MX Sand Gray (Infants) is made from a special foam material that is both lightweight and durable. The shoe features a perforated design with large openings. The sole incorporates a single piece of foam material that runs the entire length of the shoe. The foam material is soft and lightweight, providing cushioning and shock absorption for the feet.

We believe that the standout feature of the adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR MX Sand Grey (Infants) is its unique slip-on design. Unlike traditional sneakers that require lacing, Velcro, or buckles to secure them to the feet, the Foam RNNR MX Sand Gray simply slides onto the foot like a sock. This makes it incredibly easy and convenient to put on and take off, which is especially useful for parents of young children. The shoe was released on December 11th, 2021, at a retail price of $40.

name: MX Cream Clay (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR MX Cream Clay (Kids)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR MX Cream Clay Kids was released as an addition to the Yeezy series of shoe designs. This kids' sizing sneaker comes in an Mx Cream Clay/Mx Cream Clay/Mx Cream Clay colorway.

The adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR MX Cream Clay Kids is constructed with an upper featuring multiple colors, including gray, clay, and cream adorning a striped camouflage pattern. The shoe showcases an eco-friendly design, with algae used as part of its construction, and EVA foam for durability and a lightweight feel. Additionally, perforation ports keep your feet cool and comfortable.

The adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR MX Cream Clay Kids was released on August 2nd, 2021, at a retail price of $60.

name: Light (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Light (Kids)
description: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Light Kids is a highly sought-after sneaker that combines style and comfort. This shoe features a light-toned Primeknit upper with a translucent stripe, providing a sleek and modern look. The Boost midsole technology offers superior cushioning and support, making it perfect for everyday wear. The release date for this shoe is August 28th, 2021, and it retails for $160. The Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Light Kids is made with high-quality materials, ensuring durability and longevity. This shoe is a must-have for any sneaker enthusiast looking for a stylish and comfortable option for their kids. Get your hands on this limited edition sneaker before it's too late!

name: Cinder (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy 450 Cinder (Kids)
description:
The adidas Yeezy 450 Cinder Kids is a modern lifestyle sneaker featuring a futuristic and avant-garde design with a sock-like silhouette. It is known for its distinctive molded upper that extends up the ankle.

The shoes have a neutral monochrome finish with Cinder, a medium charcoal grey hue, as the main color. They have an avant-garde design aesthetic featuring a breathable knit textile upper with an elastic mesh-like structure that wraps around the foot. It also has a chunky sole unit with the midsole extending to the sides to form a midfoot cage, while the outsole has a contoured shape that allows the foot to bend and flex naturally.

One feature our experts love about the adidas Yeezy 450 Cinder Kids is the midfoot cage which helps to add structure to the sock-like build of the shoe while also keeping it lightweight. The kids’ shoes were released for retail at the price of $145 on the 24th of March, 2022.

name: Enflame Orange (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Slide Enflame Orange (Kids)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Slide Enflame Orange (Kids) is a unique addition to the Yeezy line, reimagining the classic slide design with an infusion of Kanye West's signature avant-garde aesthetics.

The Enflame Orange Yeezy slides come in a Vibrant Orange hue, which immediately makes them stand out. The monochromatic orange covers the entire slide, including the strap and underneath the footbed, showcasing a blend of minimalist design with flair. The slides are made from a foam material, which keeps them lightweight and ensures maximum comfort during wear. This is further helped by the footbed, which conforms to the shape of the foot allowing for a snug fit.

What we love most about the adidas Yeezy Slide Enflame Orange (Kids) is the outsole, which has aggressive contour lines to maximize grip and traction, helping to prevent the foot from sliding around. The kids-sized shoe was released for retail on June 21st, 2021, priced at $45.

name: Lundmark (Reflective)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Lundmark (Reflective)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Lundmark Reflective made its debut at the Yeezy Season 3 fashion show in 2016 with the Lundmark Reflective colorway released as part of June 2019's regional-exclusive release.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 has an Off-White Primeknit upper that changes in dim conditions to reveal reflective details. The sneaker has a full-length adidas Boost cushioning midsole on top of a light tan rubber outsole with a pink middle stripe. The sneaker has a transparent stripe revealing a more cream-colored inner in place of the traditional SPLY-350 boost stripe.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Lundmark Reflective was released on 11th July 2019 with its retail price set at $250.

name: Triple White
title: ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Triple White
description:
The ASICS Gel Kayano 14 Triple White is a pinnacle of style and performance designed to elevate your footwear game.

The white Gel Kayano 14 Triple boasts an elegant colorway that exudes pure sophistication. The sneaker is built with premium materials that ensure comfort and durability. The design features ASICS' renowned GEL cushioning technology, providing support and shock absorption for a smooth ride. The combination of white hues and glacier-grey accents creates a versatile look that easily pairs with various outfits.

What truly makes our experts fall in love with this sole design is its ability to balance cushioning and stability seamlessly. The dual-density midsole provides the right amount of support without compromising on comfort, making it an ideal choice for both casual wear and intense workouts. ASICS' dedication to combining innovation with practicality shines through every detail of the sole design. The ASICS Gel Kayano 14 Triple White was released on the 8th of October, 2021, and sold for $160.

name: Ronnie Fieg Tokyo Trio Super Gold
title: ASICS Gel-Lyte III Ronnie Fieg Tokyo Trio Super Gold
description:
Ronnie Fieg returned to his roots to celebrate the recent opening of KITH Tokyo with the release of the ASICS Gel Lyte III Ronnie Fieg Tokyo Trio Super Gold, now available on StockX. As part of the Tokyo Trio pack, the Super Gold colorway nods to the US Olympic Team that was set to participate in the 2020 Tokyo Olympics.

The ASICS Gel Lyte III Super Gold features a white leather upper with gold Tiger stripes and red, white, and blue detailing throughout the design carries out its USA theme. They released in July of 2020 and retailed for $180 USD.

name: Arzareth (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Arzareth (Infants)
description:
The adidas Yeezy 700V3 Arzareth (Infants) is a downsized version of the adult sneaker. Despite its smaller size, it retains many of the key features from the adult version.

Just like the adult version, this sneaker incorporates a comfortable and breathable Primeknit upper, ensuring a snug and supportive fit for infants. It has a monofilament-designed mesh top in ice blue with RPU overlays comprised of glow-in-the-dark materials. Although this model comes with no-tie stretch laces, it also comes with a set of regular laces in case you wish to switch things up. Last but not least, for ultimate comfort and durability, the herringbone rubber outsole is complemented with a PU-encapsulated EVA foam midsole with Boost technology, delivering cushioning and comfort for kids.

Our experts love the sneaker's unique and vibrant color scheme, which is a combination of blue and gray tones, providing a stylish and eye-catching look for little feet. This adidas Yeezy 700V3 Arzareth (Infants) was released on August 29th, 2020. The pair retailed for $100.

name: Vivienne Westwood
title: ASICS Hyper Gel-Lyte Vivienne Westwood
description:
The ASICS Hyper Gel Lyte Vivienne Westwood features a striking color palette and a harmonious blend of iconic fashion and cutting-edge sportswear technology, complete with a tri-density midsole and rubber outsole, culminating in a sneaker that excels in aesthetics and functionality.

The Hyper Gel Lyte Vivienne Westwood masterfully intertwines fashion and technology, showcasing the vibrant hues of the 'Daphnis & Chloe' collection that truly breathe life into the design. Contrasting orange accents add a playful touch, while the TPU midsole, infused with ASICS' renowned GEL technology, ensures unparalleled comfort. This collaboration seamlessly merges style and innovation, creating a unique and comfortable footwear experience.

Our StockX team appreciates the sneaker’s innovative tri-density midsole. The introduction of the tri-density midsole takes this concept to a new level by incorporating three different densities of cushioning materials within the same midsole unit. It's a game-changer that ensures maximum support and comfort, which our experts believe is a standout feature. The ASICS Hyper Gel Lyte Vivienne Westwood was released on the 16th of August, 2019, and sold for $225.

name: Rhuigi Villasenor
title: Puma Suede Rhuigi Villasenor
description: The Puma Suede Rhuigi Villasenor is a collaboration between Puma and LA-based designer Rhuigi Villasenor. This sneaker features a premium suede upper in a bold red colorway with contrasting white accents on the Puma Formstrip and midsole. The shoe also includes a gold Puma logo on the heel and Rhuigi Villasenor branding on the tongue and insole. Released on June 12, 2021, the Puma Suede Rhuigi Villasenor retails for $85. The shoe is available in men's sizes and is a limited edition release. Crafted with high-quality materials, the Puma Suede Rhuigi Villasenor is a stylish and comfortable sneaker that is perfect for everyday wear. The suede upper provides a soft and luxurious feel, while the rubber outsole offers excellent traction and durability. Something we love about the Puma Suede Rhuigi Villasenor is its eye-catching design that combines bold colors and contrasting accents. Our experts think the best features of this shoe are its premium materials, comfortable fit, and unique branding. Overall, we love the Puma Suede Rhuigi Villasenor for its standout style and exceptional quality.

name: Queen City (GS)
title: Puma MB1 Queen City (GS)
description:
The Puma MB1 Purple Glimmer (GS) for grade schoolers for grade schoolers is a refresh of LaMelo Ball’s debut signature shoe and features a familiar color scheme that gives the nod to the Charlotte Hornets.

A bold violet hue floods the engineered knit upper of the Puma MB1 Purple Glimmer (GS) for grade schoolers, reinforced with tonal no-sew overlays and accented with teal branding elements. The teal elements include an outlined Formstrip on the lateral toe box and LaMelo’s logo on the tongue. Underfoot, lightweight cushioning comes courtesy of a Nitro Foam midsole in a matching purple finish.

The Puma MB1 Purple Glimmer (GS) for grade schoolers was released in March 2022 and retailed for $90.

name: Antlia (Reflective)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Antlia (Reflective)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Antlia (Reflective) features a triple-Antlia Primeknit upper, with the Antlia palette taking on a soft yellow hue that is shot through with the typical gray seen on many Boost 350 V2 models. From there, the iconic "three stripes" of adidas cover the inner heel of the shoe, and "Boost" technology in a Gum-colored heel complete the design.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Antlia (Reflective) released in June of 2019 and retailed for $220

name: Alvah (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Alvah (Kids)
description:
The adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Alvah (Kids) comes draping in a muted color scheme highlighted by a gray striped monofilament black technical mesh base coupled with an identical exoskeletal glow-in-the-dark RPU dynamic cage overlay, giving the sneaker's side panels structure. 

The upper has a glow-in-the-dark cage, a suede toe cap, and a conventional lacing system that conceals the stylish 3M reflective design on the padded tongue. In addition, it has a glow-in-the-dark cage. The shoe has a snug black neoprene sock liner that centers on molding to the curve of the foot. A black polyurethane shell with the Three Stripes logo on it and a matching rubber outsole elevate the shoe. In the meantime, a rubberized toe cap is useful for durability while being lightweight. At the base of the tongue, reflective ornamentation improves visibility. The sneaker has a thick EVA midsole instead of Boost padding.

We love the kid's sneaker's distinct black and gray color scheme and unique design elements. It has a comfortable Primeknit upper, an innovative cage overlay for support and a chunky midsole. The adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Alvah (Kids) debuted on April 11th, 2019, and retailed at $160.

name: Mist (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Mist (Infants)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Mist (Infants) is an infant-sized shoe that was inspired by the Yeezy Foam RNNR Mist silhouette.

The Yeezy Foam RNNR Mist (Infants) is made from foam and features a Mist color scheme. The shoe comes with a durable rubber outsole that has a wave pattern. Furthermore, the shoe includes a slip-on design and a low-laying wide collar. It is also constructed with perforations throughout and includes a round toe. The insole is made of soft foam and features a repeating pattern that consists of a series of interconnected diamond shapes. The shoe does not include a tongue, and includes an adidas logo on the base of the sole.

Our experts say that one of the most notable features of the adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Mist (Infants) is its continuous construction. The shoe was released on March 11th, 2022, at a retail price of $40.

name: Dark Slate (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy 450 Dark Slate (Infants)
description: The adidas Yeezy 450 Dark Slate Infant is a highly sought-after sneaker that boasts a unique design and premium materials. Released on June 26, 2021, this shoe features a dark slate colorway that adds a touch of sophistication to any outfit. The upper is made of a breathable mesh material that provides comfort and durability, while the sole is crafted from adidas' signature Boost technology for superior cushioning and support. The shoe also features a laceless design that adds to its sleek and modern aesthetic. With a retail price of $120, the adidas Yeezy 450 Dark Slate Infant is a must-have for any sneaker enthusiast looking for a stylish and comfortable shoe.

name: Season 6 Taupe
title: Yeezy Suede Desert Boot Season 6 Taupe
description: The Yeezy Suede Desert Boot Season 6 Taupe is a stylish and comfortable footwear option for those who want to make a statement. The boots are made of high-quality suede material that is both durable and soft to the touch. The taupe color is versatile and can be paired with a variety of outfits. These boots were released on April 20, 2018, and have a retail price of $270. The design features a lace-up closure and a rubber sole for added traction. The Yeezy brand is known for its unique and trendy designs, and the Suede Desert Boot Season 6 Taupe is no exception. These boots are perfect for those who want to elevate their fashion game while staying comfortable.

name: Phosphor (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Phosphor (Kids)
description:
Available in kids sizing, the adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Phosphor (Kids) is a collaborative sneaker from adidas Originals and Kanye West, featuring the adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN in a "Phosphor" colorway.

This adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN offering features a nylon upper dressed in Neon Yellow, highlighted by "700" branding printed on the lateral in reflective silver. Black no-sew overlays at the heel and forefoot provide a contrasting tone to the upper. Other details include no-tie bungee laces and a ‘YEEZY x adidas’ co-branded insole. A blacked out polyurethane midsole with full-length boost cushioning rests on a matching rubber outsole with herringbone traction patterns.

What our experts love about this Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN sneaker is its design and colorway. The material used on the upper is durable and lightweight, providing a comfortable fit, while the design and color combination gives it a bright and eye-catching look. The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Phosphor (Kids) was released on April 24th, 2020, retailing at $160.

name: Sulfur (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Sulfur (Infants)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Sulfur (Infants) is a slip-on sandal that was released by adidas in collaboration with Kanye West’s Yeezy brand as the 11th product line from the adidas Yeezy brand.

The adidas Yeezy Foam runners feature a monochromatic tan appearance labeled as the Sulfur colorway which resembles a yellowish beige hue. They are made from EVA foam using a single-piece foam injection molding technique, which also gives them a sculpted appearance. The sculpted appearance is further enhanced by oval cut openings on the side walls. These work hand in hand with strategically placed vents to help with breathability and keep the foot cool.

One thing we love about the adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Sulfur (Infants) is the foam material used in construction. It gives the shoe a lightweight, flexible feel, making it comfortable for all-day use. The infant-sized shoes were released for retail on the 6th of April 2022, with a retail price of $45.

name: Ash Pearl (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Ash Pearl (Kids)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Ash Pearl (Kids) is a stylish and comfortable sneaker that brings the iconic Yeezy design to younger sneaker enthusiasts. Featuring a harmonious blend of ash pearl tones throughout the upper, this model offers a versatile and fashionable look. The Primeknit construction ensures a snug and flexible fit, making it perfect for active kids. The Boost cushioning technology provides unparalleled comfort and support, ideal for all-day wear.

The Yeezy Boost 350 V2, designed by Kanye West, has become a cultural icon since its debut. The Ash Pearl colorway offers a muted, earthy palette that pairs well with any outfit. The signature stripe running along the side adds a touch of distinction, while the ribbed midsole showcases the innovative Boost technology. These design elements highlight the model's unique blend of fashion and function, making it a must-have for young sneakerheads.

Priced at $160, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Ash Pearl (Kids) was released on March 20, 2021. This sneaker not only delivers on style but also ensures maximum comfort for active kids. Add a touch of Yeezy flair to your child's footwear collection with this versatile and trendy model.

name: Mineral Blue (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Mineral Blue (Kids)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Mineral Blue (Kids) comes in an all-Mineral Blue color scheme.

The Mineral Blue adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR for kids features an upper made from a single piece of foam compound, which offers a lightweight feel and comfort. The shoe has a slip-on construction to make it easy to put on and take off. In a unique twist, the shoe lacks laces, ensuring a snug and secure fit, and also features a textured surface. The shoe's midsole is crafted of EVA foam, providing cushioning and impact absorption. In addition, the outsole features deep grooves and a wavy pattern that provide sturdiness and traction.

What we love about the adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Mineral Blue is its futuristic and sleek silhouette, and a slip-on construction and seamless one-piece upper, creating a minimalist and modern look. The adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Mineral Blue (Kids) was released on May 29th, 2021, and sold for a retail price of $60.

name: Rihanna Fenty Aged Silver (Women's)
title: Puma Avanti C Rihanna Fenty Aged Silver (Women's)
description:
FENTY x PUMA presents the Avanti, worn by legends and reborn by Rihanna. This classic silhouette was taken from the PUMA archives and reimaged by Rihanna through her own personal design language and creative treatment. This new sport-fashion icon features a premium leather upper and a gum sole, and appears in two bespoke versions: classic black and white, and allover silver chrome.

Leather based chrome upper and formstrip ; Attached fold over tongue in leather based chrome material ; Laser etched Fenty logos on tongue, quarter, and heel FOT ; EVA foam wedge midsole ; Gum outsole ; Fenty branded footbed.

name: Orange (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Orange (Infants)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Orange (Infants) results from a team effort between adidas and rapper Kanye West in a bid to revamp the original Yeezy silhouette.

The black outsole of this adidas Yeezy Boost 700 for infants is constructed using herringbone rubber. The midsole, also in black, has a full-length adidas Boost unit. An aggressive façade arises from the mudguard's sharp-edge reflective overlay. On the upper is a polyester material in a vibrant orange colorway adorned by a shiny and reflective "700" imprint. The tongue is black, matching the sole, and the lacing system, also in a dark shade, is graced by no-tie elastic laces with webbed eyelets. The heel counter brings back the aggressive look of the mudguard with a black half-mask overlay with fluorescent accents.

The black-on-orange color scheme present on the adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Orange (Infants) is among its outstanding features. Reflective overlays on the lateral quarters, toe tip, and counter add as much visibility as it does aesthetics. The shoe’s release date was February 28, 2020, and sold for $220.

name: Earth Brown (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Slide Earth Brown (Kids)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Slide Earth Brown (Kids) was released as a collaboration between adidas and Kanye West. The slide adorns the classic slip-on Yeezy silhouette in an Earth Brown colorway.

The ‘Earth Brown’ adidas Yeezy Slide for kids is made from a durable and lightweight material, ensuring longevity and ease of wear. The slide's slip-on design allows for easy and hassle-free wearing. The footbed of the Yeezy Slide offers cushioning and support. The slide also features a ridged outsole, which offers grip and traction, guaranteeing stability.

The standout feature of this adidas Yeezy Slide Earth Brown (Kids) is its seamless fusion of comfort and style in the design. Crafted with meticulous attention to detail, the slide exhibits a rich, Earth Brown hue that captures the essence of natural tones. In addition, the slide's one-piece molded EVA foam ensures comfort and support, while the contoured footbed offers a customizable fit. The adidas Yeezy Slide Earth Brown (Kids) was released on April 16th, 2020, and sold at a retail price of $45.

name: Yeezy
title: Nike Air Max 1 FB Yeezy
description: Love him or hate him, Kanye West is a trendsetter. Over the years, Kanye’s influence has grown tremendously and in no place is it more evident than the sneaker world. Colorways bearing any resemblance to a Kanye shoe are quickly labeled as the "Yeezy" version by the sneaker community. A perfect example of the Kanye effect is the Nike Air Max 1 FB Yeezy from 2013. Released alongside a similarly colored Roshe Run, this Nike Air Max 1 featured an upper that used a combination of black, Fresh Mint, and Pink Flash. The sneakerhead community might have labeled these Yeezys – which is better than the "Blink" nickname that first surfaced due to the black and pink combination -- but the FB in the name actually stands for futbol. Without an official connection to Kanye, these never reached the price levels of Yeezys. However, the nickname and details, like the reflective 3M Swoosh on the upper and splatter print Swoosh spread across the insoles, helped them sell quickly upon initial release and has made the Yeezy Nike Air Max 1 FB one of the most popular colorways of the FB Air Max series.

name: Citrin (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Citrin (Kids)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Citrin Kids is a collaboration between adidas and Kanye West.

The Citrin adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 for Kids comes in an all-Citrin color palette. The upper is built with a mixture of PrimeKnit material and translucent monofilament mesh, offering lightweight feel and improved breathability. The shoe features adidas' Boost cushioning technology, which provides comfort and responsiveness. The midsole is made of semi-translucent TPU material. In addition, this model of sneaker features a pull tab on the heel for easy on-and-off wear. The shoe also includes a durable rubber outsole with patterned traction for grip and sturdiness.

What we think is the best feature of these sneakers is their sleek and modern design. These shoes feature a PrimeKnit upper in a soft and neutral Citrin colorway, which gives them a versatile and stylish look. The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Citrin Kids was released on September 23rd, 2019, and sold for a recommended retail price of about $160.

name: Israfil (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Israfil (Infants)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Israfil (Infants) is an infant-sized version of the popular adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Israfil. It features the same high-end materials, neutral colorway, and innovative technologies but is designed for a smaller foot.

The upper is made of patchwork-like Primeknit material, which allows for a sock-like fit and breathability. The sneaker features a mottled grey color palette with sandy yellow details, including a textured stripe extending from toe to heel. The round toe and flat heel contribute to the sneaker’s sock-like appearance. The shoe houses a lacing system with a toggle, which makes it easy to put on and take off.

What do our experts like about this sneaker? The grey and tan, semi-translucent outsole attached to the full-length Boost midsole provides traction and complements the upper’s color scheme. The infant-sized adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Israfil (Infants) was released on August 22, 2022, and retailed at $140.

name: Rihanna Fenty Golden Brown (Women's)
title: Puma Cleated Creeper Rihanna Fenty Golden Brown (Women's)
description:
The Puma Cleated Creeper Rihanna Fenty Golden Brown (Women’s) is a women’s low-top lifestyle shoe from the Fenty line with a large, chunky outsole in golden brown and Lark color palette.

Performer and singer Rhianna teamed up with Puma to deliver this big and bold Fenty platform silhouette. The golden brown suede upper delivers a tonal backdrop to the Lark-colored Puma Formstrips on both sides of the shoe. This collaboration sneaker features Puma branding in the form of debossed lettering on the lateral side, a leather tongue patch, and the pouncing puma icon on the heel counter. Color-matching laces complete the design.

Our experts think these sneakers stand out thanks to the height-adding creeper platform midsole and outsole. The jagged outsole adds personality. Get ready to push styling limits with the Puma Cleated Creeper Rihanna Fenty Golden Brown (Women’s), which was released on August 31, 2017, with a $160 price tag.

name: Rihanna Fenty Suede Green (Women's)
title: Puma Cleated Creeper Rihanna Fenty Suede Green (Women's)
description:
The Puma Cleated Creeper Rihanna Fenty Suede Green (Women's) represents a collaboration between Puma and celebrated powerhouse Rihanna, who was appointed a creative director at Puma in 2014. Part of Rihanna’s Fenty line, this sneaker is specifically sized for women.

The upper of this fashionable, edgy women’s Puma Cleated Creeper is crafted from mossy green suede and sports tonal debossed Puma branding on the side panel just under the eyestays. Gold suede is visible through the heel tab cut-out window and sports a dark green Puma logo. This gold suede also forms the side-panel Puma stripe. A gum rubber platform midsole with vertical ridges rests on a chunky outsole with deep grooves for traction.

Our favorite aspect of this women’s sneaker is the singular sockliner, which is green and burgundy plaid over a golden base. The Puma Cleated Creeper Rihanna Fenty Suede Green (Women's) was released on October 19, 2017, for $160 retail.

name: J Cole Aquarius
title: Puma RS-Dreamer J Cole Aquarius
description: The Puma RS Dreamer J Cole Blue is a stylish and functional basketball shoe that combines performance and fashion. The shoe features a blue and white colorway with a sleek design that is perfect for both on and off the court.
