The upper is made of a breathable mesh material that provides comfort and support, while the rubber outsole offers excellent traction and durability. The shoe also features Puma's innovative RS technology, which provides superior cushioning and energy return. The Puma RS Dreamer J Cole Blue was released on July 2, 2021, and retails for $125. Whether you're a basketball player or a fashion enthusiast, this shoe is a must-have for your collection.

name: White Pink
title: Puma Clyde Hardwood White Pink
description:
The Puma Clyde Hardwood White Pink is a basketball shoe specifically designed for traction and support on hardwood floors.

This iteration of the Puma Clyde Hardwood is made with a white mesh upper. This material forms the forefoot, while white leather panels appear on each side with a short line of perforations on the outer side. The outer side also features a large Puma stripe in Pink Glo. A small gray suede patch is also found on the outer side of the toe, while on the inner side, a gray arch appears with perforations. The heel is supported by a Pink Glo heel counter, and the Puma logo appears on the heel collar in gold. The tongue also features a logo patch. The shoe sits on a ProFoam midsole and a white rubber outsole.

What we like best about this shoe are the Pink Glo accents, which add pops of color to the otherwise white shoe. The Puma Clyde Hardwood White Pink was released on October 18, 2019, for $120.

name: Super Mario 64
title: Puma Future Rider Super Mario 64
description:
The Puma Future Rider Super Mario 64 is a visual homage to the iconic Nintendo video game and film series. The Future Rider’s timeless running sneaker silhouette features a white mesh base overlaid with off-white suede, blue leather Formstrip, and red, white, and green soles. Accents including a hang tag, wings, and brick pattern bring the beloved game to the shoe.

Born of a collaboration with Nintendo, the Puma Future Rider infuses the shoe with elements of the beloved game and characters. The game’s iconic bricks are rendered as a heel insert, while wings imprinted on the heel pay homage to Mario's wing cap. Tying it all together, the color palette brings Mario’s world to the shoe, with a sky-blue Formstrip, grass-green accents, and Mario’s signature bright red.

In our opinion, the best feature of the Puma Future Rider is its experimentation with classic styling. Comfortable enough for everyday wear, the innovative details of this shoe make it an instant collector item for gamers and fans worldwide. The Puma Future Rider Super Mario 64 was released on November 27, 2020, and retailed for $90.

name: Mineral Blue (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Mineral Blue (Infants)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Mineral Blue (Infants) is an infant's size sneaker that was released as a collaboration between adidas and artist Kanye West.

The Yeezy Foam RNNR in Mineral Blue for infants has a Mineral Blue colorway and features a design that allows for easy on-and-off access. The shoe features a textured sole that provides traction for little ones who are beginning to explore their surroundings. The foam material is also incredibly lightweight, making it easy for children to move around without any added weight or discomfort.

Our experts say that the standout feature of the adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Mineral Blue (Infants) is its unique foam material that covers the entire shoe. This foam is a trademark technology from adidas that also adds a layer of cushioning to the shoe, providing a comfortable and lightweight feel for the infant. The material and Mineral Blue colorway make this shoe perfect for both boys and girls. The shoe was released on May 29th, 2021 at a retail price of $40.

name: Black Red Blast
title: Puma LaMelo Ball MB.01 Black Red Blast
description: The Puma MB01 LaMelo Ball Black Red Blast is a sleek and stylish basketball shoe that is sure to turn heads on and off the court. The shoe features a black and red colorway that is both bold and eye-catching, making it the perfect choice for players who want to make a statement with their footwear. The upper of the shoe is made from a combination of synthetic leather and mesh, which provides a comfortable and breathable fit. The midsole is made from Puma's proprietary ProFoam technology, which offers excellent cushioning and support for the foot. One of the standout features of the Puma MB01 LaMelo Ball Black Red Blast is its outsole, which is made from a durable rubber material that provides excellent traction on the court. This makes it the perfect shoe for players who need to make quick cuts and changes of direction. The Puma MB01 LaMelo Ball Black Red Blast was released on February 18, 2022, and has a retail price of $135. Overall, this is a high-quality basketball shoe that offers excellent performance and style. Something we love about the Puma MB01 LaMelo Ball Black Red Blast is its bold and eye-catching colorway, which is sure to make a statement on the court.

name: Desert Sage (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Desert Sage (Infants)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Desert Sage (Infant) is a unique iteration of the iconic Yeezy Boost 350 V2 silhouette, released as part of a continued collaborative effort between adidas and Kanye West.

The shoe’s upper is constructed using PrimeKnit material and features a Desert Sage colorway, which takes inspiration from muted earthy tones – evoking a sense of desert landscapes and natural serenity. The upper showcases a mix of light green and gray shades, creating an understated yet eye-catching appearance. Other subtle details on the shoe include the signature side stripe, a hallmark of the Yeezy Boost 350 V2, and "SPLY-350" branding on the side.

One of the notable elements on the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Desert Sage (Infant) is the translucent sole, incorporating adidas' innovative BOOST cushioning technology, which provides exceptional comfort and responsiveness. The infant-sized shoe was released on March 14th, 2020, for the retail price of $140.

name: Super Mario 64
title: Puma RS-Dreamer Super Mario 64
description:
The Puma RS-Dreamer Super Mario 64 celebrates a collaboration between Super Mario Bros., which celebrated its 35th anniversary, and Nintendo.

The majority of the Puma RS-Dreamer Super Mario 64’s 5/8-cut uppers are in red, yellow, Gradient Blue, and white, which make their way onto the ProFoam midsole and front lace support. Mario branding arrives in the form of a Super Mario Bros. label at the tongue, a Mario Super star graphic at the heel, and insoles depicting scenes from the game.

The Puma RS-Dreamer Super Mario 64 was released on September 4th, 2020, at a retail price of $125.

name: Glow (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Glow (Infants)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Glow (Infant) was released as part of Kanye West's Yeezy line. This shoe is designed specifically for infants and toddlers and comes in a Glow colorway.

The Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Glow for infants features a Primeknit upper, which is a lightweight and breathable material that conforms to the shape of the foot. The shoe's midsole is made of Boost technology, which provides cushioning and energy return, making it comfortable for little ones to walk, run, and play. The outsole is made of a durable rubber material that provides grip and traction on a variety of surfaces.

We think that one of the standout features of the Adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Glow (Infant) is its glow-in-the-dark design. When exposed to light, the shoe's upper absorbs energy and glows in the dark. The shoe was released on April 25th, 2019 at a retail price of $160.

name: Cloud White (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Cloud White (Kids)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Cloud White Kids was made available as part of the adidas's partnership with Yeezy, formerly known as Kanye West. This Yeezy Boost 350 V2 release arrives in a Cloud White/Cloud White/Cloud White colorway.

The adidas innovative Boost technology is used to design the midsole of this kids’ sneaker. The shoe's upper is designed by weaving a monofilament side stripe to reveal its re-engineered Primeknit. Shades of bluish-white and cream work together to form the sneaker's design featuring a fluffy cloud. In the meantime, blue-and-white patterns are outlined on one side of the shoe, and the other displays a transparent strip.

Something our experts think is the standout feature of the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Cloud White Kids is the versatile, white-based colorway. The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Cloud White Kids was released at a retail price of $160 on September 21st, 2019.

name: Black (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Black (Infants)
description: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Black Infant is a sleek and stylish sneaker designed for infants. It features a black nylon upper with reflective detailing, giving it a unique and eye-catching look. The Boost midsole provides exceptional comfort and support, making it perfect for little feet. The release date for this shoe was May 23, 2020, and it retails for $140. The materials used in the construction of this shoe are of the highest quality, ensuring durability and longevity. The Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Black Infant is a must-have for any young sneakerhead looking to make a statement.

name: Carbon (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Carbon (Infants)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Carbon (Infants) was released as a collaboration between Kanye West and adidas. The sneaker adopts the classic low-top Yeezy Boost silhouette in a Carbon colorway.

The Carbon adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 for infants has an upper crafted from a blend of breathable and flexible materials, ensuring comfort for the wearer. Furthermore, the PrimeKnit pattern on the upper contributes to a snug and adaptive fit. The shoe's sock-like construction allows for easy on-and-off wear. It features an integrated lacing system that ensures a secure fit, and a responsive Boost cushioning technology embedded in the midsole. The shoe also incorporates a durable rubber outsole with a distinct tread pattern, offering traction and sturdiness.

What we love about this sneaker is its two-tone upper material, which creates an elegant and sophisticated look. The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Carbon (Infants) was released on October 2nd, 2020, and sold for a list price of $140.

name: Rihanna Fenty Pink (Women's)
title: Puma Bow Slide Rihanna Fenty Pink (Women's)
description:
The Puma Bow Slide Rihanna Fenty Pink (Women's) is a women's size slide that is part of a collaboration between the brand Puma and the artist Rihanna.

The Women Fenty Pink Puma Bow Slide Rihanna comes in a silver and pink color scheme, and is designed with satin on the strap. The footbed of the slide is made of EVA foam and the outsole is made of rubber. The band is made of rubber and synthetic leather, and the Puma logo is prominently placed on the side of the heel of the slide. The footbed also features the Fenty by Rihanna label and a Puma on the side.

We think that the notable feature of the slide is the oversized bow on the strap. The bow is made from satin and can be untied when needed. The Puma Bow Slide Rihanna Fenty Pink (Women's) was released on March 9th, 2017, at a retail price of $90.

name: Black
title: Puma Thunder Spectra Black
description: The PUMA Thunder pays homage to past collabs and silhouettes ahead of their time. Inspired by 90s Cell System running silhouettes and the PUMA x McQueen collaboration, the Thunder is a reimagined pair of kicks with a bulky, unapologetic look and feel. The Thunder has a distinctive athletic shape with a chunky structure that uses molded TPU laid over premium mesh and nubuck to create a disruptive sense of nostalgia. The exaggerated tooling, the blown-up proportions and the loud color blocking reserve a spot for the Thunder on the international runways.

name: Turtledove (2016) (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Turtledove (2016) (Infants)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Turtledove (2016) (Infants) is an infant-sized offering of the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 in a Turtledove colorway.

This Yeezy Boost 350 sneaker features a PrimeKnit upper dressed in Blue Graphite and Turtledove, with a semi-circle-shaped black suede patch on the medial quarter panel. A heel pull tab with a dotted red line adds some contrast to the upper. Other details include insole branding and an integrated lacing system with round, patterned rope laces. The upper rests on a Chalk White outsole with Boost cushioning and textured detailing for traction.

What our experts appreciate most about this Yeezy Boost sneaker is the design and colorway. The upper construction is lightweight and breathable, providing a comfortable fit, while the unique patterns and color combination give it a clean and stylish look. The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Turtledove (2016) (Infants) was made available on August 27th, 2016, retailing at $130.

name: Bait x Marvel Carnage (Special Box/Cannister)
title: Puma Cell Bait x Marvel Carnage (Special Box/Cannister)
description:
The Puma Cell Bait x Marvel Carnage (Special Box/Cannister) is a tennis shoe with a design and color scheme inspired by the comic book character. 

This iteration of the Puma Cell features a red mesh upper with darker red suede overlays around the toe box, heel, and across the midsole in shapes evoking Marvel’s Carnage character. White appears under these dark red overlays, representing the villain’s bright eyes. Black accents are also seen near the toe box, and the lacing system appears in black. The Puma logo can be found on the cushioned tongue, while the "Carnage" name is embossed into a red heel tab. A glossy black rubber outsole completes the look. 

What we appreciate most about this shoe is its packaging. It comes in a special collector’s box with the Carnage, Puma, and Bait logos. Each shoe is placed in its canister inside the box. The Puma Cell Bait x Marvel Carnage (Special Box/Cannister) was first released on October 4, 2018, for a retail price of $250.

name: Antlia (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Antlia (Kids)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Antlia (Kids) colorway is inspired by the Antlia galaxy, lending it a cosmic and futuristic vibe.

This model uses a softer rendering that gives the 350 V2 a muted yellow-green color and gray hues on the Primeknit upper. As with all Yeezy Boost 350 V2 models, the Antlia version incorporates adidas' signature Boost technology in the midsole, providing exceptional cushioning and comfort for all-day wear. The shoe also features a semi-translucent stripe on the lateral side, adding to its distinct aesthetic. Fluorescent features are incorporated into the flexible Primeknit upper. The outsole features a durable rubber compound with a classic herringbone pattern for reliable traction.

Something we find outstanding about this sneaker is that it includes a two-toned, re-engineered Primeknit upper. On its woven top there is a side stripe crafted of post-dyed monofilament. The laces have reflective threads sewn into them. The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Antlia (Kids) debuted on June 22nd, 2019. The kids' shoe retailed at $160.

name: Trophies Black Gold
title: Puma RS-X Trophies Black Gold
description:
These days we’ve been seeing an influx of ‘new’ celebrities emerging from social media, sport, music, and more. The RS-X Trophies disruptive design is inspired by this ongoing cultural phenomenon and reinvention of fame and recognition.

Built with RS technology on the midsole, the bulky silhouette with mesh and textile upper is stylishly decked with leather overlays. Elevating the look with gold accents along the quarter panels, the sneakers in PUMA Black – PUMA Team Gold colorway is embossed with a textile heel piece and molded sockliner with specific RS branding. Completing the look with tonal laces, the sneakers are placed atop rubber outsole with a light weight midsole.

Back in the ‘80s, the RS was an innovative and high-quality cushioning technology. PUMA has revived and reinvented this design ground up. The new RS-X range is all-things extreme, exaggerated and remixed. Embracing the future and honoring the past, the OG-inspired silhouette celebrates extreme reinvention with its bulky design, material mixes, and bold color palette.

name: Soft Vision (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy 500 Soft Vision (Infants)
description:
The adidas Yeezy 500 Soft Vision (Infants) is an infant sized iteration of the Yeezy 500, a lifestyle sneaker designed as part of a continued collaboration between adidas and the Yeezy brand by Kanye West.

The shoes feature a bulky and exaggerated design, with the upper made from a mix of materials that include leather, suede and synthetic mesh. The entire upper is covered in a light purple hue which also extends to the midsole, while the outsole is made from gum rubber. The shoe also has signature adidas Yeezy 500 details like the chunky sole unit with a unique outsole pattern.

One thing that particularly stands out on the adidas Yeezy 500 Soft Vision (Infant) is the sole unit which uses adidas' adiPRENE+ cushioning technology. It is incorporated into the midsole to provide added cushioning, keeping your feet comfortable at all times, even with all-day wear. The infant sized shoes were released for retail priced at $100 on November 2, 2019.

name: Pure Platinum
title: Nike Air Yeezy 2 Pure Platinum
description:
The Nike Air Yeezy 2 Pure Platinum is a famous sneaker that resulted from the collaboration between Nike and rapper/designer Kanye West. The Air Yeezy 2 is the second model in the Air Yeezy line, and it was released in 2012. The design incorporates various elements inspired by both athletic performance footwear and high-fashion aesthetics. 

The Nike Air Yeezy 2 Pure Platinum has a futuristic silhouette that sets it apart from traditional athletic sneakers. The sneaker includes premium materials such as suede, leather, and mesh. The molded rear section of the shoe adds a unique touch to the design and provides ankle support. An adjustable midfoot strap with a distinctive "YEEZY" logo adds both style and functionality.

Our experts love that the Nike Air Yeezy 2 Pure Platinum features symbols and hieroglyphics on the heel, tongue, and midfoot strap, influenced by the work of artist Hafiia Mark of Hieronimus & Co. This model was released on June 9th, 2012, for a starting price of $250.

name: Clay (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Clay (Kids)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Clay (Kids) is a preschool edition sneaker from the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 collaborative sneaker lineup in a ‘Clay’ colorway.

This sneaker features a re-engineered PrimeKnit upper dressed in an Orange-Brown ‘Clay’ hue highlighted by Orange accents on the heel tab, the upper’s underlay on the translucent side stripes, and the sole unit. White detailing can be seen on the PrimeKnit fabric. Collaborative details include the ‘adidas x YEEZY' branding on the insole. A translucent BOOST midsole and a solid Clay rubber outsole complete the shoe’s design. 

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Clay (Kids) was made available on March 30, 2019. Initially, it retailed at $160.

name: Black Red (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Black Red (Kids)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Black Red (Kids) opts for premium materials that infuse Kanye West's styling into the comfort-oriented sneakers. These Yeezys adopt a Prime knit upper finished in black and red accents.

Employing Yeezy 350 construction, the upper is draped in black with contrast-hued fibers across the yarn working to elicit a speckled effect. The translucent rubber midsole also takes on dark hues in line with the blacked-out motif of the darkest V2. The midsole features a full-length Boost midsole designed for lightweight cushioning and responsive performance underfoot. You'll notice the only red marks are the SPLY-350 tag on the laterals and the broken line on the heel pull loop. A signature ribbed outsole completes the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Black Red Kids design.

What our experts like about the Yeezy Boost V2 Black Red is the minimalistic design that allows Adidas to focus on the comfort offerings. The Boost midsole aids in this cause. adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Black Red (Kids) was released on December 5, 2020, retailing for $160.

name: Bone (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Bone (Infants)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Bone (Infants) is a product of a collaboration between adidas and American Rapper Kanye West.

The upper of this adidas Yeezy Boost 700 goes for a one-piece construction, and it features a polyester material in a neutral bone color. The toe tip is reinforced by black synthetics adorned by reflective silver patches. On the quarter panels, the "700" branding appears in bold fonts, decorated by a fluorescent material in a greyish-silver tint. Contrasting the bright upper is a black midsole. It features an adidas BOOST unit visible through subtle cut-outs on the heel. The heel counter also features black overlays to match the sole.

What do our experts think makes the adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Bone (Infants) outstanding? We love the bungee laces with a no-tie mechanism, making them suitable for little feet. The eyelets feature a webbed design, resulting in a better fit. These sneakers were released in infant sizing on July 11th, 2020, for $140.

name: Orange (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Orange (Kids)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Orange (Kids) is a re-imagination of the retro-inspired silhouette. This iteration shrinks the popular silhouette to accommodate children's smaller feet.

The kids adidas Yeezy Boost 700 upper is made of lightweight polyester and features a vibrant Phosphorescent Orange base, complemented by Bold Black overlays. For branding, this kid’s sneaker has an oversized ‘700’ branding prominently adorned across the lateral side panel, printed in silver characters that shine when exposed to light. It has a full-length drop-in BOOST midsole to provide responsive cushioning, and a herringbone rubber outsole for traction with cutouts to reveal the midsole.

What we love about the Boost 700 MNVN is the eye-catching reflective accents littered throughout the shoes’ forefoot and heel, adding to the shoe’s minimalist but unique design. The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Orange (Kids) was released on February 28th, 2020, with its retail price set at $140.

name: Mist (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Mist (Kids)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Mist (Kids) represents a collaboration between the world-renowned German sneaker company and rapper/entrepreneur/designer Kanye West. This comfortable, fashionable, and lightweight shoe has been specifically sized for kids.

The Kids adidas Yeezy Boost 380 in Mist colorway features a Primeknit upper in shades of gray that form a camouflage-like pattern. Circular perforations accent both side panels, primarily on a outer-side tan patch of loose-weave Primeknit. Tan rope laces with a tonal synthetic dubrae thread through eyestays that are woven directly into the Primeknit upper. A darker gray elasticized collar provides a snug, sock-like feel and surrounds a tonal insole with black dual branding.

Our favorite part of this cozy kids sneaker is the sole that enhances its comfort. A thick midsole in white Boost foam is covered with a translucent synthetic that sneaks up the upper to form the mudguard. The outsole is brown gum rubber that sports vents for Boost expansion and grooves for a non-slip grip. The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Mist (Kids) was released on March 25, 2020, for $170 retail.

name: Arzareth (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Arzareth (Kids)
description:
The adidas Yeezy 700V3 Arzareth (Kid's) has a knit monofilament-designed mesh upper that features blue, white, and gray stripes scattered throughout, and a transparent, glow-in-the-dark TPU cage adds support. 

The upper is made of a breathable and lightweight Primeknit material, ensuring a comfortable and supportive fit. For a snug, sock-like fit, a black neoprene bootie is positioned underneath this technical ensemble. The bootie-style collar of the sneaker is covered with contrast black, ensuring a secure fit around the ankle. The sneaker has a herringbone rubber outsole for sticky traction. Further, it showcases the iconic glow-in-the-dark RPU.

What we say one of the standout features of the kid's shoe is its signature chunky and sculpted midsole, which incorporates EVA foam and Boost technology. This combination provides excellent cushioning and responsiveness, making it ideal for daily wear and long walks. The shoe also boasts an innovative cage overlay for added support and structure. The adidas Yeezy 700V3 Arzareth (Kid's) debuted on August 29th, 2020, and retailed at the price of $130.

name: OG Light Brown
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 750 OG Light Brown
description: "Searching for creative freedom, Kanye West left Nike for adidas in late 2013. The minute the adidas x Kanye West partnership was announced, anticipation began to build. In true Yeezy fashion, Kanye first wore the 750 Yeezy Boost to the Grammy’s. The first colorway of the adidas Yeezy Boost 750, which is technically Brown/Carbon White/Light Brown but most commonly referred to as grey, released over NBA All-Star Weekend that took place in New York City that year. To make things fair and safe for customers, adidas launched an app to handle reservations. If you were lucky enough to get through on the app you were able to pick up your Yeezy Boosts from a nearby retailer. Kanye and adidas went above and beyond with extra personnel to make sure that every person who obtained a pair was able to pick up their pair safely. The Yeezy 750 is a bold design featuring a high cut and zippered ankle, and because of it, many sneakerheads scoffed at the shoe. The design is one of the first shoes from adidas to feature almost no visual branding. Even the Three Stripes are tucked away underneath the midfoot strap. To help launch the shoe, Kanye West and adidas held a fashion show in NYC for Kanye’s Yeezy Season 1 and live streamed the show to 42 movie theaters across the globe. To make the launch even more special for Yeezy fans, Kanye West surprised some of those who purchased the adidas Yeezy Boost by handing them their new Yeezy sneakers in person."

name: X-Ray
title: Puma Clyde Court Disrupt X-Ray
description: Puma is bringing "Trick or Treating" to a whole new level with the Puma Clyde Court Disrupt X-Ray. This Clyde sneaker comes with a black upper, black midsole, and black sole. The shoes released in October 2018 and retailed for $120. Before you leave more corpses on the court, leave a Bid for these on StockX.

name: Pokémon Bulbasaur
title: Puma Rider FV Pokémon Bulbasaur
description: The Puma Rider FV Pokemon Bulbasaur is a highly anticipated release for sneaker enthusiasts and Pokemon fans alike. This shoe features a green and white colorway inspired by the iconic Bulbasaur character, with a mix of suede and mesh materials for a comfortable and stylish fit. The release date for this shoe is set for November 12, 2022, and with a retail price of $100. The Puma Rider FV Pokemon Bulbasaur is a must-have for anyone looking to add a unique and playful touch to their sneaker collection. With its high-quality construction and attention to detail, this shoe is sure to be a hit among fans of both Puma and Pokemon.

name: J Cole Yellow
title: Puma RS-Dreamer 2 J Cole Yellow
description: The Puma Dreamer 2 J Cole Yellow is a highly anticipated release from the collaboration between Puma and rapper J Cole. The sneaker features a vibrant yellow colorway with black accents and a white midsole. The upper is constructed with a mix of suede and mesh materials, providing both durability and breathability. The shoe also features Puma's signature ProFoam technology in the midsole for added comfort and support. Released on January 28th, 2021, the Puma Dreamer 2 J Cole Yellow retails for $135. This sneaker is a must-have for fans of J Cole and Puma alike, as it combines the rapper's unique style with Puma's innovative design. Something we love about the Puma Dreamer 2 J Cole Yellow is the bold colorway that makes a statement on and off the court. Our experts think the standout feature of this sneaker is the combination of suede and mesh materials, which provide both style and functionality. Overall, we love the unique collaboration between Puma and J Cole, and the Dreamer 2 Yellow is a standout release from this partnership.

name: x TMC MCS
title: Puma x TMC MCS Track Jacket Black
description:
The Puma x TMC MCS Track Jacket Black is a bold and stylish creation that became available from the collaboration between The Marathon Continues (TMC), a renowned brand inspired by the legendary rapper Nipsey Hussle's legacy and philosophy, and a sportswear icon, Puma. The design commemorates Nipsey's powerful impact on culture and music.

The Puma x TMC MCS Track Jacket Black boasts a stylish track jacket design with a modern twist. It signifies the connection between Nipsey Hussle's long-lasting legacy and the sportswear expertise of Puma. The creation integrates the Mesh Construction System (MCS) Puma's unique design element. It features contrasting white stripes running along the sleeves and shoulders. This jacket is crafted from superior cotton and polyester to make it breathable, comfortable, and long-lasting.

What our experts find the most outstanding about this jacket is the stylish and sleek option that makes it perfect for people who love both streetwear and athletics aesthetics. The Puma x TMC MCS Track Jacket Black was released at a retail price of $100 on September 5th, 2019.

name: atmos Staple
title: Puma Suede atmos Staple
description:
The Puma Suede atmos Staple was released to headline a three-piece collection comprising footwear, a t-shirt, and a pullover hoodie by Puma, Japanese-based atmos, and New York City’s STAPLE.

Cladding premium leather, the Puma Suede arrives in a light, natural tone. The eyestays are seen in a grey hue, while the tongue, which has mismatched atmos and STAPLE branding in a vibrant pink color, adopt the natural tint on the vamp. More color appears on the quarter panels, with the lateral Formstripes sporting a dark pink shade on the lateral side and a black color adorned by shimmering green accents on the medial. The midsole has a ribbed finish on the forefoot, a textured design on the midfoot, and branded on the heel.

What makes the Puma Suede atmos Staple stand out? Our experts love the detailed branding on the heel, consisting of a colored pigeon that nods to NYC street culture and a black crow for the Japanese street footwear. These shoes were released on February 27th, 2021, for $90.

name: Stone (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy 500 Stone (Infants)
description:
The adidas Yeezy 500 Stone (Infants) is the infant-sized version of Kanye West’s Yeezy 500. It features a bulky silhouette and a neutral colorway of Stone.

Like the adult-sized version, the infant-sized adidas Yeezy 500 variation boasts a puffy appearance supported by adidas adiPRENE technology. The upper is made of a combination of lycra, cow leather, and suede. The soft suede toe and side overlays cut across the sneaker, creating bubble-like pockets that bulge out from the upper. The lace cage houses thick laces that look like smooth ropes and a padded tongue. The durable, rubber outsole offers a slightly yellower tan than the upper and midsole, which provide a subtly contrasting tone.

What do our experts at StockX love about this shoe? The upper maintains a completely minimalist color scheme without any distracting colors. The infant-size adidas Yeezy 500 Stone (Infants) was released on November 23, 2019, and retailed at $100.

name: Season 7 House Blue
title: Yeezy Desert Boot Season 7 House Blue
description:
The Yeezy Desert Boot Season 7 House Blue hails from a now-ended collaboration between adidas and cultural icon Kanye West, leaving adidas in charge of Yeezy designs.

The House Blue colorway of the Yeezy Desert Boot Season 7 features a stylish and durable upper of pale blue-gray mesh. Undulating overlays of leather and suede in different shades of gray course across the upper, from toe to heel. Rope laces over a tongue padded for comfort help ensure a snug closure. A pale gray Boost midsole offers a smooth ride with every step, and a thick, durable rubber outsole, also pale gray, provides rugged traction whether you're running errands or going on a hike.

Our favorite feature of this comfortable yet durable shoe is the pull tab on the padded tongue that eases on/off for this pair of kicks. The line of gray striping contrasts the softer hues and shapes of the upper. The Yeezy Desert Boot Season 7 House Blue was released on February 12, 2019, for $280.

name: Yecheil (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Yecheil (Kids)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Yecheil Kids comes in an all-Yecheil color scheme.

The Yecheil adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 for kids features an upper that is crafted with a flexible and breathable PrimeKnit material, providing a snug and comfortable fit. The shoe features a combination of various hues, including red, blue, yellow, and black. The shoe also features a side stripe made of a translucent monofilament material. The shoe is built with adidas' innovative Boost cushioning technology, which offers improved comfort and greater responsiveness. The shoe's rubber outsole provides traction and sturdiness.

What our experts love about the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Yecheil (Kids) is their vibrant and intricate multicolor design. These sneakers showcase a variety of bold hues, including red, blue, yellow, and green, intricately woven together on the PrimeKnit upper. The contrasting colors create a striking visual appeal. The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Yecheil Kids was released on December 20th, 2019, and sold for a retail price of $160.

name: Black (Infants) (Non-Reflective)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Black (Infants) (Non-Reflective)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Black (I) Non-Reflective is an infant sneaker crafted in collaboration with adidas and Yeezy brands.

This infant’s sneaker features a Primeknit upper construction, and the laces are all covered in an all-black pattern. The patchwork prime knit upper incorporates all the iconic 350 design cues. The final look is completed with a blacked-out sole. The sneaker's heel pull tab, which has brilliant red stitching, is the only area of color. Last but not least, the shoe has a translucent side stripe in place of the standard SPLY-350 marking. The midsole uses ridged TPU sidewalls with semi-translucent characteristics, showing full-length adidas Boost cushioning inside, while integrated lacing allows for fit customization.

Something we love about the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Black Non-Reflective is the side stripe made of post-dyed monofilament woven into the top. The laces have reflective threads sewn into them. The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Black (I) Non-Reflective was released on 7th June 2019 and retailed at $140.

name: Desert Sage (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Desert Sage (Kids)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Desert Sage (Kids) arrives outfitted in a desert sage Primeknit upper with a signature tonal stripe on the side. The shoe features Ultra Boost technology for responsive cushioning.

The adidas Yeezy Boost for kids has a breathable Primeknit upper flaunting the desert sage colorway on the Desert Sage Kids. Pops of color come on the sock liner, which sports a contrasting orange color. Soft padding on the collar adds comfort to the breathable upper. The semi-translucent ridged midsole of these Yeezys hides a full-length Ultra Boost unit, which is surmounted by a translucent rubber outsole with shades of orange. A 3M reflective strip on the rear panels complements the various patterns woven on the Primeknit upper.

What our experts love about the Boost 350 V2 Desert Sage is the minimalist build. The Desert Sage colorway dilutes the orange accents on the sneakers, creating a subdued aesthetic. The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Desert Sage (Kids) was released on March 14, 2020, retailing for $160.

name: Lundmark (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Lundmark (Kids)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Lundmark K was released in part of a continued collaboration between adidas and fashion designer/rapper Kanye West as part of the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 line.

This shoe in kids sizing features an off-white/light grey hue and has a PrimeKnit upper construction with a monofilament side stripe on the lateral side of the shoe. It also bears the iconic "SPLY-350" branding, synonymous with most shoes on the 350 V2 line, on the side, and a translucent rubber outsole that houses the Boost technology.

What our experts think are the best features of the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Lundmark Kids is the minimalistic design, as well as the chunky sole that not only adds an aesthetic element to the shoe, but also cushions the heel for maximum comfort. The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Lundmark K was released on July 13, 2019 for the price of $160.

name: Yeshaya (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Yeshaya (Kids)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Yeshaya (Kids) is a special iteration of Kanye West's Yeezy sneaker line, recognized for its minimalist yet stylish design. It features a unique "Yeshaya" colorway that offers an interesting twist on the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 silhouette.

The shoe’s upper is constructed using a combination of PrimeKnit and monofilament mesh materials. It showcases an array of light and neutral shades, including varying tones of gray, cream, and beige – creating a cohesive and versatile palette. It also has a translucent side stripe that runs along the lateral side of the shoe, which blends in with the overall color scheme. The sole, on the other hand, incorporates Boost cushioning technology for energy return and cushioning the foot.

A standout feature on the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Yeshaya (Kids) is the construction of the upper. Crafted using PrimeKnit and monofilament materials, the shoe has a snug fit, while also maintaining flexibility and breathability on the foot, ensuring a comfortable experience throughout. The shoe was released for the retail price of $160 on January 25th, 2020.

name: Clay (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Clay (Infants)
description:
West and adidas teamed up to unveil the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Clay (I), a silhouette with a warm palette and semi-translucent, three-tone vent at the side.

Featuring a dark green Primeknit upper, the Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Clay in infant sizing sits atop an orange-tinted midsole. A tan upper with salmon-like accents on the heel tab and midsole, along with hints of the pinkish color on the inner parts of the shoe peek through the translucent stripe. Orange details also appear on the heel tabs, sole unit, and the upper’s underlay.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Clay (I) was released on March 30, 2019, at a retail price of $140.

name: Glow (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Glow (Kids)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Glow Kids is a collaboration effort between adidas and Kanye West.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 for Kids comes in an all-glow colorway. The upper is crafted with a lightweight and breathable PrimeKnit material, offering comfort. The PrimeKnit material features a fluorescent lime green colorway. The sneaker is equipped with adidas' signature Boost technology in the midsole, providing cushioning and responsiveness. The shoe has a semi-translucent rubber outsole for traction and durability. The sneaker features a pull tab and strap on the heel, allowing for easy on and off.

The standout feature of the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Glow Kids is their unique glow-in-the-dark effect. These sneakers feature a fluorescent green upper that emits a luminous glow after exposure to light. The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Glow Kids was released on May 25th, 2019, and sold for a suggested retail price of $180.

name: Red October
title: Nike Air Yeezy 2 Red October
description:
The Nike Air Yeezy 2 Red October was created in collaboration with musician and fashion designer, Kanye West.

The Air Yeezy 2 Red October features a distinctive design that includes a molded upper with a reptilian texture. The midsole is composed of Phylon foam, which is lightweight and flexible, providing cushioning for the foot. The Air-Sole unit is in the heel and is visible through a window in the sole, and provides additional cushioning and support. A strap at the front of the shoe helps to secure the foot in place, while the rubber outsole provides traction on a variety of surfaces.

The outsole of the Nike Air Yeezy 2 Red October is made of a durable rubber material with a unique pattern that provides excellent traction on a variety of surfaces. We think that the most notable feature of the shoe is the striking red colorway. The bright red hue is bold and eye-catching, making the sneakers stand out. The shoe was released on February 9th, 2014, at a retail price of $250.

name: Phosphor (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Phosphor (Infants)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Phosphor (Infant) is part of the adidas Yeezy line, which is a collaboration between adidas and the rapper Kanye West.

The Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Phosphor (Infant) comes in infant sizes and has an upper that is made of lightweight and durable nylon material, which is known for being breathable, comfortable, and water-resistant. The nylon upper is combined with synthetic leather overlays, which provide additional support and durability. The shoe also features a soft textile lining and a cushioned insole, providing added comfort and support for the child's growing feet. The midsole is made of Adidas' signature Boost technology, which offers responsive cushioning and energy return with every step. The outsole is made of rubber, which provides durability and traction for active kids.

We think that the most notable feature of the adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Phosphor (Infant) is its eye-catching Phosphor colorway. The sneaker was released on April 24th, 2020, at a retail price of $140.

name: Rock Ridge Red Blast (GS)
title: Puma LaMelo Ball MB.01 Rock Ridge Red Blast (GS)
description:
The Puma LaMelo Ball MB.01 Rock Ridge Red Blast (GS) was LaMelo Ball’s first signature sneaker, released in conjunction with Puma. It features a grey and red color scheme and was one of the many colorways that Puma made available for this particular shoe.

The grade-school Puma LaMelo Ball MB.01 included a breathable upper with a greyscale finish and smaller hits of orange branding. It also boasted a Nitro-Foam cushioning system that is held in place by a semi-translucent rubber compound. The shoe uses special heel padding specifically designed to prevent ankle sprains.

What we appreciated most about this signature sneaker is the multi-directional tread on the bottom of the shoe. This feature allows it to safely stop and change directions instantly, while also allowing the word "RARE" to shine through. The Puma LaMelo Ball MB.01 Rock Ridge Red Blast (GS) was released on 18th February 2022 for $85.

name: Rubik's Cube
title: Puma RS-X3 Rubik's Cube
description: The Puma RS X3 Rubiks Cube is a vibrant and playful sneaker that pays homage to the iconic 80s puzzle game. The upper is made of a mix of materials, including mesh, leather, and suede, in a bold colorway of blue, red, yellow, and green. The Rubiks Cube theme is further emphasized by the cube-shaped lace locks and the puzzle-inspired graphic on the tongue. Released on November 21, 2019, the Puma RS X3 Rubiks Cube retails for $110. It features Puma's signature RS cushioning technology, which provides excellent comfort and support for everyday wear. The outsole is made of durable rubber, ensuring traction and grip on various surfaces. Something we love about the Puma RS X3 Rubiks Cube is its playful and nostalgic design that brings back memories of the 80s. Our experts think the best features of this sneaker are its mix of materials, bold colorway, and unique lace locks. The standout feature of the Puma RS X3 Rubiks Cube is undoubtedly its Rubiks Cube-inspired design, which is sure to turn heads and spark conversations. Overall, the Puma RS X3 Rubiks Cube is a fun and stylish sneaker that combines retro vibes with modern comfort and technology. Whether you're a fan of the Rubiks Cube or simply looking for a unique and eye-catching sneaker, the Puma RS X3 Rubiks Cube is definitely worth considering.

name: J Cole Red
title: Puma RS-Dreamer J Cole Red
description:
The Puma RS-Dreamer J Cole Red is another colorway of the RS Dreamer, a basketball shoe released by Puma in collaboration with rapper and basketball enthusiast J. Cole.

The shoes have a textile upper with suede overlays and feature a dynamic cord lacing system. The upper is predominantly red with black accents providing a contrasting effect which gives the shoe a distinctive aesthetic. The sole unit is fully black and features a ProFoam midsole for cushioning and comfort. Branding elements on the Puma RS-Dreamer include the RSD logo on the tongue and Dreamer branding on the heel.

One thing we love about the Puma RS-Dreamer J Cole Red is the bold and eye-catching aesthetics. It has a vibrant color scheme and unique patterns reflecting the energetic and expressive style associated with J. Cole. The shoes were released for retail at the price of $125 in May 2021.

name: Rhude
title: Puma Ralph Sampson Lo Rhude
description:
The Puma Ralph Sampson Lo Rhude is part of a collaboration between PUMA and Rhude, an LA-based luxury streetwear label founded by Rhuigi Villaseñor in 2015. The sneaker takes cues from the original Puma shoe inspired by Hall-of-Famer Ralph Sampson Ralph Sampson while giving it a motorsport update.

Featuring the classic Ralph Sampson low-top silhouette, the sneaker replaces the leather upper with shaggy suede for a vintage feel. Whisper White heel overlays and tonal forstrip overlays cross the Whisper White upper, creating a monotone colorway. Both the midsole and outsole are made of rubber, while the sock liner is crafted from a soft textile.

Something our experts love about this sneaker is the subtle visible branding. You can find the PUMA x Rhude wordmark on the tongue and the PUMA cat logo on the heel. The Puma Ralph Sampson Lo Rhude was released on March 6, 2020, and retailed at $130.

name: Puzzle White Yellow
title: Puma RS-X3 Puzzle White Yellow
description: The Puma RS X3 Puzzle White Yellow is a fresh take on the classic Puma RS silhouette. The shoe features a white mesh upper with yellow leather overlays, creating a bold and eye-catching look. The RS X3 Puzzle also boasts a chunky sole with Puma's signature Running System technology, providing optimal comfort and support for all-day wear. Released on November 21, 2019, the Puma RS X3 Puzzle White Yellow retails for $110. The shoe is constructed with high-quality materials, ensuring durability and longevity. The white and yellow colorway is versatile and can be paired with a variety of outfits, making it a great addition to any sneaker collection. Something we love about the Puma RS X3 Puzzle White Yellow is its unique design that combines retro and modern elements. What our experts think as best features are the comfortable sole and the attention-grabbing colorway. The standout feature of the Puma RS X3 Puzzle White Yellow is its ability to make a statement while still being practical for everyday wear. Our experts especially love how the shoe can elevate any outfit and add a pop of color to a neutral look.

name: Israfil (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Israfil (Kids)
description: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Israfil Kids is a highly sought-after sneaker that was released on August 22, 2020. This shoe features a unique colorway that combines shades of grey and blue with a touch of orange. The upper is made of Primeknit material, which provides a comfortable and breathable fit. The Boost technology in the sole offers superior cushioning and support for all-day wear. The Israfil Kids is a smaller version of the adult shoe, designed specifically for kids. It is available in sizes ranging from 10.5C to 6Y. The retail price for this shoe is $160, making it an affordable option for parents looking to give their kids a stylish and comfortable sneaker.

name: Super Mario Sunshine
title: Puma RS-Dreamer Super Mario Sunshine
description:
The Puma RS-Dreamer Super Mario Sunshine was released through a collaboration between Nintendo, J. Cole, and PUMA to celebrate 35 years of the Mario franchise.

The Super Mario Sunshine Puma RS-Dreamer has a vibrant colorway inspired by the tropical setting of Isle Delfino, combining teal, white, and black. The sneaker has a fully knitted upper in tie-dye teal with suede overlays. The heel patch includes a Shine Sprite and webbing pull loops, which can be seen on the heel and tongue. For comfort cushioning and energy return, the sneaker has RS Foam and ProFoam in the midsole. The sneaker has a textured PUMA Formstrip design, a graphic icon at the heel, Super Mario 64 branding on the tongue loop, and a cord lacing system.

Our sneaker experts think one of the most distinguished features of the Puma RS-Dreamer Super Mario Sunshine is the vibrant, multicolor, speckled detailing covering the ProFoam midsole. The shoe was released on September 17th, 2020, retailing at $125.

name: Soft Vision (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy 500 Soft Vision (Kids)
description: The adidas Yeezy 500 Soft Vision Kids is a highly sought-after sneaker that was released on November 2, 2019. This shoe features a soft pinkish-purple colorway that is perfect for kids who want to stand out from the crowd. The upper is made of premium suede and mesh materials, providing both durability and breathability. The midsole is made of adidas' signature adiPRENE technology, which offers superior cushioning and support. The outsole is made of rubber, providing excellent traction on any surface. This shoe is perfect for kids who want to look stylish and feel comfortable at the same time. The retail price for the adidas Yeezy 500 Soft Vision Kids is $130, making it an affordable option for parents who want to give their kids the best.

name: Solar Red
title: Nike Air Yeezy 2 Solar Red
description:
The Nike Air Yeezy 2 Solar Red is a "needs no introduction" sneaker, as it is a popular black and Solar Red colorway from the collaboration between Nike and Kayne West.

This Nike Air Yeezy 2 oozes creativity. The black upper has anaconda-textured side panels and a tonal Nike Swoosh on the lateral side. The heel, with its multiple mountainous grooves, is one-of-a-kind as it provides texture and depth whether it’s viewed from behind or the side. Nike Air can be seen through a window in the midsole under the heel. The Solar Red collar liner adds an energetic burst of color. In addition to the lacing system, a midfoot strap boasts Nike branding.

We have to say that the glow-in-the-dark rubber outsole is something we love about this sneaker; it’s not something you see every day, so it’s unique and innovative. The Nike Air Yeezy 2 Solar Red was released on June 9, 2012, and retailed for $250.

name: Vanta (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 V2 Vanta (Infants)
description: Make a statement with the adidas Yeezy Boost 700 V2 Vanta on your feet. This Yeezy Boost 700 V2 comes with a black upper, black midsole, and a black sole. These sneakers released in June 2019 and retailed for $300. Provide the world with some Yeezy vibes after grabbing these on StockX.

name: Lundmark (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Lundmark (Infants)
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Lundmark (Infant), a flexible sneaker specifically sized for infants, has been designed in collaboration with Kanye West to create a comfortable, supportive, and highly fashionable baby shoe.

The infant version Lundmark adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 features and upper of Warm Tan and white PrimeKnit. A jagged tan stripe runs across the lateral side of the shoe, turning white across the heel. Soft rope laces echo the tan and white sweater pattern of the upper. The sock liner is padded for ultimate comfort and accentuated with soft beige piping around the collar. There's no heel strap on this model as there is on the adult version of the shoe.

What our experts like most about this shoe is the cushioned rubber sole. Its semi-translucent color complements the warm tones of the upper to complete the look of this luxury baby booty. The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Lundmark (Infant), a comfortable shoe specifically sized for babies, was released on July 13th, 2019, for a retail price of $140.

name: Bone (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Bone (Kids)
description: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Bone Kids is a stylish and comfortable sneaker that is perfect for kids who love to stay active. The shoe features a sleek and modern design with a bone-colored upper made of lightweight nylon material. The shoe also features reflective detailing on the sides and heel for added visibility in low-light conditions. The Boost midsole provides excellent cushioning and support, while the rubber outsole offers superior traction and durability. The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Bone Kids was released on July 11, 2020, and retails for $160. This sneaker is a must-have for kids who want to look and feel their best while staying active.

name: Stone (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy 500 Stone (Kids)
description: The adidas Yeezy 500 Stone Kids is a highly sought-after sneaker that was released on November 23, 2019, with a retail price of $130. The shoe features a mix of premium materials, including suede, leather, and mesh, in a neutral colorway that is perfect for any outfit. The upper is predominantly dressed in a light beige hue, while the midsole and outsole are finished in a darker shade of brown. The Yeezy 500 Stone Kids is designed with comfort in mind, featuring a chunky midsole that provides ample cushioning and support. This sneaker is a must-have for any young sneakerhead looking to add a stylish and comfortable shoe to their collection.

name: South Beach
title: Puma Clyde Court Disrupt South Beach
description: The Puma Clyde Court Disrupt South Beach is a stylish and comfortable basketball shoe that is perfect for both on and off the court. The shoe features a vibrant colorway that is inspired by the iconic South Beach area of Miami, with a mix of teal, pink, and black accents. The upper is made from a breathable knit material that provides a snug and supportive fit, while the midsole is made from Puma's proprietary NRGY cushioning technology, which offers excellent shock absorption and energy return. One of the standout features of the Puma Clyde Court Disrupt South Beach is its unique lacing system, which is designed to provide a secure and customizable fit. The shoe also features a rubber outsole that provides excellent traction on both indoor and outdoor surfaces. The Puma Clyde Court Disrupt South Beach was released on December 8th, 2018, and has a retail price of $120. Overall, this shoe is a great choice for basketball players who want a stylish and comfortable shoe that performs well on the court. Something we love about the Puma Clyde Court Disrupt South Beach is its eye-catching colorway, which is sure to turn heads both on and off the court.

name: Red Grey Indigo
title: Puma RS-X Retro Red Grey Indigo
description:
The Puma RS-X Retro Red Gray Indigo is a performance running shoe with a vibrant High Risk Red base, indigo details, and a chunky silhouette.

Drawing inspiration from the running shoes of the 1980s, the RS-X Retro Red Gray Indigo boasts an upper made of lightweight mesh with suede and leather overlays. The thick, padded collar pays homage to the vintage Puma catalog, while RS cushioning and a PU midsole add a modern touch. In terms of detailing, small, indigo stripes streak up the side panels and tonally match the tongue pull tab, the heel pull tab, and some TPU pieces on the midsole. RS-X branding can be found on the tongue pull tab and on the lateral side of the heel panel.

Our experts at StockX like the contrasting TPU pieces on the midsole that come in indigo and High Risk Red. The Puma RS-X Retro Red Grey Indigo was released on January 1st, 2019, and retailed at $110.

name: White Black Green
title: Puma Cell Endura White Black Green
description:
During the 90s running technology boom, Puma created Cell Technology, one of the most durable and resilient cushioning technologies of the day. Twenty years later, they celebrate by reissuing a classic from the Puma Archive: The Cell Endura in a vibrant white, black and green colorway.

In 1998, Puma introduced the first iteration of Cell Technology for stable cushioning. Stability came from blow-molded polyurethane elastomer (TPU) that was configured in a pattern of hexagonal cells. Combinations of these cells allowed Puma to engineer cushioning and solve problems for a variety of running needs.

With distinctive eyelets, a chunky silhouette, and its green Cell Technology, the Cell Endura has stayed true to its OG glory, updated with new materials and new production techniques. It maintains the detailing of the original model along with the rubber toe cap plus a unique eyelet stay for the laces. The sneaker was referenced from the Puma Archive and reworked to create a sleeker toe shape. The original Cell Endura was hand-stitched but this version has evolved with the times and features digital stitching. A breathable mesh upper with suede overlays and PU coated leather overlays cover the upper which sits atop an EVA midsole and rubber outsole.

The Cell Endura drops on October 4th in leading sneaker stores, Puma.com and Puma stores worldwide. You can find them in men's sizes 7-13 and retail is set at $130.

name: Rihanna Fenty Olive (Women's)
title: Puma Bow Slide Rihanna Fenty Olive (Women's)
description:
Rihanna is no stranger to creating footwear, as she has helped design a few pairs of sneakers for PUMA. But with the Puma Bow Slide Rihanna Fenty Olive (Women's), she took a crack at designing her own slide.

This slide was actually one of many slides Rihanna produced in recent years in conjunction with Puma and her Fenty line. It featured a fairly basic olive green slide, but what helped put it over the top was the satin strap that was used to put a bow on it. It instantly made it look much more formal than it would have otherwise.

This slide was also available in other colorways, but in our expert opinion, this color was one of the best options of the bunch. It gave people the ability to dress this slide up or down based on what they planned to wear it with. The Puma Bow Slide Rihanna Fenty Olive (Women's) was released on March 9th, 2017, and it retailed for $90.

name: J. Cole Purple Heart
title: Puma RS-Dreamer J. Cole Purple Heart
description: The Puma RS Dreamer J Cole Purple Heart is a basketball-inspired sneaker that combines style and performance. The upper is made of a mix of mesh and suede, providing breathability and durability. The purple and black colorway is accented with hits of gold, giving the shoe a luxurious feel. The RS foam midsole provides cushioning and support, while the rubber outsole offers traction on the court. The Puma RS Dreamer J Cole Purple Heart was released on August 21, 2020, and retails for $125. This sneaker is a must-have for fans of J Cole and basketball enthusiasts alike.

name: Season 7 Oil
title: Yeezy Desert Boot Season 7 Oil
description:
Kanye West has released a bunch of boots through his Yeezy line over the years. The Yeezy Desert Boot Season 7 Oil is one of the many boot options he unveiled during his run with adidas.

This Yeezy Desert Boot was said to be inspired by both the Yeezy 500 sneaker and the military boots so often worn by soldiers throughout the world. It featured a mesh upper with brown suede and nubuck overlays to give it a rugged look and feel. It also included features like a large reflective tongue pull and thick laces to make it more durable. It was finished off with a chunky black rubber outsole that had big grooves in it to provide proper traction.

This boot was a departure from some of the other footwear included in Yeezy’s Season 7 collection, but that was a big part of what our experts appreciated about it. It didn’t immediately look like a Yeezy shoe, but after inspecting its details more closely, it was clear that it belonged in the Yeezy lineup. The Yeezy Desert Boot Season 7 Oil was released on February 12, 2019, for a retail price of $280.

name: Black (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Black (Kids)
description: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Black Kids is a sleek and stylish sneaker that is perfect for kids who want to stay on top of the latest trends. This shoe features a black upper made from lightweight nylon material, which provides a comfortable and breathable fit. The shoe also features reflective detailing on the upper, which adds a touch of style and visibility in low-light conditions. The Boost midsole provides excellent cushioning and support, making it perfect for active kids. The shoe was released on May 23, 2020, and retails for $160. With its sleek design and comfortable fit, the adidas Yeezy Boost 700 MNVN Black Kids is a must-have for any young sneakerhead.

name: Yeshaya (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Yeshaya (Infants)
description: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Yeshaya Infant is a highly sought-after sneaker that was released on January 25, 2020. This shoe features a sleek and stylish design that is perfect for infants. The upper is made of a breathable and durable Primeknit material that provides a comfortable fit. The shoe also features a Boost midsole that offers excellent cushioning and support. The Yeshaya colorway is a unique blend of white and grey that gives the shoe a clean and modern look. The retail price for this shoe is $140, making it an affordable option for parents who want to give their children a stylish and comfortable shoe. Overall, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Yeshaya Infant is a must-have for any sneaker enthusiast who wants to keep their little ones looking fresh.

name: Vanta (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 V2 Vanta (Kids)
description: Make a statement with the adidas Yeezy Boost 700 V2 Vanta on your feet. This Yeezy Boost 700 V2 comes with a black upper, black midsole, and a black sole. These sneakers released in June 2019 and retailed for $300. Provide the world with some Yeezy vibes after grabbing these on StockX.

name: Season 7 Taupe
title: Yeezy Desert Boot Season 7 Taupe
description: The Yeezy Desert Boot Season 7 Taupe is a stylish and comfortable footwear option for those who love to stay on top of the latest fashion trends. Made from high-quality suede and featuring a durable rubber sole, these boots are perfect for everyday wear. The taupe colorway is versatile and can be paired with a variety of outfits. The Yeezy Desert Boot Season 7 Taupe was released on February 12, 2019, and retails for $280. Whether you're running errands or hitting the town, these boots are sure to keep you looking and feeling great. Don't miss out on the chance to add these stylish boots to your collection.

name: Season 7 Cinder
title: Yeezy Desert Boot Season 7 Cinder
description: The Yeezy Desert Boot Season 7 Cinder is a sleek and stylish addition to the Yeezy line. The boot features a monochromatic cinder colorway, with a suede upper and a rubber sole. The boot is designed with a high-top silhouette, with a lace-up closure and a padded collar for added comfort. The Yeezy Desert Boot Season 7 Cinder was released on February 12, 2019, and retails for $280. The Yeezy Desert Boot Season 7 Cinder is made with high-quality materials, ensuring durability and longevity. The suede upper is soft and supple, while the rubber sole provides excellent traction and grip. The cinder colorway is versatile and can be paired with a variety of outfits, making it a great addition to any wardrobe. Something we love about the Yeezy Desert Boot Season 7 Cinder is the attention to detail in the design. The padded collar and lace-up closure provide a comfortable and secure fit, while the monochromatic colorway adds a touch of sophistication. Our experts think the standout feature of the Yeezy Desert Boot Season 7 Cinder is the combination of style and functionality. The boot is not only fashionable but also practical, making it a great choice for everyday wear. Overall, we love the Yeezy Desert Boot Season 7 Cinder for its sleek design, high-quality materials, and versatility.

name: Bone White (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy 500 Bone White (Infants)
description:
The adidas Yeezy 500 Bone White (Infants) is an infant-sized iteration of the adidas Yeezy 500 in a bone white colorway.

Why do adults get to have all the fun? Thanks to the infant sizing of this stylish adidas Yeezy 500, toddlers can now walk around in comfort. This chunky silhouette features a monochromatic bone white color combination throughout a nubuck, suede, and mesh upper construction. The figure-eight like overlay houses white laces that lace through oval eyestays. The large rubber mudguard is great for active children. The classic trefoil adidas logo is on the lower back heel. The outsole creates a wave-like appearance to ensure the youngest member of the family is walking in style.

We think a standout feature of the adidas Yeezy 500 Bone White (Infants) is the height-boosting cushioned rubber midsole and outsole with adiPRENE+ shoe tech. Released on October 24, 2019, this infant sized sneaker sold for at a retail price of $100.

name: Antlia (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Antlia (Infants)
description:
Designed by Kanye West, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Antlia (Infant) arrives in the Antlia color palette across its two-tone re-engineered Prime knit upper. The 350 V2 Antlia Infant infuses canary yellow and shades of coal grey sitting atop a gum outsole.

Combining styles from all the 350 V2s, the Antlia for infants stands out with a breathable Prime knit upper finished in colors that resemble the 350 V2 Butter. A Boost midsole designed for comfort sports the usual Yeezy styling, while the upper retains its signature SPLY 350 design. adidas adopts an innovative approach by plating a translucent strip on the laterals leading to the heel, where you'll notice the heel tab has been removed. The only break in the Antlia colorway is a light gum sole that extends to the toecap and heel, attaching to the full-length Boost midsole on both ends.

What our experts love about the 350 V2 Antlia is the breathable upper mated to the Boost midsole, which delivers unparalleled comfort. It is easy to see why people clamor to purchase these sneakers. The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Antlia (Infant) was released on June 22, 2019, and retailed for $140.

name: Puzzle Puma White
title: Puma RS-X3 Puzzle Puma White
description:
The Puma RS-X3 Puzzle Puma White is an addition to Puma's RS line of sneakers, which features retro-inspired designs with modern technology. 

The Puzzle Puma RS-X3 Puma White incorporates layers of puzzle pieces on the upper which is made from premium synthetic leather and a mesh panel that adds breathability to the upper. The upper sits on top of a chunky sole made of Puma's proprietary foam in combination with rubber, providing support, comfort, and stability. The upper is also padded with foam, adding extra comfort for the wearer. The shoe's lacing system hugs the foot securely, ensuring a snug fit. The outsole of the shoe features a durable rubber that delivers exceptional grip on different surfaces.

We think that the standout feature of the Puma RS-X3 Puzzle Puma White is its unique design, which consists of layered puzzle pieces on the upper. The design creates an illusion of three-dimensional shapes that form a visual puzzle, hence "Puzzle" in the name. The Puma RS-X3 Puzzle Puma White was released on November 21, 2019 at a retail price of $110.

name: Rihanna Fenty Black (Women's)
title: Puma Cleated Creeper Rihanna Fenty Black (Women's)
description:
Creeper shoes, which feature chunky platform crêpe soles on them, have been around since the 1940s. Rihanna put her own spin on them while designing the Puma Cleated Creeper Rihanna Fenty Black (Women's) during one of her early collaborations with Puma.

The uppers on these creeper shoes are constructed out of all-black suede, with black laces and black Puma branding to match. They also have matching black midsoles and outsoles, though these elements of the shoes are far from ordinary. Rather than running with traditional midsoles and outsoles for these sneakers, Rihanna stuck a pair of exaggerated and oversized midsoles and outsoles on them to make them stand tall while also standing out.

Our sneaker experts appreciate Rihanna's willingness to experiment when putting together the designs for these Puma shoes. It gives these Puma x Fenty sneakers a unique look while still giving a nod to the original creepers. The Puma Cleated Creeper Rihanna Fenty Black (Women's), available exclusively in women's sizes, was released on August 31, 2017, for a retail price of $160.

name: Grey Yellow Red
title: Puma RS-X Harddrive Grey Yellow Red
description:
The Puma RS-X Harddrive Grey Yellow Red is a running sneaker by Puma which combines a retro aesthetic with modern technology to offer the best of both worlds.

The shoes have a predominantly grey upper with striking accents of yellow and orange on the sides and collar area respectively. There is also a touch of black around the heel to add some contrast to the overall design. The Puma RS-X Harddrive also has a chunky sole unit with a black and white midsole, and multicolored outsole. It uses Puma’s RS-X technology in the midsole to provide cushioning and added support to your feet.

One thing that stands out on the Puma RS-X Harddrive Grey Yellow Red is the layered upper which combines different materials such as mesh, leather, and synthetic overlays. This contributes significantly to the overall aesthetic of the shoes, while also enhancing durability. The shoes were first released for retail on 30th June 2019 priced at $110.

name: Coogi Sweater
title: Puma Clyde Coogi Sweater
description:
The Puma Clyde Coogi Sweater is part of a collaboration between Puma and Coogi, an Australia-based apparel label known for its colorful sweater designs and use of premium wool.

This vibrant sneaker takes the Puma Clyde silhouette and applies a knit upper featuring a hodgepodge of colorful prints. There is no dominant color, but there is a bright yellow on the heel, toe, and along the medial side panel to catch the eye. What makes this sneaker special is that each shoe has a unique upper design. No two shoes have the same sweater pattern. The Puma form strip in black cuts down the side panel and matches the black laces. In terms of branding, a Puma logo tag can be found on the tongue.

Our StockX experts like the use of 18 karat gold eyelets and aglets. It contributes to the sneaker’s luxury aesthetic. The Puma Clyde Coogi Sweater was released on March 9th, 2017, and retailed at $200.

name: Rihanna Fenty Cool Blue (Women's)
title: Puma Fur Slide Rihanna Fenty Cool Blue (Women's)
description: The Puma Fur Slide Rihanna Fenty Cool Blue W is a stylish and comfortable slide sandal designed by Rihanna herself. The sandal features a faux fur strap in a cool blue colorway, with the Puma logo embossed on the side. The footbed is made of soft foam for added comfort, and the outsole is made of durable rubber for traction and durability. The sandal was released on June 23, 2017, and retails for $80. The Puma Fur Slide Rihanna Fenty Cool Blue W is a must-have for anyone looking for a fashionable and comfortable slide sandal that can be worn both indoors and outdoors.

name: Reform
title: Puma Clyde Court Disrupt Reform
description:
The Puma Clyde Court Disrupt Reform was introduced in conjunction with the release of Meek Mill's 'Free Meek' documentary that was available through Amazon in early 2019. All proceeds from the sneaker were donated to the REFORM Alliance Foundation established by Meek Mill and Jay Z.

The upper on this Puma Clyde Court Disrupt was entirely black save for a few pops of red around the eyelets and gold on the Puma logo that appeared on the heel. The colors chosen for the sneaker were symbolic as, according to Puma, the black was designed to represent the unjust prison sentences that many Americans are serving, while the red was used to represent the blood of those who have battled back against oppression in the U.S. over the last 60 years.

This Puma Clyde Court Disrupt sneaker looked great, but what our experts liked most about it was that it was for a good cause. We also appreciated the "WE HAD TO BE SEEN BECAUSE WE COULDN’T BE HEARD" branding on it that carried a real message. The Puma Clyde Court Disrupt Reform was released on February 1, 2019, for a $120 retail price.

name: Red Blast
title: Puma Clyde Court Disrupt Red Blast
description: After a 20 year hiatus from the basketball sneaker market, Puma is back with the release of the Puma Clyde Court Disrupt. The first offering of the sneaker comes to us just in time for the start of the 2018-19 NBA season and features an aggressive colorway paired with a sleek silhouette. The sneaker embodies the spirit and style set down by Walt "Clyde" Frazier who was the brand's first athlete to receive a signature sneaker.  The Clyde Court Disrupt maintains the timeless essence of the original Puma Clyde while featuring updates that make it a true modern basketball sneaker for players seeking out a shoe that is on the forefront of performance innovation. If you're looking for a stylish basketball sneaker that can be worn on the courts, and paired with your favorite pair of jeans for a day around town than the Puma Clyde Court Disrupt is the sneaker for you.

name: Transformers Optimus Prime
title: Puma RS-X Transformers Optimus Prime
description: The Puma RS X Transformers Optimus Prime is a limited edition sneaker that pays homage to the iconic Autobot leader. The shoe features a mix of blue, red, and silver colors, with a metallic finish that adds to its futuristic appeal. The upper is made of a combination of mesh, leather, and suede, while the sole is made of rubber for durability and traction. The RS X technology provides cushioning and support for all-day comfort. The release date for this sneaker was November 22, 2018, and it retailed for $120. This sneaker is a must-have for Transformers fans and sneakerheads alike, with its unique design and attention to detail.

name: J. Cole Concrete Jungle
title: Puma RS-Dreamer J. Cole Concrete Jungle
description: The Puma RS Dreamer J Cole Concrete Jungle is a highly anticipated release from the collaboration between Puma and rapper J Cole. The sneaker features a sleek black and grey colorway with pops of vibrant green on the outsole and branding. The upper is constructed with a mix of mesh and suede materials, providing both breathability and durability. The RS foam technology in the midsole offers superior cushioning and support for all-day comfort. Released on August 21, 2020, the Puma RS Dreamer J Cole Concrete Jungle retails for $125. This sneaker is a must-have for fans of J Cole and sneaker enthusiasts alike. The unique colorway and materials make it a standout addition to any collection. Something we love about the Puma RS Dreamer J Cole Concrete Jungle is the attention to detail in the design. The mix of materials and colors create a cohesive and stylish look that is sure to turn heads. Our experts think the standout feature of the Puma RS Dreamer J Cole Concrete Jungle is the RS foam technology in the midsole, providing unmatched comfort and support. Overall, we love the combination of style and function in this collaboration between Puma and J Cole.

name: Triple Black
title: Puma Thunder Desert Triple Black
description: The latest rendition of the Puma Thunder Desert is taking a much more simplified approach then previous Thunder pairs.  While the debut Thunder Spectra took on a bold statement with its retro color blocking and neon pops, the latest Thunder Desert drops simulate light and shadows in the desert with Triple Black and White colorways. It retains the bold signature exaggerated tooling, blown-up proportions and material mix of premium suede, textured leather and mesh. This sneaker is comprised of  Nubuck Leather & Mesh Upper with TPU overlays, EVA midsole, Rubber Outsole. This classic triple black color-way is all black for a simple clean look.  The Thunder pays homage to past collabs and silhouettes ahead of their time. Inspired by 90s Cell System running silhouettes and the PUMA x McQueen collaboration, the style is a reimagined pair of kicks with a bulky, unapologetic look and feel. These shoes are set to release worldwide in select sneaker boutiques, PUMA.com and PUMA stores August 9th, 2018 ranging in US sizes from 4-14 for a set price of $120.  If you're looking for a clean durable pair of sneakers to break out this fall, look no further than the Puma Thunder Desert.

name: Rihanna Fenty Patent Black (Women's)
title: Puma Pointy Creeper Rihanna Fenty Patent Black (Women's)
description: Here's another colorway of the women's Puma Pointed Creeper. Made in collaboration with Rihanna and her Fenty label, this pair comes in an all-black colorway. Featuring a black-based patent leather upper sitting atop a pointed creeper sole. Their release date was October 12th, 2017 and they were available at select Puma retailers worldwide. Available exclusively for women, they retailed for $160. Fans of Ri-Ri can rep her all-day, everyday in the Puma Pointed Creeper. If you're interested in buying a pair you can do so online now. Those that have pairs to sell can list them up on the marketplace so people can start putting their bids in asap.

name: Fair Aqua Ponderosa Pine
title: Puma RS-X FD Fair Aqua Ponderosa Pine
description:
The Puma RS-X FD Fair Aqua Ponderosa Pine is a reinvented version of the RS-X running sneaker, featuring a multicolor upper and performance technologies.

Unlike the original RS-X from 1986, the Puma RS-X FD "Fair Aqua Ponderosa Pine" boasts an upper made of textile and mesh and a padded collar. This collar increases comfort while contributing to the slightly bulky silhouette. The textile base comes in Fair Aqua and displays multiple textures, including perforations, a suede-like finish, and bumps. Orange lines add a pop of color and match the tone of the rubber outsole. In terms of technology, the sneaker features a responsive midsole that adds bulk to the silhouette.

Our experts like the multicolor speckles that decorate the white midsole and the padded tongue. They give the shoe a DIY appearance and make the colorway stand out. The Puma RS-X FD Fair Aqua Ponderosa Pine was released on January 1, 2019, and retailed at $110.

name: Rihanna Fenty Black (Women's)
title: Puma Avanti VL Rihanna Fenty Black (Women's)
description:
FENTY x PUMA presents the Avanti, worn by legends and reborn by Rihanna. This classic silhouette was taken from the PUMA archives and reimaged by Rihanna through her own personal design language and creative treatment.
