This new sport-fashion icon features a premium leather upper and a gum sole, and appears in two bespoke versions: classic black and white, and allover silver chrome.

Buttery soft leather upper ; Leather piping around formstrip ; Attached fold over tongue in soft leather ; Debossed Fenty logo on tongue, quarter, and heel with gold foil finish ; Brown leather lining ; EVA foam wedge midsole ; Gum outsole.

name: Alexander John The Mixtape
title: Puma RS-X Alexander John The Mixtape
description:
The Puma RS-X Alexander John The Mixtape is a multicolored running sneaker released by Puma as part of the Puma-RX series. It was a special edition release in collaboration with renowned artist Alexander John.

The shoe’s upper is made from leather material with mesh underlays which keep the shoes lightweight and ventilated. It has a vibrant color palette featuring a range of bright colors including yellow, red, green, black, and white which immediately gives the shoe a vibrant aesthetic. Additionally, these Puma RS-X are inspired by old-school Side A-Side B mixtapes and even have a few graphics drawn on including ‘SIDE A’ and ‘SIDE B’ on the left and right shoes respectively.

One thing that stands out on the Puma RS-X Alexander John The Mixtape is the chunky sole unit which uses cushioning technology to absorb any impact on your feet, keeping them comfortable for extended periods of time. The shoes were initially released at the retail price of $150 on 4th November 2018.

name: Rihanna Fenty Black (PS)
title: Puma Avanti VL Rihanna Fenty Black (PS)
description:
FENTY x PUMA presents the Avanti, worn by legends and reborn by Rihanna. This classic silhouette was taken from the PUMA archives and reimaged by Rihanna through her own personal design language and creative treatment. This new sport-fashion icon features a premium leather upper and a gum sole, and appears in two bespoke versions: classic black and white, and allover silver chrome.

Buttery soft leather upper ; Leather piping around formstrip ; Attached fold over tongue in soft leather ; Debossed Fenty logo on tongue, quarter, and heel with gold foil finish ; Brown leather lining ; EVA foam wedge midsole ; Gum outsole.

name: Bone White (Kids)
title: adidas Yeezy 500 Bone White (Kids)
description:
The adidas Yeezy 500 Bone White (Kids) is a kids’ version of the futuristic hiking-inspired sneaker in a Bone White colorway.

This iteration of the adidas Yeezy 500 features an upper constructed with cow suede, leather, and mesh. All of these elements appear in Bone White. There is also a white rubber overlay wrapping around the midsole to provide extra support and resistance. The rounded and chunky design of the white rubber outsole adds to the futuristic design. The adidas logo appears on the front of the outsole at the toe, and the pull tab on the tongue provides for easy on-and-off.

What we like best about this shoe is the adiPRENE cushioning on the insole that provides extra comfort for the wearer, making this shoe both fashionable and functional. The adidas Yeezy 500 Bone White (Kids) was first released on August 24th, 2019, at a retail price of $130.

name: Shadow Black (Friends & Family)
title: adidas Yeezy 500 Shadow Black (Friends & Family)
description: What could be a more perfect hypebeast sneaker than a F&F Yeezy sneaker? While similar to the Yeezy 500 Utility Black, this Friends & Family pair (F&F) has a few unique differences. Using tonal shadow black colorway on the entire shoe, this Yeezy 500 also has subtle blue and purple hues which can be noticed throughout the upper and outsole. Also, unlike the Utility Black pair, this colorway only has Adidas branding on the insole. Releasing in June, 2018, this pair retailed for $200.

name: Desert Sand (Infants)
title: adidas Yeezy Slide Desert Sand (Infants)
description:
During his time with adidas, Kanye West created slides in a handful of different styles. The adidas Yeezy Slide Desert Sand (Infants) was a miniature version of the Yeezy Slide done up in a desert sand color.

These Yeezy Slides were constructed out of an EVA material that made them more flexible than rubber. They also featured a hook-and-loop strap that went around the heel and made them easy to put on and take off. They had a thick seamless midsole with a sawtooth pattern on the bottom as well, which gave them a rugged look and provided them with excellent traction.

But our favorite thing about these Yeezy Slides was that they were incredibly soft, which made them an ideal choice for infants. At the same time, they didn’t force parents to sacrifice style for comfort since they included all the same features as the Yeezy Slides available in adult sizes. The adidas Yeezy Slide Desert Sand (Infants) was released on December 6, 2019, for a $35 retail price.

name: Israfil Reflective
title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Israfil Reflective
description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Israfil Reflective features an Israfil Primeknit upper with Israfil colorway using shades of a subtle blue-grey for the majority of the silhouette, followed by darker grey trim that also appears again on the soft midsole. From there, a light yellow stripe that adds some extra color to the Primeknit upper of the Israfil Reflective as it bisects the shoe, and a light beige Gum outsole complete the design.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Israfil Reflective released in August of 2020 and retailed for $250.
